##spDataVersion:	1
##Title:	Revised King James New Testament
##Abbreviation:	RKJNT
##Information:	
Revised King James New Testament: Preface

In the Revised King James New Testament I've tried to maintain the feel of the
King James Version, frequently using British spellings, and including much of
the KJV syntax and even some antiquated words. I've used the masculine in the
old, gender- inclusive sense. Brackets [ ] enclose some passages that are
generally noted in modern translations as being missing in the best manuscripts.
The RKJ New Testament was developed using various modern translations. I did not
return to the original languages in developing it.

Since one of my goals was to make a modern translation of the New Testament
widely and inexpensively available, I am placing the Revised King James New
Testament into the public domain. I no longer make any copyright claim for it.
You are only answerable to God for how you use it.

Brad Haugaard
    
