B040C001V001	40	1	1	The book of the genealogy of Jesus Christ, the son of David, the son of Abraham.
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham was the father of Isaac; and Isaac the father of Jacob; and Jacob the father of Judah and his brothers;
B040C001V003	40	1	3	And Judah the father of Perez and Zarah by Tamar; and Perez the father of Hezron; and Hezron the father of Ram;
B040C001V004	40	1	4	And Ram the father of Amminadab; and Amminadab the father of Nahshon; and Nahshon the father of Salma;
B040C001V005	40	1	5	And Salma the father of Boaz by Rahab; and Boaz the father of Obed by Ruth; and Obed the father of Jesse;
B040C001V006	40	1	6	And Jesse the father of David the king; and David the king the father of Solomon by her who had been the wife of Uriah;
B040C001V007	40	1	7	And Solomon the father of Rehoboam; and Rehoboam the father of Abijah; and Abijah the father of Asa;
B040C001V008	40	1	8	And Asa the father of Jehoshaphat; and Jehoshaphat the father of Joram; and Joram the father of Azariah;
B040C001V009	40	1	9	And Azariah the father of Jotham; and Jotham the father of Ahaz; and Ahaz the father of Hezekiah;
B040C001V010	40	1	10	And Hezekiah the father of Manasseh; and Manasseh the father of Amon; and Amon the father of Josiah;
B040C001V011	40	1	11	And Josiah the father of Jeconiah and his brothers, about the time they were carried away to Babylon:
B040C001V012	40	1	12	And after the exile to Babylon, Jeconiah became the father of Shealtiel; and Shealtiel the father of Zerubbabel;
B040C001V013	40	1	13	And Zerubbabel the father of Abiud; and Abiud the father of Eliakim; and Eliakim the father of Azor;
B040C001V014	40	1	14	And Azor the father of Zadok; and Zadok the father of Achim; and Achim the father of Eliud;
B040C001V015	40	1	15	And Eliud the father of Eleazar; and Eleazar the father of Matthan; and Matthan the father of Jacob;
B040C001V016	40	1	16	And Jacob the father of Joseph, the husband of Mary, by whom was born Jesus, who is called Christ.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	So all the generations from Abraham to David are fourteen generations; and from David until the exile to Babylon are fourteen generations; and from the exile to Babylon to Christ are fourteen generations.
B040C001V018	40	1	18	Now the birth of Jesus Christ happened in this way: When his mother Mary was betrothed to Joseph, before they came together, she was found to be with child by the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V019	40	1	19	Then Joseph her husband, being a just man, and not willing to disgrace her, decided to divorce her secretly.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	But while he thought on these things, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream, saying, Joseph, son of David, do not fear to take Mary as your wife: for that which is conceived in her is of the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V021	40	1	21	And she shall bring forth a son, and you shall call his name JESUS: for he shall save his people from their sins.
B040C001V022	40	1	22	Now all this was done to fulfill that which was spoken by the Lord through the prophet, saying,
B040C001V023	40	1	23	Behold, a virgin shall be with child, and shall bring forth a son, and they shall call his name Emmanuel, which translated means, God with us.
B040C001V024	40	1	24	Then Joseph, being raised from sleep, did as the angel of the Lord had bidden him, and took her as his wife:
B040C001V025	40	1	25	And kept her a virgin until she had brought forth a son: and he called his name JESUS.
B040C002V001	40	2	1	Now when Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judaea in the days of Herod the king, behold, wise men came from the east to Jerusalem,
B040C002V002	40	2	2	Saying, Where is he who has been born King of the Jews? for we have seen his star in the east, and have come to worship him.
B040C002V003	40	2	3	When Herod the king had heard these things, he was troubled, and all Jerusalem with him.
B040C002V004	40	2	4	And when he had gathered all the chief priests and scribes of the people together, he inquired of them where the Christ was to be born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	And they said to him, In Bethlehem of Judaea: for thus it was written by the prophet,
B040C002V006	40	2	6	And you Bethlehem, in the land of Judah, are not the least among the princes of Judah: for out of you shall come a Governor, who shall rule my people Israel.
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Then Herod, when he had secretly called the wise men, ascertained from them at what time the star appeared.
B040C002V008	40	2	8	And he sent them to Bethlehem, and said, Go and search diligently for the child; and when you have found him, bring me word, that I may come and worship him also.
B040C002V009	40	2	9	When they had heard the king, they departed; and, lo, the star, which they saw in the east, went before them, until it came and stood over where the child was.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	When they saw the star, they rejoiced with exceedingly great joy.
B040C002V011	40	2	11	And when they had come into the house, they saw the child with Mary his mother, and fell down, and worshipped him: and when they had opened their treasures, they presented to him gifts; gold, and frankincense, and myrrh.
B040C002V012	40	2	12	And being warned by God in a dream that they should not return to Herod, they departed to their own country by another way.
B040C002V013	40	2	13	And when they had departed, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph in a dream, saying, Arise, and take the child and his mother, and flee to Egypt, and remain there until I bring you word: for Herod will seek the child, to destroy him.
B040C002V014	40	2	14	And he arose, and took the child and his mother by night, and departed to Egypt:
B040C002V015	40	2	15	And was there until the death of Herod: that it might be fulfilled which was spoken by the Lord through the prophet, saying, Out of Egypt I have called my son.
B040C002V016	40	2	16	Then Herod, when he saw that he had been tricked by the wise men, was exceedingly angry, and sent forth, and killed all the children who were in Bethlehem, and in all the region, from two years old and under, according to the time which he had ascertained from the wise men.
B040C002V017	40	2	17	Then was fulfilled that which was spoken by Jeremiah the prophet, saying,
B040C002V018	40	2	18	In Rama there was heard a voice, weeping, and loud lamentation, Rachel weeping for her children, and she would not be comforted, because they were no more.
B040C002V019	40	2	19	But when Herod was dead, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph in Egypt,
B040C002V020	40	2	20	Saying, Arise, and take the child and his mother, and go to the land of Israel: for those who sought the child's life are dead.
B040C002V021	40	2	21	And he arose, and took the child and his mother, and came to the land of Israel.
B040C002V022	40	2	22	But when he heard that Archelaus was reigning in Judaea in the place of his father Herod, he was afraid to go there: and, being warned by God in a dream, he turned aside to the regions of Galilee:
B040C002V023	40	2	23	And he came and lived in a city called Nazareth: that what was spoken by the prophets might be fulfilled, He shall be called a Nazarene.
B040C003V001	40	3	1	In those days John the Baptist came, preaching in the wilderness of Judaea,
B040C003V002	40	3	2	And saying, Repent: for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.
B040C003V003	40	3	3	For this is he who was spoken of by the prophet Isaiah, when he said, The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.
B040C003V004	40	3	4	And John had a garment of camel's hair, and a leather girdle about his waist; and his food was locusts and wild honey.
B040C003V005	40	3	5	Then Jerusalem, and all Judaea, went out to him, and all the region around the Jordan,
B040C003V006	40	3	6	And were baptized by him in the Jordan, confessing their sins.
B040C003V007	40	3	7	But when he saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees come for baptism, he said to them, You brood of vipers, who warned you to flee from the wrath to come?
B040C003V008	40	3	8	Therefore, bring forth fruit in keeping with repentance:
B040C003V009	40	3	9	And do not think to say to yourselves, We have Abraham as our father: for I say to you, that God is able from these stones to raise up children to Abraham.
B040C003V010	40	3	10	And now the axe is laid to the root of the trees: therefore every tree which does not bring forth good fruit is cut down, and cast into the fire.
B040C003V011	40	3	11	I baptize you with water for repentance: but he who comes after me is mightier than I, whose sandals I am not worthy to carry: he shall baptize you with the Holy Spirit, and with fire.
B040C003V012	40	3	12	His winnowing fork is in his hand, and he will thoroughly clean his threshing floor, and gather his wheat into the barn; but he will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire.
B040C003V013	40	3	13	Then Jesus came from Galilee to the Jordan to John, to be baptized by him.
B040C003V014	40	3	14	But John tried to prevent him, saying, I need to be baptized by you, and do you come to me?
B040C003V015	40	3	15	And Jesus answered him, Let it be so now: for thus it is fitting for us to fulfill all righteousness. Then he consented.
B040C003V016	40	3	16	And Jesus, when he was baptized, went up immediately out of the water: and, lo, the heavens were opened to him, and he saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove, and lighting upon him:
B040C003V017	40	3	17	And lo, a voice from heaven, saying, This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.
B040C004V001	40	4	1	Then Jesus was led up by the Spirit into the wilderness to be tempted by the devil.
B040C004V002	40	4	2	And when he had fasted forty days and forty nights, he was hungry.
B040C004V003	40	4	3	And when the tempter came to him, he said, If you are the Son of God, command that these stones be made bread.
B040C004V004	40	4	4	But he answered and said, It is written, Man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word that proceeds out of the mouth of God.
B040C004V005	40	4	5	Then the devil took him up into the holy city, and set him on a pinnacle of the temple,
B040C004V006	40	4	6	And said to him, If you are the Son of God, cast yourself down: for it is written, He shall give his angels charge concerning you: and on their hands they shall bear you up, lest at any time you dash your foot against a stone.
B040C004V007	40	4	7	Jesus said to him, Again it is written, You shall not tempt the Lord your God.
B040C004V008	40	4	8	Again, the devil took him to an exceedingly high mountain, and showed him all the kingdoms of the world, and the glory of them;
B040C004V009	40	4	9	And said to him, All these things will I give you, if you will fall down and worship me.
B040C004V010	40	4	10	Then Jesus said to him, Begone, Satan: for it is written, You shall worship the Lord your God, and him only shall you serve.
B040C004V011	40	4	11	Then the devil left him, and, behold, angels came and ministered to him.
B040C004V012	40	4	12	Now when Jesus heard that John had been cast into prison, he departed into Galilee;
B040C004V013	40	4	13	And leaving Nazareth, he came and lived in Capernaum, which is upon the sea coast, in the region of Zebulun and Naphtali:
B040C004V014	40	4	14	That what was spoken by Isaiah the prophet might be fulfilled,
B040C004V015	40	4	15	The land of Zebulun, and the land of Naphtali, by the way of the sea, beyond the Jordan, Galilee of the Gentiles;
B040C004V016	40	4	16	The people who sat in darkness have seen a great light; and to those who sat in the region and shadow of death, a light has sprung up.
B040C004V017	40	4	17	From that time Jesus began to preach, and to say, Repent: for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.
B040C004V018	40	4	18	And walking by the sea of Galilee, he saw two brothers, Simon called Peter, and Andrew his brother, casting a net into the sea: for they were fishermen.
B040C004V019	40	4	19	And he said to them, Follow me, and I will make you fishers of men.
B040C004V020	40	4	20	And they immediately left their nets, and followed him.
B040C004V021	40	4	21	And going on from there, he saw two other brothers, James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother, in a boat with Zebedee their father, mending their nets; and he called them.
B040C004V022	40	4	22	And they immediately left the boat and their father, and followed him.
B040C004V023	40	4	23	And Jesus went about all Galilee, teaching in their synagogues, and preaching the gospel of the kingdom, and healing every kind of disease and every kind of infirmity among the people.
B040C004V024	40	4	24	And his fame went throughout all Syria: and they brought to him all sick people who were taken with various diseases and torments, those who were possessed by devils, and those who were epileptic, and paralytics; and he healed them.
B040C004V025	40	4	25	And great multitudes of people followed him from Galilee, and from Decapolis, and from Jerusalem, and from Judaea, and from beyond the Jordan.
B040C005V001	40	5	1	And seeing the multitudes, he went up on the mountain: and when he sat down, his disciples came to him:
B040C005V002	40	5	2	And he opened his mouth, and taught them, saying,
B040C005V003	40	5	3	Blessed are the poor in spirit: for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V004	40	5	4	Blessed are those who mourn: for they shall be comforted.
B040C005V005	40	5	5	Blessed are the meek: for they shall inherit the earth.
B040C005V006	40	5	6	Blessed are those who hunger and thirst for righteousness: for they shall be filled.
B040C005V007	40	5	7	Blessed are the merciful: for they shall obtain mercy.
B040C005V008	40	5	8	Blessed are the pure in heart: for they shall see God.
B040C005V009	40	5	9	Blessed are the peacemakers: for they shall be called sons of God.
B040C005V010	40	5	10	Blessed are those who are persecuted for righteousness' sake: for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V011	40	5	11	Blessed are you, when men shall revile you, and persecute you, and shall say all manner of evil against you falsely, for my sake.
B040C005V012	40	5	12	Rejoice, and be exceedingly glad: for great is your reward in heaven: for so they persecuted the prophets who were before you.
B040C005V013	40	5	13	You are the salt of the earth: but if the salt has lost its taste, with what shall it be salted? it is no longer good for anything, but to be cast out, and to be trodden under foot by men.
B040C005V014	40	5	14	You are the light of the world. A city that is set on a hill cannot be hidden.
B040C005V015	40	5	15	Nor do men light a lamp, and put it under a bushel, but on a lampstand; and it gives light to all who are in the house.
B040C005V016	40	5	16	Let your light so shine before men, that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father who is in heaven.
B040C005V017	40	5	17	Do not think that I have come to destroy the law, or the prophets: I have not come to destroy, but to fulfill.
B040C005V018	40	5	18	For truly I say to you, Until heaven and earth pass away, not the smallest letter, not the least stroke, shall by any means pass away from the law, until all is fulfilled.
B040C005V019	40	5	19	Therefore, whoever shall break one of the least commandments, and shall so teach men to do, he shall be called the least in the kingdom of heaven: but whoever shall do and teach them, the same shall be called great in the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V020	40	5	20	For I say to you, That unless your righteousness exceeds the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees, you shall never enter into the kingdom of heaven.
B040C005V021	40	5	21	You have heard that it was said to them of old, You shall not kill; and whoever shall kill shall be subject to judgment:
B040C005V022	40	5	22	But I say to you, That whoever is angry with his brother shall be in danger of judgment: and whoever shall say to his brother, Raca, shall be in danger of the council: but whoever shall say, You fool, shall be in danger of the hell of fire.
B040C005V023	40	5	23	Therefore if you bring your gift to the altar, and there remember that your brother has something against you;
B040C005V024	40	5	24	Leave your gift before the altar, and go your way; first be reconciled to your brother, and then come and offer your gift.
B040C005V025	40	5	25	Come to terms with your adversary quickly, while you are on the way with him; lest your adversary deliver you to the judge, and the judge deliver you to the officer, and you be cast into prison.
B040C005V026	40	5	26	Truly I say to you, You shall by no means come out of there, until you have paid the last farthing.
B040C005V027	40	5	27	You have heard that it was said, You shall not commit adultery:
B040C005V028	40	5	28	But I say to you, That whoever looks at a woman to lust for her has already committed adultery with her in his heart.
B040C005V029	40	5	29	And if your right eye causes you to sin, pluck it out, and cast it from you: for it is better for you that one of your members should perish, than that your whole body should be cast into hell.
B040C005V030	40	5	30	And if your right hand causes you to sin, cut it off, and cast it from you: for it is better for you that one of your members should perish, than that your whole body should be cast into hell.
B040C005V031	40	5	31	It has been said, Whoever shall divorce his wife, let him give her a certificate of divorce:
B040C005V032	40	5	32	But I say to you, That whoever shall divorce his wife, except for the cause of unchastity, causes her to commit adultery: and whoever shall marry a woman who has been divorced commits adultery.
B040C005V033	40	5	33	Again, you have heard that it has been said to them of old, You shall not swear falsely, but shall fulfill your oaths to the Lord:
B040C005V034	40	5	34	But I say to you, Do not swear at all; either by heaven; for it is God's throne:
B040C005V035	40	5	35	Or by the earth; for it is his footstool: or by Jerusalem; for it is the city of the great King.
B040C005V036	40	5	36	Nor shall you swear by your head, because you can not make one hair white or black.
B040C005V037	40	5	37	But let your statements be, Yes for yes; No for no: for whatever is more than these comes from the evil one.
B040C005V038	40	5	38	You have heard that it has been said, An eye for an eye, and a tooth for a tooth:
B040C005V039	40	5	39	But I say to you, Do not resist evil: but whoever shall strike you on your right cheek, turn to him the other also.
B040C005V040	40	5	40	And if any man wants to sue you, and take away your shirt, let him have your coat also.
B040C005V041	40	5	41	And whoever shall compel you to go one mile, go with him two.
B040C005V042	40	5	42	Give to him who asks from you, and do not turn away from him who would borrow from you.
B040C005V043	40	5	43	You have heard that it has been said, You shall love your neighbour, and hate your enemy.
B040C005V044	40	5	44	But I say to you, Love your enemies, and pray for those who persecute you;
B040C005V045	40	5	45	That you may be sons of your Father who is in heaven: for he makes his sun to rise on the evil and on the good, and sends rain on the just and on the unjust.
B040C005V046	40	5	46	For if you love those who love you, what reward have you? do not even the tax gatherers do the same?
B040C005V047	40	5	47	And if you greet your brethren only, what are you doing more than others? do not even the Gentiles do the same?
B040C005V048	40	5	48	Therefore be perfect, as your Father who is in heaven is perfect.
B040C006V001	40	6	1	Take heed that you do not practice your righteousness before men, to be seen by them: otherwise you have no reward from your Father who is in heaven.
B040C006V002	40	6	2	Therefore, when you give alms, do not sound a trumpet before you, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and in the streets, that they may have praise from men. Truly I say to you, They have received their reward.
B040C006V003	40	6	3	But when you give alms, do not let your left hand know what your right hand is doing:
B040C006V004	40	6	4	That your alms may be in secret: and your Father who sees in secret shall reward you.
B040C006V005	40	6	5	And when you pray, do not be like the hypocrites: for they love to pray standing in the synagogues and at the corners of the streets, that they may be seen by men. Truly I say to you, They have received their reward.
B040C006V006	40	6	6	But you, when you pray, enter into your inner room, and when you have shut your door, pray to your Father who is in secret; and your Father who sees in secret shall reward you.
B040C006V007	40	6	7	But when you pray, do not use meaningless repetition, as the Gentiles do: for they think that they shall be heard for their many words.
B040C006V008	40	6	8	Therefore, do not be like them: for your Father knows what things you have need of, before you ask him.
B040C006V009	40	6	9	Therefore, pray in this manner: Our Father in heaven, Hallowed be your name.
B040C006V010	40	6	10	Your kingdom come. Your will be done on earth, as it is in heaven.
B040C006V011	40	6	11	Give us this day our daily bread.
B040C006V012	40	6	12	And forgive us our debts, as we also have forgiven our debtors.
B040C006V013	40	6	13	And lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.
B040C006V014	40	6	14	For if you forgive men their trespasses, your heavenly Father will also forgive you:
B040C006V015	40	6	15	But if you do not forgive men their trespasses, neither will your Father forgive your trespasses.
B040C006V016	40	6	16	Moreover, when you fast, do not look somber as the hypocrites do: for they disfigure their faces, that they may be seen by men to be fasting. Truly I say to you, They have received their reward.
B040C006V017	40	6	17	But you, when you fast, anoint your head, and wash your face;
B040C006V018	40	6	18	That you may not be seen fasting by men, but by your Father who is in secret: and your Father, who sees in secret, shall reward you.
B040C006V019	40	6	19	Do not lay up for yourselves treasures upon earth, where moth and rust destroy, and where thieves break in and steal:
B040C006V020	40	6	20	But lay up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where neither moth nor rust destroys, and where thieves do not break in and steal:
B040C006V021	40	6	21	For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.
B040C006V022	40	6	22	The light of the body is the eye: therefore, if your eye is sound, your whole body shall be full of light.
B040C006V023	40	6	23	But if your eye is bad, your whole body shall be full of darkness. Therefore, if the light that is in you is darkness, how great is that darkness!
B040C006V024	40	6	24	No man can serve two masters: for either he will hate the one, and love the other; or else he will hold to the one, and despise the other. You cannot serve God and mammon.
B040C006V025	40	6	25	Therefore I say to you, Do not be anxious about your life, what you shall eat, or what you shall drink; nor for your body, what you shall put on. Is not life more than food, and the body more than clothing?
B040C006V026	40	6	26	Behold the birds of the air: they do not sow, nor do they reap, nor gather into barns; yet your heavenly Father feeds them. Are you not worth much more than they?
B040C006V027	40	6	27	Which of you by being anxious can add one cubit to the span of his life?
B040C006V028	40	6	28	And why are you anxious about clothing? Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow; they do not toil, nor do they spin:
B040C006V029	40	6	29	And yet I say to you, That even Solomon in all his glory was not arrayed like one of these.
B040C006V030	40	6	30	Therefore, if God so clothes the grass of the field, which today is, and tomorrow is cast into the oven, shall he not much more clothe you, O men of little faith?
B040C006V031	40	6	31	Therefore, do not be anxious, saying, What shall we eat? or, What shall we drink? or, With what shall we be clothed?
B040C006V032	40	6	32	After all these things the Gentiles seek: but your heavenly Father knows that you have need of all these things.
B040C006V033	40	6	33	But seek first his kingdom, and his righteousness; and all these things shall be added to you.
B040C006V034	40	6	34	Therefore, do not be anxious about tomorrow, for tomorrow shall be anxious for itself. Sufficient for each day are the troubles of its own.
B040C007V001	40	7	1	Judge not, that you may not be judged.
B040C007V002	40	7	2	For in the manner you judge, you shall be judged: and with the measure you use, it shall be measured to you.
B040C007V003	40	7	3	And why do you look at the speck that is in your brother's eye, but do not consider the beam that is in your own eye?
B040C007V004	40	7	4	Or how can you say to your brother, Let me pull the speck out of your eye; and, behold, a beam is in your own eye?
B040C007V005	40	7	5	You hypocrite, first remove the beam from your own eye; and then you shall see clearly to remove the speck from your brother's eye.
B040C007V006	40	7	6	Do not give that which is holy to dogs, nor cast your pearls before swine, lest they trample them under their feet, and turn and tear you to pieces.
B040C007V007	40	7	7	Ask, and it shall be given to you; seek, and you shall find; knock, and it shall be opened to you:
B040C007V008	40	7	8	For every one who asks receives; and he who seeks finds; and to him who knocks it shall be opened.
B040C007V009	40	7	9	Or what man is there among you, whom, if his son asks for bread, will give him a stone?
B040C007V010	40	7	10	Or if he asks for a fish, will give him a serpent?
B040C007V011	40	7	11	If you then, being evil, know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more shall your Father who is in heaven give good things to those who ask him?
B040C007V012	40	7	12	Therefore, all things that you would have men do for you, do for them: for this is the law and the prophets.
B040C007V013	40	7	13	Enter in at the narrow gate: for wide is the gate, and broad is the way, that leads to destruction, and many there are who enter in by it:
B040C007V014	40	7	14	But small is the gate, and narrow is the way, which leads to life, and few there are who find it.
B040C007V015	40	7	15	Beware of false prophets, who come to you in sheep's clothing, but inwardly they are ravenous wolves.
B040C007V016	40	7	16	You shall know them by their fruits. Do men gather grapes from thorn bushes, or figs from thistles?
B040C007V017	40	7	17	Even so, every good tree brings forth good fruit; but a bad tree brings forth bad fruit.
B040C007V018	40	7	18	A good tree cannot bring forth bad fruit, nor can a bad tree bring forth good fruit.
B040C007V019	40	7	19	Every tree that does not bring forth good fruit is cut down, and cast into the fire.
B040C007V020	40	7	20	Therefore, by their fruits you shall know them.
B040C007V021	40	7	21	Not every one who says to me, Lord, Lord, shall enter into the kingdom of heaven; but he who does the will of my Father who is in heaven.
B040C007V022	40	7	22	Many will say to me on that day, Lord, Lord, have we not prophesied in your name? and in your name cast out devils? and in your name done many miracles?
B040C007V023	40	7	23	And then I will declare to them, I never knew you: depart from me, you who work iniquity.
B040C007V024	40	7	24	Therefore, whoever hears these words of mine, and does them, will be like a wise man, who built his house upon a rock:
B040C007V025	40	7	25	And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house; and it did not fall: for it was founded upon a rock.
B040C007V026	40	7	26	And every one who hears these words of mine, and does not do them, is like a foolish man, who built his house upon the sand:
B040C007V027	40	7	27	And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house; and it fell: and great was the fall of it.
B040C007V028	40	7	28	And it came to pass, when Jesus had finished these sayings, the multitudes were astonished at his teaching:
B040C007V029	40	7	29	For he taught them as one having authority, and not as the scribes.
B040C008V001	40	8	1	When he had come down from the mountain, great multitudes followed him.
B040C008V002	40	8	2	And, behold, there came a leper and knelt before him, saying, Lord, if you are willing, you can make me clean.
B040C008V003	40	8	3	And Jesus put forth his hand, and touched him, saying, I am willing; be clean. And immediately his leprosy was cleansed.
B040C008V004	40	8	4	And Jesus said to him, See that you tell no man; but go your way, show yourself to the priest, and offer the gift that Moses commanded, for a testimony to them.
B040C008V005	40	8	5	And when Jesus entered into Capernaum, there came to him a centurion, begging him,
B040C008V006	40	8	6	Saying, Lord, my servant lies at home paralysed, grievously tormented.
B040C008V007	40	8	7	And Jesus said to him, I will come and heal him.
B040C008V008	40	8	8	The centurion answered and said, Lord, I am not worthy for you to come under my roof: but just speak the word, and my servant shall be healed.
B040C008V009	40	8	9	For I am a man under authority, having soldiers under me: and I say to this man, Go, and he goes; and to another, Come, and he comes; and to my slave, Do this, and he does it.
B040C008V010	40	8	10	When Jesus heard it, he marvelled, and said to those who followed, Truly I say to you, I have not found such great faith, no, not even in Israel.
B040C008V011	40	8	11	And I say to you, That many shall come from the east and west, and shall recline at table with Abraham, and Isaac, and Jacob, in the kingdom of heaven.
B040C008V012	40	8	12	But the sons of the kingdom shall be cast into the outer darkness: where there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C008V013	40	8	13	And Jesus said to the centurion, Go your way; and as you have believed, so be it done for you. And his servant was healed that same hour.
B040C008V014	40	8	14	And when Jesus had come into Peter's house, he saw his mother-in-law lying sick with a fever.
B040C008V015	40	8	15	And he touched her hand, and the fever left her: and she arose, and ministered to them.
B040C008V016	40	8	16	When evening had come, they brought to him many who were possessed by devils: and he cast out the spirits with his word, and healed all who were sick:
B040C008V017	40	8	17	That what was spoken by Isaiah the prophet might be fulfilled, He Himself took our infirmities, and bore our sicknesses.
B040C008V018	40	8	18	Now when Jesus saw great multitudes about him, he gave orders to depart to the other side.
B040C008V019	40	8	19	And a certain scribe came, and said to him, Teacher, I will follow you wherever you go.
B040C008V020	40	8	20	And Jesus said to him, The foxes have holes, and the birds of the air have nests; but the Son of man has nowhere to lay his head.
B040C008V021	40	8	21	And another of his disciples said to him, Lord, allow me first to go and bury my father.
B040C008V022	40	8	22	But Jesus said to him, Follow me; and let the dead bury their own dead.
B040C008V023	40	8	23	And when he entered into a boat, his disciples followed him.
B040C008V024	40	8	24	And, behold, there arose a great tempest on the sea, so that the boat was covered with the waves: but he was asleep.
B040C008V025	40	8	25	And his disciples came to him, and awoke him, saying, Lord, save us: we are perishing.
B040C008V026	40	8	26	And he said to them, Why are you fearful, O you of little faith? Then he arose, and rebuked the winds and the sea; and there was a great calm.
B040C008V027	40	8	27	And the men marvelled, saying, What manner of man is this, that even the winds and the sea obey him!
B040C008V028	40	8	28	And when he had come to the other side, into the country of the Gadarenes, two men possessed by devils met him, coming out of the tombs, exceedingly fierce, so that no man might pass by that way.
B040C008V029	40	8	29	And, behold, they cried out, saying, What have we to do with you, Jesus, you Son of God? have you come here to torment us before the time?
B040C008V030	40	8	30	Now there was, a good way off from them, a herd of many swine feeding.
B040C008V031	40	8	31	So the devils begged him, saying, If you cast us out, send us into the herd of swine.
B040C008V032	40	8	32	And he said to them, Go. And when they came out, they went into the herd of swine: and, behold, the whole herd of swine ran violently down a steep bank into the sea, and perished in the waters.
B040C008V033	40	8	33	And those who kept them fled, and went away into the city, and told everything, including what happened to those possessed by the devils.
B040C008V034	40	8	34	And, behold, the whole city came out to meet Jesus: and when they saw him, they begged him that he would depart out of their region.
B040C009V001	40	9	1	And he entered into a boat, and crossed over, and came to his own city.
B040C009V002	40	9	2	And, behold, they brought to him a paralytic man, lying on a mat: and Jesus, seeing their faith, said to the paralytic; Son, be of good cheer; your sins are forgiven.
B040C009V003	40	9	3	And, behold, certain of the scribes said within themselves, This man blasphemes.
B040C009V004	40	9	4	And Jesus, knowing their thoughts, said, Why do you think evil in your hearts?
B040C009V005	40	9	5	For which is easier, to say, Your sins are forgiven you; or to say, Arise, and walk?
B040C009V006	40	9	6	But that you may know that the Son of man has authority on earth to forgive sins, (then he said to the paralytic,) Arise, take up your mat, and go to your house.
B040C009V007	40	9	7	And he arose, and departed to his house.
B040C009V008	40	9	8	But when the multitudes saw it, they marvelled, and glorified God, who had given such authority to men.
B040C009V009	40	9	9	And as Jesus passed forth from there, he saw a man, named Matthew, sitting at the tax office: and he said to him, Follow me. And he arose, and followed him.
B040C009V010	40	9	10	And it came to pass, as Jesus reclined at table in the house, behold, many tax gatherers and sinners came and sat down with him and his disciples.
B040C009V011	40	9	11	And when the Pharisees saw it, they said to his disciples, Why does your Teacher eat with tax gatherers and sinners?
B040C009V012	40	9	12	But when Jesus heard that, he said to them, Those who are whole do not need a physician, but those who are sick.
B040C009V013	40	9	13	But go and learn what this means, I will have mercy, and not sacrifice: for I have not come to call the righteous, but sinners.
B040C009V014	40	9	14	Then the disciples of John came to him, saying, Why do we and the Pharisees fast, but your disciples do not fast?
B040C009V015	40	9	15	And Jesus said to them, Can the wedding guests mourn, as long as the bridegroom is with them? but the days will come, when the bridegroom shall be taken from them, and then they shall fast.
B040C009V016	40	9	16	No man puts a piece of new cloth on an old garment, for the patch pulls away from the garment, and the tear is made worse.
B040C009V017	40	9	17	Nor do men put new wine into old wineskins: for if they do, the wineskins burst, and the wine runs out, and the wineskins are destroyed: but they put new wine into new wineskins, and both are preserved.
B040C009V018	40	9	18	While he spoke these things to them, behold, a certain ruler came, and bowed before him, saying, My daughter has just died: but come and lay your hand upon her, and she shall live.
B040C009V019	40	9	19	And Jesus arose, and followed him, and so did his disciples.
B040C009V020	40	9	20	And, behold, a woman, who had suffered for twelve years with a flow of blood, came up behind him, and touched the hem of his garment:
B040C009V021	40	9	21	For she said to herself, If I may but touch his garment, I shall be made well.
B040C009V022	40	9	22	But Jesus turned around, and when he saw her, he said, Daughter, take heart; your faith has made you well. And the woman was made well from that hour.
B040C009V023	40	9	23	And when Jesus came into the ruler's house, and saw the flute players and the crowd making a noise,
B040C009V024	40	9	24	He said to them, Depart: for the girl is not dead, but sleeps. And they laughed him to scorn.
B040C009V025	40	9	25	But when the people were put forth, he went in, and took her by the hand, and the girl arose.
B040C009V026	40	9	26	And the report of this went abroad throughout all that region.
B040C009V027	40	9	27	And when Jesus departed from there, two blind men followed him, crying out, and saying, Son of David, have mercy on us.
B040C009V028	40	9	28	And when he had come into the house, the blind men came to him: and Jesus said to them, Do you believe that I am able to do this? They said to him, Yes, Lord.
B040C009V029	40	9	29	Then he touched their eyes, saying, According to your faith be it done to you.
B040C009V030	40	9	30	And their eyes were opened; and Jesus sternly charged them, saying, See that no man knows of this.
B040C009V031	40	9	31	When they departed, they spread abroad his fame in all that region.
B040C009V032	40	9	32	As they were going away, behold, a dumb man possessed by a devil was brought to him.
B040C009V033	40	9	33	And when the devil was cast out, the dumb man spoke: and the multitudes marvelled, saying, Nothing like this has ever been seen in Israel.
B040C009V034	40	9	34	But the Pharisees said, He casts out devils by the prince of the devils.
B040C009V035	40	9	35	And Jesus went about all the cities and villages, teaching in their synagogues, and preaching the gospel of the kingdom, and healing every sickness and every disease.
B040C009V036	40	9	36	But when he saw the multitudes, he was moved with compassion for them, because they were harassed, and helpless, like sheep without a shepherd.
B040C009V037	40	9	37	Then he said to his disciples, The harvest truly is plentiful, but the labourers are few;
B040C009V038	40	9	38	Therefore, pray to the Lord of the harvest, that he will send forth labourers into his harvest.
B040C010V001	40	10	1	And when he had called to him his twelve disciples, he gave them authority over unclean spirits, to cast them out, and to heal every kind of disease and every kind of infirmity.
B040C010V002	40	10	2	Now the names of the twelve apostles are these; The first, Simon, who is called Peter, and Andrew his brother; James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother;
B040C010V003	40	10	3	Philip, and Bartholomew; Thomas, and Matthew the tax gatherer; James the son of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus;
B040C010V004	40	10	4	Simon the Zealot, and Judas Iscariot, who also betrayed him.
B040C010V005	40	10	5	These twelve Jesus sent forth, and commanded them, saying, Do not go among the Gentiles, and do not enter into any city of the Samaritans:
B040C010V006	40	10	6	But rather go to the lost sheep of the house of Israel.
B040C010V007	40	10	7	And as you go, preach, saying, The kingdom of heaven is at hand.
B040C010V008	40	10	8	Heal the sick, cleanse the lepers, raise the dead, cast out devils: freely you have received, freely give.
B040C010V009	40	10	9	Provide neither gold, nor silver, nor copper for your purses,
B040C010V010	40	10	10	Nor bag for your journey, nor two coats, nor sandals, nor a staff: for the workman is worthy of his food.
B040C010V011	40	10	11	And into whatever city or village you shall enter, inquire who in it is worthy; and abide there until you depart.
B040C010V012	40	10	12	And when you come into a house, greet it.
B040C010V013	40	10	13	And if the house is worthy, let your peace come upon it: but if it is not worthy, let your peace return to you.
B040C010V014	40	10	14	And whoever shall not receive you, nor hear your words, when you depart out of that house or city, shake off the dust from your feet.
B040C010V015	40	10	15	Truly I say to you, It shall be more tolerable for the land of Sodom and Gomorrah in the day of judgment, than for that city.
B040C010V016	40	10	16	Behold, I send you forth as sheep in the midst of wolves: therefore be as wise as serpents, and as harmless as doves.
B040C010V017	40	10	17	But beware of men: for they will deliver you up to the councils, and they will scourge you in their synagogues;
B040C010V018	40	10	18	And you shall be brought before governors and kings for my sake, as a testimony to them and the Gentiles.
B040C010V019	40	10	19	But when they deliver you up, do not be anxious about how or what you shall speak: for it shall be given to you in that hour what you shall speak.
B040C010V020	40	10	20	For it is not you who speak, but the Spirit of your Father who speaks in you.
B040C010V021	40	10	21	And brother shall deliver up brother to death, and the father the child: and the children shall rise up against their parents, and cause them to be put to death.
B040C010V022	40	10	22	And you shall be hated by all men for my name's sake: but he who endures to the end shall be saved.
B040C010V023	40	10	23	But when they persecute you in this city, flee into another: for truly I say to you, You shall not have gone through the cities of Israel, before the Son of man comes.
B040C010V024	40	10	24	The disciple is not above his teacher, nor the servant above his master.
B040C010V025	40	10	25	It is enough for the disciple that he is like his teacher, and the servant like his master. If they have called the master of the house Beelzebub, how much more the members of his household?
B040C010V026	40	10	26	Therefore, do not fear them: for there is nothing covered, that shall not be revealed; and nothing hidden, that shall not be made known.
B040C010V027	40	10	27	What I tell you in the darkness, speak in the light: and what you hear whispered in your ear, proclaim from the housetops.
B040C010V028	40	10	28	And do not fear those who kill the body, but are not able to kill the soul: but rather fear him who is able to destroy both soul and body in hell.
B040C010V029	40	10	29	Are not two sparrows sold for a penny? and not one of them shall fall to the ground without your Father's consent.
B040C010V030	40	10	30	But the very hairs of your head are all numbered.
B040C010V031	40	10	31	Therefore, do not fear; you are of more value than many sparrows.
B040C010V032	40	10	32	Whoever shall confess me before men, I will also confess him before my Father who is in heaven.
B040C010V033	40	10	33	But whoever shall deny me before men, I will also deny him before my Father who is in heaven.
B040C010V034	40	10	34	Do not think that I have come to bring peace upon the earth: I did not come to bring peace, but a sword.
B040C010V035	40	10	35	For I have come to set a man against his father, and a daughter against her mother, and a daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law.
B040C010V036	40	10	36	And a man's foes shall be those of his own household.
B040C010V037	40	10	37	He who loves father or mother more than me is not worthy of me: and he who loves son or daughter more than me is not worthy of me.
B040C010V038	40	10	38	And he who does not take up his cross, and follow after me, is not worthy of me.
B040C010V039	40	10	39	He who finds his life shall lose it: and he who loses his life for my sake shall find it.
B040C010V040	40	10	40	He who receives you receives me, and he who receives me receives him who sent me.
B040C010V041	40	10	41	He who receives a prophet in the name of a prophet shall receive a prophet's reward; and he who receives a righteous man in the name of a righteous man shall receive a righteous man's reward.
B040C010V042	40	10	42	And whoever shall give to one of these little ones even a cup of cold water to drink because he is my disciple, truly I say to you, he shall not lose his reward.
B040C011V001	40	11	1	And it came to pass, when Jesus had finished instructing his twelve disciples, he departed from there to teach and to preach in their cities.
B040C011V002	40	11	2	Now when John heard in prison about the works of Christ, he sent word by two of his disciples,
B040C011V003	40	11	3	And said to him, Are you he who is to come, or should we look for another?
B040C011V004	40	11	4	Jesus answered them, Go and tell John those things which you hear and see:
B040C011V005	40	11	5	The blind receive their sight, and the lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, and the deaf hear, the dead are raised up, and the poor have the gospel preached to them.
B040C011V006	40	11	6	And blessed is he who does not find cause to stumble over me.
B040C011V007	40	11	7	And as they departed, Jesus began to say to the multitudes concerning John, What did you go out into the wilderness to see? A reed shaken by the wind?
B040C011V008	40	11	8	But what did you go out to see? A man clothed in soft clothing? behold, those who wear soft clothing are in kings' houses.
B040C011V009	40	11	9	But what did you go out to see? A prophet? yes, I say to you, and more than a prophet.
B040C011V010	40	11	10	For this is he, of whom it is written, Behold, I send my messenger before your face, who shall prepare your way before you.
B040C011V011	40	11	11	Truly I say to you, Among those who are born of women there has not arisen one greater than John the Baptist: yet he who is least in the kingdom of heaven is greater than he.
B040C011V012	40	11	12	And from the days of John the Baptist until now the kingdom of heaven suffers violence, and the violent take it by force.
B040C011V013	40	11	13	For all the prophets and the law prophesied until John.
B040C011V014	40	11	14	And if you will receive it, he is Elijah, who was to come.
B040C011V015	40	11	15	He who has ears to hear, let him hear.
B040C011V016	40	11	16	But to what shall I liken this generation? It is like children sitting in the markets, and calling to their fellows,
B040C011V017	40	11	17	And saying, We have piped for you, and you have not danced; we have mourned for you, and you have not lamented.
B040C011V018	40	11	18	For John came neither eating nor drinking, and they say, He has a devil.
B040C011V019	40	11	19	The Son of man came eating and drinking, and they say, Behold, a glutton and a drunkard, a friend of tax gatherers and sinners. But wisdom is justified by her deeds.
B040C011V020	40	11	20	Then he began to rebuke the cities in which most of his miracles had been done, because they did not repent:
B040C011V021	40	11	21	Woe to you, Chorazin! woe to you, Bethsaida! for if the miracles which were done in you had been done in Tyre and Sidon, they would have repented long ago in sackcloth and ashes.
B040C011V022	40	11	22	But I say to you, It shall be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon at the day of judgment, than for you.
B040C011V023	40	11	23	And you, Capernaum, will you be exalted to heaven? you shall be brought down to Hades: for if the miracles which have been done in you had been done in Sodom, it would have remained until this day.
B040C011V024	40	11	24	But I say to you, That it shall be more tolerable for the land of Sodom in the day of judgment, than for you.
B040C011V025	40	11	25	At that time Jesus said, I thank you, O Father, Lord of heaven and earth, because you have hidden these things from the wise and prudent, and have revealed them to babes.
B040C011V026	40	11	26	Yes, Father: for so it seemed good in your sight.
B040C011V027	40	11	27	All things have been delivered to me by my Father: and no man knows the Son, but the Father; nor does any man know the Father, except the Son, and he to whom the Son chooses to reveal him.
B040C011V028	40	11	28	Come to me, all you who labour and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest.
B040C011V029	40	11	29	Take my yoke upon you, and learn from me; for I am gentle and lowly in heart: and you shall find rest for your souls.
B040C011V030	40	11	30	For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light.
B040C012V001	40	12	1	At that time Jesus went on the sabbath day through the grainfields; and his disciples were hungry, and began to pluck the heads of grain, and to eat.
B040C012V002	40	12	2	But when the Pharisees saw it, they said to him, Behold, your disciples do that which is not lawful to do upon the sabbath day.
B040C012V003	40	12	3	But he said to them, Have you not read what David did, when he was hungry, he and those who were with him;
B040C012V004	40	12	4	How he entered into the house of God, and ate the showbread, which was not lawful for him to eat, nor for those who were with him, but only for the priests?
B040C012V005	40	12	5	Or have you not read in the law, that on the sabbath days the priests in the temple profane the sabbath, and are blameless?
B040C012V006	40	12	6	But I say to you, That in this place is one greater than the temple.
B040C012V007	40	12	7	But if you had known what this means, I will have mercy, and not sacrifice, you would not have condemned the guiltless.
B040C012V008	40	12	8	For the Son of man is Lord of the sabbath.
B040C012V009	40	12	9	And when he departed from there, he went into their synagogue:
B040C012V010	40	12	10	And, behold, there was a man who had a withered hand. And they asked him, saying, Is it lawful to heal on the sabbath? that they might accuse him.
B040C012V011	40	12	11	And he said to them, What man is there among you, if he has one sheep, and if it falls into a pit on the sabbath day, will not lay hold of it, and lift it out?
B040C012V012	40	12	12	How much more valuable then is a man than a sheep? Therefore, it is lawful to do good on the sabbath.
B040C012V013	40	12	13	Then he said to the man, Stretch forth your hand. And he stretched it forth; and it was restored, whole like the other.
B040C012V014	40	12	14	Then the Pharisees went out, and held a council against him, how they might destroy him.
B040C012V015	40	12	15	But Jesus, knowing this, withdrew from there: and great multitudes followed him, and he healed them all;
B040C012V016	40	12	16	And charged them that they should not make him known:
B040C012V017	40	12	17	That what was spoken by Isaiah the prophet might be fulfilled,
B040C012V018	40	12	18	Behold my servant, whom I have chosen; my beloved, in whom my soul is well pleased: I will put my spirit upon him, and he shall proclaim justice to the Gentiles.
B040C012V019	40	12	19	He shall not quarrel, nor cry out; nor shall any man hear his voice in the streets.
B040C012V020	40	12	20	A bruised reed he shall not break, and a smoking wick he shall not quench, until he brings justice to victory.
B040C012V021	40	12	21	And in his name shall the Gentiles hope.
B040C012V022	40	12	22	Then was brought to him one possessed by a devil, blind, and dumb: and he healed him, so that the blind and dumb man both spoke and saw.
B040C012V023	40	12	23	And all the people were amazed, and said, Is this not the son of David?
B040C012V024	40	12	24	But when the Pharisees heard it, they said, This fellow casts out devils only by Beelzebub, the prince of the devils.
B040C012V025	40	12	25	And Jesus knew their thoughts, and said to them, Every kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation; and every city or house divided against itself shall not stand:
B040C012V026	40	12	26	And if Satan casts out Satan, he is divided against himself; how then shall his kingdom stand?
B040C012V027	40	12	27	And if I cast out devils by Beelzebub, by whom do your children cast them out? therefore they shall be your judges.
B040C012V028	40	12	28	But if I cast out devils by the Spirit of God, then the kingdom of God has come upon you.
B040C012V029	40	12	29	Or how can one enter a strong man's house, and plunder his goods, unless he first binds the strong man? and then he will plunder his house.
B040C012V030	40	12	30	He who is not with me is against me; and he who does not gather with me scatters.
B040C012V031	40	12	31	Therefore I say to you, Every sin and blasphemy shall be forgiven men: but the blasphemy against the Holy Spirit shall not be forgiven men.
B040C012V032	40	12	32	And whoever speaks a word against the Son of man, it shall be forgiven him: but whoever speaks against the Holy Spirit, it shall not be forgiven him, neither in this world, nor in the world to come.
B040C012V033	40	12	33	Either make the tree good, and its fruit good; or else make the tree corrupt, and its fruit corrupt: for the tree is known by its fruit.
B040C012V034	40	12	34	You brood of vipers, how can you, being evil, speak good things? for out of the abundance of the heart the mouth speaks.
B040C012V035	40	12	35	A good man out of the good treasure of his heart brings forth good things: and an evil man out of his evil treasure brings forth evil things.
B040C012V036	40	12	36	But I say to you, That every idle word that men shall speak, they shall give account of on the day of judgment.
B040C012V037	40	12	37	For by your words you shall be justified, and by your words you shall be condemned.
B040C012V038	40	12	38	Then certain of the scribes and of the Pharisees answered, saying, Teacher, we wish see a sign from you.
B040C012V039	40	12	39	But he answered them, An evil and adulterous generation seeks after a sign; and no sign shall be given to it, but the sign of the prophet Jonah:
B040C012V040	40	12	40	For as Jonah was three days and three nights in the belly of a huge fish; so shall the Son of man be three days and three nights in the heart of the earth.
B040C012V041	40	12	41	The men of Nineveh shall rise in judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it: because they repented at the preaching of Jonah; and, behold, one greater than Jonah is here.
B040C012V042	40	12	42	The queen of the south shall rise up in the judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it: for she came from the remotest parts of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon; and, behold, one greater than Solomon is here.
B040C012V043	40	12	43	When the unclean spirit has gone out of a man, it passes through dry places, seeking rest, and finds none.
B040C012V044	40	12	44	Then it says, I will return to my house from which I came; and when it comes, it finds it empty, swept, and put in order.
B040C012V045	40	12	45	Then it goes, and takes with it seven other spirits more wicked than itself, and they enter in and live there: and the last state of that man is worse than the first. So shall it also be with this wicked generation.
B040C012V046	40	12	46	While he was still talking to the people, behold, his mother and his brothers stood outside, desiring to speak with him.
B040C012V047	40	12	47	Then one said to him, Behold, your mother and your brothers stand outside, desiring to speak with you.
B040C012V048	40	12	48	But he answered and said to him who told him, Who is my mother? and who are my brothers?
B040C012V049	40	12	49	And he stretched forth his hand toward his disciples, and said, Behold my mother and my brothers!
B040C012V050	40	12	50	For whoever shall do the will of my Father who is in heaven is my brother, and sister, and mother.
B040C013V001	40	13	1	That same day Jesus went out of the house, and sat by the sea.
B040C013V002	40	13	2	And great multitudes gathered around him, so that he went into a boat, and sat; and the whole multitude stood on the shore.
B040C013V003	40	13	3	And he spoke many things to them in parables, saying, Behold, a sower went forth to sow;
B040C013V004	40	13	4	And when he sowed, some seeds fell by the wayside, and the birds came and devoured them:
B040C013V005	40	13	5	Some fell upon stony places, where they did not have much earth: and at once they sprang up, because they had no depth of soil:
B040C013V006	40	13	6	And when the sun came up, they were scorched; and because they had no root, they withered away.
B040C013V007	40	13	7	And some fell among thorns; and the thorns sprang up, and choked them:
B040C013V008	40	13	8	But other seeds fell into good ground, and brought forth fruit, some a hundredfold, some sixtyfold, some thirtyfold.
B040C013V009	40	13	9	He who has ears, let him hear.
B040C013V010	40	13	10	And the disciples came, and said to him, Why do you speak to them in parables?
B040C013V011	40	13	11	He answered them, It has been given to you to know the mysteries of the kingdom of heaven, but to them it has not been given.
B040C013V012	40	13	12	For whoever has, to him shall more be given, and he shall have an abundance: but whoever does not have, even what he has shall be taken away.
B040C013V013	40	13	13	Therefore, I speak to them in parables: because seeing they see not; and hearing they hear not, neither do they understand.
B040C013V014	40	13	14	And in them is fulfilled the prophecy of Isaiah, who says, You shall continue to hear, but not understand; and you shall continue to see, but not perceive:
B040C013V015	40	13	15	For this people's heart has become dull, and their ears are hard of hearing, and their eyes they have closed; lest they should see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, and should understand with their heart, and should be converted, and I should heal them.
B040C013V016	40	13	16	But blessed are your eyes, for they see: and your ears, for they hear.
B040C013V017	40	13	17	For truly I say to you, That many prophets and righteous men have desired to see those things which you see, and have not seen them; and to hear those things which you hear, and have not heard them.
B040C013V018	40	13	18	Hear then the parable of the sower.
B040C013V019	40	13	19	When anyone hears the word of the kingdom, and does not understand it, then the wicked one comes, and catches away that which was sown in his heart. This is the seed that was sown by the wayside.
B040C013V020	40	13	20	The seed sown upon stony places is he who hears the word, and immediately receives it with joy;
B040C013V021	40	13	21	Yet he has no root in himself, and endures only for a while: when tribulation or persecution arises because of the word, he falls away.
B040C013V022	40	13	22	The seed sown among the thorns is he who hears the word; and the cares of this world, and the deceitfulness of riches, choke the word, and he becomes unfruitful.
B040C013V023	40	13	23	But the seed sown on the good ground is he who hears the word, and understands it; he also bears fruit, and brings forth, in one case a hundredfold, in another sixty, and in another thirty.
B040C013V024	40	13	24	He put forth another parable to them, saying, The kingdom of heaven is like a man who sowed good seed in his field:
B040C013V025	40	13	25	But while everyone slept, his enemy came and sowed tares among the wheat, and went away.
B040C013V026	40	13	26	But when the wheat had sprung up, and brought forth fruit, then the tares appeared also.
B040C013V027	40	13	27	So the servants of the landowner came and said to him, Sir, did you not sow good seed in your field? where then did the tares come from?
B040C013V028	40	13	28	He said to them, An enemy has done this. The servants said to him, Do you wish for us to go and gather them up?
B040C013V029	40	13	29	But he said, No; lest while you gather up the tares, you also pull up the wheat with them.
B040C013V030	40	13	30	Let both grow together until the harvest: and at the time of harvest I will say to the reapers, Gather together first the tares, and bind them in bundles to burn them: but gather the wheat into my barn.
B040C013V031	40	13	31	He put forth another parable to them, saying, The kingdom of heaven is like a grain of mustard seed, which a man took, and sowed in his field:
B040C013V032	40	13	32	It is the smallest of all seeds: but when it is fully grown, it is the largest of the garden plants, and becomes a tree, so that the birds of the air come and lodge in its branches.
B040C013V033	40	13	33	He spoke another parable to them; The kingdom of heaven is like leaven, which a woman took, and hid in three measures of flour, until it was all leavened.
B040C013V034	40	13	34	All these things Jesus spoke to the multitude in parables; and he spoke nothing to them without using a parable,
B040C013V035	40	13	35	That what was spoken by the prophet might be fulfilled, I will open my mouth in parables; I will utter things which have been kept secret from the foundation of the world.
B040C013V036	40	13	36	Then Jesus sent the multitude away, and went into the house: and his disciples came to him, saying, Explain to us the parable of the tares of the field.
B040C013V037	40	13	37	He answered them, He who sows the good seed is the Son of man;
B040C013V038	40	13	38	The field is the world; the good seed are the sons of the kingdom; but the tares are the sons of the wicked one;
B040C013V039	40	13	39	The enemy who sowed them is the devil; the harvest is the end of the world; and the reapers are the angels.
B040C013V040	40	13	40	Therefore, as the tares are gathered and burned in the fire; so shall it be at the end of this age.
B040C013V041	40	13	41	The Son of man shall send forth his angels, and they shall gather out of his kingdom all things that offend, and those who do iniquity;
B040C013V042	40	13	42	And shall cast them into a furnace of fire: where there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C013V043	40	13	43	Then the righteous shall shine forth as the sun in the kingdom of their Father. He who has ears, let him hear.
B040C013V044	40	13	44	Again, the kingdom of heaven is like a treasure hidden in a field, which a man found and hid again, then for joy went and sold all that he had, and bought that field.
B040C013V045	40	13	45	Again, the kingdom of heaven is like a merchant seeking fine pearls.
B040C013V046	40	13	46	When he found one pearl of great value, he went and sold all that he had, and bought it.
B040C013V047	40	13	47	Again, the kingdom of heaven is like a net, that was cast into the sea, and gathered fish of every kind:
B040C013V048	40	13	48	Which, when it was full, they drew it to shore, and sat down, and gathered the good into vessels, but cast the bad away.
B040C013V049	40	13	49	So shall it be at the end of the world: the angels shall come forth, and separate the wicked from among the just,
B040C013V050	40	13	50	And shall cast them into the furnace of fire, where there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C013V051	40	13	51	Jesus said to them, Have you understood all these things? They said to him, Yes.
B040C013V052	40	13	52	Then he said to them, Therefore every scribe who is instructed about the kingdom of heaven is like a man who is an owner of a house, who brings forth out of his treasure things new and old.
B040C013V053	40	13	53	And it came to pass, that when Jesus had finished these parables, he departed from there.
B040C013V054	40	13	54	And when he had come to his home town, he taught them in their synagogue, so that they were astonished, and said, Where did this man get this wisdom, and these miracles?
B040C013V055	40	13	55	Is this not the carpenter's son? is not his mother called Mary? and his brothers, James, and Joseph, and Simon, and Judas?
B040C013V056	40	13	56	And his sisters, are they not all with us? Where then did this man get all these things?
B040C013V057	40	13	57	And they were offended by him. But Jesus said to them, A prophet is not without honour, except in his home town, and in his own house.
B040C013V058	40	13	58	And he did not do many miracles there because of their unbelief.
B040C014V001	40	14	1	At that time Herod the tetrarch heard of the fame of Jesus,
B040C014V002	40	14	2	And he said to his servants, This is John the Baptist; he has risen from the dead; and therefore miraculous powers are at work in him.
B040C014V003	40	14	3	For Herod had laid hold on John, and bound him, and put him in prison for the sake of Herodias, his brother Philip's wife.
B040C014V004	40	14	4	For John said to him, It is not lawful for you to have her.
B040C014V005	40	14	5	And although he would have put him to death, he feared the people, because they counted him as a prophet.
B040C014V006	40	14	6	But when Herod's birthday came, the daughter of Herodias danced before them, and pleased Herod.
B040C014V007	40	14	7	Whereupon he promised with an oath to give her whatever she would ask.
B040C014V008	40	14	8	And she, having been prompted by her mother, said, Give me John the Baptist's head here on a platter.
B040C014V009	40	14	9	And the king was sorry: nevertheless, because of his oath and his guests, he commanded that it be given to her.
B040C014V010	40	14	10	And he sent, and had John beheaded in the prison.
B040C014V011	40	14	11	And his head was brought on a platter, and given to the girl: and she brought it to her mother.
B040C014V012	40	14	12	And his disciples came, and took the body, and buried it, and went and told Jesus.
B040C014V013	40	14	13	When Jesus heard of it, he departed from there by boat privately into a solitary place: and when the people heard this, they followed him on foot out of the cities.
B040C014V014	40	14	14	As Jesus went ashore, and saw a great multitude, he was moved with compassion toward them, and he healed their sick.
B040C014V015	40	14	15	And when it was evening, his disciples came to him, saying, This is a desolate place, and the day is now past; send the multitude away, that they may go into the villages and buy themselves food.
B040C014V016	40	14	16	But Jesus said to them, They need not depart; you give them something to eat.
B040C014V017	40	14	17	And they said to him, We have here but five loaves, and two fish.
B040C014V018	40	14	18	He said, Bring them here to me.
B040C014V019	40	14	19	And he commanded the multitude to sit down on the grass, and took the five loaves, and the two fish, and looking up to heaven, he blessed, and broke, and gave the loaves to his disciples, and the disciples to the multitude.
B040C014V020	40	14	20	And they all ate, and were filled: and they took up what remained of the fragments, twelve baskets full.
B040C014V021	40	14	21	And those who had eaten were about five thousand men, besides women and children.
B040C014V022	40	14	22	And immediately Jesus made his disciples get into a boat, and to go before him to the other side, while he sent the multitude away.
B040C014V023	40	14	23	And when he had sent the multitude away, he went up on the mountain by himself to pray: and when evening came, he was there alone.
B040C014V024	40	14	24	But the boat was now many stadia from the land, tossed by waves: for the wind was contrary.
B040C014V025	40	14	25	And in the fourth watch of the night Jesus went to them, walking on the sea.
B040C014V026	40	14	26	And when the disciples saw him walking on the sea, they were troubled, saying, It is a ghost; and they cried out in fear.
B040C014V027	40	14	27	But immediately Jesus spoke to them, saying, Take heart; it is I; do not be afraid.
B040C014V028	40	14	28	And Peter answered him and said, Lord, if it is you, bid me come to you on the water.
B040C014V029	40	14	29	And he said, Come. And Peter got down out of the boat, and walked on the water to Jesus.
B040C014V030	40	14	30	But when he saw the wind, he was afraid; and beginning to sink, he cried out, saying, Lord, save me.
B040C014V031	40	14	31	And immediately Jesus stretched forth his hand, and caught him, and said to him, O you of little faith, why did you doubt?
B040C014V032	40	14	32	And when they got into the boat, the wind ceased.
B040C014V033	40	14	33	Then those who were in the boat came and worshipped him, saying, Truly you are the Son of God.
B040C014V034	40	14	34	And when they had crossed over, they came to the land of Gennesaret.
B040C014V035	40	14	35	And when the men of that place recognized him, they sent out into all that country round about, and brought to him all who were diseased;
B040C014V036	40	14	36	And begged him that they might just touch the hem of his garment: and as many as touched it were made perfectly well.
B040C015V001	40	15	1	Then Pharisees and scribes came to Jesus from Jerusalem, saying,
B040C015V002	40	15	2	Why do your disciples transgress the tradition of the elders? for they do not wash their hands when they eat bread.
B040C015V003	40	15	3	But he answered and said to them, Why do you transgress the commandment of God by your tradition?
B040C015V004	40	15	4	For God commanded, saying, Honour your father and mother: and, He who curses father or mother, let him be put to death.
B040C015V005	40	15	5	But you say, Whoever shall say to his father or his mother, Whatever of mine might benefit you is a gift to God;
B040C015V006	40	15	6	Then he is free not to honour his father or his mother. Thus have you made the commandment of God void by your tradition.
B040C015V007	40	15	7	You hypocrites, well did Isaiah prophesy of you, saying,
B040C015V008	40	15	8	This people honours me with their lips; but their hearts are far from me.
B040C015V009	40	15	9	But in vain do they worship me, teaching for doctrines the commandments of men.
B040C015V010	40	15	10	And he called the multitude, and said to them, Hear, and understand:
B040C015V011	40	15	11	Not that which goes into the mouth defiles a man; but that which comes out of the mouth, this defiles a man.
B040C015V012	40	15	12	Then his disciples came, and said to him, Do you know that the Pharisees were offended, after they heard this saying?
B040C015V013	40	15	13	But he answered and said, Every plant which my heavenly Father has not planted shall be rooted up.
B040C015V014	40	15	14	Let them alone: they are blind leaders of the blind. And if the blind lead the blind, both shall fall into the ditch.
B040C015V015	40	15	15	Then Peter answered and said to him, Explain to us this parable.
B040C015V016	40	15	16	And Jesus said, Are you also still without understanding?
B040C015V017	40	15	17	Do you not yet understand, that whatever enters in at the mouth goes into the belly, and is eliminated?
B040C015V018	40	15	18	But those things which proceed out of the mouth come forth from the heart; and they defile the man.
B040C015V019	40	15	19	For out of the heart proceed evil thoughts, murders, adulteries, sexual immorality, thefts, false witness, slanders:
B040C015V020	40	15	20	These are the things which defile a man: but to eat with unwashed hands does not defile a man.
B040C015V021	40	15	21	Then Jesus went from there, and departed to the districts of Tyre and Sidon.
B040C015V022	40	15	22	And, behold, a woman of Canaan came out of that region, and cried to him, saying, Have mercy on me, O Lord, Son of David; my daughter is grievously vexed with a devil.
B040C015V023	40	15	23	But he did not answer her a word. And his disciples came and begged him, saying, Send her away; for she cries after us.
B040C015V024	40	15	24	But he answered and said, I have been sent only to the lost sheep of the house of Israel.
B040C015V025	40	15	25	Then she came and worshipped him, saying, Lord, help me.
B040C015V026	40	15	26	But he answered and said, It is not proper to take the children's bread, and to cast it to dogs.
B040C015V027	40	15	27	And she said, True, Lord: yet the dogs eat the crumbs which fall from their masters' table.
B040C015V028	40	15	28	Then Jesus answered and said to her, O woman, great is your faith: be it done for you as you wish. And her daughter was made well from that very hour.
B040C015V029	40	15	29	And Jesus departed from there, and came near to the sea of Galilee; and went up on a mountain, and sat down there.
B040C015V030	40	15	30	And great multitudes came to him, having with them those who were lame, crippled, blind, dumb, and many others, and put them down at Jesus' feet; and he healed them,
B040C015V031	40	15	31	So that the multitude wondered, when they saw the dumb speaking, the crippled made whole, the lame walking, and the blind seeing: and they glorified the God of Israel.
B040C015V032	40	15	32	Then Jesus called his disciples to himself, and said, I have compassion on the multitude, because they have been with me now three days, and have nothing to eat: and I will not send them away fasting, lest they faint on the way.
B040C015V033	40	15	33	And his disciples said to him, Where could we get enough bread in the wilderness to fill so great a multitude?
B040C015V034	40	15	34	And Jesus said to them, How many loaves do you have? And they said, Seven, and a few little fish.
B040C015V035	40	15	35	And he commanded the multitude to sit down on the ground.
B040C015V036	40	15	36	And he took the seven loaves and the fish, and gave thanks, and broke them, and gave to his disciples, and the disciples to the multitude.
B040C015V037	40	15	37	And they all ate, and were filled: and they took up the broken pieces that were left, seven baskets full.
B040C015V038	40	15	38	And those who ate were four thousand men, besides women and children.
B040C015V039	40	15	39	And he sent away the multitude, and got into the boat, and came to the region of Magadan.
B040C016V001	40	16	1	The Pharisees and the Sadducees came, and testing him, asked that he would show them a sign from heaven.
B040C016V002	40	16	2	He answered and said to them, When it is evening, you say, It will be fair weather: for the sky is red.
B040C016V003	40	16	3	And in the morning, It will be foul weather today: for the sky is red and threatening. O you hypocrites, you can discern the face of the sky; but can you not discern the signs of the times?
B040C016V004	40	16	4	A wicked and adulterous generation seeks after a sign; and there shall be no sign given to it, but the sign of the prophet Jonah. And he left them, and departed.
B040C016V005	40	16	5	When they came to the other side of the lake, his disciples found they had forgotten to take bread.
B040C016V006	40	16	6	Then Jesus said to them, Take heed, and beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees.
B040C016V007	40	16	7	And they discussed among themselves, saying, It is because we brought no bread.
B040C016V008	40	16	8	When Jesus perceived this, he said to them, O you of little faith, why do you discuss among yourselves that you have brought no bread?
B040C016V009	40	16	9	Do you not yet understand; do you not remember the five loaves of the five thousand, and how many baskets you took up?
B040C016V010	40	16	10	Or the seven loaves of the four thousand, and how many baskets you took up?
B040C016V011	40	16	11	How is it that you do not understand that I did not speak to you concerning bread, but that you should beware of the leaven of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees?
B040C016V012	40	16	12	Then they understood that he bade them not beware of the leaven of bread, but of the teaching of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees.
B040C016V013	40	16	13	When Jesus came to the district of Caesarea Philippi, he asked his disciples, saying, Who do men say that the Son of man is?
B040C016V014	40	16	14	And they said, Some say that you are John the Baptist: some, Elijah; and others, Jeremiah, or one of the prophets.
B040C016V015	40	16	15	He said to them, But who do you say that I am?
B040C016V016	40	16	16	Simon Peter answered and said, You are the Christ, the Son of the living God.
B040C016V017	40	16	17	And Jesus answered and said to him, Blessed are you, Simon, son of Jonah: for flesh and blood has not revealed this to you, but my Father who is in heaven.
B040C016V018	40	16	18	And I say also to you, That you are Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church; and the gates of Hades shall not prevail against it.
B040C016V019	40	16	19	And I will give to you the keys of the kingdom of heaven: and whatever you shall bind on earth shall be bound in heaven: and whatever you shall loose on earth shall be loosed in heaven.
B040C016V020	40	16	20	Then he charged his disciples that they should tell no man that he was the Christ.
B040C016V021	40	16	21	From that time forth Jesus began to show to his disciples that he must go to Jerusalem, and suffer many things from the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be killed, and be raised on the third day.
B040C016V022	40	16	22	Then Peter took him, and began to rebuke him, saying, God forbid it, Lord: this shall not happen to you.
B040C016V023	40	16	23	But he turned, and said to Peter, Get behind me, Satan: you are an offence to me: for you are not thinking of the things of God, but of the things of men.
B040C016V024	40	16	24	Then Jesus said to his disciples, If any man will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me.
B040C016V025	40	16	25	For whoever wishes to save his life shall lose it: and whoever loses his life for my sake shall find it.
B040C016V026	40	16	26	For what does it profit a man, if he shall gain the whole world, and lose his own soul? or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?
B040C016V027	40	16	27	For the Son of man shall come in the glory of his Father with his angels; and then he shall reward every man according to his works.
B040C016V028	40	16	28	Truly I say to you, There are some standing here, who shall not taste of death, until they see the Son of man coming in his kingdom.
B040C017V001	40	17	1	And after six days Jesus took Peter, James, and John his brother, and brought them up a high mountain where they were alone,
B040C017V002	40	17	2	And was transfigured before them: and his face shone like the sun, and his clothing was white as the light.
B040C017V003	40	17	3	And, behold, there appeared to them Moses and Elijah, talking with him.
B040C017V004	40	17	4	Then Peter answered, and said to Jesus, Lord, it is good for us to be here: if you wish, let us make three tabernacles here; one for you, one for Moses, and one for Elijah.
B040C017V005	40	17	5	While he was still speaking, behold, a bright cloud overshadowed them: and a voice out of the cloud said, This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased; hear him.
B040C017V006	40	17	6	And when the disciples heard it, they fell on their faces, and were very afraid.
B040C017V007	40	17	7	And Jesus came and touched them, and said, Arise, and do not be afraid.
B040C017V008	40	17	8	And when they had lifted up their eyes, they saw no one, except Jesus only.
B040C017V009	40	17	9	And as they came down from the mountain, Jesus charged them, saying, Tell the vision to no one, until the Son of man has risen again from the dead.
B040C017V010	40	17	10	And his disciples asked him, saying, Why then do the scribes say that Elijah must come first?
B040C017V011	40	17	11	And Jesus answered them, Elijah truly shall come first, and restore all things.
B040C017V012	40	17	12	But I say to you, That Elijah has already come, and they did not know him, but have done to him whatever they pleased. Likewise shall the Son of man suffer at their hands.
B040C017V013	40	17	13	Then the disciples understood that he spoke to them of John the Baptist.
B040C017V014	40	17	14	And when they had come to the multitude, a certain man came to him, kneeling down before him, and saying,
B040C017V015	40	17	15	Lord, have mercy on my son: for he is epileptic, and severely vexed: for often he falls into the fire, and often into the water.
B040C017V016	40	17	16	And I brought him to your disciples, and they could not cure him.
B040C017V017	40	17	17	Then Jesus answered and said, O faithless and perverse generation, how long shall I be with you? how long shall I endure you? bring him here to me.
B040C017V018	40	17	18	And Jesus rebuked the devil; and it departed out of him: and the boy was cured from that very hour.
B040C017V019	40	17	19	Then the disciples came to Jesus privately, and said, Why could we not cast it out?
B040C017V020	40	17	20	And Jesus said to them, Because of your unbelief: for truly I say to you, If you have faith as a grain of mustard seed, you shall say to this mountain, Move from here to there; and it shall move; and nothing shall be impossible for you.
B040C017V021	40	17	21	[Yet this kind does not go out except by prayer and fasting.]
B040C017V022	40	17	22	And when they came together in Galilee, Jesus said to them, The Son of man shall be betrayed into the hands of men:
B040C017V023	40	17	23	And they shall kill him, and the third day he shall be raised again. And they were exceedingly sorry.
B040C017V024	40	17	24	And when they had come to Capernaum, those who collected the tax came to Peter, and said, Does not your teacher pay the tax?
B040C017V025	40	17	25	He said, Yes. And when he came into the house, Jesus spoke to him first, saying, What do you think, Simon? from whom do the kings of the earth take customs or tribute? from their own sons, or from strangers?
B040C017V026	40	17	26	Peter said to him, From strangers. Jesus said to him, Then the sons are free.
B040C017V027	40	17	27	But lest we offend them, go to the sea, and cast in a hook, and take the first fish that comes up; and when you have opened its mouth, you shall find a shekel: take that, and give it to them for me and you.
B040C018V001	40	18	1	At that time the disciples came to Jesus, saying, Who is the greatest in the kingdom of heaven?
B040C018V002	40	18	2	And Jesus called a little child to him, and set him in the midst of them,
B040C018V003	40	18	3	And said, Truly I say to you, Unless you are converted, and become like little children, you shall not enter into the kingdom of heaven.
B040C018V004	40	18	4	Therefore, whoever shall humble himself as this little child, he is greatest in the kingdom of heaven.
B040C018V005	40	18	5	And whoever shall receive one such little child in my name receives me.
B040C018V006	40	18	6	But whoever shall cause one of these little ones who believe in me to sin, it would be better for him that a great millstone be hung around his neck, and that he be drowned in the depths of the sea.
B040C018V007	40	18	7	Woe to the world because of temptations! for it must be that temptations come; but woe to that man by whom the temptation comes!
B040C018V008	40	18	8	Therefore, if your hand or your foot causes you to sin, cut it off, and cast it from you: it is better for you to enter into life maimed or crippled, rather than having two hands or two feet to be cast into eternal fire.
B040C018V009	40	18	9	And if your eye causes you to sin, pluck it out, and cast it from you: it is better for you to enter into life with one eye, rather than having two eyes to be cast into the fire of hell.
B040C018V010	40	18	10	Take heed that you do not despise one of these little ones; for I say to you, That in heaven their angels always behold the face of my Father who is in heaven.
B040C018V011	40	18	11	[For the Son of man has come to save that which was lost.]
B040C018V012	40	18	12	What do you think? if a man has a hundred sheep, and one of them goes astray, does he not leave the ninety-nine on the mountains, and seek the one that has gone astray?
B040C018V013	40	18	13	And if he finds it, truly I say to you, he rejoices more over that sheep, than over the ninety-nine which did not go astray.
B040C018V014	40	18	14	In the same way, it is not the will of your Father who is in heaven, that one of these little ones should perish.
B040C018V015	40	18	15	If your brother shall sin against you, go and tell him his fault between you and him alone: if he shall hear you, you have gained your brother.
B040C018V016	40	18	16	But if he will not hear you, then take with you one or two more, that by the testimony of two or three witnesses every word may be established.
B040C018V017	40	18	17	And if he refuses to hear them, tell it to the church: but if he even refuses to hear the church, let him be to you as a Gentile and a tax gatherer.
B040C018V018	40	18	18	Truly I say to you, Whatever you shall bind on earth shall be bound in heaven: and whatever you shall loose on earth shall be loosed in heaven.
B040C018V019	40	18	19	Again I say to you, That if two of you shall agree on earth about anything that they shall ask, it shall be done for them by my Father who is in heaven.
B040C018V020	40	18	20	For where two or three are gathered together in my name, there am I in the midst of them.
B040C018V021	40	18	21	Then Peter came to him, and said, Lord, how often shall my brother sin against me, and I forgive him? up to seven times?
B040C018V022	40	18	22	Jesus said to him, I do not say to you, Up to seven times, but, Up to seventy times seven.
B040C018V023	40	18	23	Therefore, the kingdom of heaven is like a certain king who wanted to settle accounts with his servants.
B040C018V024	40	18	24	And when he had begun the settlement, one was brought to him, who owed him ten thousand talents.
B040C018V025	40	18	25	But because he had nothing with which to pay, his lord commanded him to be sold, and his wife, and children, and all that he had, and payment to be made.
B040C018V026	40	18	26	Therefore the servant fell down, and implored him, saying, Lord, have patience with me, and I will pay you all.
B040C018V027	40	18	27	Then the lord of that servant was moved with compassion, and released him, and forgave him the debt.
B040C018V028	40	18	28	But the same servant went out, and found one of his fellow servants, who owed him a hundred denarii: and he laid hands on him, and took him by the throat, saying, Pay me what you owe.
B040C018V029	40	18	29	And his fellow servant fell down at his feet, and begged him, saying, Have patience with me, and I will pay you all.
B040C018V030	40	18	30	He refused however, but went and cast him into prison, until he should pay the debt.
B040C018V031	40	18	31	So when his fellow servants saw what had happened, they were very sorry, and came and told their lord all that had happened.
B040C018V032	40	18	32	Then his lord, after he had called him, said to him, You wicked servant, I forgave you all that debt, because you begged me:
B040C018V033	40	18	33	Should you not also have had compassion on your fellow servant, even as I had pity on you?
B040C018V034	40	18	34	And his lord was angry, and delivered him to the torturers, until he should pay all that was due him.
B040C018V035	40	18	35	So shall my heavenly Father also do to each one of you, if you do not forgive your brother from your heart.
B040C019V001	40	19	1	And it came to pass, that when Jesus had finished these sayings, he departed from Galilee, and came into the region of Judaea beyond the Jordan;
B040C019V002	40	19	2	And great multitudes followed him; and he healed them there.
B040C019V003	40	19	3	The Pharisees also came to him, tempting him, and saying to him, Is it lawful for a man to divorce his wife for any cause?
B040C019V004	40	19	4	And he answered and said to them, Have you not read, that he who made them at the beginning made them male and female,
B040C019V005	40	19	5	And said, For this reason shall a man leave father and mother, and shall cling to his wife: and the two shall be one flesh?
B040C019V006	40	19	6	Therefore they are no longer two, but one flesh. Therefore, what God has joined together, let man not separate.
B040C019V007	40	19	7	They said to him, Why then did Moses command to give a certificate of divorce, and to put her away?
B040C019V008	40	19	8	He said to them, Because of the hardness of your hearts Moses allowed you to put away your wives: but from the beginning it was not so.
B040C019V009	40	19	9	And I say to you, Whoever shall divorce his wife, except for unchastity, and shall marry another, commits adultery.
B040C019V010	40	19	10	His disciples said to him, If this is the case of a man with his wife, it is good not to marry.
B040C019V011	40	19	11	But he said to them, Not all men can receive this saying, only those to whom it is given.
B040C019V012	40	19	12	For there are some eunuchs, who were born so, from their mothers' wombs: and there are some eunuchs, who were made eunuchs by men: and there are eunuchs, who have made themselves eunuchs for sake of the kingdom of heaven. He who is able to receive it, let him receive it.
B040C019V013	40	19	13	Then little children were brought to him, that he should put his hands on them, and pray: but the disciples rebuked them.
B040C019V014	40	19	14	But Jesus said, Let the little children come to me, and do not forbid them: for to such as these belongs the kingdom of heaven.
B040C019V015	40	19	15	And he laid his hands on them, and departed from there.
B040C019V016	40	19	16	And, behold, one came and said to him, Teacher, what good thing shall I do, that I may have eternal life?
B040C019V017	40	19	17	And he said to him, Why do you ask me what is good? there is no one good but One: but if you wish to enter into life, keep the commandments.
B040C019V018	40	19	18	He said to him, Which ones? Jesus said, You shall not murder, You shall not commit adultery, You shall not steal, You shall not bear false witness,
B040C019V019	40	19	19	Honour your father and your mother: and, You shall love your neighbour as yourself.
B040C019V020	40	19	20	The young man said to him, All these things I have kept from my youth up: what do I still lack?
B040C019V021	40	19	21	Jesus said to him, If you wish to be perfect, go and sell what you have, and give to the poor, and you shall have treasure in heaven: and come and follow me.
B040C019V022	40	19	22	But when the young man heard that, he went away sorrowful: for he had much property.
B040C019V023	40	19	23	Then Jesus said to his disciples, Truly I say to you, It is hard for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of heaven.
B040C019V024	40	19	24	And again I say to you, It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle, than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.
B040C019V025	40	19	25	When his disciples heard this, they were exceedingly amazed, saying, Who then can be saved?
B040C019V026	40	19	26	But Jesus looked at them, and said to them, With men this is impossible; but with God all things are possible.
B040C019V027	40	19	27	Then Peter answered and said to him, Behold, we have forsaken all, and followed you; what then shall we have?
B040C019V028	40	19	28	And Jesus said to them, Truly I say to you, At the renewal of all things, when the Son of man shall sit upon the throne of his glory, you who have followed me shall sit upon twelve thrones, judging the twelve tribes of Israel.
B040C019V029	40	19	29	And every one who has forsaken houses, or brothers, or sisters, or father, or mother, or children, or lands, for my name's sake, shall receive a hundredfold, and shall inherit eternal life.
B040C019V030	40	19	30	But many who are first shall be last; and the last shall be first.
B040C020V001	40	20	1	For the kingdom of heaven is like a landowner, who went out early in the morning to hire labourers to work in his vineyard.
B040C020V002	40	20	2	And when he had agreed with the labourers for a denarius a day, he sent them into his vineyard.
B040C020V003	40	20	3	And he went out about the third hour, and saw others standing idle in the marketplace,
B040C020V004	40	20	4	And said to them; Go also into the vineyard, and whatever is right I will give you. And they went.
B040C020V005	40	20	5	Again he went out about the sixth and ninth hour, and did likewise.
B040C020V006	40	20	6	And about the eleventh hour he went out, and found others standing, and said to them, Why are you standing here idle all the day?
B040C020V007	40	20	7	They said to him, Because no man has hired us. He said to them, Go also into the vineyard.
B040C020V008	40	20	8	So when evening had come, the lord of the vineyard said to his steward, Call the labourers, and give them their wages, beginning with the last to the first.
B040C020V009	40	20	9	And when those who were hired about the eleventh hour came, every man received a denarius.
B040C020V010	40	20	10	But when the first came, they supposed that they would receive more; but each of them likewise received a denarius.
B040C020V011	40	20	11	And when they had received it, they grumbled against the landowner,
B040C020V012	40	20	12	Saying, These last have worked but one hour, and you have made them equal to us, who have borne the burden and heat of the day.
B040C020V013	40	20	13	But he answered one of them, and said, Friend, I do you no wrong: did you not agree with me for a denarius?
B040C020V014	40	20	14	Take what is yours, and go your way: I wish to give to this last man, just as to you.
B040C020V015	40	20	15	Is it not lawful for me to do what I wish with what is my own? Is your eye envious, because I am good?
B040C020V016	40	20	16	So the last shall be first, and the first last.
B040C020V017	40	20	17	And Jesus, going up to Jerusalem, took the twelve disciples aside, and on the way said to them,
B040C020V018	40	20	18	Behold, we go up to Jerusalem; and the Son of man shall be betrayed to the chief priests and to the scribes, and they shall condemn him to death,
B040C020V019	40	20	19	And shall deliver him to the Gentiles to mock, and to scourge, and to crucify him: and on the third day he shall be raised up.
B040C020V020	40	20	20	Then the mother of the sons of Zebedee came to him with her sons, bowing before him, and asked a certain thing of him.
B040C020V021	40	20	21	And he said to her, What do you wish? She said to him, Grant that these two sons of mine may sit, the one on your right hand, and the other on the left, in your kingdom.
B040C020V022	40	20	22	But Jesus answered and said, You do not know what you ask. Are you able to drink of the cup that I shall drink? They said to him, We are able.
B040C020V023	40	20	23	And he said to them, You shall indeed drink of my cup: but to sit on my right hand, and on my left, is not mine to give, but it shall be given to those for whom it has been prepared by my Father.
B040C020V024	40	20	24	And when the ten heard this, they were moved with indignation against the two brothers.
B040C020V025	40	20	25	But Jesus called them to him, and said, You know that the princes of the Gentiles exercise dominion over them, and those who are great exercise authority over them.
B040C020V026	40	20	26	But it shall not be so among you: but whoever will be great among you, let him be your servant;
B040C020V027	40	20	27	And whoever will be chief among you, let him be your slave:
B040C020V028	40	20	28	Even as the Son of man did not come to be served, but to serve, and to give his life a ransom for many.
B040C020V029	40	20	29	And as they departed from Jericho, a great multitude followed him.
B040C020V030	40	20	30	And, behold, two blind men sitting by the wayside, when they heard that Jesus passed by, cried out, saying, Have mercy on us, O Lord, Son of David.
B040C020V031	40	20	31	And the multitude rebuked them, telling them to be quiet: but they cried out all the more, saying, Have mercy on us, O Lord, Son of David.
B040C020V032	40	20	32	And Jesus stood still, and called them, and said, What do you want that I should do for you?
B040C020V033	40	20	33	They said to him, Lord, we want our eyes to be opened.
B040C020V034	40	20	34	So Jesus had compassion on them, and touched their eyes: and immediately they received their sight, and they followed him.
B040C021V001	40	21	1	And when they drew near to Jerusalem, and came to Bethphage, to the mount of Olives, then Jesus sent two disciples,
B040C021V002	40	21	2	Saying to them, Go into the village opposite you, and immediately you shall find a donkey tied, and a colt with her: loose them, and bring them to me.
B040C021V003	40	21	3	And if any man says anything to you, you shall say, The Lord has need of them; and immediately he will send them.
B040C021V004	40	21	4	All this was done, that what was spoken by the prophet might be fulfilled,
B040C021V005	40	21	5	Tell the daughter of Zion, Behold, your King comes to you, meek, and sitting upon a donkey, on a colt, the foal of a donkey.
B040C021V006	40	21	6	And the disciples went, and did as Jesus commanded them,
B040C021V007	40	21	7	And brought the donkey, and the colt, and placed on them their garments, and he sat upon them.
B040C021V008	40	21	8	And a very great multitude spread their garments along the way; others cut down branches from the trees, and spread them on the way.
B040C021V009	40	21	9	And the multitudes that went before, and that followed after, cried out, saying, Hosanna to the Son of David: Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord; Hosanna in the highest.
B040C021V010	40	21	10	And when he came into Jerusalem, all the city was stirred, saying, Who is this?
B040C021V011	40	21	11	And the multitudes said, This is Jesus, the prophet of Nazareth of Galilee.
B040C021V012	40	21	12	And Jesus went into the temple of God, and cast out all those who bought and sold in the temple, and overthrew the tables of the money changers, and the seats of those who sold doves,
B040C021V013	40	21	13	And said to them, It is written, My house shall be called a house of prayer; but you have made it a den of robbers.
B040C021V014	40	21	14	And the blind and the lame came to him in the temple; and he healed them.
B040C021V015	40	21	15	And when the chief priests and scribes saw the wonderful things that he did, and the children crying out in the temple, saying, Hosanna to the Son of David; they were very displeased,
B040C021V016	40	21	16	And said to him, Do you hear what these say? And Jesus said to them, Yes; have you never read, Out of the mouths of children and nursing infants you have brought perfect praise?
B040C021V017	40	21	17	And he left them, and went out of the city to Bethany; and he lodged there.
B040C021V018	40	21	18	Now in the morning, as he returned to the city, he was hungry.
B040C021V019	40	21	19	And when he saw a fig tree by the way, he came to it, and found nothing on it but leaves, and he said to it, Let no fruit grow on you ever again. And at once the fig tree withered away.
B040C021V020	40	21	20	And when the disciples saw it, they marvelled, saying, How did the fig tree so quickly wither away?
B040C021V021	40	21	21	Jesus answered and said to them, Truly I say to you, If you have faith, and do not doubt, you shall not only do what was done to the fig tree, but also if you shall say to this mountain, Be removed, and be cast into the sea; it shall be done.
B040C021V022	40	21	22	And all things, whatever you shall ask in prayer, believing, you shall receive.
B040C021V023	40	21	23	And when he had come into the temple, the chief priests and the elders of the people came to him as he was teaching, and said, By what authority are you doing these things? and who gave you this authority?
B040C021V024	40	21	24	And Jesus answered and said to them, I also will ask you one thing, and if you answer me, I will tell you by what authority I do these things.
B040C021V025	40	21	25	The baptism of John, where was it from? from heaven, or from men? And they reasoned among themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven; he will say to us, Why then did you not believe him?
B040C021V026	40	21	26	But if we shall say, From men; we fear the people; for all hold that John was a prophet.
B040C021V027	40	21	27	And they answered Jesus, and said, We do not know. And he said to them, Neither will I tell you by what authority I do these things.
B040C021V028	40	21	28	But what do you think? A certain man had two sons; and he came to the first, and said, Son, go work today in the vineyard.
B040C021V029	40	21	29	He answered and said, I will not: but afterward he repented, and went.
B040C021V030	40	21	30	And he came to the second, and said the same. And he answered and said, I will, sir: but did not go.
B040C021V031	40	21	31	Which of the two did the will of his father? They said to him, The first. Jesus said to them, Truly I say to you, That the tax gatherers and the prostitutes go into the kingdom of God before you.
B040C021V032	40	21	32	For John came to you in the way of righteousness, and you did not believe him: but the tax gatherers and the prostitutes believed him: and even when you had seen this, you did not afterward repent and believe him.
B040C021V033	40	21	33	Hear another parable: There was a certain landowner, who planted a vineyard, and put a hedge around it, and dug a winepress in it, and built a tower, and let it out to farmers, and went to a far country:
B040C021V034	40	21	34	And when the time of the fruit drew near, he sent his servants to the tenants, that they might collect his fruit.
B040C021V035	40	21	35	And the tenants took his servants, and beat one, and killed another, and stoned another.
B040C021V036	40	21	36	Again, he sent other servants, more than the first: and they did the same to them.
B040C021V037	40	21	37	But last of all he sent to them his son, saying, They will respect my son.
B040C021V038	40	21	38	But when the tenants saw the son, they said among themselves, This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and let us seize his inheritance.
B040C021V039	40	21	39	And they took him, and cast him out of the vineyard, and killed him.
B040C021V040	40	21	40	Therefore, when the owner of the vineyard comes, what will he do to those tenants?
B040C021V041	40	21	41	They said to him, He will miserably destroy those wicked men, and will let out his vineyard to other tenants, who shall give him the fruits in their seasons.
B040C021V042	40	21	42	Jesus said to them, Did you never read in the scriptures, The stone which the builders rejected, the same has become the cornerstone: this is the Lord's doing, and it is marvellous in our eyes?
B040C021V043	40	21	43	Therefore I say to you, The kingdom of God shall be taken from you, and given to a nation which will bring forth its fruit.
B040C021V044	40	21	44	And whoever shall fall on this stone shall be broken: but on whomever it shall fall, it will grind him to powder.
B040C021V045	40	21	45	And when the chief priests and Pharisees heard his parables, they perceived that he spoke of them.
B040C021V046	40	21	46	They sought to lay hands on him, but they feared the multitude, because they held him to be a prophet.
B040C022V001	40	22	1	And Jesus answered and spoke to them again in parables, and said,
B040C022V002	40	22	2	The kingdom of heaven is like a certain king, who gave a marriage feast for his son,
B040C022V003	40	22	3	And sent forth his servants to call those who were invited to the marriage feast: but they would not come.
B040C022V004	40	22	4	Again, he sent forth other servants, saying, Tell those who are invited, Behold, I have prepared my dinner: my oxen and my fat calves have been killed, and all things are ready: come to the marriage feast.
B040C022V005	40	22	5	But they made light of it, and went their ways, one to his farm, another to his business:
B040C022V006	40	22	6	And the rest took his servants, and treated them spitefully, and killed them.
B040C022V007	40	22	7	The king was angry, and he sent forth his armies, and destroyed those murderers, and burned their city.
B040C022V008	40	22	8	Then he said to his servants, The wedding is ready, but those who were invited were not worthy.
B040C022V009	40	22	9	Therefore, go into the highways, and as many as you shall find, invite to the marriage feast.
B040C022V010	40	22	10	So those servants went out into the highways, and gathered together as many as they found, both bad and good: and the wedding hall was filled with guests.
B040C022V011	40	22	11	And when the king came in to see the guests, he saw there a man who had no wedding garment:
B040C022V012	40	22	12	And he said to him, Friend, how did you come in here not having a wedding garment? And he was speechless.
B040C022V013	40	22	13	Then the king said to the servants, Bind him hand and foot, and take him away, and cast him into outer darkness; where there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C022V014	40	22	14	For many are called, but few are chosen.
B040C022V015	40	22	15	Then the Pharisees went, and took counsel how they might entangle him in his talk.
B040C022V016	40	22	16	And they sent out to him their disciples with the Herodians, saying, Teacher, we know that you are truthful, and teach the way of God in truth, nor do you defer to any man: for you do not regard the position of men.
B040C022V017	40	22	17	Therefore tell us, What do you think? Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?
B040C022V018	40	22	18	But Jesus perceived their wickedness, and said, Why do you test me, you hypocrites?
B040C022V019	40	22	19	Show me the money used for the tax. And they brought to him a denarius.
B040C022V020	40	22	20	And he said to them, Whose image and inscription is this?
B040C022V021	40	22	21	They said to him, Caesar's. Then he said to them, Then render to Caesar the things which are Caesar's; and to God the things that are God's.
B040C022V022	40	22	22	When they had heard these words, they marvelled, and left him, and went their way.
B040C022V023	40	22	23	The same day the Sadducees, who say that there is no resurrection, came to him and asked him,
B040C022V024	40	22	24	Teacher, Moses said, If a man dies, having no children, his brother shall marry his wife, and raise up children for his brother.
B040C022V025	40	22	25	Now there were among us seven brothers: and the first, after he had married, died, and, having no children, left his wife to his brother:
B040C022V026	40	22	26	The same happened to the second, and the third, down to the seventh.
B040C022V027	40	22	27	And last of all the woman died.
B040C022V028	40	22	28	Therefore, at the resurrection, whose wife shall she be of the seven? for they all had her.
B040C022V029	40	22	29	Jesus answered them, You err, not knowing the scriptures, nor the power of God.
B040C022V030	40	22	30	For in the resurrection they neither marry, nor are given in marriage, but are like the angels in heaven.
B040C022V031	40	22	31	And as for the resurrection of the dead, have you not read that which was spoken to you by God,
B040C022V032	40	22	32	I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob? God is not the God of the dead, but of the living.
B040C022V033	40	22	33	And when the multitudes heard this, they were astonished at his teaching.
B040C022V034	40	22	34	But when the Pharisees heard that he had silenced the Sadducees, they gathered together.
B040C022V035	40	22	35	Then one of them, who was a lawyer, asked him a question to test him, saying,
B040C022V036	40	22	36	Teacher, which is the great commandment in the law?
B040C022V037	40	22	37	Jesus said to him, You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your mind.
B040C022V038	40	22	38	This is the first and greatest commandment.
B040C022V039	40	22	39	And the second is like it, You shall love your neighbour as yourself.
B040C022V040	40	22	40	On these two commandments hang all the law and the prophets.
B040C022V041	40	22	41	While the Pharisees were gathered together, Jesus asked them,
B040C022V042	40	22	42	What do you think of the Christ? whose son is he? They said to him, The Son of David.
B040C022V043	40	22	43	He said to them, How then does David in the spirit call him Lord, saying,
B040C022V044	40	22	44	The LORD said to my Lord, Sit on my right hand, until I put your enemies under your feet?
B040C022V045	40	22	45	If then David calls him Lord, how is he his son?
B040C022V046	40	22	46	And no man was able to answer him a word, nor did any man dare from that day forth to ask him any more questions.
B040C023V001	40	23	1	Then Jesus spoke to the multitude, and to his disciples,
B040C023V002	40	23	2	Saying, The scribes and the Pharisees sit in Moses' seat:
B040C023V003	40	23	3	Therefore, all they bid you to observe, that observe and do; but do not imitate their works: for they say, but do not do.
B040C023V004	40	23	4	For they bind heavy burdens, hard to bear, and lay them upon men's shoulders; but they themselves will not move them with one of their fingers.
B040C023V005	40	23	5	But all their works they do to be seen by men: they make broad their phylacteries, and enlarge the borders of their garments,
B040C023V006	40	23	6	And love the uppermost rooms at feasts, and the chief seats in the synagogues,
B040C023V007	40	23	7	And greetings in the markets, and to be called by men, Rabbi.
B040C023V008	40	23	8	But do not be called Rabbi: for one is your Teacher; and all of you are brethren.
B040C023V009	40	23	9	And call no man upon the earth your father: for one is your Father, who is in heaven.
B040C023V010	40	23	10	Neither be called masters: for one is your Master, even Christ.
B040C023V011	40	23	11	But he who is greatest among you shall be your servant.
B040C023V012	40	23	12	And whoever shall exalt himself shall be humbled; and he who shall humble himself shall be exalted.
B040C023V013	40	23	13	But woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for you shut up the kingdom of heaven against men: for you do not go in yourselves, nor do you allow those who are entering to go in.
B040C023V014	40	23	14	[Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for you devour widows' houses, and for a pretence make long prayers: therefore you shall receive the greater condemnation.]
B040C023V015	40	23	15	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for you cross sea and land to make one proselyte, and when he is made, you make him twice as much a son of hell as yourselves.
B040C023V016	40	23	16	Woe to you, blind guides, who say, Whoever shall swear by the temple, it is nothing; but whoever shall swear by the gold of the temple, he is a debtor!
B040C023V017	40	23	17	You blind fools: which is greater, the gold, or the temple that sanctifies the gold?
B040C023V018	40	23	18	And, Whoever shall swear by the altar, it is nothing; but whoever swears by the gift that is upon it, he is obligated.
B040C023V019	40	23	19	You blind fools: which is greater, the gift, or the altar that sanctifies the gift?
B040C023V020	40	23	20	Therefore, whoever shall swear by the altar, swears by it, and by all things on it.
B040C023V021	40	23	21	And whoever shall swear by the temple, swears by it, and by him who dwells in it.
B040C023V022	40	23	22	And he who swears by heaven, swears by the throne of God, and by him who sits on it.
B040C023V023	40	23	23	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for you tithe mint and dill and cummin, and have omitted the weightier matters of the law, justice, mercy, and faithfulness: these you ought to have done, without leaving the others undone.
B040C023V024	40	23	24	You blind guides, who strain out a gnat, and swallow a camel.
B040C023V025	40	23	25	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for you clean the outside of the cup and of the platter, but within they are full of extortion and self-indulgence.
B040C023V026	40	23	26	You blind Pharisee, cleanse first that which is within the cup and platter, that the outside of them may be clean also.
B040C023V027	40	23	27	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for you are like whitewashed tombs, which indeed appear beautiful outwardly, but within are full of dead men's bones, and of all uncleanness.
B040C023V028	40	23	28	Even so you also outwardly appear righteous to men, but within you are full of hypocrisy and iniquity.
B040C023V029	40	23	29	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! because you build the tombs of the prophets, and adorn the sepulchres of the righteous,
B040C023V030	40	23	30	And say, If we had lived in the days of our fathers, we would not have been partakers with them in the blood of the prophets.
B040C023V031	40	23	31	Therefore you are witnesses against yourselves, that you are the sons of those who killed the prophets.
B040C023V032	40	23	32	Fill up, then, the measure of the sins of your fathers.
B040C023V033	40	23	33	You serpents, you generation of vipers, how can you escape being condemned to hell?
B040C023V034	40	23	34	Therefore, behold, I send to you prophets, and wise men, and scribes: and some of them you shall kill and crucify; and some of them you shall scourge in your synagogues, and persecute from city to city:
B040C023V035	40	23	35	That upon you may come all the righteous blood shed upon the earth, from the blood of righteous Abel to the blood of Zechariah, son of Berachiah, whom you killed between the temple and the altar.
B040C023V036	40	23	36	Truly I say to you, All these things shall come upon this generation.
B040C023V037	40	23	37	O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, you who kill the prophets, and stone those who are sent to you, how often would I have gathered your children together, even as a hen gathers her chicks under her wings, and you would not let me!
B040C023V038	40	23	38	Behold, your house is left to you desolate.
B040C023V039	40	23	39	For I say to you, You shall not see me again, until you shall say, Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord.
B040C024V001	40	24	1	And Jesus went out, and departed from the temple: and his disciples came to him to show him the buildings of the temple.
B040C024V002	40	24	2	And Jesus said to them, Do you not see all these things? truly I say to you, There shall not be left here one stone upon another, that shall not be thrown down.
B040C024V003	40	24	3	And as he sat upon the mount of Olives, the disciples came to him privately, saying, Tell us when these things shall be? and what shall be the sign of your coming, and of the end of the age?
B040C024V004	40	24	4	And Jesus answered them, Take heed that no man deceive you.
B040C024V005	40	24	5	For many shall come in my name, saying, I am the Christ; and shall deceive many.
B040C024V006	40	24	6	And you shall hear of wars and rumours of wars: see that you are not troubled: for all these things must come to pass, but the end is not yet.
B040C024V007	40	24	7	For nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom: and there shall be famines, and earthquakes, in various places.
B040C024V008	40	24	8	All these are the beginning of birth pains.
B040C024V009	40	24	9	Then they shall deliver you up to be afflicted, and shall kill you: and you shall be hated by all nations for my name's sake.
B040C024V010	40	24	10	And then shall many fall away, and shall betray one another, and shall hate one another.
B040C024V011	40	24	11	And many false prophets shall rise, and shall deceive many.
B040C024V012	40	24	12	And because iniquity shall abound, the love of many shall grow cold.
B040C024V013	40	24	13	But he who endures to the end shall be saved.
B040C024V014	40	24	14	And this gospel of the kingdom shall be preached in all the world as a testimony to all nations; and then the end shall come.
B040C024V015	40	24	15	Therefore, when you shall see the abomination of desolation, spoken of by Daniel the prophet, standing in the holy place, (whoever reads, let him understand:)
B040C024V016	40	24	16	Then let those who are in Judaea flee into the mountains:
B040C024V017	40	24	17	Let him who is on the housetop not come down to take anything out of his house:
B040C024V018	40	24	18	Neither let him who is in the field turn back to take his cloak.
B040C024V019	40	24	19	And woe to those who are with child, and to those who nurse in those days!
B040C024V020	40	24	20	Pray that your flight may not be in the winter or on the sabbath day:
B040C024V021	40	24	21	For then there shall be great tribulation, such as has not occurred since the beginning of the world to this time, no, nor ever shall be.
B040C024V022	40	24	22	And unless those days had been cut short, no flesh would be saved: but for the sake of the elect those days shall be cut short.
B040C024V023	40	24	23	Then if any man shall say to you, Lo, here is the Christ, or there; do not believe it.
B040C024V024	40	24	24	For false Christs shall arise, and false prophets, and shall show great signs and wonders; so as to deceive, if it were possible, even the very elect.
B040C024V025	40	24	25	Behold, I have told you beforehand.
B040C024V026	40	24	26	Therefore if they shall say to you, Behold, he is in the desert; do not go forth: behold, he is in the inner rooms; do not believe it.
B040C024V027	40	24	27	For as the lightning comes out of the east, and shines even to the west; so shall also the coming of the Son of man be.
B040C024V028	40	24	28	For wherever the body is, there will the vultures be gathered together.
B040C024V029	40	24	29	Immediately after the tribulation of those days, the sun shall be darkened, and the moon shall not give its light, and the stars shall fall from heaven, and the powers of the heavens shall be shaken:
B040C024V030	40	24	30	And then the sign of the Son of man shall appear in heaven: and then shall all the tribes of the earth mourn, and they shall see the Son of man coming in the clouds of heaven with power and great glory.
B040C024V031	40	24	31	And he shall send out his angels with a great call of a trumpet, and they shall gather together his elect from the four winds, from one end of the heavens to the other.
B040C024V032	40	24	32	Now learn this parable from the fig tree; When its branch becomes tender, and puts forth leaves, you know that summer is near:
B040C024V033	40	24	33	So likewise, when you shall see all these things, know that it is near, even at the doors.
B040C024V034	40	24	34	Truly I say to you, This generation shall not pass away, until all these things are fulfilled.
B040C024V035	40	24	35	Heaven and earth shall pass away, but my words shall not pass away.
B040C024V036	40	24	36	But of that day and hour no man knows, no, not the angels of heaven, nor the Son, but my Father only.
B040C024V037	40	24	37	But as the days of Noah were, so shall also the coming of the Son of man be.
B040C024V038	40	24	38	For as in the days that were before the flood, they were eating and drinking, marrying and giving in marriage, until the day that Noah entered into the ark,
B040C024V039	40	24	39	And they did not know until the flood came and took them all away; so shall the coming of the Son of man be.
B040C024V040	40	24	40	Then shall two be in the field; one shall be taken, and the other left.
B040C024V041	40	24	41	Two women shall be grinding at the mill; one shall be taken, and the other left.
B040C024V042	40	24	42	Therefore watch: for you do not know on what day your Lord will come.
B040C024V043	40	24	43	But know this, that if the owner of the house had known at what time the thief would come, he would have watched, and would not have allowed his house to be broken into.
B040C024V044	40	24	44	Therefore you must also be ready: for the Son of man will come at an hour you do not expect.
B040C024V045	40	24	45	Who then is a faithful and wise servant, whom his lord has made ruler over his household, to give them food in due season?
B040C024V046	40	24	46	Blessed is that servant, whom his lord shall find so doing when he comes.
B040C024V047	40	24	47	Truly I say to you, That he shall put him in charge of all his goods.
B040C024V048	40	24	48	But if that evil servant shall say in his heart, My lord delays his coming;
B040C024V049	40	24	49	And shall begin to strike his fellow servants, and to eat and drink with the drunken;
B040C024V050	40	24	50	The lord of that servant shall come on a day when he does not expect him, and at a hour that he is not aware of,
B040C024V051	40	24	51	And shall cut him apart, and assign him a place with the hypocrites: where there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C025V001	40	25	1	Then shall the kingdom of heaven be likened to ten virgins, who took their lamps, and went forth to meet the bridegroom.
B040C025V002	40	25	2	And five of them were foolish, and five were wise.
B040C025V003	40	25	3	Those who were foolish took their lamps, but took no oil with them:
B040C025V004	40	25	4	But the wise took oil in their flasks with their lamps.
B040C025V005	40	25	5	While the bridegroom tarried, they all became drowsy and slept.
B040C025V006	40	25	6	And at midnight there was a cry, Behold, the bridegroom comes; go out to meet him.
B040C025V007	40	25	7	Then all those virgins arose, and trimmed their lamps.
B040C025V008	40	25	8	And the foolish said to the wise, Give us some of your oil; for our lamps are going out.
B040C025V009	40	25	9	But the wise answered, saying, No; lest there not be enough for us and you: but rather go to those who sell, and buy for yourselves.
B040C025V010	40	25	10	And while they went to buy, the bridegroom came; and those who were ready went in with him to the marriage feast: and the door was shut.
B040C025V011	40	25	11	Afterward the other virgins also came, saying, Lord, Lord, open to us.
B040C025V012	40	25	12	But he answered and said, Truly I say to you, I do not know you.
B040C025V013	40	25	13	Watch therefore, for you know neither the day nor the hour.
B040C025V014	40	25	14	For it is like a man travelling to a far country, who called his servants, and delivered to them his goods.
B040C025V015	40	25	15	To one he gave five talents, to another two, and to another one; to every man according to his ability; and he went on his journey.
B040C025V016	40	25	16	Then he who had received the five talents went at once and traded with them, and gained another five talents.
B040C025V017	40	25	17	And likewise, he who had received two, gained two more.
B040C025V018	40	25	18	But he who had received one went and dug in the earth, and hid his lord's money.
B040C025V019	40	25	19	After a long time the lord of those servants came, and settled accounts with them.
B040C025V020	40	25	20	And so he who had received five talents came and brought the other five talents, saying, Lord, you delivered to me five talents: behold, I have gained beside them five talents more.
B040C025V021	40	25	21	His lord said to him, Well done, you good and faithful servant: you have been faithful over a few things, I will make you ruler over many things: enter into the joy of your lord.
B040C025V022	40	25	22	He also who had received two talents came and said, Lord, you delivered to me two talents: behold, I have gained two more talents.
B040C025V023	40	25	23	His lord said to him, Well done, good and faithful servant; you have been faithful over a few things, I will make you ruler over many things: enter into the joy of your lord.
B040C025V024	40	25	24	Then he who had received the one talent came and said, Lord, I knew that you are a hard man, reaping where you have not sown, and gathering where you have not scattered seed:
B040C025V025	40	25	25	And I was afraid, and went and hid your talent in the earth: lo, here you have what is yours.
B040C025V026	40	25	26	His lord answered and said to him, You wicked and slothful servant, you knew that I reap where I have not sown, and gather where I have not scattered seed:
B040C025V027	40	25	27	Then you ought to have put my money in the bank, and then at my coming I should have received it back with interest.
B040C025V028	40	25	28	Take the talent from him, and give it to him who has ten talents.
B040C025V029	40	25	29	For to every one who has shall more be given, and he shall have abundance: but from him who does not have, even that which he has shall be taken away.
B040C025V030	40	25	30	And cast the unprofitable servant into outer darkness: where there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth.
B040C025V031	40	25	31	When the Son of man shall come in his glory, and all the holy angels with him, then shall he sit upon the throne of his glory:
B040C025V032	40	25	32	And before him shall be gathered all nations: and he shall separate them one from another, as a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats:
B040C025V033	40	25	33	And he shall set the sheep on his right hand, and the goats on the left.
B040C025V034	40	25	34	Then shall the King say to those on his right hand, Come, you who are blessed by my Father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world:
B040C025V035	40	25	35	For I was hungry, and you gave me food: I was thirsty, and you gave me drink: I was a stranger, and you took me in:
B040C025V036	40	25	36	Naked, and you clothed me: I was sick, and you visited me: I was in prison, and you came to me.
B040C025V037	40	25	37	Then the righteous shall answer him, saying, Lord, when did we see you hungry, and feed you? or thirsty, and give you drink?
B040C025V038	40	25	38	When did we see you a stranger, and take you in? or naked, and clothe you?
B040C025V039	40	25	39	Or when did we see you sick, or in prison, and come to you?
B040C025V040	40	25	40	And the King shall answer and say to them, Truly I say to you, as you have done it to one of the least of these, my brethren, you have done it to me.
B040C025V041	40	25	41	Then he shall say to those on the left hand, Depart from me, you cursed, into eternal fire, prepared for the devil and his angels:
B040C025V042	40	25	42	For I was hungry, and you gave me no food: I was thirsty, and you gave me no drink:
B040C025V043	40	25	43	I was a stranger, and you did not take me in: naked, and you did not clothe me: sick, and in prison, and you did not visit me.
B040C025V044	40	25	44	Then they also shall answer him, saying, Lord, when did we see you hungry, or thirsty, or a stranger, or naked, or sick, or in prison, and did not minister to you?
B040C025V045	40	25	45	Then he shall answer them, saying, Truly I say to you, as you did not do it to one of the least of these, you did not do it to me.
B040C025V046	40	25	46	And these shall go away into eternal punishment: but the righteous into eternal life.
B040C026V001	40	26	1	And it came to pass, when Jesus had finished all these sayings, he said to his disciples,
B040C026V002	40	26	2	You know that after two days is the feast of the passover, and the Son of man will be delivered up to be crucified.
B040C026V003	40	26	3	Then the chief priests, the scribes, and the elders of the people assembled together at the palace of the high priest, who was called Caiaphas,
B040C026V004	40	26	4	And conspired to take Jesus by stealth, and kill him.
B040C026V005	40	26	5	But they said, Not on the feast day, lest there be an uproar among the people.
B040C026V006	40	26	6	Now when Jesus was in Bethany, in the house of Simon the leper,
B040C026V007	40	26	7	There came to him a woman having an alabaster box of very precious ointment, and poured it on his head as he reclined at table.
B040C026V008	40	26	8	But when his disciples saw it, they were indignant, saying, To what purpose is this waste?
B040C026V009	40	26	9	For this ointment might have been sold for much, and given to the poor.
B040C026V010	40	26	10	But Jesus, aware of this, said to them, Why do you trouble the woman? for she has done a good work for me.
B040C026V011	40	26	11	For you always have the poor with you; but you do not always have me.
B040C026V012	40	26	12	When she poured this ointment on my body, she did it for my burial.
B040C026V013	40	26	13	Truly I say to you, Wherever this gospel shall be preached in the whole world, what this woman has done shall also be told in memory of her.
B040C026V014	40	26	14	Then one of the twelve, named Judas Iscariot, went to the chief priests,
B040C026V015	40	26	15	And said to them, What will you give me if I deliver him to you? And they paid him thirty pieces of silver.
B040C026V016	40	26	16	And from that time on he sought an opportunity to betray him.
B040C026V017	40	26	17	Now on the first day of the feast of unleavened bread the disciples came to Jesus, saying, Where will you have us prepare for you to eat the passover?
B040C026V018	40	26	18	And he said, Go into the city to a certain man, and say to him, The Teacher says, My time is at hand; I will keep the passover at your house with my disciples.
B040C026V019	40	26	19	And the disciples did as Jesus had directed them; and they made ready the passover.
B040C026V020	40	26	20	Now when the evening had come, he sat down with the twelve.
B040C026V021	40	26	21	And as they ate, he said, Truly I say to you, that one of you shall betray me.
B040C026V022	40	26	22	And they were exceedingly sorrowful, and every one of them began to say to him, Lord, is it I?
B040C026V023	40	26	23	And he answered and said, He who dipped his hand with me in the dish shall betray me.
B040C026V024	40	26	24	The Son of man goes as it is written of him: but woe to that man by whom the Son of man is betrayed! it would have been better for that man if he had not been born.
B040C026V025	40	26	25	Then Judas, who betrayed him, answered and said, Teacher, is it I? He said to him, You have said it.
B040C026V026	40	26	26	And as they were eating, Jesus took bread, and blessed it, and broke it, and gave it to the disciples, and said, Take, eat; this is my body.
B040C026V027	40	26	27	And he took the cup, and gave thanks, and gave it to them, saying, Drink of it, all of you;
B040C026V028	40	26	28	For this is my blood of the covenant, which is shed for many for the forgiveness of sins.
B040C026V029	40	26	29	But I say to you, I will not drink again of this fruit of the vine, until that day when I drink it anew with you in my Father's kingdom.
B040C026V030	40	26	30	And when they had sung a hymn, they went out to the mount of Olives.
B040C026V031	40	26	31	Then Jesus said to them, This night all of you shall fall away because of me: for it is written, I will strike the shepherd, and the sheep of the flock shall be scattered.
B040C026V032	40	26	32	But after I have risen, I will go before you into Galilee.
B040C026V033	40	26	33	Peter answered and said to him, Though all fall away because of you, yet I will never fall away.
B040C026V034	40	26	34	Jesus said to him, Truly I say to you, That this night, before the cock crows, you shall deny me thrice.
B040C026V035	40	26	35	Peter said to him, Though I die with you, yet I will not deny you. And all the disciples said the same.
B040C026V036	40	26	36	Then Jesus came with them to a place called Gethsemane, and said to the disciples, Sit here, while I go and pray over there.
B040C026V037	40	26	37	And he took with him Peter and the two sons of Zebedee, and began to be sorrowful and very troubled.
B040C026V038	40	26	38	Then he said to them, My soul is exceedingly sorrowful, even to death: remain here, and watch with me.
B040C026V039	40	26	39	And he went a little further, and fell on his face, and prayed, saying, O my Father, if it is possible, let this cup pass from me: nevertheless, not as I will, but as you will.
B040C026V040	40	26	40	And he came to the disciples, and found them asleep, and said to Peter, What, could you not watch with me one hour?
B040C026V041	40	26	41	Watch and pray, that you do not enter into temptation: the spirit is willing, but the flesh is weak.
B040C026V042	40	26	42	He went away again, a second time, and prayed, saying, O my Father, if this may not pass away from me, except I drink it, your will be done.
B040C026V043	40	26	43	And he came and found them asleep again: for their eyes were heavy.
B040C026V044	40	26	44	And he left them, and went away again, and prayed the third time, saying the same words.
B040C026V045	40	26	45	Then he came to his disciples, and said to them, Sleep on now, and take your rest: behold, the hour is at hand, and the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.
B040C026V046	40	26	46	Rise, let us be going: behold, he who betrays me is at hand.
B040C026V047	40	26	47	And while he yet spoke, lo, Judas, one of the twelve, came, and with him a great multitude with swords and clubs, from the chief priests and elders of the people.
B040C026V048	40	26	48	Now he who betrayed him gave them a sign, saying, Whomever I shall kiss, he is the one: hold him fast.
B040C026V049	40	26	49	And forthwith he came to Jesus, and said, Hail, Rabbi; and kissed him.
B040C026V050	40	26	50	And Jesus said to him, Friend, do that which you have come for. Then they came, and laid hands on Jesus, and took him.
B040C026V051	40	26	51	And, behold, one of those with Jesus stretched out his hand, and drew his sword, and struck a servant of the high priest, and cut off his ear.
B040C026V052	40	26	52	Then Jesus said to him, Put your sword back in its place: for all those who take up the sword shall perish by the sword.
B040C026V053	40	26	53	Do you think that I cannot now pray to my Father, and he shall at once give me more than twelve legions of angels?
B040C026V054	40	26	54	But how then shall the scriptures be fulfilled, that say it must happen this way?
B040C026V055	40	26	55	In that same hour Jesus said to the multitudes, Do you come out to take me with swords and clubs, as if I was a thief ? I sat daily with you teaching in the temple, and you did not lay hold on me.
B040C026V056	40	26	56	But all this was done, that the scriptures of the prophets might be fulfilled. Then all the disciples forsook him, and fled.
B040C026V057	40	26	57	And those who had laid hold on Jesus led him away to Caiaphas the high priest, where the scribes and the elders were assembled.
B040C026V058	40	26	58	But Peter followed him from afar to the high priest's courtyard, and went in, and sat with the guards, to see the outcome.
B040C026V059	40	26	59	Now the chief priests, and elders, and all the council, sought false witness against Jesus, to put him to death;
B040C026V060	40	26	60	But found none, though many false witnesses came forth. At last two false witnesses came,
B040C026V061	40	26	61	And said, This fellow said, I am able to destroy the temple of God, and to build it in three days.
B040C026V062	40	26	62	And the high priest arose, and said to him, Do you have no answer? what is it which these men testify against you?
B040C026V063	40	26	63	But Jesus held his peace. And the high priest answered and said to him, I charge you by the living God, that you tell us whether you are the Christ, the Son of God.
B040C026V064	40	26	64	Jesus said to him, You have said so: nevertheless I say to you, Hereafter you shall see the Son of man sitting on the right hand of power, and coming in the clouds of heaven.
B040C026V065	40	26	65	Then the high priest rent his clothes, saying, He has spoken blasphemy; what further need have we of witnesses? behold, now you have heard his blasphemy.
B040C026V066	40	26	66	What do you think? They answered and said, He is worthy of death.
B040C026V067	40	26	67	Then they spit in his face, and beat him; and others struck him with the palms of their hands,
B040C026V068	40	26	68	Saying, Prophesy to us, you Christ, Who is it who struck you?
B040C026V069	40	26	69	Now Peter sat outside in the courtyard: and a maid came to him, saying, You also were with Jesus of Galilee.
B040C026V070	40	26	70	But he denied it before them all, saying, I know not what your are saying.
B040C026V071	40	26	71	And when he went out to the porch, another maid saw him, and said to those who were there, This fellow was also with Jesus of Nazareth.
B040C026V072	40	26	72	And again he denied it with an oath, I do not know the man.
B040C026V073	40	26	73	And after a while the bystanders came to him, and said to Peter, Surely you also are one of them; for your speech betrays you.
B040C026V074	40	26	74	Then he began to curse and to swear, saying, I do not know the man. And immediately the cock crowed.
B040C026V075	40	26	75	And Peter remembered the word Jesus said to him, Before the cock crows, you shall deny me thrice. And he went out, and wept bitterly.
B040C027V001	40	27	1	When the morning had come, all the chief priests and elders of the people took counsel against Jesus to put him to death:
B040C027V002	40	27	2	And when they had bound him, they led him away, and delivered him to Pilate, the governor.
B040C027V003	40	27	3	Then Judas, who had betrayed him, when he saw that he was condemned, repented, and brought back the thirty pieces of silver to the chief priests and elders,
B040C027V004	40	27	4	Saying, I have sinned in that I have betrayed innocent blood. And they said, What is that to us? see to that yourself.
B040C027V005	40	27	5	And he cast down the pieces of silver in the temple, and departed, and went and hanged himself.
B040C027V006	40	27	6	And the chief priests took the silver pieces, and said, It is not lawful to put them into the treasury, because it is the price of blood.
B040C027V007	40	27	7	And they took counsel, and bought with the money the potter's field, to bury strangers in.
B040C027V008	40	27	8	Therefore that field has been called, The field of blood, to this day.
B040C027V009	40	27	9	Then was fulfilled that which was spoken by Jeremiah the prophet, saying, And they took the thirty pieces of silver, the price of him on whom a value had been set by the sons of Israel;
B040C027V010	40	27	10	And gave them for the potter's field, as the Lord directed me.
B040C027V011	40	27	11	And Jesus stood before the governor: and the governor asked him, Are you the King of the Jews? And Jesus said to him, You say so.
B040C027V012	40	27	12	And when he was accused by the chief priests and elders, he said nothing.
B040C027V013	40	27	13	Then Pilate said to him, Do you not hear how many things they testify against you?
B040C027V014	40	27	14	And he answered him not a word; so that the governor marvelled greatly.
B040C027V015	40	27	15	Now at the feast the governor was accustomed to release to the people one prisoner, whom they wanted.
B040C027V016	40	27	16	And they had at that time a notorious prisoner, called Barabbas.
B040C027V017	40	27	17	Therefore, when they were gathered together, Pilate said to them, Whom do you want me to release for you? Barabbas, or Jesus who is called Christ?
B040C027V018	40	27	18	For he knew that it was because of envy they had delivered him up.
B040C027V019	40	27	19	When he sat down on the judgment seat, his wife sent a message to him, saying, Have nothing to do with that just man: for I have suffered many things this day in a dream because of him.
B040C027V020	40	27	20	But the chief priests and elders persuaded the multitude that they should ask for Barabbas, and have Jesus executed.
B040C027V021	40	27	21	The governor answered them, Which of the two do you want me to release for you? They said, Barabbas.
B040C027V022	40	27	22	Pilate said to them, What shall I do then with Jesus who is called Christ? They all said to him, Let him be crucified.
B040C027V023	40	27	23	And the governor said, Why, what evil has he done? But they cried out all the more, saying, Let him be crucified.
B040C027V024	40	27	24	When Pilate saw that he could not prevail, but rather that a tumult was starting, he took water, and washed his hands before the multitude, saying, I am innocent of this man's blood: you see to it yourselves.
B040C027V025	40	27	25	Then all the people answered, and said, His blood be on us, and on our children.
B040C027V026	40	27	26	Then he released Barabbas to them: and when he had scourged Jesus, he delivered him over to be crucified.
B040C027V027	40	27	27	Then the soldiers of the governor took Jesus into the Praetorium, and gathered around him the whole cohort of soldiers.
B040C027V028	40	27	28	And they stripped him, and put a scarlet robe on him.
B040C027V029	40	27	29	And when they had weaved a crown of thorns, they put it upon his head, and a reed in his right hand: and they bowed their knees before him, and mocked him, saying, Hail, King of the Jews!
B040C027V030	40	27	30	And they spit upon him, and took the reed, and struck him on the head.
B040C027V031	40	27	31	And after had mocked him, they took the robe off of him, and put his own clothing on him, and led him away to crucify him.
B040C027V032	40	27	32	And as they came out, they found a man of Cyrene, Simon by name: they compelled him to bear his cross.
B040C027V033	40	27	33	And when they had come to a place called Golgotha, that is to say, place of a skull,
B040C027V034	40	27	34	They gave him wine to drink mixed with gall: and when he had tasted it, he would not drink.
B040C027V035	40	27	35	And they crucified him, and divided his garments among them by casting lots.
B040C027V036	40	27	36	And sitting down they watched him there;
B040C027V037	40	27	37	And set up over his head the accusation against him, which read, THIS IS JESUS THE KING OF THE JEWS.
B040C027V038	40	27	38	At that time there were two robbers crucified with him, one on the right hand, and another on the left.
B040C027V039	40	27	39	And those who passed by reviled him, wagging their heads,
B040C027V040	40	27	40	Saying, You who would destroy the temple, and build it in three days, save yourself. If you are the Son of God, come down from the cross.
B040C027V041	40	27	41	Likewise the chief priests, with the scribes and elders, mocked him, saying,
B040C027V042	40	27	42	He saved others; he cannot save himself. If he is the King of Israel, let him now come down from the cross, and we will believe in him.
B040C027V043	40	27	43	He trusted in God; let him deliver him now, if he will have him: for he said, I am the Son of God.
B040C027V044	40	27	44	The robbers also, who were crucified with him, cast the same insult at him.
B040C027V045	40	27	45	Now from the sixth hour there was darkness over all the land until the ninth hour.
B040C027V046	40	27	46	And about the ninth hour Jesus cried out with a loud voice, saying, Eli, Eli, lama sabachthani? that is to say, My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?
B040C027V047	40	27	47	Some of those who stood there, when they heard that, said, This man calls for Elijah.
B040C027V048	40	27	48	And immediately one of them ran, and took a sponge, and filled it with vinegar, and put it on a reed, and gave it to him to drink.
B040C027V049	40	27	49	The rest said, Wait, let us see whether Elijah will come to save him.
B040C027V050	40	27	50	Jesus, when he had cried out again with a loud voice, yielded up the spirit.
B040C027V051	40	27	51	And, behold, the veil of the temple was torn in two from the top to the bottom; and the earth quaked, and the rocks were split;
B040C027V052	40	27	52	And the graves were opened; and many bodies of the saints who slept arose,
B040C027V053	40	27	53	And came out of the graves after his resurrection, and went into the holy city, and appeared to many.
B040C027V054	40	27	54	Now when the centurion, and those who were with him, watching Jesus, saw the earthquake, and those things that were done, they feared greatly, saying, Truly this was the Son of God.
B040C027V055	40	27	55	And many women were there, beholding from afar. They had followed Jesus from Galilee, ministering to him.
B040C027V056	40	27	56	Among them was Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James and Joseph, and the mother of the sons of Zebedee.
B040C027V057	40	27	57	When evening had come, there came a rich man from Arimathaea, named Joseph, who had himself also become a disciple of Jesus.
B040C027V058	40	27	58	He went to Pilate, and asked for the body of Jesus. Then Pilate commanded it be delivered to him.
B040C027V059	40	27	59	And when Joseph had taken the body, he wrapped it in a clean linen cloth,
B040C027V060	40	27	60	And laid it in his own new tomb, which he had cut out in the rock: and he rolled a great stone over the door of the tomb, and departed.
B040C027V061	40	27	61	And Mary Magdalene, and the other Mary, were there, sitting opposite the tomb.
B040C027V062	40	27	62	Now the next day, which followed the day of preparation, the chief priests and Pharisees came together before Pilate,
B040C027V063	40	27	63	Saying, Sir, we remember that while he was yet alive that deceiver said, After three days I will rise again.
B040C027V064	40	27	64	Therefore, command that the tomb be made secure until the third day, lest his disciples come by night, and steal him away, and say to the people, He has risen from the dead: so the last deception shall be worse than the first.
B040C027V065	40	27	65	Pilate said to them, You have a guard: go your way; make it as secure as you can.
B040C027V066	40	27	66	So they went, and made the tomb secure, sealing the stone and posting a guard.
B040C028V001	40	28	1	At the end of the sabbath, as it began to dawn on the first day of the week, Mary Magdalene and the other Mary came to see the tomb.
B040C028V002	40	28	2	And, behold, there was a great earthquake: for an angel of the Lord descended from heaven, and came and rolled back the stone from the door, and sat upon it.
B040C028V003	40	28	3	His countenance was like lightning, and his clothing white as snow:
B040C028V004	40	28	4	And for fear of him the guards shook, and became as dead men.
B040C028V005	40	28	5	And the angel said to the women, Fear not: for I know that you seek Jesus, who was crucified.
B040C028V006	40	28	6	He is not here: for he has risen, as he said. Come, see the place where he lay.
B040C028V007	40	28	7	And go quickly, and tell his disciples that he has risen from the dead; and, behold, he goes before you into Galilee; there you shall see him: lo, I have told you.
B040C028V008	40	28	8	And they departed quickly from the tomb with fear and great joy; and ran to bring his disciples word.
B040C028V009	40	28	9	And as they went to tell his disciples, behold, Jesus met them, saying, Hail. And they came and held him by the feet, and worshipped him.
B040C028V010	40	28	10	Then Jesus said to them, Do not be afraid: go tell my brethren to go into Galilee, and there they shall see me.
B040C028V011	40	28	11	Now when they were going, behold, some of the guards came into the city, and told the chief priests all the things that had happened.
B040C028V012	40	28	12	And when they had assembled with the elders, and had taken counsel, they gave much money to the soldiers,
B040C028V013	40	28	13	Saying, Say, His disciples came by night, and stole him away while we slept.
B040C028V014	40	28	14	And if this comes to the governor's ears, we will satisfy him, and keep you out of trouble.
B040C028V015	40	28	15	So they took the money, and did as they were told: and this story is commonly reported among the Jews to this day.
B040C028V016	40	28	16	Then the eleven disciples went away into Galilee, to a mountain where Jesus had directed them.
B040C028V017	40	28	17	And when they saw him, they worshipped him: but some doubted.
B040C028V018	40	28	18	And Jesus came and spoke to them, saying, All power has been given to me in heaven and on earth.
B040C028V019	40	28	19	Go, therefore, and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit:
B040C028V020	40	28	20	Teaching them to observe all things that I have commanded you: and, lo, I am with you always, even to the end of the age.
B041C001V001	41	1	1	The beginning of the gospel of Jesus Christ, the Son of God;
B041C001V002	41	1	2	As it is written in the prophets, Behold, I send my messenger before your face, who shall prepare your way.
B041C001V003	41	1	3	The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.
B041C001V004	41	1	4	John baptized in the wilderness, and preached a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins.
B041C001V005	41	1	5	And there went out to him all the land of Judaea, and all those of Jerusalem, and they were all baptized by him in the river Jordan, confessing their sins.
B041C001V006	41	1	6	And John was clothed with camel's hair, and with a leather girdle about his waist; and he ate locusts and wild honey;
B041C001V007	41	1	7	And preached, saying, After me there comes one mightier than I, the thong of whose sandals I am not worthy to stoop down and untie.
B041C001V008	41	1	8	I have baptized you with water: but he shall baptize you with the Holy Spirit.
B041C001V009	41	1	9	And it came to pass in those days, that Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee, and was baptized by John in the Jordan.
B041C001V010	41	1	10	And immediately as he came up out of the water, he saw the heavens opened, and the Spirit like a dove descending upon him:
B041C001V011	41	1	11	And there came a voice from heaven, saying, You are my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.
B041C001V012	41	1	12	And immediately the Spirit drove him into the wilderness.
B041C001V013	41	1	13	And he was there in the wilderness forty days, tempted by Satan; and was with the wild beasts; and the angels ministered to him.
B041C001V014	41	1	14	Now after John was put in prison, Jesus came to Galilee, preaching the gospel of God,
B041C001V015	41	1	15	And saying, The time is fulfilled, and the kingdom of God is at hand: repent and believe the gospel.
B041C001V016	41	1	16	Now as he walked by the sea of Galilee, he saw Simon and Andrew his brother casting a net into the sea: for they were fishermen.
B041C001V017	41	1	17	And Jesus said to them, Come after me, and I will make you fishers of men.
B041C001V018	41	1	18	And immediately they forsook their nets, and followed him.
B041C001V019	41	1	19	And when he had gone a little farther, he saw James the son of Zebedee, and John his brother, who were in their boat mending their nets.
B041C001V020	41	1	20	And immediately he called them: and they left their father Zebedee in the boat with the hired servants, and went after him.
B041C001V021	41	1	21	And they went into Capernaum; and immediately on the sabbath day he entered into the synagogue, and taught.
B041C001V022	41	1	22	And they were astonished at his teaching: for he taught them as one who had authority, and not as the scribes.
B041C001V023	41	1	23	And there was in their synagogue a man with an unclean spirit; and he cried out,
B041C001V024	41	1	24	Saying, What have we to do with you, Jesus of Nazareth? have you come to destroy us? I know who you are, the Holy One of God.
B041C001V025	41	1	25	And Jesus rebuked him, saying, Hold your peace, and come out of him.
B041C001V026	41	1	26	And when the unclean spirit had torn him, and cried out with a loud voice, it came out of him.
B041C001V027	41	1	27	And they were all amazed, so that they questioned among themselves, saying, What is this? what a new teaching this is! for with authority he commands even the unclean spirits, and they obey him.
B041C001V028	41	1	28	And immediately his fame spread throughout all the region around Galilee.
B041C001V029	41	1	29	And as soon as they had come out of the synagogue, they entered into the house of Simon and Andrew, with James and John.
B041C001V030	41	1	30	Now Simon's mother-in-law lay sick with a fever, and immediately they told him of her.
B041C001V031	41	1	31	And he came and took her by the hand, and lifted her up; and immediately the fever left her, and she waited upon them.
B041C001V032	41	1	32	And at evening, when the sun set, they brought to him all who were diseased, and those who were possessed by devils.
B041C001V033	41	1	33	And all the city was gathered together at the door.
B041C001V034	41	1	34	And he healed many who were sick with various diseases, and cast out many devils; and did not permit the devils to speak, because they knew him.
B041C001V035	41	1	35	And in the morning, rising up a great while before day, he went out, and departed to a solitary place, and there he prayed.
B041C001V036	41	1	36	And Simon, and those who were with him, hunted for him.
B041C001V037	41	1	37	And when they found him, they said to him, Everyone is seeking for you.
B041C001V038	41	1	38	And he said to them, Let us go into the next towns, that I may preach there also: for that is why I have come.
B041C001V039	41	1	39	And he preached in their synagogues throughout all Galilee, and cast out devils.
B041C001V040	41	1	40	And a leper came to him, begging him, and kneeling down to him, and saying to him, If you will, you can make me clean.
B041C001V041	41	1	41	And Jesus, moved with compassion, put forth his hand, and touched him, and said to him, I will; be clean.
B041C001V042	41	1	42	And as soon as he had spoken, immediately the leprosy departed from him, and he was cleansed.
B041C001V043	41	1	43	And he sternly charged him, and immediately sent him away;
B041C001V044	41	1	44	He said to him, See that you say nothing to any man: but go your way, show yourself to the priest, and offer for your cleansing those things which Moses commanded, as a testimony to them.
B041C001V045	41	1	45	But he went out, and began to proclaim it freely, and to spread the matter abroad, so that Jesus could no longer openly enter a city, but stayed out in lonely places: and they came to him from every quarter.
B041C002V001	41	2	1	And he entered Capernaum again after some days; and it was reported that he was in the house.
B041C002V002	41	2	2	And immediately many gathered together, so that there was no room to receive them, no, not even around the door: and he preached the word to them.
B041C002V003	41	2	3	And they came, bringing a paralytic, who was borne by four men.
B041C002V004	41	2	4	And when they could not come near to him because of the crowd, they made a hole in the roof where he was: and when they had broken through, they let down the mat on which the paralytic lay.
B041C002V005	41	2	5	When Jesus saw their faith, he said to the paralytic, Son, your sins are forgiven.
B041C002V006	41	2	6	But there were certain of the scribes sitting there, who reasoned in their hearts,
B041C002V007	41	2	7	Why does this man speak blasphemies? who can forgive sins but God only?
B041C002V008	41	2	8	And immediately Jesus, perceiving in his spirit that they so reasoned within themselves, said to them, Why do you reason about these things in your hearts?
B041C002V009	41	2	9	Which is easier to say to the paralytic, Your sins are forgiven; or to say, Arise, and take up your mat, and walk?
B041C002V010	41	2	10	But that you may know that the Son of man has power on earth to forgive sins, (he said to the paralytic,)
B041C002V011	41	2	11	I say to you, Arise, and take up your mat, and go home.
B041C002V012	41	2	12	And immediately he arose, took up the mat, and went forth before them all; so that they were all amazed, and glorified God, saying, We never saw anything like this.
B041C002V013	41	2	13	And he went forth again on the seashore; and all the multitude came to him, and he taught them.
B041C002V014	41	2	14	And as he passed by, he saw Levi, the son of Alphaeus, sitting at the tax office, and said to him, Follow me. And he arose and followed him.
B041C002V015	41	2	15	And it came to pass, that, as Jesus reclined at table in his house, many tax gatherers and sinners also sat together with Jesus and his disciples: for there were many, and they followed him.
B041C002V016	41	2	16	And when the scribes and Pharisees saw him eat with tax gatherers and sinners, they said to his disciples, How is it that he eats and drinks with tax gatherers and sinners?
B041C002V017	41	2	17	When Jesus heard it, he said to them, Those who are well have no need of a physician, but those who are sick: I came not to call the righteous, but sinners.
B041C002V018	41	2	18	Now the disciples of John and of the Pharisees were fasting: and they came and said to him, Why do the disciples of John and of the Pharisees fast, but your disciples do not fast?
B041C002V019	41	2	19	And Jesus said to them, Can the attendants of the bridegroom fast, while the bridegroom is with them? as long as they have the bridegroom with them, they cannot fast.
B041C002V020	41	2	20	But the days will come, when the bridegroom shall be taken away from them, and then they shall fast.
B041C002V021	41	2	21	No man sews a piece of unshrunk cloth on an old garment: because the new patch pulls away from the old, and the tear is made worse.
B041C002V022	41	2	22	And no man puts new wine into old wineskins: because the new wine bursts the wineskins, the wine is spilled, and the wineskins are ruined: but new wine must be put into new wineskins.
B041C002V023	41	2	23	And it came to pass, that he went through the grainfields on the sabbath day; and his disciples began, as they went, to pluck the heads of grain.
B041C002V024	41	2	24	And the Pharisees said to him, Behold, why are they doing what is not lawful on the sabbath day?
B041C002V025	41	2	25	And he said to them, Have you never read what David did, when he had need, and was hungry, he, and those who were with him?
B041C002V026	41	2	26	How he went into the house of God in the days of Abiathar the high priest, and ate the showbread, which is not lawful for any but the priests to eat, and gave also to them who were with him?
B041C002V027	41	2	27	And he said to them, The sabbath was made for man, and not man for the sabbath:
B041C002V028	41	2	28	Therefore, the Son of man is Lord also of the sabbath.
B041C003V001	41	3	1	And he entered again into the synagogue; and there was a man there who had a withered hand.
B041C003V002	41	3	2	And they watched him, to see whether he would heal him on the sabbath day; that they might accuse him.
B041C003V003	41	3	3	And he said to the man who had the withered hand, Stand and come here.
B041C003V004	41	3	4	And he said to them, Is it lawful to do good on the sabbath days, or to do evil? to save life, or to kill? But they held their peace.
B041C003V005	41	3	5	And when he had looked around on them with anger, grieved at the hardness of their hearts, he said to the man, Stretch forth your hand. And he stretched it out: and his hand was restored.
B041C003V006	41	3	6	And the Pharisees went forth, and immediately took counsel with the Herodians against him, how they might destroy him.
B041C003V007	41	3	7	But Jesus withdrew with his disciples to the sea: and a great multitude from Galilee followed him; and also from Judaea,
B041C003V008	41	3	8	And from Jerusalem, and from Idumaea, and from beyond the Jordan, and from around Tyre and Sidon; a great multitude, when they heard the many things he did, came to him.
B041C003V009	41	3	9	And he told his disciples that a boat should be ready for him because of the multitude, lest they should crowd him.
B041C003V010	41	3	10	For he had healed many; so as many as had diseases pressed upon him to touch him.
B041C003V011	41	3	11	And unclean spirits, when they saw him, fell down before him, and cried out, saying, You are the Son of God.
B041C003V012	41	3	12	And he sternly commanded them that they should not make him known.
B041C003V013	41	3	13	And he went up to the mountain, and called to him those he wanted: and they came to him.
B041C003V014	41	3	14	And he ordained twelve, that they should be with him, and that he might send them forth to preach,
B041C003V015	41	3	15	And to have authority to cast out devils:
B041C003V016	41	3	16	Simon, whom he called Peter;
B041C003V017	41	3	17	And James the son of Zebedee, and John the brother of James; to whom he gave the surname Boanerges, which means, Sons of thunder:
B041C003V018	41	3	18	And Andrew, and Philip, and Bartholomew, and Matthew, and Thomas, and James the son of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus, and Simon the Zealot,
B041C003V019	41	3	19	And Judas Iscariot, who betrayed him. And they went into a house.
B041C003V020	41	3	20	And the multitude came together again, so that they could not so much as eat bread.
B041C003V021	41	3	21	And when his family heard of it, they went out to lay hold on him: for they said, He is beside himself.
B041C003V022	41	3	22	And the scribes who came down from Jerusalem said, He is possessed by Beelzebub, and by the prince of the devils he casts out devils.
B041C003V023	41	3	23	And he called them to himself, and said to them in parables, How can Satan cast out Satan?
B041C003V024	41	3	24	If a kingdom is divided against itself, that kingdom cannot stand.
B041C003V025	41	3	25	And if a house is divided against itself, that house cannot stand.
B041C003V026	41	3	26	And if Satan rises up against himself, and is divided, he cannot stand, but is coming to an end.
B041C003V027	41	3	27	No man can enter into a strong man's house, and plunder his goods, unless he first binds the strong man; and then he will plunder his house.
B041C003V028	41	3	28	Truly I say to you, All sins shall be forgiven the sons of men, and whatever blasphemies they shall speak:
B041C003V029	41	3	29	But he who blasphemes against the Holy Spirit shall never have forgiveness, but is guilty of an eternal sin:
B041C003V030	41	3	30	Because they said, He has an unclean spirit.
B041C003V031	41	3	31	Then his brothers and mother came, and, standing outside, sent to him, calling him.
B041C003V032	41	3	32	And the multitude sat about him, and they said to him, Behold, your mother and your brothers are outside seeking for you.
B041C003V033	41	3	33	And he answered them, saying, Who is my mother, or my brothers?
B041C003V034	41	3	34	And he looked around at those who sat about him, and said, Behold my mother and my brothers!
B041C003V035	41	3	35	For whoever shall do the will of God is my brother, and my sister, and mother.
B041C004V001	41	4	1	And again he began to teach by the seaside: and a great multitude gathered around him, so that he entered into a boat, and sat in it; and the whole multitude was on the shore.
B041C004V002	41	4	2	And he taught them many things by parables, and said to them in his teaching,
B041C004V003	41	4	3	Listen; Behold, a sower went out to sow:
B041C004V004	41	4	4	And it came to pass, as he sowed, some seed fell by the wayside, and the birds of the air came and devoured it.
B041C004V005	41	4	5	And some fell on stony ground, where it did not have much earth; and immediately it sprang up, because it had no depth of soil:
B041C004V006	41	4	6	But when the sun came up, it was scorched; and because it had no root, it withered away.
B041C004V007	41	4	7	And some fell among thorns, and the thorns grew up, and choked it, and it yielded no fruit.
B041C004V008	41	4	8	And other seed fell on good ground, and yielded fruit that sprang up and increased; and brought forth, some thirty, and some sixty, and some a hundredfold.
B041C004V009	41	4	9	And he said to them, He who has ears to hear, let him hear.
B041C004V010	41	4	10	And when he was alone, those who were about him with the twelve asked him about the parable.
B041C004V011	41	4	11	And he said to them, To you it has been given to know the mystery of the kingdom of God: but to those who are outside, all these things are done in parables:
B041C004V012	41	4	12	That seeing they may see, and not perceive; and hearing they may hear, and not understand; lest they should be converted, and their sins be forgiven.
B041C004V013	41	4	13	And he said to them, Do you not understand this parable? How then will you understand all the parables?
B041C004V014	41	4	14	The sower sows the word.
B041C004V015	41	4	15	And these are the ones by the wayside, where the word is sown; when they have heard, Satan comes immediately, and takes away the word that was sown in them.
B041C004V016	41	4	16	And likewise, these are the ones who are like seed sown on stony ground; who, when they have heard the word, immediately receive it with gladness;
B041C004V017	41	4	17	But have no root in themselves, and so endure but for a time: afterward, when affliction or persecution arises for the word's sake, they immediately fall away.
B041C004V018	41	4	18	And these are the ones who are like seed sown among thorns; they hear the word,
B041C004V019	41	4	19	And the cares of this world, and the deceitfulness of riches, and the lust for other things enter in, and choke the word, and it becomes unfruitful.
B041C004V020	41	4	20	And these are the ones who are like seed sown on good ground; they hear the word, and receive it, and bring forth fruit, some thirty, some sixty, and some a hundredfold.
B041C004V021	41	4	21	And he said to them, Is a lamp brought in to be put under a bushel, or under a bed? and not to be set on a lampstand?
B041C004V022	41	4	22	For there is nothing hidden, which shall not be revealed; nor is anything kept secret that shall not come to light.
B041C004V023	41	4	23	If any man has ears to hear, let him hear.
B041C004V024	41	4	24	And he said to them, Take heed what you hear: with the measure you use, it shall be measured to you: and more besides.
B041C004V025	41	4	25	For he who has, to him shall more be given: and he who has not, from him shall be taken even that which he has.
B041C004V026	41	4	26	And he said, The kingdom of God is like a man who casts seed upon the ground;
B041C004V027	41	4	27	And goes to sleep and rises, night and day, and the seed sprouts and grows up, though he does not know how.
B041C004V028	41	4	28	For the earth brings forth fruit by itself; first the blade, then the ear, after that the full grain in the ear.
B041C004V029	41	4	29	But when the grain is ripe, immediately he puts the sickle to it, because the harvest has come.
B041C004V030	41	4	30	And he said, To what shall we liken the kingdom of God? or what parable shall we use for it?
B041C004V031	41	4	31	It is like a grain of mustard seed, which is the smallest seed planted in the ground:
B041C004V032	41	4	32	But when it is sown, it grows up, and becomes greater than all garden herbs, and shoots out great branches; so that the birds of the air may nest under the shadow of it.
B041C004V033	41	4	33	And with many such parables he spoke the word to them, as they were able to hear it.
B041C004V034	41	4	34	And he did not speak to them without a parable: and when they were alone, he explained all things to his disciples.
B041C004V035	41	4	35	And the same day, when evening had come, he said to them, Let us pass over to the other side.
B041C004V036	41	4	36	And when they had sent the multitude away, they took him just as he was in the boat. And there were also with him other boats.
B041C004V037	41	4	37	And there arose a great storm of wind, and the waves beat into the boat, so that it was almost swamped.
B041C004V038	41	4	38	And he was in the stern, asleep on a pillow: and they awoke him, and said to him, Teacher, do you not care that we perish?
B041C004V039	41	4	39	And he arose, and rebuked the wind, and said to the sea, Peace, be still. And the wind ceased, and there was a great calm.
B041C004V040	41	4	40	And he said to them, Why are you so fearful? how is it that you have no faith?
B041C004V041	41	4	41	And they were exceedingly fearful, and said to one another, What manner of man is this, that even the wind and the sea obey him?
B041C005V001	41	5	1	And they came to the other side of the sea, into the country of the Garasenes.
B041C005V002	41	5	2	And when he got out of the boat, immediately there met him from out of the tombs a man with an unclean spirit,
B041C005V003	41	5	3	Who had his dwelling among the tombs; and no man could bind him, no, not even with chains:
B041C005V004	41	5	4	Because he had been often bound with fetters and chains, and he had pulled apart the chains, and broken the fetters in pieces: no man could subdue him.
B041C005V005	41	5	5	And always, night and day, he was in the mountains, and in the tombs, crying out, and cutting himself with stones.
