B041C006V001	41	6	1	And he went out from there, and came into his own country; and his disciples followed him.
B041C006V002	41	6	2	And when the sabbath day came, he began to teach in the synagogue: and many who heard him were astonished, saying, Where did this man get these things? and what wisdom is this which is given to him, that even such miracles are performed by his hands?
B041C006V003	41	6	3	Is this not the carpenter, the son of Mary, the brother of James, and Joseph, of Judas, and Simon? and are not his sisters here with us? And they were offended by him.
B041C006V004	41	6	4	But Jesus said to them, A prophet is not without honour, except in his own country, and among his own kin, and in his own house.
B041C006V005	41	6	5	And he could do no miracles there, except to lay his hands upon a few sick people, and heal them.
B041C006V006	41	6	6	And he marvelled because of their unbelief. And he went among the villages, teaching.
B041C006V007	41	6	7	And he called to him the twelve, and began to send them forth two by two; and gave them authority over unclean spirits;
B041C006V008	41	6	8	And commanded them to take nothing for their journey, except a staff; no bread, no bag, no money in their belts:
B041C006V009	41	6	9	But to wear sandals; and not to put on two tunics.
B041C006V010	41	6	10	And he said to them, Wherever you enter a house, abide there until you depart from that place.
B041C006V011	41	6	11	And whoever will not receive you, or hear you, when you depart from there, shake the dust off your feet as a testimony against them.
B041C006V012	41	6	12	And they went out, and preached that men should repent.
B041C006V013	41	6	13	And they cast out many devils, and anointed with oil many who were sick, and healed them.
B041C006V014	41	6	14	And King Herod heard of it; (for his name was spread abroad). And some said that John the Baptist had risen from the dead, and therefore mighty works showed themselves forth in him.
B041C006V015	41	6	15	Others said, He is Elijah. And others said, He is a prophet, like one of the prophets of old.
B041C006V016	41	6	16	But when Herod heard of it, he said, It is John, whom I beheaded: he has risen from the dead.
B041C006V017	41	6	17	For Herod himself had John arrested, and bound him in prison because of Herodias, his brother Philip's wife: for he had married her.
B041C006V018	41	6	18	For John had said to Herod, It is not lawful for you to have your brother's wife.
B041C006V019	41	6	19	Therefore Herodias had a grudge against him, and would have killed him; but she could not:
B041C006V020	41	6	20	For Herod feared John, knowing that he was a just and holy man, and kept him safe; and when he heard him, he was perplexed, but he enjoyed listening to him.
B041C006V021	41	6	21	But an opportunity came on Herod's birthday, when he had a banquet for his lords, high captains, and chief men of Galilee;
B041C006V022	41	6	22	When the daughter of Herodias came in, and danced, and pleased Herod and those who sat with him, the king said to the girl, Ask of me whatever you wish, and I will give it to you.
