B041C006V028	41	6	28	And brought his head on a platter, and gave it to the girl: and she gave it to her mother.
B041C006V029	41	6	29	And when his disciples heard of it, they came and took his body, and laid it in a tomb.
B041C006V030	41	6	30	And the apostles gathered together with Jesus, and told him all things, both what they had done, and what they had taught.
B041C006V031	41	6	31	And he said to them, Come by yourselves to a lonely place, and rest a while: for there were many coming and going, and they had no leisure even to eat.
