B041C011V026	41	11	26	[But if you do not forgive, neither will your Father who is in heaven forgive your trespasses.]
B041C011V027	41	11	27	And they came again to Jerusalem: and as he was walking in the temple, the chief priests, and the scribes, and the elders came to him,
B041C011V028	41	11	28	And said to him, By what authority do you do these things? and who gave you this authority to do these things?
B041C011V029	41	11	29	And Jesus answered them, I will ask you one question; answer me, and I will tell you by what authority I do these things.
B041C011V030	41	11	30	The baptism of John, was it from heaven, or from men? answer me.
B041C011V031	41	11	31	And they reasoned among themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven; he will say, Why then did you not believe him?
B041C011V032	41	11	32	But if we shall say, From men; they feared the people: for all held that John was indeed a prophet.
B041C011V033	41	11	33	So they answered and said to Jesus, We cannot tell. And Jesus said to them, Neither will I tell you by what authority I do these things.
B041C012V001	41	12	1	And he began to speak to them in parables. A certain man planted a vineyard, and set a hedge about it, and dug a place for the winepress, and built a tower, and rented it out to farmers, and went to a far country.
B041C012V002	41	12	2	And at harvest time he sent a servant to the farmers, that he might receive from them some of the fruit of the vineyard.
B041C012V003	41	12	3	But they caught him, and beat him, and sent him away empty-handed.
B041C012V004	41	12	4	And he sent to them another servant; and they wounded him in the head, and treated him shamefully.
B041C012V005	41	12	5	And he sent another; but they killed him, and so they did to many others; beating some, and killing some.
B041C012V006	41	12	6	Having yet one more to send, his well-beloved son, he sent him last of all to them, saying, They will respect my son.
B041C012V007	41	12	7	But the farmers said to themselves, This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and the inheritance shall be ours.
B041C012V008	41	12	8	And they took him, and killed him, and threw him out of the vineyard.
B041C012V009	41	12	9	Therefore, what shall the owner of the vineyard do? he will come and destroy the farmers, and will give the vineyard to others.
B041C012V010	41	12	10	Have you not read this scripture; The stone which the builders rejected has become the chief cornerstone:
B041C012V011	41	12	11	This was the Lord's doing, and it is marvellous in our eyes?
B041C012V012	41	12	12	And they sought to lay hold of him, but feared the people: for they knew that he had spoken the parable against them: and they left him, and went their way.
B041C012V013	41	12	13	And they sent to him some of the Pharisees and Herodians, to catch him in his words.
B041C012V014	41	12	14	And when they had come, they said to him, Teacher, we know that you are truthful, and defer to no man: for you do not regard the position of men, but teach the way of God in truth: Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?
B041C012V015	41	12	15	Shall we pay, or shall we not pay? But he, knowing their hypocrisy, said to them, Why are you testing me? bring me a denarius, that I may see it.
B041C012V016	41	12	16	And they brought it. And he said to them, Whose is this image and inscription? And they said to him, Caesar's.
B041C012V017	41	12	17	And Jesus answered, saying to them, Give to Caesar the things that are Caesar's, and to God the things that are God's. And they marvelled at him.
B041C012V018	41	12	18	Then the Sadducees, who say there is no resurrection, came to him, and they questioned him, saying,
B041C012V019	41	12	19	Teacher, Moses wrote for us, If a man's brother dies, and leaves his wife, but leaves no child, his brother should take his wife, and raise up children for his brother.
B041C012V020	41	12	20	Now there were seven brothers: and the first took a wife, and died, leaving no child.
B041C012V021	41	12	21	And the second took her, and died without leaving a child: and the third likewise.
B041C012V022	41	12	22	All seven had her, and left no child: last of all the woman died also.
B041C012V023	41	12	23	Therefore, in the resurrection, when they shall rise, which one's wife shall she be? for all seven had her as wife.
B041C012V024	41	12	24	Jesus answered them, Is this not the reason you err, because you do not know the scriptures or the power of God?
B041C012V025	41	12	25	For when they shall rise from the dead, they neither marry, nor are given in marriage; but are like the angels in heaven.
B041C012V026	41	12	26	And as for the dead rising: have you not read in the book of Moses, how God spoke to him in the bush, saying, I am the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob?
B041C012V027	41	12	27	He is not the God of the dead, but the God of the living: therefore you are greatly mistaken.
B041C012V028	41	12	28	And one of the scribes came, and having heard them arguing, and perceiving that he had answered them well, asked him, Which is the first commandment of all?
B041C012V029	41	12	29	And Jesus answered him, The first of all the commandments is, Hear, O Israel; The Lord our God is one Lord:
B041C012V030	41	12	30	And you shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your mind, and with all your strength.
B041C012V031	41	12	31	And the second is this, You shall love your neighbour as yourself. There is no other commandment greater than these.
B041C012V032	41	12	32	And the scribe said to him, Well said, Teacher, you have spoken the truth: for there is one God; and there is none other but he:
B041C012V033	41	12	33	And to love him with all the heart, and with all the understanding, and with all the soul, and with all the strength, and to love one's neighbour as oneself, is more than all burnt offerings and sacrifices.
B041C012V034	41	12	34	And when Jesus saw that he answered wisely, he said to him, You are not far from the kingdom of God. And after that no man dared ask him anything.
B041C012V035	41	12	35	And while he taught in the temple, Jesus said, How is it that the scribes say that the Christ is the Son of David?
B041C012V036	41	12	36	For David himself said by the Holy Spirit, The LORD said to my Lord, Sit on my right hand, until I put your enemies under your feet.
B041C012V037	41	12	37	Therefore, David himself calls him Lord; so how can he be his son? And the great crowd heard him gladly.
B041C012V038	41	12	38	And in his teaching he said to them, Beware of the scribes, who love to go about in long clothing, and love greetings in the marketplaces,
B041C012V039	41	12	39	And the chief seats in the synagogues, and places of honour at feasts:
B041C012V040	41	12	40	They devour widows' houses, and for a pretence make long prayers: these shall receive greater condemnation.
B041C012V041	41	12	41	And Jesus sat across from the treasury, and watched how the people put money into the treasury: and many who were rich cast in much.
B041C012V042	41	12	42	And a certain poor widow came, and she put in two small copper coins, which make a farthing.
B041C012V043	41	12	43	And he called his disciples to him, and said to them, Truly I say to you, That this poor widow has put more into the treasury than all the others:
B041C012V044	41	12	44	For all the others gave out of their abundance; but she gave out of her poverty, putting in everything she had, all she had to live on.
B041C013V001	41	13	1	And as he went out of the temple, one of his disciples said to him, Teacher, see what wonderful stones and buildings!
B041C013V002	41	13	2	Jesus said to him, Do you see these great buildings? there shall not be one stone left upon another, that shall not be thrown down.
B041C013V003	41	13	3	And as he sat upon the mount of Olives across from the temple, Peter and James and John and Andrew asked him privately,
B041C013V004	41	13	4	Tell us, when shall these things be? and what will be the sign that all these things are about to be fulfilled?
B041C013V005	41	13	5	And Jesus said to them, Take heed lest any man deceive you:
B041C013V006	41	13	6	For many will come in my name, saying, I am he; and shall deceive many.
B041C013V007	41	13	7	And when you hear of wars and rumours of wars, do not be troubled: for such things must happen; but the end is not yet.
B041C013V008	41	13	8	For nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom: and there shall be earthquakes in various places, and there shall be famines: these are the beginnings of birth pains.
B041C013V009	41	13	9	But take heed for yourselves: for they will deliver you up to councils; and you shall be beaten in the synagogues: and you shall be brought before rulers and kings for my sake, as a testimony to them.
B041C013V010	41	13	10	And the gospel must first be preached among all nations.
B041C013V011	41	13	11	But when they bring you to trial, do not worry about what you shall say: but whatever is given to you in that hour, speak that: for it is not you who speaks, but the Holy Spirit.
B041C013V012	41	13	12	Now brother will betray brother to death, and a father his son; and children shall rise up against their parents, and shall cause them to be put to death.
B041C013V013	41	13	13	And you shall be hated by all men for my name's sake: but he who endures to the end shall be saved.
B041C013V014	41	13	14	When you see the abomination of desolation standing where it should not be, (let him who reads understand,) then let those who are in Judaea flee to the mountains:
B041C013V015	41	13	15	And let him who is on the housetop not go down into the house, nor enter it to take anything out of his house:
B041C013V016	41	13	16	And let him who is in the field not turn back again for his cloak.
B041C013V017	41	13	17	But woe to those who are with child, and to those who are nursing infants in those days!
B041C013V018	41	13	18	Pray that your flight may not be in the winter.
B041C013V019	41	13	19	For in those days there shall be affliction, such as has not been from the beginning of God's creation to this time, nor ever shall be again.
B041C013V020	41	13	20	And unless the Lord had shortened those days, no one would be saved: but for the sake of the elect, whom he has chosen, he has shortened the days.
B041C013V021	41	13	21	And then if any man says to you, Lo, here is the Christ; or, lo, there he is; do not believe him:
B041C013V022	41	13	22	For false Christs and false prophets shall arise, and shall show signs and wonders, to seduce, if it were possible, even the elect.
B041C013V023	41	13	23	But take heed: behold, I have told you all things in advance.
B041C013V024	41	13	24	But in those days, after that tribulation, the sun shall be darkened, and the moon shall not give her light,
B041C013V025	41	13	25	And the stars of heaven shall fall, and the powers that are in heaven shall be shaken.
B041C013V026	41	13	26	And then they shall see the Son of man coming in the clouds with great power and glory.
B041C013V027	41	13	27	And then he shall send his angels, and shall gather together his elect from the four winds, from the remotest part of the earth to the remotest part of heaven.
B041C013V028	41	13	28	Now learn a parable from the fig tree; When its branch becomes tender, and puts forth leaves, you know that summer is near:
B041C013V029	41	13	29	Even so, when you see these things come to pass, know that it is near, even at the door.
B041C013V030	41	13	30	Truly I say to you, that this generation shall not pass away, until all these things have happened.
B041C013V031	41	13	31	Heaven and earth shall pass away: but my words shall not pass away.
B041C013V032	41	13	32	But of that day and that hour no man knows, no, not even the angels which are in heaven, nor the Son, but only the Father.
B041C013V033	41	13	33	Take heed, watch and pray: for you do not know when the time will come.
B041C013V034	41	13	34	It is like a man taking a far journey, who left his house, and gave authority to his servants, and to each man his work, and commanded the doorkeeper to watch.
B041C013V035	41	13	35	Watch therefore: for you do not know when the master of the house comes, at evening, or at midnight, or at the cockcrowing, or in the morning:
B041C013V036	41	13	36	Lest he come suddenly and find you sleeping.
B041C013V037	41	13	37	And what I say to you I say to all, Watch.
B041C014V001	41	14	1	After two days was the feast of the passover, and of unleavened bread: and the chief priests and the scribes sought how they might take him secretly, and put him to death.
B041C014V002	41	14	2	But they said, Not on the feast day, lest there be an uproar among the people.
B041C014V003	41	14	3	And while he was in Bethany in the house of Simon the leper, as he reclined at table, there came a woman having an alabaster vial of perfume of pure nard; and she broke the vial, and poured it on his head.
B041C014V004	41	14	4	And some were indignant, and said to themselves, Why was this perfume wasted?
B041C014V005	41	14	5	For it might have been sold for more than three hundred denarii, and have been given to the poor. And they reproved her.
B041C014V006	41	14	6	And Jesus said, Let her alone; why are you troubling her? she has done a beautiful thing to me.
B041C014V007	41	14	7	For you have the poor with you always, and whenever you wish you may do them good: but you will not always have me.
B041C014V008	41	14	8	She has done what she could: she has come beforehand to anoint my body for burial.
B041C014V009	41	14	9	Truly I say to you, Wherever this gospel shall be preached throughout the whole world, what she has done shall be spoken of in remembrance of her.
B041C014V010	41	14	10	And Judas Iscariot, one of the twelve, went to the chief priests, to betray him to them.
B041C014V011	41	14	11	And when they heard this, they were glad, and promised to give him money. And he sought an opportunity to betray him.
B041C014V012	41	14	12	On the first day of unleavened bread, when they killed the passover lamb, his disciples said to him, Where do you want us to go and prepare the passover for you to eat?
B041C014V013	41	14	13	And he sent two of his disciples, and said to them, Go into the city, and there you shall meet a man carrying a pitcher of water: follow him.
B041C014V014	41	14	14	And wherever he enters, say to the owner of the house, The Teacher says, Where is the guest chamber, where I shall eat the passover with my disciples?
B041C014V015	41	14	15	And he will show you a large upper room furnished and ready: make preparations for us there.
B041C014V016	41	14	16	And his disciples went forth, and came into the city, and found it as he had said to them: and they made the passover ready.
B041C014V017	41	14	17	And in the evening he came with the twelve.
B041C014V018	41	14	18	And as they sat and ate, Jesus said, Truly I say to you, One of you who eats with me shall betray me.
B041C014V019	41	14	19	And they began to be sorrowful, and to say to him one by one, Is it I?
B041C014V020	41	14	20	And he answered them, It is one of the twelve, one who dips with me in the bowl.
B041C014V021	41	14	21	The Son of man shall indeed go, just as it is written of him: but woe to that man by whom the Son of man is betrayed! it would be better for that man if he had never been born.
B041C014V022	41	14	22	And as they ate, Jesus took bread, and blessed, and broke it, and gave to them, and said, Take it: this is my body.
B041C014V023	41	14	23	And he took the cup, and when he had given thanks, he gave it to them: and they all drank from it.
B041C014V024	41	14	24	And he said to them, This is my blood of the covenant, which is shed for many.
B041C014V025	41	14	25	Truly I say to you, I will drink no more of the fruit of the vine, until that day when I drink it anew in the kingdom of God.
B041C014V026	41	14	26	And when they had sung a hymn, they went out to the mount of Olives.
B041C014V027	41	14	27	And Jesus said to them, All you shall fall away because of me: for it is written, I will strike the shepherd, and the sheep shall be scattered.
B041C014V028	41	14	28	But after I have risen, I will go before you into Galilee.
B041C014V029	41	14	29	But Peter said to him, Although all shall fall away, I will not.
B041C014V030	41	14	30	And Jesus said to him, Truly I say to you, That this day, this very night, before the cock crows twice, you shall deny me three times.
B041C014V031	41	14	31	But he spoke the more vehemently, If I should die with you, I will not deny you. And they all said the same.
B041C014V032	41	14	32	And they came to a place named Gethsemane: and he said to his disciples, Sit here, while I pray.
B041C014V033	41	14	33	And he took with him Peter and James and John, and he began to be filled with horror and deeply troubled;
B041C014V034	41	14	34	And he said to them, My soul is exceedingly sorrowful, to the point of death: stay here, and watch.
B041C014V035	41	14	35	And he went forward a little, and fell on the ground, and prayed that, if it were possible, the hour might pass from him.
B041C014V036	41	14	36	And he said, Abba, Father, all things are possible for you; take away this cup from me: nevertheless not what I will, but what you will.
B041C014V037	41	14	37	And he came, and found them sleeping, and said to Peter, Simon, are you sleeping? could you not watch for one hour?
B041C014V038	41	14	38	Watch and pray, that you may not enter into temptation. The spirit is willing, but the flesh is weak.
B041C014V039	41	14	39	And again he went away, and prayed, and spoke the same words.
B041C014V040	41	14	40	And when he returned, he found them asleep again, (for their eyes were heavy,) and they did not know what to answer him.
B041C014V041	41	14	41	And he came the third time, and said to them, Are you still sleeping and resting? enough, the hour has come; behold, the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.
B041C014V042	41	14	42	Rise up, let us go; behold, he who betrays me is at hand.
B041C014V043	41	14	43	And immediately, while he yet spoke, Judas came, one of the twelve, and with him a great multitude with swords and clubs, from the chief priests and the scribes and the elders.
B041C014V044	41	14	44	And he who betrayed him had given them a signal, saying, Whomever I kiss is the one; take him, and lead him away safely.
B041C014V045	41	14	45	And as soon as he came, he went immediately to him, and said, Master; and kissed him.
B041C014V046	41	14	46	And they laid their hands on him, and took him.
B041C014V047	41	14	47	And one of those who stood nearby drew a sword, and struck the servant of the high priest, and cut off his ear.
B041C014V048	41	14	48	And Jesus said to them, Have you come out, as against a thief, with swords and clubs to take me?
B041C014V049	41	14	49	I was with you daily in the temple teaching, and you did not seize me: but the scriptures must be fulfilled.
B041C014V050	41	14	50	And they all forsook him, and fled.
B041C014V051	41	14	51	And a certain young man followed him, having a linen cloth wrapped around his naked body; and they laid hold on him:
B041C014V052	41	14	52	But he left the linen cloth, and fled from them naked.
B041C014V053	41	14	53	And they led Jesus away to the high priest: and all the chief priests and the elders and the scribes were assembled.
B041C014V054	41	14	54	And Peter followed him from afar, even into the courtyard of the high priest: and he sat with the servants, and warmed himself at the fire.
B041C014V055	41	14	55	And the chief priests and all the council sought for testimony against Jesus to put him to death; but found none.
B041C014V056	41	14	56	For many bore false witness against him, but their testimonies did not agree.
B041C014V057	41	14	57	And some arose, and bore false witness against him, saying,
B041C014V058	41	14	58	We heard him say, I will destroy this temple that is made with hands, and within three days I will build another made without hands.
B041C014V059	41	14	59	But even then their testimonies did not agree.
B041C014V060	41	14	60	And the high priest stood up in the midst, and asked Jesus, Have you no answer? what is it that these men are testifying against you?
B041C014V061	41	14	61	But he held his peace, and said nothing. Again the high priest asked him, Are you the Christ, the Son of the Blessed One?
B041C014V062	41	14	62	And Jesus said, I am: and you shall see the Son of man sitting on the right hand of power, and coming in the clouds of heaven.
B041C014V063	41	14	63	Then the high priest tore his clothes, and said, Why do we need any further witnesses?
B041C014V064	41	14	64	You have heard the blasphemy: what do you think? And they all condemned him as worthy of death.
B041C014V065	41	14	65	And some began to spit on him, and to cover his face, and to strike him, and to say to him, Prophesy: and as the guards took him they beat him with their fists.
B041C014V066	41	14	66	And as Peter was below in the courtyard, one of the maids of the high priest came:
B041C014V067	41	14	67	And when she saw Peter warming himself, she looked at him, and said, You also were with Jesus of Nazareth.
B041C014V068	41	14	68	But he denied it, saying, I do not know or understand what you are saying. And he went out into the entryway.
B041C014V069	41	14	69	And the maid saw him again, and began to say to those who stood by, This is one of them.
B041C014V070	41	14	70	And he denied it again. And a little later, those who stood nearby again said to Peter, Surely you are one of them: for you are also a Galilaean.
B041C014V071	41	14	71	But he began to curse and to swear, saying, I do not know this man of whom you speak.
B041C014V072	41	14	72	And the second time the cock crowed. And Peter remembered that Jesus said to him, Before the cock crows twice, you shall deny me three times. And when he remembered this, he wept.
B041C015V001	41	15	1	And immediately in the morning the chief priests held a consultation with the elders and scribes and the whole council, and bound Jesus, and carried him away, and delivered him to Pilate.
B041C015V002	41	15	2	And Pilate asked him, Are you the King of the Jews? And he said to him, You say so.
B041C015V003	41	15	3	And the chief priests accused him of many things: but he answered nothing.
B041C015V004	41	15	4	And Pilate asked him again, saying, Have you no answer to make? behold how many things they testify against you.
B041C015V005	41	15	5	But Jesus made no further answer; so that Pilate was amazed.
B041C015V006	41	15	6	Now at the feast he released to them one prisoner, whomever they requested.
B041C015V007	41	15	7	And there was one named Barabbas, who was in prison with his fellow rebels, who had committed murder in the insurrection.
B041C015V008	41	15	8	And the multitude approached and began asking him to do for them as he usually did.
B041C015V009	41	15	9	Pilate answered them, saying, Do you want me to release for you the King of the Jews?
B041C015V010	41	15	10	For he knew that the chief priests had delivered him out of envy.
B041C015V011	41	15	11	But the chief priests incited the people to have him release Barabbas to them.
B041C015V012	41	15	12	And Pilate answered and said again to them, What then shall I do with him whom you call the King of the Jews?
B041C015V013	41	15	13	And they cried out again, Crucify him.
B041C015V014	41	15	14	Then Pilate said to them, Why, what evil has he done? And they cried out all the louder, Crucify him.
B041C015V015	41	15	15	And so Pilate, wanting to satisfy the people, released Barabbas to them, and delivered Jesus, when he had scourged him, to be crucified.
B041C015V016	41	15	16	And the soldiers led him away into the hall, called the Praetorium; and they called together the whole band of soldiers.
B041C015V017	41	15	17	And they clothed him with purple, and weaved a crown of thorns, and put it on him,
B041C015V018	41	15	18	And began to acclaim him, Hail, King of the Jews!
B041C015V019	41	15	19	And they struck him on the head with a cane, and spat upon him, and bowed their knees in worship to him.
B041C015V020	41	15	20	And when they had mocked him, they took the purple off of him, and put his own clothes on him, and led him out to crucify him.
B041C015V021	41	15	21	And they compelled Simon, a Cyrenian who was passing by on his way in from the country, the father of Alexander and Rufus, to bear his cross.
B041C015V022	41	15	22	And they brought him to the place called Golgotha, which means, The place of a skull.
B041C015V023	41	15	23	And they gave him wine to drink mingled with myrrh: but he would not take it.
B041C015V024	41	15	24	And when they had crucified him, they divided his garments, casting lots for them, to decide what each man should take.
B041C015V025	41	15	25	And it was the third hour when they crucified him.
B041C015V026	41	15	26	And the inscription of the accusation against him was written above him, THE KING OF THE JEWS.
B041C015V027	41	15	27	And with him they crucified two thieves; one on his right hand, and the other on his left.
B041C015V028	41	15	28	[And the scripture was fulfilled, which says, And he was numbered with the transgressors.]
B041C015V029	41	15	29	And those who passed by kept abusing him, wagging their heads, and saying, Ah, you who would destroy the temple, and build it in three days,
B041C015V030	41	15	30	Save yourself, and come down from the cross.
B041C015V031	41	15	31	Likewise, the chief priests mocked him among themselves and with the scribes, He saved others; but he cannot save himself.
B041C015V032	41	15	32	Let Christ, the King of Israel, descend now from the cross, that we may see and believe. And those who were crucified with him also reviled him.
B041C015V033	41	15	33	And when the sixth hour had come, there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour.
B041C015V034	41	15	34	And at the ninth hour Jesus cried out with a loud voice, saying, Eloi, Eloi, lama sabachthani? which means, My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?
B041C015V035	41	15	35	And some of those who stood by, when they heard it, said, Behold, he is calling Elijah.
B041C015V036	41	15	36	And one ran and filled a sponge full of vinegar, and put it on a reed, and gave it to him to drink, saying, Wait; let us see whether Elijah will come to take him down.
B041C015V037	41	15	37	And Jesus cried out with a loud voice, and breathed his last.
B041C015V038	41	15	38	And the veil of the temple was torn in two from the top to the bottom.
B041C015V039	41	15	39	And when the centurion, who stood facing him, saw how he breathed his last, he said, Truly this man was the Son of God.
B041C015V040	41	15	40	There were also women looking on from afar: among whom was Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James the less and of Joses, and Salome;
B041C015V041	41	15	41	(Who, when he was in Galilee, followed him, and ministered to him;) and many other women who came up with him to Jerusalem.
B041C015V042	41	15	42	And when the evening had come, because it was the preparation day, that is, the day before the sabbath,
B041C015V043	41	15	43	Joseph of Arimathaea, an honoured member of the council, who also waited for the kingdom of God, came, and went in boldly to Pilate, and asked for the body of Jesus.
B041C015V044	41	15	44	And Pilate wondered if he was dead so soon: and calling the centurion, he asked him if he was already dead.
B041C015V045	41	15	45	And when he learned from the centurion that it was so, he gave the body to Joseph.
B041C015V046	41	15	46	So he bought a fine linen cloth, and took him down, and wrapped him in the linen, and laid him in a tomb which was cut out of the rock, and rolled a stone against the door of the tomb.
B041C015V047	41	15	47	Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joses watched where he was laid.
B041C016V001	41	16	1	And when the sabbath was past, Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James, and Salome, bought sweet spices, that they might go and anoint him.
B041C016V002	41	16	2	And very early in the morning of the first day of the week, they came to the tomb at the rising of the sun.
B041C016V003	41	16	3	And they said to one another, Who shall roll the stone away from the door of the tomb for us?
B041C016V004	41	16	4	And when they looked, they saw that the stone, which was very large, had already been rolled away.
B041C016V005	41	16	5	And entering into the tomb, they saw a young man sitting on the right side, clothed in a long white garment; and they were amazed.
B041C016V006	41	16	6	And he said to them, Do not be afraid: You seek Jesus of Nazareth, who was crucified: he has risen; he is not here: behold the place where they laid him.
B041C016V007	41	16	7	But go your way, tell his disciples and Peter that he goes before you into Galilee: there you shall see him, as he told you.
B041C016V008	41	16	8	And they went out quickly, and fled from the tomb; for they were trembling and amazed: and they said nothing to anyone; for they were afraid.
B041C016V009	41	16	9	[Now when Jesus rose early on the first day of the week, he appeared first to Mary Magdalene, out of whom he had cast seven devils.
B041C016V010	41	16	10	And she went and told those who had been with him, as they mourned and wept.
B041C016V011	41	16	11	And they, when they heard that he was alive, and that she had seen him, did not believe.
B041C016V012	41	16	12	After that he appeared in another form to two of them, as they walked, and went into the country.
B041C016V013	41	16	13	And they went and told it to the others, who also did not believe them.
B041C016V014	41	16	14	Afterward, he appeared to the eleven as they sat eating, and rebuked them for their unbelief and hardness of heart, because they did not believe those who saw him after he had risen.
B041C016V015	41	16	15	And he said to them, Go into all the world, and preach the gospel to every creature.
B041C016V016	41	16	16	He who believes and is baptized shall be saved; but he who does not believe shall be condemned.
B041C016V017	41	16	17	And these signs shall follow those who believe; In my name they shall cast out devils; they shall speak with new tongues;
B041C016V018	41	16	18	They shall pick up serpents; and if they drink any deadly thing, it shall not hurt them; they shall lay hands on the sick, and they shall recover.
B041C016V019	41	16	19	So after the Lord had spoken to them, he was received up into heaven, and sat on the right hand of God.
B041C016V020	41	16	20	And they went forth, and preached everywhere, the Lord working with them, and confirming the word with accompanying signs.]
B042C001V001	42	1	1	Since many have undertaken to set forth in order a narrative of those things which have happened among us,
B042C001V002	42	1	2	Just as they have been delivered to us, by those who from the beginning were eyewitnesses, and ministers of the word;
B042C001V003	42	1	3	It seemed good to me also, having carefully investigated all these things from the very beginning, to write to you an orderly account, most excellent Theophilus,
B042C001V004	42	1	4	That you might know the certainty of those things, about which you have been instructed.
B042C001V005	42	1	5	There was in the days of Herod, the king of Judaea, a certain priest named Zechariah, of the division of Abija: and his wife was one of the daughters of Aaron, and her name was Elizabeth.
B042C001V006	42	1	6	And they were both righteous before God, walking blamelessly in all the commandments and ordinances of the Lord.
B042C001V007	42	1	7	And they had no child, because Elizabeth was barren, and they were both now well along in years.
B042C001V008	42	1	8	And it came to pass, that while he executed the priest's service before God while his division was on duty,
B042C001V009	42	1	9	According to the custom of the priest's office, he was chosen by lot to enter the temple of the Lord and burn incense.
B042C001V010	42	1	10	And the whole multitude of people were praying outside at the time of incense offering.
B042C001V011	42	1	11	And there appeared to him an angel of the Lord standing on the right side of the altar of incense.
B042C001V012	42	1	12	And when Zechariah saw him, he was troubled, and fear came upon him.
B042C001V013	42	1	13	But the angel said to him, Fear not, Zechariah: for your prayer has been heard; and your wife Elizabeth shall bear you a son, and you shall call his name John.
B042C001V014	42	1	14	And you shall have joy and gladness; and many shall rejoice at his birth.
B042C001V015	42	1	15	For he shall be great in the sight of the Lord, and shall drink neither wine nor strong drink; and he shall be filled with the Holy Spirit, even from his mother's womb.
B042C001V016	42	1	16	And he shall turn many of the children of Israel to the Lord their God.
B042C001V017	42	1	17	And he shall go before him in the spirit and power of Elijah, to turn the hearts of the fathers to the children, and the disobedient to the wisdom of the just; to make ready a people prepared for the Lord.
B042C001V018	42	1	18	And Zechariah said to the angel, How shall I know this? for I am an old man, and my wife is well along in years.
B042C001V019	42	1	19	And the angel answered him, I am Gabriel, who stands in the presence of God; and have been sent to speak to you, and to bring you this good news.
B042C001V020	42	1	20	Behold, you shall be silent, unable to speak, until the day that these things come to pass, because you have not believed my words, which shall be fulfilled in their time.
B042C001V021	42	1	21	And the people waited for Zechariah, and wondered why he delayed so long in the temple.
B042C001V022	42	1	22	And when he came out, he could not speak to them: and they realized that he had seen a vision in the temple: for he beckoned to them, and remained speechless.
B042C001V023	42	1	23	And it came to pass, that, as soon as the days of his service were finished, he departed to his own house.
B042C001V024	42	1	24	And after those days his wife Elizabeth conceived, and hid herself five months, saying,
B042C001V025	42	1	25	Thus has the Lord dealt with me in the days when he looked on me, to take away my disgrace among men.
B042C001V026	42	1	26	And in the sixth month the angel Gabriel was sent from God to a city of Galilee, named Nazareth,
B042C001V027	42	1	27	To a virgin engaged to a man whose name was Joseph, of the house of David; and the virgin's name was Mary.
B042C001V028	42	1	28	And the angel came to her, and said, Hail, you who are highly favoured, the Lord is with you.
B042C001V029	42	1	29	And she was troubled at his words, and wondered what kind of greeting this might be.
B042C001V030	42	1	30	And the angel said to her, Fear not, Mary, for you have found favour with God.
B042C001V031	42	1	31	And behold, you shall conceive in your womb, and bring forth a son, and shall call his name JESUS.
B042C001V032	42	1	32	He shall be great, and shall be called the Son of the Most High: and the Lord God shall give to him the throne of his father David:
B042C001V033	42	1	33	And he shall reign over the house of Jacob forever; and of his kingdom there shall be no end.
B042C001V034	42	1	34	Then Mary said to the angel, How shall this be, since I am a virgin?
B042C001V035	42	1	35	And the angel answered her, The Holy Spirit shall come upon you, and the power of the Most High shall overshadow you: therefore the holy child to be born shall be called the Son of God.
B042C001V036	42	1	36	And, behold, your cousin Elizabeth has also conceived a son in her old age: and she who was called barren is in her sixth month.
B042C001V037	42	1	37	For with God nothing shall be impossible.
B042C001V038	42	1	38	And Mary said, Behold, I am the handmaid of the Lord; let it be to me according to your word. And the angel departed from her.
B042C001V039	42	1	39	And at that time Mary arose, and went into the hill country with haste, into a city of Judah;
B042C001V040	42	1	40	And entered into the house of Zechariah, and greeted Elizabeth.
B042C001V041	42	1	41	And it came to pass, that, when Elizabeth heard Mary's greeting, the baby leaped in her womb; and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit:
B042C001V042	42	1	42	And she spoke out with a loud voice, and said, Blessed are you among women, and blessed is the fruit of your womb.
B042C001V043	42	1	43	And why do I deserve to have the mother of my Lord come to me?
B042C001V044	42	1	44	For, lo, as soon as the voice of your greeting sounded in my ears, the baby leaped in my womb for joy.
B042C001V045	42	1	45	And blessed is she who believed that those things which were told her from the Lord would be fulfilled.
B042C001V046	42	1	46	And Mary said, My soul magnifies the Lord,
B042C001V047	42	1	47	And my spirit rejoices in God my Saviour.
B042C001V048	42	1	48	For he has looked upon the low estate of his handmaiden: for, behold, from henceforth all generations shall call me blessed.
B042C001V049	42	1	49	For he who is mighty has done great things for me; and holy is his name.
B042C001V050	42	1	50	And his mercy is on those who fear him from generation to generation.
B042C001V051	42	1	51	He has shown strength with his arm; he has scattered those who were proud in the imagination of their hearts.
B042C001V052	42	1	52	He has put down the mighty from their thrones, and exalted the humble.
B042C001V053	42	1	53	He has filled the hungry with good things; and the rich he has sent away empty.
B042C001V054	42	1	54	He has helped his servant Israel, in remembrance of his mercy;
B042C001V055	42	1	55	As he spoke to our fathers, to Abraham, and to his seed forever.
B042C001V056	42	1	56	And Mary remained with her about three months, and returned to her own house.
B042C001V057	42	1	57	Now the time came for Elizabeth to give birth; and she brought forth a son.
B042C001V058	42	1	58	And her neighbours and her cousins heard how the Lord had shown great mercy upon her; and they rejoiced with her.
B042C001V059	42	1	59	And it came to pass, that on the eighth day they came to circumcise the child; and they were going to call him Zechariah, after the name of his father.
B042C001V060	42	1	60	And his mother answered and said, No; he shall be called John.
B042C001V061	42	1	61	And they said to her, There is no one of your family who is called by this name.
B042C001V062	42	1	62	And they made signs to his father, what he would have him called.
B042C001V063	42	1	63	And he asked for a writing tablet, and wrote, His name is John. And they all marvelled.
B042C001V064	42	1	64	And his mouth was opened immediately, and his tongue loosed, and he spoke, and praised God.
B042C001V065	42	1	65	And fear came upon all who lived around them: and all these things were spoken of throughout all the hill country of Judaea.
B042C001V066	42	1	66	And all who heard them laid them up in their hearts, saying, What shall this child shall turn out to be! And the hand of the Lord was with him.
B042C001V067	42	1	67	And his father Zechariah was filled with the Holy Spirit, and prophesied, saying,
B042C001V068	42	1	68	Blessed is the Lord God of Israel; for he has visited and redeemed his people,
B042C001V069	42	1	69	And has raised up a horn of salvation for us in the house of his servant David;
B042C001V070	42	1	70	As he spoke by the mouths of his holy prophets, from long ago:
B042C001V071	42	1	71	That we would be saved from our enemies, and from the hand of all who hate us;
B042C001V072	42	1	72	To show the mercy promised to our fathers, and to remember his holy covenant;
B042C001V073	42	1	73	The oath which he swore to our father Abraham,
B042C001V074	42	1	74	That he would grant to us, that we, being delivered out of the hand of our enemies, might serve him without fear,
B042C001V075	42	1	75	In holiness and righteousness before him, all the days of our lives.
B042C001V076	42	1	76	And you, child, shall be called the prophet of the Most High: for you shall go before the face of the Lord to prepare his ways;
B042C001V077	42	1	77	To give to his people the knowledge of salvation by the forgiveness of their sins;
B042C001V078	42	1	78	Through the tender mercy of our God, the sunrise from on high will visit us,
B042C001V079	42	1	79	To give light to those who sit in darkness and in the shadow of death, to guide our feet into the way of peace.
B042C001V080	42	1	80	And the child grew, and grew strong in spirit, and lived in the deserts until the day of his public appearance to Israel.
B042C002V001	42	2	1	And it came to pass in those days, that there went out a decree from Caesar Augustus, that all the world should be taxed.
B042C002V002	42	2	2	(This was the first census taken when Quirinius was governor of Syria.)
B042C002V003	42	2	3	And all went to be registered, every one into his own city.
B042C002V004	42	2	4	And Joseph also went up from Galilee, out of the city of Nazareth, into Judaea, to the city of David, which is called Bethlehem; (because he was of the house and lineage of David:)
B042C002V005	42	2	5	To be registered with Mary his espoused wife, who was with child.
B042C002V006	42	2	6	And so it was, that, while they were there, the time came for her to give birth.
B042C002V007	42	2	7	And she brought forth her firstborn son, and wrapped him in strips of cloth, and laid him in a manger; because there was no room for them in the inn.
B042C002V008	42	2	8	And in that same region there were shepherds in the field, keeping watch over their flock by night.
B042C002V009	42	2	9	And, lo, an angel of the Lord came upon them, and the glory of the Lord shone round about them: and they were very afraid.
B042C002V010	42	2	10	And the angel said to them, Fear not: for, behold, I bring you good news of great joy, which shall be for all people.
B042C002V011	42	2	11	For to you is born this day in the city of David a Saviour, who is Christ the Lord.
B042C002V012	42	2	12	And this shall be a sign to you; You shall find a baby wrapped in strips of cloth, lying in a manger.
B042C002V013	42	2	13	And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly host praising God, and saying,
B042C002V014	42	2	14	Glory to God in the highest, and on earth peace to men with whom he is pleased.
B042C002V015	42	2	15	And it came to pass, as the angels went away from them into heaven, the shepherds said to one another, Let us go straight to Bethlehem, and see this thing which has come to pass, which the Lord has made known to us.
B042C002V016	42	2	16	And they came with haste, and found Mary, and Joseph, and the baby lying in a manger.
B042C002V017	42	2	17	And when they had seen, they made known what was told them concerning this child.
B042C002V018	42	2	18	And all those who heard it wondered at those things which were told them by the shepherds.
B042C002V019	42	2	19	But Mary kept all these things, and pondered them in her heart.
B042C002V020	42	2	20	And the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all the things that they had heard and seen, just as it was told to them.
B042C002V021	42	2	21	And when eight days had passed, when he was to be circumcised, he was given the name JESUS, the name given him by the angel before he was conceived in the womb.
B042C002V022	42	2	22	And when the days of her purification according to the law of Moses were finished, they brought him to Jerusalem, to present him to the Lord;
B042C002V023	42	2	23	(As it is written in the law of the Lord, Every male that opens the womb shall be called holy to the Lord;)
B042C002V024	42	2	24	And to offer a sacrifice according to that which is said in the law of the Lord, A pair of turtledoves, or two young pigeons.
B042C002V025	42	2	25	And, behold, there was a man in Jerusalem, whose name was Simeon; and he was just and devout, waiting for the consolation of Israel: and the Holy Spirit was upon him.
B042C002V026	42	2	26	And it was revealed to him by the Holy Spirit, that he should not see death, before he had seen the Lord's Christ.
B042C002V027	42	2	27	And he came by the Spirit into the temple: and when the parents brought in the child Jesus, to do for him according to the custom of the law,
B042C002V028	42	2	28	He took him up in his arms, and blessed God, and said,
B042C002V029	42	2	29	Lord, now let your servant depart in peace, according to your word:
B042C002V030	42	2	30	For my eyes have seen your salvation,
B042C002V031	42	2	31	Which you have prepared in the presence of all people;
B042C002V032	42	2	32	A light of revelation for the Gentiles, and the glory of your people Israel.
B042C002V033	42	2	33	And his father and mother marvelled at those things which were spoken of him.
B042C002V034	42	2	34	And Simeon blessed them, and said to Mary his mother, Behold, this child is appointed to cause the fall and rising of many in Israel; and to be a sign which shall be spoken against;
B042C002V035	42	2	35	(Yea, a sword shall pierce through your own soul also,) that the thoughts of many hearts may be revealed.
B042C002V036	42	2	36	And there was Anna, a prophetess, the daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Asher: she was of a great age, and had lived with a husband seven years from her virginity;
B042C002V037	42	2	37	And she was a widow of about fourscore and four years, who did not depart from the temple, but served God with fasting and prayer night and day.
B042C002V038	42	2	38	And coming at that hour she also gave thanks to the Lord, and spoke of him to all those who looked for the redemption of Jerusalem.
B042C002V039	42	2	39	And when they had performed all things according to the law of the Lord, they returned to Galilee, to their own city of Nazareth.
B042C002V040	42	2	40	And the child grew, and became strong in spirit, filled with wisdom: and the grace of God was upon him.
B042C002V041	42	2	41	Now his parents went to Jerusalem every year at the feast of the passover.
B042C002V042	42	2	42	And when he was twelve years old, they went up to the feast, according to the custom.
B042C002V043	42	2	43	And after they had spent the full number of days, as they returned, the child Jesus stayed behind in Jerusalem; and his parents did not know.
B042C002V044	42	2	44	But supposing him to have been in their company, they went a day's journey; then they sought him among their relatives and acquaintances.
B042C002V045	42	2	45	And when they could not find him, they returned to Jerusalem, seeking him.
B042C002V046	42	2	46	And it came to pass, that after three days they found him in the temple, sitting in the midst of the teachers, both hearing them, and asking them questions.
B042C002V047	42	2	47	And all who heard him were astonished at his understanding and answers.
B042C002V048	42	2	48	And when they saw him, they were amazed: and his mother said to him, Son, why have you treated us this way? behold, your father and I have sought you anxiously.
B042C002V049	42	2	49	And he said to them, Why were you seeking me? did you not know that I must be about my Father's business?
B042C002V050	42	2	50	And they did not understand what he said to them.
B042C002V051	42	2	51	And he went down with them, to Nazareth, and was obedient to them: but his mother kept all these things in her heart.
B042C002V052	42	2	52	And Jesus increased in wisdom and stature, and in favour with God and man.
B042C003V001	42	3	1	Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, when Pontius Pilate was governor of Judaea, Herod tetrarch of Galilee, his brother Philip tetrarch of Ituraea and of the region of Trachonitis, and Lysanias tetrarch of Abilene,
B042C003V002	42	3	2	When Annas and Caiaphas were high priests, the word of God came to John the son of Zechariah in the wilderness.
B042C003V003	42	3	3	And he went into all the country about the Jordan, preaching a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins;
B042C003V004	42	3	4	As it is written in the book of the words of Isaiah the prophet, The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.
B042C003V005	42	3	5	Every valley shall be filled, and every mountain and hill shall be brought low; and the crooked shall be made straight, and the rough ways shall be made smooth;
B042C003V006	42	3	6	And all flesh shall see the salvation of God.
B042C003V007	42	3	7	Then he said to the multitude that came forth to be baptized by him, O generation of vipers, who warned you to flee from the wrath to come?
B042C003V008	42	3	8	Bring forth fruit worthy of repentance, and do not begin to say to yourselves, We have Abraham as our father: for I say to you that God is able to raise up children for Abraham from these stones.
B042C003V009	42	3	9	Even now the axe is laid at the root of the trees: every tree that does not bring forth good fruit is cut down, and cast into the fire.
B042C003V010	42	3	10	And the people asked him, What shall we do then?
B042C003V011	42	3	11	He answered and said to them, He who has two coats, let him share with him who has none; and he who has food, let him do likewise.
B042C003V012	42	3	12	Then tax gatherers also came to be baptized, and said to him, Teacher, what shall we do?
B042C003V013	42	3	13	And he said to them, Collect no more than you have been ordered to.
B042C003V014	42	3	14	And the soldiers likewise questioned him, saying, And what shall we do? And he said to them, Do not extort money from anyone or accuse anyone falsely; and be content with your wages.
B042C003V015	42	3	15	And as the people were expectant, and wondering in their hearts if John was the Christ,
B042C003V016	42	3	16	John answered, saying to them all, I indeed baptize you with water; but one mightier than I comes, the thongs of whose sandals I am not worthy to untie: he shall baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire:
B042C003V017	42	3	17	Whose winnowing fork is in his hand, and he will thoroughly clear his threshing floor, and will gather the wheat into his barn; but the chaff he will burn with unquenchable fire.
B042C003V018	42	3	18	And in his exhortation he preached many other things to the people.
B042C003V019	42	3	19	But Herod the tetrarch, having been reproved by him because of Herodias, his brother Philip's wife, and because of all the evils which Herod had done,
B042C003V020	42	3	20	Added this to them all: he shut John up in prison.
B042C003V021	42	3	21	Now when all the people were baptized, it came to pass, that Jesus also was baptized, and as he was praying, heaven was opened,
B042C003V022	42	3	22	And the Holy Spirit descended in a bodily shape like a dove upon him, and a voice came from heaven, which said, You are my beloved Son; in you I am well pleased.
B042C003V023	42	3	23	And Jesus was about thirty years of age when he began his work, being (as was supposed) the son of Joseph, who was the son of Heli,
B042C003V024	42	3	24	The son of Matthat, the son of Levi, the son of Melchi, the son of Jannai, the son of Joseph,
B042C003V025	42	3	25	The son of Mattathiah, the son of Amos, the son of Nahum, the son of Esli, the son of Naggai,
B042C003V026	42	3	26	The son of Maath, the son of Mattathiah, the son of Semein, the son of Josech, the son of Joda,
B042C003V027	42	3	27	The son of Johanan, the son of Rhesa, the son of Zerubbabel, the son of Shealtiel, the son of Neri,
B042C003V028	42	3	28	The son of Melchi, the son of Addi, the son of Cosam, the son of Elmadam, the son of Er,
B042C003V029	42	3	29	The son of Joshua, the son of Eliezer, the son of Jorim, the son of Matthat, the son of Levi,
B042C003V030	42	3	30	The son of Symeon, the son of Judah, the son of Joseph, the son of Jonam, the son of Eliakim,
B042C003V031	42	3	31	The son of Melea, the son of Menna, the son of Mattatha, the son of Nathan, the son of David,
B042C003V032	42	3	32	The son of Jesse, the son of Obed, the son of Boaz, the son of Salmon, the son of Nahshon,
B042C003V033	42	3	33	The son of Amminadab, the son of Arni, the son of Hezron, the son of Perez, the son of Judah,
B042C003V034	42	3	34	The son of Jacob, the son of Isaac, the son of Abraham, the son of Terah, the son of Nahor,
B042C003V035	42	3	35	The son of Serug, the son of Reu, the son of Peleg, the son of Eber, the son of Shelah,
