B042C004V001	42	4	1	And Jesus, being full of the Holy Spirit, returned from the Jordan and was led by the Spirit in the wilderness,
B042C004V002	42	4	2	For forty days, while tempted by the devil. And during those days he ate nothing: and when they had ended, he was hungry.
B042C004V003	42	4	3	And the devil said to him, If you are the Son of God, command this stone to become bread.
B042C004V004	42	4	4	And Jesus answered him, It is written, Man shall not live on bread alone.
B042C004V005	42	4	5	And the devil, taking him up to a high mountain, showed him all the kingdoms of the world in a moment of time.
B042C004V006	42	4	6	And the devil said to him, I will give you all this power and its glory: for it has been delivered to me; and I give it to whomever I will.
