B042C004V011	42	4	11	And in their hands they shall bear you up, lest you strike your foot against a stone.
B042C004V012	42	4	12	And Jesus answered and said to him, It is said, You shall not tempt the Lord your God.
B042C004V013	42	4	13	And when the devil had ended all the temptation, he departed from him until an opportune time.
B042C004V014	42	4	14	And Jesus returned in the power of the Spirit to Galilee: and news about him went out to all the surrounding region.
B042C004V015	42	4	15	And he taught in their synagogues, and was praised by all.
B042C004V016	42	4	16	And he came to Nazareth, where he had been brought up: and, as was his custom, he went into the synagogue on the sabbath day, and stood up to read.
B042C004V017	42	4	17	And there was given to him the book of the prophet Isaiah. And when he had opened the book, he found the place where it was written,
B042C004V018	42	4	18	The Spirit of the Lord is upon me, because he has anointed me to preach the gospel to the poor; he has sent me to heal the brokenhearted, to preach deliverance to the captives, and recovery of sight to the blind, to set at liberty those who are oppressed,
B042C004V019	42	4	19	To preach the year of the Lord's favour.
B042C004V020	42	4	20	And he closed the book, and he gave it again to the attendant, and sat down. And the eyes of all those who were in the synagogue were fastened upon him.
B042C004V021	42	4	21	And he said to them, Today is this scripture fulfilled in your hearing.
B042C004V022	42	4	22	And all spoke well of him, and wondered at the gracious words which proceeded out of his mouth. And they said, Is this not Joseph's son?
B042C004V023	42	4	23	And he said to them, You will surely quote to me this proverb, Physician, heal yourself: whatever we have heard you did in Capernaum, do here in your home town as well.
B042C004V024	42	4	24	And he said, Truly I say to you, No prophet is accepted in his own home town.
B042C004V025	42	4	25	But I tell you a truth, there were many widows in Israel in the days of Elijah, when the sky was shut up three years and six months, when there was great famine throughout all the land;
B042C004V026	42	4	26	But Elijah was sent to none of them, but only to Sarepta, in the land of Sidon, to a woman who was a widow.
B042C004V027	42	4	27	And there were many lepers in Israel in the time of Elisha the prophet; and none of them was cleansed, only Naaman the Syrian.
B042C004V028	42	4	28	And all in the synagogue, when they heard these things, were filled with anger,
B042C004V029	42	4	29	And rose up, and drove him out of the city, and led him to the brow of the hill on which their city was built, that they might cast him down the cliff.
B042C004V030	42	4	30	But he passed through the midst of them and went his way,
B042C004V031	42	4	31	And came down to Capernaum, a city of Galilee, and taught them on the sabbath days.
B042C004V032	42	4	32	And they were astonished at his teaching: for his word was with power.
B042C004V033	42	4	33	And in the synagogue there was a man, who had a spirit of an unclean devil, and he cried out with a loud voice,
B042C004V034	42	4	34	Saying, Let us alone; what have we to do with you, Jesus of Nazareth? have you come to destroy us? I know you who you are; the Holy One of God.
B042C004V035	42	4	35	And Jesus rebuked him, saying, Hold your peace, and come out of him. And when the devil had thrown him down in their midst, he came out of him, without doing him any harm.
B042C004V036	42	4	36	And they were all amazed, and spoke among themselves, saying, What word is this? for with authority and power he commands the unclean spirits, and they come out.
