B042C006V022	42	6	22	Blessed are you, when men hate you, and when they exclude you, and insult you, and cast out your name as evil, for the Son of man's sake.
B042C006V023	42	6	23	Rejoice in that day, and leap for joy: for, behold, your reward in heaven is great: for their fathers did the same to the prophets.
B042C006V024	42	6	24	But woe to you who are rich! for you have received your comfort.
B042C006V025	42	6	25	Woe to you who are full! for you shall hunger. Woe to you who laugh now! for you shall mourn and weep.
B042C006V026	42	6	26	Woe to you, when all men speak well of you! for so their fathers did to the false prophets.
B042C006V027	42	6	27	But I say to you who hear, Love your enemies, do good to those who hate you,
B042C006V028	42	6	28	Bless those who curse you, and pray for those who abuse you.
B042C006V029	42	6	29	And to him who strikes you on the cheek, offer him the other also; and from him who takes away your coat do not withhold your shirt either.
B042C006V030	42	6	30	Give to every man who asks of you; and from him who takes away what is yours, do not ask for it back.
B042C006V031	42	6	31	And as you would have men do to you, do the same to them.
B042C006V032	42	6	32	For if you love those who love you, what credit is that to you? for sinners also love those who love them.
B042C006V033	42	6	33	And if you do good to those who do good to you, what credit is that to you? for sinners also do the same.
B042C006V034	42	6	34	And if you lend to those from whom you hope to receive, what credit is that to you? for sinners also lend to sinners to receive repayment.
B042C006V035	42	6	35	But love your enemies, and do good, and lend, expecting nothing back; and your reward shall be great, and you shall be the children of the Most High: for he is kind to the unthankful and to the evil.
B042C006V036	42	6	36	Be merciful, as your Father also is merciful.
B042C006V037	42	6	37	Do not judge, and you shall not be judged: do not condemn, and you shall not be condemned: forgive, and you shall be forgiven:
B042C006V038	42	6	38	Give, and it shall be given to you; a good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over, shall men put in your lap. For the measure you give to others shall be the same measure given back to you.
B042C006V039	42	6	39	And he spoke a parable to them, Can the blind lead the blind? shall they not both fall into the ditch?
