B042C006V048	42	6	48	He is like a man who built a house, and dug deep, and laid the foundation on a rock: and when the flood arose, the river beat violently upon that house, but could not shake it: for it was founded upon a rock.
B042C006V049	42	6	49	But he who hears, and does not obey, is like a man who built a house upon the ground without a foundation; and the river beat violently against it, and immediately it fell; and the ruin of that house was great.
B042C007V001	42	7	1	Now when he finished saying all this in the hearing of the people, he entered Capernaum.
