B042C007V045	42	7	45	You gave me no kiss: but since I came in this woman has not ceased to kiss my feet.
B042C007V046	42	7	46	You did not anoint my head with oil: but this woman has anointed my feet with perfume.
B042C007V047	42	7	47	Therefore I say to you, Her sins, which are many, are forgiven; for she loved much: but he who is forgiven little, loves little.
B042C007V048	42	7	48	And he said to her, Your sins are forgiven.
B042C007V049	42	7	49	And those who reclined at table with him began to say among themselves, Who is this who even forgives sins?
B042C007V050	42	7	50	And he said to the woman, Your faith has saved you; go in peace.
B042C008V001	42	8	1	And it came to pass soon after, that he went through cities and villages, preaching and bringing the glad news of the kingdom of God. And the twelve were with him,
B042C008V002	42	8	2	Along with certain women who had been healed of evil spirits and infirmities: Mary of Magdala, out of whom seven devils had gone out,
B042C008V003	42	8	3	And Joanna, the wife of Chuza, Herod's steward, and Susanna, and many others, who helped support them out of their own means.
B042C008V004	42	8	4	And when many people were gathered together, and came to him from town after town, he spoke in a parable:
B042C008V005	42	8	5	A sower went out to sow his seed: and as he sowed, some fell by the wayside; and it was trodden down, and the birds of the air devoured it.
B042C008V006	42	8	6	And some fell upon the rock; and as soon as it had sprung up, it withered away, because it lacked moisture.
B042C008V007	42	8	7	And some fell among thorns; and the thorns sprang up with it, and choked it.
B042C008V008	42	8	8	And other fell on good ground, and sprang up, and bore a crop a hundred times as great. And when he said these things, he called out, He who has ears to hear, let him hear.
B042C008V009	42	8	9	And his disciples asked him, What does this parable mean?
B042C008V010	42	8	10	And he said, To you it is given to know the mysteries of the kingdom of God: but to others it is in parables; that seeing they might not see, and hearing they might not understand.
B042C008V011	42	8	11	Now the meaning of the parable is this: The seed is the word of God.
B042C008V012	42	8	12	Those by the wayside are the ones who hear; then the devil comes, and takes the word from their hearts, lest they should believe and be saved.
B042C008V013	42	8	13	Those on the rock are the ones, who, when they hear, receive the word with joy; but they have no root; they believe for a while, but in time of temptation fall away.
B042C008V014	42	8	14	And the seed which fell among thorns are those, who, when they have heard, go forth, and are choked by the cares and riches and pleasures of this life, and bring no fruit to maturity.
B042C008V015	42	8	15	But the seed on the good ground are those, who in an honest and good heart, having heard the word, keep it, and bring forth fruit with patience.
B042C008V016	42	8	16	No man, when he has lighted a lamp, covers it with a container, or puts it under a bed; but sets it on a stand, that those who enter may see the light.
B042C008V017	42	8	17	For nothing is hidden, that shall not be disclosed; nor anything secret, that shall not be made known and come into the open.
B042C008V018	42	8	18	Therefore, take heed how you listen: for whoever has, to him shall be given; and whoever has not, from him shall be taken even that which he seems to have.
B042C008V019	42	8	19	Then his mother and brothers came to him, and could not reach him because of the crowd.
B042C008V020	42	8	20	And he was told, Your mother and brothers are standing outside, wanting to see you.
B042C008V021	42	8	21	And he answered and said to them, My mother and my brothers are those who hear the word of God, and do it.
B042C008V022	42	8	22	Now it came to pass on a certain day, that he got into a boat with his disciples: and he said to them, Let us go over to the other side of the lake. And they launched forth.
B042C008V023	42	8	23	But as they sailed he fell asleep: and a storm of wind came down upon the lake; and they were filling with water, and were in danger.
B042C008V024	42	8	24	And they came to him, and woke him, saying, Master, Master, we are perishing. Then he arose, and rebuked the wind and the raging of the water: and they ceased, and there was a calm.
B042C008V025	42	8	25	And he said to them, Where is your faith? And they were afraid and amazed, saying to one another, Who is this! for he commands even the winds and water, and they obey him.
B042C008V026	42	8	26	And they arrived at the country of the Gerasenes, which is across from Galilee.
B042C008V027	42	8	27	And when he stepped onto the land, he was met by a man from the city, who had devils, and for a long time had worn no clothes, nor did he live in a house, but in the tombs.
B042C008V028	42	8	28	When he saw Jesus, he cried out, and fell down before him, and with a loud voice said, What have I to do with you, Jesus, Son of God most high? I beg you, do not torment me.
B042C008V029	42	8	29	(For he had commanded the unclean spirit to come out of the man. For often it had seized him: and though he was kept under guard, bound with chains and in fetters; he would break the bonds and be driven by the devil into the desert.)
B042C008V030	42	8	30	And Jesus asked him, saying, What is your name? And he said, Legion: because many devils had entered into him.
B042C008V031	42	8	31	And they begged him that he would not command them to go out into the abyss.
B042C008V032	42	8	32	Now there was a herd of many swine feeding there on the mountain: and they begged him to let them enter these. And he gave them permission.
B042C008V033	42	8	33	Then the devils went out of the man, and entered into the swine: and the herd ran violently down a steep place into the lake, and were drowned.
B042C008V034	42	8	34	When those who fed them saw what had happened, they fled, and went and told it in the city and in the country.
B042C008V035	42	8	35	Then they went out to see what had happened, and came to Jesus, and found the man from whom the devils had gone out sitting at the feet of Jesus, clothed, and in his right mind: and they were afraid.
B042C008V036	42	8	36	Those who saw it happen told them how he who was possessed by the devils was healed.
B042C008V037	42	8	37	Then all the people from the region of the Gerasenes begged him to depart from them; for they were taken with great fear: and he got into the boat, and returned.
B042C008V038	42	8	38	Now the man out of whom the devils had gone begged to be with him: but Jesus sent him away, saying,
B042C008V039	42	8	39	Return to your own house, and describe what great things God has done for you. And he went his way, and proclaimed throughout the whole city what great things Jesus had done for him.
B042C008V040	42	8	40	And it came to pass, that when Jesus returned, the people welcomed him: for they were all waiting for him.
B042C008V041	42	8	41	And, behold, there came a man named Jairus, a ruler of the synagogue: and he fell down at Jesus' feet, and begged him to come to his house:
B042C008V042	42	8	42	For he had only one daughter, about twelve years old, and she lay dying. But as he went the people crowded around him.
B042C008V043	42	8	43	And a woman who had a flow of blood for twelve years, and could not be healed by anyone,
B042C008V044	42	8	44	Came up behind him, and touched the edge of his garment: and immediately the flow of blood stopped.
B042C008V045	42	8	45	And Jesus said, Who touched me? When they all denied it, Peter said, Master, the multitudes crowd and press around you.
B042C008V046	42	8	46	And Jesus said, Somebody has touched me: for I know that power has gone out of me.
B042C008V047	42	8	47	And when the woman saw that she had not escaped notice, she came trembling, fell down before him, and told him before all the people why she had touched him, and how she was immediately healed.
B042C008V048	42	8	48	And he said to her, Daughter, your faith has made you well; go in peace.
B042C008V049	42	8	49	While he was speaking, a man came from the ruler of the synagogue's house, and said to him, Your daughter is dead; do not trouble the Teacher further.
B042C008V050	42	8	50	But when Jesus heard this, he said, Do not fear: only believe, and she shall be made well.
B042C008V051	42	8	51	And when he came into the house, he allowed no one to go in, except Peter, and James, and John, and the father and mother of the girl.
B042C008V052	42	8	52	And all wept, and bewailed her: but he said, Do not weep; she is not dead, but sleeps.
B042C008V053	42	8	53	And they laughed him to scorn, knowing that she was dead.
B042C008V054	42	8	54	And he put them all out, and took her by the hand, and called, saying, Child, arise.
B042C008V055	42	8	55	And her spirit returned, and she arose immediately: and he commanded that she be given food.
B042C008V056	42	8	56	And her parents were astonished: but he directed them to tell no one what had happened.
B042C009V001	42	9	1	Then he called the twelve together, and gave them power and authority over all devils, and to cure diseases.
B042C009V002	42	9	2	And he sent them to preach the kingdom of God, and to heal the sick.
B042C009V003	42	9	3	And he said to them, Take nothing for your journey, no staff, no bag, no bread, no money; not even an extra tunic.
B042C009V004	42	9	4	And whatever house you enter, stay there until you leave the town.
B042C009V005	42	9	5	And whoever will not receive you, when you go out of that town, shake off the dust from your feet as a testimony against them.
B042C009V006	42	9	6	And they departed, and went through the towns, preaching the gospel, and healing everywhere.
B042C009V007	42	9	7	Now Herod the tetrarch heard of all that was happening: and he was perplexed, because it was said by some that John had been raised from the dead;
B042C009V008	42	9	8	And by some, that Elijah had appeared; and by others, that one of the old prophets had risen again.
B042C009V009	42	9	9	And Herod said, I beheaded John: but who is this of whom I hear such things? And he desired to see him.
B042C009V010	42	9	10	And the apostles, when they returned, told him all that they had done. And he took them, and went aside privately into the city of Bethsaida.
B042C009V011	42	9	11	And the people, when they learned of it, followed him: and he received them, and spoke to them of the kingdom of God, and healed those who needed healing.
B042C009V012	42	9	12	And when the day began to wear away, the twelve came, and said to him, Send the crowd away, that they may go into the towns and country round about, and find lodging and food: for we are here in a remote place.
B042C009V013	42	9	13	But he said to them, You give them something to eat. And they said, We have no more than five loaves and two fish; unless we go and buy food for all these people.
B042C009V014	42	9	14	For there were about five thousand men. And he said to his disciples, Make them sit down in groups of about fifty each.
B042C009V015	42	9	15	And they did so, and made them all sit down.
B042C009V016	42	9	16	Then he took the five loaves and the two fish, and looking up to heaven, he blessed them, and broke them, and gave them to the disciples to set before the multitude.
B042C009V017	42	9	17	And they ate, and were all filled: and they picked up twelve baskets of broken pieces that remained.
B042C009V018	42	9	18	And it came to pass, as he was alone praying, his disciples were with him: and he asked them, Who do the people say that I am?
B042C009V019	42	9	19	They answered, John the Baptist; but some say, Elijah; and others say that one of the old prophets has risen again.
B042C009V020	42	9	20	He said to them, But who do you say that I am? Peter answered, The Christ of God.
B042C009V021	42	9	21	And he strictly warned them, and commanded them not to tell this to anyone;
B042C009V022	42	9	22	Saying, The Son of man must suffer many things, and be rejected by the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be slain, and be raised on the third day.
B042C009V023	42	9	23	And he said to them all, If anyone will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross daily, and follow me.
B042C009V024	42	9	24	For whoever will save his life shall lose it: but whoever will lose his life for my sake, he shall save it.
B042C009V025	42	9	25	For what advantage is there for a man if he gains the whole world, and loses or forfeits himself?
B042C009V026	42	9	26	For whoever shall be ashamed of me and of my words, of him shall the Son of man be ashamed, when he shall come in his glory, and the glory of his Father, and of the holy angels.
B042C009V027	42	9	27	But I tell you truly, there are some standing here who shall not taste death until they see the kingdom of God.
B042C009V028	42	9	28	And it came to pass about eight days after these teachings, he took Peter and John and James, and went up on a mountain to pray.
B042C009V029	42	9	29	And as he prayed, the appearance of his face was altered, and his clothing became dazzling white.
B042C009V030	42	9	30	And, behold, two men were talking with him, Moses and Elijah:
B042C009V031	42	9	31	Who appeared in glory, and spoke of his departure, which he would accomplish at Jerusalem.
B042C009V032	42	9	32	But Peter and those who were with him were heavy with sleep: but when they were fully awake, they saw his glory, and the two men who stood with him.
B042C009V033	42	9	33	And it came to pass, as the two men departed from him, Peter said to Jesus, Master, it is good for us to be here: let us make three shelters; one for you, and one for Moses, and one for Elijah: but he did not know what he was saying.
B042C009V034	42	9	34	While he spoke, a cloud came and enveloped them: and they were afraid as they entered the cloud.
B042C009V035	42	9	35	And a voice came out of the cloud, saying, This is my Son, my Chosen: hear him.
B042C009V036	42	9	36	And when the voice had spoken, they found Jesus was alone. And they kept quiet, and told no one in those days any of those things which they had seen.
B042C009V037	42	9	37	And it came to pass, that on the next day, when they had come down from the hill, many people met him.
B042C009V038	42	9	38	And, behold, a man of the crowd cried out, saying, Teacher, I beg you, look upon my son: for he is my only child.
B042C009V039	42	9	39	And, lo, a spirit takes him, and he suddenly cries out; and it convulses him until he foams at the mouth, and it mauls him and hardly ever leaves him.
B042C009V040	42	9	40	And I begged your disciples to cast it out; but they could not.
B042C009V041	42	9	41	And Jesus answered, O faithless and perverse generation, how long shall I be with you, and endure you? Bring your son here.
B042C009V042	42	9	42	And as he was coming, the devil threw him down, and violently convulsed him. And Jesus rebuked the unclean spirit, and healed the child, and gave him back to his father.
B042C009V043	42	9	43	And they were all amazed at the mighty power of God. But while they were all marvelling at everything Jesus did, he said to his disciples,
B042C009V044	42	9	44	Let these words sink down into your ears: the Son of man shall be delivered into the hands of men.
B042C009V045	42	9	45	But they did not understand this statement, and it was hidden from them, so they did not understand it: and they were afraid to ask him about it.
B042C009V046	42	9	46	Then there arose a dispute among them about which of them was the greatest.
B042C009V047	42	9	47	And Jesus, perceiving what they were thinking in their hearts, took a child, and put him beside him,
B042C009V048	42	9	48	And said to them, Whoever shall receive this child in my name receives me: and whoever shall receive me receives him who sent me: for he who is least among you, that one shall be great.
B042C009V049	42	9	49	And John answered, Master, we saw someone casting out devils in your name; and we forbade him, because he does not follow along with us.
B042C009V050	42	9	50	And Jesus said to him, Do not forbid him: for he who is not against you is for you.
B042C009V051	42	9	51	And it came to pass, when the time had come for him to be taken up, he resolutely set his face to go to Jerusalem,
B042C009V052	42	9	52	And sent messengers ahead of him: and they went, and entered into a village of the Samaritans, to make ready for him.
B042C009V053	42	9	53	But they did not receive him, because his face was set to go to Jerusalem.
B042C009V054	42	9	54	And when his disciples James and John saw this, they said, Lord, do you want us to command fire to come down from heaven, and consume them?
B042C009V055	42	9	55	But he turned, and rebuked them,
B042C009V056	42	9	56	And they went to another village.
B042C009V057	42	9	57	And it came to pass, that, as they went along the way, a man said to him, Lord, I will follow you wherever you go.
B042C009V058	42	9	58	And Jesus said to him, Foxes have holes, and birds of the air have nests; but the Son of man has nowhere to lay his head.
B042C009V059	42	9	59	And he said to another, Follow me. But he said, Lord, allow me first to go and bury my father.
B042C009V060	42	9	60	Jesus said to him, Let the dead bury their own dead: but you go and preach the kingdom of God.
B042C009V061	42	9	61	And another said, Lord, I will follow you; but let me first go bid farewell to those who are at my home.
B042C009V062	42	9	62	And Jesus said to him, No man, having put his hand to the plough, and looking back, is fit for the kingdom of God.
B042C010V001	42	10	1	After these things the Lord appointed seventy others also, and sent them out two by two before him into every town and place where he would go.
B042C010V002	42	10	2	And he said to them, The harvest truly is great, but the labourers are few: therefore pray to the Lord of the harvest, that he would send forth labourers into his harvest.
B042C010V003	42	10	3	Go your ways: behold, I send you forth as lambs among wolves.
B042C010V004	42	10	4	Carry neither purse, nor bag, nor sandals: and greet no man along the way.
B042C010V005	42	10	5	And into whatever house you enter, first say, Peace be to this house.
B042C010V006	42	10	6	And if a son of peace is there, your peace shall rest upon him: if not, it shall turn to you.
B042C010V007	42	10	7	Remain in the same house, eating and drinking such things as they give: for the labourer is worthy of his wages. Do not go from house to house.
B042C010V008	42	10	8	And into whatever town you enter, and they receive you, eat such things as are set before you:
B042C010V009	42	10	9	And heal the sick who are in it, and say to them, The kingdom of God has come near to you.
B042C010V010	42	10	10	But into whatever town you enter, and they do not receive you, go out into its streets and say,
B042C010V011	42	10	11	Even the very dust of your town, which clings to us, we wipe off against you: nevertheless, be sure of this, that the kingdom of God has come near to you.
B042C010V012	42	10	12	I say to you, that it shall be more tolerable in that day for Sodom, than for that town.
B042C010V013	42	10	13	Woe to you, Chorazin! woe to you, Bethsaida! for if the mighty works done in you had been done in Tyre and Sidon, they would have repented long ago, sitting in sackcloth and ashes.
B042C010V014	42	10	14	But it shall be more tolerable for Tyre and Sidon at the judgment, than for you.
B042C010V015	42	10	15	And you, Capernaum, will not be exalted to heaven; you shall be thrust down to Hades.
B042C010V016	42	10	16	He who hears you hears me; and he who despises you despises me; and he who despises me despises him who sent me.
B042C010V017	42	10	17	And the seventy returned with joy, saying, Lord, even the devils are subject to us through your name.
B042C010V018	42	10	18	And he said to them, I beheld Satan fall like lightning from heaven.
B042C010V019	42	10	19	Behold, I give to you power to tread on serpents and scorpions, and over all the power of the enemy: and nothing shall by any means hurt you.
B042C010V020	42	10	20	Nevertheless, do not rejoice in this, that the spirits are subject to you; but rather rejoice because your names are written in heaven.
B042C010V021	42	10	21	In that hour Jesus rejoiced in the Holy Spirit, and said, I thank you, O Father, Lord of heaven and earth, that you have hidden these things from the wise and prudent, and have revealed them to babes: yea, Father; for so it seemed good in your sight.
B042C010V022	42	10	22	All things have been given to me by my Father: and no man knows who the Son is, but the Father; and who the Father is, but the Son, and he to whom the Son chooses to reveal him.
B042C010V023	42	10	23	And he turned to his disciples, and said privately, Blessed are the eyes which see the things that you see:
B042C010V024	42	10	24	For I tell you, that many prophets and kings desired to see those things which you see, and have not seen them; and to hear those things which you hear, and have not heard them.
B042C010V025	42	10	25	And, behold, a certain lawyer stood up, and tested him, saying, Teacher, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?
B042C010V026	42	10	26	He said to him, What is written in the law? how do you read it?
B042C010V027	42	10	27	And he answered, You shall love the Lord your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your strength, and with all your mind; and your neighbour as yourself.
B042C010V028	42	10	28	And he said to him, You have answered right: do this, and you shall live.
B042C010V029	42	10	29	But he, desiring to justify himself, said to Jesus, And who is my neighbour?
B042C010V030	42	10	30	And Jesus answered, A certain man went down from Jerusalem to Jericho, and fell among robbers, who stripped him of his clothing, and wounded him, and departed, leaving him half dead.
B042C010V031	42	10	31	And by chance a certain priest came down that way: and when he saw him, he passed by on the other side.
B042C010V032	42	10	32	And likewise a Levite, when he came to that place and saw him, passed by on the other side.
B042C010V033	42	10	33	But a certain Samaritan, as he traveled, came where he was: and when he saw him, he had compassion on him,
B042C010V034	42	10	34	And went to him, and bound up his wounds, pouring on oil and wine, and set him on his own beast, and brought him to an inn, and took care of him.
B042C010V035	42	10	35	And on the next day, when he departed, he took out two denarii, and gave them to the innkeeper, and said to him, Take care of him; and whatever more you spend, when I come again, I will repay you.
