B042C010V037	42	10	37	And he said, He who showed mercy on him. Then Jesus said to him, Go, and do likewise.
B042C010V038	42	10	38	Now it came to pass, as they went, that he entered into a certain village: and a woman named Martha received him into her house.
B042C010V039	42	10	39	And she had a sister named Mary, who sat at Jesus' feet, and heard his words.
B042C010V040	42	10	40	But Martha was distracted by many tasks, and came to him, and said, Lord, do you not care that my sister has left me to serve alone? then tell her to help me.
B042C010V041	42	10	41	And Jesus answered her, Martha, Martha, you are worried and troubled about many things:
B042C010V042	42	10	42	But only one thing is necessary: and Mary has chosen the good part, which shall not be taken away from her.
B042C011V001	42	11	1	And it came to pass, that, as he was praying in a certain place, when he ceased, one of his disciples said to him, Lord, teach us to pray, as John also taught his disciples.
B042C011V002	42	11	2	And he said to them, when you pray, say, Father, Hallowed be your name. Your kingdom come.
B042C011V003	42	11	3	Give us day by day our daily bread.
B042C011V004	42	11	4	And forgive our sins; for we also forgive everyone who is indebted to us. And lead us not into temptation.
B042C011V005	42	11	5	And he said to them, Suppose you have a friend and go to him at midnight, and say to him, Friend, lend me three loaves;
B042C011V006	42	11	6	For a friend of mine on a journey has come to me, and I have nothing to set before him.
B042C011V007	42	11	7	And from within he shall answer and say, Do not trouble me: the door is now shut, and my children are with me in bed; I cannot rise and give you anything.
B042C011V008	42	11	8	I say to you, Though he will not rise and give him anything because he is his friend, yet because of his persistence he will rise and give him as much as he needs.
B042C011V009	42	11	9	And I say to you, Ask, and it shall be given to you; seek, and you shall find; knock, and it shall be opened to you.
B042C011V010	42	11	10	For every one who asks receives; and he who seeks finds; and to him who knocks it shall be opened.
B042C011V011	42	11	11	Which of you fathers, if your son asks for a fish, will give him a serpent?
B042C011V012	42	11	12	Or if he asks for an egg, will offer him a scorpion?
B042C011V013	42	11	13	If you then, being evil, know how to give good gifts to your children: how much more shall your heavenly Father give the Holy Spirit to those who ask him?
B042C011V014	42	11	14	And he was casting out a devil that was dumb. And it came to pass, when the devil had gone out, the dumb man spoke; and the crowd was amazed.
B042C011V015	42	11	15	But some of them said, He casts out devils by Beelzebub, the chief of the devils.
B042C011V016	42	11	16	And others, tempting him, sought from him a sign from heaven.
B042C011V017	42	11	17	But he, knowing their thoughts, said to them, Every kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation; and a house divided against itself falls.
B042C011V018	42	11	18	If Satan is divided against himself, how shall his kingdom stand? for you say that I cast out devils through Beelzebub.
B042C011V019	42	11	19	And if I cast out devils by Beelzebub, by whom do your sons cast them out? therefore they shall be your judges.
B042C011V020	42	11	20	But if I cast out devils by the finger of God, then the kingdom of God has come upon you.
B042C011V021	42	11	21	When a strong man, fully armed, guards his house, his goods are safe:
B042C011V022	42	11	22	But when one stronger than he shall come upon him, and overcome him, he takes from him all his armour in which he trusted, and divides the spoils.
B042C011V023	42	11	23	He who is not with me is against me: and he who does not gather with me scatters.
B042C011V024	42	11	24	When an unclean spirit has gone out of a man, it passes through dry places, seeking rest; and finding none, he says, I will return to my house from which I came.
B042C011V025	42	11	25	And when it comes, it finds it swept and in order.
B042C011V026	42	11	26	Then it goes, and brings seven other spirits more wicked than itself; and they enter in, and live there: and the last state of that man is worse than the first.
B042C011V027	42	11	27	And it came to pass, as he spoke these things, a certain woman in the crowd lifted up her voice, and said to him, Blessed is the womb that bore you, and the breasts which you sucked.
B042C011V028	42	11	28	But he said, Rather, blessed are those who hear the word of God, and keep it.
B042C011V029	42	11	29	And when the people were gathered thick together, he began to say, This is an evil generation: it seeks a sign; and no sign shall be given it, but the sign of Jonah the prophet.
B042C011V030	42	11	30	For as Jonah became a sign to the Ninevites, so shall the Son of man be to this generation.
B042C011V031	42	11	31	The queen of the south shall rise up in the judgment with the men of this generation, and condemn them: for she came from the ends of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon; and, behold, one greater than Solomon is here.
B042C011V032	42	11	32	The men of Nineveh shall rise up in the judgment with this generation, and shall condemn it: for they repented at the preaching of Jonah; and, behold, one greater than Jonah is here.
B042C011V033	42	11	33	No man, after lighting a lamp, puts it in a cellar, or under a bushel, but on a lampstand, that those who come in may see the light.
B042C011V034	42	11	34	The light of the body is the eye: therefore when your eye is good, your whole body also is full of light; but when your eye is bad, your body also is full of darkness.
B042C011V035	42	11	35	Take heed, then, that the light which is within you is not darkness.
B042C011V036	42	11	36	Therefore, if your whole body is full of light, having no dark part in it, it shall be fully illuminated, as when the bright shining of a lamp gives you light.
B042C011V037	42	11	37	And as he spoke, a certain Pharisee begged him to dine with him: and he went in, and reclined at the table.
B042C011V038	42	11	38	And the Pharisee was surprised when he saw that he had not first washed before dinner.
B042C011V039	42	11	39	And the Lord said to him, Now you Pharisees clean the outside of the cup and the platter; but inside you are full of greed and wickedness.
B042C011V040	42	11	40	You fools, did not he who made the outside also make the inside?
B042C011V041	42	11	41	But rather give what you have within as alms; and, behold, all things are clean for you.
B042C011V042	42	11	42	But woe to you, Pharisees! for you tithe mint and rue and all manner of herbs, but neglect justice and the love of God: these you ought to have done, and not left the others undone.
B042C011V043	42	11	43	Woe to you, Pharisees! for you love the best seats in the synagogues, and greetings in the marketplaces.
B042C011V044	42	11	44	Woe to you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for you are like unmarked graves, which men walk over unaware.
B042C011V045	42	11	45	Then one of the lawyers answered him, Teacher, by saying this you insult us also.
B042C011V046	42	11	46	And he said, Woe to you also, lawyers! for you load men with burdens they can hardly carry, and you yourselves will not touch the burdens with one of your fingers.
B042C011V047	42	11	47	Woe to you! for you build the tombs of the prophets, and your fathers killed them.
B042C011V048	42	11	48	Truly you bear witness that you approve of the deeds of your fathers: for they killed them, and you build their tombs.
B042C011V049	42	11	49	For this reason also the wisdom of God said, I will send them prophets and apostles, and some of them they shall kill and persecute,
B042C011V050	42	11	50	That the blood of all the prophets, which was shed from the foundation of the world, may be required of this generation;
B042C011V051	42	11	51	From the blood of Abel to the blood of Zechariah, who perished between the altar and the temple: truly I say to you, It shall be required of this generation.
B042C011V052	42	11	52	Woe to you, lawyers! for you have taken away the key of knowledge: you did not enter in yourselves, and those who were entering in you hindered.
B042C011V053	42	11	53	And as he left, the scribes and Pharisees began to be hostile, and to question him closely on many things:
B042C011V054	42	11	54	Lying in wait for him, and seeking to catch something out of his mouth, that they might accuse him.
B042C012V001	42	12	1	In the meantime, when a great crowd of people had gathered, so that they trod upon each other, he began to say first to his disciples, Beware of the leaven of the Pharisees, which is hypocrisy.
B042C012V002	42	12	2	For there is nothing covered, that shall not be revealed; nor hidden, that shall not be known.
B042C012V003	42	12	3	Therefore, whatever you have spoken in darkness shall be heard in the light; and that which you have spoken in the ear behind closed doors shall be proclaimed upon the housetops.
B042C012V004	42	12	4	And I say to you, my friends, Do not be afraid of those who kill the body, and after that have no more that they can do.
B042C012V005	42	12	5	But I will warn you whom to fear: Fear him, who after he has killed has power to cast into hell; yes, I say to you, Fear him.
B042C012V006	42	12	6	Are not five sparrows sold for twopence, and not one of them is forgotten before God?
B042C012V007	42	12	7	But even the very hairs of your head are all numbered. Therefore do not fear: you are of more value than many sparrows.
B042C012V008	42	12	8	And I say to you, Whoever shall confess me before men, him shall the Son of man also confess before the angels of God:
B042C012V009	42	12	9	But he who denies me before men shall be denied before the angels of God.
B042C012V010	42	12	10	And whoever shall speak a word against the Son of man, it shall be forgiven him: but he who blasphemes against the Holy Spirit shall not be forgiven.
B042C012V011	42	12	11	And when they bring you to the synagogues, and to magistrates, and authorities, take no thought of how you shall defend yourself, or what you shall say:
B042C012V012	42	12	12	For the Holy Spirit shall teach you in that very hour what you ought to say.
B042C012V013	42	12	13	And one of the company said to him, Teacher, tell my brother to divide the inheritance with me.
B042C012V014	42	12	14	And he said to him, Man, who made me a judge or a divider over you?
B042C012V015	42	12	15	And he said to them, Take heed, and beware of every form of greed: for a man's life does not consist of the abundance of the things which he possesses.
B042C012V016	42	12	16	And he spoke a parable to them, saying, The ground of a certain rich man brought forth plentifully:
B042C012V017	42	12	17	And he thought to himself, What shall I do, because I have no room to store my crops?
B042C012V018	42	12	18	And he said, This is what I will do: I will pull down my barns, and build bigger ones; and there I will store all my grain and goods.
B042C012V019	42	12	19	And I will say to my soul, Soul, you have many goods laid up for many years; take your ease, eat, drink, and be merry.
B042C012V020	42	12	20	But God said to him, You fool, this night your soul shall be required of you: then who shall own those things, which you have prepared?
B042C012V021	42	12	21	So it is with him who lays up treasure for himself, and is not rich toward God.
B042C012V022	42	12	22	And he said to his disciples, Therefore I say to you, Take no thought for your life, what you shall eat; or for the body, what you shall put on.
B042C012V023	42	12	23	For life is more than food, and the body is more than clothing.
B042C012V024	42	12	24	Consider the ravens: for they neither sow nor reap; they have no storehouse or barn; yet God feeds them: how much more valuable are you than the birds!
B042C012V025	42	12	25	And which of you by being anxious can add one cubit to his stature?
B042C012V026	42	12	26	If you then are not able to do such a small thing, why are you anxious about the rest?
B042C012V027	42	12	27	Consider the lilies, how they grow: they do not toil or spin; and yet I say to you, that Solomon in all his glory was not arrayed like one of these.
B042C012V028	42	12	28	If then God so clothes the grass, which is in the field today, and tomorrow is cast into the oven; how much more will he clothe you, O you of little faith?
B042C012V029	42	12	29	And do not seek what you shall eat, or what you shall drink, and do not be of an anxious mind.
B042C012V030	42	12	30	For the nations of the world seek after all these things: and your Father knows that you have need of them.
B042C012V031	42	12	31	But rather seek the kingdom of God; and all these things shall be added to you.
B042C012V032	42	12	32	Fear not, little flock; for it is your Father's good pleasure to give you the kingdom.
B042C012V033	42	12	33	Sell what you have, and give alms; provide yourselves purses which do not grow old, a treasure in heaven that does not fail, where no thief approaches and no moth destroys.
B042C012V034	42	12	34	For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.
B042C012V035	42	12	35	Be dressed and ready, and keep your lamps burning;
B042C012V036	42	12	36	And be like men who wait for their lord to return from the wedding feast; that when he comes and knocks, they may open the door for him immediately.
B042C012V037	42	12	37	Blessed are those servants, whom the lord shall find watching when he comes: truly I say to you, that he shall dress himself to serve, and make them sit down at the table, and will come forth and serve them.
B042C012V038	42	12	38	And if he shall come in the second watch, or come in the third watch, and find them so, blessed are those servants.
B042C012V039	42	12	39	And know this, that if the owner of the house had known at what hour the thief would come, he would have watched, and would not have allowed his house to be broken into.
B042C012V040	42	12	40	Therefore you be ready also: for the Son of man will come at a hour when you do not expect.
B042C012V041	42	12	41	Then Peter said to him, Lord, are you speaking this parable to us, or to everyone?
B042C012V042	42	12	42	And the Lord said, Who then is the faithful and wise steward, whom his lord shall make ruler over his servants, to give them their portion of food at the proper time?
B042C012V043	42	12	43	Blessed is that servant, whom his lord shall find so doing when he comes.
B042C012V044	42	12	44	Truly I say to you, that he will make him ruler over all that he has.
B042C012V045	42	12	45	But if that servant says in his heart, My lord delays his coming; and begins to beat the menservants and maidservants, and to eat and drink, and to be drunken;
B042C012V046	42	12	46	The lord of that servant will come on a day when he is not looking for him, and at a hour he is not aware of, and will cut him in pieces, and will assign him a place with the unbelievers.
B042C012V047	42	12	47	And that servant, who knew his lord's will, and did not prepare himself, and did not do his will, shall be beaten with many blows.
B042C012V048	42	12	48	But he who did not know, and committed things worthy of a beating, shall be beaten with few blows. For to whomever much is given, of him shall much be required: and to whom men have committed much, of him they will ask all the more.
B042C012V049	42	12	49	I have come to send fire on the earth; and how I wish it was already kindled.
B042C012V050	42	12	50	But I have a baptism to undergo; and how distressed I am until it is accomplished!
B042C012V051	42	12	51	Do you suppose that I have come to give peace on earth? I tell you, No; but rather division:
B042C012V052	42	12	52	For from henceforth there shall be five in one house, divided, three against two, and two against three.
B042C012V053	42	12	53	They shall be divided father against son, and son against father; mother against daughter, and daughter against mother; mother-in-law against her daughter-in-law, and daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law.
B042C012V054	42	12	54	And he also said to the people, When you see a cloud rise out of the west, immediately you say, A shower is coming; and so it does.
B042C012V055	42	12	55	And when you see the south wind blow, you say, There will be heat; and it comes to pass.
B042C012V056	42	12	56	You hypocrites, you can discern the face of the sky and of the earth; but how is it that you do not discern this time?
B042C012V057	42	12	57	And why do you not even judge for yourselves what is right?
B042C012V058	42	12	58	When you go with your adversary to the magistrate, as you are on the way, make every effort to settle with him, lest he drag you before the judge, and the judge deliver you to the officer, and the officer cast you into prison.
B042C012V059	42	12	59	I tell you, you shall not get out of there, until you have paid the very last farthing.
B042C013V001	42	13	1	There were some present at that time who told him of the Galilaeans, whose blood Pilate had mingled with their sacrifices.
B042C013V002	42	13	2	And Jesus answered, saying to them, Do you suppose these Galilaeans were greater sinners than all the other Galilaeans, because they suffered such things?
B042C013V003	42	13	3	I tell you, No: but, unless you repent, you shall all likewise perish.
B042C013V004	42	13	4	Or those eighteen, upon whom the tower in Siloam fell and killed them, do you think that they were more guilty than all the men who lived in Jerusalem?
B042C013V005	42	13	5	I tell you, No: but, unless you repent, you shall all likewise perish.
B042C013V006	42	13	6	Then he spoke this parable; A certain man had a fig tree planted in his vineyard; and he came and sought fruit on it, and found none.
B042C013V007	42	13	7	Then he said to the keeper of his vineyard, Behold, these three years I have come seeking fruit on this fig tree, and have found none: cut it down; why should it use up the ground?
B042C013V008	42	13	8	And he answered and said to him, Lord, let it alone this year also, until I shall dig about it, and put manure on it:
B042C013V009	42	13	9	And if it bears fruit, fine: and if not, then you can cut it down.
B042C013V010	42	13	10	And he was teaching in one of the synagogues on the sabbath.
B042C013V011	42	13	11	And, behold, there was a woman who had been crippled by a spirit for eighteen years, and was bowed over, and could not straighten up at all.
B042C013V012	42	13	12	And when Jesus saw her, he called her to him, and said to her, Woman, you are freed from your sickness.
B042C013V013	42	13	13	And he laid his hands on her: and immediately she straightened up, and glorified God.
B042C013V014	42	13	14	And the ruler of the synagogue, indignant because Jesus had healed on the sabbath day, said to the people, There are six days in which men ought to work: therefore come during them and be healed, and not on the sabbath day.
B042C013V015	42	13	15	The Lord then answered him, and said, You hypocrite, does not each one of you on the sabbath untie his ox or his donkey from the stall, and lead him away to water?
B042C013V016	42	13	16	And ought not this woman, being a daughter of Abraham, whom Satan has bound, lo, these eighteen years, be loosed from this bond on the sabbath day?
B042C013V017	42	13	17	And when he had said these things, all his adversaries were ashamed: and all the people rejoiced over all the glorious things he was doing.
B042C013V018	42	13	18	Then he said, What is the kingdom of God like? and to what shall I compare it?
B042C013V019	42	13	19	It is like a mustard seed, which a man took, and planted in his garden; and it grew, and became a great tree; and the birds of the air lodged in its branches.
B042C013V020	42	13	20	And again he said, To what shall I compare the kingdom of God?
B042C013V021	42	13	21	It is like leaven, which a woman took and hid in three measures of flour, until it was all leavened.
B042C013V022	42	13	22	And he went through the cities and villages, teaching, and traveling toward Jerusalem.
B042C013V023	42	13	23	Then someone said to him, Lord, will only a few be saved? And he said to them,
B042C013V024	42	13	24	Strive to enter in at the narrow gate: for many, I say to you, will seek to enter in, and shall not be able.
B042C013V025	42	13	25	When once the master of the house has risen up, and has shut the door, and you begin to stand without, and to knock at the door, saying, Lord, Lord, open up to us; then he shall answer and say to you, I do not know where you are from:
B042C013V026	42	13	26	Then you shall begin to say, We ate and drank in your presence, and you taught in our streets.
B042C013V027	42	13	27	But he shall say, I tell you, I do not know where you are from; depart from me, all you workers of iniquity.
B042C013V028	42	13	28	There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth, when you see Abraham, and Isaac, and Jacob, and all the prophets, in the kingdom of God, and yourselves thrust out.
B042C013V029	42	13	29	And they shall come from the east, and from the west, and from the north, and from the south, and shall recline at table in the kingdom of God.
B042C013V030	42	13	30	And, behold, there are some who are last who shall be first, and there are some who are first who shall be last.
B042C013V031	42	13	31	That same hour some of the Pharisees came, saying to him, Get away, and depart from here: for Herod wants to kill you.
B042C013V032	42	13	32	And he said to them, Go tell that fox, Behold, I cast out devils and perform cures today and tomorrow, and the third day I shall complete my course.
B042C013V033	42	13	33	Nevertheless, I must journey on today, and tomorrow, and the day following: for it cannot be that a prophet should perish outside of Jerusalem.
B042C013V034	42	13	34	O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, which kills the prophets, and stones those who are sent to you; how often would I have gathered your children together, as a hen gathers her brood under her wings, and you would not allow it!
B042C013V035	42	13	35	Behold, your house is left to you desolate: and truly I say to you, You shall not see me, until the time comes when you shall say, Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord.
B042C014V001	42	14	1	And it came to pass, as he went into the house of one of the chief Pharisees to eat on the sabbath day, that they watched him.
B042C014V002	42	14	2	And, behold, there was a certain man in front of him who had dropsy.
B042C014V003	42	14	3	And Jesus spoke to the lawyers and Pharisees, asking, Is it lawful to heal on the sabbath day?
B042C014V004	42	14	4	But they held their peace. And he took hold of him, and healed him, and let him go;
B042C014V005	42	14	5	And answered them, saying, If one of you has a son or an ox fall into a pit on the sabbath day, which of you will not immediately pull him out?
B042C014V006	42	14	6	And they could not answer these things.
B042C014V007	42	14	7	And he told a parable to those who were invited, when he noticed how they chose the places of honour; saying to them,
B042C014V008	42	14	8	When you are invited by someone to a wedding, do not sit down at the place of honour; for one more distinguished than you may have been invited;
B042C014V009	42	14	9	And he who invited both of you will come and say to you, Give this man your place; and with shame you will begin to take the lowest place.
B042C014V010	42	14	10	But when you are invited, go and sit in the lowest place; that when he who invited you comes, he may say to you, Friend, go up higher: then you shall have honour in the presence of those who are at the table with you.
B042C014V011	42	14	11	For whoever exalts himself shall be abased; and he who humbles himself shall be exalted.
B042C014V012	42	14	12	Then he said to his host, When you give a luncheon or dinner, do not invite your friends, your brothers, your kinsmen, or your rich neighbours; lest they invite you in return, and you are repaid.
B042C014V013	42	14	13	But when you have a feast, call the poor, the maimed, the lame, the blind:
B042C014V014	42	14	14	And you shall be blessed; for they cannot repay you: but you shall be repaid at the resurrection of the just.
B042C014V015	42	14	15	And when one of those who reclined at table with him heard these things, he said to him, Blessed is he who shall eat bread in the kingdom of God.
B042C014V016	42	14	16	Then he said to him, A certain man made a great banquet, and invited many:
B042C014V017	42	14	17	And at the banquet time he sent his servant to say to those who were invited, Come; for everything is now ready.
B042C014V018	42	14	18	And they all alike began to make excuses. The first said to him, I have bought a piece of land, and I must go and see it: Please excuse me.
B042C014V019	42	14	19	And another said, I have bought five yoke of oxen, and I am going to try them out: Please excuse me.
B042C014V020	42	14	20	And another said, I have married a wife, and therefore I cannot come.
B042C014V021	42	14	21	So the servant returned, and told his lord these things. Then the master of the house became angry and said to his servant, Go out quickly into the streets and lanes of the city, and bring in here the poor, and the crippled, and the blind, and the lame.
B042C014V022	42	14	22	And the servant said, Lord, it has been done as you have commanded, and yet there is still room.
B042C014V023	42	14	23	And the lord said to the servant, Go out into the highways and along the hedgerows, and compel them to come in, that my house may be filled.
B042C014V024	42	14	24	For I say to you, That none of those men who were invited shall taste my banquet.
B042C014V025	42	14	25	And great multitudes went with him: and he turned, and said to them,
B042C014V026	42	14	26	If anyone comes to me, and does not hate his father, and mother, and wife, and children, and brothers, and sisters, yea, and even his own life, he cannot be my disciple.
B042C014V027	42	14	27	And whoever does not carry his own cross, and come after me, cannot be my disciple.
B042C014V028	42	14	28	For which of you, intending to build a tower, does not sit down first and count the cost, whether he has sufficient money to finish it?
B042C014V029	42	14	29	Lest perhaps, after he has laid the foundation, and is not able to finish it, all who behold it will begin to mock him,
B042C014V030	42	14	30	Saying, This man began to build, and was not able to finish.
B042C014V031	42	14	31	Or what king, going to make war against another king, does not sit down first, and consider whether he is able with ten thousand to meet him who comes against him with twenty thousand?
B042C014V032	42	14	32	Or else, while the other is still a great way off, he sends a delegation, and asks terms of peace.
B042C014V033	42	14	33	So likewise, whoever of you does not forsake all that he has, cannot be my disciple.
