B042C014V035	42	14	35	It is fit for neither the land or the manure pile; it is cast out. He who has ears to hear, let him hear.
B042C015V001	42	15	1	Then all the tax gatherers and sinners drew near to hear him.
B042C015V002	42	15	2	And the Pharisees and scribes murmured, saying, This man receives sinners, and eats with them.
B042C015V003	42	15	3	And he spoke this parable to them, saying,
B042C015V004	42	15	4	What man of you, having a hundred sheep, if he lose one of them, does not leave the ninety-nine in the wilderness, and go after the one that is lost, until he finds it?
B042C015V005	42	15	5	And when he has found it, he lays it on his shoulders, rejoicing.
B042C015V006	42	15	6	And when he comes home, he calls together his friends and neighbours, saying to them, Rejoice with me; for I have found my sheep which was lost.
B042C015V007	42	15	7	I say to you, that likewise there shall be more joy in heaven over one sinner who repents, than over ninety-nine righteous persons, who do not need to repent.
B042C015V008	42	15	8	Or what woman, having ten pieces of silver, if she lose one piece, does not light a lamp, and sweep the house, and seek diligently until she finds it?
B042C015V009	42	15	9	And when she has found it, she calls her friends and her neighbours together, saying, Rejoice with me; for I have found the coin which I had lost.
B042C015V010	42	15	10	Likewise, I say to you, there is joy in the presence of the angels of God over one sinner who repents.
B042C015V011	42	15	11	And he said, A certain man had two sons:
B042C015V012	42	15	12	And the younger of them said to his father, Father, give me my part of the estate. So he divided his property between them.
B042C015V013	42	15	13	And not many days after the younger son gathered everything together, and took a journey into a far country, and there wasted his estate with riotous living.
B042C015V014	42	15	14	And when he had spent everything, there arose a mighty famine in that land; and he began to be in want.
B042C015V015	42	15	15	And he went and hired himself to a citizen of that country; and he sent him into his fields to feed swine.
B042C015V016	42	15	16	And he would gladly have filled his stomach with the pods the swine were eating: but no man gave him anything.
B042C015V017	42	15	17	And when he came to himself, he said, How many of my father's hired servants have bread enough to spare, and I perish with hunger!
B042C015V018	42	15	18	I will arise and go to my father, and will say to him, Father, I have sinned against heaven, and in your sight,
B042C015V019	42	15	19	And am no longer worthy to be called your son: treat me as one of your hired servants.
B042C015V020	42	15	20	And he arose, and went to his father. But when he was yet a great way off, his father saw him, and had compassion, and ran, and threw his arms around his neck, and kissed him.
B042C015V021	42	15	21	And the son said to him, Father, I have sinned against heaven, and in your sight, and am no longer worthy to be called your son.
B042C015V022	42	15	22	But the father said to his servants, Bring forth the best robe, and put it on him; and put a ring on his hand, and sandals on his feet:
B042C015V023	42	15	23	And bring the fatted calf, and kill it; and let us eat, and be merry:
B042C015V024	42	15	24	For this son of mine was dead, and is alive again; he was lost, and is found. And they began to be merry.
B042C015V025	42	15	25	Now his elder son was in the field: and as he came and drew near to the house, he heard music and dancing.
B042C015V026	42	15	26	And he called one of the servants, and asked what these things meant.
B042C015V027	42	15	27	And he said to him, Your brother has come; and your father has killed the fatted calf, because he has received him back safe and sound.
B042C015V028	42	15	28	And he was angry, and would not go in: therefore his father came out, and pleaded with him.
B042C015V029	42	15	29	And he answered his father, Lo, these many years I have served you and never disobeyed your commandment: and yet you never gave me a kid, that I might make merry with my friends:
B042C015V030	42	15	30	But as soon as this son of yours comes home, who has devoured your estate with prostitutes, you kill for him the fatted calf.
B042C015V031	42	15	31	And he said to him, Son, you are always with me, and all that I have is yours.
B042C015V032	42	15	32	But we had to make merry, and be glad: for this brother of yours was dead, and is alive again; and was lost, and is found.
B042C016V001	42	16	1	And he also said to his disciples, There was a certain rich man, who had a steward, and charges were brought to him that the steward was wasting his goods.
B042C016V002	42	16	2	And he called him, and said to him, What is this that I hear of you? give an account of your stewardship; for you may no longer be steward.
B042C016V003	42	16	3	Then the steward said to himself, What shall I do? for my lord is taking away my stewardship: I am not strong enough to dig; and I am ashamed to beg.
B042C016V004	42	16	4	I know what to do, so that when I am put out of the stewardship, people will receive me into their houses.
B042C016V005	42	16	5	So he called in every one of his lord's debtors, and said to the first, How much do you owe to my lord?
B042C016V006	42	16	6	And he said, A hundred measures of oil. And he said to him, Take your bill, and sit down quickly, and write fifty.
B042C016V007	42	16	7	Then he said to another, And how much do you owe? And he said, A hundred measures of wheat. And he said to him, Take your bill, and write eighty.
B042C016V008	42	16	8	And the lord commended the dishonest steward, because he had acted shrewdly: for the children of this world are more shrewd in dealing with own kind than are the children of light.
B042C016V009	42	16	9	And I say to you, Make friends for yourselves using worldly wealth; that, when it fails, they may receive you into the eternal habitations.
B042C016V010	42	16	10	He who is faithful in that which is least is faithful also in much: and he who is dishonest in the least is also dishonest in much.
B042C016V011	42	16	11	Therefore, if you have not been faithful with worldly wealth, who will entrust you with true riches?
B042C016V012	42	16	12	And if you have not been faithful with that which is another man's, who shall give you possessions of your own?
B042C016V013	42	16	13	No servant can serve two masters: for either he will hate the one, and love the other; or else he will hold to the one, and despise the other. You cannot serve God and money.
B042C016V014	42	16	14	The Pharisees, who were covetous, heard all these things: and they derided him.
B042C016V015	42	16	15	And he said to them, You justify yourselves before men; but God knows your hearts: for that which is highly esteemed among men is an abomination in the sight of God.
B042C016V016	42	16	16	The law and the prophets were until John: since that time the kingdom of God is preached, and every man forces his way into it.
B042C016V017	42	16	17	And it is easier for heaven and earth to pass away, than for one dot of the law to fail.
B042C016V018	42	16	18	Whoever divorces his wife, and marries another, commits adultery: and whoever marries a divorced woman commits adultery.
B042C016V019	42	16	19	There was a certain rich man, who was clothed in purple and fine linen, and feasted sumptuously every day:
B042C016V020	42	16	20	And there was a certain beggar named Lazarus, who was laid at his gate, covered with sores,
B042C016V021	42	16	21	And he longed to eat the crumbs which fell from the rich man's table. Even the dogs came and licked his sores.
B042C016V022	42	16	22	And it came to pass, that the beggar died, and was carried by the angels into Abraham's bosom: the rich man also died, and was buried;
B042C016V023	42	16	23	And in Hades he lift up his eyes, being in torment, and saw Abraham far off, and Lazarus in his bosom.
B042C016V024	42	16	24	And he cried out, Father Abraham, have mercy on me, and send Lazarus, that he may dip the tip of his finger in water, and cool my tongue; for I am tormented in this flame.
B042C016V025	42	16	25	But Abraham said, Son, remember that in your lifetime you received your good things, and Lazarus received evil things: but now he is comforted, and you are tormented.
B042C016V026	42	16	26	And beside all this, between us and you a great gulf has been fixed: so that those who would pass from here to you cannot; nor can any pass over from there to us.
B042C016V027	42	16	27	He said, Then I beg you, father, that you would send him to my father's house:
B042C016V028	42	16	28	For I have five brothers. Have him warn them, lest they also come into this place of torment.
B042C016V029	42	16	29	Abraham said to him, They have Moses and the prophets; let them hear them.
B042C016V030	42	16	30	And he said, No, father Abraham: but if someone went to them from the dead, they will repent.
B042C016V031	42	16	31	And he said to him, If they will not hear Moses and the prophets, neither will they be persuaded if someone rises from the dead.
B042C017V001	42	17	1	Then he said to the disciples, It is certain that stumbling blocks will come: but woe to him through whom they come!
B042C017V002	42	17	2	It would be better for him to have a millstone hung around his neck and be cast into the sea than for him to cause one of these little ones to stumble.
B042C017V003	42	17	3	Be on your guard: If your brother sins, rebuke him; and if he repents, forgive him.
B042C017V004	42	17	4	And if he sins against you seven times in a day, and seven times a day comes to you, saying, I repent; you must forgive him.
B042C017V005	42	17	5	And the apostles said to the Lord, Increase our faith.
B042C017V006	42	17	6	And the Lord said, If you had faith as a grain of mustard seed, you could say to this mulberry tree, Be plucked up by the root, and be planted in the sea; and it would obey you.
B042C017V007	42	17	7	But which of you, having a servant plowing or feeding cattle, will say to him when he has come in from the field, Go sit down to eat?
B042C017V008	42	17	8	Will he not rather say to him, Make something for my supper, and gird yourself, and serve me until I eat and drink; and afterward you shall eat and drink?
B042C017V009	42	17	9	Does he thank that servant because he did as he was commanded?
B042C017V010	42	17	10	So likewise you, when you have done all those things which are commanded of you, say, We are unworthy servants: we have merely done our duty.
B042C017V011	42	17	11	And it came to pass, as he went to Jerusalem, that he passed between Samaria and Galilee.
B042C017V012	42	17	12	And as he entered into a certain village, ten leprous men met him. They stood at a distance,
B042C017V013	42	17	13	And they lifted up their voices, and said, Jesus, Master, have mercy on us.
B042C017V014	42	17	14	And when he saw them, he said to them, Go show yourselves to the priests. And it came to pass, that, as they went, they were cleansed.
B042C017V015	42	17	15	And one of them, when he saw that he was healed, turned back, and with a loud voice glorified God,
B042C017V016	42	17	16	And fell down on his face at his feet, giving him thanks: and he was a Samaritan.
B042C017V017	42	17	17	And Jesus answered, Were there not ten cleansed? but where are the nine?
B042C017V018	42	17	18	Was no one found who returned to give glory to God, except this foreigner.
B042C017V019	42	17	19	And he said to him, Arise, go your way: your faith has made you well.
B042C017V020	42	17	20	And when he was asked by the Pharisees, when the kingdom of God should come, he answered them and said, The kingdom of God does not come with signs:
B042C017V021	42	17	21	Nor shall they say, Look, here it is! or, look there! for, behold, the kingdom of God is within you.
B042C017V022	42	17	22	And he said to the disciples, The days will come, when you shall desire to see one of the days of the Son of man, and you shall not see it.
B042C017V023	42	17	23	And they shall say to you, See here!; or, see there!: do not go not after them, or follow them.
B042C017V024	42	17	24	For as the lightning flashes in one part of the sky and shines to the other; so shall also the Son of man be in his day.
B042C017V025	42	17	25	But first he must suffer many things, and be rejected by this generation.
B042C017V026	42	17	26	As it was in the days of Noah, so it shall also be in the days of the Son of man.
B042C017V027	42	17	27	They ate, they drank, they married wives, they were given in marriage, until the day that Noah entered the ark, and the flood came, and destroyed them all.
B042C017V028	42	17	28	It was the same in the days of Lot; they ate, they drank, they bought, they sold, they planted, they built;
B042C017V029	42	17	29	But on the day that Lot went out of Sodom it rained fire and brimstone from heaven, and destroyed them all.
B042C017V030	42	17	30	Even so shall it be on the day when the Son of man is revealed.
B042C017V031	42	17	31	On that day, let him who is upon the housetop, and his goods in the house, not come down to take them away: and likewise let not him who is in the field turn back.
B042C017V032	42	17	32	Remember Lot's wife.
B042C017V033	42	17	33	Whoever shall seek to save his life shall lose it; and whoever shall lose his life shall preserve it.
B042C017V034	42	17	34	I tell you, in that night two shall be in one bed; one shall be taken, and the other shall be left.
B042C017V035	42	17	35	Two women shall be grinding together; one shall be taken, and the other left.
B042C017V036	42	17	36	[Two men shall be in the field; one shall be taken, and the other left.]
B042C017V037	42	17	37	And they answered and said to him, Where, Lord? And he said to them, Wherever the body is, there will the vultures be gathered.
B042C018V001	42	18	1	And he spoke a parable to them to show that men ought always to pray, and not loose heart;
B042C018V002	42	18	2	Saying, There was a judge in a city, who did not fear God or respect man:
B042C018V003	42	18	3	And there was a widow in that city; and she kept coming to him, saying, Give me justice against my adversary.
B042C018V004	42	18	4	And he would not for a while: but afterward he said to himself, Though I do not fear God or respect man;
B042C018V005	42	18	5	Yet because this widow bothers me, I will give her justice, lest by her continual coming she wear me out.
B042C018V006	42	18	6	And the Lord said, Hear what the unjust judge says.
B042C018V007	42	18	7	And shall not God vindicate his elect, who cry day and night to him, and will he delay long with them?
B042C018V008	42	18	8	I tell you that he will vindicate them speedily. Nevertheless, when the Son of man comes, shall he find faith on the earth?
B042C018V009	42	18	9	And he spoke this parable to certain people who trusted in themselves that they were righteous, and despised others:
B042C018V010	42	18	10	Two men went up into the temple to pray; the one a Pharisee, and the other a tax gatherer.
B042C018V011	42	18	11	The Pharisee stood and prayed thus with himself, God, I thank you that I am not as other men are, extortioners, unjust, adulterers, or even as this tax gatherer.
B042C018V012	42	18	12	I fast twice in the week, I give tithes of all that I possess.
B042C018V013	42	18	13	And the tax gatherer, standing far off, would not lift up so much as his eyes to heaven, but beat upon his breast, saying, God be merciful to me, a sinner.
B042C018V014	42	18	14	I tell you, this man went down to his house justified rather than the other: for every one who exalts himself shall be abased; and he who humbles himself shall be exalted.
B042C018V015	42	18	15	And they also brought infants to him, that he would touch them: but when his disciples saw this, they rebuked them.
B042C018V016	42	18	16	But Jesus called them to him, and said, Let the little children come to me, and do not hinder them: for to such belongs the kingdom of God.
B042C018V017	42	18	17	Truly I say to you, Whoever does not receive the kingdom of God as a little child shall by no means enter it.
B042C018V018	42	18	18	And a certain ruler asked him, Good Teacher, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?
B042C018V019	42	18	19	And Jesus said to him, Why do you call me good? no one is good, except God alone.
B042C018V020	42	18	20	You know the commandments, Do not commit adultery, Do not kill, Do not steal, Do not bear false witness, Honour your father and your mother.
B042C018V021	42	18	21	And he said, All these I have kept from my youth up.
B042C018V022	42	18	22	Now when Jesus heard this, he said to him, You still lack one thing: sell all that you have, and give to the poor, and you shall have treasure in heaven: and come, follow me.
B042C018V023	42	18	23	And when he heard this, he was very sorrowful: for he was very rich.
B042C018V024	42	18	24	And when Jesus saw that he was very sorrowful, he said, How hard it is for those who have riches to enter the kingdom of God!
B042C018V025	42	18	25	It is easier for a camel to go through a needle's eye, than for a rich man to enter the kingdom of God.
B042C018V026	42	18	26	And those who heard it said, Who then can be saved?
B042C018V027	42	18	27	And he said, Things that are impossible with men are possible with God.
B042C018V028	42	18	28	Then Peter said, Lo, we have left all, and followed you.
B042C018V029	42	18	29	And he said to them, Truly I say to you, There is no man who has left house, or parents, or brothers, or wife, or children, for the sake of the kingdom of God,
B042C018V030	42	18	30	Who shall not receive many times more in this present time, and in the world to come, life everlasting.
B042C018V031	42	18	31	Then he took the twelve aside, and said to them, Behold, we are going up to Jerusalem, and all things that are written by the prophets concerning the Son of man shall be accomplished.
B042C018V032	42	18	32	For he shall be delivered to the Gentiles, and shall be mocked, and spitefully treated, and spit upon:
B042C018V033	42	18	33	And they shall flog him, and put him to death: and on the third day he shall rise again.
B042C018V034	42	18	34	And they understood none of these things: this saying was hidden from them, and they did not comprehend the things which were spoken.
B042C018V035	42	18	35	And it came to pass, that when he came near to Jericho, a certain blind man sat by the road begging:
B042C018V036	42	18	36	And hearing the multitude pass by, he asked what it meant.
B042C018V037	42	18	37	And they told him, Jesus of Nazareth is passing by.
B042C018V038	42	18	38	And he cried out, Jesus, Son of David, have mercy on me.
B042C018V039	42	18	39	And those who led the way rebuked him, telling him to hold his peace: but he cried out all the more, Son of David, have mercy on me.
B042C018V040	42	18	40	And Jesus stood still, and commanded him to be brought to him: and when he had come near, he asked him,
B042C018V041	42	18	41	What do you want me to do for you? And he said, Lord, I want to receive my sight.
B042C018V042	42	18	42	And Jesus said to him, Receive your sight: your faith has healed you.
B042C018V043	42	18	43	And immediately he received his sight, and followed him, glorifying God: and all the people, when they saw it, gave praise to God.
B042C019V001	42	19	1	And Jesus entered and was passing through Jericho.
B042C019V002	42	19	2	And, behold, there was a man named Zacchaeus, who was the chief among the tax gatherers, and he was rich.
B042C019V003	42	19	3	And he sought to see who Jesus was; but could not because of the crowd, for he was of small stature.
B042C019V004	42	19	4	And he ran ahead, and climbed up into a sycomore tree to see him: for he was to pass that way.
B042C019V005	42	19	5	And when Jesus came to the place, he looked up, and saw him, and said to him, Zacchaeus, make haste, and come down; for today I must stay at your house.
B042C019V006	42	19	6	And he made haste, and came down, and received him joyfully.
B042C019V007	42	19	7	And when they saw it, they all murmured, saying, He has gone to be the guest of a man who is a sinner.
B042C019V008	42	19	8	And Zacchaeus stood, and said to the Lord; Behold, Lord, the half of my goods I give to the poor; and if I have defrauded any man of anything, I will repay it fourfold.
B042C019V009	42	19	9	And Jesus said to him, This day salvation has come to this house, because he also is a son of Abraham.
B042C019V010	42	19	10	For the Son of man has come to seek and to save that which was lost.
B042C019V011	42	19	11	And while they listened to these things, he told a parable, because he was near to Jerusalem, and because they thought that the kingdom of God would immediately appear.
B042C019V012	42	19	12	Therefore he said, A certain nobleman went into a far country to receive for himself a kingdom, and then to return.
B042C019V013	42	19	13	And he called his ten servants, and gave them ten minas, and said to them, Trade with these until I come.
B042C019V014	42	19	14	But his citizens hated him, and sent a message after him, saying, We do not want this man to reign over us.
B042C019V015	42	19	15	And it came to pass, that when he returned, having received the kingdom, that he commanded the servants to whom he had given the money to be called to him, that he might know how much every man had gained by trading.
B042C019V016	42	19	16	The first came, saying, Lord, your mina has gained ten minas.
B042C019V017	42	19	17	And he said to him, Well done, you good servant: because you have been faithful in a very little, take authority over ten cities.
B042C019V018	42	19	18	And the second came, saying, Lord, your mina has gained five minas.
B042C019V019	42	19	19	And he said likewise to him, You shall be in authority over five cities.
B042C019V020	42	19	20	And another came, saying, Lord, behold, here is your mina, which I have kept laid up in a handkerchief:
B042C019V021	42	19	21	For I feared you, because you are a severe man: you take up what you have not laid down, and reap what you did not sow.
B042C019V022	42	19	22	And he said to him, Out of your own mouth will I judge you, you wicked servant. You knew that I was a severe man, taking up what I did not lay down, and reaping what I did not sow:
B042C019V023	42	19	23	Why then did you not put my money into the bank, that at my coming I might have collected it with interest?
B042C019V024	42	19	24	And he said to those who stood by, Take from him the mina, and give it to him who has ten minas.
B042C019V025	42	19	25	And they said to him, Lord, he already has ten minas.
B042C019V026	42	19	26	I say to you, To everyone who has shall more be given; and from him who has not, even what he has shall be taken away from him.
B042C019V027	42	19	27	As for my enemies, those who did not want me to reign over them, bring them here, and kill them in front of me.
B042C019V028	42	19	28	And when he had spoken these things, he went on ahead, ascending to Jerusalem.
B042C019V029	42	19	29	And it came to pass, when he had come near to Bethphage and Bethany, at the mount called Olivet, he sent two of his disciples,
B042C019V030	42	19	30	Saying, Go into the village opposite you; and as you enter it you shall find a colt tied, on which no one has ever sat: untie it, and bring it here.
B042C019V031	42	19	31	And if anyone asks you, Why are you untying it? you shall say, Because the Lord has need of it.
B042C019V032	42	19	32	And those who were sent went their way, and found it as he had said.
B042C019V033	42	19	33	And as they were untying the colt, its owners said to them, Why are you untying the colt?
B042C019V034	42	19	34	And they said, The Lord has need of it.
B042C019V035	42	19	35	And they brought it to Jesus: and they cast their garments upon the colt, and they put Jesus on it.
B042C019V036	42	19	36	And as he went, they spread their clothes on the road.
B042C019V037	42	19	37	And as he was coming near, at the descent of the mount of Olives, the whole multitude of the disciples began to rejoice and praise God with a loud voice for all the mighty works that they had seen;
B042C019V038	42	19	38	Saying, Blessed is the King who comes in the name of the Lord: peace in heaven, and glory in the highest.
B042C019V039	42	19	39	And some of the Pharisees in the multitude said to him, Teacher, rebuke your disciples.
B042C019V040	42	19	40	And he answered and said to them, I tell you that if they should hold their peace, the very stones would cry out.
B042C019V041	42	19	41	And when he had come near, he beheld the city, and wept over it,
B042C019V042	42	19	42	Saying, If you, even you, had only known on this day, the things which make for peace! but now they are hidden from your eyes.
B042C019V043	42	19	43	For the days shall come upon you, when your enemies shall build an embankment about you, and surround you, and keep you in on every side,
B042C019V044	42	19	44	And shall level you to the ground, and your children within you; and they shall not leave in you one stone upon another; because you did not know the time of your visitation.
B042C019V045	42	19	45	And he went into the temple, and began to cast out those who were selling;
B042C019V046	42	19	46	Saying to them, It is written, My house shall be a house of prayer: but you have made it a den of thieves.
B042C019V047	42	19	47	And he taught daily in the temple. But the chief priests and the scribes and the leaders of the people sought to destroy him,
B042C019V048	42	19	48	But could not find what they might do: for all the people hung upon his words.
B042C020V001	42	20	1	And it came to pass, on one of those days, as he taught the people in the temple, and preached the gospel, the chief priests and the scribes came up to him with the elders,
B042C020V002	42	20	2	And said to him, Tell us by what authority you do these things? or who it is who gave you this authority?
B042C020V003	42	20	3	And he answered and said to them, I will also ask you one thing; and you answer me:
B042C020V004	42	20	4	The baptism of John, was it from heaven, or from men?
B042C020V005	42	20	5	And they discussed among themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven; he will say, Why then did you not believe him?
B042C020V006	42	20	6	But if we say, From men, all the people will stone us, for they are persuaded that John was a prophet.
B042C020V007	42	20	7	And they answered that they did not know from where it came.
B042C020V008	42	20	8	And Jesus said to them, Neither will tell I you by what authority I do these things.
B042C020V009	42	20	9	Then he began to tell the people this parable; A certain man planted a vineyard, and rented it out to tenants, and went into a far country for a long time.
B042C020V010	42	20	10	And at harvest time he sent a servant to the tenants, that they should give him some of the fruit of the vineyard: but the tenants beat him, and sent him away empty-handed.
B042C020V011	42	20	11	He sent another servant: and they beat him also, and treated him shamefully, and sent him away empty-handed.
B042C020V012	42	20	12	And he sent a third: and they wounded him, and cast him out.
B042C020V013	42	20	13	Then the lord of the vineyard said, What shall I do? I will send my beloved son: it may be they will respect him when they see him.
B042C020V014	42	20	14	But when the tenants saw him, they reasoned among themselves, saying, This is the heir: come, let us kill him, that the inheritance may be ours.
B042C020V015	42	20	15	So they cast him out of the vineyard, and killed him. What then shall the lord of the vineyard do to them?
B042C020V016	42	20	16	He shall come and destroy these tenants, and shall give the vineyard to others. When they heard this, they said, God forbid.
B042C020V017	42	20	17	And he looked at them, and said, What then is this that is written, The stone which the builders rejected has become the cornerstone?
B042C020V018	42	20	18	Whoever shall fall upon that stone shall be broken; but on whomever it shall fall, it will grind him to powder.
B042C020V019	42	20	19	And the chief priests and the scribes sought to lay hands on him that same hour, for they perceived that he had spoken this parable against them; but they feared the people.
B042C020V020	42	20	20	So they watched him, and sent forth spies, who pretended to be sincere, that they might catch him in his words, that they might deliver him to the power and authority of the governor.
B042C020V021	42	20	21	And they asked him, Teacher, we know that you speak and teach correctly, and that you are not partial to any person, but teach the way of God truly:
B042C020V022	42	20	22	Is it lawful for us to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?
B042C020V023	42	20	23	But he perceived their craftiness, and said to them,
B042C020V024	42	20	24	Show me a denarius. Whose image and inscription are on it? They answered, Caesar's.
B042C020V025	42	20	25	And he said to them, Then render to Caesar the things which are Caesar's, and to God the things which are God's.
B042C020V026	42	20	26	And they could not trap him in what he said before the people: they marvelled at his answer, and held their peace.
B042C020V027	42	20	27	Then some of the Sadducees, who deny that there is any resurrection, came to him, and they asked him,
B042C020V028	42	20	28	Teacher, Moses wrote to us, If any man's brother dies, leaving a wife and no children, that man should take the widow, and raise up children for his brother.
B042C020V029	42	20	29	Now there were seven brothers: the first took a wife, and died without children.
B042C020V030	42	20	30	And the second,
B042C020V031	42	20	31	And the third took her; as did all seven: and they left no children, and died.
B042C020V032	42	20	32	Last of all the woman died.
B042C020V033	42	20	33	Therefore, in the resurrection, whose wife will she be? for all seven had her as wife.
B042C020V034	42	20	34	Jesus answered and said to them, The people of this age marry, and are given in marriage:
B042C020V035	42	20	35	But those who shall be accounted worthy to obtain that age, and the resurrection from the dead, neither marry, nor are given in marriage:
B042C020V036	42	20	36	Nor can they die any more: for they are like the angels; and are the children of God, since they are children of the resurrection.
B042C020V037	42	20	37	That the dead are raised, even Moses showed in the account of the bush, when he called the Lord the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.
B042C020V038	42	20	38	For he is not the God of the dead, but of the living: for all are alive to him.
B042C020V039	42	20	39	Then certain of the scribes answered, Teacher, you have spoken well.
B042C020V040	42	20	40	And after that they dared not ask him any more questions.
B042C020V041	42	20	41	And he said to them, How is it that they say the Christ is David's son?
B042C020V042	42	20	42	David himself says in the book of Psalms, The LORD said to my Lord, Sit at my right hand,
B042C020V043	42	20	43	Until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet.
B042C020V044	42	20	44	Therefore David calls him Lord; so how is he then his son?
B042C020V045	42	20	45	Then in the hearing of all the people he said to his disciples,
B042C020V046	42	20	46	Beware of the scribes, who like to walk about in long robes, and love greetings in the marketplaces, and the best seats in the synagogues, and the places of honour at feasts;
B042C020V047	42	20	47	They devour widows' houses, and for a show make long prayers: they shall receive the greater condemnation.
B042C021V001	42	21	1	And he looked up, and saw the rich people putting their gifts into the treasury.
B042C021V002	42	21	2	And he also saw a certain poor widow putting in two small copper coins.
B042C021V003	42	21	3	And he said, Truly I say to you, that this poor widow has put in more than all of them:
B042C021V004	42	21	4	For all these have given offerings to God out of their abundance: but she in her poverty has put in all she had to live on.
B042C021V005	42	21	5	And as some spoke of the temple, how it was adorned with beautiful stones and gifts, he said,
B042C021V006	42	21	6	As for these things which you behold, the days will come, in which there shall not be one stone left upon another; every one of them shall be thrown down.
B042C021V007	42	21	7	And they asked him, saying, Teacher, when shall these things happen? and what sign will there be that these things are about to take place?
B042C021V008	42	21	8	And he said, Take heed that you are not deceived: for many shall come in my name, saying, I am the Christ; and, the time draws near: do not go after them.
B042C021V009	42	21	9	And when you hear of wars and disturbances, do not be terrified: for these things must first come to pass; but the end does not follow immediately.
B042C021V010	42	21	10	Then said he to them, Nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom:
B042C021V011	42	21	11	And there shall be great earthquakes in various places, and famines, and pestilences; and fearful sights and great signs from heaven.
B042C021V012	42	21	12	But before all this, they shall lay their hands on you, and persecute you, delivering you up to the synagogues, and into prisons, and you shall be brought before kings and rulers for my name's sake.
B042C021V013	42	21	13	And it shall be a time for you to bear testimony.
B042C021V014	42	21	14	Therefore, settle it in your hearts, not to meditate beforehand how you shall answer:
B042C021V015	42	21	15	For I will give you a mouth and wisdom, which all your adversaries shall not be able to resist or refute.
B042C021V016	42	21	16	And you shall be betrayed both by parents, and brothers, and relatives, and friends; and some of you shall they cause to be put to death.
B042C021V017	42	21	17	And you shall be hated by all for my name's sake.
B042C021V018	42	21	18	But not a hair of your head shall perish.
B042C021V019	42	21	19	By your perseverance you shall win your souls.
B042C021V020	42	21	20	And when you shall see Jerusalem surrounded by armies, then know that its desolation is near.
B042C021V021	42	21	21	Then let those who are in Judaea flee to the mountains; and let those who are inside the city depart; and let not those who are in the country enter into it.
B042C021V022	42	21	22	For these are days of vengeance, that all things which are written may be fulfilled.
B042C021V023	42	21	23	But woe to those who are with child, and to those who nurse infants, in those days! for there shall be great distress in the land, and wrath upon this people.
B042C021V024	42	21	24	And they shall fall by the edge of the sword, and shall be led away captive into all nations: and Jerusalem shall be trodden down by the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles are fulfilled.
B042C021V025	42	21	25	And there shall be signs in the sun, and in the moon, and in the stars; and upon the earth nations shall be distressed and perplexed by the roaring waves of the sea;
B042C021V026	42	21	26	Men's hearts failing them for fear and foreboding of those things which are coming upon the earth: for the powers of the heavens shall be shaken.
B042C021V027	42	21	27	And then they shall see the Son of man coming in a cloud with power and great glory.
B042C021V028	42	21	28	And when these things begin to come to pass, then look up, and lift up your heads; for your redemption draws near.
B042C021V029	42	21	29	And he told them a parable; Behold the fig tree, and all the trees;
B042C021V030	42	21	30	When they shoot forth leaves, you see and know for yourselves that summer is at hand.
B042C021V031	42	21	31	So likewise, when you see these things come to pass, know that the kingdom of God is at hand.
B042C021V032	42	21	32	Truly I say to you, This generation shall not pass away, until all is fulfilled.
B042C021V033	42	21	33	Heaven and earth shall pass away: but my words shall not pass away.
B042C021V034	42	21	34	And take heed to yourselves, lest at any time your hearts be weighed down with dissipation, and drunkenness, and the cares of this life, so that day comes upon you unexpectedly like a snare.
B042C021V035	42	21	35	For as a snare shall it come upon all those who live on the face of the whole earth.
B042C021V036	42	21	36	Watch therefore, and pray always, that you may be strong and accounted worthy to escape all these things that shall come to pass, and to stand before the Son of man.
B042C021V037	42	21	37	Now in the daytime he was teaching in the temple; and at night he went out, and stayed on the mount that is called Olivet.
B042C021V038	42	21	38	And all the people came to the temple early in the morning to hear him.
B042C022V001	42	22	1	Now the feast of unleavened bread, which is called the Passover, drew near.
B042C022V002	42	22	2	And the chief priests and scribes sought how they might kill him; for they feared the people.
B042C022V003	42	22	3	Then Satan entered into Judas, called Iscariot, one the twelve.
B042C022V004	42	22	4	And he went his way, and discussed with the chief priests and captains, how he might betray him to them.
B042C022V005	42	22	5	They were glad, and agreed to give him money.
B042C022V006	42	22	6	So he consented, and sought an opportunity to betray him to them in the absence of the multitude.
B042C022V007	42	22	7	Then came the day of unleavened bread, when the passover lamb must be killed.
B042C022V008	42	22	8	And he sent Peter and John, saying, Go and prepare the passover for us, that we may eat it.
B042C022V009	42	22	9	And they said to him, Where will you have us prepare it?
B042C022V010	42	22	10	And he said to them, Behold, when you enter the city, a man shall meet you there, bearing a pitcher of water; follow him into the house that he enters.
B042C022V011	42	22	11	And you shall say to the owner of the house, The Teacher says to you, Where is the guest chamber, where I shall eat the passover with my disciples?
B042C022V012	42	22	12	And he shall show you a large upper room, furnished: make ready there.
B042C022V013	42	22	13	And they went, and found it as he had said to them: and they made ready the passover.
B042C022V014	42	22	14	And when the hour had come, he sat down, and the apostles with him.
B042C022V015	42	22	15	And he said to them, I have earnestly desired to eat this passover with you before I suffer:
B042C022V016	42	22	16	For I say to you, I will not eat it again, until it is fulfilled in the kingdom of God.
B042C022V017	42	22	17	And he took the cup, and gave thanks, and said, Take this, and divide it among yourselves:
B042C022V018	42	22	18	For I say to you, I will not drink again of the fruit of the vine, until the kingdom of God shall come.
B042C022V019	42	22	19	And he took bread, and gave thanks, and broke it, and gave to them, saying, This is my body which is given for you: do this in remembrance of me.
B042C022V020	42	22	20	Likewise he took the cup after supper, saying, This cup is the new covenant in my blood.
B042C022V021	42	22	21	But, behold, the hand of him who betrays me is with me on the table.
B042C022V022	42	22	22	Truly the Son of man goes, as it was determined: but woe to that man by whom he is betrayed!
B042C022V023	42	22	23	And they began to enquire among themselves, which of them it was that should do this thing.
B042C022V024	42	22	24	And there was also a dispute among them as to which of them should be accounted the greatest.
B042C022V025	42	22	25	And he said to them, The kings of the Gentiles exercise lordship over them; and those who exercise authority over them are called benefactors.
B042C022V026	42	22	26	But not so with you: but he who is greatest among you, let him be as the youngest; and he who rules, as he who serves.
B042C022V027	42	22	27	For which is greater, he who reclines at table, or he who serves? is it not he who reclines at table? but I am among you as one who serves.
B042C022V028	42	22	28	You are those who have stood by me in my trials.
B042C022V029	42	22	29	And I grant to you a kingdom, as my Father has granted to me;
B042C022V030	42	22	30	That you may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom, and sit on thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel.
B042C022V031	42	22	31	And the Lord said, Simon, Simon, behold, Satan has demanded to have you, that he might sift you as wheat:
B042C022V032	42	22	32	But I have prayed for you, that your faith will not fail: and when you have turned back, strengthen your brethren.
B042C022V033	42	22	33	And he said to him, Lord, I am ready to go with you, both into prison, and to death.
B042C022V034	42	22	34	And he said, I tell you, Peter, the cock shall not crow this day, before you have thrice denied that you know me.
B042C022V035	42	22	35	And he said to them, When I sent you out without purse, or bag, or sandals, did you lack anything? And they said, Nothing.
B042C022V036	42	22	36	Then he said to them, But now, he who has a purse, let him take it, and likewise a bag: and he who has no sword, let him sell his garment, and buy one.
B042C022V037	42	22	37	For I say to you, that this scripture must yet be fulfilled in me, And he was reckoned among the transgressors: for that which refers to me has its fulfillment.
B042C022V038	42	22	38	And they said, Lord, behold, here are two swords. And he said to them, It is enough.
B042C022V039	42	22	39	And he came out, and went, as was his custom, to the mount of Olives; and his disciples followed him.
B042C022V040	42	22	40	When he arrived at the place, he said to them, Pray that you may not enter into temptation.
B042C022V041	42	22	41	And he withdrew from them about a stone's throw, and knelt down, and prayed,
B042C022V042	42	22	42	Saying, Father, if you are willing, remove this cup from me: nevertheless not my will, but yours, be done.
B042C022V043	42	22	43	And there appeared to him an angel from heaven, strengthening him.
B042C022V044	42	22	44	And being in an agony he prayed more earnestly: and his sweat was like great drops of blood falling down to the ground.
B042C022V045	42	22	45	And when he rose up from prayer, and came to his disciples, he found them sleeping for sorrow,
B042C022V046	42	22	46	And said to them, Why do you sleep? rise and pray, that you may not enter into temptation.
B042C022V047	42	22	47	And while he yet spoke, behold a multitude came, and he who was called Judas, one of the twelve, went before them, and drew near to Jesus to kiss him.
B042C022V048	42	22	48	But Jesus said to him, Judas, do you betray the Son of man with a kiss?
B042C022V049	42	22	49	When those who were around him saw what was about to happen, they said to him, Lord, shall we strike with the sword?
B042C022V050	42	22	50	And one of them struck the servant of the high priest, and cut off his right ear.
B042C022V051	42	22	51	And Jesus answered, No more of this. And he touched his ear, and healed him.
B042C022V052	42	22	52	Then Jesus said to the chief priests, and officers of the temple, and the elders, who had come to him, Have you come out, as against a robber, with swords and clubs?
B042C022V053	42	22	53	When I was with you daily in the temple, you did not stretch forth hands against me: but this is your hour, when darkness reigns.
B042C022V054	42	22	54	Then they seized him, and led him away, and brought him into the high priest's house. And Peter followed from afar.
B042C022V055	42	22	55	And when they had kindled a fire in the middle of the courtyard, and sat down together, Peter sat among them.
B042C022V056	42	22	56	But a certain maid beheld him as he sat by the fire, and earnestly looked upon him, and said, This man was also with him.
B042C022V057	42	22	57	And he denied it, saying, Woman, I do not know him.
B042C022V058	42	22	58	And after a little while another saw him, and said, You are also one of them. And Peter said, Man, I am not.
B042C022V059	42	22	59	And after about an hour another insisted, Truly this man was also with him: for he is a Galilaean.
B042C022V060	42	22	60	And Peter said, Man, I do not know what you are saying. And immediately, while he yet spoke, the cock crowed.
B042C022V061	42	22	61	And the Lord turned, and looked at Peter. And Peter remembered the word of the Lord, how he had said to him, Before the cock crows today, you shall deny me thrice.
B042C022V062	42	22	62	And he went out, and wept bitterly.
B042C022V063	42	22	63	And the men who held Jesus mocked him, and struck him.
B042C022V064	42	22	64	And they blindfolded him, and struck him on the face, and asked him, Prophesy, who was it who struck you?
B042C022V065	42	22	65	And they spoke many other insulting things against him.
B042C022V066	42	22	66	And as soon as it was day, the elders of the people and the chief priests and the scribes came together, and led him into their council, saying,
B042C022V067	42	22	67	Are you the Christ? tell us. And he said to them, If I tell you, you will not believe:
B042C022V068	42	22	68	And if I question you, you will not answer me.
B042C022V069	42	22	69	Hereafter shall the Son of man sit on the right hand of the power of God.
B042C022V070	42	22	70	Then they all said, Are you then the Son of God? And he said to them, You say that I am.
B042C022V071	42	22	71	And they said, What need have we of further testimony? for we ourselves have heard from his own mouth.
B042C023V001	42	23	1	And the whole multitude of them arose, and led him to Pilate.
B042C023V002	42	23	2	And they began to accuse him, saying, We found this fellow perverting our nation, and forbidding us to give taxes to Caesar, saying that he himself is Christ a King.
B042C023V003	42	23	3	And Pilate asked him, Are you the King of the Jews? And he answered him, You have said so.
B042C023V004	42	23	4	Then Pilate said to the chief priests and to the people, I find no fault in this man.
B042C023V005	42	23	5	And they were the more fierce, saying, He stirs up the people, teaching throughout all Judaea, beginning in Galilee and coming all the way to this place.
B042C023V006	42	23	6	When Pilate heard this, he asked whether the man was a Galilaean.
B042C023V007	42	23	7	And as soon as he learned that he belonged to Herod's jurisdiction, he sent him to Herod, who was himself also in Jerusalem at that time.
B042C023V008	42	23	8	And when Herod saw Jesus, he was exceedingly glad: for he had long wanted to see him, because he had heard many things about him; and he hoped to see a miracle done by him.
B042C023V009	42	23	9	Then he questioned him at length; but he made no answer.
B042C023V010	42	23	10	The chief priests and scribes stood and vehemently accused him.
B042C023V011	42	23	11	And Herod with his men of war treated him with contempt, and mocked him, and arrayed him in a gorgeous robe, and sent him again to Pilate.
B042C023V012	42	23	12	And that same day Pilate and Herod became friends: for before there had been enmity between them.
B042C023V013	42	23	13	And Pilate, when he had called together the chief priests and the rulers and the people,
B042C023V014	42	23	14	Said to them, You have brought this man to me, as one who perverts the people: but, behold, having examined him before you, I found no fault in this man regarding those things of which you accuse him:
B042C023V015	42	23	15	No, nor did Herod: for I sent you to him; and, lo, nothing worthy of death has been done by him.
B042C023V016	42	23	16	Therefore I will chastise him, and release him.
B042C023V017	42	23	17	[For he was obliged to release one man to them at the feast.]
B042C023V018	42	23	18	But they all cried out at once, saying, Away with this man, and release to us Barabbas:
B042C023V019	42	23	19	(Who for a certain sedition made in the city, and for murder, was cast into prison.)
B042C023V020	42	23	20	Pilate, wanting to release Jesus, spoke to them again.
B042C023V021	42	23	21	But they cried out, saying, Crucify him, crucify him.
B042C023V022	42	23	22	And he said to them a third time, Why, what evil has he done? I have found in him no crime deserving death: therefore I will chastise him, and let him go.
B042C023V023	42	23	23	And they were insistent, with loud voices demanding that he be crucified. And their voices prevailed.
B042C023V024	42	23	24	So Pilate pronounced the sentence they demanded.
B042C023V025	42	23	25	And he released to them the one they asked for, he who had been cast into prison for sedition and murder; but he delivered Jesus over to their will.
B042C023V026	42	23	26	And as they led him away, they laid hold upon one Simon, a Cyrenian, coming in from the country, and on him they laid the cross, that he might carry it after Jesus.
B042C023V027	42	23	27	And there followed him a great company of people, and of women who bewailed and lamented him.
B042C023V028	42	23	28	But Jesus, turning to them, said, Daughters of Jerusalem, do not weep for me, but weep for yourselves, and for your children.
B042C023V029	42	23	29	For, behold, the days are coming when they shall say, Blessed are the barren, and the wombs that never bore, and the breasts which never nursed.
B042C023V030	42	23	30	Then shall they begin to say to the mountains, Fall upon us; and to the hills, Cover us.
B042C023V031	42	23	31	For if they do these things when the wood is green, what shall happen when it is dry?
B042C023V032	42	23	32	And there were also two others, criminals, who were led away with him to be put to death.
B042C023V033	42	23	33	And when they had come to the place, which is called The Skull, there they crucified him, and the criminals, one on the right hand, and the other on the left.
B042C023V034	42	23	34	Then Jesus said, Father, forgive them; for they do not know what they do. And they divided his clothing by casting lots.
B042C023V035	42	23	35	The people stood watching. And the rulers derided him, saying, He saved others; let him save himself, if he is the Christ, the chosen of God.
B042C023V036	42	23	36	And the soldiers also mocked him, coming to him, and offering him wine vinegar,
B042C023V037	42	23	37	And saying, If you are the king of the Jews, save yourself.
B042C023V038	42	23	38	Now there was also an inscription written over him, THIS IS THE KING OF THE JEWS.
B042C023V039	42	23	39	And one of the criminals who was hung there railed at him, saying, If you are the Christ, save yourself and us.
