B042C024V001	42	24	1	Now upon the first day of the week, very early in the morning, they came to the tomb, bringing the spices which they had prepared.
B042C024V002	42	24	2	And they found the stone rolled away from the tomb.
B042C024V003	42	24	3	They entered, but did not find the body of the Lord Jesus.
B042C024V004	42	24	4	And it came to pass, as they were much perplexed about this, behold, two men stood by them in shining garments:
B042C024V005	42	24	5	They were afraid, and bowed their faces to the earth, and the men said to them, Why do you seek the living among the dead?
B042C024V006	42	24	6	He is not here, but has risen: remember how he spoke to you when he was still in Galilee,
B042C024V007	42	24	7	Saying, The Son of man must be delivered into the hands of sinful men, and be crucified, and the third day rise again.
B042C024V008	42	24	8	And they remembered his words,
