B042C024V017	42	24	17	And he said to them, What is it that you are discussing with each other as you walk? And they stood still, looking downcast.
B042C024V018	42	24	18	And one of them, whose name was Cleopas, answered him, Are you the only visitor in Jerusalem who does not know the things which have come to pass there in these days?
B042C024V019	42	24	19	And he said to them, What things? And they said to him, Concerning Jesus of Nazareth, who was a prophet mighty in deed and word before God and all the people:
B042C024V020	42	24	20	And how the chief priests and our rulers delivered him up to be condemned to death, and have crucified him.
B042C024V021	42	24	21	But we trusted that it was he who would redeem Israel: and beside all this, today is the third day since these things happened.
B042C024V022	42	24	22	Yea, and certain women of our company astonished us, for they were at the tomb early;
B042C024V023	42	24	23	And they did not find his body. They came back, saying that they had seen a vision of angels, who said that he was alive.
B042C024V024	42	24	24	And certain of those who were with us went to the tomb, and found it just as the women had said: but him they did not see.
B042C024V025	42	24	25	Then he said to them, O fools, and slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have spoken:
B042C024V026	42	24	26	Was it not necessary for the Christ to have suffered these things, and to enter into his glory?
B042C024V027	42	24	27	And beginning with Moses and all the prophets, he explained to them all the things concerning himself in the scriptures.
B042C024V028	42	24	28	And they drew near to the village, where they were going: and he acted as though he would have gone farther.
B042C024V029	42	24	29	But they urged him strongly, saying, Stay with us: for it is getting toward evening, and the day is nearly over. And he went in to stay with them.
B042C024V030	42	24	30	And it came to pass, as he was at table with them, he took bread, and blessed it, and broke it, and gave it to them.
B042C024V031	42	24	31	And their eyes were opened, and they recognized him; and he vanished out of their sight.
B042C024V032	42	24	32	And they said to one another, Did not our hearts burn within us, while he talked with us along the way, and while he opened to us the scriptures?
B042C024V033	42	24	33	They rose up that same hour, and returned to Jerusalem, and found the eleven gathered together, along with those who were with them,
B042C024V034	42	24	34	Saying, The Lord has risen indeed, and has appeared to Simon.
B042C024V035	42	24	35	And they told what had happened on the road, and how he was recognized by them in the breaking of bread.
B042C024V036	42	24	36	And as they spoke of this, Jesus himself stood in the midst of them, and said to them, Peace be with you.
B042C024V037	42	24	37	But they were terrified and frightened, and supposed that they were seeing a spirit.
B042C024V038	42	24	38	And he said to them, Why are you troubled? and why do doubts arise in your hearts?
B042C024V039	42	24	39	Behold my hands and my feet, that it is I myself: touch me, and see; for a spirit does not have flesh and bones, as you see that I have.
B042C024V040	42	24	40	And when he had thus spoken, he showed them his hands and his feet.
B042C024V041	42	24	41	And while they still did not believe because of joy, and marvelled, he said to them, Have you anything here to eat?
B042C024V042	42	24	42	And they gave him a piece of a broiled fish.
B042C024V043	42	24	43	And he took it, and ate it before them.
B042C024V044	42	24	44	He said to them, These are the words which I spoke to you, while I was yet with you, that all things must be fulfilled which are written about me in the law of Moses, and in the prophets, and in the psalms.
B042C024V045	42	24	45	Then he opened their minds, that they might understand the scriptures,
B042C024V046	42	24	46	And said to them, Thus it is written, that the Christ should suffer, and rise from the dead on the third day:
B042C024V047	42	24	47	And that repentance for forgiveness of sins should be preached in his name among all nations, beginning at Jerusalem.
B042C024V048	42	24	48	You are witnesses of these things.
B042C024V049	42	24	49	And behold, I send the promise of my Father upon you: but stay in the city, until you are clothed with power from on high.
B042C024V050	42	24	50	And he led them out as far as Bethany, and he lifted up his hands, and blessed them.
B042C024V051	42	24	51	And it came to pass, while he blessed them, he was parted from them, and carried up into heaven.
B042C024V052	42	24	52	And they worshipped him, and returned to Jerusalem with great joy:
B042C024V053	42	24	53	And were continually in the temple, praising God.
B043C001V001	43	1	1	In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.
B043C001V002	43	1	2	He was in the beginning with God.
B043C001V003	43	1	3	All things were made by him; and without him was nothing made that was made.
B043C001V004	43	1	4	In him was life; and the life was the light of men.
B043C001V005	43	1	5	And the light shines in the darkness; and the darkness has not comprehended it.
B043C001V006	43	1	6	There was a man sent from God, whose name was John.
B043C001V007	43	1	7	He came as a witness, to bear witness of the Light, that all men through him might believe.
B043C001V008	43	1	8	He was not the Light, but was sent to bear witness to the Light.
B043C001V009	43	1	9	The true Light, which enlightens every man, was coming into the world.
B043C001V010	43	1	10	He was in the world, and the world was made by him, but the world did not know him.
B043C001V011	43	1	11	He came to his own, and his own did not receive him.
B043C001V012	43	1	12	But as many as received him, to them he gave the right to become the children of God, even to those who believe in his name:
B043C001V013	43	1	13	Who were born, not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will of man, but of God.
B043C001V014	43	1	14	And the Word was made flesh, and dwelt among us, (and we beheld his glory, glory as of the only begotten from the Father,) full of grace and truth.
B043C001V015	43	1	15	John bore witness to him, and cried out, saying, This was he of whom I spoke, He who comes after me ranks above me: for he was before me.
B043C001V016	43	1	16	And of his fulness we have all received, and grace upon grace.
B043C001V017	43	1	17	For the law was given by Moses, but grace and truth came through Jesus Christ.
B043C001V018	43	1	18	No man has seen God at any time; but God the only Son, who is in the bosom of the Father, he has made him known.
B043C001V019	43	1	19	And this is the witness of John, when the Jews sent priests and Levites from Jerusalem to ask him, Who are you?
B043C001V020	43	1	20	And he confessed, and did not deny; but confessed, I am not the Christ.
B043C001V021	43	1	21	And they asked him, What then? Are you Elijah? And he said, I am not. Are you the prophet? And he answered, No.
B043C001V022	43	1	22	Then they said to him, Who are you? that we may give an answer to those who sent us. What do you say about yourself?
B043C001V023	43	1	23	He said, I am the voice of one crying out in the wilderness, Make straight the way of the Lord, as the prophet Isaiah said.
B043C001V024	43	1	24	Now they had been sent by the Pharisees.
B043C001V025	43	1	25	And they asked him, Why do you baptize then, if you are not the Christ, or Elijah, or the prophet?
B043C001V026	43	1	26	John answered them, saying, I baptize with water: but one stands among you, whom you do not know;
B043C001V027	43	1	27	It is he who comes after me, the thong of whose sandal I am not worthy to untie.
B043C001V028	43	1	28	These things took place in Bethany, beyond the Jordan, where John was baptizing.
B043C001V029	43	1	29	The next day John saw Jesus coming to him, and said, Behold the Lamb of God, who takes away the sin of the world.
B043C001V030	43	1	30	This is he of whom I said, After me comes a man who ranks above me: for he was before me.
B043C001V031	43	1	31	And I did not know him: but I came baptizing with water that he might be revealed to Israel.
B043C001V032	43	1	32	And John bore witness, saying, I saw the Spirit descending from heaven like a dove, and it remained upon him.
B043C001V033	43	1	33	And I did not know him: but he who sent me to baptize with water said to me, He upon whom you see the Spirit descend and remain, this is he who baptizes with the Holy Spirit.
B043C001V034	43	1	34	And I have seen, and have borne witness that this is the Son of God.
B043C001V035	43	1	35	Again the next day John stood with two of his disciples;
B043C001V036	43	1	36	And looking upon Jesus as he walked, he said, Behold the Lamb of God!
B043C001V037	43	1	37	And the two disciples heard him speak, and they followed Jesus.
B043C001V038	43	1	38	Then Jesus turned, and saw them following, and said to them, What do you seek? They said to him, Rabbi, (which translated means Teacher,) where are you staying?
B043C001V039	43	1	39	He said to them, Come and see. They came and saw where he was staying, and remained with him that day: for it was about the tenth hour.
B043C001V040	43	1	40	One of the two who heard John speak, and followed him, was Andrew, Simon Peter's brother.
B043C001V041	43	1	41	He first found his brother Simon, and said to him, We have found the Messiah, which translated means Christ.
B043C001V042	43	1	42	And he brought him to Jesus. And when Jesus saw him, he said, You are Simon the son of John: you shall be called Cephas, which translated means, Peter.
B043C001V043	43	1	43	The day following Jesus decided to go forth into Galilee; and he found Philip, and said to him, Follow me.
B043C001V044	43	1	44	Now Philip was of Bethsaida, the city of Andrew and Peter.
B043C001V045	43	1	45	Philip found Nathanael, and said to him, We have found him, of whom Moses in the law, and the prophets, wrote about, Jesus of Nazareth, the son of Joseph.
B043C001V046	43	1	46	And Nathanael said to him, Can any good thing come out of Nazareth? Philip said to him, Come and see.
B043C001V047	43	1	47	Jesus saw Nathanael coming to him, and said of him, Behold an Israelite indeed, in whom is no guile!
B043C001V048	43	1	48	Nathanael said to him, How do you know me? Jesus answered and said to him, Before Philip called you, when you were under the fig tree, I saw you.
B043C001V049	43	1	49	Nathanael answered and said to him, Rabbi, you are the Son of God; you are the King of Israel.
B043C001V050	43	1	50	Jesus answered him, Because I said to you, I saw you under the fig tree, do you believe? you shall see greater things than these.
B043C001V051	43	1	51	And he said to him, Truly, truly, I say to you, You shall see heaven opened, and the angels of God ascending and descending upon the Son of man.
B043C002V001	43	2	1	On the third day there was a marriage in Cana of Galilee; and the mother of Jesus was there:
B043C002V002	43	2	2	And both Jesus and his disciples were invited to the marriage.
B043C002V003	43	2	3	And when the wine gave out, the mother of Jesus said to him, They have no wine.
B043C002V004	43	2	4	Jesus said to her, Woman, what have I to do with you? my hour has not yet come.
B043C002V005	43	2	5	His mother said to the servants, Whatever he says to you, do it.
B043C002V006	43	2	6	Now there were six waterpots of stone set there, for the Jewish custom of purification, containing twenty or thirty gallons apiece.
B043C002V007	43	2	7	Jesus said to them, Fill the waterpots with water. And they filled them up to the brim.
B043C002V008	43	2	8	And he said to them, Now draw some out, and take it to the steward of the feast. So they took it.
B043C002V009	43	2	9	When the steward of the feast tasted the water that had become wine, and did not know where it came from: (but the servants who drew the water knew;) the steward of the feast called the bridegroom,
B043C002V010	43	2	10	And said to him, Every man serves the good wine at the beginning; and when men have drunk freely, then that which is worse: but you have kept the good wine until now.
B043C002V011	43	2	11	This, the beginning of his miraculous signs, Jesus performed in Cana of Galilee, and manifested his glory; and his disciples believed in him.
B043C002V012	43	2	12	After this he went down to Capernaum, he, and his mother, and his brothers, and his disciples: and they stayed there not many days.
B043C002V013	43	2	13	And the passover of the Jews was at hand, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem,
B043C002V014	43	2	14	And found in the temple those who sold oxen and sheep and doves, and the changers of money sitting there:
B043C002V015	43	2	15	And when he had made a whip of small cords, he drove them all out of the temple, with the sheep, and the oxen; and he poured out the changers' money, and overturned their tables;
B043C002V016	43	2	16	And said to those who sold doves, Take these things away; do not make my Father's house a house of merchandise.
B043C002V017	43	2	17	And his disciples remembered that it was written, Zeal for your house will consume me.
B043C002V018	43	2	18	Then the Jews answered and said to him, What sign do you show us, seeing that you do these things?
B043C002V019	43	2	19	Jesus answered and said to them, Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it up.
B043C002V020	43	2	20	Then the Jews said, It took forty-six years to build this temple, and will you raise it up in three days?
B043C002V021	43	2	21	But he spoke of the temple of his body.
B043C002V022	43	2	22	Therefore, when he had risen from the dead, his disciples remembered he had said this to them; and they believed the scripture, and the word which Jesus had spoken.
B043C002V023	43	2	23	Now when he was in Jerusalem at the passover, during the feast, many believed in his name, when they saw the miraculous signs which he did.
B043C002V024	43	2	24	But Jesus did not entrust himself to them, because he knew all men,
B043C002V025	43	2	25	And needed no one to testify about man: for he himself knew what was in man.
B043C003V001	43	3	1	There was a man of the Pharisees, named Nicodemus, a ruler of the Jews:
B043C003V002	43	3	2	He came to Jesus by night, and said to him, Rabbi, we know that you are a teacher come from God: for no man can do the miraculous signs that you do, unless God is with him.
B043C003V003	43	3	3	Jesus answered and said to him, Truly, truly, I say to you, Unless a man is born again, he cannot see the kingdom of God.
B043C003V004	43	3	4	Nicodemus said to him, How can a man be born when he is old? can he enter a second time into his mother's womb, and be born?
B043C003V005	43	3	5	Jesus answered, Truly, truly, I say to you, Unless a man is born of water and the Spirit, he cannot enter the kingdom of God.
B043C003V006	43	3	6	That which is born of the flesh is flesh; and that which is born of the Spirit is spirit.
B043C003V007	43	3	7	Do not marvel that I said to you, You must be born again.
B043C003V008	43	3	8	The wind blows where it wishes, and you hear the sound of it, but can not tell from where it comes, and where it goes: so it is with everyone who is born of the Spirit.
B043C003V009	43	3	9	Nicodemus answered and said to him, How can these things be?
B043C003V010	43	3	10	Jesus answered and said to him, Are you a teacher of Israel, and do not know these things?
B043C003V011	43	3	11	Truly, truly, I say to you, We speak what we know, and testify of what we have seen; but you do not receive our testimony.
B043C003V012	43	3	12	If I have told you earthly things, and you do not believe, how shall you believe, if I tell you of heavenly things?
B043C003V013	43	3	13	No man has ascended to heaven, but he who came down from heaven, the Son of man.
B043C003V014	43	3	14	And as Moses lifted up the serpent in the wilderness, so must the Son of man be lifted up:
B043C003V015	43	3	15	That whoever believes in him may have eternal life.
B043C003V016	43	3	16	For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whoever believes in him should not perish, but have eternal life.
B043C003V017	43	3	17	For God did not send his Son into the world to condemn the world; but that the world might be saved through him.
B043C003V018	43	3	18	He who believes in him is not condemned: but he who does not believe is condemned already, because he has not believed in the name of the only begotten Son of God.
B043C003V019	43	3	19	And this is the judgment, that the light has come into the world, and men loved darkness rather than light, because their deeds were evil.
B043C003V020	43	3	20	For everyone who does evil hates the light, and does not come to the light, lest his deeds should be exposed.
B043C003V021	43	3	21	But he who practices the truth comes to the light, that his deeds may be shown to have been done through God.
B043C003V022	43	3	22	After these things Jesus and his disciples came into the land of Judaea; and there he remained with them, and baptized.
B043C003V023	43	3	23	And John also was baptizing in Aenon near Salim, because there was much water there: and people came, and were baptized.
B043C003V024	43	3	24	For John had not yet been cast into prison.
B043C003V025	43	3	25	Then there arose a question between some of John's disciples and a Jew about purifying.
B043C003V026	43	3	26	And they came to John, and said to him, Rabbi, he who was with you beyond the Jordan, to whom you bore witness, behold, he is baptizing, and all men are going to him.
B043C003V027	43	3	27	John answered, A man can receive nothing, unless it has been given to him from heaven.
B043C003V028	43	3	28	You yourselves bear me witness, that I said, I am not the Christ, but that I have been sent before him.
B043C003V029	43	3	29	He who has the bride is the bridegroom: but the friend of the bridegroom, who stands and hears him, rejoices greatly because of the bridegroom's voice: therefore this joy of mine is fulfilled.
B043C003V030	43	3	30	He must increase, but I must decrease.
B043C003V031	43	3	31	He who comes from above is above all: he who is of the earth is earthly, and speaks of the earth: he who comes from heaven is above all.
B043C003V032	43	3	32	And what he has seen and heard, to that he testifies; yet no man receives his testimony.
B043C003V033	43	3	33	He who has received his testimony has set his seal to this, that God is true.
B043C003V034	43	3	34	For he whom God has sent speaks the words of God: for God gives the Spirit without measure.
B043C003V035	43	3	35	The Father loves the Son, and has given all things into his hand.
B043C003V036	43	3	36	He who believes in the Son has eternal life: but he who disobeys the Son shall not see life; but the wrath of God rests upon him.
B043C004V001	43	4	1	Therefore, when the Lord learned that the Pharisees had heard that Jesus made and baptized more disciples than John,
B043C004V002	43	4	2	(Though Jesus himself did not baptize, but his disciples,)
B043C004V003	43	4	3	He left Judaea, and departed again into Galilee.
B043C004V004	43	4	4	And he had to go through Samaria.
B043C004V005	43	4	5	Then he came to a city of Samaria, which is called Sychar, near the parcel of ground that Jacob gave to his son Joseph.
B043C004V006	43	4	6	Now Jacob's well was there. Jesus, therefore, being wearied from his journey, sat by the well: and it was about the sixth hour.
B043C004V007	43	4	7	There came a woman of Samaria to draw water: Jesus said to her, Give me a drink.
B043C004V008	43	4	8	(For his disciples had gone away to the city to buy food.)
B043C004V009	43	4	9	Then the woman of Samaria said to him, How is it that you, being a Jew, ask for a drink from me, a woman of Samaria? for the Jews have no dealings with the Samaritans.
B043C004V010	43	4	10	Jesus answered and said to her, If you knew the gift of God, and who it is who says to you, Give me a drink; you would have asked him, and he would have given you living water.
B043C004V011	43	4	11	The woman said to him, Sir, you have nothing to draw with, and the well is deep: from where do you get that living water?
B043C004V012	43	4	12	Are you greater than our father Jacob, who gave us the well, and drank from it himself, and his children, and his cattle?
B043C004V013	43	4	13	Jesus answered and said to her, Whoever drinks of this water shall thirst again:
B043C004V014	43	4	14	But whoever drinks of the water that I shall give him shall never thirst; but the water that I shall give him shall be in him a well of water springing up into eternal life.
B043C004V015	43	4	15	The woman said to him, Sir, give me this water, that I may not thirst, nor come here to draw.
B043C004V016	43	4	16	Jesus said to her, Go, call your husband, and come here.
B043C004V017	43	4	17	The woman answered and said, I have no husband. Jesus said to her, You have well said, I have no husband:
B043C004V018	43	4	18	For you have had five husbands; and he whom you now have is not your husband: in that you spoke truly.
B043C004V019	43	4	19	The woman said to him, Sir, I perceive that you are a prophet.
B043C004V020	43	4	20	Our fathers worshipped on this mountain; but you say that Jerusalem is the place where men ought to worship.
B043C004V021	43	4	21	Jesus said to her, Woman, believe me, the hour comes when you shall worship the Father neither on this mountain, nor in Jerusalem.
B043C004V022	43	4	22	You do not know what you worship: we know what we worship: for salvation is from the Jews.
B043C004V023	43	4	23	But the hour comes, and now is, when the true worshippers shall worship the Father in spirit and in truth: for the Father seeks such to worship him.
B043C004V024	43	4	24	God is Spirit: and those who worship him must worship him in spirit and in truth.
B043C004V025	43	4	25	The woman said to him, I know that Messiah comes, who is called Christ: when he comes, he will tell us all things.
B043C004V026	43	4	26	Jesus said to her, I who speak to you am he.
B043C004V027	43	4	27	And at this moment his disciples came, and marvelled that he was speaking with a woman: yet no one said, What do you seek? or, Why are you talking with her?
B043C004V028	43	4	28	Then the woman left her waterpot, and went into the city, and said to the people,
B043C004V029	43	4	29	Come, see a man who told me all that I ever did: is this not the Christ?
B043C004V030	43	4	30	Then they went out of the city, and came to him.
B043C004V031	43	4	31	In the meanwhile his disciples urged him, saying, Rabbi, eat.
B043C004V032	43	4	32	But he said to them, I have food to eat of which you know nothing.
B043C004V033	43	4	33	Therefore the disciples said to one another, Has any man brought him food?
B043C004V034	43	4	34	Jesus said to them, My food is to do the will of him who sent me, and to finish his work.
B043C004V035	43	4	35	Do you not say, There are yet four months, and then comes harvest? behold, I say to you, Lift up your eyes, and look on the fields; for they are already white for harvest.
B043C004V036	43	4	36	And he who reaps receives wages, and gathers fruit for life eternal: that both he who sows and he who reaps may rejoice together.
B043C004V037	43	4	37	And here the saying holds true, One sows, and another reaps.
B043C004V038	43	4	38	I sent you to reap that upon which you bestowed no labour: other men laboured, and you have entered into their labours.
B043C004V039	43	4	39	And many of the Samaritans of that city believed in him because of the words of the woman's testimony, He told me all that I ever did.
B043C004V040	43	4	40	So when the Samaritans came to him, they begged him to stay with them: and he stayed there two days.
B043C004V041	43	4	41	And many more believed because of his own word;
B043C004V042	43	4	42	And they said to the woman, Now we believe, no longer because of your words: for now we have heard him ourselves, and know that this is indeed the Christ, the Saviour of the world.
B043C004V043	43	4	43	Now after two days he departed from there, and went into Galilee.
B043C004V044	43	4	44	For Jesus himself testified, that a prophet has no honour in his own country.
B043C004V045	43	4	45	When he came to Galilee, the Galilaeans welcomed him, having seen all the things that he did in Jerusalem at the feast: for they also went to the feast.
B043C004V046	43	4	46	So Jesus came again to Cana of Galilee, where he had made the water into wine. And there was a certain royal official, whose son was sick at Capernaum.
B043C004V047	43	4	47	When he heard that Jesus had come out of Judaea into Galilee, he went to him, and begged him to come down, and heal his son: for he was at the point of death.
B043C004V048	43	4	48	Then Jesus said to him, Unless you see signs and wonders, you will not believe.
B043C004V049	43	4	49	The royal official said to him, Sir, come down before my child dies.
B043C004V050	43	4	50	Jesus said to him, Go your way; your son lives. And the man believed the word that Jesus had spoken to him, and he went his way.
B043C004V051	43	4	51	And as he was going down, his servants met him, and told him, Your son lives.
B043C004V052	43	4	52	Then he enquired of them the hour when he began to mend. And they said to him, Yesterday at the seventh hour the fever left him.
B043C004V053	43	4	53	Then the father realized that this was the very hour when Jesus said to him, Your son lives: and he believed, and his whole household.
B043C004V054	43	4	54	This was the second miraculous sign Jesus did after he came out of Judaea into Galilee.
B043C005V001	43	5	1	After this there was a feast of the Jews; and Jesus went up to Jerusalem.
B043C005V002	43	5	2	Now there is in Jerusalem by the sheep gate a pool, which is called in the Hebrew tongue Bethesda, and which has five porches.
B043C005V003	43	5	3	On these lay a great multitude of disabled, blind, lame, and paralysed people, [waiting for the moving of the water.
B043C005V004	43	5	4	For an angel went down at certain seasons into the pool, and stirred up the water: whoever then first stepped into the water after the stirring up was cured of whatever disease he had.]
B043C005V005	43	5	5	And a certain man was there, who had an infirmity for thirty-eight years.
B043C005V006	43	5	6	When Jesus saw him lying there, and knew that he had been a long time in that condition, he said to him, Do you want to be made well?
B043C005V007	43	5	7	The sick man answered him, Sir, I have no man to put me into the pool when the water is stirred up: but while I am coming, another steps down before me.
B043C005V008	43	5	8	Jesus said to him, Rise, take up your mat, and walk.
B043C005V009	43	5	9	And immediately the man was made whole, and took up his mat, and walked: Now that day was the sabbath.
B043C005V010	43	5	10	The Jews therefore said to the man who was cured, It is the sabbath day: it is not lawful for you to carry your mat.
B043C005V011	43	5	11	He answered them, He who made me well said to me, Take up your mat, and walk.
B043C005V012	43	5	12	Then they asked him, What man is it who said to you, Take up your mat, and walk?
B043C005V013	43	5	13	But the man who was healed did not know who it was: for Jesus had quietly withdrawn while there was a crowd in that place.
B043C005V014	43	5	14	Afterward Jesus found him in the temple, and said to him, Behold, you have been made well: sin no more, lest something worse come upon you.
B043C005V015	43	5	15	The man departed, and told the Jews that it was Jesus who had made him well.
B043C005V016	43	5	16	And therefore the Jews persecuted Jesus, because he had done these things on the sabbath day.
B043C005V017	43	5	17	But Jesus answered them, My Father works even until now, and I work.
B043C005V018	43	5	18	Therefore the Jews sought all the more to kill him, because he not only had broken the sabbath, but also said that God was his Father, making himself equal with God.
B043C005V019	43	5	19	Then Jesus answered and said to them, Truly, truly, I say to you, The Son can do nothing by himself, but only what he sees the Father doing: for whatever things he does, these things the Son does likewise.
B043C005V020	43	5	20	For the Father loves the Son, and shows him all things that he is doing: and he will show him greater works than these, that you may marvel.
B043C005V021	43	5	21	For as the Father raises up the dead, and gives them life; even so the Son gives life to whom he will.
B043C005V022	43	5	22	For the Father judges no man, but has committed all judgment to the Son:
B043C005V023	43	5	23	That all men should honour the Son, even as they honour the Father. He who does not honour the Son does not honour the Father who has sent him.
B043C005V024	43	5	24	Truly, truly, I say to you, He who hears my word, and believes him who sent me, has eternal life, and shall not come into judgment; but has passed from death into life.
B043C005V025	43	5	25	Truly, truly, I say to you, The hour is coming, and now is, when the dead shall hear the voice of the Son of God: and those who hear shall live.
B043C005V026	43	5	26	For as the Father has life in himself; so he has granted to the Son to have life in himself;
B043C005V027	43	5	27	And has given him authority to execute judgment, because he is the Son of man.
B043C005V028	43	5	28	Do not marvel at this: for the hour is coming, in which all who are in the tombs shall hear his voice,
B043C005V029	43	5	29	And shall come forth; those who have done good, to the resurrection of life; and those who have done evil, to the resurrection of judgment.
B043C005V030	43	5	30	I can do nothing by myself: as I hear, I judge: and my judgment is just; because I do not seek my own will, but the will of him who sent me.
B043C005V031	43	5	31	If I bear witness to myself, my witness is not true.
B043C005V032	43	5	32	There is another who bears witness of me; and I know that the witness which he bears of me is true.
B043C005V033	43	5	33	You sent to John, and he bore witness to the truth.
B043C005V034	43	5	34	Not that the testimony I receive is from man: but these things I say, that you might be saved.
B043C005V035	43	5	35	He was a burning and a shining light: and you were willing for a season to rejoice in his light.
B043C005V036	43	5	36	But I have a greater witness than that of John: for the works which the Father has given me to finish, the very works that I do, these bear witness of me, that the Father has sent me.
B043C005V037	43	5	37	And the Father himself, who has sent me, has borne witness of me. You have neither heard his voice at any time, nor seen his form.
B043C005V038	43	5	38	And you do not have his word abiding in you: for you do not believe him whom he has sent.
B043C005V039	43	5	39	You search the scriptures; for in them you think you have eternal life: and it is they that testify of me.
B043C005V040	43	5	40	Yet you will not come to me, that you might have life.
B043C005V041	43	5	41	I do not receive honour from men.
B043C005V042	43	5	42	But I know you, that you do not have the love of God in you.
B043C005V043	43	5	43	I have come in my Father's name, and you do not receive me: if another shall come in his own name, him you will receive.
B043C005V044	43	5	44	How can you believe, when you receive honour from one another, and do not seek the honour that comes from him who alone is God?
B043C005V045	43	5	45	Do not think that I will accuse you to the Father: there is one who accuses you, Moses, in whom you trust.
B043C005V046	43	5	46	For had you believed Moses, you would have believed me: for he wrote of me.
B043C005V047	43	5	47	But if you do not believe his writings, how shall you believe my words?
B043C006V001	43	6	1	After these things Jesus went over the sea of Galilee, that is, the sea of Tiberias.
B043C006V002	43	6	2	And a great multitude followed him, because they saw the miraculous signs which he performed on those who were diseased.
B043C006V003	43	6	3	And Jesus went up on the mountain, and there he sat with his disciples.
B043C006V004	43	6	4	And the passover, the feast of the Jews, was near.
B043C006V005	43	6	5	When Jesus lifted up his eyes, and saw a great company coming to him, he said to Philip, Where shall we buy bread, that these may eat?
B043C006V006	43	6	6	And this he said to test him: for he knew what he would do.
B043C006V007	43	6	7	Philip answered him, Two hundred denarii of bread is not sufficient for every one of them to have a little.
B043C006V008	43	6	8	One of his disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter's brother, said to him,
B043C006V009	43	6	9	There is a lad here, who has five barley loaves, and two small fish: but what are they among so many?
B043C006V010	43	6	10	And Jesus said, Make the people sit down. Now there was much grass in the place; so the men sat down, in number about five thousand.
B043C006V011	43	6	11	And Jesus took the loaves; and when he had given thanks, he distributed to those who were seated; and he did likewise with the fish, as much as they wanted.
B043C006V012	43	6	12	When they were filled, he said to his disciples, Gather up the fragments that remain, that nothing may be lost.
B043C006V013	43	6	13	Therefore they gathered them together, and filled twelve baskets with the fragments of the five barley loaves left over by those who had eaten.
B043C006V014	43	6	14	Then those men, when they had seen the miraculous sign that Jesus did, said, This is truly the prophet who is to come into the world.
B043C006V015	43	6	15	When Jesus perceived that they would come and take him by force, to make him a king, he departed again to the mountain by himself.
B043C006V016	43	6	16	And when evening came, his disciples went down to the sea,
B043C006V017	43	6	17	And entered into a boat, and went over the sea toward Capernaum. And it was now dark, and Jesus had not come to them.
B043C006V018	43	6	18	And the sea arose because of a great wind that blew.
B043C006V019	43	6	19	So when they had rowed about three or four miles, they saw Jesus walking on the sea, and drawing near to the boat: and they were afraid.
B043C006V020	43	6	20	But he said to them, It is I; do not be afraid.
B043C006V021	43	6	21	Then they gladly received him into the boat: and immediately the boat was at the land where they were going.
B043C006V022	43	6	22	The day following, the people who stood on the other side of the sea saw that there was no other boat there, except the one into which his disciples had entered, and that Jesus did not go with his disciples into the boat, but that his disciples had gone away alone.
B043C006V023	43	6	23	But now some other boats came from Tiberias near to the place where they ate bread after the Lord had given thanks.
B043C006V024	43	6	24	When the people saw that Jesus was not there, nor his disciples, they got into the small boats, and came to Capernaum, seeking Jesus.
B043C006V025	43	6	25	And when they had found him on the other side of the sea, they said to him, Rabbi, when did you come here?
B043C006V026	43	6	26	Jesus answered them and said, Truly, truly, I say to you, You seek me, not because you saw the miraculous signs, but because you ate of the loaves, and were filled.
B043C006V027	43	6	27	Do not labour for the food which perishes, but for that food which endures to eternal life, which the Son of man shall give to you: for on him has God the Father set his seal.
B043C006V028	43	6	28	Then they said to him, What shall we do, that we might work the works of God?
B043C006V029	43	6	29	Jesus answered and said to them, This is the work of God, that you believe in him whom he has sent.
B043C006V030	43	6	30	Therefore they said to him, What sign do you show then, that we may see, and believe you? what work do you perform?
B043C006V031	43	6	31	Our fathers ate manna in the desert; as it is written, He gave them bread from heaven to eat.
B043C006V032	43	6	32	Then Jesus said to them, Truly, truly, I say to you, Moses did not give you the bread from heaven; but my Father gives you the true bread from heaven.
B043C006V033	43	6	33	For the bread of God is he who comes down from heaven, and gives life to the world.
B043C006V034	43	6	34	Then they said to him, Lord, give us this bread always.
B043C006V035	43	6	35	And Jesus said to them, I am the bread of life: he who comes to me shall never hunger; and he who believes in me shall never thirst.
B043C006V036	43	6	36	But I said to you, That you have seen me, and do not believe.
B043C006V037	43	6	37	All those whom the Father gives me shall come to me; and he who comes to me I will by no means cast out.
B043C006V038	43	6	38	For I came down from heaven, not to do my own will, but the will of him who sent me.
B043C006V039	43	6	39	And this is the will of him who sent me, that of all he has given me I should lose nothing, but should raise it up on the last day.
B043C006V040	43	6	40	And this is the will of my Father, that every one who sees the Son, and believes in him, may have eternal life: and I will raise him up on the last day.
B043C006V041	43	6	41	Then the Jews murmured at him, because he said, I am the bread which came down from heaven.
B043C006V042	43	6	42	And they said, Is this not Jesus, the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know? how is it then that he now says, I came down from heaven?
B043C006V043	43	6	43	Jesus answered and said to them, Do not murmur among yourselves.
B043C006V044	43	6	44	No man can come to me, unless the Father who sent me draws him: and I will raise him up on the last day.
B043C006V045	43	6	45	It is written in the prophets, And they shall all be taught by God. Therefore, every man who has heard, and has learned from the Father, comes to me.
B043C006V046	43	6	46	Not that any man has seen the Father, except he who is from God; he has seen the Father.
B043C006V047	43	6	47	Truly, truly, I say to you, He who believes has eternal life.
B043C006V048	43	6	48	I am the bread of life.
B043C006V049	43	6	49	Your fathers ate manna in the wilderness, and are dead.
B043C006V050	43	6	50	This is the bread which comes down from heaven, that a man may eat of it and not die.
B043C006V051	43	6	51	I am the living bread which came down from heaven: if any man eat of this bread, he shall live forever: and the bread that I will give is my flesh, which I will give for the life of the world.
B043C006V052	43	6	52	The Jews then argued among themselves, saying, How can this man give us his flesh to eat?
B043C006V053	43	6	53	Then Jesus said to them, Truly, truly, I say to you, Unless you eat the flesh of the Son of man, and drink his blood, you have no life in you.
B043C006V054	43	6	54	Whoever eats my flesh, and drinks my blood, has eternal life; and I will raise him up on the last day.
B043C006V055	43	6	55	For my flesh is food indeed, and my blood is drink indeed.
B043C006V056	43	6	56	He who eats my flesh, and drinks my blood, dwells in me, and I in him.
B043C006V057	43	6	57	As the living Father sent me, and I live by the Father: so he who eats me shall live because of me.
B043C006V058	43	6	58	This is the bread which came down from heaven: not as the fathers ate manna, and died: he who eats this bread shall live forever.
B043C006V059	43	6	59	These things he said in the synagogue, as he taught in Capernaum.
B043C006V060	43	6	60	Many of his disciples, when they heard this, said, This is a hard saying; who can hear it?
B043C006V061	43	6	61	But Jesus, knowing in himself that his disciples murmured at this, said to them, Does this offend you?
B043C006V062	43	6	62	What then if you should see the Son of man ascend to where he was before?
B043C006V063	43	6	63	The spirit gives life; the flesh profits nothing: the words I speak to you are spirit and life.
B043C006V064	43	6	64	But there are some of you who do not believe. For Jesus knew from the beginning those who did not believe, and who would betray him.
B043C006V065	43	6	65	And he said, Therefore I said to you, that no one can come to me, unless it is granted to him by the Father.
B043C006V066	43	6	66	From that time many of his disciples drew back, and no longer walked with him.
B043C006V067	43	6	67	Then Jesus said to the twelve, Do you also want to go away?
B043C006V068	43	6	68	Then Simon Peter answered him, Lord, to whom shall we go? you have the words of eternal life.
B043C006V069	43	6	69	And we believe and have come to know that you are the Christ, the Son of the living God.
B043C006V070	43	6	70	Jesus answered them, Have not I chosen you twelve, and one of you is a devil?
B043C006V071	43	6	71	He spoke of Judas Iscariot the son of Simon: for it was he, one of the twelve, who would betray him.
B043C007V001	43	7	1	After these things Jesus walked in Galilee: for he would not walk in Judaea, because the Jews sought to kill him.
B043C007V002	43	7	2	Now the Jewish feast of tabernacles was at hand.
B043C007V003	43	7	3	His brothers said to him, Depart from here, and go into Judaea, that your disciples may also see the works that you do.
B043C007V004	43	7	4	For there is no man who does anything in secret, if he seeks to be known openly. If you do these things, show yourself to the world.
B043C007V005	43	7	5	For his brothers did not believe in him either.
B043C007V006	43	7	6	Then Jesus said to them, My time has not yet come: but your time is always here.
B043C007V007	43	7	7	The world cannot hate you; but me it hates, because I testify of it, that its works are evil.
B043C007V008	43	7	8	You go up to this feast: I am not going up to this feast; for my time has not yet fully come.
B043C007V009	43	7	9	When he had said these words to them, he remained in Galilee.
B043C007V010	43	7	10	But when his brothers had gone up, then he also went up to the feast, not openly, but as it were in secret.
B043C007V011	43	7	11	Then the Jews sought him at the feast, and said, Where is he?
B043C007V012	43	7	12	And there was much murmuring among the people concerning him: for some said, He is a good man: others said, No; he deceives the people.
B043C007V013	43	7	13	Yet no man spoke openly of him for fear of the Jews.
B043C007V014	43	7	14	Now about the middle of the feast Jesus went up into the temple, and taught.
B043C007V015	43	7	15	And the Jews marvelled, saying, How has this man become learned, having never studied?
B043C007V016	43	7	16	Jesus answered them, and said, My teaching is not mine, but his who sent me.
B043C007V017	43	7	17	If any man is willing to do his will, he shall know of the teaching, whether it is of God, or whether I speak from myself.
B043C007V018	43	7	18	He who speaks from himself seeks his own glory: but he who seeks the glory of the one who sent him, he is true, and there is no unrighteousness in him.
B043C007V019	43	7	19	Did not Moses give you the law, and yet none of you keeps the law? Why do you seek to kill me?
B043C007V020	43	7	20	The people answered and said, You have a devil: who seeks to kill you?
B043C007V021	43	7	21	Jesus answered and said to them, I have done one work, and you all marvel.
B043C007V022	43	7	22	Moses gave you circumcision; (though it is not from Moses, but from the fathers;) and on the sabbath day you circumcise a man.
B043C007V023	43	7	23	If a man may receive circumcision on the sabbath day, that the law of Moses should not be broken; are you angry at me, because I have made an entire man well on the sabbath day?
B043C007V024	43	7	24	Do not judge according to appearance, but judge righteously.
B043C007V025	43	7	25	Then some people of Jerusalem said, Is this not the man whom they seek to kill?
B043C007V026	43	7	26	But, lo, he speaks openly, and they say nothing to him. Do the rulers really know that this is the Christ?
B043C007V027	43	7	27	Yet we know where this man is from: but when the Christ comes, no man will know where he is from.
B043C007V028	43	7	28	Then Jesus cried out in the temple as he taught, saying, You both know me, and you know where I am from: and I have not come of my own accord, but he who sent me is true, and him you do not know.
B043C007V029	43	7	29	But I know him: for I am from him, and he has sent me.
B043C007V030	43	7	30	Then they sought to seize him: but no man laid hands on him, because his hour had not yet come.
B043C007V031	43	7	31	And many of the people believed in him, and said, When the Christ comes, will he do more miraculous signs than this man has done?
B043C007V032	43	7	32	The Pharisees heard the people muttering such things about him; and the chief priests and Pharisees sent officers to arrest him.
B043C007V033	43	7	33	Then Jesus said to them, Yet for a little while shall I be with you, and then I go to him who sent me.
B043C007V034	43	7	34	You shall seek me, and shall not find me: and where I am, there you cannot come.
B043C007V035	43	7	35	Then the Jews said among themselves, Where will he go, that we shall not find him? will he go to those dispersed among the Greeks, and teach the Greeks?
B043C007V036	43	7	36	What manner of saying is this, You shall seek me, and shall not find me: and where I am, there you cannot come?
B043C007V037	43	7	37	On the last day, the great day of the feast, Jesus stood and cried out, If any man thirst, let him come to me, and drink.
B043C007V038	43	7	38	He who believes in me, as the scripture has said, out of his innermost being shall flow rivers of living water.
B043C007V039	43	7	39	(But this he spoke of the Spirit, which those who believe in him were to receive: for the Holy Spirit had not yet been given; because Jesus was not yet glorified.)
B043C007V040	43	7	40	Many of the people, when they heard this, said, Truly this is the Prophet.
B043C007V041	43	7	41	Others said, This is the Christ. But some said, Shall Christ come out of Galilee?
B043C007V042	43	7	42	Has not the scripture said, That Christ comes from the seed of David, and out of the town of Bethlehem, the village where David lived?
B043C007V043	43	7	43	So there was a division among the people because of him.
B043C007V044	43	7	44	And some would have seized him; but no man laid hands on him.
B043C007V045	43	7	45	Then the officers came to the chief priests and Pharisees; who said to them, Why have you not brought him?
B043C007V046	43	7	46	The officers answered, Never did a man speak like this man.
B043C007V047	43	7	47	Then the Pharisees answered them, Are you also deceived?
B043C007V048	43	7	48	Have any of the rulers or the Pharisees believed in him?
B043C007V049	43	7	49	But this crowd, which does not know the law, is cursed.
B043C007V050	43	7	50	Nicodemus (who came to Jesus earlier, and who was one of them) said to them,
B043C007V051	43	7	51	Does our law judge any man, before it hears him, and knows what he is doing?
B043C007V052	43	7	52	They answered and said to him, Are you also from Galilee? Search, and see: no prophet arises out of Galilee.
B043C007V053	43	7	53	[And everyone went to his own house.
B043C008V001	43	8	1	But Jesus went to the mount of Olives.
B043C008V002	43	8	2	And early in the morning he came again into the temple, and all the people came to him; and he sat down, and taught them.
B043C008V003	43	8	3	And the scribes and Pharisees brought to him a woman caught in adultery; and when they had placed her in the midst,
B043C008V004	43	8	4	They said to him, Teacher, this woman was caught in adultery, in the very act.
B043C008V005	43	8	5	Now Moses, in the law, commanded us to stone such women; but what do you say?
B043C008V006	43	8	6	This they said, testing him, that they might have grounds to accuse him. But Jesus stooped down, and with his finger wrote on the ground.
B043C008V007	43	8	7	But when they continued asking him, he stood up, and said to them, He who is without sin among you, let him be the first to cast a stone at her.
B043C008V008	43	8	8	And again he stooped down, and wrote on the ground.
B043C008V009	43	8	9	And when they heard it, they went out one by one, beginning with the eldest: and Jesus was left alone, with the woman standing there.
B043C008V010	43	8	10	When Jesus stood up, and saw no one but the woman, he said to her, Woman, where are your accusers? has no man condemned you?
B043C008V011	43	8	11	She said, No man, Lord. And Jesus said to her, Neither do I condemn you: go, and sin no more.]
B043C008V012	43	8	12	Then Jesus spoke again to them, saying, I am the light of the world: he who follows me shall not walk in darkness, but shall have the light of life.
B043C008V013	43	8	13	Therefore, the Pharisees said to him, You bear testimony of yourself; your testimony is not true.
B043C008V014	43	8	14	Jesus answered and said to them, Though I bear testimony of myself, yet my testimony is true: for I know where I came from, and where I go; but you do not know where I come from, or where I go.
B043C008V015	43	8	15	You judge after the flesh; I judge no man.
B043C008V016	43	8	16	And yet if I do judge, my judgment is true: for I am not alone, but I am with he who sent me.
B043C008V017	43	8	17	It is also written in your law, that the testimony of two men is true.
B043C008V018	43	8	18	I am one who bears witness of myself, and the Father who sent me bears witness of me.
B043C008V019	43	8	19	Then they said to him, Where is your Father? Jesus answered, You neither know me, nor my Father: if you had known me, you would have known my Father also.
B043C008V020	43	8	20	These words Jesus spoke in the treasury, as he taught in the temple: and no man laid hands on him; for his hour had not yet come.
B043C008V021	43	8	21	Then Jesus said again to them, I go my way, and you shall seek me, and shall die in your sins: where I go, you cannot come.
B043C008V022	43	8	22	Then the Jews said, Will he kill himself? because he said, Where I go, you cannot come.
B043C008V023	43	8	23	And he said to them, You are from below; I am from above: you are of this world; I am not of this world.
B043C008V024	43	8	24	Therefore I said to you, that you shall die in your sins: for if you do not believe that I am he, you shall die in your sins.
B043C008V025	43	8	25	Then they said to him, Who are you? And Jesus said to them, That which I have been saying to you from the beginning.
B043C008V026	43	8	26	I have many things to say and to judge about you: but he who sent me is true; and I speak to the world those things which I have heard from him.
B043C008V027	43	8	27	They did not understood that he spoke to them of the Father.
B043C008V028	43	8	28	Then Jesus said to them, When you have lifted up the Son of man, then you shall know that I am he, and that I do nothing by myself; but I speak these things as my Father has taught me.
B043C008V029	43	8	29	And he who sent me is with me: the Father has not left me alone; for I always do those things that please him.
B043C008V030	43	8	30	As he spoke these words, many believed in him.
B043C008V031	43	8	31	Then Jesus said to those Jews who believed in him, If you continue in my word, then you are my disciples indeed;
B043C008V032	43	8	32	And you shall know the truth, and the truth shall make you free.
B043C008V033	43	8	33	They answered him, We are Abraham's seed, and were never in bondage to any man: how is it that you say, You shall be made free?
B043C008V034	43	8	34	Jesus answered them, Truly, truly, I say to you, Whoever commits sin is the slave of sin.
B043C008V035	43	8	35	And the slave does not abide in the house forever: but the Son abides forever.
B043C008V036	43	8	36	If the Son shall make you free, you shall be free indeed.
B043C008V037	43	8	37	I know that you are Abraham's seed; but you seek to kill me, because my word has no place in you.
B043C008V038	43	8	38	I speak that which I have seen in the presence of my Father: and you do that which you have heard from your father.
B043C008V039	43	8	39	They answered and said to him, Abraham is our father. Jesus said to them, If you were Abraham's children, you would do the works of Abraham.
B043C008V040	43	8	40	But now you seek to kill me, a man who has told you the truth, which I have heard from God: this Abraham did not do.
B043C008V041	43	8	41	You do the deeds of your father. Then they said to him, We are not illegitimate children; we have one Father, even God.
B043C008V042	43	8	42	Jesus said to them, If God were your Father, you would love me: for I proceeded forth and came from God; for I did not come of my own accord, but he sent me.
B043C008V043	43	8	43	Why do you not understand my speech? it is because you cannot bear to hear my word.
B043C008V044	43	8	44	You are of your father the devil, and you want to do the desires of your father. He was a murderer from the beginning, and does not stand in the truth, because there is no truth in him. When he speaks a lie, he speaks from his own nature: for he is a liar, and the father of lies.
B043C008V045	43	8	45	And because I tell you the truth, you do not believe me.
B043C008V046	43	8	46	Which of you convicts me of sin? And if I say the truth, why do you not believe me?
B043C008V047	43	8	47	He who is of God hears God's words: therefore you do not hear them, because you are not of God.
B043C008V048	43	8	48	Then the Jews answered and said to him, Do we not rightly say that you are a Samaritan, and have a devil?
B043C008V049	43	8	49	Jesus answered, I do not have a devil; but I honour my Father, and you dishonour me.
B043C008V050	43	8	50	I do not seek my own glory: but there is one who seeks it, and he is the judge.
B043C008V051	43	8	51	Truly, truly, I say to you, If anyone keeps my word, he shall never see death.
B043C008V052	43	8	52	Then the Jews said to him, Now we know that you have a devil. Abraham is dead, and the prophets; and you say, If anyone keeps my word, he shall never taste of death.
B043C008V053	43	8	53	Are you greater than our father Abraham, who is dead? and the prophets are also dead: whom do you make yourself out to be?
B043C008V054	43	8	54	Jesus answered, If I glorify myself, my glory is nothing: it is my Father who glorifies me; of whom you say, that he is your God:
B043C008V055	43	8	55	Yet you have not known him; but I know him: and if I should say, I do not know him, I would be a liar like you: but I do know him, and keep his word.
B043C008V056	43	8	56	Your father Abraham rejoiced to see my day: and he saw it, and was glad.
B043C008V057	43	8	57	Then the Jews said to him, You are not yet fifty years old, and have you seen Abraham?
B043C008V058	43	8	58	Jesus said to them, Truly, truly, I say to you, Before Abraham was, I am.
B043C008V059	43	8	59	Then they took up stones to cast at him: but Jesus hid himself, and went out of the temple.
B043C009V001	43	9	1	And as he passed by, he saw a man who was blind from his birth.
B043C009V002	43	9	2	And his disciples asked him, Rabbi, who sinned, this man, or his parents, that he was born blind?
B043C009V003	43	9	3	Jesus answered, It was not that this man sinned, or his parents: but it was so the works of God would be made manifest in him.
B043C009V004	43	9	4	We must work the works of him who sent me, while it is day: the night comes, when no man can work.
B043C009V005	43	9	5	As long as I am in the world, I am the light of the world.
B043C009V006	43	9	6	When he had said this, he spat on the ground, and made clay of the spittle, and he anointed the eyes of the blind man with the clay,
B043C009V007	43	9	7	And said to him, Go, wash in the pool of Siloam, (which means, Sent.) He went his way, and washed, and came back seeing.
B043C009V008	43	9	8	The neighbours, and those who had seen him before as a beggar, said, Is this not the one who sat and begged?
B043C009V009	43	9	9	Some said, This is he: others said, No, but he is like him: but he said, I am the one.
B043C009V010	43	9	10	Therefore they said to him, How were your eyes opened?
B043C009V011	43	9	11	He answered and said, A man who is called Jesus made clay, and anointed my eyes, and said to me, Go to Siloam, and wash: and I went and washed, and I received my sight.
B043C009V012	43	9	12	Then they said to him, Where is he? He said, I do not know.
B043C009V013	43	9	13	They brought to the Pharisees him who had been blind.
B043C009V014	43	9	14	And it was the sabbath day when Jesus made the clay, and opened his eyes.
B043C009V015	43	9	15	Then again the Pharisees asked him how he had received his sight. He said to them, He put clay on my eyes, and I washed, and I see.
B043C009V016	43	9	16	Therefore, some of the Pharisees said, This man is not of God, because he does not keep the sabbath day. Others said, How can a man who is a sinner do such miraculous signs? And there was a division among them.
B043C009V017	43	9	17	They said to the blind man again, What do you say of him, since he opened your eyes? He said, He is a prophet.
B043C009V018	43	9	18	But the Jews did not believe that he had been blind, and received his sight, until they called the parents of the one who had received his sight.
B043C009V019	43	9	19	And they asked them, Is this your son, who you say was born blind? how then does he now see?
B043C009V020	43	9	20	His parents answered them and said, We know that this is our son, and that he was born blind:
B043C009V021	43	9	21	But by what means he now sees, we do not know; or who has opened his eyes, we do not know: he is of age; ask him: he shall speak for himself.
B043C009V022	43	9	22	His parents said this because they feared the Jews: for the Jews had agreed already, that if any man confessed him to be the Christ, he would be put out of the synagogue.
B043C009V023	43	9	23	Therefore his parents said, He is of age; ask him.
B043C009V024	43	9	24	Then again they called the man who was blind, and said to him, Give God the praise: we know that this man is a sinner.
B043C009V025	43	9	25	He answered and said, Whether he is a sinner, I do not know: one thing I do know, that, though I was blind, now I see.
B043C009V026	43	9	26	Then they said to him again, What did he do to you? how did he open your eyes?
B043C009V027	43	9	27	He answered them, I have told you already, and you did not listen: why do you want to hear it again? do you also want to be his disciples?
B043C009V028	43	9	28	Then they reviled him, and said, You are his disciple; but we are Moses' disciples.
B043C009V029	43	9	29	We know that God spoke to Moses: as for this man, we know not where he comes from.
B043C009V030	43	9	30	The man answered and said to them, Why, this is a marvellous thing; you do not know where he is from, yet he has opened my eyes.
B043C009V031	43	9	31	Now we know that God does not hear sinners: but if any man is a worshipper of God, and does his will, he hears him.
B043C009V032	43	9	32	Since the world began it has not been heard that any man opened the eyes of one who was born blind.
B043C009V033	43	9	33	If this man were not from God, he could do nothing.
B043C009V034	43	9	34	They answered and said to him, You were born in utter sin, and do you teach us? And they cast him out.
B043C009V035	43	9	35	Jesus heard that they had cast him out; and when he had found him, he said to him, Do you believe in the Son of man?
B043C009V036	43	9	36	He answered and said, Who is he, Lord, that I might believe in him?
B043C009V037	43	9	37	And Jesus said to him, You have both seen him, and it is he who talks with you.
B043C009V038	43	9	38	And he said, Lord, I believe. And he worshipped him.
B043C009V039	43	9	39	And Jesus said, For judgment I came into this world, that those who do not see might see; and that those who see might be made blind.
B043C009V040	43	9	40	And some of the Pharisees who were with him heard these words, and said to him, Are we blind also?
B043C009V041	43	9	41	Jesus said to them, If you were blind, you would have no sin: but now you say, We see; therefore your sin remains.
B043C010V001	43	10	1	Truly, truly, I say to you, He who does not enter by the door into the sheepfold, but climbs in by some other way, he is a thief and a robber.
B043C010V002	43	10	2	But he who enters by the door is the shepherd of the sheep.
B043C010V003	43	10	3	To him the gatekeeper opens; and the sheep hear his voice: and he calls his sheep by name, and leads them out.
B043C010V004	43	10	4	And when he has brought out all his own, he goes before them, and the sheep follow him: for they know his voice.
B043C010V005	43	10	5	A stranger they will not follow, but will flee from him: for they do not know the voice of strangers.
B043C010V006	43	10	6	Jesus spoke this parable to them: but they did not understand what he was saying to them.
B043C010V007	43	10	7	Then Jesus said to them again, Truly, truly, I say to you, I am the door of the sheep.
B043C010V008	43	10	8	All who came before me are thieves and robbers: but the sheep did not hear them.
B043C010V009	43	10	9	I am the door: if any man enters by me, he shall be saved, and shall go in and out, and find pasture.
B043C010V010	43	10	10	The thief comes only to steal, and to kill, and to destroy: I have come that they might have life, and that they might have it more abundantly.
B043C010V011	43	10	11	I am the good shepherd: the good shepherd lays down his life for the sheep.
B043C010V012	43	10	12	But he who is a hireling, and not the shepherd, who does not own the sheep, sees the wolf coming, and leaves the sheep, and flees: and the wolf attacks them, and scatters the sheep.
B043C010V013	43	10	13	The hireling flees, because he is a hireling, and does not care for the sheep.
B043C010V014	43	10	14	I am the good shepherd, and I know my own, and my own know me,
B043C010V015	43	10	15	Just as the Father knows me, and I know the Father: and I lay down my life for the sheep.
B043C010V016	43	10	16	And I have other sheep, which are not of this fold: I must bring them also, and they shall hear my voice; and there shall be one fold, and one shepherd.
B043C010V017	43	10	17	Therefore my Father loves me, because I lay down my life, that I might take it up again.
B043C010V018	43	10	18	No man takes it from me, but I lay it down of my own accord. I have power to lay it down, and I have power to take it up again. This commandment I have received from my Father.
B043C010V019	43	10	19	There was again a division among the Jews because of these words.
B043C010V020	43	10	20	And many of them said, He has a devil, and is mad; why do you listen to him?
B043C010V021	43	10	21	Others said, These are not the words of one who has a devil. Can a devil open the eyes of the blind?
B043C010V022	43	10	22	And it was the feast of the dedication in Jerusalem, and it was winter.
B043C010V023	43	10	23	And Jesus walked in the temple in Solomon's porch.
B043C010V024	43	10	24	Then the Jews came round about him, and said to him, How long will you keep us in suspense? If you are the Christ, tell us plainly.
B043C010V025	43	10	25	Jesus answered them, I told you, and you do not believe: the works that I do in my Father's name, they bear witness of me.
B043C010V026	43	10	26	But you do not believe, because you are not my sheep.
B043C010V027	43	10	27	My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me:
B043C010V028	43	10	28	And I give them eternal life; and they shall never perish, nor shall any man pluck them out of my hand.
B043C010V029	43	10	29	My Father, who gave them to me, is greater than all; and no man is able to pluck them out of my Father's hand.
B043C010V030	43	10	30	I and the Father are one.
B043C010V031	43	10	31	Then the Jews took up stones again to stone him.
B043C010V032	43	10	32	Jesus answered them, I have shown you many good works from my Father; for which of those works do you stone me?
B043C010V033	43	10	33	The Jews answered him, saying, We do not stone you for a good work; but for blasphemy; because you, being a man, make yourself out to be God.
B043C010V034	43	10	34	Jesus answered them, Is it not written in your law, I said, You are gods?
B043C010V035	43	10	35	If he called them gods, to whom the word of God came, and the scripture cannot be broken;
B043C010V036	43	10	36	Do you say of him, whom the Father has sanctified, and sent into the world, You blaspheme; because I said, I am the Son of God?
B043C010V037	43	10	37	If I do not do the works of my Father, do not believe me.
B043C010V038	43	10	38	But if I do them, though you do not believe me, believe the works: that you may know, and believe, that the Father is in me, and I am in the Father.
B043C010V039	43	10	39	Therefore they sought again to seize him: but he escaped from their hands,
B043C010V040	43	10	40	And went away again beyond the Jordan into the place where John first baptized; and there he abode.
B043C010V041	43	10	41	And many came to him, and said, John did no miraculous sign: but all things that John spoke of this man were true.
B043C010V042	43	10	42	And many believed in him there.
B043C011V001	43	11	1	Now a certain man named Lazarus was sick. He was of Bethany, the town of Mary and her sister Martha.
B043C011V002	43	11	2	(It was Mary who anointed the Lord with ointment, and wiped his feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was sick.)
B043C011V003	43	11	3	Therefore his sisters sent to him, saying, Lord, behold, he whom you love is sick.
B043C011V004	43	11	4	When Jesus heard that, he said, This sickness is not to death, but for the glory of God, that the Son of God might be glorified through it.
B043C011V005	43	11	5	Now Jesus loved Martha, and her sister, and Lazarus.
B043C011V006	43	11	6	Therefore, when he heard that he was sick, he remained for two more days where he was.
B043C011V007	43	11	7	Then after that he said to his disciples, Let us go to Judaea again.
B043C011V008	43	11	8	His disciples said to him, Rabbi, the Jews were just recently seeking to stone you; and would you go there again?
B043C011V009	43	11	9	Jesus answered, Are there not twelve hours in the day? If any man walks in the day, he does not stumble, because he sees the light of this world.
B043C011V010	43	11	10	But if a man walks in the night, he stumbles, because there is no light in him.
B043C011V011	43	11	11	These things he spoke: and then he said to them, Our friend Lazarus sleeps; but I go, that I may awaken him.
B043C011V012	43	11	12	Then his disciples said, Lord, if he is sleeping, he shall recover.
B043C011V013	43	11	13	Yet Jesus spoke of his death: but they thought that he had spoken of natural sleep.
B043C011V014	43	11	14	Then Jesus said to them plainly, Lazarus is dead.
B043C011V015	43	11	15	And I am glad for your sakes that I was not there, so that you may believe; but let us go to him.
B043C011V016	43	11	16	Then Thomas, who is called Didymus, said to his fellow disciples, Let us also go, that we may die with him.
B043C011V017	43	11	17	When Jesus came, he found that he had been in the tomb four days already.
B043C011V018	43	11	18	Now Bethany was near Jerusalem, less than two miles off:
B043C011V019	43	11	19	And many of the Jews came to Martha and Mary, to comfort them concerning their brother.
B043C011V020	43	11	20	Then Martha, as soon as she heard that Jesus was coming, went and met him: but Mary sat in the house.
B043C011V021	43	11	21	Then Martha said to Jesus, Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have died.
B043C011V022	43	11	22	But I know, that even now, whatever you ask of God, God will give you.
B043C011V023	43	11	23	Jesus said to her, Your brother shall rise again.
B043C011V024	43	11	24	Martha said to him, I know that he shall rise again in the resurrection on the last day.
B043C011V025	43	11	25	Jesus said to her, I am the resurrection, and the life: he who believes in me, though he die, yet shall he live:
B043C011V026	43	11	26	And whoever lives and believes in me shall never die. Do you believe this?
B043C011V027	43	11	27	She said to him, Yes, Lord: I believe that you are the Christ, the Son of God, who was to come into the world.
B043C011V028	43	11	28	And when she said this, she went her way, and called Mary her sister quietly, saying, The Teacher has come, and is calling for you.
B043C011V029	43	11	29	As soon as she heard this, she rose quickly, and came to him.
B043C011V030	43	11	30	Now Jesus had not yet come into the town, but was still at the place where Martha had met him.
B043C011V031	43	11	31	When the Jews who were with her in the house, comforting her, saw that Mary rose up hastily and went out, they followed her, supposing that she was going to the tomb to weep there.
B043C011V032	43	11	32	Then when Mary came to where Jesus was, and saw him, she fell down at his feet, saying to him, Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have died.
B043C011V033	43	11	33	Therefore, when Jesus saw her weeping, and the Jews also weeping who came with her, he was deeply moved, and was troubled,
B043C011V034	43	11	34	And said, Where have you laid him? They said to him, Lord, come and see.
B043C011V035	43	11	35	Jesus wept.
B043C011V036	43	11	36	Then the Jews said, Behold how he loved him!
B043C011V037	43	11	37	But some of them said, Could not this man, who opened the eyes of the blind, have kept this man from dying?
B043C011V038	43	11	38	Jesus, again deeply moved within himself, came to the tomb. It was a cave, and a stone lay upon it.
B043C011V039	43	11	39	Jesus said, Take away the stone. Martha, the sister of the dead man, said to him, Lord, by this time he stinks: for he has been dead four days.
B043C011V040	43	11	40	Jesus said to her, Did I not say to you, that, if you would believe, you would see the glory of God?
B043C011V041	43	11	41	Then they took away the stone. And Jesus lifted up his eyes, and said, Father, I thank you that you have heard me.
B043C011V042	43	11	42	And I knew that you always hear me: but because of the people who stand here I said it, that they may believe that you have sent me.
B043C011V043	43	11	43	And when he had said this, he cried out with a loud voice, Lazarus, come forth.
B043C011V044	43	11	44	And the dead man came forth, bound hand and foot with graveclothes: and his face was wrapped with a cloth. Jesus said to them, Unbind him, and let him go.
B043C011V045	43	11	45	Then many of the Jews who came with Mary, and had seen the things which Jesus did, believed in him.
B043C011V046	43	11	46	But some of them went away to the Pharisees, and told them the things Jesus had done.
B043C011V047	43	11	47	Then the chief priests and the Pharisees gathered a council, and said, What should we do? for this man performs many miraculous signs.
B043C011V048	43	11	48	If we let him go on like this, all men will believe in him: and the Romans shall come and take away both our place and our nation.
B043C011V049	43	11	49	And one of them, named Caiaphas, who was the high priest that year, said to them, You know nothing at all,
B043C011V050	43	11	50	Nor do you consider that it is expedient for you, that one man should die for the people, so that the whole nation should not perish.
B043C011V051	43	11	51	And this he did not speak of his own accord: but being high priest that year, he prophesied that Jesus should die for the nation;
B043C011V052	43	11	52	And not for that nation only, but also that he should gather together into one the children of God who are scattered abroad.
B043C011V053	43	11	53	Then from that day forth they planned together how to put him to death.
B043C011V054	43	11	54	Therefore Jesus no longer walked openly among the Jews; but went away from there to a region near the wilderness, into a city called Ephraim, and there he stayed with his disciples.
B043C011V055	43	11	55	And the Jewish passover was near at hand: and many from the country went up to Jerusalem before the passover, to purify themselves.
B043C011V056	43	11	56	They sought for Jesus, and spoke among themselves, as they stood in the temple, What do you think, that he will not come to the feast?
B043C011V057	43	11	57	Now the chief priests and the Pharisees had given a commandment, that, if any man knew where he was, he should report it, that they might seize him.
B043C012V001	43	12	1	Six days before the passover Jesus came to Bethany, where Lazarus was, whom Jesus raised from the dead.
B043C012V002	43	12	2	There they made him a supper; and Martha served: and Lazarus was one of those at the table with him.
B043C012V003	43	12	3	Then Mary took a pound of ointment of pure nard, very costly, and anointed the feet of Jesus, and wiped his feet with her hair: and the house was filled with the fragrance of the ointment.
B043C012V004	43	12	4	Then one of his disciples, Judas Iscariot, who would later betray him, said,
B043C012V005	43	12	5	Why was this ointment not sold for three hundred denarii, and given to the poor?
B043C012V006	43	12	6	He said this, not because he cared for the poor; but because he was a thief, and had the money box, and stole what was put in it.
B043C012V007	43	12	7	Then Jesus said, Let her alone: she has kept it for the day of my burial.
B043C012V008	43	12	8	For the poor you have with you always; but me you do not always have.
B043C012V009	43	12	9	Now a large multitude of the Jews learned that he was there: and they came not only because of Jesus, but also that they might see Lazarus, whom he had raised from the dead.
B043C012V010	43	12	10	But the chief priests discussed how they might put Lazarus to death also;
B043C012V011	43	12	11	Because on account of him many of the Jews went away, and believed in Jesus.
B043C012V012	43	12	12	On the next day many people who had come to the feast, when they heard that Jesus was coming to Jerusalem,
B043C012V013	43	12	13	Took branches of palm trees, and went forth to meet him, and cried out, Hosanna: Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord, even the King of Israel.
B043C012V014	43	12	14	And Jesus, when he had found a young donkey, sat on it; as it is written,
B043C012V015	43	12	15	Fear not, daughter of Zion: behold, your King comes, sitting on a donkey's colt.
B043C012V016	43	12	16	These things his disciples did not understand at first: but when Jesus was glorified, then they remembered that these things were written of him, and that they had done these things to him.
B043C012V017	43	12	17	Now the people who were with him when he called Lazarus out of his grave, and raised him from the dead, kept bearing witness.
B043C012V018	43	12	18	For this cause also the people went out to meet him, because they heard that he had done this miraculous sign.
B043C012V019	43	12	19	Therefore the Pharisees said among themselves, You see, you have accomplished nothing: behold, the world has gone after him.
B043C012V020	43	12	20	And there were certain Greeks among those who came up to worship at the feast:
B043C012V021	43	12	21	They came to Philip, who was from Bethsaida of Galilee, and said to him, Sir, we want to see Jesus.
B043C012V022	43	12	22	Philip came and told Andrew: then Andrew and Philip told Jesus.
B043C012V023	43	12	23	And Jesus answered them, saying, The hour has come for the Son of man to be glorified.
B043C012V024	43	12	24	Truly, truly, I say to you, Unless a grain of wheat falls into the ground and dies, it remains alone: but if it dies, it brings forth much fruit.
B043C012V025	43	12	25	He who loves his life shall lose it; and he who hates his life in this world shall keep it for life eternal.
B043C012V026	43	12	26	If any man serves me, let him follow me; and where I am, there shall my servant be also: if any man serves me, the Father will honour him.
B043C012V027	43	12	27	Now is my soul troubled; and shall I say, Father, save me from this hour? but it is for this reason that I came to this hour.
B043C012V028	43	12	28	Father, glorify your name. Then there came a voice from heaven, saying, I have both glorified it, and will glorify it again.
B043C012V029	43	12	29	The crowd that stood by, and heard it, said that it thundered: others said, An angel spoke to him.
B043C012V030	43	12	30	Jesus answered and said, This voice came not for me, but for your sakes.
B043C012V031	43	12	31	Now is the judgment of this world: now shall the prince of this world be cast out.
B043C012V032	43	12	32	And I, if I be lifted up from the earth, will draw all men to myself.
B043C012V033	43	12	33	This he said, to signify what sort of death he should die.
B043C012V034	43	12	34	The people answered him, We have heard out of the law that the Christ abides forever: and how is it that you say, The Son of man must be lifted up? who is this Son of man?
B043C012V035	43	12	35	Then Jesus said to them, Yet for a little while is the light with you. Walk while you have the light, lest darkness overtake you: for he who walks in darkness does not know where he goes.
B043C012V036	43	12	36	While you have light, believe in the light, that you may be sons of light. These things Jesus spoke, and departed, and hid himself from them.
B043C012V037	43	12	37	But though he had done so many miraculous signs before them, yet they did not believe in him:
B043C012V038	43	12	38	That the word spoken by Isaiah the prophet might be fulfilled, Lord, who has believed our report? and to whom has the arm of the Lord been revealed?
B043C012V039	43	12	39	Therefore they could not believe, because as Isaiah also said,
B043C012V040	43	12	40	He has blinded their eyes, and hardened their heart; that they should not see with their eyes, nor understand with their hearts, and turn to me, that I should heal them.
B043C012V041	43	12	41	These things Isaiah said because he saw his glory and spoke of him.
B043C012V042	43	12	42	Nevertheless, even among the chief rulers, many believed in him; but because of the Pharisees they did not confess him, lest they should be put out of the synagogue:
B043C012V043	43	12	43	For they loved the praise of men more than the praise of God.
B043C012V044	43	12	44	Jesus cried out and said, He who believes in me, believes not in me, but in him who sent me.
B043C012V045	43	12	45	And he who sees me sees him who sent me.
B043C012V046	43	12	46	I have come as a light into the world, that whoever believes in me should not abide in darkness.
B043C012V047	43	12	47	And if any man hears my words, and does not believe, I do not judge him: for I did not come to judge the world, but to save the world.
B043C012V048	43	12	48	He who rejects me, and does not receive my words, has one who judges him: the word that I have spoken, that shall judge him on the last day.
B043C012V049	43	12	49	For I have not spoken of my own accord; but the Father who sent me, he commanded what I should say, and what I should speak.
B043C012V050	43	12	50	And I know that his commandment is life eternal: therefore, whatever I speak, I speak as the Father has bidden me.
B043C013V001	43	13	1	Now before the feast of the passover, when Jesus knew that his hour had come to depart out of this world to the Father, having loved his own who were in the world, he loved them to the end.
B043C013V002	43	13	2	It was during supper, and the devil had already put into the heart of Judas Iscariot, Simon's son, to betray Jesus.
B043C013V003	43	13	3	Knowing that the Father had given all things into his hands, and that he had come from God, and was returning to God;
B043C013V004	43	13	4	Jesus rose from supper, and laid aside his garments; and took a towel, and girded himself.
B043C013V005	43	13	5	After that he poured water into a basin, and began to wash the disciples' feet, and to wipe them with the towel with which he was girded.
B043C013V006	43	13	6	Then he came to Simon Peter: and Peter said to him, Lord, do you wash my feet?
B043C013V007	43	13	7	Jesus answered and said to him, What I do you do not understand now; but you shall understand later.
B043C013V008	43	13	8	Peter said to him, You shall never wash my feet. Jesus answered him, If I do not wash you, you have no part with me.
B043C013V009	43	13	9	Simon Peter said to him, Lord, not only my feet, but also my hands and my head.
B043C013V010	43	13	10	Jesus said to him, He who has bathed needs only to wash his feet, but he is clean all over: and you are clean, but not all of you.
B043C013V011	43	13	11	For he knew who would betray him; therefore he said, Not all of you are clean.
B043C013V012	43	13	12	So after he had washed their feet, and had put on his garments, and had taken his place again, he said to them, Do you know what I have done to you?
B043C013V013	43	13	13	You call me Teacher and Lord: and you say well; for so I am.
B043C013V014	43	13	14	If I then, your Lord and Teacher, have washed your feet; you also ought to wash one another's feet.
B043C013V015	43	13	15	For I have given you an example, that you should do as I have done to you.
B043C013V016	43	13	16	Truly, truly, I say to you, The servant is not greater than his lord; neither is he who is sent greater than he who sent him.
B043C013V017	43	13	17	If you know these things, happy are you if you do them.
B043C013V018	43	13	18	I do not speak of all of you: I know whom I have chosen: but it is that the scripture may be fulfilled, He who eats bread with me has lifted up his heel against me.
B043C013V019	43	13	19	Now I tell you before it happens, that, when it has come to pass, you may believe that I am he.
B043C013V020	43	13	20	Truly, truly, I say to you, He who receives whomever I send receives me; and he who receives me receives him who sent me.
B043C013V021	43	13	21	When Jesus had said this, he was troubled in spirit, and testified, Truly, truly, I say to you, that one of you shall betray me.
B043C013V022	43	13	22	Then the disciples looked at one another, uncertain of whom he spoke.
B043C013V023	43	13	23	Now there was leaning on Jesus' bosom one of his disciples, whom Jesus loved.
B043C013V024	43	13	24	Therefore Simon Peter beckoned to him, that he should ask of whom he spoke.
B043C013V025	43	13	25	He, lying on Jesus' breast, said to him, Lord, who is it?
B043C013V026	43	13	26	Jesus answered, It is he to whom I shall give this morsel, when I have dipped it. And when he had dipped the morsel, he gave it to Judas Iscariot, the son of Simon.
B043C013V027	43	13	27	And after the morsel, Satan entered into him. Then Jesus said to him, What you do, do quickly.
B043C013V028	43	13	28	Now no man at the table knew why he spoke this to him.
B043C013V029	43	13	29	Some of them thought, because Judas had the money box, that Jesus had said to him, Buy those things that we need for the feast; or, that he should give something to the poor.
B043C013V030	43	13	30	Having received the morsel he went out immediately: and it was night.
B043C013V031	43	13	31	When he had gone out, Jesus said, Now is the Son of man glorified, and God is glorified in him.
B043C013V032	43	13	32	If God is glorified in him, God shall also glorify him in himself, and shall immediately glorify him.
B043C013V033	43	13	33	Little children, yet a little while I am with you. You shall seek me: and as I said to the Jews, so now I say to you: Where I go, you cannot come.
B043C013V034	43	13	34	A new commandment I give to you, That you love one another; as I have loved you, so you also love one another.
B043C013V035	43	13	35	By this shall all men know that you are my disciples, if you have love for one another.
B043C013V036	43	13	36	Simon Peter said to him, Lord, where are you going? Jesus answered him, Where I go, you cannot follow me now; but you shall follow me afterwards.
B043C013V037	43	13	37	Peter said to him, Lord, why can I not follow you now? I will lay down my life for your sake.
B043C013V038	43	13	38	Jesus answered him, Will you lay down your life for my sake? Truly, truly, I say to you, The cock shall not crow, until you have denied me thrice.
B043C014V001	43	14	1	Let not your hearts be troubled: believe in God, believe also in me.
B043C014V002	43	14	2	In my Father's house are many dwelling places: if it were not so, I would have told you. I go to prepare a place for you.
B043C014V003	43	14	3	And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again, and receive you to myself; that where I am, there you may be also.
B043C014V004	43	14	4	And you know the way to the place where I go.
B043C014V005	43	14	5	Thomas said to him, Lord, we do not know where you are going; so how can we know the way?
B043C014V006	43	14	6	Jesus said to him, I am the way, the truth, and the life: no man comes to the Father, but by me.
B043C014V007	43	14	7	If you had known me, you would have known my Father also: and from henceforth you know him, and have seen him.
B043C014V008	43	14	8	Philip said to him, Lord, show us the Father, and it will satisfy us.
B043C014V009	43	14	9	Jesus said to him, Have I been so long with you, and yet you do not know me, Philip? he who has seen me has seen the Father; and how then do you say, Show us the Father?
B043C014V010	43	14	10	Do you not believe that I am in the Father, and the Father in me? the words that I speak to you I do not speak of my own accord: but the Father who dwells in me, he does his works.
B043C014V011	43	14	11	Believe me that I am in the Father, and the Father in me: or else believe me because of the works themselves.
B043C014V012	43	14	12	Truly, truly, I say to you, He who believes in me, the works that I do he shall do also; and he shall do greater works than these; because I go to my Father.
B043C014V013	43	14	13	And whatever you shall ask in my name, that will I do, that the Father may be glorified in the Son.
B043C014V014	43	14	14	If you shall ask anything in my name, I will do it.
B043C014V015	43	14	15	If you love me, you will keep my commandments.
B043C014V016	43	14	16	And I will pray to the Father, and he shall give you another Comforter, that he may abide with you forever;
B043C014V017	43	14	17	That is the Spirit of truth; whom the world cannot receive, because it does not see him, neither does it know him: but you know him; for he dwells with you, and shall be in you.
B043C014V018	43	14	18	I will not leave you comfortless: I will come to you.
B043C014V019	43	14	19	Yet a little while, and the world will see me no more; but you shall see me: because I live, you also shall live.
B043C014V020	43	14	20	On that day you shall know that I am in my Father, and you in me, and I in you.
B043C014V021	43	14	21	He who has my commandments, and keeps them, he it is who loves me: and he who loves me shall be loved by my Father, and I will love him, and will manifest myself to him.
B043C014V022	43	14	22	Judas, not Iscariot, said to him, Lord, how is it that you will manifest yourself to us, and not to the world?
B043C014V023	43	14	23	Jesus answered and said to him, If a man loves me, he will keep my word: and my Father will love him, and we will come to him, and make our abode with him.
B043C014V024	43	14	24	He who does not love me does not keep my words: and the word which you hear is not mine, but the Father's who sent me.
B043C014V025	43	14	25	These things I have spoken to you while I am still present with you.
B043C014V026	43	14	26	But the Comforter, the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my name, he shall teach you all things, and bring all things to your remembrance, whatever I have said to you.
B043C014V027	43	14	27	Peace I leave with you, my peace I give to you: not as the world gives, do I give to you. Let not your heart be troubled, neither let it be afraid.
B043C014V028	43	14	28	You have heard how I said to you, I go away, and come again to you. If you loved me, you would rejoice, because I said, I go to the Father: for my Father is greater than I.
B043C014V029	43	14	29	And now I have told you before it comes to pass, that, when it has come to pass, you might believe.
B043C014V030	43	14	30	Hereafter I will not talk much with you: for the prince of this world comes; he has no power over me,
B043C014V031	43	14	31	But that the world may know that I love the Father, and as the Father commanded me, even so I do. Arise, let us go from here.
B043C015V001	43	15	1	I am the true vine, and my Father is the vinedresser.
B043C015V002	43	15	2	Every branch in me that does not bear fruit he takes away: and every branch that bears fruit, he prunes it, that it may bring forth more fruit.
B043C015V003	43	15	3	Now you are clean through the word which I have spoken to you.
B043C015V004	43	15	4	Abide in me, and I in you. As the branch cannot bear fruit by itself, unless it abides in the vine; neither can you, unless you abide in me.
B043C015V005	43	15	5	I am the vine, you are the branches: He who abides in me, and I in him, the same brings forth much fruit: for without me you can do nothing.
B043C015V006	43	15	6	If a man does not abide in me, he is thrown away as a branch, and withers; and men gather them, and cast them into the fire, and they are burned.
B043C015V007	43	15	7	If you abide in me, and my words abide in you, ask whatever you wish, and it shall be done for you.
B043C015V008	43	15	8	By this is my Father glorified, that you bear much fruit; and so prove to be my disciples.
B043C015V009	43	15	9	As the Father has loved me, so I have loved you: abide in my love.
B043C015V010	43	15	10	If you keep my commandments, you shall abide in my love; even as I have kept my Father's commandments, and abide in his love.
B043C015V011	43	15	11	These things have I spoken to you, that my joy might remain in you, and that your joy might be full.
B043C015V012	43	15	12	This is my commandment, That you love one another, as I have loved you.
B043C015V013	43	15	13	Greater love has no man than this, that a man lay down his life for his friends.
B043C015V014	43	15	14	You are my friends, if you do what I command you.
B043C015V015	43	15	15	No longer do I call you servants; for the servant does not know what his lord is doing: but I have called you friends; for all things that I have heard from my Father I have made known to you.
B043C015V016	43	15	16	You have not chosen me, but I have chosen you, and appointed you to go and bring forth fruit, and that your fruit should remain: so that whatever you shall ask from the Father in my name, he may give it to you.
B043C015V017	43	15	17	This I command you, that you love one another.
B043C015V018	43	15	18	If the world hates you, know that it hated me before it hated you.
B043C015V019	43	15	19	If you were of the world, the world would love its own: but because you are not of the world, because I have chosen you out of the world, therefore the world hates you.
B043C015V020	43	15	20	Remember the word that I said to you, The servant is not greater than his lord. If they have persecuted me, they will also persecute you; if they have kept my word, they will keep yours also.
B043C015V021	43	15	21	But all these things they will do to you for my name's sake, because they do not know him who sent me.
B043C015V022	43	15	22	If I had not come and spoken to them, they would not have sin: but now they have no excuse for their sin.
B043C015V023	43	15	23	He who hates me hates my Father also.
B043C015V024	43	15	24	If I had not done among them the works which no other man has done, they would not have sin: but now they have seen and hated both me and my Father.
B043C015V025	43	15	25	But this came to pass, that the word might be fulfilled that is written in their law, They hated me without a cause.
B043C015V026	43	15	26	But when the Comforter comes, whom I will send to you from the Father, even the Spirit of truth, who proceeds from the Father, he shall testify of me:
B043C015V027	43	15	27	And you also shall bear witness, because you have been with me from the beginning.
B043C016V001	43	16	1	These things have I spoken to you, that you should not stumble.
B043C016V002	43	16	2	They shall put you out of the synagogues: yea, the time comes when whoever kills you will think that he is serving God.
B043C016V003	43	16	3	And these things they will do to you, because they have not known the Father, nor me.
B043C016V004	43	16	4	But these things I have spoken to you, that when the time shall come, you may remember that I told you of them. These things I did not say to you at the beginning, because I was with you.
B043C016V005	43	16	5	But now I go to him who sent me; and none of you asks me, Where are you going?
B043C016V006	43	16	6	But because I have said these things to you, sorrow has filled your heart.
B043C016V007	43	16	7	Nevertheless, I tell you the truth; It is for your good that I go away: for if I do not go away, the Comforter will not come to you; but if I depart, I will send him to you.
B043C016V008	43	16	8	And when he has come, he will convict the world of sin, and of righteousness, and of judgment:
B043C016V009	43	16	9	Of sin, because they do not believe in me;
B043C016V010	43	16	10	Of righteousness, because I go to my Father, and you will see me no more;
B043C016V011	43	16	11	Of judgment, because the prince of this world is judged.
B043C016V012	43	16	12	I have yet many things to say to you, but you cannot bear them now.
B043C016V013	43	16	13	Yet when he, the Spirit of truth, has come, he will guide you into all truth: for he shall not speak of his own accord; but whatever he shall hear, that shall he speak: and he will show you things to come.
B043C016V014	43	16	14	He shall glorify me: for he shall take what is mine, and shall show it to you.
B043C016V015	43	16	15	All things that the Father has are mine: therefore I said that he shall take what is mine, and shall show it to you.
B043C016V016	43	16	16	In a little while you shall not see me: and again, in a little while, you shall see me.
B043C016V017	43	16	17	Then some of his disciples said among themselves, What is this that he says to us, In a little while you shall not see me: and again, in a little while, you shall see me: and, Because I go to the Father?
B043C016V018	43	16	18	Therefore they said, What is this that he says, A little while? we cannot tell what he is saying.
B043C016V019	43	16	19	Now Jesus knew that they wanted to question him, and said to them, Do you enquire among yourselves about what I meant when I said, In a little while you shall not see me: and again, in a little while, you shall see me?
B043C016V020	43	16	20	Truly, truly, I say to you, You shall weep and lament, but the world shall rejoice: and you shall be sorrowful, but your sorrow shall be turned into joy.
B043C016V021	43	16	21	A woman, when she is in travail, has sorrow, because her hour has come: but as soon as she has delivered the child, she remembers the anguish no more, for joy that a child has been born into the world.
B043C016V022	43	16	22	So also you have sorrow now: but I will see you again, and your heart shall rejoice, and no man shall take your joy from you.
B043C016V023	43	16	23	And in that day you shall ask me nothing. Truly, truly, I say to you, Whatever you shall ask the Father in my name, he will give it to you.
B043C016V024	43	16	24	Until now you have asked for nothing in my name: ask, and you shall receive, that your joy may be full.
B043C016V025	43	16	25	These things I have spoken to you in parables: but the time comes when I shall no longer speak to you in parables, but I shall tell you plainly of the Father.
B043C016V026	43	16	26	On that day you shall ask in my name; and I do not say to you that I will ask the Father for you:
B043C016V027	43	16	27	For the Father himself loves you, because you have loved me, and have believed that I came from the Father.
B043C016V028	43	16	28	I came forth from the Father, and have come into the world: again, I leave the world, and go to the Father.
B043C016V029	43	16	29	His disciples said to him, Lo, now you speak plainly, and are not using a proverb.
B043C016V030	43	16	30	Now we are sure that you know all things, and do not need any man to question you: by this we believe that you came forth from God.
B043C016V031	43	16	31	Jesus answered them, Do you now believe?
B043C016V032	43	16	32	Behold, the hour comes, yea, has now come, when you shall be scattered, every man to his own home, and shall leave me alone: and yet I am not alone, because the Father is with me.
B043C016V033	43	16	33	These things I have spoken to you, that in me you might have peace. In the world you shall have tribulation: but be of good cheer; I have overcome the world.
B043C017V001	43	17	1	These words Jesus spoke, and lifted up his eyes to heaven, and said, Father, the hour has come; glorify your Son, that your Son may glorify you:
B043C017V002	43	17	2	Since you have given him power over all flesh, that he should give eternal life to as many as you have given him.
B043C017V003	43	17	3	And this is life eternal, that they might know you, the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom you have sent.
B043C017V004	43	17	4	I have glorified you on the earth: I have finished the work which you gave me to do.
B043C017V005	43	17	5	And now, O Father, glorify me together with you; with the glory which I had with you before the world was.
B043C017V006	43	17	6	I have manifested your name to the men whom you gave me out of the world: yours they were, and you gave them to me; and they have kept your word.
B043C017V007	43	17	7	Now they know that all things that you have given me are from you.
B043C017V008	43	17	8	For I have given to them the words which you gave me; and they have received them, and have known surely that I came from you, and they have believed that you did send me.
B043C017V009	43	17	9	I pray for them: I pray not for the world, but for those whom you have given me; for they are yours.
B043C017V010	43	17	10	And all mine are yours, and yours are mine; and I am glorified in them.
B043C017V011	43	17	11	And now I am no longer in the world, but these are in the world, and I come to you. Holy Father, keep those whom you have given me in your own name, that they may be one, as we are.
B043C017V012	43	17	12	While I was with them in the world, I kept them in your name: those you gave me I have kept, and none of them has been lost, except the son of perdition; that the scripture might be fulfilled.
B043C017V013	43	17	13	And now I come to you; and these things I speak in the world, that they might have my joy fulfilled in themselves.
B043C017V014	43	17	14	I have given them your word; and the world has hated them, because they are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.
B043C017V015	43	17	15	I do not pray that you would take them out of the world, but that you would keep them from the evil one.
B043C017V016	43	17	16	They are not of the world, even as I am not of the world.
B043C017V017	43	17	17	Sanctify them in the truth: your word is truth.
B043C017V018	43	17	18	As you have sent me into the world, even so have I also sent them into the world.
B043C017V019	43	17	19	And for their sakes I sanctify myself, that they also might be sanctified in the truth.
B043C017V020	43	17	20	I do not pray for these alone, but also for those who shall believe in me through their word;
B043C017V021	43	17	21	That they all may be one; as you, Father, are in me, and I in you, that they also may be one in us: that the world may believe that you have sent me.
B043C017V022	43	17	22	And the glory which you gave me I have given to them; that they may be one, even as we are one:
B043C017V023	43	17	23	I in them, and you in me, that they may be made perfectly one; and that the world may know that you have sent me, and have loved them, as you have loved me.
B043C017V024	43	17	24	Father, I desire that they also, whom you have given me, may be with me where I am; that they may behold my glory, which you have given me: for you loved me before the foundation of the world.
B043C017V025	43	17	25	O righteous Father, the world has not known you: but I have known you, and these know that you have sent me.
B043C017V026	43	17	26	And I have declared to them your name, and will declare it: that the love with which you have loved me may be in them, and I in them.
B043C018V001	43	18	1	When Jesus had spoken these words, he went forth with his disciples over the ravine of the Kedron, to where there was a garden into which he and his disciples entered.
B043C018V002	43	18	2	And Judas also, who betrayed him, knew the place: for Jesus often met there with his disciples.
B043C018V003	43	18	3	Judas then, having received a band of men and officers from the chief priests and Pharisees, came there with lanterns and torches and weapons.
B043C018V004	43	18	4	Then Jesus, knowing all that would come upon him, went forth, and said to them, Whom do you seek?
B043C018V005	43	18	5	They answered him, Jesus of Nazareth. Jesus said to them, I am he. And Judas, who betrayed him, stood with them.
B043C018V006	43	18	6	As soon as he had said to them, I am he, they drew back, and fell to the ground.
B043C018V007	43	18	7	Then he asked them again, Whom do you seek? And they said, Jesus of Nazareth.
B043C018V008	43	18	8	Jesus answered, I have told you that I am he: therefore if you seek me, let these men go their way:
B043C018V009	43	18	9	This happened so that what he had spoken might be fulfilled, Of those whom you gave me I have lost none.
B043C018V010	43	18	10	Then Simon Peter, having a sword, drew it, and struck the high priest's servant, cutting off his right ear. The servant's name was Malchus.
B043C018V011	43	18	11	Then Jesus said to Peter, Put your sword into its sheath: the cup which my Father has given me, shall I not drink it?
B043C018V012	43	18	12	Then the band and the captain and officers of the Jews took Jesus, and bound him,
B043C018V013	43	18	13	And led him first to Annas; for he was father-in-law to Caiaphas, who was the high priest that year.
B043C018V014	43	18	14	Now Caiaphas was the one, who gave counsel to the Jews, that it was expedient that one man should die for the people.
B043C018V015	43	18	15	And Simon Peter followed Jesus, as did another disciple: that disciple was known to the high priest, and went with Jesus into the court of the high priest.
B043C018V016	43	18	16	But Peter stood outside at the door. Then the other disciple, who was known to the high priest, went out and spoke to her who kept the door, and brought in Peter.
B043C018V017	43	18	17	Then the maid who kept the door said to Peter, Are you not also one of this man's disciples? He said, I am not.
B043C018V018	43	18	18	Now the servants and officers who stood there had made a fire of coals; for it was cold: and they warmed themselves: and Peter stood with them, and warmed himself.
B043C018V019	43	18	19	The high priest then asked Jesus about his disciples, and about his teaching.
B043C018V020	43	18	20	Jesus answered him, I spoke openly to the world; I always taught in the synagogue, and in the temple, where the Jews all come together; and I said nothing in secret.
B043C018V021	43	18	21	Why do you ask me? ask those who heard what I spoke to them: they know what I said.
B043C018V022	43	18	22	And when he had said this, one of the officers who stood by struck Jesus with the palm of his hand, saying, Is that how you answer the high priest?
B043C018V023	43	18	23	Jesus answered him, If I have spoken evil, bear witness of the evil: but if well, why do you strike me?
B043C018V024	43	18	24	Then Annas sent him bound to Caiaphas the high priest.
B043C018V025	43	18	25	And Simon Peter stood and warmed himself. They said to him, Are you not also one of his disciples? He denied it, and said, I am not.
B043C018V026	43	18	26	One of the servants of the high priest, a kinsman of the man whose ear Peter cut off, said, Did I not see you in the garden with him?
B043C018V027	43	18	27	Peter denied it again: and immediately the cock crowed.
B043C018V028	43	18	28	Then they led Jesus from Caiaphas to the praetorium: and it was early; and they themselves did not go into the praetorium, so they would not be defiled, but might eat the passover.
B043C018V029	43	18	29	Pilate then went out to them, and said, What accusation do you bring against this man?
B043C018V030	43	18	30	They answered and said to him, If he were not an evildoer, we would not have delivered him up to you.
B043C018V031	43	18	31	Then Pilate said to them, You take him and judge him according to your own law. The Jews said to him, It is not lawful for us to put any man to death:
B043C018V032	43	18	32	This was so the word of Jesus might be fulfilled, which he spoke to signify what kind of death he should die.
B043C018V033	43	18	33	Then Pilate entered the praetorium again, and called Jesus, and said to him, Are you the King of the Jews?
B043C018V034	43	18	34	Jesus answered him, Do you say this of your own accord, or did others tell you of me?
B043C018V035	43	18	35	Pilate answered, Am I a Jew? Your own nation and the chief priests have delivered you up to me: what have you done?
B043C018V036	43	18	36	Jesus answered, My kingdom is not of this world: if my kingdom were of this world, then my servants would fight, that I should not be delivered up to the Jews: but my kingdom is not of this world.
B043C018V037	43	18	37	So Pilate said to him, You are a king then? Jesus answered, You say that I am a king. To this end was I born, and for this cause I came into the world, that I should bear witness to the truth. Every one who is of the truth hears my voice.
B043C018V038	43	18	38	Pilate said to him, What is truth? And when he had said this, he went out again to the Jews, and said to them, I find no fault in him.
B043C018V039	43	18	39	But you have a custom, for me to release someone to you at the passover: do you want me to release to you the King of the Jews?
B043C018V040	43	18	40	Then they all cried again, saying, Not this man, but Barabbas. Now Barabbas was a robber.
B043C019V001	43	19	1	Then Pilate took Jesus, and scourged him.
B043C019V002	43	19	2	And the soldiers plaited a crown of thorns, and put it on his head, and they put on him a purple robe,
B043C019V003	43	19	3	And came up to him and said, Hail, King of the Jews! and struck him with their hands.
B043C019V004	43	19	4	Pilate went forth again, and said to them, Behold, I bring him forth to you, that you may know that I find no fault in him.
B043C019V005	43	19	5	Then Jesus came forth, wearing the crown of thorns, and the purple robe. And Pilate said to them, Behold the man!
B043C019V006	43	19	6	When the chief priests and officers saw him, they cried out, saying, Crucify him, crucify him. Pilate said to them, You take him and crucify him: for I find no fault in him.
B043C019V007	43	19	7	The Jews answered him, We have a law, and by our law he ought to die, because he made himself out to be the Son of God.
B043C019V008	43	19	8	When Pilate heard these words, he was even more afraid;
B043C019V009	43	19	9	And went again into the praetorium, and said to Jesus, Where are you from? But Jesus gave him no answer.
B043C019V010	43	19	10	Then Pilate said to him, You do not speak to me? do you not know that I have power to release you, and power to crucify you?
B043C019V011	43	19	11	Jesus answered, You would have no power over me unless it was given to you from above: therefore he who delivered me to you has the greater sin.
B043C019V012	43	19	12	And from then Pilate sought to release him: but the Jews cried out, saying, If you let this man go, you are no friend of Caesar's: whoever makes himself a king sets himself against Caesar.
B043C019V013	43	19	13	When Pilate heard these words, he brought Jesus forth, and sat down in the judgment seat in a place that is called the Pavement, but in the Hebrew, Gabbatha.
B043C019V014	43	19	14	And it was the day of preparation for the passover, about the sixth hour: and he said to the Jews, Behold your King!
B043C019V015	43	19	15	But they cried out, Away with him, away with him, crucify him. Pilate said to them, Shall I crucify your King? The chief priests answered, We have no king but Caesar.
B043C019V016	43	19	16	Then he delivered him to them to be crucified.
B043C019V017	43	19	17	And they took Jesus and led him away, and he, bearing his cross, went forth to a place called the place of a skull, which is called in Hebrew, Golgotha:
B043C019V018	43	19	18	Where they crucified him, and two others with him, one on either side and Jesus in the middle.
B043C019V019	43	19	19	And Pilate wrote a title, and put it on the cross. And the writing was, JESUS OF NAZARETH, THE KING OF THE JEWS.
B043C019V020	43	19	20	Many of the Jews read this title: for the place where Jesus was crucified was near the city: and it was written in Hebrew, and Latin, and Greek.
B043C019V021	43	19	21	Then the chief priests of the Jews said to Pilate, Do not write, The King of the Jews; but that he said, I am King of the Jews.
B043C019V022	43	19	22	Pilate answered, What I have written I have written.
B043C019V023	43	19	23	Then the soldiers, when they had crucified Jesus, took his garments, and made four parts, to every soldier a part; and also his coat: now the coat was without seam, woven from the top throughout.
B043C019V024	43	19	24	Therefore they said among themselves, Let us not tear it, but cast lots for it, to decide whose it shall be. This was so the scripture might be fulfilled, which says, They divided my garments among them, and for my clothing they cast lots. Therefore the soldiers did these things.
B043C019V025	43	19	25	Now by the cross of Jesus stood his mother, and his mother's sister, Mary the wife of Clopas, and Mary Magdalene.
B043C019V026	43	19	26	When Jesus saw his mother, and the disciple whom he loved, standing by, he said to his mother, Woman, behold your son!
B043C019V027	43	19	27	Then he said to the disciple, Behold your mother! And from that hour that disciple took her into his own home.
B043C019V028	43	19	28	After this, Jesus, knowing that all things were now accomplished, said in fulfillment of the scripture, I thirst.
B043C019V029	43	19	29	Now there was a vessel full of vinegar set there: and they soaked a sponge with vinegar, and put it upon a hyssop branch, and held it to his mouth.
B043C019V030	43	19	30	When Jesus received the vinegar, he said, It is finished: and he bowed his head, and gave up his spirit.
B043C019V031	43	19	31	Because it was the day of preparation, in order that the bodies would not remain upon the cross during the sabbath day (for that sabbath day was a high day,) the Jews asked Pilate that their legs might be broken, and that they might be taken away.
B043C019V032	43	19	32	The soldiers came and broke the legs of the first, and of the other who was crucified with him.
B043C019V033	43	19	33	But when they came to Jesus, and saw that he was dead already, they did not break his legs:
B043C019V034	43	19	34	But one of the soldiers pierced his side with a spear, and immediately there came out blood and water.
B043C019V035	43	19	35	And he who saw it has borne witness, and his witness is true: and he knows what he says is true, that you also might believe.
B043C019V036	43	19	36	For these things came to pass that the scripture should be fulfilled, Not one of his bones shall be broken.
B043C019V037	43	19	37	And again another scripture says, They shall look on him whom they have pierced.
B043C019V038	43	19	38	After this, Joseph of Arimathaea, being a disciple of Jesus, but secretly for fear of the Jews, asked Pilate that he might take away the body of Jesus: and Pilate gave him permission. Therefore he came and took his body.
B043C019V039	43	19	39	And Nicodemus also came, who first came to Jesus by night, and brought a mixture of myrrh and aloes, about a hundred pounds' weight.
B043C019V040	43	19	40	They took the body of Jesus, and bound it in linen cloths with the spices, as is the burial custom of the Jews.
B043C019V041	43	19	41	Now in the place where he was crucified there was a garden; and in the garden a new tomb, in which no one had yet been laid.
B043C019V042	43	19	42	Because of the Jewish day of preparation, as the tomb was near at hand, they laid Jesus there.
B043C020V001	43	20	1	The first day of the week Mary Magdalene came early, when it was yet dark, to the tomb, and saw the stone taken away from the tomb.
B043C020V002	43	20	2	Then she ran, and came to Simon Peter, and to the other disciple, whom Jesus loved, and said to them, They have taken away the Lord out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have laid him.
B043C020V003	43	20	3	Therefore Peter went forth, with the other disciple, toward the tomb.
B043C020V004	43	20	4	So they both ran together: and the other disciple outran Peter, and came first to the tomb.
B043C020V005	43	20	5	And he stooped down, and looked in, and saw the linen wrappings lying there; but he did not go in.
B043C020V006	43	20	6	Then Simon Peter came, following him, and went into the tomb, and saw the linen wrappings lying there,
B043C020V007	43	20	7	And the cloth, which had been around his head, was not lying with the linen wrappings, but was rolled up in a place by itself.
B043C020V008	43	20	8	Then the other disciple, who came first to the tomb, went in also and he saw, and believed.
B043C020V009	43	20	9	For as yet they did not understand the scripture, that he must rise again from the dead.
B043C020V010	43	20	10	Then the disciples went away again to their own homes.
B043C020V011	43	20	11	But Mary stood outside the tomb weeping: and as she wept, she stooped down, and looked into the tomb,
B043C020V012	43	20	12	And saw two angels in white sitting, one at the head, and the other at the feet, where the body of Jesus had lain.
B043C020V013	43	20	13	And they said to her, Woman, why do you weep? She said to them, Because they have taken away my Lord, and I do not know where they have laid him.
B043C020V014	43	20	14	And when she had said this, she turned around, and saw Jesus standing, but did not know that it was Jesus.
B043C020V015	43	20	15	Jesus said to her, Woman, why do you weep? whom do you seek? She, supposing him to be the gardener, said to him, Sir, if you have carried him away, tell me where you have laid him, and I will take him away.
B043C020V016	43	20	16	Jesus said to her, Mary. She turned, and said to him, Rabboni; which is to say, Teacher.
B043C020V017	43	20	17	Jesus said to her, Do not hold me; for I have not yet ascended to my Father: but go to my brethren, and say to them, I ascend to my Father, and your Father; and to my God, and your God.
B043C020V018	43	20	18	Mary Magdalene came and told the disciples that she had seen the Lord, and that he had spoken these things to her.
B043C020V019	43	20	19	Then at evening of the same day, the first day of the week, when the doors were shut where the disciples were assembled for fear of the Jews, Jesus came and stood in their midst, and said to them, Peace be with you.
B043C020V020	43	20	20	And when he had said this, he showed them his hands and his side. The disciples were overjoyed when they saw the Lord.
B043C020V021	43	20	21	Then Jesus said to them again, Peace be with you: as my Father has sent me, even so I send you.
B043C020V022	43	20	22	And when he had said this, he breathed on them, and said to them, Receive the Holy Spirit:
B043C020V023	43	20	23	If you forgive the sins of any one, they are forgiven; if you retain the sins of any one, they are retained.
B043C020V024	43	20	24	But Thomas, one of the twelve, called Didymus, was not with them when Jesus came.
B043C020V025	43	20	25	The other disciples said to him, We have seen the Lord. But he said to them, Unless I shall see in his hands the mark of the nails, and put my finger into the print of the nails, and thrust my hand into his side, I will not believe.
B043C020V026	43	20	26	After eight days his disciples were again inside, and Thomas with them: then Jesus came, though the doors were shut, and stood in their midst, and said, Peace be with you.
B043C020V027	43	20	27	Then he said to Thomas, Reach here with your finger, and behold my hands; and reach here with your hand, and thrust it into my side: and do not be faithless, but believing.
B043C020V028	43	20	28	And Thomas said to him, My Lord and my God.
B043C020V029	43	20	29	Jesus said to him, Because you have seen me, you have believed: blessed are those who have not seen, and yet have believed.
B043C020V030	43	20	30	Now Jesus performed many other miraculous signs in the presence of his disciples, which are not written in this book:
B043C020V031	43	20	31	But these are written, that you might believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God; and that believing you might have life through his name.
B043C021V001	43	21	1	After these things Jesus showed himself again to the disciples by the sea of Tiberias; and he showed himself in this way:
B043C021V002	43	21	2	Simon Peter, Thomas called Didymus, Nathanael of Cana in Galilee, the sons of Zebedee, and two other of his disciples were together.
B043C021V003	43	21	3	Simon Peter said to them, I am going fishing. They said to him, We will go with you. They went forth, and entered a boat; but that night they caught nothing.
B043C021V004	43	21	4	But when the morning was breaking, Jesus stood on the shore: but the disciples did not know that it was Jesus.
B043C021V005	43	21	5	Then Jesus said to them, Children, have you any fish? They answered him, No.
B043C021V006	43	21	6	And he said to them, Cast the net on the right side of the boat, and you shall find some. Therefore they cast it, and they were not able to draw it in because of the multitude of fish.
B043C021V007	43	21	7	Therefore the disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, It is the Lord. Now when Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord, he put on his outer garment, (for he was stripped for work,) and cast himself into the sea.
B043C021V008	43	21	8	And the other disciples came in the boat; (for they were not far from land, only about a hundred yards,) dragging the net full of fish.
B043C021V009	43	21	9	As soon as they had come to land, they saw a fire of coals there, and fish laid on it, and bread.
B043C021V010	43	21	10	Jesus said to them, Bring some of the fish which you have caught.
B043C021V011	43	21	11	Simon Peter went up, and drew the net to land, full of great fish, a hundred and fifty-three: and though there were so many, yet the net was not broken.
B043C021V012	43	21	12	Jesus said to them, Come and have breakfast. And none of the disciples dared ask him, Who are you? knowing that it was the Lord.
B043C021V013	43	21	13	Then Jesus came, and took bread, and gave it to them, and did the same with the fish.
B043C021V014	43	21	14	This was now the third time that Jesus showed himself to his disciples, after he had risen from the dead.
B043C021V015	43	21	15	So when they had eaten, Jesus said to Simon Peter, Simon, son of John, do you love me more than these? He said to him, Yes, Lord; you know that I love you. He said to him, Feed my lambs.
B043C021V016	43	21	16	He said to him a second time, Simon, son of John, do you love me? He said to him, Yes, Lord; you know that I love you. He said to him, Tend my sheep.
B043C021V017	43	21	17	He said to him a third time, Simon, son of John, do you love me? Peter was grieved because he said to him the third time, Do you love me? And he said to him, Lord, you know all things; you know that I love you. Jesus said to him, Feed my sheep.
B043C021V018	43	21	18	Truly, truly, I say to you, When you were young, you girded yourself, and walked where you wanted: but when you grow old, you shall stretch forth your hands, and another shall gird you, and carry you where you do not want to go.
B043C021V019	43	21	19	This he spoke to signify by what kind of death he would glorify God. And when he had spoken this, he said to him, Follow me.
B043C021V020	43	21	20	Then Peter, turning about, saw the disciple whom Jesus loved following; the one who had leaned on his breast at supper, and said, Lord, who is the one who betrays you?
B043C021V021	43	21	21	Peter, seeing him, said to Jesus, Lord, what about this man?
B043C021V022	43	21	22	Jesus said to him, If I want him to remain until I come, what is that to you? you follow me.
B043C021V023	43	21	23	Then this saying went abroad among the brethren, that this disciple should not die: yet Jesus did not said to him, He shall not die; but, If I want him to remain until I come, what is that to you?
B043C021V024	43	21	24	This is the disciple who testifies of these things, and wrote these things: and we know that his testimony is true.
B043C021V025	43	21	25	And there are also many other things which Jesus did, which, if every one of them were to be written, I suppose that even the world itself could not contain the books that would be written.
B044C001V001	44	1	1	In my former treatise, O Theophilus, I wrote of all that Jesus began to do and teach,
B044C001V002	44	1	2	Until the day he was taken up, after he had, through the Holy Spirit, given commands to the apostles whom he had chosen.
B044C001V003	44	1	3	To them he showed himself alive after his suffering by many infallible proofs, being seen by them over forty days, and speaking of the things concerning the kingdom of God:
B044C001V004	44	1	4	And, while eating with them, commanded them not to depart from Jerusalem, but to wait for the promise of the Father, of which, he said, you have heard me speak.
B044C001V005	44	1	5	For John baptized with water; but you shall be baptized with the Holy Spirit not many days from now.
B044C001V006	44	1	6	When they had come together, they asked him, saying, Lord, will you at this time restore the kingdom to Israel?
B044C001V007	44	1	7	And he said to them, It is not for you to know the times or the seasons, which the Father has fixed by his own authority.
B044C001V008	44	1	8	But you shall receive power when the Holy Spirit has come upon you: and you shall be witnesses to me both in Jerusalem, and in all Judaea, and in Samaria, and to the remotest part of the earth.
B044C001V009	44	1	9	And when he had spoken these things, while they watched, he was taken up; and a cloud received him out of their sight.
B044C001V010	44	1	10	And while they looked steadfastly toward heaven as he went up, behold, two men stood by them in white apparel;
B044C001V011	44	1	11	Who said, You men of Galilee, why do you stand gazing up into heaven? this same Jesus, who has been taken up from you into heaven, shall come in the same way that you have seen him go into heaven.
B044C001V012	44	1	12	Then they returned to Jerusalem from the mount called Olivet, which is from Jerusalem a sabbath day's journey.
B044C001V013	44	1	13	And when they had come in, they went into an upper room where they were staying; Peter, and John, and James, and Andrew, Philip, and Thomas, Bartholomew, and Matthew, James the son of Alphaeus, and Simon the Zealot, and Judas the son of James.
B044C001V014	44	1	14	They all continued with one accord in prayer, with the women, and Mary the mother of Jesus, and with his brothers.
B044C001V015	44	1	15	In those days Peter stood up in the midst of the disciples, and said, (together they were about a hundred and twenty,)
B044C001V016	44	1	16	Brethren, this scripture had to be fulfilled, which the Holy Spirit spoke by the mouth of David concerning Judas, who was the guide to those who arrested Jesus.
B044C001V017	44	1	17	For he was numbered with us, and had his part in this ministry.
B044C001V018	44	1	18	(Now this man purchased a field with the reward of his wickedness; and falling headlong, he burst apart in the middle, and all his bowels gushed out.
B044C001V019	44	1	19	And it became known to all who dwelt in Jerusalem; so that the field is called in their tongue, Akeldama, that is to say, The field of blood.)
B044C001V020	44	1	20	For it is written in the book of Psalms, Let his habitation become desolate, and let no man live in it: and his office let another take.
B044C001V021	44	1	21	Therefore, of those men who have accompanied us all the time that the Lord Jesus went in and out among us,
B044C001V022	44	1	22	Beginning with the baptism of John until the day that he was taken up from us, one of these must be ordained to be a witness with us of his resurrection.
B044C001V023	44	1	23	And they appointed two, Joseph called Barsabbas, who was surnamed Justus, and Matthias.
B044C001V024	44	1	24	And they prayed, and said, You, Lord, who know the hearts of all men, show which of these two you have chosen,
B044C001V025	44	1	25	To take part in this ministry and apostleship, from which Judas turned aside, that he might go to his own place.
B044C001V026	44	1	26	And they drew lots for them; and the lot fell to Matthias; and he was numbered with the eleven apostles.
B044C002V001	44	2	1	And when the day of Pentecost had come, they were all together in one place.
B044C002V002	44	2	2	And suddenly there came a sound from heaven as of a rushing mighty wind, and it filled all the house where they were sitting.
B044C002V003	44	2	3	And there appeared to them tongues, as of fire, which separated and came to rest upon each of them.
B044C002V004	44	2	4	And they were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and began to speak with other tongues, as the Spirit gave them utterance.
B044C002V005	44	2	5	And there were dwelling in Jerusalem Jews, devout men, out of every nation under heaven.
B044C002V006	44	2	6	Now when this sound was heard, the multitude came together, and were bewildered, because every one heard them speak in his own language.
B044C002V007	44	2	7	And they were all amazed and marvelled, saying one to another, Behold, are not all these who speak Galilaeans?
B044C002V008	44	2	8	And how is it we each hear them in our own tongue, in the language to which we were born?
B044C002V009	44	2	9	Parthians, and Medes, and Elamites, and dwellers in Mesopotamia, and in Judaea, and Cappadocia, in Pontus, and Asia,
B044C002V010	44	2	10	Phrygia, and Pamphylia, in Egypt, and in the parts of Libya around Cyrene, and strangers from Rome, both Jews and proselytes,
B044C002V011	44	2	11	Cretans and Arabs, we hear them speak in our tongues of the mighty works of God.
B044C002V012	44	2	12	And they were all amazed, and were in doubt, saying one to another, What does this mean?
B044C002V013	44	2	13	Others said mockingly, These men are full of new wine.
B044C002V014	44	2	14	But Peter, standing up with the eleven, lifted up his voice, and said to them, You men of Judaea, and all you who live in Jerusalem, let this be known to you, and listen to my words:
B044C002V015	44	2	15	For these men are not drunk, as you suppose, for it is only the third hour of the day.
B044C002V016	44	2	16	But this is that which was spoken of by the prophet Joel;
B044C002V017	44	2	17	And it shall come to pass in the last days, declares God, That I will pour out my Spirit upon all flesh: and your sons and your daughters shall prophesy, and your young men shall see visions, and your old men shall dream dreams:
B044C002V018	44	2	18	And in those days I will pour out my Spirit on my menservants and on my maidservants; and they shall prophesy:
B044C002V019	44	2	19	And I will show wonders in heaven above, and signs on the earth beneath; blood, and fire, and vapour of smoke:
B044C002V020	44	2	20	The sun shall be turned into darkness, and the moon into blood, before the great and glorious day of the Lord shall come:
B044C002V021	44	2	21	And it shall come to pass, that whoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.
B044C002V022	44	2	22	You men of Israel, hear these words; Jesus of Nazareth, a man attested to you by God with miracles and wonders and signs, which God performed by him in your midst, as you yourselves know:
B044C002V023	44	2	23	This man, being delivered up by the definite plan and foreknowledge of God, you have taken, and by the hands of wicked men have crucified and slain.
B044C002V024	44	2	24	But God has raised him up, having freed him from the pains of death: because it was not possible that he should be held by it.
B044C002V025	44	2	25	For David speaks of him, I saw the Lord always before my face, for he is on my right hand, that I should not be shaken:
B044C002V026	44	2	26	Therefore did my heart rejoice, and my tongue was glad; moreover my flesh shall also abide in hope:
B044C002V027	44	2	27	Because you will not leave my soul in Hades, neither will you allow your Holy One to see decay.
B044C002V028	44	2	28	You have made known to me the ways of life; you shall make me full of joy with your presence.
B044C002V029	44	2	29	Brethren, let me say confidently to you of the patriarch David; that he is both dead and buried, and his tomb is with us to this day.
B044C002V030	44	2	30	Therefore, being a prophet, and knowing that God had sworn with an oath that he would seat one of his descendants upon his throne;
B044C002V031	44	2	31	He foresaw this and spoke of the resurrection of Christ, that his soul was not left in Hades, neither did his flesh see corruption.
B044C002V032	44	2	32	This Jesus God has raised up, of which we are all witnesses.
B044C002V033	44	2	33	Therefore, being exalted at the right hand of God, and having received from the Father the promise of the Holy Spirit, he has poured forth this, which you now see and hear.
B044C002V034	44	2	34	For David did not ascend into the heavens: but he himself says, The LORD said to my Lord, Sit on my right hand,
B044C002V035	44	2	35	Until I make your foes a footstool for your feet.
B044C002V036	44	2	36	Therefore, let all the house of Israel know assuredly, that God has made this Jesus, whom you crucified, both Lord and Christ.
B044C002V037	44	2	37	Now when they heard this, they were pricked to the heart, and said to Peter and to the rest of the apostles, Brethren, what shall we do?
B044C002V038	44	2	38	Then Peter said to them, Repent, and let every one of you be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ for the remission of sins, and you shall receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.
B044C002V039	44	2	39	For the promise is for you, and for your children, and for all who are far off, even as many as the Lord our God shall call.
B044C002V040	44	2	40	And with many other words did he testify and exhort them, saying, Save yourselves from this perverse generation.
B044C002V041	44	2	41	Then those who received his word were baptized: and that same day there were added to their number about three thousand souls.
B044C002V042	44	2	42	And they continued steadfastly in the apostles' teaching and fellowship, and in the breaking of bread, and in prayer.
B044C002V043	44	2	43	And fear came upon every soul: and many wonders and signs were done through the apostles.
B044C002V044	44	2	44	And all who believed were together, and had all things in common;
B044C002V045	44	2	45	And they sold their possessions and goods, and distributed them to all men, as every man had need.
B044C002V046	44	2	46	And they continued daily to assemble in the temple, and to break bread from house to house, and to eat their food with gladness and sincerity of heart,
B044C002V047	44	2	47	Praising God, and having favour with all the people. And the Lord added to their number daily those who were being saved.
B044C003V001	44	3	1	Now Peter and John went up together to the temple at the hour of prayer, the ninth hour.
B044C003V002	44	3	2	And a certain man, lame from his mother's womb, was being carried to the temple gate which is called Beautiful, where they laid him daily to ask for alms from those who entered into the temple;
B044C003V003	44	3	3	Seeing Peter and John about to go into the temple, he asked for alms.
B044C003V004	44	3	4	And Peter, fastening his eyes upon him with John, said, Look at us.
B044C003V005	44	3	5	And he gave his attention to them, expecting to receive something from them.
B044C003V006	44	3	6	Then Peter said, Of silver and gold I have none; but what I have I give to you: In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, walk!
B044C003V007	44	3	7	And he took him by the right hand, and lifted him up: and immediately his feet and ankles received strength.
B044C003V008	44	3	8	And leaping up he stood, and walked, and entered with them into the temple, walking, and leaping, and praising God.
B044C003V009	44	3	9	And all the people saw him walking and praising God:
B044C003V010	44	3	10	And they knew that it was the one who sat begging for alms at the Beautiful gate of the temple: and they were filled with wonder and amazement at that which had happened to him.
B044C003V011	44	3	11	And as he clung to Peter and John, all the people ran together to them in the porch that is called Solomon's, greatly amazed.
B044C003V012	44	3	12	And when Peter saw it, he answered the people, You men of Israel, why do you marvel at this? or why do you look so earnestly at us, as though by our own power or holiness we made this man walk?
B044C003V013	44	3	13	The God of Abraham, and of Isaac, and of Jacob, the God of our fathers, has glorified his Son Jesus; whom you delivered up, and denied in the presence of Pilate, when he had decided to let him go.
B044C003V014	44	3	14	But you denied the Holy and Just One, and asked for a murderer to be granted to you;
B044C003V015	44	3	15	And killed the Prince of life, whom God has raised from the dead. Of this we are witnesses.
B044C003V016	44	3	16	And his name, through faith in his name, has made this man strong, whom you see and know: and the faith which is through Jesus has given him this perfect health in the presence of you all.
B044C003V017	44	3	17	And now, brethren, I know that you acted in ignorance, as did your rulers.
B044C003V018	44	3	18	But those things which God foretold by the mouths of all his prophets, that his Christ should suffer, he has fulfilled.
B044C003V019	44	3	19	Therefore repent, and be converted, that your sins may be blotted out, that times of refreshing may come from the presence of the Lord;
B044C003V020	44	3	20	And that he may send the Christ, who was appointed for you, even Jesus:
B044C003V021	44	3	21	Whom heaven must receive until the time of the restoration of all things which God has spoken about by the mouths of all his holy prophets since the most ancient times.
B044C003V022	44	3	22	For Moses said, The Lord your God shall raise up for you a prophet like me from among your brethren; you shall hear him in all things, whatever he shall say to you.
B044C003V023	44	3	23	And it shall come to pass, that anyone who will not hear that prophet, shall be destroyed from among the people.
B044C003V024	44	3	24	Yea, and all the prophets, from Samuel and those who followed after, as many as have spoken, have foretold these days.
B044C003V025	44	3	25	You are the children of the prophets, and of the covenant which God made with your fathers, saying to Abraham, And in your seed shall all the families of the earth be blessed.
B044C003V026	44	3	26	God, having raised up his servant, sent him first to bless you, by turning every one of you away from your iniquities.
B044C004V001	44	4	1	And as they spoke to the people, the priests, and the captain of the temple, and the Sadducees, came upon them.
B044C004V002	44	4	2	They were indignant that they taught the people, and preached in Jesus the resurrection from the dead.
B044C004V003	44	4	3	And they laid hands on them, and put them in prison until the next day: for it was already evening.
B044C004V004	44	4	4	Yet many of those who heard the word believed; and the number of the men was about five thousand.
B044C004V005	44	4	5	And it came to pass on the next day, that their rulers, and elders, and scribes,
B044C004V006	44	4	6	And Annas the high priest, and Caiaphas, and Jonathan, and Alexander, and as many as were of the family of the high priest, were gathered together at Jerusalem.
B044C004V007	44	4	7	And when they had set them in their midst, they asked, By what power, or by what name, have you done this?
B044C004V008	44	4	8	Then Peter, filled with the Holy Spirit, said to them, You rulers of the people, and elders,
B044C004V009	44	4	9	If we are to be examined this day about a good deed done to a cripple, by what means he was made well;
B044C004V010	44	4	10	Then let it be known to you all, and to all the people of Israel, that by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, whom you crucified, whom God raised from the dead, by him does this man stand here before you well.
B044C004V011	44	4	11	This is the stone which was rejected by you builders, but which has become the very cornerstone.
B044C004V012	44	4	12	And there is salvation in no one else: for there is no other name under heaven given among men, by which we must be saved.
B044C004V013	44	4	13	Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and perceived that they were unlearned and ignorant men, they marvelled; and they recognized that they had been with Jesus.
B044C004V014	44	4	14	And beholding the man who was healed standing with them, they could say nothing against it.
B044C004V015	44	4	15	But when they had commanded them to go aside, out of the council, they conferred among themselves,
B044C004V016	44	4	16	Saying, What shall we do with these men? for that a notable miracle has indeed been done by them is apparent to everyone who lives in Jerusalem; and we cannot deny it.
B044C004V017	44	4	17	But that it may spread no further among the people, let us sternly warn them, that they speak no more to any man in this name.
B044C004V018	44	4	18	And they called them, and commanded them not to speak or teach at all in the name of Jesus.
B044C004V019	44	4	19	But Peter and John answered and said to them, Whether it is right in the sight of God to listen to you more than to God, judge for yourselves.
B044C004V020	44	4	20	But we cannot but speak the things which we have seen and heard.
B044C004V021	44	4	21	So when they had threatened them further, they let them go, finding no way to punish them, because of the people: for everyone glorified God for what had been done.
B044C004V022	44	4	22	For the man was more than forty years old, on whom this miracle of healing was performed.
B044C004V023	44	4	23	And being let go, they went to their own people, and reported all that the chief priests and elders had said to them.
B044C004V024	44	4	24	And when they heard this, they lifted up their voices to God with one accord, and said, Lord, you are he who made the heaven, and earth, and the sea, and all that is in them:
B044C004V025	44	4	25	Who by the mouth of our father David said, Why did the Gentiles rage, and the people imagine vain things?
B044C004V026	44	4	26	The kings of the earth took their stand, and the rulers were gathered together against the Lord, and against his Christ.
B044C004V027	44	4	27	For truly in this city, against your holy servant Jesus, whom you have anointed, both Herod, and Pontius Pilate, with the Gentiles and the people of Israel, were gathered together,
B044C004V028	44	4	28	To do whatever your hand and your counsel predestined to be done.
B044C004V029	44	4	29	And now, Lord, behold their threatenings, and grant to your servants that they may speak your word with all boldness,
B044C004V030	44	4	30	while you stretch forth your hand to heal, and signs and wonders are done through the name of your holy servant Jesus.
B044C004V031	44	4	31	And when they had prayed, the place where they were assembled was shaken; and they were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and they spoke the word of God with boldness.
B044C004V032	44	4	32	And the multitude of those who believed were of one heart and of one soul: and no one said that any of the things which he possessed was his own; but they had all things in common.
B044C004V033	44	4	33	And with great power the apostles gave witness of the resurrection of the Lord Jesus: and great grace was upon them all.
B044C004V034	44	4	34	Nor were any among them lacking: for as many as owned land or houses sold them, and brought the proceeds of the things that were sold,
B044C004V035	44	4	35	And laid them down at the apostles' feet: and distribution was made to each according to his need.
B044C004V036	44	4	36	And Joseph, a Levite from Cyprus, who was surnamed by the apostles Barnabas, (which means, The son of encouragement,)
B044C004V037	44	4	37	Sold a field he owned, and brought the money, and laid it at the apostles' feet.
B044C005V001	44	5	1	But a certain man named Ananias, with Sapphira his wife, sold a piece of property,
B044C005V002	44	5	2	And, with his wife's knowledge, kept back part of the price, and brought a certain part of it, and laid it at the apostles' feet.
B044C005V003	44	5	3	But Peter said, Ananias, why has Satan filled your heart to lie to the Holy Spirit, and to keep back part of the price of the land?
B044C005V004	44	5	4	While it was unsold, was it not your own? and even after it was sold, was not the money in your own power? why have you conceived this deed in your heart? you have not lied to men, but to God.
B044C005V005	44	5	5	On hearing these words Ananias fell down and died: and great fear came on all those who heard these things.
B044C005V006	44	5	6	And the young men arose, wrapped him up, and carried him out, and buried him.
B044C005V007	44	5	7	And it was about three hours later, when his wife, not knowing what had happened, came in.
B044C005V008	44	5	8	And Peter said to her, Tell me whether you sold the land for so much? And she said, Yes, for that much.
B044C005V009	44	5	9	Then Peter said to her, How is it that you have agreed to test the Spirit of the Lord? behold, the feet of those who have buried your husband are at the door, and shall carry you out as well.
B044C005V010	44	5	10	Then she immediately fell down at his feet, and died: and the young men came in, and found her dead, and, carrying her forth, buried her by her husband.
B044C005V011	44	5	11	And great fear came upon all the church, and upon as many as heard these things.
B044C005V012	44	5	12	And by the hands of the apostles were many signs and wonders being performed among the people; and they were all together in Solomon's porch.
B044C005V013	44	5	13	And none of the rest dared join them: but the people held them in great esteem.
B044C005V014	44	5	14	And even more believers were added to the Lord, multitudes both of men and women.
B044C005V015	44	5	15	So that they brought forth the sick into the streets, and laid them on beds and mats, that at least the shadow of Peter passing by might fall upon some of them.
B044C005V016	44	5	16	There also came a multitude from the cities around Jerusalem, bringing sick people, and those who were vexed with unclean spirits: and they were all healed.
B044C005V017	44	5	17	Then the high priest rose up, and all those who were with him, (that is, the party of the Sadducees,) and were filled with indignation,
B044C005V018	44	5	18	And laid hands on the apostles, and put them in the public jail.
B044C005V019	44	5	19	But at night an angel of the Lord opened the prison doors, and brought them forth, and said,
B044C005V020	44	5	20	Go, stand in the temple and declare to the people all the words of this life.
B044C005V021	44	5	21	And when they heard that, they entered the temple early in the morning, and taught. Now the high priest came, and those who were with him, and called the council together, the full senate of Israel, and sent to the prison to have them brought.
B044C005V022	44	5	22	But when the officers arrived, and did not find them in the prison, they returned, and reported,
B044C005V023	44	5	23	We found the prison quite securely shut, and the guards standing at the doors: but when we opened them, we found no one within.
B044C005V024	44	5	24	Now when the high priest and the captain of the temple and the chief priests heard these things, they were perplexed and wondered what would come of this.
B044C005V025	44	5	25	Then someone came and told them, Behold, the men whom you put in prison are standing in the temple, and teaching the people.
B044C005V026	44	5	26	Then the captain with the officers went, and brought them without violence: for they feared the people might stone them.
B044C005V027	44	5	27	And when they had brought them, they set them before the council: and the high priest asked them,
B044C005V028	44	5	28	Did we not sternly command you that you should not teach in this name? and, behold, you have filled Jerusalem with your doctrine, and you intend to bring this man's blood upon us.
B044C005V029	44	5	29	Then Peter and the other apostles answered and said, We ought to obey God rather than men.
B044C005V030	44	5	30	The God of our fathers raised up Jesus, whom you killed by hanging him on a tree.
B044C005V031	44	5	31	God has exalted him with his right hand to be a Prince and a Saviour, to give repentance to Israel, and forgiveness of sins.
B044C005V032	44	5	32	And we are witnesses of these things; and so is the Holy Spirit, whom God has given to those who obey him.
B044C005V033	44	5	33	When they heard that, they were cut to the heart, and wanted to kill them.
B044C005V034	44	5	34	But then there stood up in the council a Pharisee, named Gamaliel, a teacher of the law, who had a good reputation among all the people, and he commanded that the apostles be put outside for a while;
B044C005V035	44	5	35	And he said to them, You men of Israel, take care what you intend to do about these men.
B044C005V036	44	5	36	For before these days Theudas rose up, who boasted of being somebody; and a number of men, about four hundred, joined themselves to him. He was slain; and all those who followed him were scattered, and brought to nothing.
B044C005V037	44	5	37	After this man, Judas of Galilee rose up in the days of the census, and drew away many people after him: he also perished; and all those who followed him were dispersed.
B044C005V038	44	5	38	And now I say to you, Stay away from these men, and let them alone: for if this counsel or this work is from men, it will come to nothing:
B044C005V039	44	5	39	But if it is from God, you cannot overthrow it; you might even be found fighting against God.
B044C005V040	44	5	40	And they agreed with him: and when they had called in the apostles, and beaten them, they commanded that they should not speak in the name of Jesus, and let them go.
B044C005V041	44	5	41	And they departed from the presence of the council, rejoicing that they were counted worthy to suffer shame for his name.
B044C005V042	44	5	42	And daily in the temple, and in every house, they did not cease to teach and preach Jesus as the Christ.
B044C006V001	44	6	1	And in those days, when the number of the disciples was increasing, there arose a murmuring among the Hellenists against the Hebrews, because their widows were neglected in the daily distribution of food.
B044C006V002	44	6	2	Then the twelve called the multitude of the disciples to them, and said, It is not right that we should neglect the word of God to serve tables.
B044C006V003	44	6	3	Therefore, brethren, select from among you seven men of good reputation, full of the Holy Spirit and wisdom, whom we may appoint over this business.
B044C006V004	44	6	4	But we will give ourselves continually to prayer, and to the ministry of the word.
B044C006V005	44	6	5	And the saying pleased the whole multitude: and they chose Stephen, a man full of faith and of the Holy Spirit, and Philip, and Prochorus, and Nicanor, and Timon, and Parmenas, and Nicolas, a proselyte from Antioch.
B044C006V006	44	6	6	These they set before the apostles: and when they had prayed, they laid their hands on them.
B044C006V007	44	6	7	And the word of God increased; and the number of the disciples multiplied greatly in Jerusalem; and a great company of the priests were obedient to the faith.
B044C006V008	44	6	8	And Stephen, full of faith and power, did great wonders and miraculous signs among the people.
B044C006V009	44	6	9	Then there arose some from what is called the synagogue of the Freedmen, including Cyrenians, Alexandrians, and some from Cilicia and Asia, and disputed with Stephen.
B044C006V010	44	6	10	But they were not able to resist the wisdom and the spirit by which he spoke.
B044C006V011	44	6	11	Then they secretly instigated men, who said, We have heard him speak blasphemous words against Moses, and against God.
B044C006V012	44	6	12	And they stirred up the people, and the elders, and the scribes, and came upon him, and caught him, and brought him to the council,
B044C006V013	44	6	13	And they set up false witnesses, who said, This man does not cease to speak blasphemous words against this holy place, and the law:
B044C006V014	44	6	14	For we have heard him say that this Jesus of Nazareth shall destroy this place, and shall change the customs which Moses delivered to us.
B044C006V015	44	6	15	And all who sat in the council, looking steadfastly at him, saw that his face was like the face of an angel.
B044C007V001	44	7	1	Then the high priest said, Are these things so?
B044C007V002	44	7	2	And he said, Brethren and fathers, listen; The God of glory appeared to our father Abraham, when he was in Mesopotamia, before he lived in Harran,
B044C007V003	44	7	3	And said to him, Depart from your country, and from your family, and come into the land which I shall show you.
B044C007V004	44	7	4	Then he came out of the land of the Chaldaeans, and lived in Harran: and from there, when his father was dead, God sent him into this land, in which you now live.
B044C007V005	44	7	5	And he gave him no inheritance in it, no, not even enough to set his foot on: yet he promised that he would give it to him for a possession, and to his descendants after him, even though as yet he had no child.
B044C007V006	44	7	6	And God spoke to this effect, That his descendants would be strangers in a foreign land; and that they would bring them into bondage, and mistreat them for four hundred years.
B044C007V007	44	7	7	And the nation to whom they shall be in bondage I will judge, said God: and after that they shall come forth, and serve me in this place.
B044C007V008	44	7	8	And he gave him the covenant of circumcision: and so Abraham became the father of Isaac, and circumcised him on the eighth day; and Isaac became the father of Jacob; and Jacob became the father of the twelve patriarchs.
B044C007V009	44	7	9	And the patriarchs, moved with envy, sold Joseph into Egypt: but God was with him,
B044C007V010	44	7	10	And delivered him out of all his afflictions, and gave him favour and wisdom in the sight of Pharaoh, king of Egypt; who made him governor over Egypt and all his house.
B044C007V011	44	7	11	Now there came a famine over all the land of Egypt and Canaan, and great affliction: and our fathers could find no food.
B044C007V012	44	7	12	But when Jacob heard that there was grain in Egypt, he sent out our fathers the first time.
B044C007V013	44	7	13	And at the second time Joseph made himself known to his brothers; and Joseph's family was made known to Pharaoh.
B044C007V014	44	7	14	Then Joseph sent for his father Jacob, and for all his family, seventy-five in all.
B044C007V015	44	7	15	So Jacob went down to Egypt, and died, he, and our fathers,
B044C007V016	44	7	16	And they were carried over into Shechem, and laid in the tomb that Abraham bought for a sum of money from the sons of Emmor, the father of Shechem.
B044C007V017	44	7	17	But when the time of the promise drew near, which God had sworn to Abraham, the people grew and multiplied in Egypt,
B044C007V018	44	7	18	Until another king arose, who knew nothing of Joseph.
B044C007V019	44	7	19	He dealt treacherously with our race, and mistreated our fathers, forcing them to expose their young children, that they might not live.
B044C007V020	44	7	20	At this time Moses was born, and was exceedingly fair in God's sight, and he was cared for in his father's house for three months:
B044C007V021	44	7	21	And when he was exposed, Pharaoh's daughter took him up, and raised him as her own son.
B044C007V022	44	7	22	And Moses was instructed in all the wisdom of the Egyptians, and was mighty in words and in deeds.
B044C007V023	44	7	23	When he was forty years old, it came into his heart to visit his brethren, the sons of Israel.
B044C007V024	44	7	24	And seeing one of them suffer wrong, he defended him, and avenged him who was oppressed, and struck the Egyptian:
B044C007V025	44	7	25	For he supposed his brethren understood that God was granting them deliverance by his hand: but they did not understand.
B044C007V026	44	7	26	And the next day he appeared to some as they fought, and tried to reconcile them, saying, Men, you are brethren; why do you wrong one another?
B044C007V027	44	7	27	But he who was doing his neighbour wrong thrust him away, saying, Who made you a ruler and a judge over us?
B044C007V028	44	7	28	Do you want to kill me, as you did the Egyptian yesterday?
B044C007V029	44	7	29	At this remark, Moses fled, and became a stranger in the land of Midian, where he became the father of two sons.
B044C007V030	44	7	30	And when forty years had passed, there appeared to him in the wilderness of mount Sinai an angel of the Lord in a flame of fire in a bush.
B044C007V031	44	7	31	When Moses saw it, he wondered at the sight: and as he drew near to behold it, the voice of the Lord came to him,
B044C007V032	44	7	32	Saying, I am the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob. Then Moses trembled, and dared not look.
B044C007V033	44	7	33	Then the Lord said to him, Take the sandals off your feet: for the place where you stand is holy ground.
B044C007V034	44	7	34	I have surely seen the affliction of my people in Egypt, and I have heard their groaning, and have come down to deliver them. Now come, and I will send you to Egypt.
B044C007V035	44	7	35	This Moses whom they rejected, saying, Who made you a ruler and a judge? was the one God sent to be a ruler and a deliverer by the hand of the angel who appeared to him in the bush.
B044C007V036	44	7	36	He brought them out, after he had shown wonders and signs in the land of Egypt, and at the Red sea, and in the wilderness for forty years.
B044C007V037	44	7	37	This is the Moses who said to the sons of Israel, The Lord your God shall raise up for you a prophet like me from among your brethren.
B044C007V038	44	7	38	This is he who was in the congregation in the wilderness, with the angel who spoke to him on mount Sinai, and with our fathers: and he received the living oracles to give to us.
B044C007V039	44	7	39	Our fathers would not obey him, but thrust him from them, and in their hearts turned back again to Egypt,
B044C007V040	44	7	40	Saying to Aaron, Make us gods to go before us: as for this Moses, who brought us out of the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become of him.
B044C007V041	44	7	41	And they made a calf in those days, and offered a sacrifice to the idol, and rejoiced in the works of their own hands.
B044C007V042	44	7	42	Then God turned away and gave them up to worship the host of heaven; as it is written in the book of the prophets, Was it to me you offered slain beasts and sacrifices forty years in the wilderness, O house of Israel?
B044C007V043	44	7	43	You took up the tabernacle of Moloch, and the star of your god Rephan, figures which you made to worship: therefore I will carry you away beyond Babylon.
B044C007V044	44	7	44	Our fathers had the tabernacle of witness in the wilderness, made according to the pattern appointed by the one who spoke to Moses.
B044C007V045	44	7	45	Our fathers then brought it in with Joshua when they took possession of the land of the Gentiles, whom God drove out before our fathers. And so it remained there until the days of David;
B044C007V046	44	7	46	Who found favour with God, and desired to find a dwelling place for the God of Jacob.
B044C007V047	44	7	47	But it was Solomon who built him a house.
B044C007V048	44	7	48	Yet the most High does not dwell in temples made with hands; as the prophet says,
B044C007V049	44	7	49	Heaven is my throne, and earth is my footstool: what house will you build for me? says the Lord: or what is the place in which I can rest?
B044C007V050	44	7	50	Has not my hand made all these things?
B044C007V051	44	7	51	You stiffnecked people, uncircumcised in heart and ears, you always resist the Holy Spirit: as your fathers did, so you do.
B044C007V052	44	7	52	Which of the prophets did your fathers not persecute? and they killed those who told beforehand of the coming of the Righteous One; whom you have now betrayed and murdered:
B044C007V053	44	7	53	You who have received the law as delivered by angels, and have not kept it.
B044C007V054	44	7	54	When they heard these things, they were cut to the heart, and they gnashed their teeth at him.
B044C007V055	44	7	55	But he, being full of the Holy Spirit, looked up steadfastly into heaven, and saw the glory of God, and Jesus standing on the right hand of God,
B044C007V056	44	7	56	And said, Behold, I see the heavens opened, and the Son of man standing on the right hand of God.
B044C007V057	44	7	57	Then they cried out with a loud voice, and stopped their ears, and ran upon him with one accord,
B044C007V058	44	7	58	And cast him out of the city, and stoned him: and the witnesses laid down their clothes at a young man's feet, whose name was Saul.
B044C007V059	44	7	59	And as they stoned Stephen he called upon God, saying, Lord Jesus, receive my spirit.
B044C007V060	44	7	60	And he knelt down, and cried with a loud voice, Lord, do not hold this sin against them. And when he had said this, he fell asleep.
B044C008V001	44	8	1	And Saul was consenting to his death. And on that day a great persecution began against the church in Jerusalem; and they were all scattered abroad throughout the regions of Judaea and Samaria, except the apostles.
B044C008V002	44	8	2	And devout men buried Stephen, and made great lamentation over him.
B044C008V003	44	8	3	As for Saul, he ravaged the church, entering into every house, and dragging off men and women and committing them to prison.
B044C008V004	44	8	4	Therefore, those who were scattered abroad went about preaching the word.
B044C008V005	44	8	5	Then Philip went down to the city of Samaria, and preached Christ to them.
B044C008V006	44	8	6	And the people with one accord gave heed to the things of which Philip spoke, hearing and seeing the miraculous signs which he did.
B044C008V007	44	8	7	For unclean spirits, crying out with loud voices, came out of many who were possessed: and many taken with paralysis, and those who were lame, were healed.
B044C008V008	44	8	8	And there was great joy in that city.
B044C008V009	44	8	9	But there was a certain man, named Simon, who formerly practiced sorcery in the city, and amazed the people of Samaria, claiming that he was someone great:
B044C008V010	44	8	10	And they all gave heed to him, from the least to the greatest, saying, This man is the great power of God.
B044C008V011	44	8	11	And they gave heed to him, because for so long he had amazed them with sorceries.
B044C008V012	44	8	12	But when they believed Philip as he preached about the good news of the kingdom of God, and the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized, both men and women.
B044C008V013	44	8	13	Even Simon himself believed: and when he was baptized, he continued with Philip, and was amazed, beholding the miracles and signs which were done.
B044C008V014	44	8	14	Now when the apostles who were at Jerusalem heard that Samaria had received the word of God, they sent to them Peter and John:
B044C008V015	44	8	15	Who, when they had come down, prayed for them, that they might receive the Holy Spirit:
B044C008V016	44	8	16	(For as yet he had fallen upon none of them: they had simply been baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.)
B044C008V017	44	8	17	Then they laid their hands on them, and they received the Holy Spirit.
B044C008V018	44	8	18	And when Simon saw that through laying on of the apostles' hands the Holy Spirit was given, he offered them money,
B044C008V019	44	8	19	Saying, Give me also this power, that on whomever I lay hands, he may receive the Holy Spirit.
B044C008V020	44	8	20	But Peter said to him, Your silver perish with you, because you thought that the gift of God may be purchased with money.
B044C008V021	44	8	21	You have no part or portion in this matter: for your heart is not right in the sight of God.
B044C008V022	44	8	22	Therefore, repent of this wickedness, and pray to God, that perhaps the intent of your heart may be forgiven you.
B044C008V023	44	8	23	For I perceive that you are full of bitterness, and in the bondage of iniquity.
B044C008V024	44	8	24	Then Simon answered, Pray to the Lord for me, that none of these things which you have spoken may come upon me.
B044C008V025	44	8	25	And when they had testified and preached the word of the Lord, they returned to Jerusalem, and preached the gospel in many villages of the Samaritans.
B044C008V026	44	8	26	And the angel of the Lord spoke to Philip, saying, Arise, and go toward the south to the road that goes down from Jerusalem to Gaza. This is a desert road.
B044C008V027	44	8	27	And he arose and went: and, behold, a man of Ethiopia, a eunuch of great authority under Candace, queen of the Ethiopians, who had charge of all her treasure, and had come to Jerusalem to worship,
B044C008V028	44	8	28	Was returning, and sitting in his chariot reading Isaiah the prophet.
B044C008V029	44	8	29	Then the Spirit said to Philip, Go near, and join this chariot.
B044C008V030	44	8	30	And Philip ran to him, and heard him reading the prophet Isaiah, and said, Do you understand what you are reading?
B044C008V031	44	8	31	And he said, How can I, unless some man should guide me? And he invited Philip to come up and sit with him.
B044C008V032	44	8	32	Now the passage of scripture which he read was this, He was led as a sheep to the slaughter; and like a lamb silent before his shearer, so he did not open his mouth:
B044C008V033	44	8	33	In his humiliation justice was taken from him: and who shall describe his generation? for his life was taken from the earth.
B044C008V034	44	8	34	And the eunuch answered Philip, I pray you, of whom does the prophet speak? of himself, or of some other man?
B044C008V035	44	8	35	Then Philip opened his mouth, and beginning at the same scripture, preached Jesus to him.
B044C008V036	44	8	36	And as they went on their way, they came to some water: and the eunuch said, See, here is water; what prevents me from being baptized?
B044C008V037	44	8	37	[And Philip said, If you believe with all your heart, you may. And he answered, I believe that Jesus Christ is the Son of God.]
B044C008V038	44	8	38	And he commanded the chariot to stand still: and they both went down into the water, Philip and the eunuch; and he baptized him.
B044C008V039	44	8	39	And when they had come up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord caught Philip away, and the eunuch saw him no more: but he went on his way rejoicing.
B044C008V040	44	8	40	But Philip found himself at Azotus: and passing through he preached in all the cities, until he came to Caesarea.
B044C009V001	44	9	1	And Saul, still breathing out threats and slaughter against the disciples of the Lord, went to the high priest,
B044C009V002	44	9	2	And asked him for letters to the synagogues in Damascus, so that if he found any belonging to the way, whether they were men or women, he might bring them bound to Jerusalem.
B044C009V003	44	9	3	And as he traveled, he came near Damascus: and suddenly there flashed around him a light from heaven:
B044C009V004	44	9	4	And he fell to the earth, and heard a voice saying to him, Saul, Saul, why do you persecute me?
B044C009V005	44	9	5	And he said, Who are you, Lord? And he said, I am Jesus, whom you are persecuting.
B044C009V006	44	9	6	Arise, and go into the city, and you shall be told what you must do.
B044C009V007	44	9	7	And the men who traveled with him stood speechless, hearing a voice, but seeing no one.
B044C009V008	44	9	8	And Saul arose from the earth; and when his eyes were opened, he saw nothing: so they led him by the hand, and brought him into Damascus.
B044C009V009	44	9	9	And he was three days without sight, and neither ate nor drank.
B044C009V010	44	9	10	And there was a certain disciple at Damascus, named Ananias; and the Lord said to him in a vision, Ananias. And he said, Behold, I am here, Lord.
B044C009V011	44	9	11	And the Lord said to him, Arise, and go into the street which is called Straight, and enquire in the house of Judas for one called Saul, of Tarsus: for, behold, he is praying,
B044C009V012	44	9	12	And has seen in a vision a man named Ananias coming in, and putting his hands on him, that he might regain his sight.
B044C009V013	44	9	13	Then Ananias answered, Lord, I have heard from many about this man, how much evil he has done to your saints at Jerusalem:
B044C009V014	44	9	14	And he is here and has authority from the chief priests to bind all who call upon your name.
B044C009V015	44	9	15	But the Lord said to him, Go: for he is a chosen instrument of mine, to bear my name before the Gentiles, and kings, and the sons of Israel:
B044C009V016	44	9	16	I will show him how much he must suffer for my name's sake.
B044C009V017	44	9	17	And Ananias went his way, and entered the house; and putting his hands on him said, Brother Saul, the Lord Jesus, who appeared to you on the road as you came, has sent me, that you might regain your sight, and be filled with the Holy Spirit.
B044C009V018	44	9	18	And immediately there fell from his eyes something like scales: and he received his sight, and arose, and was baptized.
B044C009V019	44	9	19	And when he had received food, he was strengthened. Then Saul was for some days with the disciples who were at Damascus.
B044C009V020	44	9	20	And immediately he preached Christ in the synagogues, saying that he is the Son of God.
B044C009V021	44	9	21	But all who heard him were amazed, and said; Is this not the one who destroyed those who called on this name in Jerusalem, and did he not come here that he might bring them bound to the chief priests?
B044C009V022	44	9	22	But Saul increased all the more in strength, and confounded the Jews who lived at Damascus, by proving that Jesus is the Christ.
B044C009V023	44	9	23	And after many days were past, the Jews plotted to kill him:
B044C009V024	44	9	24	But their plot was made known to Saul. They watched the gates day and night to kill him.
B044C009V025	44	9	25	Then the disciples took him by night, and let him down in a basket through an opening in the wall.
B044C009V026	44	9	26	And when Saul had come to Jerusalem, he tried to join himself to the disciples: but they were all afraid of him, and did not believe that he was a disciple.
B044C009V027	44	9	27	But Barnabas took him, and brought him to the apostles, and declared to them how he had seen the Lord on the road, and that he had spoken to him, and how he had preached boldly at Damascus in the name of Jesus.
B044C009V028	44	9	28	And he was with them, freely coming and going in Jerusalem.
B044C009V029	44	9	29	And he spoke boldly in the name of the Lord Jesus, and disputed with the Hellenistic Jews: but they attempted to kill him.
B044C009V030	44	9	30	When the brethren learned of this, they brought him down to Caesarea, and sent him forth to Tarsus.
B044C009V031	44	9	31	Then the church had rest throughout all Judaea and Galilee and Samaria, and was being built up; and walking in the fear of the Lord, and in the comfort of the Holy Spirit, it grew in numbers.
B044C009V032	44	9	32	And it came to pass, as Peter passed throughout all those parts, he came down also to the saints who lived at Lydda.
B044C009V033	44	9	33	And there he found a certain man named Aeneas, who had been bedridden eight years, for he was a paralytic.
B044C009V034	44	9	34	And Peter said to him, Aeneas, Jesus Christ heals you: arise, and make your bed. And he arose immediately.
B044C009V035	44	9	35	And all who lived at Lydda and Sharon saw him, and turned to the Lord.
B044C009V036	44	9	36	Now there was at Joppa a certain disciple named Tabitha, which translated is Dorcas: this woman was full of good works and acts of charity.
B044C009V037	44	9	37	And it came to pass in those days, that she was sick, and died; and when they had washed her, they laid her in an upper room.
B044C009V038	44	9	38	And since Lydda was near to Joppa, and the disciples had heard that Peter was there, they sent to him two men, urging him to come to them and not delay.
B044C009V039	44	9	39	Then Peter arose and went with them. When he had come, they brought him into the upper room: and all the widows stood by him weeping, and showing the coats and garments which Dorcas made, while she was with them.
B044C009V040	44	9	40	But Peter put them all out, and knelt down, and prayed; and turning to the body said, Tabitha, arise. And she opened her eyes: and when she saw Peter, she sat up.
B044C009V041	44	9	41	And he gave her his hand, and lifted her up, and when he had called the saints and widows, presented her alive.
B044C009V042	44	9	42	And it became known throughout all Joppa; and many believed in the Lord.
B044C009V043	44	9	43	And it came to pass, that he tarried many days in Joppa with one Simon, a tanner.
B044C010V001	44	10	1	There was a certain man in Caesarea named Cornelius, a centurion of what was called the Italian cohort,
B044C010V002	44	10	2	A devout man, and one who feared God with all his house, and he gave many alms to the people, and prayed to God always.
B044C010V003	44	10	3	About the ninth hour of the day he saw in a vision an angel of God coming in to him, and saying to him, Cornelius.
B044C010V004	44	10	4	And when he looked on him, he was afraid, and said, What is it, Lord? And he said to him, Your prayers and your alms have come up as a memorial before God.
B044C010V005	44	10	5	Now send men to Joppa, and bring back one Simon, whose surname is Peter:
B044C010V006	44	10	6	He lodges with Simon, a tanner, whose house is by the sea.
B044C010V007	44	10	7	And when the angel who spoke to Cornelius had departed, he called two of his household servants, and a devout soldier from among those who waited upon him continually;
B044C010V008	44	10	8	And when he had explained all these things to them, he sent them to Joppa.
B044C010V009	44	10	9	On the next day, as they went on their journey, and drew near to the city, Peter went up upon the housetop to pray, about the sixth hour:
B044C010V010	44	10	10	And he became very hungry, and wanted to eat: but while they were making ready, he fell into a trance,
B044C010V011	44	10	11	And saw heaven opened, and something descending, like a great sheet, let down by four corners to the earth:
B044C010V012	44	10	12	In it were all manner of four-footed beasts of the earth, and creeping things, and birds of the air.
B044C010V013	44	10	13	And a voice came to him, Rise, Peter; kill, and eat.
B044C010V014	44	10	14	But Peter said, Not so, Lord; for I have never eaten anything that is common or unclean.
B044C010V015	44	10	15	And the voice spoke to him a second time, What God has cleansed, do not call unholy.
B044C010V016	44	10	16	This was done three times: and the sheet was immediately taken up again into heaven.
B044C010V017	44	10	17	Now while Peter was perplexed about the meaning of the vision which he had seen, behold, the men who were sent by Cornelius, having made enquiry for Simon's house, stood before the gate,
B044C010V018	44	10	18	And called out, asking whether Simon, known as Peter, was lodging there.
B044C010V019	44	10	19	While Peter thought about the vision, the Spirit said to him, Behold, three men seek you.
B044C010V020	44	10	20	Arise therefore, and go downstairs, and accompany them without doubting: for I have sent them.
B044C010V021	44	10	21	Then Peter went down to the men who had been sent to him by Cornelius; and said, Behold, I am the one you seek: what is the cause for which you have come?
B044C010V022	44	10	22	And they said, Cornelius the centurion, a just man, and one who fears God, and who is well spoken of among all the nation of the Jews, was directed by a holy angel to send for you to come to his house, and to hear a message from you.
B044C010V023	44	10	23	Then he called them in, and gave them lodging. And on the next day Peter went away with them, and certain brethren from Joppa accompanied him.
B044C010V024	44	10	24	And the day after they entered Caesarea. Cornelius was waiting for them, and had called together his kinsmen and near friends.
B044C010V025	44	10	25	And as Peter was coming in, Cornelius met him, and fell down at his feet, and worshipped him.
B044C010V026	44	10	26	But Peter raised him up, saying, Stand up; I am also a man.
B044C010V027	44	10	27	And as he talked with him, he went in, and found many who had come together.
B044C010V028	44	10	28	And he said to them, You know that it is an unlawful thing for a man who is a Jew to keep company, or visit one from another nation; but God has shown me that I should not call any man common or unclean.
B044C010V029	44	10	29	Therefore, I came to you without objection, as soon as I was sent for: therefore I ask for what intent you have sent for me?
B044C010V030	44	10	30	And Cornelius said, Four days ago about this hour, I was keeping the ninth hour of prayer in my house, and, behold, a man stood before me in bright clothing,
B044C010V031	44	10	31	And said, Cornelius, your prayer has been heard, and your alms are remembered by God.
B044C010V032	44	10	32	Therefore send to Joppa, and ask for Simon, who is called Peter; he is lodging in the house of one Simon, a tanner, by the sea.
B044C010V033	44	10	33	Therefore I immediately sent to you; and you have been kind enough to come. Now then, we are all present here before God, to hear all things that you have been commanded by the Lord.
B044C010V034	44	10	34	Then Peter opened his mouth, and said, Truly I perceive that God shows no partiality:
B044C010V035	44	10	35	But in every nation the man who fears him, and works righteousness, is accepted by him.
B044C010V036	44	10	36	The word which God sent to the sons of Israel, preaching peace through Jesus Christ: (he is Lord of all:)
B044C010V037	44	10	37	You know that word, which was proclaimed throughout all Judaea, beginning in Galilee, after the baptism which John preached;
B044C010V038	44	10	38	How God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Spirit and with power: how he went about doing good, and healing all who were oppressed by the devil; for God was with him.
B044C010V039	44	10	39	And we are witnesses of all things which he did both in the land of the Jews, and in Jerusalem. And they killed him by hanging him on a tree:
B044C010V040	44	10	40	But God raised him up on the third day, and showed him openly;
B044C010V041	44	10	41	Not to all the people, but to witnesses chosen beforehand by God, that is, to us, who ate and drank with him after he rose from the dead.
B044C010V042	44	10	42	And he commanded us to preach to the people, and to testify that it is he who was ordained by God to be the Judge of the living and dead.
B044C010V043	44	10	43	To him all the prophets bear witness that through his name whoever believes in him shall receive forgiveness of sins.
B044C010V044	44	10	44	While Peter was still speaking these words, the Holy Spirit fell upon all those who heard the word.
B044C010V045	44	10	45	And those of the circumcision who believed, as many as came with Peter, were astonished because the gift of the Holy Spirit was also poured out upon the Gentiles.
B044C010V046	44	10	46	For they heard them speaking with tongues, and magnifying God. Then Peter said,
B044C010V047	44	10	47	Can anyone forbid water for these to be baptized, who have received the Holy Spirit just as we have?
B044C010V048	44	10	48	And he commanded them to be baptized in the name of the Lord. Then they asked him to remain for a few days.
B044C011V001	44	11	1	Now the apostles and brethren who were in Judaea heard that the Gentiles had also received the word of God.
B044C011V002	44	11	2	And when Peter had come up to Jerusalem, those who were of the circumcision party criticized him,
B044C011V003	44	11	3	Saying, You went into the house of uncircumcised men, and ate with them.
B044C011V004	44	11	4	But Peter related the matter from the beginning, and explained it to them in order, saying,
B044C011V005	44	11	5	I was in the city of Joppa praying: and in a trance I saw a vision, A certain object descended, like a great sheet, let down from heaven by four corners; and it came down to me:
B044C011V006	44	11	6	When I had fastened my eyes upon it and considered it, I saw four-footed beasts of the earth, and wild beasts, and creeping things, and birds of the air.
B044C011V007	44	11	7	And I heard a voice saying to me, Arise, Peter; kill and eat.
B044C011V008	44	11	8	But I said, Not so, Lord: for nothing common or unclean has at any time entered into my mouth.
B044C011V009	44	11	9	But the voice answered me again from heaven, What God has cleansed, do not call unholy.
B044C011V010	44	11	10	And this happened three times: and then all was drawn up again into heaven.
B044C011V011	44	11	11	And, behold, immediately three men arrived at the house where I was, sent from Caesarea to me.
B044C011V012	44	11	12	And the Spirit told me to go with them, without doubting. And these six brethren accompanied me, and we entered the man's house:
B044C011V013	44	11	13	And he told us how he had seen an angel in his house, who stood and said to him, Send men to Joppa, and call for Simon, who is called Peter;
B044C011V014	44	11	14	Who shall give you a message, by which you and all your household shall be saved.
B044C011V015	44	11	15	And as I began to speak, the Holy Spirit fell upon them, just as upon us in the beginning.
B044C011V016	44	11	16	Then I remembered the word of the Lord, that he said, John baptized with water; but you shall be baptized with the Holy Spirit.
B044C011V017	44	11	17	Therefore, if God gave them the same gift he gave to us when we believed in the Lord Jesus Christ; who was I, that I could withstand God?
B044C011V018	44	11	18	When they heard these things, they held their peace, and glorified God, saying, Then God has also granted to the Gentiles the repentance that leads to life.
B044C011V019	44	11	19	Now those who were scattered abroad by the persecution that arose over Stephen travelled as far as Phoenicia, and Cyprus, and Antioch, preaching the word to no one but the Jews.
B044C011V020	44	11	20	But some of them were men from Cyprus and Cyrene, who, when they had come to Antioch, spoke to the Greeks also, preaching the Lord Jesus.
B044C011V021	44	11	21	And the hand of the Lord was with them: and a great number believed, and turned to the Lord.
B044C011V022	44	11	22	Then news of these things came to the ears of the church which was in Jerusalem: and they sent forth Barnabas to Antioch.
B044C011V023	44	11	23	When he came, and had seen the grace of God, he was glad, and exhorted them all, that with resolute hearts they would cling to the Lord;
B044C011V024	44	11	24	For he was a good man, and full of the Holy Spirit and of faith: and many people were added to the Lord.
B044C011V025	44	11	25	Then Barnabas departed to Tarsus, to look for Saul:
B044C011V026	44	11	26	And when he had found him, he brought him to Antioch. And it came to pass, that for a whole year they met with the church, and taught many people. And the disciples were first called Christians in Antioch.
B044C011V027	44	11	27	And in these days prophets came down from Jerusalem to Antioch.
B044C011V028	44	11	28	And one of them named Agabus stood up, and foretold by the Spirit that there would be a great famine throughout all the world: and this came to pass in the days of Claudius.
B044C011V029	44	11	29	Then the disciples, every man according to his ability, determined to send relief to the brethren who lived in Judaea:
B044C011V030	44	11	30	Which they did, sending it to the elders by the hands of Barnabas and Saul.
B044C012V001	44	12	1	Now about that time Herod the king stretched forth his hands to mistreat some who belonged to the church.
B044C012V002	44	12	2	And he killed James the brother of John with the sword.
B044C012V003	44	12	3	And because he saw it pleased the Jews, he proceeded to arrest Peter also. (This was during the days of unleavened bread.)
B044C012V004	44	12	4	And when he had apprehended him, he put him in prison, and delivered him to four squads of four soldiers to keep him; intending after passover to bring him forth to the people.
B044C012V005	44	12	5	Therefore Peter was kept in prison: but prayer to God was made for him without ceasing by the church.
B044C012V006	44	12	6	And the night before Herod would have brought him forth, Peter was sleeping between two soldiers, bound with two chains: and the keepers before the door were guarding the prison.
B044C012V007	44	12	7	And, behold, an angel of the Lord appeared, and a light shone in the prison: and he struck Peter on the side, and woke him, saying, Arise quickly. And the chains fell off his hands.
B044C012V008	44	12	8	And the angel said to him, Gird yourself, and put on your sandals. And he did so. And he said to him, Wrap your garment about you, and follow me.
B044C012V009	44	12	9	And he went out, and followed him; but he did not know that what was being done by the angel was real; but thought he was seeing a vision.
B044C012V010	44	12	10	When they were past the first and second guards, they came to the iron gate that leads to the city; which opened for them of its own accord: and they went out, and passed on through one street; and forthwith the angel departed from him.
B044C012V011	44	12	11	And when Peter had come to himself, he said, Now I know for sure that the Lord has sent his angel, and has delivered me out of the hand of Herod, and from all that the Jewish people were expecting.
B044C012V012	44	12	12	When he realized this, he went to the house of Mary, the mother of John, who was also called Mark; where many were gathered together praying.
B044C012V013	44	12	13	And as Peter knocked at the door of the gate, a maid named Rhoda came to answer.
B044C012V014	44	12	14	And when she recognized Peter's voice, in her joy she did not open the gate, but ran in, and told that Peter stood before the gate.
B044C012V015	44	12	15	And they said to her, You are mad. But she constantly affirmed that it was so. Then they said, It is his angel.
B044C012V016	44	12	16	But Peter continued knocking: and when they had opened the door, and saw him, they were astonished.
B044C012V017	44	12	17	But he, beckoning to them with his hand to hold their peace, declared to them how the Lord had brought him out of the prison. And he said, Tell these things to James, and to the brethren. Then he departed, and went to another place.
B044C012V018	44	12	18	Now as soon as it was day, there was no small stir among the soldiers over what had become of Peter.
B044C012V019	44	12	19	And when Herod sought for him, and did not find him, he examined the guards, and commanded that they should be put to death. Then he went down from Judaea to Caesarea, and remained there.
B044C012V020	44	12	20	And Herod was highly displeased with the people of Tyre and Sidon: but they came with one accord to him, and, having made Blastus the king's chamberlain, their friend, they asked for peace; because their country was fed by the king's country.
B044C012V021	44	12	21	And upon a set day Herod, arrayed in royal robes, sat upon his throne, and made an oration to them.
B044C012V022	44	12	22	And the people gave a shout, saying, It is the voice of a god, and not of a man.
B044C012V023	44	12	23	Immediately an angel of the Lord struck him, because he did not give God the glory: and he was eaten by worms, and died.
B044C012V024	44	12	24	But the word of God grew and spread.
B044C012V025	44	12	25	And Barnabas and Saul returned from Jerusalem when they had fulfilled their ministry, bringing with them John, who was also called Mark.
B044C013V001	44	13	1	Now there were in the church that was at Antioch certain prophets and teachers; Barnabas, Simeon who was called Niger, Lucius of Cyrene, Manaen, who had been brought up with Herod the tetrarch, and Saul.
B044C013V002	44	13	2	As they ministered to the Lord, and fasted, the Holy Spirit said, Separate for me Barnabas and Saul for the work to which I have called them.
B044C013V003	44	13	3	And when they had fasted and prayed, and laid their hands upon them, they sent them away.
B044C013V004	44	13	4	So, being sent forth by the Holy Spirit, they departed to Seleucia; and from there they sailed to Cyprus.
B044C013V005	44	13	5	And when they were at Salamis, they preached the word of God in the synagogues of the Jews: and they also had John to assist them.
B044C013V006	44	13	6	And when they had gone through the whole island and had come to Paphos, they found a certain Jewish sorcerer, a false prophet, whose name was Bar-Jesus:
B044C013V007	44	13	7	Who was with the proconsul of the country, Sergius Paulus, a prudent man; who called for Barnabas and Saul, and desired to hear the word of God.
B044C013V008	44	13	8	But Elymas the sorcerer (for so is his name translated) opposed them, seeking to turn the proconsul away from the faith.
B044C013V009	44	13	9	Then Saul, (who is also called Paul,) filled with the Holy Spirit, set his eyes upon him,
B044C013V010	44	13	10	And said, You who are full of all deceit and all villainy, you child of the devil, you enemy of all righteousness, will you not cease to pervert the right ways of the Lord?
B044C013V011	44	13	11	And now, behold, the hand of the Lord is upon you, and you shall be blind, not seeing the sun for a time. And immediately there fell upon him a mist and a darkness; and he went about seeking those who would lead him by the hand.
B044C013V012	44	13	12	Then the proconsul, when he saw what was done, believed, being astonished at the teaching of the Lord.
B044C013V013	44	13	13	Now when Paul and his company set sail from Paphos, they came to Perga in Pamphylia: and John departed from them and returned to Jerusalem.
B044C013V014	44	13	14	But when they departed from Perga, they came to Antioch in Pisidia, and went into the synagogue on the sabbath day, and sat down.
B044C013V015	44	13	15	And after the reading of the law and the prophets the rulers of the synagogue sent to them, saying, Brethren, if you have any word of exhortation for the people, say on.
B044C013V016	44	13	16	Then Paul stood up, and beckoning with his hand said, Men of Israel, and you who fear God, listen.
B044C013V017	44	13	17	The God of the people of Israel chose our fathers, and exalted the people when they lived in the land of Egypt, and with an uplifted arm he brought them out of it.
B044C013V018	44	13	18	And for about forty years he endured their conduct in the wilderness.
B044C013V019	44	13	19	And when he had destroyed seven nations in the land of Canaan, he gave them their land as an inheritance, for the space of four hundred and fifty years.
B044C013V020	44	13	20	And after that he gave them judges, until Samuel the prophet.
B044C013V021	44	13	21	And afterward they asked for a king: and God gave to them Saul the son of Kish, a man of the tribe of Benjamin, for the space of forty years.
B044C013V022	44	13	22	And when he had removed him, he raised up David to be their king; to whom also he gave testimony, and said, I have found David the son of Jesse, a man after my own heart, who shall fulfill all my will.
B044C013V023	44	13	23	Of this man's descendants God, according to his promise, has raised up for Israel a Saviour, Jesus.
B044C013V024	44	13	24	Before his coming John had preached the baptism of repentance to all the people of Israel.
B044C013V025	44	13	25	And as John was finishing his course, he said, Who do you think I am? I am not he. But, behold, one comes after me, the sandals of whose feet I am not worthy to untie.
B044C013V026	44	13	26	Brethren, sons of the stock of Abraham, and those among you who fear God, to us has been sent the word of this salvation.
B044C013V027	44	13	27	For those who live in Jerusalem, and their rulers, because they did not recognize him nor understand the words of the prophets which are read every sabbath day, have fulfilled these by condemning him.
B044C013V028	44	13	28	And though they found no cause for death in him, yet they asked Pilate that he be slain.
B044C013V029	44	13	29	And when they had fulfilled all that was written of him, they took him down from the tree, and laid him in a tomb.
B044C013V030	44	13	30	But God raised him from the dead:
B044C013V031	44	13	31	And he was seen for many days by those who came up with him from Galilee to Jerusalem, who are now his witnesses to the people.
B044C013V032	44	13	32	And we declare to you good news, that the promise which was made to the fathers,
B044C013V033	44	13	33	God has fulfilled to us, their children, in that he has raised up Jesus again; as it is written in the second psalm, You are my Son, this day I have begotten you.
B044C013V034	44	13	34	And concerning the fact that he raised him from the dead, no more to return to decay, he spoke in this way, I will give you the holy and sure blessings of David.
B044C013V035	44	13	35	Therefore, he says in another psalm, You shall not allow your Holy One to see decay.
B044C013V036	44	13	36	For David, after he had served the will of God in his generation, fell asleep, and was laid with his fathers, and saw corruption:
B044C013V037	44	13	37	But he, whom God raised again, saw no corruption.
B044C013V038	44	13	38	Therefore, let it be known to you, brethren, that through this man the forgiveness of sins is proclaimed to you:
B044C013V039	44	13	39	And by him all who believe are justified from all the things from which you could not be justified by the law of Moses.
B044C013V040	44	13	40	Beware, therefore, lest that which is spoken of in the prophets come upon you;
B044C013V041	44	13	41	Behold, you scoffers, and wonder, and perish: for I am doing a work in your days, a work which you shall by no means believe, though a man declare it to you.
B044C013V042	44	13	42	And as they went out of the synagogue, the people begged that these words might be told to them the next sabbath.
B044C013V043	44	13	43	Now when the congregation had broken up, many of the Jews and devout converts followed Paul and Barnabas: who spoke to them, urging them to continue in the grace of God.
B044C013V044	44	13	44	And the next sabbath day almost the whole city came together to hear the word of God.
B044C013V045	44	13	45	But when the Jews saw the multitudes, they were filled with envy, and contradicted those things which were spoken by Paul, and reviled him.
B044C013V046	44	13	46	Then Paul and Barnabas grew bold, and said, It was necessary that the word of God should have first been spoken to you: but seeing that you thrust it from you, and judge yourselves unworthy of eternal life, lo, we turn to the Gentiles.
B044C013V047	44	13	47	For so the Lord has commanded us, saying, I have set you to be a light for the Gentiles, that you should bring salvation to the ends of the earth.
B044C013V048	44	13	48	And when the Gentiles heard this, they were glad, and glorified the word of the Lord: and as many as were appointed for eternal life believed.
B044C013V049	44	13	49	And the word of the Lord spread throughout all the region.
B044C013V050	44	13	50	But the Jews stirred up the devout and honourable women, and the chief men of the city, and raised a persecution against Paul and Barnabas, and expelled them from their region.
B044C013V051	44	13	51	But they shook the dust off of their feet against them, and went to Iconium.
B044C013V052	44	13	52	And the disciples were filled with joy, and with the Holy Spirit.
B044C014V001	44	14	1	And it came to pass in Iconium, that they went together into the synagogue of the Jews, and so spoke, that a great multitude both of the Jews and of the Greeks believed.
B044C014V002	44	14	2	But the unbelieving Jews stirred up the Gentiles, and poisoned their minds against the brethren.
B044C014V003	44	14	3	Therefore, for a long time they remained there, speaking boldly in the Lord, who gave testimony to the word of his grace, and granted signs and wonders to be done by their hands.
B044C014V004	44	14	4	But the multitude of the city was divided: and part held with the Jews, and part with the apostles.
B044C014V005	44	14	5	And when there was an attempt made by both the Gentiles, and the Jews with their rulers, to abuse them, and to stone them,
B044C014V006	44	14	6	They learned of it, and fled to Lystra and Derbe, cities of Lycaonia, and to the surrounding region:
B044C014V007	44	14	7	And there they preached the gospel.
B044C014V008	44	14	8	Now there sat a certain man at Lystra without strength in his feet; he was a cripple from his mother's womb, who never had walked.
B044C014V009	44	14	9	He heard Paul speak: and Paul, who steadfastly beheld him, and perceiving that he had faith to be healed,
B044C014V010	44	14	10	Said with a loud voice, Stand upright on your feet. And he leaped up and walked.
B044C014V011	44	14	11	And when the people saw what Paul had done, they lifted up their voices, saying in the speech of Lycaonia, The gods have come down to us in the likeness of men.
B044C014V012	44	14	12	And they called Barnabas, Zeus; and Paul, Hermes, because he was the chief speaker.
B044C014V013	44	14	13	Then the priest of Zeus, whose temple was in front of their city, brought oxen and garlands to the gates, and would have offered a sacrifice with the people.
B044C014V014	44	14	14	When the apostles, Barnabas and Paul, heard this, they tore their clothes, and ran in among the people, crying out,
B044C014V015	44	14	15	Men, why do you these things? We also are men of the same nature as you, and we preach to you that you should turn from these vain things to the living God, who made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and all things that are in them.
B044C014V016	44	14	16	In times past he allowed all nations to walk in their own ways;
B044C014V017	44	14	17	Nevertheless, he did not leave himself without a witness, in that he did good, and gave you rain from heaven, and fruitful seasons, filling your hearts with food and gladness.
B044C014V018	44	14	18	And even with these words they scarcely restrained the people from offering sacrifice to them.
B044C014V019	44	14	19	And certain Jews came from Antioch and Iconium, who, having persuaded the people, stoned Paul, and dragged him out of the city, supposing he was dead.
