B044C015V040	44	15	40	And Paul chose Silas, and departed, being commended by the brethren to the grace of God.
B044C015V041	44	15	41	And he went through Syria and Cilicia, strengthening the churches.
B044C016V001	44	16	1	Then he came to Derbe and Lystra: and, behold, a certain disciple was there, named Timothy, the son of a certain woman, who was Jewish, and believed; but his father was a Greek;
B044C016V002	44	16	2	And he was well spoken of by the brethren who were in Lystra and Iconium.
B044C016V003	44	16	3	Paul wanted him to go forth with him; and took and circumcised him because of the Jews who were in those parts: for they all knew that his father was a Greek.
B044C016V004	44	16	4	And as they went through the cities, they delivered to them the decrees, that were ordained by the apostles and elders who were in Jerusalem.
B044C016V005	44	16	5	And so the churches were strengthened in the faith, and increased in number daily.
B044C016V006	44	16	6	Now when they had gone throughout Phrygia and the region of Galatia, having been forbidden by the Holy Spirit to preach the word in Asia,
B044C016V007	44	16	7	After they had come to Mysia, they tried to go into Bithynia: but the Spirit of Jesus did not allow them.
B044C016V008	44	16	8	And passing by Mysia, they came down to Troas.
B044C016V009	44	16	9	And a vision appeared to Paul in the night; There stood a man of Macedonia, pleading with him, saying, Come over into Macedonia, and help us.
B044C016V010	44	16	10	And after he had seen the vision, we immediately endeavoured to go into Macedonia, concluding that the Lord had called us to preach the gospel to them.
B044C016V011	44	16	11	Therefore, setting sail from Troas, we came on a straight course to Samothrace, and the next day to Neapolis;
B044C016V012	44	16	12	And from there to Philippi, which is the chief city of that part of Macedonia, and a Roman colony: and we remained in that city some days.
B044C016V013	44	16	13	And on the sabbath we went out of the city to the riverside, where we expected there would be a place of prayer; and we sat down, and spoke to the women who gathered there.
B044C016V014	44	16	14	And a certain woman named Lydia, a seller of purple, of the city of Thyatira, who worshipped God, heard us. The Lord opened her heart, so she attended to the things which were spoken by Paul.
B044C016V015	44	16	15	And when she was baptized, and her household, she begged us, saying, If you have judged me to be faithful to the Lord, come to my house, and stay there. And she persuaded us.
B044C016V016	44	16	16	And it came to pass, as we went to prayer, a certain slave girl possessed by a spirit of divination met us, and she brought her masters much gain by fortune-telling:
B044C016V017	44	16	17	She followed Paul and us, and cried out, These men are servants of the most high God, who proclaim to you the way of salvation.
B044C016V018	44	16	18	And this she did for many days. But Paul, being greatly annoyed, turned and said to the spirit, I command you in the name of Jesus Christ to come out of her. And it came out that same hour.
B044C016V019	44	16	19	And when her masters saw that their hope for profit was gone, they caught Paul and Silas, and dragged them into the marketplace before the rulers,
B044C016V020	44	16	20	And having brought them to the magistrates, they said, These men, being Jews, are troubling our city exceedingly,
B044C016V021	44	16	21	And they teach customs which are not lawful for us Romans to accept, or to observe.
B044C016V022	44	16	22	And the multitude also rose up against them: and the magistrates tore the clothes off of them, and commanded that they be beaten with rods.
B044C016V023	44	16	23	And when they had struck them with many blows, they cast them into prison, charging the jailer to keep them securely:
B044C016V024	44	16	24	And he, having received this charge, thrust them into the inner prison, and made their feet fast in the stocks.
B044C016V025	44	16	25	And at midnight Paul and Silas prayed, and sang praises to God: and the prisoners heard them.
B044C016V026	44	16	26	And suddenly there was a great earthquake, so that the foundations of the prison were shaken: and immediately all the doors were opened, and everyone's chains were unfastened.
B044C016V027	44	16	27	And the keeper of the prison awakened out of his sleep, and seeing the prison doors open, he drew his sword, and was about to kill himself, supposing that the prisoners had fled.
B044C016V028	44	16	28	But Paul cried out with a loud voice, saying, Do yourself no harm: for we are all here.
B044C016V029	44	16	29	Then he called for a light, and rushed in, and came trembling, and fell down before Paul and Silas,
B044C016V030	44	16	30	And brought them out, and said, Men, what must I do to be saved?
B044C016V031	44	16	31	And they said, Believe in the Lord Jesus Christ, and you shall be saved, you and your household.
B044C016V032	44	16	32	And they spoke the word of the Lord to him, and to all who were in his house.
B044C016V033	44	16	33	And he took them that same hour of the night, and washed their wounds; and was immediately baptized, he and all his household.
B044C016V034	44	16	34	And when he had brought them into his house, he set food before them, and rejoiced with all his household, because they believed in God.
B044C016V035	44	16	35	And when it was day, the magistrates sent officers, saying, Let those men go.
B044C016V036	44	16	36	And the keeper of the prison told this to Paul, The magistrates have sent to let you go: now therefore depart, and go in peace.
B044C016V037	44	16	37	But Paul said to them, They have beaten us openly, uncondemned, men who are Romans, and have cast us into prison; and now do they send us away secretly? no indeed; let them come themselves and fetch us out.
B044C016V038	44	16	38	And the officers told these words to the magistrates: and they were afraid when they heard that they were Romans.
B044C016V039	44	16	39	And they came to appease them, and brought them out, and asked them to depart from the city.
B044C016V040	44	16	40	So they went out of the prison, and entered the house of Lydia: and when they had seen the brethren, they encouraged them, then departed.
B044C017V001	44	17	1	Now when they had passed through Amphipolis and Apollonia, they came to Thessalonica, where there was a synagogue of the Jews:
B044C017V002	44	17	2	And Paul, as his manner was, went in to them, and for three sabbath days reasoned with them from the scriptures,
B044C017V003	44	17	3	Explaining and proving, that Christ needed to suffer, and to rise again from the dead; and saying, this Jesus, whom I preach to you, is the Christ.
B044C017V004	44	17	4	And some of them believed, and joined Paul and Silas; as did a great multitude of the devout Greeks, and not a few of the chief women.
B044C017V005	44	17	5	But the Jews who did not believe were moved with envy, and took certain wicked fellows of the rabble, and gathered a crowd, and set all the city in an uproar, and assaulted the house of Jason, and sought to bring them out to the people.
B044C017V006	44	17	6	And when they did not find them, they dragged Jason and certain brethren to the rulers of the city, crying out, These men who have turned the world upside down have come here also;
B044C017V007	44	17	7	And Jason has welcomed them: and they do all that is contrary to the decrees of Caesar, saying that there is another king, Jesus.
B044C017V008	44	17	8	And the people and the rulers of the city were troubled when they heard these things.
B044C017V009	44	17	9	And when they had taken security from Jason, and from the others, they let them go.
B044C017V010	44	17	10	And the brethren immediately sent Paul and Silas away by night to Beroea. When they arrived they went into the synagogue of the Jews.
B044C017V011	44	17	11	These were more noble than those in Thessalonica, for they received the word with all readiness of mind, and searched the scriptures daily, to see whether these things were so.
B044C017V012	44	17	12	Therefore, many of them believed; together with not a few prominent Greek women, and many men as well.
B044C017V013	44	17	13	But when the Jews of Thessalonica learned that the word of God was being preached by Paul at Beroea, they came there also, and stirred up the people.
B044C017V014	44	17	14	Then immediately the brethren sent Paul away to the sea: but Silas and Timothy remained there.
B044C017V015	44	17	15	And those who conducted Paul brought him to Athens: and receiving a commandment for Silas and Timothy to come to him with all speed, they departed.
B044C017V016	44	17	16	Now while Paul waited for them at Athens, his spirit was stirred in him, when he saw the city wholly given to idolatry.
B044C017V017	44	17	17	Therefore, he reasoned in the synagogue with the Jews, and with the devout persons, and in the market daily with those who happened to be there.
B044C017V018	44	17	18	Then certain philosophers of the Epicureans, and of the Stoics, encountered him. And some said, What is this babbler trying to say? and others, He seems to be a proclaimer of strange gods: because he preached to them Jesus, and the resurrection.
B044C017V019	44	17	19	And they took him, and brought him to the Areopagus, saying, May we know what this new doctrine is, of which you speak?
B044C017V020	44	17	20	For you bring certain strange things to our ears: therefore we want to know what these things mean.
B044C017V021	44	17	21	(For all the Athenians, and the strangers there, spent their time in nothing else, but telling, or hearing something new.)
B044C017V022	44	17	22	Then Paul stood in the midst of the Areopagus, and said, Men of Athens, I perceive that in all things you are very religious.
B044C017V023	44	17	23	For as I passed by, and beheld the objects of your devotions, I found an altar with this inscription, TO THE UNKNOWN GOD. Therefore, what you worship as unknown, this I declare to you.
B044C017V024	44	17	24	The God who made the world and all things in it, since he is Lord of heaven and earth, does not dwell in temples made with hands;
B044C017V025	44	17	25	Neither is he served by men's hands, as though he needed anything, for he himself gives to all life, and breath, and all things;
B044C017V026	44	17	26	And he has made from one all nations of men to live on all the face of the earth, and has determined their allotted times, and the boundaries of their habitation;
B044C017V027	44	17	27	That they should seek God, in the hope that they might grope for him, and find him, though he is not far from every one of us:
B044C017V028	44	17	28	For in him we live, and move, and have our being; as some of your own poets have said, For we also are his offspring.
B044C017V029	44	17	29	Being then the offspring of God, we ought not to think that the Deity is like gold, or silver, or stone, formed by art and man's imagination.
B044C017V030	44	17	30	Those times of ignorance God overlooked; but now he commands all men everywhere to repent:
B044C017V031	44	17	31	Because he has appointed a day in which he will judge the world in righteousness, by a man whom he has ordained; and he has given assurance of this to all men by raising him from the dead.
B044C017V032	44	17	32	And when they heard of the resurrection of the dead, some mocked: and others said, We will hear you again on this matter.
B044C017V033	44	17	33	So Paul departed from among them.
B044C017V034	44	17	34	Yet certain men joined him, and believed: among them was Dionysius the Areopagite, and a woman named Damaris, and others with them.
B044C018V001	44	18	1	After these things Paul departed from Athens, and went to Corinth;
B044C018V002	44	18	2	And found a certain Jew named Aquila, born in Pontus, lately come from Italy, with his wife Priscilla; (because Claudius had commanded all Jews to depart from Rome:) and came to see them.
B044C018V003	44	18	3	And because he was of the same craft, he stayed with them, and worked: for they were tentmakers by occupation.
B044C018V004	44	18	4	And he reasoned in the synagogue every sabbath, and persuaded the Jews and the Greeks.
B044C018V005	44	18	5	And when Silas and Timothy had come from Macedonia, Paul devoted himself to preaching, and testified to the Jews that Jesus was the Christ.
B044C018V006	44	18	6	And when they opposed and reviled him, he shook out his clothing, and said to them, May your blood be upon your own heads; I am clean: henceforth I will go to the Gentiles.
B044C018V007	44	18	7	And he departed from there, and entered a certain man's house, named Justus, one who worshipped God, whose house was next to the synagogue.
B044C018V008	44	18	8	And Crispus, the chief ruler of the synagogue, believed in the Lord with all his household; and many of the Corinthians heard and believed, and were baptized.
B044C018V009	44	18	9	Then the Lord spoke to Paul at night by a vision, Do not be afraid, but speak, and do not hold your peace:
B044C018V010	44	18	10	For I am with you, and no man shall attack and hurt you: for I have many people in this city.
B044C018V011	44	18	11	And he stayed there a year and six months, teaching the word of God among them.
B044C018V012	44	18	12	And when Gallio was the proconsul of Achaia, the Jews rose up with one accord against Paul, and brought him to the judgment seat,
B044C018V013	44	18	13	Saying, This fellow persuades men to worship God contrary to the law.
B044C018V014	44	18	14	And when Paul was about to open his mouth, Gallio said to the Jews, If it were a matter of wrongdoing or vicious crime, O Jews, I would have reason to bear with you:
B044C018V015	44	18	15	But if it is a question of words and names, and of your own law, look to it yourselves; for I will not be a judge of such matters.
B044C018V016	44	18	16	And he drove them from the judgment seat.
B044C018V017	44	18	17	Then they all took Sosthenes, the chief ruler of the synagogue, and beat him before the judgment seat. And Gallio was not concerned about any of these things.
B044C018V018	44	18	18	And after this Paul remained there many days longer, and then took his leave of the brethren, and sailed from there to Syria, and with him were Priscilla and Aquila. He cut his hair in Cenchrea: for he had made a vow.
B044C018V019	44	18	19	And he came to Ephesus, and left them there: but he entered into the synagogue, and reasoned with the Jews.
B044C018V020	44	18	20	When they asked him to remain longer with them, he did not consent;
B044C018V021	44	18	21	But bade them farewell, saying, I will return to you, if God wills. And he sailed from Ephesus.
B044C018V022	44	18	22	And when he had landed at Caesarea, he went up and greeted the church, then went down to Antioch.
B044C018V023	44	18	23	And after he had spent some time there, he departed, and went throughout the region of Galatia and on through Phrygia, strengthening all the disciples.
B044C018V024	44	18	24	Now a certain Jew named Apollos, born at Alexandria, an eloquent man, and mighty in the scriptures, came to Ephesus.
B044C018V025	44	18	25	This man was instructed in the way of the Lord; and being fervent in spirit, he spoke and diligently taught the things concerning Jesus, though he knew only the baptism of John.
B044C018V026	44	18	26	And he began to speak boldly in the synagogue: and when Aquila and Priscilla heard him, they took him aside, and explained to him the way of God more accurately.
B044C018V027	44	18	27	And when he wanted to go to Achaia, the brethren wrote, exhorting the disciples to welcome him: and when he had come, he greatly helped those who through grace had believed:
B044C018V028	44	18	28	For he mightily refuted the Jews, and that publicly, showing by the scriptures that Jesus was the Christ.
B044C019V001	44	19	1	And it came to pass, while Apollos was at Corinth, that Paul, having passed through the upper regions, came to Ephesus: and finding certain disciples,
B044C019V002	44	19	2	He said to them, Did you receive the Holy Spirit when you believed? And they said to him, We have not even heard that there is a Holy Spirit.
B044C019V003	44	19	3	And he said to them, Into what then were you baptized? And they said, Into John's baptism.
B044C019V004	44	19	4	Then Paul said, John baptized with the baptism of repentance, saying to the people, that they should believe in the one who would come after him, that is, in Jesus.
B044C019V005	44	19	5	When they heard this, they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.
B044C019V006	44	19	6	And when Paul had laid his hands upon them, the Holy Spirit came upon them; and they spoke with tongues, and prophesied.
B044C019V007	44	19	7	And there were about twelve of them in all.
B044C019V008	44	19	8	And he went into the synagogue, and spoke boldly for the space of three months, reasoning and persuading them about the kingdom of God.
B044C019V009	44	19	9	But when some were hardened, and did not believe, but spoke evil of the way before the multitude, he departed from them, took away the disciples, and held discussions daily in the school of Tyrannus.
B044C019V010	44	19	10	And this continued for two years; so that all those who lived in Asia heard the word of the Lord Jesus, both Jews and Greeks.
B044C019V011	44	19	11	And God performed extraordinary miracles by the hands of Paul:
B044C019V012	44	19	12	So that handkerchiefs or aprons he had touched were brought to the sick, and diseases departed from them, and the evil spirits went out of them.
B044C019V013	44	19	13	Then certain of the itinerant Jewish exorcists took it upon themselves to pronounce the name of the Lord Jesus over those who had evil spirits, saying, We command you by Jesus whom Paul preaches.
B044C019V014	44	19	14	There were seven sons of Sceva, a Jewish high priest, who were doing this.
B044C019V015	44	19	15	And the evil spirit answered, Jesus I know, and Paul I know; but who are you?
B044C019V016	44	19	16	And the man who had the evil spirit leaped on them, subdued them and overcame them, so that they fled out of that house naked and wounded.
B044C019V017	44	19	17	And this became known to all the Jews and Greeks dwelling in Ephesus; and fear fell upon them all, and the name of the Lord Jesus was magnified.
B044C019V018	44	19	18	And many who believed came, and confessed, and disclosed their deeds.
B044C019V019	44	19	19	Many of those who used magic arts brought their books together, and burned them before all: and they counted the price of them, and found it to be fifty thousand pieces of silver.
B044C019V020	44	19	20	So the word of God grew and prevailed mightily.
B044C019V021	44	19	21	After these things had ended, Paul resolved in the spirit to pass through Macedonia and Achaia and go to Jerusalem, saying, After I have been there, I must also see Rome.
B044C019V022	44	19	22	So he sent to Macedonia two of those who had ministered to him, Timothy and Erastus; but he stayed in Asia for a while.
B044C019V023	44	19	23	And about that time there arose no small stir about the way.
B044C019V024	44	19	24	For a certain man named Demetrius, a silversmith, who made silver shrines for Diana, brought no small gain to the craftsmen;
B044C019V025	44	19	25	These he called together, along with workmen of similar occupations, and said, Men, you know that by this craft we have our wealth.
B044C019V026	44	19	26	Moreover you see and hear, that not only in Ephesus, but almost throughout all Asia, this Paul has persuaded and turned away many people, saying that gods made with hands are not gods at all:
B044C019V027	44	19	27	So not only is our craft in danger of being discredited; but also the temple of the great goddess Diana may count for nothing, and her magnificence may be degraded, she whom all Asia and the world worships.
B044C019V028	44	19	28	And when they heard this, they were filled with rage, and cried out, Great is Diana of the Ephesians.
B044C019V029	44	19	29	And the whole city was filled with confusion: and dragging Gaius and Aristarchus, men of Macedonia and Paul's companions in travel, they rushed with one accord into the theatre.
B044C019V030	44	19	30	Paul wanted to enter in among the people, but the disciples would not let him.
B044C019V031	44	19	31	And certain of the chief officials of Asia, who were his friends, sent to him, asking him not to venture into the theatre.
B044C019V032	44	19	32	Some cried out one thing, and some another: for the assembly was confused; and most of them did not know why they had come together.
B044C019V033	44	19	33	And some of the multitude called upon Alexander, whom the Jews had put forward. And Alexander beckoned with his hand, and would have made a defence to the people.
B044C019V034	44	19	34	But when they recognized that he was a Jew, they all cried out with one voice for about two hours, Great is Diana of the Ephesians.
B044C019V035	44	19	35	And when the town clerk had calmed the people, he said, Men of Ephesus, what man is there who does not know that the city of the Ephesians is the guardian of the great goddess Diana, and of the image which fell down from heaven?
B044C019V036	44	19	36	Seeing then that these things cannot be denied, you ought to be quiet, and to do nothing rash.
B044C019V037	44	19	37	For you have brought here these men, who are neither robbers of temples, nor blasphemers of our goddess.
B044C019V038	44	19	38	Therefore, if Demetrius, and the craftsmen who are with him, have a complaint against any man, the courts are open, and there are proconsuls: let them bring charges against one another.
B044C019V039	44	19	39	But if you require anything beyond this, it shall be settled in the regular assembly.
B044C019V040	44	19	40	For we are in danger of being charged with rioting today, since there is no cause we can give to justify this disorder.
B044C019V041	44	19	41	And when he had spoken thus, he dismissed the assembly.
B044C020V001	44	20	1	And after the uproar had ceased, Paul called the disciples to him, and after exhorting them, he embraced them and departed to go to Macedonia.
B044C020V002	44	20	2	And when he had gone through those parts, and had given them much encouragement, he came to Greece,
B044C020V003	44	20	3	And there he remained three months. And when the Jews laid in wait for him, as he was about to sail into Syria, he decided to return through Macedonia.
B044C020V004	44	20	4	And he was accompanied into Asia by Sopater of Beroea, son of Pyrrhus; and the Thessalonians, Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timothy; and from Asia, Tychicus and Trophimus.
B044C020V005	44	20	5	These went on ahead and waited for us at Troas.
B044C020V006	44	20	6	And we sailed away from Philippi after the days of unleavened bread, and came to them at Troas in five days; where we stayed seven days.
B044C020V007	44	20	7	And upon the first day of the week, when the disciples came together to break bread, Paul preached to them, and because he intended to depart the next day; he continued his speech until midnight.
B044C020V008	44	20	8	And there were many lights in the upper chamber, where they were gathered together.
B044C020V009	44	20	9	And there sat in a window a certain young man named Eutychus, who was sinking into a deep sleep: and as Paul kept talking, he was overcome by sleep, and fell down from the third floor, and was taken up dead.
B044C020V010	44	20	10	And Paul went down, and bent over him, and embraced him saying, Do not trouble yourselves; for his life is in him.
B044C020V011	44	20	11	When Paul came up again, and had broken bread, and eaten, he talked a long while, even until the break of day, then he departed.
B044C020V012	44	20	12	And they took the young man home alive, and were not a little comforted.
B044C020V013	44	20	13	And we went ahead to the ship, and sailed to Assos, intending to take Paul aboard there: for so he had directed, intending himself to go by foot.
B044C020V014	44	20	14	And when he met with us at Assos, we took him aboard, and came to Mitylene.
B044C020V015	44	20	15	And we sailed from there, and arrived the next day opposite Chios; and the following day we crossed over to Samos; and the next day we came to Miletus.
B044C020V016	44	20	16	For Paul had determined to sail past Ephesus, because he did not want to spend time in Asia: for he was making haste, so that if possible, he would be in Jerusalem on the day of Pentecost.
B044C020V017	44	20	17	And from Miletus he sent to Ephesus, and called for the elders of the church.
B044C020V018	44	20	18	And when they had come to him, he said to them, You yourselves know, from the first day that I came to Asia, in what manner I have lived among you at all times,
B044C020V019	44	20	19	Serving the Lord with all humility of mind, and with many tears, and with trials which befell me by the plots of the Jews:
B044C020V020	44	20	20	How I kept back nothing that was profitable for you, but have taught you publicly, and from house to house,
B044C020V021	44	20	21	Testifying both to the Jews, and to the Greeks, of repentance toward God, and faith in our Lord Jesus Christ.
B044C020V022	44	20	22	And now, behold, I go bound in the spirit, to Jerusalem, not knowing the things that shall befall me there:
B044C020V023	44	20	23	Except that the Holy Spirit testifies to me in every city, that bonds and afflictions await me.
B044C020V024	44	20	24	But I do not count my life as precious to myself, so that I might finish my course, and the ministry, which I have received from the Lord Jesus, to testify to the gospel of the grace of God.
B044C020V025	44	20	25	And now, behold, I know that you all, among whom I have gone about preaching the kingdom of God, shall see my face no more.
B044C020V026	44	20	26	Therefore, I testify to you this day, that I am innocent of the blood of all men.
B044C020V027	44	20	27	For I have not hesitated to declare to you all the counsel of God.
B044C020V028	44	20	28	Take heed for yourselves, and for all the flock, over which the Holy Spirit has made you overseers, to shepherd the church of God, which he has purchased with his own blood.
B044C020V029	44	20	29	For I know this, that after my departure savage wolves shall enter in among you, not sparing the flock.
B044C020V030	44	20	30	And from among your own selves men shall arise, speaking perverse things, to draw away the disciples after them.
B044C020V031	44	20	31	Therefore watch, and remember, that for three years I did not cease to warn every one night and day with tears.
B044C020V032	44	20	32	And now, brethren, I commit you to God, and to the word of his grace, which is able to build you up, and to give you an inheritance among all those who are sanctified.
B044C020V033	44	20	33	I have coveted no man's silver, or gold, or apparel.
B044C020V034	44	20	34	You yourselves know, that these hands have ministered to my needs, and to the needs of those who were with me.
B044C020V035	44	20	35	I have shown you in all things, that by labouring in this manner you ought to support the weak, and to remember the words the Lord Jesus himself said, It is more blessed to give than to receive.
B044C020V036	44	20	36	And when he had spoken thus, he knelt down, and prayed with them all.
B044C020V037	44	20	37	And they all wept bitterly, and fell on Paul's neck, and kissed him,
B044C020V038	44	20	38	Sorrowing most of all for the words which he spoke, that they should see his face no more. And they accompanied him to the ship.
B044C021V001	44	21	1	And it came to pass, that after we parted from them, and had set sail, we came by a straight course to Cos, and the following day to Rhodes, and from there to Patara:
B044C021V002	44	21	2	And finding a ship sailing over to Phoenicia, we went aboard, and set forth.
B044C021V003	44	21	3	Now when we had sighted Cyprus, we passed it on our left, and sailed to Syria, and landed at Tyre: for there the ship was to unload its cargo.
B044C021V004	44	21	4	And finding disciples, we remained there seven days: and they kept saying to Paul by the Spirit, that he should not go up to Jerusalem.
B044C021V005	44	21	5	And when our days there had ended, we departed and went our way; and they all accompanied us on our way, with wives and children, until we were out of the city: and we knelt down on the shore, and prayed.
B044C021V006	44	21	6	Then when we had taken leave of one another, we got on the ship; and they returned home again.
B044C021V007	44	21	7	And when we had finished our voyage from Tyre, we came to Ptolemais, and greeted the brethren, and stayed with them one day.
B044C021V008	44	21	8	The next day we departed, and went to Caesarea: and we entered the house of Philip the evangelist, who was one of the seven; and stayed with him.
B044C021V009	44	21	9	And he had four unmarried daughters who prophesied.
B044C021V010	44	21	10	And while we remained there some days, there came down from Judaea a certain prophet, named Agabus.
B044C021V011	44	21	11	When he had come to us, he took Paul's belt, and bound his own hands and feet, and said, Thus says the Holy Spirit, So shall the Jews at Jerusalem bind the man who owns this belt, and shall deliver him into the hands of the Gentiles.
B044C021V012	44	21	12	When we heard these things, both we, and the people of that place, begged him not to go up to Jerusalem.
B044C021V013	44	21	13	Then Paul answered, What do you mean by weeping and breaking my heart? for I am ready not only to be bound, but also to die in Jerusalem for the name of the Lord Jesus.
B044C021V014	44	21	14	And when he would not be persuaded, we ceased, saying, The will of the Lord be done.
B044C021V015	44	21	15	And after those days we packed our baggage, and went up to Jerusalem.
B044C021V016	44	21	16	There also went with us certain of the disciples of Caesarea, who brought us to the house of Mnason of Cyprus, an early disciple, with whom we should lodge.
B044C021V017	44	21	17	And when we had come to Jerusalem, the brethren received us gladly.
B044C021V018	44	21	18	The following day Paul went in with us to James; and all the elders were present.
B044C021V019	44	21	19	And when he had greeted them, he declared in detail the things God had done among the Gentiles through his ministry.
B044C021V020	44	21	20	And when they heard it, they glorified the Lord, and said to him, You see, brother, how many thousands of Jews there are who believe; and they are all zealous for the law:
B044C021V021	44	21	21	And they have been informed about you, that you teach all the Jews who are among the Gentiles to forsake Moses, saying that they ought not to circumcise their children, nor to walk after our customs.
B044C021V022	44	21	22	What then is to be done? for they will surely hear that you have come.
B044C021V023	44	21	23	Therefore, do this that we tell you: We have four men who have taken a vow;
B044C021V024	44	21	24	Them take, and purify yourself with them, and pay their expenses, that they may shave their heads: thus all will know that those things, of which they were informed concerning you, are nothing; but that you yourself also walk in obedience to the law.
B044C021V025	44	21	25	As for the Gentiles who believe, we have written with our decision that they should keep themselves from things offered to idols, and from blood, and from what is strangled, and from sexual immorality.
B044C021V026	44	21	26	Then Paul took the men, and the next day purified himself with them, then entered the temple to give notice when the days of purification would be fulfilled and an offering should be made for each one of them.
B044C021V027	44	21	27	And when the seven days had almost ended, the Jews who were of Asia, when they saw him in the temple, stirred up all the people, and laid hands on him,
B044C021V028	44	21	28	Crying out, Men of Israel, help: This is the man who teaches all men everywhere against the people, and the law, and this place: and further, he has also brought Greeks into the temple, and has polluted this holy place.
B044C021V029	44	21	29	(For they had earlier seen him in the city with Trophimus, an Ephesian, whom they supposed that Paul had brought into the temple.)
B044C021V030	44	21	30	And all the city was aroused, and the people ran together: and they took Paul, and dragged him out of the temple: and immediately the doors were shut.
B044C021V031	44	21	31	And as they tried to kill him, word came to the commander of the Roman garrison, that all Jerusalem was in an uproar.
B044C021V032	44	21	32	He immediately took soldiers and centurions, and ran down to them: and when they saw the commander and the soldiers, they stopped beating Paul.
B044C021V033	44	21	33	Then the commander came near, and arrested him, and commanded him to be bound with two chains; and asked who he was, and what he had done.
B044C021V034	44	21	34	Some among the multitude cried out one thing, some another: and when he could not learn the truth because of the tumult, he commanded him to be brought to the barracks.
B044C021V035	44	21	35	And when he came to the stairs, he had to be carried by the soldiers because of the violence of the people.
B044C021V036	44	21	36	For the multitude of people followed, crying out, Away with him.
B044C021V037	44	21	37	And as Paul was to be led into the barracks, he said to the commander, May I speak to you? And he replied, Can you speak Greek?
B044C021V038	44	21	38	Are you not that Egyptian, who some time ago caused a rebellion, and led out into the wilderness four thousand men who were murderers?
B044C021V039	44	21	39	But Paul said, I am a Jew from Tarsus, a city in Cilicia, a citizen of no ordinary city: and, I beg you, allow me to speak to the people.
B044C021V040	44	21	40	And when he had given him permission, Paul stood on the stairs, and beckoned with his hand to the people. And when there was a great silence, he spoke to them in the Hebrew tongue, saying,
B044C022V001	44	22	1	Brethren, and fathers, hear my defence which I make to you now.
B044C022V002	44	22	2	And when they heard that he spoke in the Hebrew tongue to them, they kept silent: and he said,
B044C022V003	44	22	3	I am a Jew, born in Tarsus, a city in Cilicia, yet brought up in this city at the feet of Gamaliel, and taught according to the strict manner of the law of our fathers, and was zealous for God, as you all are this day.
B044C022V004	44	22	4	And I persecuted this way to the death, binding and delivering into prisons both men and women,
B044C022V005	44	22	5	As the high priest and all the council of the elders can bear witness. For I received from them letters to the brethren, and I went to Damascus to take those who were there and bring them bound to Jerusalem, to be punished.
B044C022V006	44	22	6	And it came to pass, that as I made my journey, and had come near to Damascus about noon, suddenly there shone from heaven a great light around me.
B044C022V007	44	22	7	And I fell to the ground, and heard a voice saying to me, Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting me?
B044C022V008	44	22	8	And I answered, Who are you, Lord? And he said to me, I am Jesus of Nazareth, whom you are persecuting.
B044C022V009	44	22	9	And those who were with me saw the light, but they did not hear the voice of the one who spoke to me.
B044C022V010	44	22	10	And I said, What shall I do, Lord? And the Lord said to me, Arise, and go into Damascus; and there it shall be told to you all things which are appointed for you to do.
B044C022V011	44	22	11	And since I could not see because of the glory of that light, I was led by the hand by those who were with me, and came into Damascus.
B044C022V012	44	22	12	And one Ananias, a devout man according to the law, having a good reputation among all the Jews who lived there,
B044C022V013	44	22	13	Came to me, and stood, and said to me, Brother Saul, receive your sight. And that very hour I could see him.
B044C022V014	44	22	14	And he said, The God of our fathers has chosen you to know his will, and to see the Just One, and to hear the voice of his mouth.
B044C022V015	44	22	15	For you shall be his witness to all men of what you have seen and heard.
B044C022V016	44	22	16	And now why do you delay? arise, and be baptized, and wash away your sins, calling on his name.
B044C022V017	44	22	17	And it came to pass, that when I had come again to Jerusalem, while I prayed in the temple, I fell into a trance;
B044C022V018	44	22	18	And saw him saying to me, Make haste, and quickly get out of Jerusalem: for they will not receive your testimony concerning me.
B044C022V019	44	22	19	And I said, Lord, they know that in every synagogue I imprisoned and beat those who believed in you:
B044C022V020	44	22	20	And when the blood of your martyr Stephen was shed, I was standing by, and consenting to his death, and kept the garments of those who killed him.
B044C022V021	44	22	21	And he said to me, Depart: for I will send you far away to the Gentiles.
B044C022V022	44	22	22	And until this word they listened to him, then they lifted up their voices, and said, Away with such a fellow from the earth: for it is not fit that he should live.
B044C022V023	44	22	23	And as they were crying out, and waving their garments, and throwing dust into the air,
B044C022V024	44	22	24	The commander ordered him to be brought into the barracks, and directed that he should be examined by scourging; that he might know why they cried out against him so.
B044C022V025	44	22	25	And as they bound him with thongs, Paul said to the centurion who stood by, Is it lawful for you to scourge a man who is a Roman, and uncondemned?
B044C022V026	44	22	26	When the centurion heard that, he went and told the commander, saying, Take heed what you do: for this man is a Roman.
B044C022V027	44	22	27	Then the commander came, and said to him, Tell me, are you a Roman? He said, Yes.
B044C022V028	44	22	28	And the commander answered, I obtained this citizenship with a great sum of money. And Paul said, But I was born a citizen.
B044C022V029	44	22	29	Then immediately those who would have examined him departed from him; and the commander was also afraid after he learned that he was a Roman and that he had bound him.
B044C022V030	44	22	30	On the next day, because he wanted to know exactly why he was accused by the Jews, he loosed him from his bonds, and commanded the chief priests and all the council to appear, and brought Paul down, and set him before them.
B044C023V001	44	23	1	And Paul, earnestly looking at the council, said, Brethren, I have lived in all good conscience before God until this day.
B044C023V002	44	23	2	And the high priest Ananias commanded those who stood by him to strike him on the mouth.
B044C023V003	44	23	3	Then Paul said to him, God shall strike you, you whitewashed wall: do you sit to judge me according to the law, yet contrary to the law command me to be struck?
B044C023V004	44	23	4	And those who stood by said, Do you revile God's high priest?
B044C023V005	44	23	5	Then Paul said, I did not know, brethren, that he was the high priest: for it is written, You shall not speak evil of a ruler of your people.
B044C023V006	44	23	6	But when Paul perceived that one part were Sadducees, and the other Pharisees, he cried out in the council, Brethren, I am a Pharisee, the son of a Pharisee: it is for the hope of the resurrection of the dead that I am on trial.
B044C023V007	44	23	7	And when he had said this, there arose a dissension between the Pharisees and the Sadducees: and the assembly was divided.
B044C023V008	44	23	8	For the Sadducees say that there is no resurrection, nor angels, or spirits: but the Pharisees acknowledge both.
B044C023V009	44	23	9	And there arose a great cry: and the scribes that were of the Pharisees' party arose, and argued vigorously, saying, We find no evil in this man: what if a spirit or an angel has spoken to him?
B044C023V010	44	23	10	And when there arose a great dissension, the commander, fearing lest Paul should be pulled in pieces by them, commanded the soldiers to go down, and to take him by force from among them, and bring him into the barracks.
B044C023V011	44	23	11	And the next night the Lord stood by him, and said, Take courage: for as you have testified of me in Jerusalem, so you must also bear witness in Rome.
B044C023V012	44	23	12	And when it was day, the Jews banded together, and bound themselves under a oath, saying that they would neither eat nor drink until they had killed Paul.
B044C023V013	44	23	13	And there were more than forty who made this conspiracy.
B044C023V014	44	23	14	And they came to the chief priests and elders, and said, We have bound ourselves under a great oath, that we will eat nothing until we have slain Paul.
B044C023V015	44	23	15	Now therefore, you and the council notify the commander to bring him down to you tomorrow, as though you would enquire more thoroughly concerning him: and we, before he ever comes near, are ready to kill him.
B044C023V016	44	23	16	And when Paul's sister's son heard of their lying in wait, he went and entered the barracks, and told Paul.
B044C023V017	44	23	17	Then Paul called one of the centurions to him, and said, Take this young man to the commander: for he has a certain thing to tell him.
B044C023V018	44	23	18	So he took him, and brought him to the commander, and said, Paul the prisoner called me and asked me to bring this young man to you, as he has something to say to you.
B044C023V019	44	23	19	Then the commander took him by the hand, and drew him aside privately, and asked, What is it that you have to tell me?
B044C023V020	44	23	20	And he said, The Jews have agreed to ask you to bring Paul down tomorrow to the council, as though they would enquire of him more thoroughly.
B044C023V021	44	23	21	But do not yield to them: for there lie in wait for him more than forty men, who have bound themselves with an oath, that they will neither eat nor drink until they have killed him: and now they are ready, waiting for a promise from you.
B044C023V022	44	23	22	So the commander let the young man depart, and charged him, Tell no man that you have revealed these things to me.
B044C023V023	44	23	23	And he called two centurions, saying, Make ready two hundred soldiers, seventy horsemen, and two hundred spearmen to go to Caesarea, at the third hour of the night;
B044C023V024	44	23	24	And provide mounts for Paul to ride, and bring him safely to Felix the governor.
B044C023V025	44	23	25	And he wrote a letter after this manner:
B044C023V026	44	23	26	Claudius Lysias to the most excellent governor Felix, greetings.
B044C023V027	44	23	27	This man was taken by the Jews, and would have been killed by them: then I came with the troops, and rescued him, having learned that he was a Roman.
B044C023V028	44	23	28	And when I wanted to learn the reason they accused him, I brought him down to their council:
B044C023V029	44	23	29	And I perceived that he was accused regarding questions of their law, but there was no charge against him worthy of death or imprisonment.
B044C023V030	44	23	30	And when I was told that there was a plot against the man, I immediately sent him to you, and also commanded his accusers to state before you whatever they have against him.
B044C023V031	44	23	31	Then the soldiers, as it was commanded, took Paul, and brought him by night to Antipatris.
B044C023V032	44	23	32	On the next day they left the horsemen to go with him, and returned to the barracks.
B044C023V033	44	23	33	When they came to Caesarea, and delivered the letter to the governor, they also presented Paul before him.
B044C023V034	44	23	34	And when he had read the letter, he asked what province he was from. And when he learned that he was from Cilicia;
B044C023V035	44	23	35	He said, I will hear you when your accusers have come. And he commanded him to be kept in Herod's palace.
B044C024V001	44	24	1	And after five days Ananias the high priest came down with some of the elders, and with a certain lawyer named Tertullus, who informed the governor of their charges against Paul.
B044C024V002	44	24	2	And when he was called, Tertullus began to accuse him, saying, Seeing that because of you we enjoy great quietness, and that very worthy reforms are done for this nation by your provision,
B044C024V003	44	24	3	We accept this always, and in all places, most noble Felix, with all thankfulness.
B044C024V004	44	24	4	But, that I may not be further tedious to you, I ask that by your clemency you would hear a few words from us.
B044C024V005	44	24	5	For we have found this man to be a pestilent fellow, and a agitator among all the Jews throughout the world, and a ringleader of the sect of the Nazarenes.
B044C024V006	44	24	6	He has also tried to profane the temple: but we seized him, [and would have judged him according to our law.
B044C024V007	44	24	7	But Lysias the commander came upon us, and with great violence took him out of our hands,
B044C024V008	44	24	8	Commanding his accusers to come to you.] By examining him yourself you will be able to learn the truth of all these things of which we accuse him.
B044C024V009	44	24	9	And the Jews agreed with the accusation, saying that these things were so.
B044C024V010	44	24	10	Then Paul, after the governor had beckoned for him to speak, answered: Because I know that you have been for many years a judge over this nation, I cheerfully make my defence.
B044C024V011	44	24	11	As you may ascertain, it has been no more than twelve days since I went up to Jerusalem to worship.
B044C024V012	44	24	12	And neither in the temple, or in the synagogues, or in the city did they find me disputing with any man, or stirring up the people:
B044C024V013	44	24	13	Nor can they prove the things of which they now accuse me.
B044C024V014	44	24	14	But this I confess to you, that according to the way which they call a sect, so I worship the God of my fathers, believing all things which are written in the law and the prophets,
B044C024V015	44	24	15	And have hope toward God, which they themselves also have, that there shall be a resurrection of the dead, both of the just and unjust.
B044C024V016	44	24	16	So I discipline myself, to always have a clear conscience before God and men.
B044C024V017	44	24	17	Now, after many years, I came to bring to my nation alms and offerings.
B044C024V018	44	24	18	I was purified when they found me doing this in the temple, without a crowd or a tumult. But certain Jews from Asia were there,
B044C024V019	44	24	19	Who ought to be here before you, and object, if they have anything against me.
B044C024V020	44	24	20	Or else let these men here say if they found any wrongdoing in me when I stood before the council,
B044C024V021	44	24	21	Unless it be for this one thing, that I cried out while standing among them, For the resurrection of the dead I am on trial before you this day.
B044C024V022	44	24	22	And Felix, having a more accurate knowledge of the way, put them off, saying, When Lysias the commander shall come down, I will decide your case.
B044C024V023	44	24	23	And he commanded a centurion to guard Paul, and to let him have some liberty, and that he should not prevent his friends from ministering to him.
B044C024V024	44	24	24	And after some days, when Felix came with his wife Drusilla, who was a Jewess, he sent for Paul, and heard him concerning faith in Christ Jesus.
B044C024V025	44	24	25	And as he reasoned with them about righteousness, self-control, and the judgment to come, Felix was frightened, and answered, Go your way for now; when I have a convenient opportunity, I will call for you.
B044C024V026	44	24	26	He also hoped that Paul would give him money: therefore he sent for him often, and conversed with him.
B044C024V027	44	24	27	But after two years Felix was succeeded by Porcius Festus: and Felix, wanting to do a favour for the Jews, left Paul imprisoned.
B044C025V001	44	25	1	Now three days after Festus had come into the province, he went up from Caesarea to Jerusalem.
B044C025V002	44	25	2	Then the high priest and the chief men of the Jews brought to him charges against Paul, and begged him,
B044C025V003	44	25	3	Asking as a favour, that he would have him brought to Jerusalem, for they were planning an ambush to kill him along the way.
B044C025V004	44	25	4	But Festus answered, that Paul was being kept at Caesarea, and that he himself would soon depart for there.
B044C025V005	44	25	5	Therefore, let the influential ones among you go down with me, and accuse this man, if there is any wickedness in him.
B044C025V006	44	25	6	And when he had remained among them more than ten days, he went down to Caesarea; and the next day, sitting on the judgment seat, commanded Paul to be brought.
B044C025V007	44	25	7	And when he had come, the Jews who came down from Jerusalem stood around, and brought many and grievous complaints against Paul, which they could not prove.
B044C025V008	44	25	8	Paul answered for himself, Neither against the law of the Jews, nor against the temple, nor against Caesar, have I offended in any way.
B044C025V009	44	25	9	But Festus, wanting to do the Jews a favour, answered Paul, Are you willing to go up to Jerusalem, and there be judged about these charges before me?
B044C025V010	44	25	10	Then Paul said, I stand at Caesar's judgment seat, where I ought to be judged: to the Jews I have done no wrong, as you very well know.
B044C025V011	44	25	11	If I am an offender, or have committed anything worthy of death, I do not refuse to die: but if there is no truth to the things of which these men accuse me, no man may deliver me to them. I appeal to Caesar.
B044C025V012	44	25	12	Then Festus, when he had conferred with the council, answered, You have appealed to Caesar; to Caesar you shall go.
B044C025V013	44	25	13	And after some days king Agrippa and Bernice came to Caesarea to greet Festus.
B044C025V014	44	25	14	And when they had been there many days, Festus declared Paul's case to the king, saying, There is a certain man left a prisoner by Felix:
B044C025V015	44	25	15	About whom, when I was in Jerusalem, the chief priests and the elders of the Jews informed me, asking for a judgment against him.
B044C025V016	44	25	16	I answered them, It is not the manner of the Romans to deliver any man to die, before he who is accused meets the accusers face to face, and has the opportunity to defend himself concerning the crime laid against him.
B044C025V017	44	25	17	Therefore, when they had come here, I made no delay, but on the next day sat on the judgment seat, and commanded the man to be brought forth.
B044C025V018	44	25	18	When the accusers stood up, they brought no accusation of such things as I supposed:
B044C025V019	44	25	19	But had certain disagreements with him about their own superstition, and about one Jesus, who was dead, but whom Paul claimed to be alive.
B044C025V020	44	25	20	And because I was at a loss how to investigate such questions, I asked him whether he would go to Jerusalem, and be judged there about these matters.
B044C025V021	44	25	21	But when Paul appealed to be held for a decision by the emperor, I commanded him to be kept until I might send him to Caesar.
B044C025V022	44	25	22	Then Agrippa said to Festus, I would like hear the man myself. Tomorrow, he said, you shall hear him.
B044C025V023	44	25	23	So on the next day, Agrippa and Bernice came, with great pomp, and entered into the place of hearing, with the chief captains, and principal men of the city. At Festus' command, Paul was brought forth.
B044C025V024	44	25	24	And Festus said, King Agrippa, and all men who are present with us, you see this man, about whom all the multitude of the Jews have petitioned me, both in Jerusalem, and also here, crying out that he ought no longer to live.
B044C025V025	44	25	25	But when I found that he had committed nothing worthy of death, and that he has appealed to the emperor, I have determined to send him.
B044C025V026	44	25	26	But I have nothing definite to write to my lord concerning him. Therefore I have brought him forth before you, and especially before you, O king Agrippa, that, after examination, I might have something to write.
B044C025V027	44	25	27	For it seems to me unreasonable to send a prisoner, and not to specify the crimes laid against him.
B044C026V001	44	26	1	Then Agrippa said to Paul, You are permitted to speak for yourself. Then Paul stretched forth his hand, and made his defence:
B044C026V002	44	26	2	I consider myself fortunate, king Agrippa, because I shall make my defence this day before you regarding all the things of which I am accused by the Jews:
B044C026V003	44	26	3	Especially because I know you to be an expert in all customs and controversies of the Jews: therefore I beg you to hear me patiently.
B044C026V004	44	26	4	The manner of my life from my youth, which was at first spent among my own nation and in Jerusalem, is known by all the Jews.
B044C026V005	44	26	5	They have known me for a long time, and, if they are willing to testify to it, that I lived as a Pharisee, according to the most strict sect of our religion.
B044C026V006	44	26	6	And now I stand and am judged for the hope of the promise made by God to our fathers:
B044C026V007	44	26	7	The promise which our twelve tribes, earnestly serving God day and night, hope to attain. For the sake of this hope, king Agrippa, I am accused by the Jews.
B044C026V008	44	26	8	Why should it be thought incredible to any of you, that God should raise the dead?
B044C026V009	44	26	9	I truly thought to myself, that I ought to do many things to oppose to the name of Jesus of Nazareth.
B044C026V010	44	26	10	And this I did in Jerusalem: and I had many of the saints shut up in prison, by authority of the chief priests; and when they were put to death, I cast my vote against them.
B044C026V011	44	26	11	And I punished them often in every synagogue, and tried to force them to blaspheme; and being furiously enraged against them, I persecuted them even in foreign cities.
B044C026V012	44	26	12	Thus engaged, I journeyed to Damascus with authority and commission from the chief priests.
B044C026V013	44	26	13	At midday, O king, I saw on the way a light from heaven, brighter than the sun, shining around me and those who traveled with me.
B044C026V014	44	26	14	And when we had all fallen to the earth, I heard a voice speaking to me, saying in the Hebrew tongue, Saul, Saul, why do you persecute me? it is hard for you to kick against the goads.
B044C026V015	44	26	15	And I said, Who are you, Lord? And he said, I am Jesus whom you are persecuting.
B044C026V016	44	26	16	But rise, and stand on your feet: for I have appeared to you for this purpose, to make you a minister and a witness both of these things which you have seen, and of those things in which I will appear to you.
B044C026V017	44	26	17	I will deliver you from the people, and from the Gentiles, to whom I now send you,
B044C026V018	44	26	18	To open their eyes, and to turn them from darkness to light, and from the power of Satan to God, that they may receive forgiveness of sins, and an inheritance along with those who are sanctified by faith in me.
B044C026V019	44	26	19	Wherefore, O king Agrippa, I was not disobedient to the heavenly vision:
B044C026V020	44	26	20	But declared first to those of Damascus, then at Jerusalem, and throughout all the regions of Judaea, and then to the Gentiles, that they should repent and turn to God, and perform deeds worthy of repentance.
B044C026V021	44	26	21	For these reasons the Jews caught me in the temple, and tried to kill me.
B044C026V022	44	26	22	Having obtained help from God, I continue to this day, witnessing both to small and great, saying nothing other than what the prophets and Moses said would come to pass:
B044C026V023	44	26	23	That Christ would suffer, and that he would be the first to rise from the dead, and would proclaim light to the people, and to the Gentiles.
B044C026V024	44	26	24	And as he spoke thus in his defence, Festus said with a loud voice, Paul, you are raving; your great learning is making you mad.
B044C026V025	44	26	25	But he said, I am not mad, most noble Festus; but speak forth words of truth and soberness.
B044C026V026	44	26	26	For the king knows of these things, and before him I speak freely: for I am persuaded that none of these things are hidden from him; for this was not done in a corner.
B044C026V027	44	26	27	King Agrippa, do you believe the prophets? I know that you believe.
B044C026V028	44	26	28	Then Agrippa said to Paul, In such a short time do you think you can persuade me to become a Christian?
B044C026V029	44	26	29	And Paul said, I would to God, that in a short or long time, not only you, but also all who hear me this day, might be as I am, except for these chains.
B044C026V030	44	26	30	The king rose up, and the governor, and Bernice, and those who sat with them:
B044C026V031	44	26	31	And when they had withdrawn, they talked among themselves, saying, This man has done nothing worthy of death or imprisonment.
B044C026V032	44	26	32	Then Agrippa said to Festus, This man might have been set at liberty, if he had not appealed to Caesar.
B044C027V001	44	27	1	And when it was determined that we should sail to Italy, they delivered Paul and certain other prisoners to one named Julius, a centurion of the Augustan cohort.
B044C027V002	44	27	2	And boarding a ship of Adramyttium, we put out to sea, meaning to sail to ports on the coast of Asia; and Aristarchus, a Macedonian from Thessalonica, was with us.
B044C027V003	44	27	3	The next day we put in at Sidon; and Julius treated Paul kindly, and gave him liberty to go to his friends, that they might care for him.
B044C027V004	44	27	4	And when we had put out to sea from there, we sailed under the lee of Cyprus, because the winds were contrary.
B044C027V005	44	27	5	And when we had sailed over the sea by the coast of Cilicia and Pamphylia, we came to Myra in Lycia.
B044C027V006	44	27	6	And there the centurion found a ship of Alexandria sailing to Italy; and he put us aboard.
B044C027V007	44	27	7	And when we had sailed slowly for many days, and with difficulty had arrived off Cnidus, the wind would not allow us to go on, so we sailed under the lee of Crete, off Salmone;
B044C027V008	44	27	8	And, with difficulty passing it, came to a place which is called The fair havens; near the city of Lasea.
B044C027V009	44	27	9	Much time had been spent, and the sailing was now dangerous, because the fast was already past, so Paul admonished them,
B044C027V010	44	27	10	And said to them, Sirs, I perceive that this voyage will be disastrous, with much damage, not only to the cargo and ship, but also to our lives.
B044C027V011	44	27	11	But the centurion believed the pilot and the owner of the ship, more than those things which were spoken by Paul.
B044C027V012	44	27	12	And because the haven was not suitable to winter in, the majority advised to put out to sea from there, in hopes of reaching Phoenix, a harbour of Crete, which faces toward the southwest and northwest, and wintering there.
B044C027V013	44	27	13	And when the south wind blew softly, supposing that they had obtained their purpose, they weighed anchor, and sailed close along the shore of Crete.
B044C027V014	44	27	14	But not long after there arose a tempestuous wind, called the northeaster.
B044C027V015	44	27	15	And when the ship was caught, and could not make headway into the wind, we let her be driven along.
B044C027V016	44	27	16	And running under the lee of a small island called Cauda, we had much work to secure the ship's boat.
B044C027V017	44	27	17	When they had taken it up, they used ropes to undergird the ship; and, fearing lest they should run into the sandbars of Syrtis, let down the sea anchor, and so were driven along.
B044C027V018	44	27	18	As we were exceedingly tossed by the tempest, the next day they threw the cargo overboard;
B044C027V019	44	27	19	And the third day they cast out the ship's tackle with their own hands.
B044C027V020	44	27	20	And when neither sun nor stars appeared in many days, and no small tempest lay upon us, all hope that we should be saved was abandoned.
B044C027V021	44	27	21	Then as they had been long without food, Paul stood forth in the midst of them, and said, Men, you should have listened to me, and not have set sail from Crete, and incurred this damage and loss.
B044C027V022	44	27	22	But now I encourage you to be of good cheer; for there shall be no loss of life among you, but only the ship will be lost.
B044C027V023	44	27	23	For this night there stood before me an angel of God, whose I am, and whom I serve,
B044C027V024	44	27	24	Saying, Do not fear, Paul; you must be brought before Caesar: and, lo, God has given you all those who sail with you.
B044C027V025	44	27	25	Therefore, men, be of good cheer: for I believe God, that it shall be exactly as I was told.
B044C027V026	44	27	26	Yet we must be cast upon a certain island.
B044C027V027	44	27	27	But when the fourteenth night had come, as we were driven about on the Sea of Adria, about midnight the sailors sensed that they were approaching land;
B044C027V028	44	27	28	And took soundings, and found the water was twenty fathoms: and when they had gone a little further, they sounded again, and found it was fifteen fathoms.
B044C027V029	44	27	29	Then fearing lest we should run upon the rocks, they cast four anchors out of the stern, and wished for the day.
B044C027V030	44	27	30	As the sailors were about to flee the ship, and had let down the ship's boat into the sea, pretending they would cast out anchors from the bow,
B044C027V031	44	27	31	Paul said to the centurion and to the soldiers, Unless these men stay in the ship, you cannot be saved.
B044C027V032	44	27	32	Then the soldiers cut off the ropes to the boat, and let her fall away.
B044C027V033	44	27	33	And when day was coming on, Paul begged them all to take food, saying, Today is the fourteenth day that you have continued in suspense and in fasting, having taken nothing.
B044C027V034	44	27	34	Therefore I urge you to take food; this is for your strength. Not a hair shall perish from the head of any of you.
B044C027V035	44	27	35	And when he had spoken thus, he took bread, and gave thanks to God in the presence of them all: and when he had broken it, he began to eat.
B044C027V036	44	27	36	Then they were all of good cheer, and they also took some food.
B044C027V037	44	27	37	In all, there were two hundred and seventy-six of us in the ship.
B044C027V038	44	27	38	And when they had eaten enough, they lightened the ship by casting the wheat into the sea.
B044C027V039	44	27	39	And when it was day, they did not recognize the land: but they saw a certain bay with a beach, onto which they intended, if it were possible, to drive the ship.
B044C027V040	44	27	40	So they cast off the anchors, and left them in the sea, and loosening the rudder ropes, they hoisted the foresail to the wind, and made for the beach.
B044C027V041	44	27	41	But striking a sandbar, they ran the ship aground; and the bow stuck fast, and remained immovable, and the stern was broken apart by the violence of the waves.
B044C027V042	44	27	42	And the soldiers planned to kill the prisoners, lest any of them should swim away, and escape.
B044C027V043	44	27	43	But the centurion, wanting to save Paul, kept them from their purpose; and commanded that those who could swim should cast themselves first into the sea, and get to land:
B044C027V044	44	27	44	Then the rest should follow, some on boards, and some on broken pieces of the ship. And so it came to pass, that they all escaped safely to land.
B044C028V001	44	28	1	And when they had escaped, then we learned that the island was called Malta.
B044C028V002	44	28	2	And the native people showed us unusual kindness: for they kindled a fire, and welcomed every one of us, because it had begun to rain and was cold.
B044C028V003	44	28	3	And when Paul had gathered a bundle of sticks, and laid them on the fire, a viper came out because of the heat, and fastened on his hand.
B044C028V004	44	28	4	And when the natives saw the creature hanging on his hand, they said to themselves, No doubt this man is a murderer, and though he has escaped the sea, yet justice does not allow him to live.
B044C028V005	44	28	5	And he shook off the creature into the fire, and suffered no harm.
B044C028V006	44	28	6	They expected he would have swollen up, or suddenly fallen down dead: but after they watched a great while, and saw no harm come to him, they changed their minds, and said that he was a god.
B044C028V007	44	28	7	In the same vicinity were estates owned by the chief man of the island, whose name was Publius; who welcomed us, and courteously entertained us for three days.
B044C028V008	44	28	8	And it came to pass, that the father of Publius lay sick, afflicted with a fever and dysentery: Paul went in to see him, and prayed, and laid his hands on him, and healed him.
B044C028V009	44	28	9	When this was done, the others on the island who had diseases, came, and were healed.
B044C028V010	44	28	10	And they honoured us with many honours; and when we departed, they put on board everything we needed.
B044C028V011	44	28	11	And after three months we departed in a ship of Alexandria, which had wintered in the isle, whose figurehead was Castor and Pollux.
B044C028V012	44	28	12	And landing at Syracuse, we remained there three days.
B044C028V013	44	28	13	And from there we circled around and came to Rhegium: and after one day the south wind blew, and we arrived the next day at Puteoli,
B044C028V014	44	28	14	Where we found brethren, and were asked to remain with them seven days: and so we went toward Rome.
B044C028V015	44	28	15	And when the brethren there heard of us, they came to meet us, as far as Appii forum and The three taverns: when Paul saw them, he thanked God, and took courage.
B044C028V016	44	28	16	And when we came to Rome, Paul was allowed to live by himself with a soldier who guarded him.
B044C028V017	44	28	17	And it came to pass, that after three days Paul called the chief men of the Jews together: and when they had come together, he said to them, Brethren, though I have done nothing against the people, or customs of our fathers, yet I was delivered as a prisoner from Jerusalem into the hands of the Romans.
B044C028V018	44	28	18	When they had examined me, they would have let me go, because there was no cause for putting me to death.
B044C028V019	44	28	19	But when the Jews spoke against it, I was forced to appeal to Caesar; not that I had any charge to bring against my own nation.
B044C028V020	44	28	20	Therefore, for this reason I have called for you, to see you, and to speak with you: because it is for the hope of Israel that I am bound with this chain.
B044C028V021	44	28	21	And they said to him, We neither received letters from Judaea concerning you, nor have any of the brethren who have come here reported or spoken any evil against you.
B044C028V022	44	28	22	But we desire to hear from you what your views are: for concerning this sect, we know that it is spoken against everywhere.
B044C028V023	44	28	23	And when they had appointed a day, many came to him in his lodging; to whom he explained and testified of the kingdom of God, trying to persuade them concerning Jesus, both out of the law of Moses, and out of the prophets, from morning until evening.
B044C028V024	44	28	24	And some believed the things which were spoken, and some did not believe.
B044C028V025	44	28	25	And when they could not agree among themselves, they departed, after Paul spoke one last statement, Well did the Holy Spirit speak by Isaiah the prophet to our fathers,
B044C028V026	44	28	26	Saying, Go to this people, and say, You shall keep hearing, and shall not understand; and keep seeing, but not perceive:
B044C028V027	44	28	27	For the heart of this people has grown calloused, and with their ears they barely hear, and they have closed their eyes; lest they should see with their eyes, and hear with their ears, and understand with their heart, and turn, that I should heal them.
B044C028V028	44	28	28	Therefore let it be known to you, that the salvation of God has been sent to the Gentiles, and they will hear it.
B044C028V029	44	28	29	[And when he had said these words, the Jews departed, and had a great dispute among themselves.]
B044C028V030	44	28	30	And he lived two years in his own rented house, and welcomed all who came to see him,
B044C028V031	44	28	31	Preaching the kingdom of God, and teaching those things which concern the Lord Jesus Christ, with all boldness, and no man hindered him.
B045C001V001	45	1	1	Paul, a servant of Jesus Christ, called to be an apostle, set apart for the gospel of God,
B045C001V002	45	1	2	(Which he promised beforehand by his prophets in the holy scriptures,)
B045C001V003	45	1	3	Concerning his Son, who was born a descendant of David according to the flesh;
B045C001V004	45	1	4	And through the Spirit of holiness was declared with power to be the Son of God by the resurrection from the dead: Jesus Christ our Lord,
B045C001V005	45	1	5	By whom we have received grace and apostleship, to bring about the obedience of faith among all the nations, for his name's sake;
B045C001V006	45	1	6	And you also are among those called to belong to Jesus Christ:
B045C001V007	45	1	7	To all who are in Rome, beloved of God, called to be saints: Grace to you and peace from God our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B045C001V008	45	1	8	First, I thank my God through Jesus Christ for you all, because your faith is spoken of throughout the whole world.
B045C001V009	45	1	9	For God is my witness, whom I serve with my spirit in the gospel of his Son, that without ceasing I make mention of you in my prayers;
B045C001V010	45	1	10	Making request, that by some means I might now at last, by the will of God, succeed in coming to you.
B045C001V011	45	1	11	For I long to see you, that I may impart to you some spiritual gift, so you may be established;
B045C001V012	45	1	12	That is, that we may together be comforted, each by the other's faith, both yours and mine.
B045C001V013	45	1	13	Now I would not have you be ignorant, brethren, that I often intended to come to you, (but was prevented until now,) that I might have some fruit among you also, even as among the other Gentiles.
B045C001V014	45	1	14	I am debtor both to the Greeks, and to the barbarians; both to the wise, and to the foolish.
B045C001V015	45	1	15	So, for my part, I am ready to preach the gospel to you who are in Rome also.
B045C001V016	45	1	16	For I am not ashamed of the gospel, for it is the power of God for salvation to everyone who believes; to the Jew first, and also to the Greek.
B045C001V017	45	1	17	For in it the righteousness of God is revealed from faith to faith: as it is written, The just shall live by faith.
B045C001V018	45	1	18	For the wrath of God is revealed from heaven against all the ungodliness and wickedness of men who suppress the truth by unrighteousness;
B045C001V019	45	1	19	Because that which may be known about God is evident to them; for God has shown it to them.
B045C001V020	45	1	20	For since the creation of the world his invisible nature, his eternal power and deity, has been clearly seen, being understood by the things that have been made; so that they are without excuse:
B045C001V021	45	1	21	Because, though they knew God, they did not glorify him as God, nor were they thankful; but they became futile in their speculations, and their foolish hearts were darkened.
B045C001V022	45	1	22	Professing themselves to be wise, they became fools,
B045C001V023	45	1	23	And exchanged the glory of the immortal God for images resembling corruptible man, and birds, and four-footed beasts, and creeping things.
B045C001V024	45	1	24	Therefore God gave them up, through the lusts of their own hearts, to sexual impurity, to dishonour their own bodies among themselves:
B045C001V025	45	1	25	Because they exchanged the truth of God for a lie, and worshipped and served the creature rather than the Creator, who is blessed forever. Amen.
B045C001V026	45	1	26	For this cause God gave them up to vile affections: for even their women exchanged natural relations for that which is against nature:
B045C001V027	45	1	27	And likewise the men, leaving their natural relations with woman, burned in their lust toward one another; men with men doing that which is unseemly, and receiving in themselves the due penalty for their error.
B045C001V028	45	1	28	And as they did not see fit to acknowledge God, God gave them over to a depraved mind, to do those things which are not proper.
B045C001V029	45	1	29	They were filled with all unrighteousness, wickedness, covetousness, malice; full of envy, murder, strife, deceit, malevolence; whisperers,
B045C001V030	45	1	30	Slanderers, haters of God, insolent, arrogant, boasters, inventors of evil things, disobedient to parents,
B045C001V031	45	1	31	Without understanding, untrustworthy, without natural affection, unmerciful:
B045C001V032	45	1	32	Who knowing the just decree of God, that those who commit such things are worthy of death, not only do these things, but applaud those who practice them.
B045C002V001	45	2	1	Therefore you are without excuse, O man, whoever you are, when you pass judgement: for when you pass judgement on another, you condemn yourself; for you who pass judgement do the same things.
B045C002V002	45	2	2	But we are sure that the judgment of God rightly falls upon those who do such things.
B045C002V003	45	2	3	And do you think, O man, that when you pass judgement on those who do such things, yet do the same yourself, that you shall escape the judgment of God?
B045C002V004	45	2	4	Or do you despise the riches of his kindness and forbearance and patience; not knowing that the kindness of God leads you to repentance?
B045C002V005	45	2	5	But because of your hard and unrepentant heart you are storing up for yourself wrath on the day of wrath when the righteous judgment of God shall be revealed;
B045C002V006	45	2	6	Who will render to every man according to his deeds:
B045C002V007	45	2	7	To those who by patience in well doing seek for glory and honour and immortality, eternal life:
B045C002V008	45	2	8	But to those who are contentious, and do not obey the truth, but obey unrighteousness, indignation and wrath.
B045C002V009	45	2	9	There shall be tribulation and anguish upon every soul of man who does evil, first for the Jew, and also for the Greek;
B045C002V010	45	2	10	But glory, honour, and peace for every man who does good works, for the Jew first, and also for the Greek:
B045C002V011	45	2	11	For there is no partiality with God.
B045C002V012	45	2	12	For as many as have sinned without the law shall also perish without the law: and as many as have sinned under the law shall be judged by the law;
B045C002V013	45	2	13	(For it is not the hearers of the law who are justified before God, but it is the doers of the law who shall be justified.
B045C002V014	45	2	14	For when the Gentiles, who do not have the law, do by nature the things contained in the law, these, though not having the law, are a law to themselves.
B045C002V015	45	2	15	They show the work of the law written in their hearts, their conscience also bearing witness, and their thoughts either accusing or perhaps defending them.)
B045C002V016	45	2	16	On that day God shall judge the secrets of men through Jesus Christ, as my gospel proclaims.
B045C002V017	45	2	17	Behold, if you call yourself a Jew, and rely upon the law, and boast of your relationship with God,
B045C002V018	45	2	18	And know his will, and approve the things that are excellent, being instructed out of the law;
B045C002V019	45	2	19	And are confident that you yourself are a guide to the blind, a light for those who are in darkness,
B045C002V020	45	2	20	An instructor for the foolish, a teacher of infants, having the embodiment of knowledge and truth in the law:
B045C002V021	45	2	21	You, therefore, who teach others, do you not teach yourself? you who preach that a man should not steal, do you steal?
B045C002V022	45	2	22	You who say a man should not commit adultery, do you commit adultery? you who abhor idols, do you rob temples?
B045C002V023	45	2	23	You who make your boast in the law, do you dishonour God by breaking the law?
B045C002V024	45	2	24	For as it is written, The name of God is blasphemed among the Gentiles because of you.
B045C002V025	45	2	25	For circumcision is truly of value, if you keep the law: but if you are a breaker of the law, your circumcision has becomes uncircumcision.
B045C002V026	45	2	26	Therefore, if the uncircumcised keeps the requirements of the law, shall not his uncircumcision be counted as circumcision?
B045C002V027	45	2	27	And shall not the physically uncircumcised, if he keeps the law, judge you, who, though you have the letter of the law and circumcision, are transgressors of the law?
B045C002V028	45	2	28	For he is not a Jew, who is one outwardly; neither is circumcision that which is outward in the flesh:
B045C002V029	45	2	29	But he is a Jew, who is one inwardly; and circumcision is of the heart, by the spirit, and not by the letter; and his praise is not from men, but from God.
B045C003V001	45	3	1	Then what advantage has the Jew? or what profit is there in circumcision?
B045C003V002	45	3	2	Much in every way: First, because the oracles of God were entrusted to them.
B045C003V003	45	3	3	What if some did not believe? shall their unbelief nullify the faithfulness of God?
B045C003V004	45	3	4	God forbid: let God be true, even if every man is a liar; as it is written, That you might be justified in your words, and might overcome when you are judged.
B045C003V005	45	3	5	But if our unrighteousness demonstrates the righteousness of God, what shall we say? That God is unrighteous who takes vengeance? (I speak as a man)
B045C003V006	45	3	6	God forbid: for then how shall God judge the world?
B045C003V007	45	3	7	But if, through my lie, the truthfulness of God brings him even greater glory; why am I still condemned as a sinner?
B045C003V008	45	3	8	And why not say, (as we are slanderously reported as saying, and as some affirm that we say,) Let us do evil, that good may come? Their condemnation is just.
B045C003V009	45	3	9	What then? are we better than they? No, by no means: for we have already charged that both Jews and Greeks are all under sin;
B045C003V010	45	3	10	As it is written, There is no one righteous, no, not one:
B045C003V011	45	3	11	There is no one who understands, there is no one who seeks after God.
B045C003V012	45	3	12	They have all left the way, together they have become unprofitable; there is no one who does good, no, not one.
B045C003V013	45	3	13	Their throats are an open grave; with their tongues they have used deceit; the poison of asps is under their lips:
B045C003V014	45	3	14	Their mouth is full of cursing and bitterness:
B045C003V015	45	3	15	Their feet are swift to shed blood:
B045C003V016	45	3	16	Destruction and misery are in their ways:
B045C003V017	45	3	17	And the way of peace have they not known:
B045C003V018	45	3	18	There is no fear of God before their eyes.
B045C003V019	45	3	19	Now we know that whatever the law says, it says to those who are under the law: that every mouth may be stopped, and all the world may be held accountable to God.
B045C003V020	45	3	20	Therefore, by the works of the law no flesh shall be justified in his sight: for through the law comes the knowledge of sin.
B045C003V021	45	3	21	But now the righteousness of God apart from the law has been manifested, though it is witnessed to by the law and the prophets;
B045C003V022	45	3	22	This is the righteousness of God which is by faith in Jesus Christ for all who believe: for there is no difference:
B045C003V023	45	3	23	For all have sinned, and fall short of the glory of God;
B045C003V024	45	3	24	Being justified freely by his grace through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus:
B045C003V025	45	3	25	Whom God has set forth to be an atoning sacrifice through faith in his blood. He did this to declare his righteousness, for in the forbearance of God, he passed over sins of the past;
B045C003V026	45	3	26	To declare at this present time his righteousness: that he might be just, and the justifier of the one who has faith in Jesus.
B045C003V027	45	3	27	Where then is boasting? It is excluded. By what law? of works? No: but by the law of faith.
B045C003V028	45	3	28	Therefore we conclude that a man is justified by faith apart from the law.
B045C003V029	45	3	29	Is he the God of the Jews only? is he not also the God of the Gentiles? Yes, of the Gentiles also:
B045C003V030	45	3	30	Since God is one, and he shall justify the circumcised by faith, and the uncircumcised through faith.
B045C003V031	45	3	31	Do we then make the law void through faith? Not at all: rather, we establish the law.
B045C004V001	45	4	1	What then shall we say that Abraham, our forefather according to the flesh, has found?
B045C004V002	45	4	2	For if Abraham was justified by works, he has something of which to boast; but not before God.
B045C004V003	45	4	3	For what does the scripture say? Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness.
B045C004V004	45	4	4	Now to the one who works, his reward is not counted as a gift, but as his due.
B045C004V005	45	4	5	But to the one who does not work, but believes in him who justifies the ungodly, his faith is counted as righteousness.
B045C004V006	45	4	6	Thus David speaks of the blessedness of the man to whom God credits righteousness apart from works:
B045C004V007	45	4	7	Blessed are those whose iniquities are forgiven, and whose sins are covered.
B045C004V008	45	4	8	Blessed is the man whose sin the Lord will not count against him.
B045C004V009	45	4	9	Is this blessedness upon the circumcised only, or upon the uncircumcised as well? for we say that faith was credited to Abraham as righteousness.
B045C004V010	45	4	10	How then was it credited? when he was circumcised, or uncircumcised? It was not while circumcised, but while uncircumcised.
B045C004V011	45	4	11	And he received the sign of circumcision, a seal of the righteousness which he had by faith while uncircumcised: that he might be the father of all those who believe without being circumcised; that righteousness might be credited to them as well:
B045C004V012	45	4	12	And the father of the circumcised who are not merely circumcised, but who also walk in the steps of the faith that our father Abraham had while he was yet uncircumcised.
B045C004V013	45	4	13	For the promise, that he should be the heir of the world, was not given to Abraham, or to his descendants, through the law, but through the righteousness of faith.
B045C004V014	45	4	14	For if those who are of the law are heirs, then faith is made void, and the promise is made invalid:
B045C004V015	45	4	15	Because the law brings wrath: but where there is no law, there is no transgression.
B045C004V016	45	4	16	Therefore it is by faith, that it might be by grace; so that the promise might be certain to all his descendants; not only to those who are of the law, but also to those who are of the faith of Abraham; who is the father of us all,
B045C004V017	45	4	17	(As it is written, I have made you a father of many nations,) before him in whom he believed, even God, who gives life to the dead, and calls into being those things which are not.
B045C004V018	45	4	18	Against all hope he believed, that he might become the father of many nations, according to that which was spoken, So shall your descendants be.
B045C004V019	45	4	19	And he did not weaken in faith when he considered his own body, now as good as dead, for he was about a hundred years old, or the deadness of Sarah's womb:
B045C004V020	45	4	20	He did not waver through unbelief in the promise of God; but was strong in faith, giving glory to God;
B045C004V021	45	4	21	And was fully persuaded that, what he had promised, he was able also to perform.
B045C004V022	45	4	22	And therefore it was credited to him as righteousness.
B045C004V023	45	4	23	Now it was not for him alone that these words were written, It was credited to him;
B045C004V024	45	4	24	But also for us. It shall be credited to those of us who believe in him who raised Jesus our Lord from the dead.
B045C004V025	45	4	25	He was delivered to death for our offences, and was raised again for our justification.
B045C005V001	45	5	1	Therefore, being justified by faith, we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus Christ:
B045C005V002	45	5	2	By whom we also have access by faith into this grace in which we stand, and we rejoice in the hope of the glory of God.
B045C005V003	45	5	3	And not only this, but we also rejoice in tribulations: knowing that tribulation works perseverance;
B045C005V004	45	5	4	And perseverance, character; and character, hope:
B045C005V005	45	5	5	And hope does not disappoint; because the love of God has been poured into our hearts by the Holy Spirit who has been given to us.
B045C005V006	45	5	6	For when we were still without strength, at the right time Christ died for the ungodly.
B045C005V007	45	5	7	For one will hardly die for a righteous man: though perhaps for a good man someone would even dare to die.
B045C005V008	45	5	8	But God shows his love toward us, in that while we were yet sinners, Christ died for us.
B045C005V009	45	5	9	Having been justified by his blood, how much more shall we be saved from the wrath of God through him.
B045C005V010	45	5	10	For if, when we were enemies, we were reconciled to God by the death of his Son, how much more, having being reconciled, shall we shall be saved by his life.
B045C005V011	45	5	11	And not only this, but we also rejoice in God through our Lord Jesus Christ, by whom we have now received reconciliation.
B045C005V012	45	5	12	Therefore, since through one man sin entered into the world, and death by sin; so death spread to all men, for all have sinned:
B045C005V013	45	5	13	For though sin was in the world before the law: sin is not taken into account when there is no law.
B045C005V014	45	5	14	Nevertheless death reigned from Adam to Moses, even over those who had not sinned in the same way as Adam, who is the pattern of him who was to come.
B045C005V015	45	5	15	But the free gift is not like the offence. For if through the offence of the one many died, how much more did the grace of God, and the gift that came by the grace of the one man, Jesus Christ, overflow to many.
B045C005V016	45	5	16	And the effect of the gift is not like the effect of the one who sinned, judgment following one trespass and resulting in condemnation; but the free gift came following many offences and resulted in justification.
B045C005V017	45	5	17	For if by one man's offence death reigned through that one; much more shall those who receive abundance of grace and the gift of righteousness reign in life through the one, Jesus Christ.
B045C005V018	45	5	18	Therefore, as the offence of one brought judgment upon all men, resulting in condemnation; even so by the righteousness of one came justification that brings life for all men.
B045C005V019	45	5	19	For just as by one man's disobedience many were made sinners, so by the obedience of one shall many be made righteous.
B045C005V020	45	5	20	The law entered, that offences might increase. But where sin increased, grace increased all the more:
B045C005V021	45	5	21	So that as sin has reigned in death, even so might grace reign through righteousness to bring eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.
B045C006V001	45	6	1	What shall we say then? Shall we continue in sin, that grace may abound?
B045C006V002	45	6	2	By no means. How shall we, who are dead to sin, live in it any longer?
B045C006V003	45	6	3	Do you not know, that all of us who were baptized into Christ Jesus were baptized into his death?
B045C006V004	45	6	4	Therefore, we were buried with him by baptism into death: so that as Christ was raised up from the dead by the glory of the Father, even so we also might walk in newness of life.
B045C006V005	45	6	5	For if we have been united with him by sharing a death like his, so shall we also share a resurrection like his:
B045C006V006	45	6	6	Knowing this, that our old man has been crucified with him, that the body of sin might be destroyed, that henceforth we should no longer be enslaved by sin.
B045C006V007	45	6	7	For he who has died is freed from sin.
B045C006V008	45	6	8	Now if we have died with Christ, we believe that we shall also live with him:
B045C006V009	45	6	9	Knowing that Christ, having been raised from the dead, will never die again: death no longer has power over him.
B045C006V010	45	6	10	For in his death, he died to sin once for all: but in his life, he lives to God.
B045C006V011	45	6	11	In the same way, consider yourselves also to be dead to sin, but alive to God in Christ Jesus.
B045C006V012	45	6	12	Therefore, do not let sin reign in your mortal bodies, to make you obey its lusts.
B045C006V013	45	6	13	Do not yield your members to sin as instruments of unrighteousness: but yield yourselves to God, as those who are alive from the dead, and your members as instruments of righteousness to God.
B045C006V014	45	6	14	For sin shall not be your master: for you are not under the law, but under grace.
B045C006V015	45	6	15	What then? shall we sin, because we are not under the law, but under grace? By no means.
B045C006V016	45	6	16	Do you not know that if you yield yourselves as slaves to obey someone, you are slaves of the one you obey; whether of sin, which leads to death, or of obedience, which leads to righteousness?
B045C006V017	45	6	17	But thanks be to God, that you who were once the slaves of sin, have obeyed from the heart that standard of teaching which was entrusted to you.
B045C006V018	45	6	18	Being then set free from sin, you became the slaves of righteousness.
B045C006V019	45	6	19	I speak after the manner of men, because of the infirmity of your flesh: for as you have yielded your members as slaves to uncleanness and to ever increasing iniquity; so now yield your members as slaves to righteousness, leading to holiness.
B045C006V020	45	6	20	For when you were the slaves of sin, you were free from the control of righteousness.
B045C006V021	45	6	21	But what benefit did you get from those things of which you are now ashamed? for the result of those things is death.
B045C006V022	45	6	22	But now, having been set free from sin, and having become slaves of God, you gain the benefit that leads to holiness, and the result is eternal life.
B045C006V023	45	6	23	For the wages of sin is death; but the gift of God is eternal life through Christ Jesus our Lord.
B045C007V001	45	7	1	Do you not know, brethren, (for I speak to those who know the law,) that the law has jurisdiction over a person only as long as he lives?
B045C007V002	45	7	2	For the woman who has a husband is bound by the law to her husband as long as he lives; but if the husband dies, she is released from the law concerning her husband.
B045C007V003	45	7	3	So then, if she marries another man while her husband lives, she shall be called an adulteress: but if her husband dies, she is free from that law; so that she is not an adulteress, though she marries another man.
B045C007V004	45	7	4	Likewise, my brethren, you have died to the law through the body of Christ; so that you might belong to another, to him who was raised from the dead that we might bring forth fruit for God.
B045C007V005	45	7	5	For when we were in the flesh, the passions of sin, which were aroused by the law, were at work in our members to bring forth fruit for death.
B045C007V006	45	7	6	But now we have been released from the law, dead to that which held us bound; so that we serve in newness of spirit, and not in the oldness of the letter.
B045C007V007	45	7	7	What shall we say then? Is the law sin? By no means. On the contrary, I would not have known sin, but by the law: for I would not have known about coveting unless the law had said, You shall not covet.
B045C007V008	45	7	8	But sin, taking opportunity through the commandment, produced in me all kinds of covetousness. For without the law sin is dead.
B045C007V009	45	7	9	For I was once alive without the law: but when the commandment came, sin became alive, and I died.
B045C007V010	45	7	10	And the commandment, which was intended to bring life, I found to bring death.
B045C007V011	45	7	11	For sin, taking opportunity through the commandment, deceived me, and by it killed me.
B045C007V012	45	7	12	Therefore the law is holy, and the commandment is holy, and just, and good.
B045C007V013	45	7	13	Then did that which is good bring death to me? By no means. But sin, that it might appear to be sin, worked death in me by that which is good; that through the commandment sin might become exceedingly sinful.
B045C007V014	45	7	14	For we know that the law is spiritual: but I am carnal, sold into bondage to sin.
B045C007V015	45	7	15	I do not understand that which I do: for I do not do what I want to do; but what I hate is the very thing I do.
B045C007V016	45	7	16	But if I do that which I do not want to do, I agree that the law is good.
B045C007V017	45	7	17	Now then it is no longer I who does it, but sin which dwells in me.
B045C007V018	45	7	18	For I know that in myself (that is, in my flesh,) no good thing dwells: for to desire what is right is present within me; but to perform what is right, this I cannot do.
B045C007V019	45	7	19	For I do not do the good that I want: but the evil which I do not want, that is what I do.
B045C007V020	45	7	20	Now if I do what I do not want, it is no longer I who do it, but sin which dwells in me.
B045C007V021	45	7	21	So I find this law at work, that when I want to do good, evil is present with me.
B045C007V022	45	7	22	For I delight in the law of God in my inner man:
B045C007V023	45	7	23	But I see another law in the members of my body, warring against the law of my mind, and bringing me into captivity to the law of sin which is in my members.
B045C007V024	45	7	24	O wretched man that I am! who shall deliver me from this body of death?
B045C007V025	45	7	25	Thanks be to God through Jesus Christ our Lord. So then, with my mind I myself serve the law of God; but with my flesh the law of sin.
B045C008V001	45	8	1	Therefore, there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus.
B045C008V002	45	8	2	For the law of the Spirit of life in Christ Jesus has made me free from the law of sin and death.
B045C008V003	45	8	3	For what the law could not do, in that it was weak through the flesh, God did, sending his own Son in the likeness of sinful flesh, as an offering for sin; condemning sin in the flesh:
B045C008V004	45	8	4	That the righteousness of the law might be fulfilled in us, who do not walk in the ways of the flesh, but in the ways of the Spirit.
B045C008V005	45	8	5	For those who live according to the flesh set their minds on the things of the flesh; but those who live according to the Spirit set their minds on the things of the Spirit.
B045C008V006	45	8	6	Now the mind set on the flesh is death; but the mind set on the spirit is life and peace.
B045C008V007	45	8	7	Because the mind set on the flesh is hostile to God: for it is not subject to the law of God, indeed it cannot be.
B045C008V008	45	8	8	So then those who are in the flesh cannot please God.
B045C008V009	45	8	9	But you are not in the flesh, but in the Spirit, if the Spirit of God lives in you. Now if any man does not have the Spirit of Christ, he does not belong to him.
B045C008V010	45	8	10	And if Christ is in you, the body is dead because of sin; but the Spirit is alive because of righteousness.
B045C008V011	45	8	11	And if the Spirit of him who raised Jesus from the dead lives in you, he who raised Christ Jesus from the dead shall also give life to your mortal bodies by his Spirit who dwells in you.
B045C008V012	45	8	12	Therefore, brethren, we are debtors, but not to the flesh, to live according to the flesh.
B045C008V013	45	8	13	For if you live according to the flesh, you shall die: but if through the Spirit you put to death the deeds of the body, you shall live.
B045C008V014	45	8	14	For as many as are led by the Spirit of God are the sons of God.
B045C008V015	45	8	15	For you have not received a spirit of bondage leading to fear; but you have received the Spirit of adoption, by which we cry out, Abba, Father.
B045C008V016	45	8	16	The Spirit himself bears witness with our spirit, that we are the children of God:
B045C008V017	45	8	17	And if children, then heirs; heirs of God, and joint-heirs with Christ; if indeed we suffer with him that we may also be glorified with him.
B045C008V018	45	8	18	For I consider that the sufferings of this present time are not worthy to be compared with the glory which shall be revealed to us.
B045C008V019	45	8	19	For the creation waits in earnest expectation for the revealing of the sons of God.
B045C008V020	45	8	20	For the creation was made subject to futility, not of its own will, but by the will of him who subjected it, in hope,
B045C008V021	45	8	21	That the creation itself shall also be delivered from its bondage to corruption into the glorious liberty of the children of God.
B045C008V022	45	8	22	For we know that the whole creation groans in the pains of childbirth until now.
B045C008V023	45	8	23	And not only the creation, but ourselves as well, who have the first-fruits of the Spirit, even we groan within ourselves, waiting for our adoption as sons, the redemption of our bodies.
B045C008V024	45	8	24	For we are saved by this hope: but hope that is seen is not hope: for what man hopes for what he sees?
B045C008V025	45	8	25	But if we hope for what we do not see, then we wait for it with patience.
B045C008V026	45	8	26	Likewise the Spirit helps us in our weakness: for we do not know how to pray as we ought: but the Spirit himself intercedes for us with groanings too deep for words.
B045C008V027	45	8	27	And he who searches our hearts knows the mind of the Spirit, because he intercedes for the saints according to the will of God.
B045C008V028	45	8	28	And we know that all things work together for good to those who love God, to those who are the called according to his purpose.
B045C008V029	45	8	29	For whom he foreknew, he also predestined to be conformed to the image of his Son, that he might be the firstborn among many brethren.
B045C008V030	45	8	30	And whom he predestined, those he also called: and whom he called, those he also justified: and whom he justified, those he also glorified.
B045C008V031	45	8	31	What then shall we say about these things? If God is for us, who can be against us?
B045C008V032	45	8	32	He who did not spare his own Son, but delivered him up for us all, how shall he not also, with him, freely give us all things?
B045C008V033	45	8	33	Who shall bring any charge against God's elect? It is God who justifies.
B045C008V034	45	8	34	Who is there to condemn? It is Christ who died, yes, and more than that, who was raised again, who is at the right hand of God, and who also intercedes for us.
B045C008V035	45	8	35	Who shall separate us from the love of Christ? shall tribulation, or distress, or persecution, or famine, or nakedness, or peril, or sword?
B045C008V036	45	8	36	As it is written, For your sake we are killed all the day long; we are regarded as sheep for the slaughter.
B045C008V037	45	8	37	No, in all these things we are more than conquerors through him who loved us.
B045C008V038	45	8	38	For I am persuaded, that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor principalities, nor things present, nor things to come, nor powers,
B045C008V039	45	8	39	Nor height, nor depth, nor anything else in all creation, shall be able to separate us from the love of God, which is in Christ Jesus our Lord.
B045C009V001	45	9	1	I speak the truth in Christ, I am not lying, my conscience also bearing me witness in the Holy Spirit,
B045C009V002	45	9	2	That I have great heaviness and continual sorrow in my heart.
B045C009V003	45	9	3	For I could wish that I myself were accursed, cut off from Christ, for the sake of my brethren, my kinsmen according to the flesh:
B045C009V004	45	9	4	They are the Israelites; to whom belongs the adoption as sons, and the glory, and the covenants, and the giving of the law, and the temple worship, and the promises;
B045C009V005	45	9	5	To them belong the fathers, and from them, according to the flesh, came Christ, who is over all, God blessed forever. Amen.
B045C009V006	45	9	6	But it is not as though the word of God has had no effect. For they are not all Israel, who are descended from Israel:
B045C009V007	45	9	7	Nor are they all the children of Abraham because they are descended from him: but, Through Isaac shall your descendants be named.
B045C009V008	45	9	8	That is, It is not those who are the children of the flesh who are the children of God: but the children of the promise are counted as descendants.
B045C009V009	45	9	9	For this is the word of the promise, At this time I will come, and Sarah shall have a son.
B045C009V010	45	9	10	And not only this; but also when Rebekah had conceived children by one man, our father Isaac;
B045C009V011	45	9	11	(Though they were not yet born, and had done nothing good or evil, in order that the purpose of God according to his choice might stand, not because of works, but because of him who calls;)
B045C009V012	45	9	12	It was said to her, The elder shall serve the younger.
B045C009V013	45	9	13	As it is written, Jacob I have loved, but Esau I have hated.
B045C009V014	45	9	14	What shall we say then? Is there unrighteousness with God? Not at all.
B045C009V015	45	9	15	For he says to Moses, I will have mercy on whom I will have mercy, and I will have compassion on whom I will have compassion.
B045C009V016	45	9	16	So then it does not depend on him who wills or runs, but on God who shows mercy.
B045C009V017	45	9	17	For the scripture says to Pharaoh, For this very purpose I have raised you up, that I might show my power in you, and that my name might be declared throughout all the earth.
B045C009V018	45	9	18	Therefore, he has mercy on whom he will have mercy, and he hardens whomever he wills.
B045C009V019	45	9	19	You will say to me, Why then does he still find fault? For who can resist his will?
B045C009V020	45	9	20	But who are you, O man, to answer back to God? Shall the thing formed say to the one who formed it, Why have you made me this way?
B045C009V021	45	9	21	Does not the potter have the right to make from the same lump of clay one vessel for noble use, and another for common use?
B045C009V022	45	9	22	What if God, desiring to show his wrath, and to make his power known, endured with great patience the vessels of wrath made for destruction:
B045C009V023	45	9	23	That he might make known the riches of his glory to the vessels of mercy, which he had prepared beforehand for glory,
B045C009V024	45	9	24	Even us, whom he has called, not only from among the Jews, but also from among the Gentiles?
B045C009V025	45	9	25	As he says also in Hosea, I will call them my people, who were not my people; and call her beloved, who was not beloved.
B045C009V026	45	9	26	And it shall come to pass, that in the place where it was said to them, You are not my people; there they shall be called the sons of the living God.
B045C009V027	45	9	27	Isaiah also cries out concerning Israel, Though the number of the sons of Israel be as the sand of the sea, only a remnant shall be saved:
B045C009V028	45	9	28	For the Lord will execute his sentence upon the earth with speed and finality.
B045C009V029	45	9	29	And as Isaiah said beforehand, Unless the Lord of hosts had left us descendants, we would have become as Sodom, and been made like Gomorrah.
B045C009V030	45	9	30	What shall we say then? That the Gentiles, who did not follow after righteousness, have attained righteousness, the righteousness which is by faith;
B045C009V031	45	9	31	But Israel, which followed after the law of righteousness, has not fulfilled that law.
B045C009V032	45	9	32	Why? Because they did not seek it by faith, but as if it were based on works. They have stumbled over the stumbling stone;
B045C009V033	45	9	33	As it is written, Behold, I lay in Zion a stumbling stone, a rock that will make them fall: but whoever believes in him shall never be put to shame.
B045C010V001	45	10	1	Brethren, my heart's desire and prayer to God for them is that they might be saved.
B045C010V002	45	10	2	For I bear them witness that they have a zeal for God, but not according to knowledge.
B045C010V003	45	10	3	For being ignorant of God's righteousness, and seeking to establish their own, they have not submitted themselves to the righteousness of God.
B045C010V004	45	10	4	For Christ is the end of the law, so that there may be righteousness for every one who believes.
B045C010V005	45	10	5	Moses describes the righteousness which is of the law, The man who practices these things shall live by them.
B045C010V006	45	10	6	But the righteousness which is by faith speaks in this way, Do not say in your heart, Who shall ascend into heaven? (that is, to bring Christ down from above:)
B045C010V007	45	10	7	Or, Who shall descend into the deep? (that is, to bring Christ up from the dead.)
B045C010V008	45	10	8	But what does it say? The word is near you, even in your mouth, and in your heart: that is, the word of faith, which we preach:
B045C010V009	45	10	9	That if you shall confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord, and shall believe in your heart that God has raised him from the dead, you shall be saved.
B045C010V010	45	10	10	For with the heart man believes and is made righteous; and with the mouth confesses and is saved.
B045C010V011	45	10	11	For the scripture says, Whoever believes in him shall not be put to shame.
B045C010V012	45	10	12	For there is no difference between the Jew and the Greek: for the same Lord is Lord over all, bestowing his riches on all who call upon him.
B045C010V013	45	10	13	For whoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.
B045C010V014	45	10	14	But how shall they call upon him in whom they have not believed? and how shall they believe in him of whom they have not heard? and how shall they hear without a preacher?
B045C010V015	45	10	15	And how shall they preach, unless they are sent? as it is written, How beautiful are the feet of those who bring glad tidings of good things!
B045C010V016	45	10	16	But they have not all obeyed the gospel. For Isaiah says, Lord, who has believed our report?
B045C010V017	45	10	17	So faith comes by hearing, and hearing by the word of Christ.
B045C010V018	45	10	18	But I say, Have they not heard? Yes truly, for: Their voice went into all the earth, and their words to the ends of the world.
B045C010V019	45	10	19	But I say, Did Israel not know? First Moses says, I will provoke you to jealousy by those who are not a nation, by a foolish nation I will anger you.
B045C010V020	45	10	20	And Isaiah is very bold, saying, I was found by those who did not seek me; I revealed myself to those who did not ask for me.
B045C010V021	45	10	21	But to Israel he says, All day long I have stretched forth my hands to a disobedient and obstinate people.
B045C011V001	45	11	1	I say then, Has God cast away his people? By no means. For I also am an Israelite, a descendant of Abraham, of the tribe of Benjamin.
B045C011V002	45	11	2	God has not cast away his people whom he foreknew. Do you not know what the scripture says of Elijah? how he appealed to God against Israel, saying,
B045C011V003	45	11	3	Lord, they have killed your prophets, and pulled down your altars; and I alone am left, and they seek my life.
B045C011V004	45	11	4	But what is the answer God gives to him? I have kept for myself seven thousand men, who have not bowed the knee to Baal.
B045C011V005	45	11	5	Even so, at this present time, there is a remnant, chosen by grace.
B045C011V006	45	11	6	And if by grace, then it is no longer by works: otherwise grace is no longer grace.
B045C011V007	45	11	7	What then? Israel has not obtained that which it sought; but the elect have obtained it, and the rest were blinded.
B045C011V008	45	11	8	As it is written, God has given them the spirit of stupor, eyes that should not see, and ears that should not hear; down to this day.
B045C011V009	45	11	9	And David says, Let their table be made a snare, and a trap, and a stumbling block, and a retribution to them:
B045C011V010	45	11	10	Let their eyes be darkened, that they may not see, and bow down their backs forever.
B045C011V011	45	11	11	I say then, Have they stumbled to fall beyond recovery? By no means: but rather through their fall salvation has come to the Gentiles, to provoke them to jealousy.
B045C011V012	45	11	12	Now if their fall means riches for the world, and their failure riches for the Gentiles; how much more will their fullness bring?
B045C011V013	45	11	13	For I speak to you Gentiles. Inasmuch as I am the apostle to the Gentiles, I make much of my ministry:
B045C011V014	45	11	14	That I might provoke to envy my own people, and might save some of them.
B045C011V015	45	11	15	For if their rejection is the reconciliation of the world, what shall their acceptance be, but life from the dead?
B045C011V016	45	11	16	For if the piece of dough offered as firstfruits is holy, then the whole lump is also holy: and if the root is holy, so are the branches.
B045C011V017	45	11	17	And if some of the branches were broken off, and you, a wild olive shoot, were grafted in among them, and with them partake in the rich root of the olive tree;
B045C011V018	45	11	18	Do not boast over the branches. If you boast, remember that you do not support the root, but the root supports you.
B045C011V019	45	11	19	You will say, Branches were broken off, that I might be grafted in.
B045C011V020	45	11	20	That is true; because of unbelief they were broken off, and you stand only by faith. Do not be conceited, but fear:
B045C011V021	45	11	21	For if God did not spare the natural branches, he will not spare you.
B045C011V022	45	11	22	Therefore behold the kindness and severity of God: on those who fell, severity; but toward you, kindness, if you continue in his kindness: otherwise you shall also be cut off.
B045C011V023	45	11	23	And they also, if they do not persist in unbelief, shall be grafted in: for God is able to graft them in again.
B045C011V024	45	11	24	For if you were cut off from an olive tree which is wild by nature, and contrary to nature were grafted onto a good olive tree: how much more shall these, which are the natural branches, be grafted into their own olive tree?
B045C011V025	45	11	25	Brethren, I would not have you be ignorant of this mystery, lest you should be wise in your own conceits; that a hardening in part has happened to Israel, until the full number of Gentiles has come in.
B045C011V026	45	11	26	And so all Israel shall be saved: as it is written, There shall come out of Zion the Deliverer, who shall banish ungodliness from Jacob:
B045C011V027	45	11	27	For this is my covenant with them, when I shall take away their sins.
B045C011V028	45	11	28	Concerning the gospel, they are enemies of God, for your sakes: but concerning election, they are beloved for the sake of the fathers.
B045C011V029	45	11	29	For the gifts and calling of God are never revoked.
B045C011V030	45	11	30	For as you in times past have not obeyed God, yet have now obtained mercy because of their disobedience:
B045C011V031	45	11	31	Even so they have now become disobedient, that through the mercy shown you they may now also obtain mercy.
B045C011V032	45	11	32	For God has consigned all men to disobedience, that he might have mercy upon all.
B045C011V033	45	11	33	O the depth of the riches both of the wisdom and knowledge of God! how unsearchable are his judgments, and his ways past finding out!
B045C011V034	45	11	34	For who has known the mind of the Lord? or who has been his counsellor?
B045C011V035	45	11	35	Or who has first given to him, that he might be repaid?
B045C011V036	45	11	36	For from him, and through him, and to him, are all things. To him be glory forever. Amen.
B045C012V001	45	12	1	Therefore I urge you, brethren, by the mercies of God, to present your bodies a living sacrifice, holy, acceptable to God, which is your reasonable service of worship.
B045C012V002	45	12	2	And do not be conformed to this world: but be transformed by the renewing of your mind, that you may prove what the will of God is, that which is good, and acceptable, and perfect.
B045C012V003	45	12	3	For through the grace given to me, I say to every man among you not to think of himself more highly than he ought to think; but to think soberly, according to the measure of faith God has given him.
B045C012V004	45	12	4	For as we have many members in one body, and all the members do not have the same function:
B045C012V005	45	12	5	So we, though many, are one body in Christ, and individually are members one of another.
B045C012V006	45	12	6	Having gifts differing according to the grace that is given to us, let us use them: if prophecy, according to the proportion of our faith;
B045C012V007	45	12	7	If service, in our serving; or he who teaches, in his teaching;
B045C012V008	45	12	8	Or he who exhorts, in exhortation: he who gives, with generosity; he who leads, with diligence; he who shows mercy, with cheerfulness.
B045C012V009	45	12	9	Let love be genuine. Abhor that which is evil; cling to that which is good.
B045C012V010	45	12	10	Be devoted to one another with brotherly love; honour one another more than yourselves;
B045C012V011	45	12	11	Not lacking in zeal; aglow with the spirit; serving the Lord;
B045C012V012	45	12	12	Rejoicing in hope; patient in tribulation; faithful in prayer;
B045C012V013	45	12	13	Contributing to the saints who are in need; practicing hospitality.
B045C012V014	45	12	14	Bless those who persecute you: bless, and do not curse.
B045C012V015	45	12	15	Rejoice with those who rejoice, and weep with those who weep.
B045C012V016	45	12	16	Be in harmony with one another. Do not be haughty, but associate with the lowly. Do not be wise in your own conceits.
B045C012V017	45	12	17	Do not repay any man evil for evil, but take thought of those things that are right in the sight of all men.
B045C012V018	45	12	18	If it is possible, as much as it lies with you, live peaceably with all men.
B045C012V019	45	12	19	Dearly beloved, do not avenge yourselves, but rather give place for the wrath of God: for it is written, Vengeance is mine; I will repay, says the Lord.
B045C012V020	45	12	20	Therefore, if your enemy is hungry, feed him; if he is thirsty, give him something to drink: for in so doing you shall heap coals of fire upon his head.
B045C012V021	45	12	21	Do not be overcome by evil, but overcome evil with good.
B045C013V001	45	13	1	Let every man be subject to the governing authorities. For there is no authority but from God: and those authorities that exist have been ordained by God.
B045C013V002	45	13	2	Therefore, whoever resists the authorities, resists the ordinance of God: and those who resist shall bring condemnation upon themselves.
B045C013V003	45	13	3	For rulers are not a terror for those who do good works, but to those who do evil. Do you want to have no fear of the one in authority? do that which is good, and you shall have his praise:
B045C013V004	45	13	4	For he is a minister of God for your good. But if you do that which is evil, be afraid; for he does not bear the sword in vain: for he is a minister of God to execute wrath upon the one who does evil.
B045C013V005	45	13	5	Therefore you must be subject, not only to avoid wrath, but also for conscience sake.
B045C013V006	45	13	6	For this reason you also pay taxes: for they are God's ministers, attending continually to this very service.
B045C013V007	45	13	7	Therefore, give to all men what is due them: tax to whom tax is due; revenue to whom revenue; respect to whom respect; honour to whom honour.
B045C013V008	45	13	8	Owe no man anything, but to love one another: for he who loves others has fulfilled the law.
B045C013V009	45	13	9	For the commandments, You shall not commit adultery, You shall not kill, You shall not steal, You shall not covet; and any other commandments, are summed up in this saying, You shall love your neighbour as yourself.
B045C013V010	45	13	10	Love does no wrong to a neighbour: therefore love is the fulfillment of the law.
B045C013V011	45	13	11	And besides that, you know the hour, that it is now high time to awaken from sleep: for now our salvation is nearer than when we believed.
B045C013V012	45	13	12	The night is far gone, the day is at hand: therefore let us cast off the works of darkness, and let us put on the armour of light.
B045C013V013	45	13	13	Let us conduct ourselves properly, as in the day; not in carousing and drunkenness, not in debauchery and sensuality, not in strife and jealousy.
B045C013V014	45	13	14	But put on the Lord Jesus Christ, and make no provision for the flesh, to gratify its lusts.
B045C014V001	45	14	1	Accept him who is weak in the faith, and do not dispute over his opinions.
B045C014V002	45	14	2	For one believes that he may eat all things: another, who is weak, eats only vegetables.
B045C014V003	45	14	3	Let not him who eats despise him who does not eat; and let not him who does not eat judge him who eats: for God has accepted him.
B045C014V004	45	14	4	Who are you to judge another man's servant? to his own master he stands or falls. And he shall be upheld: for the Lord is able to make him stand.
B045C014V005	45	14	5	One man esteems one day above another: another esteems every day alike. Let each man be fully convinced in his own mind.
B045C014V006	45	14	6	He who observes the day, observes it for the Lord; He who eats, eats to the Lord, for he gives God thanks; and he who does not eat, abstains for the Lord, and gives God thanks.
B045C014V007	45	14	7	For none of us lives for himself, and none of us dies for himself.
B045C014V008	45	14	8	For if we live, we live for the Lord; and if we die, we die for the Lord: therefore, whether we live or die, we are the Lord's.
B045C014V009	45	14	9	For to this end Christ both died, and rose to life, that he might be Lord of both the dead and the living.
B045C014V010	45	14	10	Why do you judge your brother? or why do you despise your brother? for we shall all stand before the judgment seat of God.
B045C014V011	45	14	11	For it is written, As I live, says the Lord, every knee shall bow to me, and every tongue shall confess to God.
B045C014V012	45	14	12	So then, every one of us shall give an account of himself to God.
B045C014V013	45	14	13	Therefore, let us not judge one another any more: but rather decide never to put a stumbling block or an obstacle in a brother's way.
B045C014V014	45	14	14	I know, and am persuaded in the Lord Jesus, that there is nothing unclean of itself: but to him who considers anything to be unclean, to him it is unclean.
B045C014V015	45	14	15	But if your brother is hurt because of your food, you are no longer walking in love. Do not destroy with your food him for whom Christ died.
B045C014V016	45	14	16	Therefore, do not let your good be spoken of as evil:
B045C014V017	45	14	17	For the kingdom of God is not food and drink; but righteousness, and peace, and joy in the Holy Spirit.
B045C014V018	45	14	18	For he who serves Christ in this way is acceptable to God, and approved by men.
B045C014V019	45	14	19	Therefore, let us follow after the things which make for peace, and things which edify one another.
B045C014V020	45	14	20	Do not destroy the work of God for food. All things indeed are pure; but it is wrong for a man to cause another to fall by what he eats.
B045C014V021	45	14	21	It is good not to eat meat, or to drink wine, or do anything that causes your brother to stumble.
B045C014V022	45	14	22	Do you have a conviction? keep it for yourself before God. Happy is he who does not condemn himself in that thing which he approves.
B045C014V023	45	14	23	But he who doubts is condemned if he eats, because his eating is not from faith: and whatever is not from faith is sin.
B045C015V001	45	15	1	We then who are strong ought to bear with the infirmities of the weak, and not to please ourselves.
B045C015V002	45	15	2	Let every one of us please his neighbour for his good, to edify him.
B045C015V003	45	15	3	For even Christ did not please himself; but, as it is written, The reproaches of those who reproached you fell upon me.
B045C015V004	45	15	4	For whatever things were written in the past were written for our instruction, that through endurance and the encouragement of the scriptures, we might have hope.
B045C015V005	45	15	5	Now may the God of endurance and encouragement grant you to live in harmony with one another, according to Christ Jesus:
B045C015V006	45	15	6	That you may with one heart and one mouth glorify the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B045C015V007	45	15	7	Therefore welcome one another, as Christ welcomed us to the glory of God.
B045C015V008	45	15	8	Now I say that Christ became a minister to the circumcised for the truth of God, to confirm the promises made to the fathers:
B045C015V009	45	15	9	And that the Gentiles might glorify God for his mercy; as it is written, For this cause I will praise you among the Gentiles, and sing to your name.
B045C015V010	45	15	10	And again he says, Rejoice, you Gentiles, with his people.
B045C015V011	45	15	11	And again, Praise the Lord, all you Gentiles; and praise him, all you people.
B045C015V012	45	15	12	And again, Isaiah says, The root of Jesse shall come, and he shall rise to reign over the Gentiles; in him shall the Gentiles hope.
B045C015V013	45	15	13	Now may the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace in believing, that you may abound in hope, through the power of the Holy Spirit.
B045C015V014	45	15	14	And I myself am also convinced about you, my brethren, that you are full of goodness, filled with all knowledge, and able also to admonish one another.
B045C015V015	45	15	15	Nevertheless, brethren, I have written more boldly to you on some points, as a reminder, because of the grace given to me by God,
B045C015V016	45	15	16	That I should be a minister of Christ Jesus to the Gentiles, in the priestly service of the gospel of God, that the offering of the Gentiles might be acceptable, being sanctified by the Holy Spirit.
B045C015V017	45	15	17	Therefore, through Jesus Christ I have reason to glory in my work for God.
B045C015V018	45	15	18	For I will not dare to speak of any work except what Christ has done through me, to make the Gentiles obedient, by word and deed,
B045C015V019	45	15	19	Through the power of signs and wonders, by the power of the Spirit of God; so that from Jerusalem, and all the way around to Illyricum, I have fully preached the gospel of Christ.
B045C015V020	45	15	20	So I aspired to preach the gospel, not where Christ was named, lest I should build upon another man's foundation:
B045C015V021	45	15	21	But as it is written, Those who were not told of him shall see: and those who have not heard shall understand.
B045C015V022	45	15	22	This is why I have been often hindered from coming to you.
B045C015V023	45	15	23	But now, having no more opportunity for work in these parts, and having a great desire these many years to come to you;
B045C015V024	45	15	24	I hope to see you on my way to Spain, and to be helped on my journey there by you, after I have enjoyed your company for a while.
B045C015V025	45	15	25	But now I go to Jerusalem to minister to the saints.
B045C015V026	45	15	26	For it has pleased those of Macedonia and Achaia to make a contribution for the poor among the saints who are at Jerusalem.
B045C015V027	45	15	27	It has truly pleased them to do this; and indeed they are indebted to them. For if the Gentiles have been made partakers of their spiritual things, their duty is to minister to them in material things.
B045C015V028	45	15	28	Therefore, when I have completed this, and have made certain they have received this fruit, I will come visit you on my way to Spain.
B045C015V029	45	15	29	And I am sure that, when I come to you, I shall come in the fulness of the blessing of Christ.
B045C015V030	45	15	30	Now I urge you, brethren, for the sake of our Lord Jesus Christ, and by the love of the Spirit, that you strive together with me in your prayers to God for me;
B045C015V031	45	15	31	That I may be delivered from those who do not believe in Judaea; and that my service for Jerusalem may be accepted by the saints;
B045C015V032	45	15	32	That I may come to you with joy by the will of God, and may together with you be refreshed.
B045C015V033	45	15	33	The God of peace be with you all. Amen.
B045C016V001	45	16	1	I commend to you Phoebe our sister, who is a servant of the church which is at Cenchreae:
B045C016V002	45	16	2	That you receive her in the Lord, in a manner befitting the saints, and that you assist her in whatever matter she may have need of you: for she has been a help to many, and to myself as well.
B045C016V003	45	16	3	Greet Prisca and Aquila, my fellow workers in Christ Jesus:
B045C016V004	45	16	4	Who have for my life risked their own necks: to whom not only do I give thanks, but also all the churches of the Gentiles.
B045C016V005	45	16	5	Also greet the church that is in their house. Greet my well-beloved Epaenetus, who was the first convert in Asia for Christ.
B045C016V006	45	16	6	Greet Mary, who bestowed much labour upon you.
B045C016V007	45	16	7	Greet Andronicus and Junias, my kinsmen, and my fellow prisoners, who are of note among the apostles, who also were in Christ before me.
B045C016V008	45	16	8	Greet Ampliatus, my beloved in the Lord.
B045C016V009	45	16	9	Greet Urban, our fellow worker in Christ, and Stachys, my beloved.
B045C016V010	45	16	10	Greet Apelles, tested and approved in Christ. Greet those who are of Aristobulus' household.
B045C016V011	45	16	11	Greet Herodion, my kinsman. Greet those of the household of Narcissus, who are in the Lord.
B045C016V012	45	16	12	Greet Tryphaena and Tryphosa, who labour in the Lord. Greet the beloved Persis, who laboured much in the Lord.
B045C016V013	45	16	13	Greet Rufus, chosen in the Lord, and his mother and mine.
B045C016V014	45	16	14	Greet Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas, and the brethren who are with them.
B045C016V015	45	16	15	Greet Philologus, and Julia, Nereus, and his sister, and Olympas, and all the saints who are with them.
B045C016V016	45	16	16	Greet one another with a holy kiss. All the churches of Christ greet you.
B045C016V017	45	16	17	Now I urge you, brethren, take note of those who cause divisions and difficulties, contrary to the doctrine which you have learned; and avoid them.
B045C016V018	45	16	18	For they do not serve our Lord Christ, but their own bellies; and by smooth words and flattering speech they deceive the hearts of the simple.
B045C016V019	45	16	19	For your obedience is known to all, and therefore I am glad on your behalf: yet I would have you be wise regarding that which is good, and simple concerning evil.
B045C016V020	45	16	20	And the God of peace shall soon crush Satan under your feet. The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
B045C016V021	45	16	21	Timothy, my fellow worker, and Lucius, and Jason, and Sosipater, my kinsmen, greet you.
B045C016V022	45	16	22	I Tertius, who wrote this letter, greet you in the Lord.
B045C016V023	45	16	23	Gaius, host to me and the whole church, greets you. Erastus, the treasurer of the city, and our brother Quartus, greet you.
B045C016V024	45	16	24	[The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all. Amen.]
B045C016V025	45	16	25	Now to him who is able to establish you according to my gospel and the preaching of Jesus Christ, according to the revelation of the mystery which was kept secret for long ages past,
B045C016V026	45	16	26	But now has been made manifest, and through the scriptures of the prophets, according to the commandment of the eternal God, has been made known to all nations to bring about the obedience of faith:
B045C016V027	45	16	27	To the only wise God, be glory through Jesus Christ forever. Amen.
B046C001V001	46	1	1	Paul, called to be an apostle of Jesus Christ through the will of God, and Sosthenes our brother,
B046C001V002	46	1	2	To the church of God which is at Corinth, to those who are sanctified in Christ Jesus, called to be saints, with all those in every place who call upon the name of Jesus Christ our Lord, both their Lord and ours:
B046C001V003	46	1	3	Grace to you, and peace, from God our Father, and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C001V004	46	1	4	I thank my God always for you, because of the grace of God which has been given you in Jesus Christ;
B046C001V005	46	1	5	That in everything you have been enriched by him, in all speech, and in all knowledge;
B046C001V006	46	1	6	So the testimony about Christ has been confirmed in you:
B046C001V007	46	1	7	Therefore you lack no spiritual gift; as you await the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ:
B046C001V008	46	1	8	Who shall also confirm you to the end, blameless in the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C001V009	46	1	9	God is faithful, by whom you were called into fellowship with his Son Jesus Christ our Lord.
B046C001V010	46	1	10	Now I urge you, brethren, by the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that you all agree, and that there be no divisions among you; but that you be perfectly joined together in the same mind and in the same judgment.
B046C001V011	46	1	11	For it has been declared to me about you, my brethren, by Chloe's people, that there are quarrels among you.
B046C001V012	46	1	12	What I mean to say is that every one of you says, I am of Paul; and I of Apollos; and I of Cephas; and I of Christ.
B046C001V013	46	1	13	Is Christ divided? was Paul crucified for you? or were you baptized in the name of Paul?
B046C001V014	46	1	14	I thank God that I baptized none of you, except Crispus and Gaius;
B046C001V015	46	1	15	Lest anyone should say that you had been baptized in my name.
B046C001V016	46	1	16	(I also baptized the household of Stephanas: besides that, I do not know whether I baptized anyone else.)
B046C001V017	46	1	17	For Christ did not send me to baptize, but to preach the gospel: not with eloquent words of wisdom, lest the cross of Christ should be emptied of its power.
B046C001V018	46	1	18	For the preaching of the cross is to those who are perishing foolishness; but to those of us who are being saved it is the power of God.
B046C001V019	46	1	19	For it is written, I will destroy the wisdom of the wise, and frustrate the cleverness of the clever.
B046C001V020	46	1	20	Where is the wise man? where is the scribe? where is the debater of this age? has not God made foolish the wisdom of this world?
B046C001V021	46	1	21	For since, in the wisdom of God, the world by its wisdom did not come to know God, it pleased God through the foolishness of our preaching to save those who believe.
B046C001V022	46	1	22	For Jews require a sign, and Greeks seek after wisdom:
B046C001V023	46	1	23	But we preach Christ crucified, to the Jews a stumbling block, and to the Greeks foolishness;
B046C001V024	46	1	24	But to those who are called, both Jews and Greeks, Christ the power of God, and the wisdom of God.
B046C001V025	46	1	25	Because the foolishness of God is wiser than men; and the weakness of God is stronger than men.
B046C001V026	46	1	26	For consider your calling, brethren: that not many were wise according to the flesh, not many mighty, not many noble:
B046C001V027	46	1	27	But God has chosen the foolish things of the world to shame the wise; and God has chosen the weak things of the world to shame the things which are mighty;
B046C001V028	46	1	28	And God has chosen base things of the world, and things which are despised, and things which are not, to reduce to nothing things that are:
B046C001V029	46	1	29	That no flesh should boast in his presence.
B046C001V030	46	1	30	But because of him you are in Christ Jesus, who became for us wisdom from God, and righteousness, and holiness, and redemption:
B046C001V031	46	1	31	So that, just as it is written, Let him who boasts, boast in the Lord.
B046C002V001	46	2	1	And when I came to you, brethren, I did not come with lofty speech or wisdom as I declared to you the testimony of God.
B046C002V002	46	2	2	For I determined not to know anything among you, except Jesus Christ, and him crucified.
B046C002V003	46	2	3	And I was with you in weakness, and in fear, and in much trembling.
B046C002V004	46	2	4	And my speech and my preaching were not with persuasive words of man's wisdom, but in demonstration of the Spirit and of power:
B046C002V005	46	2	5	That your faith should not rest on the wisdom of men, but on the power of God.
B046C002V006	46	2	6	Yet we do speak wisdom among those who are mature: yet not the wisdom of this world, nor of the rulers of this world, who are being brought to nothing:
B046C002V007	46	2	7	But we speak the wisdom of God, once secret and hidden, which God ordained for our glory before the ages:
B046C002V008	46	2	8	Wisdom which none of the rulers of this world understood: for had they understood it, they would not have crucified the Lord of glory.
B046C002V009	46	2	9	But as it is written, Eye has not seen, nor ear heard, nor has it entered the heart of man, the things which God has prepared for those who love him.
B046C002V010	46	2	10	But God has revealed them to us by his Spirit: for the Spirit searches all things, even the deep things of God.
B046C002V011	46	2	11	For what man knows the thoughts of a man, except the spirit which is within the man? even so no one knows the thoughts of God except the Spirit of God.
B046C002V012	46	2	12	Now we have received, not the spirit of the world, but the spirit which is from God; that we might know the things that are freely given to us by God.
B046C002V013	46	2	13	Of these things we speak, not in words taught by man's wisdom, but in those taught by the Spirit; comparing spiritual things with spiritual.
B046C002V014	46	2	14	But the natural man does not receive the things of the Spirit of God: for they are foolishness to him: neither can he understand them, because they are spiritually discerned.
B046C002V015	46	2	15	He who is spiritual judges the worth of all things, yet he himself is judged by no man.
B046C002V016	46	2	16	For who has known the mind of the Lord, that he may instruct him? But we have the mind of Christ.
B046C003V001	46	3	1	And I, brethren, could not speak to you as to spiritual men, but as to men of the flesh, as babes in Christ.
B046C003V002	46	3	2	I have fed you with milk, and not with solid food: for until now you were not able to bear it, nor are you yet able.
B046C003V003	46	3	3	For you are still fleshly: for while there is among you envy, and strife, are you not fleshly, and walking as mere men?
B046C003V004	46	3	4	For while one says, I am of Paul; and another, I am of Apollos; are you not mere men?
B046C003V005	46	3	5	Who then is Paul, and who is Apollos, but ministers by whom you believed, as the Lord assigned to each his task?
B046C003V006	46	3	6	I have planted, Apollos watered; but God gave the growth.
B046C003V007	46	3	7	So then, neither he who plants nor he who waters is anything; but only God who gives the growth.
B046C003V008	46	3	8	Now he who plants and he who waters are equal: and every man shall receive his own reward according to his own labour.
B046C003V009	46	3	9	For we are labourers together with God: you are God's field, God's building.
B046C003V010	46	3	10	According to the grace of God which is given to me, as a wise master builder, I have laid the foundation, and another builds upon it. But let every man take heed how he builds upon it.
B046C003V011	46	3	11	For no other foundation can man lay than that which is laid, which is Jesus Christ.
B046C003V012	46	3	12	Now if any man builds upon this foundation with gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, or straw;
B046C003V013	46	3	13	Each man's work shall be made manifest: for the day shall declare it, because it shall be revealed by fire; and the fire shall test the quality of every man's work.
B046C003V014	46	3	14	If any man's work remains, which he has built upon it, he shall receive a reward.
B046C003V015	46	3	15	If any man's work shall be burned, he shall suffer loss: but he himself shall be saved; but only as through fire.
B046C003V016	46	3	16	Do you not know that you are God's temple, and that the Spirit of God dwells in you?
B046C003V017	46	3	17	If any man defiles God's temple, God shall destroy him; for the temple of God is holy, and you are that temple.
B046C003V018	46	3	18	Let no man deceive himself. If any man among you thinks he is wise in this world, let him become a fool, that he may be wise.
B046C003V019	46	3	19	For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God. For it is written, He catches the wise in their own craftiness.
B046C003V020	46	3	20	And again, The Lord knows the thoughts of the wise, that they are futile.
B046C003V021	46	3	21	Therefore, let no one glory in men. For all things are yours;
B046C003V022	46	3	22	Whether Paul, or Apollos, or Cephas, or the world, or life, or death, or things present, or things to come; all are yours;
B046C003V023	46	3	23	And you are Christ's; and Christ is God's.
B046C004V001	46	4	1	Let a man regard us in this manner, as servants of Christ, and stewards of the mysteries of God.
B046C004V002	46	4	2	Moreover, it is required of stewards that they be found trustworthy.
B046C004V003	46	4	3	But with me it is a very small thing if I should be judged by you, or by any human court: in fact, I do not even judge my own self.
B046C004V004	46	4	4	For I know of nothing against myself; yet I am not by this justified: but he who judges me is the Lord.
B046C004V005	46	4	5	Therefore, judge nothing before the time; before the Lord comes, who will both bring to light the things hidden in darkness, and will disclose the motives of the heart: and then every man shall have his praise from God.
B046C004V006	46	4	6	And these things, brethren, I have applied to myself and Apollos for your sakes; that through us you might learn not to go beyond that which is written, that none of you might become puffed up in favour of one against another.
B046C004V007	46	4	7	For who makes you superior to another? and what do you have that you did not receive? now if you did receive it, why do you boast, as if you had not received it?
B046C004V008	46	4	8	Already you are full, already you are rich, you have become as kings without us: and I would that you had become kings, that we might also reign with you.
B046C004V009	46	4	9	For I think that God has exhibited us apostles last of all, as if we were condemned to death: for we have become a spectacle to the world, to angels and to men.
B046C004V010	46	4	10	We are fools for Christ's sake, but you are wise in Christ; we are weak, but you are strong; you are honoured, but we are despised.
B046C004V011	46	4	11	Even to this present hour we both hunger and thirst, and are ill-clothed, and are buffeted, and are homeless;
B046C004V012	46	4	12	And we labour, working with our own hands: when reviled, we bless; when persecuted, we endure it:
B046C004V013	46	4	13	When slandered, we answer kindly; we have been made the filth of the world, the offscouring of all things, even to this day.
B046C004V014	46	4	14	I do not write these things to shame you, but as my beloved children I warn you.
B046C004V015	46	4	15	For though you have ten thousand instructors in Christ, yet you do not have many fathers: for in Christ Jesus I became your father through the gospel.
B046C004V016	46	4	16	Therefore I urge you, be imitators of me.
B046C004V017	46	4	17	For this reason I have sent to you Timothy, who is my beloved son, and faithful in the Lord, who shall remind you of my ways in Christ, as I teach everywhere in every church.
B046C004V018	46	4	18	Now some are puffed up, as though I were not coming to you.
B046C004V019	46	4	19	But I will come to you shortly, if the Lord wills, and will find out, not the speech of those who are puffed up, but their power.
B046C004V020	46	4	20	For the kingdom of God does not consist of talk, but of power.
B046C004V021	46	4	21	What do you wish? shall I come to you with a rod, or in love, and in a spirit of gentleness?
B046C005V001	46	5	1	It is actually reported that there is immorality among you, and such immorality as does not even occur among the Gentiles, that one of you has his father's wife.
B046C005V002	46	5	2	And you are puffed up, and have not mourned instead. Let him who has done this deed be removed from among you.
B046C005V003	46	5	3	For I, though absent in body, am present in spirit, and have already judged him who has done this deed, just as though I were present.
B046C005V004	46	5	4	In the name of our Lord Jesus, when you are gathered together, with my spirit, with the power of our Lord Jesus,
B046C005V005	46	5	5	Deliver this man to Satan for the destruction of his flesh, that his spirit may be saved on the day of the Lord Jesus.
B046C005V006	46	5	6	Your boasting is not good. Do you not know that a little leaven leavens the whole lump?
B046C005V007	46	5	7	Clean out the old leaven, that you may be a new lump, since you really are unleavened. For Christ our passover has been sacrificed for us:
B046C005V008	46	5	8	Therefore let us keep the feast, not with old leaven, the leaven of malice and wickedness; but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.
B046C005V009	46	5	9	I wrote to you in a letter not to keep company with the sexually immoral:
B046C005V010	46	5	10	Not at all meaning the immoral of this world, or the covetous, or swindlers, or idolaters; for then you would have to go out of the world.
B046C005V011	46	5	11	But now I write to you not to keep company with any man who is called a brother if he is sexually immoral, or covetous, or an idolater, or a slanderer, or a drunkard, or an swindler; with such a one do not even eat.
B046C005V012	46	5	12	For what have I to do with judging those who are outside? are you not to judge those who are within?
B046C005V013	46	5	13	Those who are outside God judges. Put out from among yourselves the wicked person.
B046C006V001	46	6	1	Does any of you dare, if you have a dispute against another, to go to law before the ungodly, instead of before the saints?
B046C006V002	46	6	2	Do you not know that the saints shall judge the world? and if the world shall be judged by you, are you unworthy to judge the smallest matters?
B046C006V003	46	6	3	Do you not know that we shall judge angels? how much more, things that pertain to this life?
B046C006V004	46	6	4	If then you have such disputes, set them before those who are least esteemed in the church.
B046C006V005	46	6	5	I speak this to your shame. Can it be that there is not a wise man among you who shall be able to judge between his brethren?
B046C006V006	46	6	6	But brother goes to law against brother, and that before the unbelievers.
B046C006V007	46	6	7	Now, it is utterly a defeat for you that you go to law one with another. Why do you not rather suffer the wrong? why do you not rather allow yourselves to be defrauded?
B046C006V008	46	6	8	Instead, you yourselves do wrong, and defraud, and you do this to your brethren.
B046C006V009	46	6	9	Do you not know that the unrighteous shall not inherit the kingdom of God? Do not be deceived: neither the sexually immoral, nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor homosexual offenders,
B046C006V010	46	6	10	Nor thieves, nor the covetous, nor drunkards, nor slanderers, nor swindlers, shall inherit the kingdom of God.
B046C006V011	46	6	11	And such were some of you: but you are washed, but you are sanctified, but you are justified in the name of the Lord Jesus, and by the Spirit of our God.
B046C006V012	46	6	12	All things are lawful for me, but all things are not beneficial: all things are lawful for me, but I will not be brought under the power of anything.
B046C006V013	46	6	13	Food is for the belly, and the belly for food: but God shall destroy both of them. The body is not for sexual immorality, but for the Lord; and the Lord for the body.
B046C006V014	46	6	14	And God has raised up the Lord, and will also raise up us by his power.
B046C006V015	46	6	15	Do you not know that your bodies are the members of Christ? shall I then take the members of Christ, and make them the members of a prostitute? Never.
B046C006V016	46	6	16	Or do you not know that he who is joined to a prostitute becomes one body with her? for the two, he says, shall become one flesh.
B046C006V017	46	6	17	But he who is joined to the Lord is one spirit with him.
B046C006V018	46	6	18	Flee sexual immorality. Every other sin that a man commits is outside his body; but he who commits sexual immorality sins against his own body.
B046C006V019	46	6	19	Do you not know that your body is a temple of the Holy Spirit, who is in you, whom you have received from God, and that you are not your own?
B046C006V020	46	6	20	For you have been bought with a price: therefore glorify God in your body.
B046C007V001	46	7	1	Now concerning the things about which you wrote to me: It is good for a man not to touch a woman.
B046C007V002	46	7	2	Nevertheless, to avoid impurity, let every man have his own wife, and let every woman have her own husband.
B046C007V003	46	7	3	Let the husband fulfill his marital duty to his wife: and likewise the wife to the husband.
B046C007V004	46	7	4	The wife does not have authority over her own body, but the husband does: and likewise the husband does not have authority over his own body, but the wife does.
B046C007V005	46	7	5	Do not deprive one another, except by consent for a time, that you may give yourselves to prayer; and then come together again, that Satan may not tempt you for your lack of self-control.
B046C007V006	46	7	6	But I speak this as a concession, and not as a commandment.
B046C007V007	46	7	7	For I wish that all men were as I am. But every man has his proper gift from God, one of this type, and another of that.
B046C007V008	46	7	8	Therefore I say to the unmarried and widows, It is good for them to remain single, as I am.
B046C007V009	46	7	9	But if they cannot contain themselves, let them marry: for it is better to marry than to burn with passion.
B046C007V010	46	7	10	And to the married I give this command, not I, but the Lord, Let the wife not depart from her husband:
B046C007V011	46	7	11	But if she does depart, let her remain unmarried, or be reconciled to her husband: and let the husband not divorce his wife.
B046C007V012	46	7	12	But to the rest I say, not the Lord: If any brother has a wife who does not believe, and she is willing to live with him, let him not divorce her.
B046C007V013	46	7	13	And the woman who has a husband who does not believe, and if he is willing to live with her, let her not leave him.
B046C007V014	46	7	14	For the unbelieving husband is sanctified by the wife, and the unbelieving wife is sanctified by the husband: otherwise your children would be unclean; but now are they holy.
B046C007V015	46	7	15	But if the unbelieving one departs, let him depart. A brother or a sister is not under bondage in such cases: for God has called us to peace.
B046C007V016	46	7	16	For how do you know, O wife, whether you shall save your husband? or how do you know, O man, whether you shall save your wife?
B046C007V017	46	7	17	But as the Lord has assigned to every man, as God has called every one, so let him walk. And this is my rule in all the churches.
B046C007V018	46	7	18	Was any man circumcised when he was called? let him not become uncircumcised. Was any uncircumcised when called? let him not be circumcised.
B046C007V019	46	7	19	Circumcision is nothing, and uncircumcision is nothing, but keeping of the commandments of God is what matters.
B046C007V020	46	7	20	Let every man remain in the same situation in which he was called.
B046C007V021	46	7	21	Were you called when a slave? do not let it trouble you: but if you may become free, do so.
B046C007V022	46	7	22	For he who is called in the Lord while a slave, is the Lord's freedman: likewise he who is called while free, is Christ's slave.
B046C007V023	46	7	23	You were bought with a price; do not become the slaves of men.
B046C007V024	46	7	24	Brethren, let every man, in whatever situation he was in when called, remain there with God.
B046C007V025	46	7	25	Now concerning virgins I have no commandment from the Lord: yet I give my judgment, as one who has obtained mercy from the Lord to be trustworthy.
B046C007V026	46	7	26	I think then, in view of the present distress, that it is good for a man to remain as he is.
B046C007V027	46	7	27	Are you bound to a wife? do not seek to be released. Are you released from a wife? do not seek a wife.
B046C007V028	46	7	28	But if you do marry, you have not sinned; and if a virgin marries, she has not sinned. Nevertheless, those who marry shall have trouble in this life: and I seek to spare you.
B046C007V029	46	7	29	But this I say, brethren, the time is short: from now on let those who have wives be as though they had none;
B046C007V030	46	7	30	And those who weep, as though they did not weep; and those who rejoice, as though they did not rejoice; and those who buy, as though they did not possess;
B046C007V031	46	7	31	And those who use this world, as though not engrossed in it: for the form of this world passes away.
B046C007V032	46	7	32	I would have you be without concern. He who is unmarried is concerned for the things that belong to the Lord, how he may please the Lord:
B046C007V033	46	7	33	But he who is married is concerned for the things that are of the world, how he may please his wife,
B046C007V034	46	7	34	And his interests are divided. And the unmarried woman or the virgin cares for the things of the Lord, that she may be holy both in body and in spirit: but she who is married cares for the things of the world, how she may please her husband.
B046C007V035	46	7	35	And this I speak for your own benefit; not to restrain you, but to promote that which is seemly, and that you may attend to the Lord without distraction.
B046C007V036	46	7	36	But if any man thinks that he is behaving improperly toward the virgin he is engaged to, if she is passing the flower of her youth, and if need so requires, let him do what he wishes, he does not sin: let them marry.
B046C007V037	46	7	37	Nevertheless, he who stands steadfast in his heart, being under no compulsion, but having power over his own will, and having determined in his heart that he will keep his virginity, does well.
B046C007V038	46	7	38	So then he who marries does well; but he who does not marry does better.
B046C007V039	46	7	39	The wife is bound as long as her husband lives; but if her husband dies, she is at liberty to marry whom she wishes; only in the Lord.
B046C007V040	46	7	40	But in my judgment she is happier if she remains as she is: and I also think that I have the Spirit of God.
B046C008V001	46	8	1	Now regarding things offered to idols, we know that we all have knowledge. Knowledge puffs up, but love builds up.
B046C008V002	46	8	2	And if any man thinks that he knows something, he does not yet know as he ought to know.
B046C008V003	46	8	3	But if any man loves God, he is known by him.
B046C008V004	46	8	4	Therefore, concerning the eating of those things that are offered in sacrifice to idols, we know that an idol is nothing in the world, and that there is no God but one.
B046C008V005	46	8	5	For though there are things that are called gods, in heaven and on earth, (and indeed there are many gods, and many lords,)
B046C008V006	46	8	6	But for us there is but one God, the Father, from whom are all things, and we exist for him; and one Lord Jesus Christ, through whom are all things, and we exist through him.
B046C008V007	46	8	7	Yet, not every man has this knowledge: for some are still accustomed to idols, and eat a thing as if it were really offered to an idol; and because their conscience is weak it is defiled.
B046C008V008	46	8	8	But food does not commend us to God: if we eat, we are none the better; if we do not eat, we are none the worse.
B046C008V009	46	8	9	But take heed lest by any means this liberty of yours become a stumbling block to those who are weak.
B046C008V010	46	8	10	For if any man sees you, who have knowledge, eating in an idol's temple, shall not the conscience of the one who is weak be emboldened to eat those things which are offered to idols?
B046C008V011	46	8	11	And so through your knowledge the weak brother is ruined, he for whom Christ died.
B046C008V012	46	8	12	Thus, when you sin against the brethren in this way, and wound their weak conscience, you sin against Christ.
B046C008V013	46	8	13	Therefore, if food makes my brother fall, I will never again eat meat, lest I make my brother fall.
B046C009V001	46	9	1	Am I not an apostle? am I not free? have I not seen Jesus Christ our Lord? are you not my work in the Lord?
B046C009V002	46	9	2	If I am not an apostle to others, yet doubtless I am to you: for you are the seal of my apostleship in the Lord.
B046C009V003	46	9	3	My defence to those who examine me is this:
B046C009V004	46	9	4	Do we not have the right to eat and to drink?
B046C009V005	46	9	5	Do we not have the right to take along a believing wife, as do the other apostles, and the brothers of the Lord, and Cephas?
B046C009V006	46	9	6	Or is it only Barnabas and I who do not have the right to refrain from working?
B046C009V007	46	9	7	Who serves as a soldier at his own expense? who plants a vineyard, and does not eat of its fruit? or who feeds a flock, and does not drink of the milk of the flock?
B046C009V008	46	9	8	Do I say these things merely on human authority? or does not the law say the same?
B046C009V009	46	9	9	For it is written in the law of Moses, You shall not muzzle the mouth of the ox that treads out the grain. Is God concerned about oxen?
B046C009V010	46	9	10	Or does he say it altogether for our sakes? For our sakes it is written: that he who plows should plow in hope; and he who threshes should thresh in hope of a share of the crop.
B046C009V011	46	9	11	If we have sown spiritual things among you, is it too much if we reap material things from you?
B046C009V012	46	9	12	If others share this rightful claim upon you, do we not have a greater claim? Nevertheless, we have not used this right, but endure all things, lest we should hinder the gospel of Christ.
B046C009V013	46	9	13	Do you not know that those who perform the temple services eat the food of the temple? and those who serve at the altar share what is offered at the altar?
B046C009V014	46	9	14	In the same way the Lord ordained that those who preach the gospel should live by the gospel.
B046C009V015	46	9	15	But I have used none of these things: nor am I writing these things that it should be done for me: for it would be better for me to die, than for any man to make my boast an empty one.
B046C009V016	46	9	16	For if I preach the gospel, I have nothing to boast about: for it is a necessity laid upon me; woe to me if I do not preach the gospel!
B046C009V017	46	9	17	If I do this willingly, I have a reward: but if against my will, a commission has been entrusted to me.
B046C009V018	46	9	18	What is my reward then? That when I preach the gospel, I may offer the gospel without charge, not taking advantage of my rights in the gospel.
B046C009V019	46	9	19	For though I am free from all men, yet I have made myself the servant to all, that I might win the more.
B046C009V020	46	9	20	To the Jews I became as a Jew, that I might win the Jews; to those who are under the law, as under the law, that I might win those who are under the law;
B046C009V021	46	9	21	To those who are without the law, as without the law, (though I am not without the law of God, but am under the law of Christ,) that I might win those who are without the law.
B046C009V022	46	9	22	To the weak I became weak, that I might win the weak: I have become all things to all men, that I might by all means save some.
B046C009V023	46	9	23	And this I do for the gospel's sake, that I might be a partaker in its blessings.
B046C009V024	46	9	24	Do you not know that those who run in a race all run, but only one receives the prize? Run in such a way that you may obtain it.
B046C009V025	46	9	25	And every man who competes is temperate in all things. Now they do it to obtain a perishable crown; but we an imperishable.
B046C009V026	46	9	26	Therefore, I do not run aimlessly; and I do not fight as one who beats the air:
B046C009V027	46	9	27	But I beat my body, and bring it into subjection: lest by any means, when I have preached to others, I myself should be disqualified.
B046C010V001	46	10	1	For I do not want you to be ignorant, brethren, that all our fathers were under the cloud, and all passed through the sea;
B046C010V002	46	10	2	And were all baptized into Moses in the cloud and in the sea;
B046C010V003	46	10	3	And all ate the same spiritual food;
B046C010V004	46	10	4	And all drank the same spiritual drink: for they drank from that spiritual Rock that followed them: and that Rock was Christ.
B046C010V005	46	10	5	But with many of them God was not well pleased: for they were overthrown in the wilderness.
B046C010V006	46	10	6	Now these things are examples for us, so we should not lust after evil things, as they lusted.
B046C010V007	46	10	7	Nor be idolaters, as were some of them; as it is written, The people sat down to eat and drink, and rose up to play.
B046C010V008	46	10	8	Let us not commit sexual immorality, as some of them did, and twenty-three thousand fell in one day.
B046C010V009	46	10	9	Nor let us tempt the Lord, as some of them did, and were destroyed by serpents.
B046C010V010	46	10	10	Nor grumble, as some of them did, and were destroyed by the destroyer.
B046C010V011	46	10	11	Now all these things happened to them as examples: and they were written for our instruction, upon whom the end of the ages has come.
B046C010V012	46	10	12	Therefore, let him who thinks he stands take heed lest he fall.
B046C010V013	46	10	13	No temptation has overtaken you but such as is common to man: but God is faithful, who will not allow you to be tempted beyond what you are able to endure; but with the temptation will also make a way to escape, that you may be able to bear it.
B046C010V014	46	10	14	Therefore, my dearly beloved, flee from idolatry.
B046C010V015	46	10	15	I speak as to sensible men; judge for yourselves what I say.
B046C010V016	46	10	16	The cup of blessing which we bless, is it not a sharing in the blood of Christ? The bread which we break, is it not a sharing in the body of Christ?
B046C010V017	46	10	17	Because there is one bread, we who are many are one body: for we are all partakers of that one bread.
B046C010V018	46	10	18	Behold the people of Israel: are not those who eat of the sacrifices partakers in the altar?
B046C010V019	46	10	19	What do I say then? that an idol is anything, or that food offered in sacrifice to idols is anything?
B046C010V020	46	10	20	No, but I say, that the things which the Gentiles sacrifice, they sacrifice to devils, and not to God: and I do not want you to have fellowship with devils.
B046C010V021	46	10	21	You cannot drink the cup of the Lord, and the cup of devils: you cannot be partakers of the Lord's table, and of the table of devils.
B046C010V022	46	10	22	Shall we provoke the Lord to jealousy? are we stronger than he?
B046C010V023	46	10	23	All things are lawful for me, but not all things are beneficial: all things are lawful for me, but not all things are constructive.
B046C010V024	46	10	24	Let no man seek his own good, but the good of others.
B046C010V025	46	10	25	Eat whatever is sold in the meat market, without asking questions for conscience sake:
B046C010V026	46	10	26	For the earth is the Lord's, and all it contains.
B046C010V027	46	10	27	If any of those who do not believe ask you to a meal, and you are disposed to go; eat whatever is set before you, without asking questions for conscience sake.
B046C010V028	46	10	28	But if any man says to you, This has been offered in sacrifice to idols, do not eat, for the sake of the one who informed you, and for conscience sake:
B046C010V029	46	10	29	I do not mean your conscience, but his: for why is my liberty judged by another man's conscience?
B046C010V030	46	10	30	If I partake with thankfulness, why am I denounced because of that for which I give thanks?
B046C010V031	46	10	31	Therefore, whether you eat, or drink, or whatever you do, do all to the glory of God.
B046C010V032	46	10	32	Do not give offence to the Jews, or to the Greeks, or to the church of God:
B046C010V033	46	10	33	Just as I try to please all men in all things, not seeking my own good, but that of the many, that they may be saved.
B046C011V001	46	11	1	Be imitators of me, just as I am of Christ.
B046C011V002	46	11	2	Now I praise you, brethren, that you remember me in all things, and keep the traditions, just as I delivered them to you.
B046C011V003	46	11	3	But I would have you know, that the head of every man is Christ; and the head of the woman is the man; and the head of Christ is God.
B046C011V004	46	11	4	Every man praying or prophesying, while having his head covered, dishonours his head.
B046C011V005	46	11	5	But every woman who prays or prophesies with her head uncovered dishonours her head: for it is the same as if her head were shaven.
B046C011V006	46	11	6	For if the woman will not be covered, let her also be shorn: but if it is shameful for a woman to be shorn or shaven, let her be covered.
B046C011V007	46	11	7	For a man ought not to cover his head, since he is the image and glory of God: but the woman is the glory of the man.
B046C011V008	46	11	8	For the man is not from the woman; but the woman from the man.
B046C011V009	46	11	9	Neither was the man created for the woman; but the woman for the man.
B046C011V010	46	11	10	For this reason the woman ought to have a symbol of authority on her head, because of the angels.
B046C011V011	46	11	11	Nevertheless, in the Lord, the woman is not independent of the man, nor is the man independent of the woman.
B046C011V012	46	11	12	For as the woman was made from the man, even so the man is born from the woman; but all things are from God.
B046C011V013	46	11	13	Judge for yourselves: is it proper for a woman pray to God uncovered?
B046C011V014	46	11	14	Does not even nature itself teach you, that, if a man has long hair, it is a shame to him?
B046C011V015	46	11	15	But if a woman has long hair, it is a glory to her: for her hair is given her for a covering.
B046C011V016	46	11	16	But if any man is inclined to be contentious, we have no other custom, nor do the churches of God.
B046C011V017	46	11	17	Now in the following instructions I do not praise you, for you come together not for the better, but for the worse.
B046C011V018	46	11	18	For, first of all, when you come together as the church, I hear that there are divisions among you; and I partly believe it.
B046C011V019	46	11	19	For there must be factions among you, so that those who are approved may be made evident among you.
B046C011V020	46	11	20	When you come together in one place, it is not to eat the Lord's supper.
B046C011V021	46	11	21	For in eating every one goes ahead with his own supper: and one is hungry, and another is drunken.
B046C011V022	46	11	22	What? do you not have houses in which to eat and to drink? or do you despise the church of God, and shame those who have nothing? What shall I say to you? shall I praise you in this? I will not.
B046C011V023	46	11	23	For I have received from the Lord that which I also delivered to you, That the Lord Jesus, on the night he was betrayed, took bread:
B046C011V024	46	11	24	And when he had given thanks, he broke it, and said, This is my body, which is for you: do this in remembrance of me.
B046C011V025	46	11	25	In the same manner he took the cup, after supper, saying, This cup is the new covenant in my blood: do this, as often as you drink it, in remembrance of me.
B046C011V026	46	11	26	For as often as you eat this bread, and drink this cup, you proclaim the Lord's death until he comes.
B046C011V027	46	11	27	Therefore, whoever shall eat this bread, and drink this cup of the Lord, unworthily, shall be guilty of profaning the body and blood of the Lord.
B046C011V028	46	11	28	Let a man examine himself before he eats of the bread, and drinks of the cup.
B046C011V029	46	11	29	For he who eats and drinks unworthily, not discerning the Lord's body, eats and drinks judgement upon himself.
B046C011V030	46	11	30	For this reason many are weak and sickly among you, and many sleep.
B046C011V031	46	11	31	For if we would judge ourselves, we should not be judged.
B046C011V032	46	11	32	But when we are judged, we are chastened by the Lord, that we should not be condemned with the world.
B046C011V033	46	11	33	Therefore, my brethren, when you come together to eat, wait for one another.
B046C011V034	46	11	34	And if any man is hungry, let him eat at home; so you do not come together to be condemned. And the rest I will set in order when I come.
B046C012V001	46	12	1	Now concerning spiritual gifts, brethren, I would not have you be ignorant.
B046C012V002	46	12	2	You know that when you were pagans, you were carried away by these dumb idols, however you were led.
B046C012V003	46	12	3	Therefore, I want you to understand, that no man speaking by the Spirit of God calls Jesus accursed: and that no man can say that Jesus is Lord, except by the Holy Spirit.
B046C012V004	46	12	4	Now there are various kinds of gifts, but the same Spirit.
B046C012V005	46	12	5	And there are various kinds of service, but the same Lord.
B046C012V006	46	12	6	And there are various kinds of working, but it is the same God who works all of them in all men.
B046C012V007	46	12	7	But the manifestation of the Spirit is given to each man for the common good.
B046C012V008	46	12	8	For to one is given by the Spirit the word of wisdom; to another the word of knowledge by the same Spirit;
B046C012V009	46	12	9	To another faith by the same Spirit; to another the gifts of healing by that one Spirit;
B046C012V010	46	12	10	To another the working of miracles; to another prophecy; to another discerning of spirits; to another various kinds of tongues; to another the interpretation of tongues:
B046C012V011	46	12	11	But all these things are by one and the same Spirit, who distributes to every man as he wills.
B046C012V012	46	12	12	For just as the body is one, and has many members, and all the members of the body, though many, are one body: so it is with Christ.
B046C012V013	46	12	13	For by one Spirit we were all baptized into one body, whether Jews or Greeks, whether slave or free; and have all been made to drink of one Spirit.
B046C012V014	46	12	14	For the body is not one member, but many.
B046C012V015	46	12	15	If the foot shall say, Because I am not the hand, I am not part of the body; is it therefore not part of the body?
B046C012V016	46	12	16	And if the ear shall say, Because I am not the eye, I am not part of the body; is it therefore not part of the body?
B046C012V017	46	12	17	If the whole body were an eye, where would the hearing be? If the whole were hearing, where would the sense of smell be?
B046C012V018	46	12	18	But now God has set the members, every one of them, in the body, as it has pleased him.
B046C012V019	46	12	19	And if they were all one member, where would the body be?
B046C012V020	46	12	20	But as it is, there are many members, yet one body.
B046C012V021	46	12	21	And the eye cannot say to the hand, I have no need of you: nor again the head to the feet, I have no need of you.
B046C012V022	46	12	22	No, those members of the body, which seem to be more feeble, are the most necessary:
B046C012V023	46	12	23	And those members of the body, which we think to be less honourable, upon these we bestow more abundant honour; and our unpresentable parts are treated with special modesty,
B046C012V024	46	12	24	Of which our presentable parts have no need: but God has composed the body, giving more abundant honour to that part which lacked it:
B046C012V025	46	12	25	That there should be no division in the body; but that the members should have the same care for one another.
B046C012V026	46	12	26	And if one member suffers, all the members suffer with it; or if one member is honoured, all the members rejoice with it.
B046C012V027	46	12	27	Now you are the body of Christ, and individually members of it.
B046C012V028	46	12	28	And God has appointed in the church, first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, after that workers of miracles, then those with gifts of healing, helpers, administrators, and those who speak in different tongues.
B046C012V029	46	12	29	Are all apostles? are all prophets? are all teachers? are all workers of miracles?
B046C012V030	46	12	30	Do all have gifts of healing? do all speak with tongues? do all interpret?
B046C012V031	46	12	31	But earnestly desire the best gifts: and yet I will show you a more excellent way.
B046C013V001	46	13	1	If I speak with the tongues of men and of angels, but have not love, I have become a noisy gong, or a clanging cymbal.
B046C013V002	46	13	2	And if I have the gift of prophecy, and understand all mysteries, and all knowledge; and if I have all faith, so that I can remove mountains, but have not love, I am nothing.
B046C013V003	46	13	3	And if I give all my goods to feed the poor, and if I give my body to be burned, but have not love, I gain nothing.
B046C013V004	46	13	4	Love is patient, and is kind; love does not envy; love does not boast, and is not arrogant;
B046C013V005	46	13	5	It is not rude, does not insist on its own way, is not easily provoked, it keeps no account of wrongs suffered;
B046C013V006	46	13	6	It does not rejoice in injustice, but rejoices in the truth;
B046C013V007	46	13	7	Bears all things, believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things.
B046C013V008	46	13	8	Love never fails: but where there are prophecies, they shall pass away; where there are tongues, they shall cease; where there is knowledge, it shall vanish away.
B046C013V009	46	13	9	For we know in part, and we prophesy in part.
B046C013V010	46	13	10	But when that which is perfect comes, then that which is partial shall pass away.
B046C013V011	46	13	11	When I was a child, I spoke as a child, I understood as a child, I thought as a child: but when I became a man, I put away childish things.
B046C013V012	46	13	12	For now we see in a mirror dimly; but then face to face: now I know in part; but then I shall know fully, even as I am fully known.
B046C013V013	46	13	13	And now abide faith, hope, love, these three; but the greatest of these is love.
B046C014V001	46	14	1	Follow after love, and desire spiritual gifts, but especially that you may prophesy.
B046C014V002	46	14	2	For he who speaks in an unknown tongue does not speak to men, but to God: for no man understands him; yet in the spirit he speaks mysteries.
B046C014V003	46	14	3	But he who prophesies speaks to men for their edification, and exhortation, and comfort.
B046C014V004	46	14	4	He who speaks in an unknown tongue edifies himself; but he who prophesies edifies the church.
B046C014V005	46	14	5	I would like for you all to speak in tongues, but even more that you would prophesy: for greater is he who prophesies than he who speaks with tongues, unless he interprets, so that the church may be edified.
B046C014V006	46	14	6	Now, brethren, if I come to you speaking with tongues, how will I benefit you, unless I shall speak to you some revelation, or knowledge, or prophesy, or instruction?
B046C014V007	46	14	7	Even lifeless things which give sound, such as the pipe or harp, unless they make a distinction in the sounds, how shall it be known what is played?
B046C014V008	46	14	8	For if the trumpet gives an uncertain sound, who shall prepare himself for the battle?
B046C014V009	46	14	9	So likewise you, unless you utter by the tongue words that are easy to understand, how shall it be known what is spoken? for you shall speak into the air.
B046C014V010	46	14	10	There are, it may be, many kinds of languages in the world, and none of them is without meaning.
B046C014V011	46	14	11	But if I do not know the meaning of the language, I shall be to him who speaks a foreigner, and he who speaks shall be a foreigner to me.
B046C014V012	46	14	12	So with you, since you are zealous for spiritual gifts, seek to excel in edifying the church.
B046C014V013	46	14	13	Therefore, let him who speaks in an unknown tongue pray that he may interpret.
B046C014V014	46	14	14	For if I pray in an unknown tongue, my spirit prays, but my mind is unfruitful.
B046C014V015	46	14	15	What am I to do? I will pray with the spirit, and I will pray with the mind also: I will sing with the spirit, and I will sing with the mind also.
B046C014V016	46	14	16	Otherwise when you bless with the spirit, how shall he who is ungifted say Amen to your giving of thanks, seeing that he does not understand what you say?
B046C014V017	46	14	17	For you may truly give thanks well, but the other man is not edified.
B046C014V018	46	14	18	I thank my God, that I speak with tongues more than all of you:
B046C014V019	46	14	19	Yet in the church I would rather speak five words with my understanding, that by my voice I might teach others also, than ten thousand words in an unknown tongue.
B046C014V020	46	14	20	Brethren, do not be children in understanding: in evil be infants, but in understanding be men.
B046C014V021	46	14	21	In the law it is written, By men of strange tongues and by the lips of foreigners I will speak to this people; and yet for all that they will not hear me, says the Lord.
B046C014V022	46	14	22	Therefore tongues are a sign, not for those who believe, but for those who do not believe: but prophesy is not only for those who do not believe, but also for those who do believe.
B046C014V023	46	14	23	Therefore, if the whole church comes together in one place, and all speak in tongues, and those who are ungifted, or unbelievers, come in, will they not say that you are mad?
B046C014V024	46	14	24	But if all prophesy, and one comes in who does not believe, or is ungifted, he is convicted by all, he is judged by all:
B046C014V025	46	14	25	The secrets of his heart are disclosed; and so falling down on his face he will worship God, and report that God is really among you.
B046C014V026	46	14	26	What then, brethren? when you come together, every one of you has a psalm, has a teaching, has a tongue, has a revelation, has an interpretation. Let all things be done for edification.
B046C014V027	46	14	27	If anyone speaks in an unknown tongue, let there be two, or at the most three, and each in turn; and let one interpret.
B046C014V028	46	14	28	But if there is no interpreter, let him keep silent in the church; and let him speak to himself, and to God.
B046C014V029	46	14	29	Let two or three prophets speak, and let the others judge.
B046C014V030	46	14	30	If anything is revealed to another who sits by, let the first hold his peace.
B046C014V031	46	14	31	For you may all prophesy one by one, that all may learn, and all may be encouraged.
B046C014V032	46	14	32	And the spirits of the prophets are subject to the prophets.
B046C014V033	46	14	33	For God is not a God of confusion, but of peace. As in all churches of the saints,
B046C014V034	46	14	34	Let the women keep silent in the churches: for it is not permitted for them to speak; but they should be subordinate, as the law says.
B046C014V035	46	14	35	And if they wish to learn anything, let them ask their husbands at home: for it is a disgrace for women to speak in the church.
B046C014V036	46	14	36	What? did the word of God come forth from you? or has it come only to you?
B046C014V037	46	14	37	If any man thinks he is a prophet, or spiritual, let him acknowledge that what I write to you is a commandment of the Lord.
B046C014V038	46	14	38	But if any man does not recognize this, he is not recognized.
B046C014V039	46	14	39	Therefore, brethren, desire to prophesy, and do not forbid speaking in tongues.
B046C014V040	46	14	40	But let all things be done decently and in order.
B046C015V001	46	15	1	Now, brethren, I would remind you of the gospel which I preached to you, which you have received, and in which you stand;
B046C015V002	46	15	2	By which you are also saved, if you hold fast to what I preached to you, unless you believed in vain.
B046C015V003	46	15	3	For I delivered to you as of first importance that which I received, that Christ died for our sins according to the scriptures;
B046C015V004	46	15	4	And that he was buried, and that he rose again the third day according to the scriptures:
B046C015V005	46	15	5	And that he appeared to Cephas, then to the twelve:
B046C015V006	46	15	6	After that, he appeared to more than five hundred brethren at once; of whom the greater part are still alive, though some have fallen asleep.
B046C015V007	46	15	7	After that, he appeared to James; then to all the apostles.
B046C015V008	46	15	8	And last of all he appeared to me also, as to one untimely born.
B046C015V009	46	15	9	For I am the least of the apostles, and am not worthy to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the church of God.
B046C015V010	46	15	10	But by the grace of God I am what I am: and his grace which was bestowed upon me was not in vain; but I laboured more abundantly than all of them: yet not I, but the grace of God which was with me.
B046C015V011	46	15	11	Therefore, whether it was I or they, this we preach, and this you believed.
B046C015V012	46	15	12	Now if Christ is preached, that he rose from the dead, how is it that some among you say that there is no resurrection from the dead?
B046C015V013	46	15	13	But if there is no resurrection of the dead, then Christ has not risen:
B046C015V014	46	15	14	And if Christ has not risen, then our preaching is in vain, and your faith is also in vain.
B046C015V015	46	15	15	Yea, and we are found to be false witnesses of God; because we have testified of God that he raised up Christ, whom he has raised not up, if it is true that the dead do not rise.
B046C015V016	46	15	16	For if the dead are not raised, then Christ has not been raised:
B046C015V017	46	15	17	And if Christ has not been raised, your faith is in vain; you are still in your sins.
B046C015V018	46	15	18	Then those also who have fallen asleep in Christ have perished.
B046C015V019	46	15	19	If for this life only we have hope in Christ, we are of all men most miserable.
B046C015V020	46	15	20	But Christ has indeed been raised from the dead, the first-fruits of those who sleep.
B046C015V021	46	15	21	For since by man came death, by man also came the resurrection of the dead.
B046C015V022	46	15	22	For just as in Adam all die, even so in Christ shall all be made alive.
B046C015V023	46	15	23	But every man in his own order: Christ the first-fruits; afterward those who are Christ's at his coming.
B046C015V024	46	15	24	Then comes the end, when he delivers up the kingdom to God the Father; after he has destroyed all rule and all authority and power.
B046C015V025	46	15	25	For he must reign, until he has put all enemies under his feet.
B046C015V026	46	15	26	The last enemy that shall be destroyed is death.
B046C015V027	46	15	27	For he has put all things under his feet. But when he says all things are put under him, it is clear that he himself is excepted, who put all things under him.
B046C015V028	46	15	28	And when all things shall be subjected to him, then shall the Son himself be subject to him who put all things under him, that God may be all in all.
B046C015V029	46	15	29	Otherwise, what shall they do who are baptized for the dead, if the dead are not raised at all? why then are they baptized for the dead?
B046C015V030	46	15	30	And why do we stand in jeopardy every hour?
B046C015V031	46	15	31	I assure you, just as I rejoice in you through Christ Jesus our Lord: I die daily.
B046C015V032	46	15	32	If for merely human reasons I fought beasts in Ephesus, what advantage is that to me, if the dead are not raised? let us eat and drink; for tomorrow we die.
B046C015V033	46	15	33	Do not be deceived: bad company corrupts good morals.
B046C015V034	46	15	34	Awaken to sobriety, and do not sin; for some do not have the knowledge of God: I speak this to your shame.
B046C015V035	46	15	35	But some will say, How are the dead raised up? and with what kind of body will they come?
B046C015V036	46	15	36	You fool, that which you sow does not come to life, unless it dies:
B046C015V037	46	15	37	And that which you sow is not the body that shall be, but a bare seed, perhaps of wheat, or of some other grain:
B046C015V038	46	15	38	But God gives it a body as he has determined, and to every kind of seed its own body.
B046C015V039	46	15	39	All flesh is not the same flesh: but there is one flesh of men, another flesh of beasts, another of fish, and another of birds.
B046C015V040	46	15	40	There are also celestial bodies, and terrestrial bodies: but the glory of the celestial is of one kind, and the glory of the terrestrial is of another.
B046C015V041	46	15	41	There is one glory of the sun, and another glory of the moon, and another glory of the stars: for star differs from star in glory.
B046C015V042	46	15	42	So also is the resurrection of the dead. It is sown perishable; it is raised imperishable:
B046C015V043	46	15	43	It is sown in dishonour; it is raised in glory: it is sown in weakness; it is raised in power:
B046C015V044	46	15	44	It is sown a natural body; it is raised a spiritual body. If there is a natural body, there is also a spiritual body.
B046C015V045	46	15	45	And so it is written, The first man, Adam, was made a living being; the last Adam, a life-giving spirit.
B046C015V046	46	15	46	Yet, it is not that which is spiritual that is first, but that which is natural; and afterward that which is spiritual.
B046C015V047	46	15	47	The first man was of the earth, made of dust: the second man is from heaven.
B046C015V048	46	15	48	As was the man of dust, so it is with those who are of dust: and as is the man of heaven, so it is with those who are of heaven.
B046C015V049	46	15	49	And as we have borne the image of the man of dust, we shall also bear the image of the man of heaven.
B046C015V050	46	15	50	Now this I say, brethren, that flesh and blood cannot inherit the kingdom of God; nor does the perishable inherit the imperishable.
B046C015V051	46	15	51	Behold, I tell you a mystery; We shall not all sleep, but we shall all be changed,
B046C015V052	46	15	52	In a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet: for the trumpet shall sound, and the dead shall be raised imperishable, and we shall be changed.
B046C015V053	46	15	53	For the perishable must put on the imperishable, and the mortal must put on immortality.
B046C015V054	46	15	54	When the perishable has put on the imperishable, and the mortal has put on immortality, then shall be brought to pass the saying that is written, Death is swallowed up in victory.
B046C015V055	46	15	55	O death, where is your sting? O grave, where is your victory?
B046C015V056	46	15	56	The sting of death is sin; and the power of sin is the law.
B046C015V057	46	15	57	But thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ.
B046C015V058	46	15	58	Therefore, my beloved brethren, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the work of the Lord, knowing that your labour is not in vain in the Lord.
B046C016V001	46	16	1	Now concerning the collection for the saints, as I have directed the churches of Galatia, so you do also.
B046C016V002	46	16	2	Upon the first day of the week let every one of you lay aside and save something, as he has prospered, that there need be no collections when I come.
B046C016V003	46	16	3	And when I come, whomever you shall approve I will send with letters, to take your gift to Jerusalem.
B046C016V004	46	16	4	And if it seems fitting that I go also, they shall go with me.
B046C016V005	46	16	5	Now I will come to you, after I pass through Macedonia: for I intend to pass through Macedonia;
B046C016V006	46	16	6	And it may be that I will stay with you a while, or even spend the winter, that you may speed me on my journey, wherever I go.
B046C016V007	46	16	7	For I do not want to see you now just in passing; but I hope to stay some time with you, if the Lord permits.
B046C016V008	46	16	8	But I will stay at Ephesus until Pentecost,
B046C016V009	46	16	9	For a wide door for effectual work has opened to me, and there are many adversaries.
B046C016V010	46	16	10	Now if Timothy comes, see that he has no cause for fear while he is with you: for he is doing the work of the Lord, as I am.
B046C016V011	46	16	11	Therefore, let no man despise him: but send him forth in peace, that he may come to me: for I am expecting him with the brethren.
B046C016V012	46	16	12	Regarding our brother Apollos, I strongly urged him to go to you with the brethren: but it was not at all his desire to go at this time; but he will come when he has the opportunity.
B046C016V013	46	16	13	Be watchful, stand fast in the faith, act like men, be strong.
B046C016V014	46	16	14	Let all that you do be done in love.
B046C016V015	46	16	15	I urge you, brethren, (you know that those of the house of Stephanas were the first-fruits of Achaia, and that they have devoted themselves to serving the saints,)
B046C016V016	46	16	16	That you submit yourselves to such as these, and to everyone who helps in the work, and labours earnestly.
B046C016V017	46	16	17	I am glad that Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus have come: for that which was lacking from you they have supplied.
B046C016V018	46	16	18	For they have refreshed my spirit and yours: therefore acknowledge such men.
B046C016V019	46	16	19	The churches of Asia greet you. Aquila and Prisca greet you warmly in the Lord, along with the church that is in their house.
B046C016V020	46	16	20	All the brethren greet you. Greet one another with a holy kiss.
B046C016V021	46	16	21	I, Paul, write this greeting with my own hand.
B046C016V022	46	16	22	If any man does not love the Lord, let him be accursed. Our Lord, come.
B046C016V023	46	16	23	The grace of our Lord Jesus be with you.
B046C016V024	46	16	24	My love be with you all in Christ Jesus. Amen.
B047C001V001	47	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, and Timothy our brother, to the church of God which is at Corinth, with all the saints who are in all Achaia:
B047C001V002	47	1	2	Grace to you and peace from God our Father, and from the Lord Jesus Christ.
B047C001V003	47	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of mercies, and the God of all comfort;
B047C001V004	47	1	4	Who comforts us in all our troubles, that we may be able to comfort those who are in any trouble with the comfort with which we ourselves are comforted by God.
B047C001V005	47	1	5	For as we abundantly share in the sufferings of Christ, so through Christ we also abundantly share in comfort.
B047C001V006	47	1	6	But if we are afflicted, it is for your comfort and salvation; and if we are comforted, it is for your comfort, which works in you when you patiently endure the same sufferings which we suffer.
B047C001V007	47	1	7	And our hope for you is steadfast, knowing, that as you are partakers of our sufferings, so you also partake of our comfort.
B047C001V008	47	1	8	For we would not have you ignorant of our trouble, brethren, which came to us in Asia, that we were pressed down beyond measure, beyond our strength, so that we despaired even of life.
B047C001V009	47	1	9	Indeed, we had the sentence of death in ourselves, that we should not trust in ourselves, but in God who raises the dead:
B047C001V010	47	1	10	Who has delivered us from so deadly a peril, and who will deliver us: we trust in him, that he will deliver us again,
B047C001V011	47	1	11	As you help by praying for us. Then thanks will be given by many on our behalf for the favour bestowed upon us by the prayers of many.
B047C001V012	47	1	12	For our boast is in this: the testimony of our conscience, that in simplicity and godly sincerity, not with fleshly wisdom, but by the grace of God, we have conducted ourselves in the world, and still more toward you.
B047C001V013	47	1	13	For we write nothing to you, except what you can read and understand; and I trust you shall understand fully;
B047C001V014	47	1	14	Just as also you have understood us in part and recognized that you can be proud of us, even as we can be proud of you in the day of the Lord Jesus.
B047C001V015	47	1	15	And in this confidence I intended to come to you first, that you might benefit twice;
B047C001V016	47	1	16	I planned to visit you on my way to Macedonia, and again visit you when I returned from Macedonia, and to be helped by you on my way to Judaea.
B047C001V017	47	1	17	When I planned this, did I do it lightly? or the things that I plan, do I plan according to the flesh, that I should say yes, yes when I may mean no, no?
B047C001V018	47	1	18	But as God is true, our word to you was not yes and no.
B047C001V019	47	1	19	For the Son of God, Jesus Christ, who was preached among you by us, by myself and Silvanus and Timothy, was not yes and no, but in him is always yes.
B047C001V020	47	1	20	For as many as are the promises of God, in him they are yes. And so our Amen is through him, to the glory of God.
B047C001V021	47	1	21	Now he who establishes us with you in Christ, and has anointed us, is God;
B047C001V022	47	1	22	Who has also sealed us, and given us the Spirit in our hearts as a pledge.
B047C001V023	47	1	23	I call God as a witness upon my soul, that it was to spare you that I did not come to Corinth.
B047C001V024	47	1	24	Not that we lord it over your faith, but we work with you for your joy: for in your faith you stand firm.
B047C002V001	47	2	1	But I determined that I would not make another painful visit to you.
B047C002V002	47	2	2	For if I make you sorrowful, who will there be to make me glad, but the same one I made sorrowful?
B047C002V003	47	2	3	And I wrote this same thing to you, lest, when I came, I should have sorrow from those who ought to make me rejoice; for I had confidence in all of you, that my joy would be the joy of all of you.
B047C002V004	47	2	4	For I wrote to you out of much affliction and anguish of heart, with many tears; not that you should be grieved, but that you might know the abundant love which I have for you.
B047C002V005	47	2	5	But if anyone has caused grief, he has not grieved me, but to some degree, not to put it too severely, to all of you.
B047C002V006	47	2	6	Sufficient for such a man is this punishment, which was inflicted by the majority.
B047C002V007	47	2	7	So you ought rather to forgive him, and comfort him, lest perhaps he may be overwhelmed with excessive sorrow.
B047C002V008	47	2	8	Therefore I urge you, that you would reaffirm your love for him.
B047C002V009	47	2	9	For to this end I wrote, that I might test you and know whether you are obedient in all things.
B047C002V010	47	2	10	But whom you forgive anything, I forgive also: for what I have forgiven, if I have forgiven anything, was for your sakes in the presence of Christ;
B047C002V011	47	2	11	Lest Satan should take advantage of us: for we are not ignorant of his schemes.
B047C002V012	47	2	12	Now, when I came to Troas to preach Christ's gospel, a door was opened for me by the Lord,
B047C002V013	47	2	13	Yet I had no rest in my spirit, because I did not find Titus my brother: so I took leave of them, and I went from there into Macedonia.
B047C002V014	47	2	14	Now thanks be to God, who always leads us in triumph in Christ, and makes manifest through us the fragrance of the knowledge of him in every place.
B047C002V015	47	2	15	For we are an aroma of Christ to God, among those who are being saved, and among those who are perishing:
B047C002V016	47	2	16	To the one we are the aroma of death to death; and to the other the aroma of life to life. And who is equal to such a calling?
B047C002V017	47	2	17	For we are not as so many, who peddle the word of God: but as men of sincerity, as from God, we speak in Christ in the sight of God.
B047C003V001	47	3	1	Are we beginning to commend ourselves again? or do we need, as some others, letters of recommendation to you, or letters of recommendation from you?
B047C003V002	47	3	2	You are our letter, written on our hearts, known and read by all men:
B047C003V003	47	3	3	And you show that you are letters of Christ delivered by us, written not with ink, but with the Spirit of the living God; not on tablets of stone, but on tablets of human hearts.
B047C003V004	47	3	4	And such is the trust we have through Christ before God.
B047C003V005	47	3	5	Not that we are sufficient in ourselves to claim anything as coming from ourselves; but our sufficiency is from God;
B047C003V006	47	3	6	Who has also made us able ministers of a new covenant; not of the letter, but of the spirit: for the letter kills, but the spirit gives life.
B047C003V007	47	3	7	For if the ministry of death, written and engraved in stone, was glorious, so that the children of Israel could not steadfastly behold the face of Moses because of the glory of his countenance; and that glory fading:
B047C003V008	47	3	8	Shall not the ministry of the spirit be even more glorious?
B047C003V009	47	3	9	For if the ministry of condemnation had glory, far more does the ministry of righteousness exceed it in glory.
B047C003V010	47	3	10	For even that which was glorious no longer has glory, because of the glory that surpasses it.
B047C003V011	47	3	11	For if that which has faded away came with glory, how much more glorious is that which remains.
B047C003V012	47	3	12	Seeing then that we have such a hope, we use great boldness of speech:
B047C003V013	47	3	13	Not as Moses, who put a veil over his face, so the sons of Israel could not gaze upon that which was fading.
B047C003V014	47	3	14	But their minds were hardened: for to this day the same veil remains unlifted at the reading of the old covenant; because it is only removed through Christ.
B047C003V015	47	3	15	But even to this day, when Moses is read, the veil is upon their hearts.
B047C003V016	47	3	16	But whenever a man shall turn to the Lord, the veil shall be taken away.
B047C003V017	47	3	17	Now the Lord is the Spirit: and where the Spirit of the Lord is, there is liberty.
B047C003V018	47	3	18	But we all, with unveiled faces beholding as in a mirror the glory of the Lord, are changed into that same image, from glory to glory, and this is from the Lord, the Spirit.
B047C004V001	47	4	1	Therefore, since we have this ministry by God's mercy, we do not loose heart;
B047C004V002	47	4	2	But we have renounced the hidden, shameful things, and do not walk in craftiness, nor handle the word of God deceitfully; but by the manifestation of the truth we commend ourselves to every man's conscience in the sight of God.
B047C004V003	47	4	3	But if our gospel is veiled, it is veiled to those who are perishing.
B047C004V004	47	4	4	For the god of this world has blinded the minds of those who do not believe, lest they should see the light of the glorious gospel of Christ, who is the image of God.
B047C004V005	47	4	5	For we do not preach ourselves, but Christ Jesus as Lord; and ourselves as your servants for Jesus' sake.
B047C004V006	47	4	6	For God, who commanded the light to shine out of darkness, has shone in our hearts, to give the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Christ.
B047C004V007	47	4	7	But we have this treasure in earthen vessels, that the transcendent power may be shown to be from God, and not from us.
B047C004V008	47	4	8	We are troubled on every side, yet not crushed; we are perplexed, but not in despair;
B047C004V009	47	4	9	Persecuted, but not forsaken; struck down, but not destroyed;
B047C004V010	47	4	10	Always carrying about in our body the dying of Jesus, that the life of Jesus might also be made manifest in our body.
B047C004V011	47	4	11	For we who live are always being delivered over to death for Jesus' sake, that the life of Jesus might also be made manifest in our mortal flesh.
B047C004V012	47	4	12	So then death works in us, but life in you.
B047C004V013	47	4	13	As it is written, I believed, and therefore I have spoken; so we, with the same spirit of faith, also believe, and therefore speak;
B047C004V014	47	4	14	Knowing that he who raised up the Lord Jesus shall also raise us up with Jesus, and shall present us with you in his presence.
B047C004V015	47	4	15	For all things are for your sakes, that as grace extends to more and more people, it might cause thanksgiving to abound, to the glory of God.
B047C004V016	47	4	16	For this reason we do not loose heart; but though our outer man perish, yet the inner man is renewed day by day.
B047C004V017	47	4	17	For our light affliction, which is but for a moment, prepares for us an incomparable and eternal weight of glory;
B047C004V018	47	4	18	So we do not look at the things which are seen, but at the things which are not seen: for the things which are seen are temporal; but the things which are not seen are eternal.
B047C005V001	47	5	1	For we know that if the earthly tent in which we live is destroyed, we have a building from God, a house not made with hands, eternal in the heavens.
B047C005V002	47	5	2	For in this house we groan, earnestly desiring to be clothed with our dwelling which is from heaven:
B047C005V003	47	5	3	So that being clothed we shall not be found naked.
B047C005V004	47	5	4	For we who are in this tent groan, being burdened: not that we would be unclothed, but rather further clothed, that mortality might be swallowed up by life.
B047C005V005	47	5	5	Now he who has made us for this very thing is God, who has also given to us the Spirit as a pledge.
B047C005V006	47	5	6	Therefore, we are always confident, knowing that while we are at home in the body, we are absent from the Lord:
B047C005V007	47	5	7	(For we walk by faith, not by sight:)
B047C005V008	47	5	8	We are confident, and would rather be absent from the body, and present with the Lord.
B047C005V009	47	5	9	Therefore we labour, that whether at home or absent, we may please him.
B047C005V010	47	5	10	For we must all appear before the judgment seat of Christ; that every one may receive what is due him for the things done in the body, according to what he has done, whether good or bad.
B047C005V011	47	5	11	Therefore, knowing the fear of the Lord, we persuade men. But what we are is plain to God; and I also trust it is plain to your consciences.
B047C005V012	47	5	12	For we do not commend ourselves to you again, but give you occasion to be proud of us, that you may have something to answer those who take pride in appearance, and not in the heart.
B047C005V013	47	5	13	For if we are out of our minds, it is for God: or if we are in our right minds, it is for you.
B047C005V014	47	5	14	For the love of Christ controls us; because we are convinced that one died for all, therefore all died:
B047C005V015	47	5	15	And he died for all, that those who live should not henceforth live for themselves, but for him who died for them, and rose again.
B047C005V016	47	5	16	Therefore, we no longer regard man according to the flesh: though once we regarded Christ according to the flesh, yet now we regard him thus no longer.
B047C005V017	47	5	17	Therefore if any man is in Christ, he is a new creature: old things have passed away; behold, new things have come.
B047C005V018	47	5	18	And all these things are from God, who has reconciled us to himself through Jesus Christ, and has given to us the ministry of reconciliation;
B047C005V019	47	5	19	That is, that God was in Christ, reconciling the world to himself, not counting men's sins against them; and he has committed to us the word of reconciliation.
B047C005V020	47	5	20	Now then, we are ambassadors for Christ, as if God were making his appeal through us: we beg you on Christ's behalf, be reconciled to God.
B047C005V021	47	5	21	For our sakes he has made him to be sin, who knew no sin; that in him we might become the righteousness of God.
B047C006V001	47	6	1	We then, as workers together with him, urge you not to receive the grace of God in vain.
B047C006V002	47	6	2	(For he says, I have heard you at the acceptable time, and on the day of salvation I have helped you: behold, now is the acceptable time; behold, now is the day of salvation.)
B047C006V003	47	6	3	We give no offence in anything, that the ministry may not be discredited:
B047C006V004	47	6	4	But as the ministers of God we commend ourselves in all things; in much endurance, in afflictions, in hardships, in distress,
B047C006V005	47	6	5	In beatings, in imprisonments, in tumults, in labours, in sleeplessness, in hunger;
B047C006V006	47	6	6	By purity, by knowledge, by patience, by kindness, in the Holy Spirit, in unfeigned love,
B047C006V007	47	6	7	By the word of truth, by the power of God, by the weapons of righteousness in the right hand and in the left,
B047C006V008	47	6	8	In honour and dishonour, in evil report and good report: regarded as deceivers, and yet true;
B047C006V009	47	6	9	As unknown, and yet well known; as dying, yet, behold, we live; as chastened, and yet not killed;
B047C006V010	47	6	10	As sorrowful, yet always rejoicing; as poor, yet making many rich; as having nothing, and yet possessing all things.
B047C006V011	47	6	11	O Corinthians, we have spoken freely to you, our hearts are open wide.
B047C006V012	47	6	12	There is no restraint in our affection for you, but you are restrained in your affection for us.
B047C006V013	47	6	13	As a fair exchange, (I speak as to children,) widen your hearts also.
B047C006V014	47	6	14	Do not be unequally yoked with unbelievers: for what partnership does righteousness have with unrighteousness? and what fellowship has light with darkness?
B047C006V015	47	6	15	And what harmony has Christ with Belial? or what does he who believes have in common with an unbeliever?
B047C006V016	47	6	16	And what agreement has the temple of God with idols? for we are the temple of the living God; as God has said, I will live in them, and walk among them; and I will be their God, and they shall be my people.
B047C006V017	47	6	17	Therefore, come out from among them, and be separate, says the Lord, and do not touch the unclean thing; and I will welcome you,
B047C006V018	47	6	18	And will be a Father to you, and you shall be my sons and daughters, says the Lord Almighty.
B047C007V001	47	7	1	Therefore, having these promises, dearly beloved, let us cleanse ourselves from all filthiness of the flesh and spirit, perfecting holiness in the fear of God.
B047C007V002	47	7	2	Open your hearts to us; we have wronged no man, we have corrupted no man, we have defrauded no man.
B047C007V003	47	7	3	I do not speak this to condemn you: for I have said before, that you are in our hearts to die with you and to live with you.
B047C007V004	47	7	4	Great is my confidence in you, great is my pride in you: I am filled with comfort, I am exceedingly joyful in all our tribulation.
B047C007V005	47	7	5	For, when we had come into Macedonia, our flesh had no rest, but we were troubled on every side; fighting without, fears within.
B047C007V006	47	7	6	But God, who comforts those who are cast down, comforted us by the coming of Titus;
B047C007V007	47	7	7	And not by his coming only, but also by the comfort with which he was comforted in you, when he told us of your earnest desire, your mourning, your zeal for me; so that I rejoiced still more.
B047C007V008	47	7	8	For though I made you sorry with a letter, I do not regret it, though I did regret: for I perceive that the letter caused you sorrow, though only for a while.
B047C007V009	47	7	9	Now I rejoice, not that you were made sorrowful, but that your sorrow brought you to repentance: for you were made sorrowful in a godly manner, so that you suffered no harm from us.
B047C007V010	47	7	10	For godly sorrow produces repentance leading to salvation and leaves no regret: but the sorrow of the world produces death.
B047C007V011	47	7	11	For behold what earnestness this godly sorrow has produced in you, what eagerness to clear yourselves, what indignation, what fear, what longing, what zeal, what readiness to punish wrongdoing! In all things you have shown yourselves to be innocent in this matter.
B047C007V012	47	7	12	Therefore, though I wrote to you, I did not do it because of the one who committed the wrong, nor because of the one who suffered the wrong, but that your zeal for us might be revealed to you in the sight of God.
B047C007V013	47	7	13	Therefore we are comforted. And besides our comfort, we especially rejoiced at the joy of Titus, because his spirit was refreshed by you all.
B047C007V014	47	7	14	For if I have boasted at all to him about you, I was not put to shame; but as we spoke all things to you in truth, even so our boasting to Titus has proved true.
B047C007V015	47	7	15	And his inward affection abounds even more toward you, as he remembers the obedience of you all, how with fear and trembling you received him.
B047C007V016	47	7	16	I rejoice that in all things I have confidence in you.
B047C008V001	47	8	1	And now, brethren, we want you to know of the grace of God bestowed on the churches of Macedonia;
B047C008V002	47	8	2	For during a great test of affliction, the abundance of their joy and their deep poverty overflowed in a wealth of liberality.
B047C008V003	47	8	3	For I bear witness that they gave according to their ability, yea, and beyond their ability, and of their own accord;
B047C008V004	47	8	4	Begging us most insistently that we would allow them the privilege of taking part in this service to the saints.
B047C008V005	47	8	5	And this they did, not as we expected, but they first gave themselves to the Lord, and to us by the will of God.
B047C008V006	47	8	6	So we urged Titus, since he had already begun, that he would also finish this gracious work among you.
B047C008V007	47	8	7	Therefore, as you excel in everything, in faith, and utterance, and knowledge, and in all earnestness, and in your love for us, see that you excel in this gracious work as well.
B047C008V008	47	8	8	I do not speak this as a commandment, but to use the zeal of others to test the sincerity of your own love.
B047C008V009	47	8	9	For you know the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, that, though he was rich, yet for your sakes he became poor, that through his poverty you might become rich.
B047C008V010	47	8	10	And here I give my advice about what is best for you: a year ago you were the first not only to give, but to desire to do so.
B047C008V011	47	8	11	Therefore, complete the doing of it; that as there was a readiness in desiring it, so there may also be a completion of it, according to your means.
B047C008V012	47	8	12	For if there is first a willing mind, it is acceptable, according to what a man has, and not according to that he does not have.
B047C008V013	47	8	13	I do not intend that other men be eased, and you burdened,
B047C008V014	47	8	14	But for there to be equality; at this time your abundance may be a supply for their want, that their abundance may also be a supply for your want: that there may be equality.
B047C008V015	47	8	15	As it is written, He who gathered much did not have too much; and he who gathered little had no lack.
B047C008V016	47	8	16	But thanks be to God, who put the same earnest care for you into the heart of Titus.
B047C008V017	47	8	17	For he not only accepted our appeal; but being very earnest, he is going to you of his own accord.
B047C008V018	47	8	18	And we have sent with him the brother whose fame in the gospel ministry has spread throughout all the churches;
B047C008V019	47	8	19	And not only that, but who was also chosen by the churches to travel with us in this gracious work, which is administered by us for the glory of the Lord himself, and to show our good will.
B047C008V020	47	8	20	We intend that that no man should blame us about this abundant gift which we are administering:
B047C008V021	47	8	21	For we take care to do what is honest, not only in the sight of the Lord, but also in the sight of men.
B047C008V022	47	8	22	And we have sent with them our brother, whom we have often tested and found to be diligent in many things, but now much more diligent, because of the great confidence which he has in you.
B047C008V023	47	8	23	As for Titus, he is my partner and fellow worker among you; and as for our brethren, they are messengers of the churches, a glory to Christ.
B047C008V024	47	8	24	Therefore show to them, before the churches, the proof of your love, and the reason for our boasting about you.
B047C009V001	47	9	1	Now regarding this ministry to the saints, it is superfluous for me to write to you:
B047C009V002	47	9	2	For I know your eagerness, of which I boast to the Macedonians, saying that you in Achaia were ready a year ago; and your zeal has stirred up most of them.
B047C009V003	47	9	3	But I have sent the brethren, lest our boasting about you in this matter should be in vain; that, as I said, you may be ready:
B047C009V004	47	9	4	Lest if any from Macedonia come with me, and find you unprepared, we (to say nothing of you) should be put to shame by this confidence.
B047C009V005	47	9	5	Therefore, I thought it necessary to urge these brethren, that they would go on ahead to you, and arrange beforehand your generous gift, which you promised, that it might be ready, as a willing gift, and not as one grudgingly given.
B047C009V006	47	9	6	Now this I say, He who sows sparingly shall also reap sparingly; and he who sows bountifully shall also reap bountifully.
B047C009V007	47	9	7	Every man must do as he has decided in his heart; not grudgingly, or under compulsion: for God loves a cheerful giver.
B047C009V008	47	9	8	And God is able to make all grace abound to you; that you, always having enough in all things, may abound in every good work.
B047C009V009	47	9	9	As it is written, He has scattered abroad; he has given to the poor: his righteousness endures forever.
B047C009V010	47	9	10	Now he who provides seed to the sower and bread for food, will supply and multiply your seed for sowing, and increase the fruits of your righteousness;
B047C009V011	47	9	11	You will be enriched in everything, so you can be generous, and through us your generosity will result in thanksgiving to God.
B047C009V012	47	9	12	For the performance of this service not only supplies the wants of the saints, but also overflows in many thanksgivings to God.
B047C009V013	47	9	13	Because of the proof given by this service, they will glorify God because of your obedience to the gospel of Christ, which you profess, and for your liberal contribution to them, and to all;
B047C009V014	47	9	14	And in their prayers, their hearts will go out to you because of the surpassing grace of God in you.
B047C009V015	47	9	15	Thanks be to God for his inexpressible gift.
B047C010V001	47	10	1	Now I, Paul, urge you by the meekness and gentleness of Christ, I who am meek in your presence, but bold when I am absent from you.
B047C010V002	47	10	2	I urge you, that when I am present I may not be bold with the confidence with which I expect to be bold against some, who think that we walk according to the flesh.
B047C010V003	47	10	3	For though we walk in the flesh, we do not wage war according to the flesh:
B047C010V004	47	10	4	For the weapons of our warfare are not of the flesh, but are mighty before God for the pulling down of strongholds.
B047C010V005	47	10	5	We cast down arguments, and every lofty thing that exalts itself against the knowledge of God, and bring every thought into captivity to the obedience of Christ;
B047C010V006	47	10	6	And we have a readiness to punish all disobedience, when your obedience is complete.
B047C010V007	47	10	7	Do you look on things according to their outward appearance? If any man trusts that he is Christ's, let him remind himself, that, as he is Christ's, so are we.
B047C010V008	47	10	8	For though I should boast somewhat freely of our authority, which the Lord has given us for building you up, and not for your destruction, I shall not be put to shame.
B047C010V009	47	10	9	I do not wish to seem to be frightening you by my letters.
B047C010V010	47	10	10	For his letters, they say, are weighty and powerful; but his bodily presence is weak, and his speech contemptible.
B047C010V011	47	10	11	Let such people realize this, that, the way we are in word by letters when we are absent, so we will also be in deeds when we are present.
B047C010V012	47	10	12	We do not dare to classify or compare ourselves with some who commend themselves: but in measuring themselves by themselves, and comparing themselves among themselves, they are not wise.
B047C010V013	47	10	13	But we will not boast of things without limit, but will keep within the field which God has assigned to us, a field which reaches even to you.
B047C010V014	47	10	14	For we do not stretch beyond our limit, as though we had not reached to you: for we were the first to come as far as to you with the gospel of Christ:
B047C010V015	47	10	15	We do not boast of things without limit, that is, of other men's labours; but we have hope, when your faith has increased, that our field among you shall be greatly enlarged,
B047C010V016	47	10	16	So we may preach the gospel in the regions beyond you, and not to boast of work already done in another man's field.
B047C010V017	47	10	17	But he who boasts, let him boast in the Lord.
B047C010V018	47	10	18	For it is not he who commends himself who is approved, but he whom the Lord commends.
B047C011V001	47	11	1	I wish you would bear with me a little in my folly: and indeed you are bearing with me.
B047C011V002	47	11	2	For I am jealous of you with a godly jealousy: for I have betrothed you to one husband, that I might present you to Christ as a pure virgin.
B047C011V003	47	11	3	But I fear, lest, as the serpent deceived Eve through his cunning, so your minds will be led astray from the simplicity that is in Christ.
B047C011V004	47	11	4	For if one comes and preaches another Jesus, whom we have not preached, or if you receive another spirit, which you have not received, or another gospel, which you have not accepted, you bear with him well enough.
B047C011V005	47	11	5	I consider that I am not in the least inferior to these superlative apostles.
B047C011V006	47	11	6	But though I am unskilled in speech, yet I am not in knowledge; we have made this plain to you in all things.
B047C011V007	47	11	7	Have I committed an offence by abasing myself that you might be exalted, because I have preached the gospel of God to you without cost?
B047C011V008	47	11	8	I robbed other churches, taking wages from them, to serve you.
B047C011V009	47	11	9	And when I was present with you, and in want, I burdened no man: for that which I lacked the brethren who came from Macedonia supplied: and in all things I have kept myself from being burdensome to you, and so I will continue to do.
B047C011V010	47	11	10	As the truth of Christ is in me, no man in the regions of Achaia shall stop me from this boasting.
B047C011V011	47	11	11	Why? because I do not love you? God knows I do.
B047C011V012	47	11	12	But what I do, that I will continue to do, that I may undermine the claim of those who desire opportunity to be regarded as our equals in that of which they boast.
B047C011V013	47	11	13	For such men are false apostles, deceitful workers, disguising themselves as apostles of Christ.
B047C011V014	47	11	14	And no wonder; for even Satan disguises himself as an angel of light.
B047C011V015	47	11	15	Therefore it is no surprise if his servants are also disguised as servants of righteousness; their end shall be according to their works.
B047C011V016	47	11	16	I say again, Let no man think me a fool; but if you do, receive me as a fool, that I too may boast a little.
B047C011V017	47	11	17	That which I am speaking, I do not speak with the Lord's authority, but, as it were, foolishly, in boastful confidence.
B047C011V018	47	11	18	Seeing that many boast according to the flesh, I will boast also.
B047C011V019	47	11	19	For you endure fools gladly, seeing you yourselves are so wise.
B047C011V020	47	11	20	For you bear it if a man brings you into bondage, if a man devours you, if a man takes advantage of you, if a man exalts himself, if a man strikes you on the face.
B047C011V021	47	11	21	To my shame, I must say, we were too weak to do that. Yet in whatever else anyone dares to boast, (I speak foolishly,) I also dare to boast.
B047C011V022	47	11	22	Are they Hebrews? so am I. Are they Israelites? so am I. Are they descendants of Abraham? so am I.
B047C011V023	47	11	23	Are they servants of Christ? (I speak as a fool) I am more so; in labours more abundant, in beatings beyond number, in prison more frequently, in danger of death often.
B047C011V024	47	11	24	From the Jews I five times received forty lashes less one.
B047C011V025	47	11	25	Thrice I was beaten with rods, once I was stoned, thrice I suffered shipwreck, a night and a day I have spent in the deep;
B047C011V026	47	11	26	On frequent journeys, in perils from rivers, in perils from robbers, in perils from my own countrymen, in perils from the Gentiles, in perils in the city, in perils in the wilderness, in perils on the sea, in perils among false brethren;
B047C011V027	47	11	27	In toil and hardship, in many sleepless nights, in hunger and thirst, often without food, in cold and nakedness.
B047C011V028	47	11	28	Beside those things that are external, there is upon me the daily pressure of concern for all the churches.
B047C011V029	47	11	29	Who is weak, and I am not weak? who is made to fall, and I do not burn inwardly?
B047C011V030	47	11	30	If I must boast, I will boast of things which show my weakness.
B047C011V031	47	11	31	The God and Father of our Lord Jesus, who is blessed forevermore, knows that I do not lie.
B047C011V032	47	11	32	In Damascus the governor, under Aretas the king, guarded the city of Damascus with a garrison in order to apprehend me:
B047C011V033	47	11	33	but through a window in the wall I was let down in a basket, and escaped his hands.
B047C012V001	47	12	1	Though it is not profitable for me to boast, I will go on to visions and revelations of the Lord.
B047C012V002	47	12	2	I knew a man in Christ who fourteen years ago, (whether in the body, I cannot tell; or whether out of the body, I cannot tell: God knows;) was caught up to the third heaven.
B047C012V003	47	12	3	And I know that this man, (whether in the body, or out of the body, I cannot tell: God knows;)
B047C012V004	47	12	4	Was caught up into paradise, and heard inexpressible words, which it is not lawful for a man to utter.
B047C012V005	47	12	5	Of such a man I will boast: yet of myself I will not boast, except of my weaknesses.
B047C012V006	47	12	6	If I should desire to boast, I shall not be a fool; for I will speak the truth: but I refrain, lest any man should think of me beyond that which he sees in me, or hears from me.
B047C012V007	47	12	7	And lest I should exalt myself beyond measure through the abundance of revelations, there was given to me a thorn in the flesh, a messenger from Satan to buffet me, lest I should be exalted beyond measure.
B047C012V008	47	12	8	I begged the Lord thrice, that this might depart from me.
B047C012V009	47	12	9	And he said to me, My grace is sufficient for you: for my strength is made perfect in weakness. Therefore, most gladly will I boast in my weaknesses, that the power of Christ may rest upon me.
B047C012V010	47	12	10	Therefore, for Christ's sake, I take pleasure in weaknesses, in insults, in hardships, in persecutions, in distresses: for when I am weak, then I am strong.
B047C012V011	47	12	11	I have made a fool of myself; you have compelled me: for I ought to have been commended by you: for in nothing am I behind these superlative apostles, though I am nothing.
B047C012V012	47	12	12	The signs of a true apostle were performed among you with all patience, by signs, and wonders, and miracles.
B047C012V013	47	12	13	For in what way were you less favoured than other churches, except that I myself was not burdensome to you? forgive me this wrong.
B047C012V014	47	12	14	Behold, for the third time I am ready to come to you; and I will not be burdensome to you: for I do not seek what is yours, but you: for the children ought not to save up for the parents, but the parents for the children.
B047C012V015	47	12	15	And I will very gladly spend and be spent for your souls. If I love you more abundantly, am I to be loved the less?
B047C012V016	47	12	16	But be that as it may, I did not burden you: nevertheless, being crafty, I caught you with guile.
B047C012V017	47	12	17	Did I take advantage of you by any of those whom I sent to you?
B047C012V018	47	12	18	I urged Titus to go, and with him I sent the brother. Did Titus take advantage of you? did we not act in the same spirit and walk in the same steps?
B047C012V019	47	12	19	All this time have you been thinking that we are defending ourselves to you? we speak before God in Christ: but we do all things, dearly beloved, for your strengthening.
B047C012V020	47	12	20	For I fear that when I come, I shall not find you as I wish, and you shall not find me to be as you wish; lest perhaps there may be quarreling, jealousy, outbursts of wrath, rivalries, slander, gossip, conceit, disorder:
B047C012V021	47	12	21	And I fear that, when I come again, my God may humble me before you, and I shall mourn over many who have sinned and have not repented of the impurity and sexual sin and licentiousness which they have committed.
B047C013V001	47	13	1	This is the third time I am coming to you. By the mouths of two or three witnesses must every matter be established.
B047C013V002	47	13	2	The second time I was with you I warned those who have sinned in the past; and now, being absent, I warn them again, and all the others, that, if I come again, I will not spare them,
B047C013V003	47	13	3	Since you seek a proof that Christ is speaking through me. He is not weak in dealing with you, but is mighty among you.
B047C013V004	47	13	4	For though he was crucified in weakness, yet he lives by the power of God. For we also are weak in him, but we shall live with him by the power of God to serve you.
B047C013V005	47	13	5	Examine yourselves to see whether you are in the faith; test your own selves. Do you not realize that Jesus Christ is in you, unless indeed you fail the test?
B047C013V006	47	13	6	But I trust that you shall know that we have not failed the test.
B047C013V007	47	13	7	Now I pray to God that you do no wrong; not that we should appear approved, but that you should do that which is right, even if we appear to be failures.
B047C013V008	47	13	8	For we can do nothing against the truth, but only for the truth.
B047C013V009	47	13	9	For we are glad when we are weak, and you are strong: and this is our prayer, for your perfection.
B047C013V010	47	13	10	Therefore I write these things while absent, that when present I need not be severe in using the power which the Lord has given me for building up, and not for tearing down.
B047C013V011	47	13	11	Finally, brethren, farewell. Aim to be perfect, be of good comfort, be of one mind, live in peace; and the God of love and peace shall be with you.
B047C013V012	47	13	12	Greet one another with a holy kiss.
B047C013V013	47	13	13	All the saints greet you.
B047C013V014	47	13	14	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ, and the love of God, and the fellowship of the Holy Spirit, be with you all.
B048C001V001	48	1	1	Paul, an apostle, (not sent from men, nor by man, but by Jesus Christ, and God the Father, who raised him from the dead;)
B048C001V002	48	1	2	And all the brethren who are with me, to the churches of Galatia:
B048C001V003	48	1	3	Grace to you and peace from God the Father, and our Lord Jesus Christ,
B048C001V004	48	1	4	Who gave himself for our sins, that he might deliver us from this present evil world, according to the will of our God and Father:
B048C001V005	48	1	5	To whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.
B048C001V006	48	1	6	I marvel that you are so quickly deserting him who called you by the grace of Christ, for another gospel:
B048C001V007	48	1	7	Which is not truly another; but there are some who trouble you, and would pervert the gospel of Christ.
B048C001V008	48	1	8	But even if we, or an angel from heaven, should preach any other gospel to you than that which we have preached to you, let him be eternally accursed.
B048C001V009	48	1	9	As we said before, so now I say again, If any man preach any other gospel to you than that which you have received, let him be eternally accursed.
B048C001V010	48	1	10	Do I now seek the favour of men, or of God? or do I seek to please men? if I were still pleasing men, I should not be a servant of Christ.
B048C001V011	48	1	11	But I want you to know, brethren, that the gospel which I preached is not from man.
B048C001V012	48	1	12	For I neither received it from man, nor was I taught it, but it came by revelation from Jesus Christ.
B048C001V013	48	1	13	For you have heard of my former life in Judaism, that beyond measure I persecuted the church of God, and tried to destroy it:
B048C001V014	48	1	14	And advanced in Judaism beyond many Jews of my age, being more exceedingly zealous for the traditions of my fathers.
B048C001V015	48	1	15	But when it pleased God, who set me apart from my mother's womb, and called me by his grace,
B048C001V016	48	1	16	To reveal his Son in me, that I might preach him among the Gentiles; I did not immediately confer with flesh and blood:
B048C001V017	48	1	17	Nor did I go up to Jerusalem to those who were apostles before me; but I went into Arabia, and returned again to Damascus.
B048C001V018	48	1	18	Then, after three years, I went up to Jerusalem to see Peter, and stayed with him fifteen days.
B048C001V019	48	1	19	But of the other apostles I saw none, except James, the Lord's brother.
B048C001V020	48	1	20	(Now these things which I am writing to you, behold, before God, I do not lie.)
B048C001V021	48	1	21	Afterwards I went into the regions of Syria and Cilicia;
B048C001V022	48	1	22	And was still unknown by face to the churches of Christ in Judaea:
B048C001V023	48	1	23	But they had only heard, That he who persecuted us in times past now preaches the faith which he once tried to destroy.
B048C001V024	48	1	24	And they glorified God because of me.
B048C002V001	48	2	1	Then, fourteen years later, I went up again to Jerusalem with Barnabas, and took Titus with me also.
B048C002V002	48	2	2	I went up because of a revelation, and communicated to them the gospel which I preach among the Gentiles, but privately to those who were of repute, lest by any means I should be running, or had run, in vain.
B048C002V003	48	2	3	But not even Titus, who was with me, though a Greek, was compelled to be circumcised.
B048C002V004	48	2	4	That arose because of false brethren who secretly slipped in to spy out the liberty which we have in Christ Jesus, that they might bring us into bondage.
B048C002V005	48	2	5	We did not yield in subjection to them, not even for a hour; that the truth of the gospel might remain with you.
B048C002V006	48	2	6	But those who seemed to be important, (what they were makes no difference to me: God shows no partiality:) well, those who seemed to be important added nothing to me:
B048C002V007	48	2	7	But instead, when they saw that I had been entrusted with the gospel to the uncircumcised, as Peter had been entrusted with the gospel to the circumcised;
B048C002V008	48	2	8	(For he who worked effectively in Peter in his apostleship to the circumcised, also worked in me for the Gentiles:)
B048C002V009	48	2	9	And when James, Cephas, and John, who were reputed to be pillars, perceived the grace that was given to me, they gave to me and Barnabas the right hand of fellowship; that we should go to the Gentiles, and they to the circumcised.
B048C002V010	48	2	10	They only asked that we would remember the poor; the very thing which I also was eager to do.
B048C002V011	48	2	11	But when Peter came to Antioch, I opposed him to his face, because he stood condemned.
B048C002V012	48	2	12	For before certain men came from James, he ate with the Gentiles: but when they had come, he withdrew and separated himself, fearing those who were of the circumcision.
B048C002V013	48	2	13	And the other Jews joined him in insincerity; so that even Barnabas was carried away with their insincerity.
B048C002V014	48	2	14	But when I saw that they did not walk uprightly according to the truth of the gospel, I said to Cephas before them all, If you, being a Jew, live like the Gentiles, and not like the Jews, why do you compel the Gentiles to live like the Jews?
B048C002V015	48	2	15	We who are Jews by nature, and not Gentile sinners,
B048C002V016	48	2	16	Knowing that a man is not justified by the works of the law, but by faith in Jesus Christ, even we have believed in Jesus Christ, that we might be justified by faith in Christ, and not by the works of the law: for by the works of the law shall no flesh be justified.
B048C002V017	48	2	17	But if, while seeking to be justified by Christ, we ourselves are also shown to be sinners, is Christ therefore a minister of sin? God forbid.
B048C002V018	48	2	18	For if I build again the things which I destroyed, I prove myself to be a transgressor.
B048C002V019	48	2	19	For through the law I am dead to the law, that I might live to God.
B048C002V020	48	2	20	I have been crucified with Christ: nevertheless I live; yet not I, but Christ lives in me: and the life which I now live in the flesh I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved me, and gave himself for me.
B048C002V021	48	2	21	I do not nullify the grace of God: for if righteousness comes by the law, then Christ died in vain.
B048C003V001	48	3	1	O foolish Galatians, who has bewitched you, before whose eyes Jesus Christ has been publicly portrayed as crucified?
B048C003V002	48	3	2	This one thing I would learn from you, Did you receive the Spirit by works of the law, or by hearing with faith?
B048C003V003	48	3	3	Are you so foolish? having begun in the Spirit, are you now being made perfect by the flesh?
B048C003V004	48	3	4	Have you suffered so many things in vain? if it really was in vain.
B048C003V005	48	3	5	He who provides to you the Spirit, and works miracles among you, does he do it by the works of the law, or by hearing with faith?
B048C003V006	48	3	6	Thus Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness.
B048C003V007	48	3	7	Therefore, understand that those who are of faith are the children of Abraham.
B048C003V008	48	3	8	And the scripture, foreseeing that God would justify the Gentiles through faith, preached the gospel to Abraham beforehand, saying, In you shall all nations be blessed.
B048C003V009	48	3	9	So then, those who are of faith are blessed with Abraham, the man of faith.
B048C003V010	48	3	10	For all who depend on the works of the law are under a curse: for it is written, Cursed is everyone who does not continue to do all things which are written in the book of the law.
B048C003V011	48	3	11	But it is evident that no man is justified by the law in the sight of God, for: The just shall live by faith.
B048C003V012	48	3	12	But the law does not rest on faith: rather, The man who does these things shall live by them.
B048C003V013	48	3	13	Christ has redeemed us from the curse of the law, having been made a curse for us: for it is written, Cursed is every one who hangs on a tree.
B048C003V014	48	3	14	He redeemed us so that the blessing of Abraham might come upon the Gentiles through Jesus Christ; that we might receive the promise of the Spirit through faith.
B048C003V015	48	3	15	Brethren, I speak after the manner of men; Though it is only a man's covenant, yet when it is ratified, no man annuls or adds to it.
B048C003V016	48	3	16	Now to Abraham and his seed were the promises made. He does not say, And to seeds, as to many; but to one, And to your seed, which is Christ.
B048C003V017	48	3	17	And this is what I mean, that the law, which came four hundred and thirty years later, cannot annul the covenant which was previously ratified by God, and thus make the promise void.
B048C003V018	48	3	18	For if the inheritance is based on the law, then it is no longer based on a promise: but God gave it to Abraham by a promise.
B048C003V019	48	3	19	Then what purpose does the law serve? It was added because of transgressions, until the seed should come to whom the promise was made. It was ordained by angels through the hand of a mediator.
B048C003V020	48	3	20	Now a mediator is not for one party only, but God is one.
B048C003V021	48	3	21	Is the law then against the promises of God? Absolutely not: for if there had been a law given which could impart life, then righteousness truly would have been through the law.
B048C003V022	48	3	22	But the scripture has declared all to be prisoners of sin, so that the promise, given on the basis of faith in Jesus Christ, might be given to those who believe.
B048C003V023	48	3	23	But before faith came, we were kept under the law, shut up until faith should be revealed.
B048C003V024	48	3	24	Therefore, the law was our tutor to bring us to Christ, that we might be justified by faith.
B048C003V025	48	3	25	But now that faith has come, we are no longer under a tutor.
B048C003V026	48	3	26	For you are all sons of God by faith in Christ Jesus.
B048C003V027	48	3	27	For as many of you as have been baptized into Christ have put on Christ.
B048C003V028	48	3	28	There is neither Jew nor Greek, there is neither slave nor free, there is neither male nor female: for you are all one in Christ Jesus.
B048C003V029	48	3	29	And if you are Christ's, then you are Abraham's seed, and heirs according to the promise.
B048C004V001	48	4	1	Now I say, That the heir, as long as he is a child, does not differ at all from a servant, though he is owner of all;
B048C004V002	48	4	2	But is under guardians and trustees until the time appointed by the father.
B048C004V003	48	4	3	So we, when we were children, were in bondage to the elementary principles of the world:
B048C004V004	48	4	4	But when the time had fully come, God sent forth his Son, born of a woman, born under the law,
B048C004V005	48	4	5	To redeem those who were under the law, that we might be adopted as sons.
B048C004V006	48	4	6	And because you are sons, God has sent forth the Spirit of his Son into your hearts, crying, Abba, Father.
B048C004V007	48	4	7	Therefore, you are no longer a slave, but a son; and if a son, then an heir through God.
B048C004V008	48	4	8	But previously, when you did not know God, you were slaves to those who by nature are not gods.
B048C004V009	48	4	9	But now that you have come to know God, or rather, to be known by God, how is it that you turn back again to those weak and beggarly principles, to which you again desire to be in bondage?
B048C004V010	48	4	10	You observe days, and months, and seasons, and years.
B048C004V011	48	4	11	I am afraid for you, lest I have bestowed labour upon you in vain.
B048C004V012	48	4	12	Brethren, I urge you, be as I am; for I became as you are: you have not injured me at all.
B048C004V013	48	4	13	You know it was because of infirmity of the flesh that I first preached the gospel to you.
B048C004V014	48	4	14	And though my fleshly condition was a trial for you, you did not despise or reject me; but received me as an angel from God, as Christ Jesus himself.
B048C004V015	48	4	15	Where then is the blessed joy you had? for I bear you witness, that, if possible, you would have plucked out your own eyes, and have given them to me.
B048C004V016	48	4	16	Have I therefore become your enemy, because I tell you the truth?
B048C004V017	48	4	17	They zealously seek you, but not for good; they would alienate you, that you might seek them.
B048C004V018	48	4	18	But it is always good to be zealously sought after in a good way, and not only when I am present with you.
B048C004V019	48	4	19	My little children, with whom I again suffer birth pains until Christ is formed in you,
B048C004V020	48	4	20	I desire to be present with you now, and to change my tone; for I am perplexed about you.
B048C004V021	48	4	21	Tell me, you who desire to be under the law, do you not hear the law?
B048C004V022	48	4	22	For it is written that Abraham had two sons, one by a slave woman, the other by a free woman.
B048C004V023	48	4	23	He who was born by the slave woman was born according to the flesh; but the son born by the free woman was through the promise.
B048C004V024	48	4	24	These things are an allegory: for these women are the two covenants; the one from mount Sinai, who bears children into bondage; this is Hagar.
B048C004V025	48	4	25	For this Hagar is mount Sinai in Arabia, and corresponds to the present Jerusalem, which is in bondage with her children.
B048C004V026	48	4	26	But the Jerusalem which is above is free, and she is our mother.
B048C004V027	48	4	27	For it is written, Rejoice, you who are barren and bear no children; break forth and shout, you who are not in the pangs of birth: for the desolate woman has many more children than she who has a husband.
B048C004V028	48	4	28	Now we, brethren, like Isaac, are the children of promise.
B048C004V029	48	4	29	But as it was then, he who was born according to the flesh persecuted him who was born according to the Spirit, so it is now.
B048C004V030	48	4	30	Nevertheless, what does the scripture say? Cast out the slave woman and her son: for the son of the slave woman shall not be an heir with the son of the free woman.
B048C004V031	48	4	31	So then, brethren, we are not children of the slave woman, but of the free woman.
B048C005V001	48	5	1	It is for liberty that Christ has made us free. Therefore, stand fast and do not submit again to a yoke of slavery.
B048C005V002	48	5	2	Behold, I, Paul say to you, that if you are circumcised, Christ shall be of no value to you.
B048C005V003	48	5	3	For I testify again to every man who receives circumcision, that he is obliged to obey the whole law.
B048C005V004	48	5	4	You who would be justified by the law, you have been alienated from Christ; you have fallen from grace.
B048C005V005	48	5	5	For we through the Spirit, by faith, wait for the hope of righteousness.
B048C005V006	48	5	6	For in Jesus Christ neither circumcision nor uncircumcision counts for anything; but faith which works through love.
B048C005V007	48	5	7	You ran well; who hindered you, that you should not obey the truth?
B048C005V008	48	5	8	This persuasion does not come from him who calls you.
B048C005V009	48	5	9	A little leaven leavens the whole lump.
B048C005V010	48	5	10	I have confidence in you through the Lord, that you will take no other view: but he who troubles you shall bear his judgment, whoever he may be.
B048C005V011	48	5	11	And if I, brethren, still preach circumcision, why do I yet suffer persecution? In that case the stumbling block of the cross has been removed.
B048C005V012	48	5	12	I wish those who trouble you would even emasculate themselves.
B048C005V013	48	5	13	For, brethren, you have been called to liberty; only do not use your liberty as an opportunity for the flesh, but in love serve one another.
B048C005V014	48	5	14	For all the law is fulfilled in one command; You shall love your neighbour as yourself.
B048C005V015	48	5	15	But if you bite and devour one another, take heed that you are not consumed by one another.
B048C005V016	48	5	16	This I say, Walk in the Spirit, and you shall not fulfill the desires of the flesh.
B048C005V017	48	5	17	For the desires of the flesh are against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh: and these are in conflict with one another: so that you cannot do the things that you wish.
B048C005V018	48	5	18	But if you are led by the Spirit, you are not under the law.
B048C005V019	48	5	19	Now the works of the flesh are obvious; they are; sexual immorality, impurity, licentiousness,
B048C005V020	48	5	20	Idolatry, witchcraft, hatred, strife, jealousy, fits of rage, selfishness, dissensions, factions,
B048C005V021	48	5	21	Envy, drunkenness, orgies, and the like: of which I forewarn you, as I have also warned you in the past, that those who do such things shall not inherit the kingdom of God.
B048C005V022	48	5	22	But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness,
B048C005V023	48	5	23	Gentleness, self-control: against such things there is no law.
B048C005V024	48	5	24	And those who are Christ's have crucified the flesh with its passions and desires.
B048C005V025	48	5	25	If we live by the Spirit, let us also walk by the Spirit.
B048C005V026	48	5	26	Let us not become conceited, provoking and envying one another.
B048C006V001	48	6	1	Brethren, if a man is caught in a trespass, you who are spiritual, restore him in the spirit of gentleness; considering yourselves, lest you also be tempted.
B048C006V002	48	6	2	Bear one another's burdens, and so fulfill the law of Christ.
B048C006V003	48	6	3	For if a man thinks himself to be something, when he is nothing, he deceives himself.
B048C006V004	48	6	4	But let every man test his own work, and then he can take pride in himself, and not in comparison to another.
B048C006V005	48	6	5	For every man shall bear his own burden.
B048C006V006	48	6	6	Let him who is taught the word share all good things with him who teaches.
B048C006V007	48	6	7	Do not be deceived; God is not mocked: for whatever a man sows, that shall he also reap.
B048C006V008	48	6	8	For he who sows to his flesh shall from the flesh reap corruption; but he who sows to the Spirit shall from the Spirit reap eternal life.
B048C006V009	48	6	9	And let us not be weary in well-doing: for in due season we shall reap, if we do not loose heart.
B048C006V010	48	6	10	Therefore, as we have opportunity, let us do good to all men, especially to those who are of the household of faith.
B048C006V011	48	6	11	See what large letters I make as I write to you with my own hand.
B048C006V012	48	6	12	Those who desire to make a good showing in the flesh would compel you to be circumcised; but only to avoid suffering persecution for the cross of Christ.
B048C006V013	48	6	13	For not even those who are circumcised keep the law; but they desire to have you circumcised, that they may glory in your flesh.
B048C006V014	48	6	14	But God forbid that I should glory, except in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, by whom the world is crucified to me, and I to the world.
B048C006V015	48	6	15	For neither circumcision nor uncircumcision counts for anything, but only a new creation.
B048C006V016	48	6	16	And as many as walk according to this rule, peace be upon them, and mercy, and upon the Israel of God.
B048C006V017	48	6	17	Henceforth let no man trouble me: for I bear on my body the marks of the Lord Jesus.
B048C006V018	48	6	18	Brethren, the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Amen.
B049C001V001	49	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, to the saints who are at Ephesus, the faithful in Christ Jesus:
B049C001V002	49	1	2	Grace to you, and peace, from God our Father, and from the Lord Jesus Christ.
B049C001V003	49	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who has blessed us in Christ with all spiritual blessings in the heavenly places:
B049C001V004	49	1	4	Just as he has chosen us in him before the foundation of the world, that we should be holy and without blame before him. In love
B049C001V005	49	1	5	He predestined us to adoption as sons through Jesus Christ, according to his good pleasure and will,
B049C001V006	49	1	6	To the praise of his glorious grace, which he freely bestowed upon us in the beloved.
B049C001V007	49	1	7	In him we have redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of sins, according to the riches of his grace;
B049C001V008	49	1	8	Which he has lavished upon us in all wisdom and prudence;
B049C001V009	49	1	9	Having made known to us the mystery of his will, according to his good pleasure which he set forth in him:
B049C001V010	49	1	10	That in the fulness of time he might gather all things together under Christ, both things which are in heaven, and things which are on earth. In him
B049C001V011	49	1	11	We have also obtained an inheritance, being predestined according to the purpose of him who works all things after the counsel of his own will:
B049C001V012	49	1	12	That we who first trusted in Christ should live for the praise of his glory.
B049C001V013	49	1	13	In him you also, after you heard the word of truth, the gospel of your salvation: having also believed, you were sealed with the promised Holy Spirit,
B049C001V014	49	1	14	Who is the guarantee of our inheritance until the redemption of those who are God's possession, to the praise of his glory.
B049C001V015	49	1	15	Therefore, I also, after I heard of your faith in the Lord Jesus, and love for all the saints,
B049C001V016	49	1	16	Do not cease to give thanks for you, making mention of you in my prayers;
B049C001V017	49	1	17	That the God of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of glory, may give to you a spirit of wisdom and revelation in the knowledge of him:
B049C001V018	49	1	18	That the eyes of your heart may be enlightened; so you may know what is the hope of his calling, the riches of his glorious inheritance in the saints,
B049C001V019	49	1	19	And what is the incomparable greatness of his power toward us who believe. It is the working of his mighty power,
B049C001V020	49	1	20	Which he exerted in Christ, when he raised him from the dead, and set him at his own right hand in the heavenly places,
B049C001V021	49	1	21	Far above all rule, and authority, and power, and dominion, and every name that is named, not only in this world, but also in that which is to come.
B049C001V022	49	1	22	And he has put all things under his feet, and has appointed him to be the head over all things for the church,
B049C001V023	49	1	23	Which is his body, the fulness of him who fills all things everywhere.
B049C002V001	49	2	1	And you were dead in trespasses and sins;
B049C002V002	49	2	2	In which you walked in times past, according to the ways of this world, according to the prince of the power of the air, the spirit who now works in the sons of disobedience.
B049C002V003	49	2	3	Among them we all lived in times past in the lusts of our flesh, fulfilling the desires of the flesh and of the mind; and were by nature the children of wrath, like the others.
B049C002V004	49	2	4	But God, who is rich in mercy, because of his great love with which he loved us,
B049C002V005	49	2	5	Even when we were dead in transgressions, has made us alive together with Christ, (by grace you are saved;)
B049C002V006	49	2	6	And has raised us up with him, and made us sit together in the heavenly places in Christ Jesus:
B049C002V007	49	2	7	That in the ages to come he might show the incomparable riches of his grace in his kindness toward us through Christ Jesus.
B049C002V008	49	2	8	For by grace you have been saved through faith; and that not of yourselves: it is the gift of God:
B049C002V009	49	2	9	Not because of works, lest any man should boast.
B049C002V010	49	2	10	For we are his workmanship, created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God has prepared beforehand for us to do.
B049C002V011	49	2	11	Therefore remember, that in times past you Gentiles in the flesh, who are called Uncircumcision by those who are called the Circumcision, (that which is performed in the flesh by hands;)
B049C002V012	49	2	12	That at that time you were without Christ, being aliens from the commonwealth of Israel, and strangers to the covenants of promise, having no hope, and without God in the world:
B049C002V013	49	2	13	But now in Christ Jesus you who once were far off have been brought near by the blood of Christ.
B049C002V014	49	2	14	For he is our peace, who has made both one, and has broken down the wall of hostility between us;
B049C002V015	49	2	15	Having abolished in his flesh the enmity, the law of commandments and ordinances; to create in himself one new man in place of two, thus making peace;
B049C002V016	49	2	16	And that he might reconcile both to God, in one body, through the cross, thereby putting to death the enmity.
B049C002V017	49	2	17	And he came and preached peace to you who were far off, and to those who were near.
B049C002V018	49	2	18	For through him we both have access by one Spirit to the Father.
B049C002V019	49	2	19	Now then, you are no longer strangers and foreigners, but fellow citizens with the saints, and members of the household of God;
B049C002V020	49	2	20	Built upon the foundation of the apostles and prophets, Jesus Christ himself being the cornerstone;
B049C002V021	49	2	21	In whom the whole building is joined together and grows to become a holy temple in the Lord:
B049C002V022	49	2	22	In whom you also are built together into a dwelling of God in the Spirit.
B049C003V001	49	3	1	For this reason I, Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus for you Gentiles,
B049C003V002	49	3	2	If indeed you have heard of the stewardship of the grace of God which was given to me for you:
B049C003V003	49	3	3	That by revelation he made known to me the mystery; as I wrote before briefly.
B049C003V004	49	3	4	When you read this, you will be able to understand my insight into the mystery of Christ,
B049C003V005	49	3	5	Which in other ages was not made known to the sons of men as it has now been revealed to his holy apostles and prophets by the Spirit;
B049C003V006	49	3	6	That is, that the Gentiles are fellow heirs, members of the same body, and sharers together of the promise in Christ Jesus through the gospel:
B049C003V007	49	3	7	Of which I was made a minister, according to the gift of the grace of God given to me by the working of his power.
B049C003V008	49	3	8	To me, though I am the very least of all the saints, was this grace given, that I should preach among the Gentiles the unsearchable riches of Christ;
B049C003V009	49	3	9	And make all men see what is the plan of the mystery, which from past ages has been hidden in God, who created all things:
B049C003V010	49	3	10	That now, to the rulers and authorities in the heavenly places, the manifold wisdom of God might be known through the church,
B049C003V011	49	3	11	According to the eternal purpose which he accomplished in Christ Jesus our Lord:
B049C003V012	49	3	12	In whom we have boldness and access with confidence by faith in him.
B049C003V013	49	3	13	Therefore I ask that you not be discouraged at my tribulations for you, which are your glory.
B049C003V014	49	3	14	For this reason I bow my knees to the Father,
B049C003V015	49	3	15	From whom every family in heaven and earth is named,
B049C003V016	49	3	16	That he would grant you, according to the riches of his glory, to be strengthened with might by his Spirit in the inner man;
B049C003V017	49	3	17	That Christ may dwell in your hearts by faith; that you, being rooted and grounded in love,
B049C003V018	49	3	18	May be able to comprehend, with all the saints, its breadth, and length, and height, and depth;
B049C003V019	49	3	19	And to know the love of Christ, which passes knowledge, that you might be filled with all the fulness of God.
B049C003V020	49	3	20	Now to him who is able to do immeasurably beyond all that we ask or think, according to the power that works within us,
B049C003V021	49	3	21	To him be glory in the church and in Christ Jesus throughout all generations, for ever and ever. Amen.
B049C004V001	49	4	1	Therefore I, a prisoner of the Lord, urge you to walk in a manner worthy of the calling to which you have been called,
B049C004V002	49	4	2	With all humility and gentleness, with patience, bearing with one another in love;
B049C004V003	49	4	3	Endeavouring to keep the unity of the Spirit in the bond of peace.
B049C004V004	49	4	4	There is one body, and one Spirit, just as you were called to one hope in your calling;
B049C004V005	49	4	5	One Lord, one faith, one baptism,
B049C004V006	49	4	6	One God and Father of all, who is above all, and through all, and in all.
B049C004V007	49	4	7	But to every one of us grace was given according to the measure of the gift of Christ.
B049C004V008	49	4	8	Therefore it says, When he ascended on high, he led a host of captives, and gave gifts to men.
B049C004V009	49	4	9	(In saying that he ascended, what does that mean but that he also descended into the lower parts of the earth?
B049C004V010	49	4	10	He who descended is the same one who ascended far above all the heavens, that he might fill all things.)
B049C004V011	49	4	11	And he gave some as apostles; and some as prophets; and some as evangelists; and some as pastors and teachers;
B049C004V012	49	4	12	For the equipping of the saints for the work of the ministry, for the building up of the body of Christ:
B049C004V013	49	4	13	Until we all attain the unity of the faith, and of the knowledge of the Son of God, to mature manhood, to the measure of the stature of the fulness of Christ:
B049C004V014	49	4	14	That we may no longer be children, tossed to and fro, and carried about with every wind of doctrine, by the cunning of men, by their craftiness in deceitful scheming.
B049C004V015	49	4	15	But speaking the truth in love, we are to grow up in all things into him, who is the head, that is, Christ:
B049C004V016	49	4	16	From whom the whole body, fitted and joined together by that which every joint supplies, according to the proper working of every part, causes the body to grow, for the building up of itself in love.
B049C004V017	49	4	17	This I say, therefore, and testify in the Lord, that you must no longer walk as other Gentiles walk, in the futility of their minds,
B049C004V018	49	4	18	Having their understanding darkened, being alienated from the life of God through the ignorance that is in them, because of the blindness of their hearts:
B049C004V019	49	4	19	Who, being past feeling, have given themselves over to licentiousness, greedy to practice all kinds of uncleanness.
B049C004V020	49	4	20	But you did not learn Christ that way;
B049C004V021	49	4	21	If indeed you have heard him, and have been taught by him, as the truth is in Jesus,
B049C004V022	49	4	22	Then put off the old man, which belongs to your former life, which is corrupt through deceitful lusts;
B049C004V023	49	4	23	And be renewed in the spirit of your minds;
B049C004V024	49	4	24	And put on the new man, who, in the likeness of God, is created in true righteousness and holiness.
B049C004V025	49	4	25	Therefore, putting away lying, let every man speak the truth with his neighbour: for we are members of one another.
B049C004V026	49	4	26	Be angry, and do not sin: do not let the sun go down upon your wrath:
B049C004V027	49	4	27	Give no opportunity to the devil.
B049C004V028	49	4	28	Let him who stole, steal no more: but rather let him labour, doing with his hands that which is good, that he may have something to give to him who has need.
B049C004V029	49	4	29	Let no corrupt words proceed out of your mouth, but only that which is good for edifying, that it may impart grace to the hearers.
B049C004V030	49	4	30	And do not grieve the Holy Spirit of God, by whom you have been sealed for the day of redemption.
B049C004V031	49	4	31	Let all bitterness, and wrath, and anger, and quarreling, and slander, be put away from you, along with all types of malice:
B049C004V032	49	4	32	And be kind to one another, tenderhearted, forgiving one another, even as God in Christ has forgiven you.
B049C005V001	49	5	1	Therefore be imitators of God, as dear children;
B049C005V002	49	5	2	And walk in love, as Christ also has loved us, and has given himself up for us, an offering and a sacrifice, a sweet smelling aroma to God.
B049C005V003	49	5	3	But sexual immorality, and all impurity, or covetousness, must not even be named among you, as is befitting saints;
B049C005V004	49	5	4	Nor let there be filthiness, or foolish talk, or coarse jesting, which are not proper: but rather giving of thanks.
B049C005V005	49	5	5	For this you know: that no sexually immoral or impure person, or covetous man, (for such a man is an idolater,) has any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God.
B049C005V006	49	5	6	Let no man deceive you with vain words: for because of these things the wrath of God comes upon the sons of disobedience.
B049C005V007	49	5	7	Therefore, do not be partakers with them.
B049C005V008	49	5	8	For you were once darkness, but now you are light in the Lord: walk as children of light;
B049C005V009	49	5	9	(For the fruit of the Spirit consists in all goodness and righteousness and truth;)
B049C005V010	49	5	10	And try to learn what is pleasing to the Lord.
B049C005V011	49	5	11	Have no fellowship with the unfruitful works of darkness, but rather reprove them,
B049C005V012	49	5	12	For it is a shame even to speak of those things which are done by the disobedient in secret.
B049C005V013	49	5	13	But all things that are exposed by the light become visible: for everything that is made visible is light.
B049C005V014	49	5	14	Therefore he says, Awaken, you who sleep, and arise from the dead, and Christ shall give you light.
B049C005V015	49	5	15	See then that you walk carefully, not as fools, but as wise men,
B049C005V016	49	5	16	Making the most of the time, because the days are evil.
B049C005V017	49	5	17	Therefore, do not be unwise, but understand what the will of the Lord is.
B049C005V018	49	5	18	And do not be drunk with wine, which is debauchery; but be filled with the Spirit;
B049C005V019	49	5	19	Speaking to one another with psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord;
B049C005V020	49	5	20	Always giving thanks for all things to God the Father in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ;
B049C005V021	49	5	21	Submitting to one another out of reverence for Christ.
B049C005V022	49	5	22	Wives, submit to your own husbands, as to the Lord.
B049C005V023	49	5	23	For the husband is the head of the wife, even as Christ is the head of the church, his body: and he himself is its saviour.
B049C005V024	49	5	24	Therefore, as the church is subject to Christ, so let wives be to their own husbands in everything.
B049C005V025	49	5	25	Husbands, love your wives, just as Christ loved the church, and gave himself up for her;
B049C005V026	49	5	26	That he might sanctify her, having cleansed her by the washing of water through the word,
B049C005V027	49	5	27	That he might present her to himself a glorious church, without spot, or wrinkle, or any such thing; but that she should be holy and without blemish.
B049C005V028	49	5	28	So husbands ought to love their wives as their own bodies. He who loves his wife loves himself.
B049C005V029	49	5	29	For no man ever hated his own flesh; but he nourishes and cherishes it, just as the Lord does the church:
B049C005V030	49	5	30	Because we are members of his body.
B049C005V031	49	5	31	For this reason a man shall leave his father and mother, and be joined to his wife, and the two shall be one flesh.
B049C005V032	49	5	32	This is a great mystery: but I speak concerning Christ and the church.
B049C005V033	49	5	33	Nevertheless, let every one of you love his wife as himself; and let the wife see that she respects her husband.
B049C006V001	49	6	1	Children, obey your parents in the Lord: for this is right.
B049C006V002	49	6	2	Honour your father and mother; (which is the first commandment with a promise;)
B049C006V003	49	6	3	That it may be well with you, and you may live long on the earth.
B049C006V004	49	6	4	And you fathers, do not provoke your children to anger: but bring them up in the discipline and instruction of the Lord.
B049C006V005	49	6	5	Slaves, be obedient to those who are your earthly masters, with fear and trembling, in sincerity of heart, as to Christ;
B049C006V006	49	6	6	Not with eye-service, as men-pleasers; but as the servants of Christ, doing the will of God from the heart;
B049C006V007	49	6	7	Doing service with a good will, as to the Lord, and not to men:
B049C006V008	49	6	8	Knowing that whatever good thing any man does, he shall receive the same back from the Lord, whether he is a slave or free.
B049C006V009	49	6	9	And, you masters, do the same to them, and give up threatening: knowing that both your Master and theirs is in heaven; and there is no partiality with him.
B049C006V010	49	6	10	Finally, be strong in the Lord, and in the strength of his might.
B049C006V011	49	6	11	Put on the whole armour of God, that you may be able to stand against the wiles of the devil.
B049C006V012	49	6	12	For we do not wrestle against flesh and blood, but against rulers, against authorities, against the powers of darkness of this world, against spiritual hosts of wickedness in the heavenly places.
B049C006V013	49	6	13	Therefore, take up the whole armour of God, that you may be able to withstand on the evil day, and having done all, to stand.
B049C006V014	49	6	14	Stand therefore, having your loins girded about with truth, and having on the breastplate of righteousness;
B049C006V015	49	6	15	And your feet shod with the readiness that is from the gospel of peace.
B049C006V016	49	6	16	In addition to all these, take up the shield of faith, with which you shall be able to quench all the fiery darts of the wicked one.
B049C006V017	49	6	17	And take the helmet of salvation, and the sword of the Spirit, which is the word of God:
B049C006V018	49	6	18	Praying always in the Spirit with all manner of prayer and supplication. To that end keep alert in it with all perseverance, making supplication for all the saints;
B049C006V019	49	6	19	And for me, that words may be given to me, that I may open my mouth boldly, to make known the mystery of the gospel,
B049C006V020	49	6	20	For which I am an ambassador in chains: that in proclaiming it I may speak boldly, as I ought to speak.
B049C006V021	49	6	21	Now, that you may also know my affairs, and how I am doing, Tychicus, the beloved brother and faithful minister in the Lord, shall make all these things known to you.
B049C006V022	49	6	22	I have sent him to you for this very purpose, that you might know our affairs, and that he might comfort your hearts.
B049C006V023	49	6	23	Peace be to the brethren, and love with faith, from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B049C006V024	49	6	24	Grace be to all those who love our Lord Jesus Christ with an undying love.
B050C001V001	50	1	1	Paul and Timothy, servants of Jesus Christ, to all the saints in Christ Jesus who are at Philippi, with the overseers and deacons:
B050C001V002	50	1	2	Grace to you, and peace, from God our Father, and from the Lord Jesus Christ.
B050C001V003	50	1	3	I thank my God upon every remembrance of you,
B050C001V004	50	1	4	Always, in every prayer of mine for you all, I make my requests with joy,
B050C001V005	50	1	5	Because of your fellowship in the gospel from the first day until now;
B050C001V006	50	1	6	Being confident of this very thing, that he who has begun a good work in you will carry it on to completion until the day of Jesus Christ.
B050C001V007	50	1	7	It is right for me to think this way of you all, because I have you in my heart; since both in my imprisonment, and in the defence and confirmation of the gospel, you are all partakers with me of grace.
B050C001V008	50	1	8	For God is my witness, how greatly I long for you all with the affection of Jesus Christ.
B050C001V009	50	1	9	And this I pray, that your love may abound more and more in knowledge and in all discernment;
B050C001V010	50	1	10	That you may approve things that are excellent; that you may be pure and blameless for the day of Christ;
B050C001V011	50	1	11	Being filled with the fruits of righteousness, which are from Jesus Christ, to the glory and praise of God.
B050C001V012	50	1	12	But I would have you understand, brethren, that the things which happened to me have really served to advance the gospel;
B050C001V013	50	1	13	So that my imprisonment in Christ has become known throughout the entire praetorian guard, and to all the others;
B050C001V014	50	1	14	And many of the brethren, growing confident in the Lord because of my imprisonment, are much more bold to speak the word without fear.
B050C001V015	50	1	15	Some indeed preach Christ from envy and rivalry; and some also from good will;
B050C001V016	50	1	16	The later out of love, knowing that I am appointed for the defence of the gospel:
B050C001V017	50	1	17	The former preach Christ out of selfish ambition, not sincerely, supposing to add affliction to my imprisonment
B050C001V018	50	1	18	What then? Only that in every way, whether in pretence, or in truth, Christ is preached; and in this I rejoice, yea, and will rejoice.
B050C001V019	50	1	19	For I know that this shall turn out for my deliverance through your prayers and the help of the Spirit of Jesus Christ,
B050C001V020	50	1	20	According to my earnest expectation and hope, that in nothing shall I be ashamed, but that with all boldness, now as always, Christ shall be exalted in my body, whether by life, or by death.
B050C001V021	50	1	21	For to me to live is Christ, and to die is gain.
B050C001V022	50	1	22	But if I live in the flesh, that means fruitful labour for me: yet what I shall choose I do not know.
B050C001V023	50	1	23	For I am hard-pressed between the two, having a desire to depart, and to be with Christ; which is far better:
B050C001V024	50	1	24	Nevertheless, to remain in the flesh is more necessary for you.
B050C001V025	50	1	25	And having this confidence, I know that I shall remain and continue with you all for your progress and joy in the faith;
B050C001V026	50	1	26	That in me your rejoicing may be more abundant in Jesus Christ, through my coming to you again.
B050C001V027	50	1	27	Only conduct yourselves in a manner worthy of the gospel of Christ: that whether I come and see you, or am absent, I may hear of you, that you are standing fast in one spirit, with one mind striving together for the faith of the gospel;
B050C001V028	50	1	28	And in no way terrified by your adversaries: which is to them a sign of their destruction, but to you of your salvation, and that from God.
B050C001V029	50	1	29	For to you it is granted on behalf of Christ, not only to believe in him, but also to suffer for his sake;
B050C001V030	50	1	30	Having the same conflict which you saw to be mine, and now hear to be mine still.
B050C002V001	50	2	1	If, therefore, there is any encouragement in Christ, if any consolation in love, if any fellowship in the Spirit, if any affection and compassion,
B050C002V002	50	2	2	Fulfill my joy by being likeminded, having the same love, being of one accord and of one mind.
B050C002V003	50	2	3	Let nothing be done through selfishness or vain conceit; but in lowliness of mind let each esteem the others as better than himself.
B050C002V004	50	2	4	Let each of you not only look to your own interests, but also to the interests of others.
B050C002V005	50	2	5	Let this attitude be in you, which was also in Christ Jesus:
B050C002V006	50	2	6	Who, though being in the form of God, did not regard equality with God something to be grasped:
B050C002V007	50	2	7	But made himself of no reputation, and took upon himself the form of a servant, and was made in the likeness of men:
B050C002V008	50	2	8	And being found in form as a man, he humbled himself, and became obedient to the point of death, even death on a cross.
B050C002V009	50	2	9	Therefore, God has highly exalted him, and given him the name which is above every name:
B050C002V010	50	2	10	That at the name of Jesus every knee should bow, in heaven, and on earth, and under the earth;
B050C002V011	50	2	11	And every tongue confess that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the glory of God the Father.
B050C002V012	50	2	12	Therefore, my beloved, as you have always obeyed, so now, not only in my presence, but much more in my absence, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling.
B050C002V013	50	2	13	For it is God who works in you both to will and to do his good pleasure.
B050C002V014	50	2	14	Do all things without grumbling and disputing:
B050C002V015	50	2	15	That you may be blameless and innocent, the children of God, without blemish, in the midst of a crooked and perverse generation, among whom you shine as lights in the world;
B050C002V016	50	2	16	Holding forth the word of life; that I may rejoice in the day of Christ, that I have not run in vain, nor laboured in vain.
B050C002V017	50	2	17	Even if I am poured out as a drink offering upon the sacrifice and service of your faith, I am glad, and rejoice with you all.
B050C002V018	50	2	18	In the same way, you also should be glad, and rejoice with me.
B050C002V019	50	2	19	But I hope in the Lord Jesus to send Timothy to you shortly, that I may also be of good cheer, when I receive news from you.
B050C002V020	50	2	20	For I have no man like him, of so kindred a spirit, who will genuinely care for your welfare.
B050C002V021	50	2	21	For all seek after their own interests, not those of Jesus Christ's.
B050C002V022	50	2	22	But you know he has proven himself, that, as a son with his father, he has served with me in the gospel.
B050C002V023	50	2	23	Therefore, I hope to send him presently, as soon as I shall see how it will go with me.
B050C002V024	50	2	24	And I trust in the Lord that I myself shall also come shortly.
B050C002V025	50	2	25	Yet I thought it necessary to send to you Epaphroditus, my brother, and companion in labour, and fellow soldier, and your messenger and minister to my needs.
B050C002V026	50	2	26	For he longed after you all, and was full of distress, because you had heard that he had been sick.
B050C002V027	50	2	27	Indeed he was sick, and near to death: but God had mercy on him; and not on him only, but also on me, lest I should have sorrow upon sorrow.
B050C002V028	50	2	28	Therefore, I sent him the more eagerly, that, when you see him again, you may rejoice, and I may be less anxious.
B050C002V029	50	2	29	Therefore, receive him in the Lord with all gladness; and hold such men in high regard:
B050C002V030	50	2	30	Because for the work of Christ he was near to death, not regarding his life, to complete the service you could not give.
B050C003V001	50	3	1	Finally, my brethren, rejoice in the Lord. For me to write the same things to you is no trouble, and is a safeguard for you.
B050C003V002	50	3	2	Beware of the dogs, beware of evil workers, beware of the mutilators of the flesh.
B050C003V003	50	3	3	For we are the true circumcision, who worship God in the spirit, and rejoice in Christ Jesus, and put no confidence in the flesh,
B050C003V004	50	3	4	Though I myself might have confidence in the flesh. If any other man thinks that he has reason to trust in the flesh, I have more:
B050C003V005	50	3	5	Circumcised the eighth day, of the people of Israel, of the tribe of Benjamin, a Hebrew of Hebrews; regarding the law, a Pharisee;
B050C003V006	50	3	6	Concerning zeal, a persecutor of the church; regarding the righteousness which is of the law, blameless.
B050C003V007	50	3	7	But whatever things were gain to me, those I have counted as loss for Christ.
B050C003V008	50	3	8	Furthermore, I count all things as loss compared to the excellency of knowing Christ Jesus my Lord: for whom I have suffered the loss of all things, and count them as rubbish, that I may win Christ,
B050C003V009	50	3	9	And be found in him, not having my own righteousness, based on the law, but that which is through faith in Christ, the righteousness which is from God by faith:
B050C003V010	50	3	10	That I may know him, and the power of his resurrection, and the fellowship of his sufferings, becoming like him in his death;
B050C003V011	50	3	11	If only I might attain to the resurrection of the dead.
B050C003V012	50	3	12	Not that I have already attained it, or have already become perfect: but I press on, that I may lay hold of that for which Christ Jesus laid hold of me.
B050C003V013	50	3	13	Brethren, I do not consider myself to have laid hold of it yet: but this one thing I do, forgetting those things which are behind, and reaching forth to those things which are ahead,
B050C003V014	50	3	14	I press on toward the goal for the prize, to which God has called me upward in Christ Jesus.
B050C003V015	50	3	15	Therefore, let us, as many as are mature, be of this mind: and if in anything you are of a different mind, God shall also reveal this to you.
B050C003V016	50	3	16	Only let us hold true to that which we have already attained.
B050C003V017	50	3	17	Brethren, join together in following me, and note those who walk according to our example.
B050C003V018	50	3	18	For many, of whom I have told you often, and now tell you even with weeping, walk as enemies of the cross of Christ:
B050C003V019	50	3	19	Whose end is destruction, whose god is their belly, and whose glory is in their shame, with minds set on earthly things.
B050C003V020	50	3	20	But our citizenship is in heaven; from whence we eagerly look for a Saviour, the Lord Jesus Christ:
B050C003V021	50	3	21	Who shall change our lowly body, that it may be fashioned like his glorious body, by the power which enables him even to subject all things to himself.
B050C004V001	50	4	1	Therefore, my brethren, whom I dearly love and long for, my joy and crown, in this way stand fast in the Lord, my beloved.
B050C004V002	50	4	2	I urge Euodia, and urge Syntyche to be of the same mind in the Lord.
B050C004V003	50	4	3	And I ask you also, true yokefellow, help these women, for they have laboured with me in the gospel, together with Clement, and the rest of my fellow labourers, whose names are in the book of life.
B050C004V004	50	4	4	Rejoice in the Lord always: and again I say, Rejoice.
B050C004V005	50	4	5	Let your forbearing spirit be known to all men. The Lord is at hand.
B050C004V006	50	4	6	Be anxious about nothing; but in everything by prayer and supplication with thanksgiving let your requests be made known to God.
B050C004V007	50	4	7	And the peace of God, which passes all understanding, shall keep your hearts and minds in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V008	50	4	8	Finally, brethren, whatever things are true, whatever things are honest, whatever things are just, whatever things are pure, whatever things are lovely, whatever things are admirable; if there is any virtue, and if there is anything worthy of praise, think on these things.
B050C004V009	50	4	9	Those things, which you have learned, and received, and heard, and seen in me, do: and the God of peace shall be with you.
B050C004V010	50	4	10	But I rejoice in the Lord greatly, that now at last you have revived your care for me; indeed, you did care, but you lacked opportunity.
B050C004V011	50	4	11	Not that I speak from want: for I have learned, in whatever state I am, to be content.
B050C004V012	50	4	12	I know how to be abased, and I know how to abound: in all circumstances I have learned how to be full and to be hungry, both to abound and to suffer need.
B050C004V013	50	4	13	I can do all things through him who strengthens me.
B050C004V014	50	4	14	Nevertheless, you have done well to share in my affliction.
B050C004V015	50	4	15	Now you Philippians also know, that at the beginning of the gospel ministry, when I departed from Macedonia, no church shared with me in giving and receiving, but you alone.
B050C004V016	50	4	16	For even in Thessalonica you more than once sent help to provide for my needs.
B050C004V017	50	4	17	Not because I desire a gift: but I desire the fruit that increases to your credit.
B050C004V018	50	4	18	But I have received all, and abound: I am full, having received from Epaphroditus the things which were sent from you, a fragrant offering, a sacrifice acceptable and well-pleasing to God.
B050C004V019	50	4	19	And my God shall supply all your needs according to his riches in glory in Christ Jesus.
B050C004V020	50	4	20	Now to our God and Father be glory for ever and ever. Amen.
B050C004V021	50	4	21	Greet every saint in Christ Jesus. The brethren who are with me greet you.
B050C004V022	50	4	22	All the saints greet you, especially those who are of Caesar's household.
B050C004V023	50	4	23	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.
B051C001V001	51	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, and Timothy our brother,
B051C001V002	51	1	2	To the saints and faithful brethren in Christ who are at Colossae: Grace to you, and peace, from God our Father.
B051C001V003	51	1	3	We give thanks to God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, praying always for you,
B051C001V004	51	1	4	Since we heard of your faith in Christ Jesus, and of the love which you have for all the saints,
B051C001V005	51	1	5	Because of the hope which is laid up for you in heaven, of which you have already heard in the word of truth, the gospel;
B051C001V006	51	1	6	Which has come to you. In all the world it brings forth fruit and grows, as it does also in you, since the day you heard of it, and understood the grace of God in truth:
B051C001V007	51	1	7	As you learned it from Epaphras, our dear fellow servant, who is a faithful minister of Christ on our behalf;
B051C001V008	51	1	8	Who has also declared to us your love in the Spirit.
B051C001V009	51	1	9	For this reason, since the day we heard it, we do not cease to pray for you, and to ask that you might be filled with the knowledge of his will in all wisdom and spiritual understanding;
B051C001V010	51	1	10	That you might walk in a manner worthy of the Lord, to please him in all things, being fruitful in every good work, and increasing in the knowledge of God;
B051C001V011	51	1	11	Strengthened with all power, according to his glorious might, with all endurance and patience with joyfulness;
B051C001V012	51	1	12	Giving thanks to the Father, who has made us qualified to be partakers of the inheritance of the saints in light.
B051C001V013	51	1	13	He has delivered us from the dominion of darkness, and has transferred us into the kingdom of his dear Son:
B051C001V014	51	1	14	In whom we have redemption, the forgiveness of sins.
B051C001V015	51	1	15	He is the image of the invisible God, the firstborn over all creation:
B051C001V016	51	1	16	For by him were all things created that are in heaven, and that are in earth, visible and invisible, whether thrones, or dominions, or rulers, or authorities: all things were created by him, and for him:
B051C001V017	51	1	17	And he is before all things, and in him all things hold together.
B051C001V018	51	1	18	He is also the head of the body, the church: he is the beginning, the firstborn from the dead; that in all things he might have preeminence.
B051C001V019	51	1	19	For it pleased the Father, that all his fulness should dwell in him;
B051C001V020	51	1	20	And through him to reconcile all things to himself, whether things on earth, or things in heaven; having made peace through the blood of his cross.
B051C001V021	51	1	21	And you who were at one time alienated and enemies in your minds because of wicked deeds,
B051C001V022	51	1	22	He has now reconciled in his body of flesh through death, to present you holy and blameless and irreproachable in his sight:
B051C001V023	51	1	23	If you continue in the faith, grounded and steadfast, and are not moved away from the hope of the gospel which you have heard, which was preached to every creature under heaven; and of which I, Paul, was made a minister.
B051C001V024	51	1	24	Now I rejoice in my sufferings for you, and fill up in my flesh that which is lacking in the afflictions of Christ for his body's sake, which is the church:
B051C001V025	51	1	25	Of which I was made a minister, according to the commission of God, which was given to me for you, to make the word of God fully known;
B051C001V026	51	1	26	That is, the mystery which has been hidden from ages and from generations, but has now been made manifest to his saints;
B051C001V027	51	1	27	To whom God has chosen to make known among the Gentiles the riches of the glory of this mystery; which is Christ in you, the hope of glory.
B051C001V028	51	1	28	Him we preach, warning every man, and teaching every man in all wisdom; that we may present every man perfect in Christ Jesus.
B051C001V029	51	1	29	For this I labour, striving according to his power, which works mightily within me.
B051C002V001	51	2	1	For I want you to know what a great struggle I have for you, and for those at Laodicea, and for as many as have not seen my face in the flesh;
B051C002V002	51	2	2	That their hearts might be comforted as they are knit together in love, and that they might gain all the riches of the full assurance that comes from understanding, that they may know the mystery of God, of Christ;
B051C002V003	51	2	3	In whom are hidden all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge.
B051C002V004	51	2	4	And this I say, lest any man should deceive you with enticing words.
B051C002V005	51	2	5	For though I am absent in the flesh, yet I am with you in the spirit, rejoicing and beholding your good order, and the steadfastness of your faith in Christ.
B051C002V006	51	2	6	Therefore, as you have received Christ Jesus the Lord, so walk in him:
B051C002V007	51	2	7	Rooted and built up in him, and established in the faith, as you have been taught, and abounding with thanksgiving.
B051C002V008	51	2	8	Beware, lest any man spoil you through philosophy and vain deceit, which depend on the traditions of men and the rudiments of the world, and not on Christ.
B051C002V009	51	2	9	For in him all the fulness of Deity dwells in bodily form.
B051C002V010	51	2	10	And you are complete in him, who is the head of all rule and authority.
B051C002V011	51	2	11	In him also you were circumcised with the circumcision made without hands, in putting off the body of the flesh by the circumcision of Christ:
B051C002V012	51	2	12	Having been buried with him in baptism, you have also risen with him through faith in the working of God, who raised him from the dead.
B051C002V013	51	2	13	And you, being dead in your transgressions and the uncircumcision of your flesh, he has made alive together with him, having forgiven us all transgressions;
B051C002V014	51	2	14	Cancelling the bond of debt, with its legal decrees against us, which was contrary to us, and taking it out of the way, nailing it to his cross;
B051C002V015	51	2	15	And having disarmed rulers and authorities, he made a show of them openly, triumphing over them in it.
B051C002V016	51	2	16	Therefore, let no man judge you in matters of food, or drink, or regarding a festival, or a new moon, or a sabbath day:
B051C002V017	51	2	17	Which are a shadow of things to come; but the reality belongs to Christ.
B051C002V018	51	2	18	Let no man defraud you of your reward, delighting in self-abasement and the worship of angels, taking his stand on visions, vainly puffed up by his fleshly mind,
B051C002V019	51	2	19	And not holding fast to the Head, from whom all the body, supported and knit together by its joints and ligaments, grows with a growth that is from God.
B051C002V020	51	2	20	Therefore, if you are dead with Christ to the elementary principles of the world, why, as though still living in the world, do you submit to such ordinances as,
B051C002V021	51	2	21	Do not touch; do not taste; do not handle?
B051C002V022	51	2	22	These all refer to things which perish with use; and are based on the commandments and doctrines of men.
B051C002V023	51	2	23	These things indeed have an appearance of wisdom with their self-imposed worship, and self-abasement, and severity to the body; but are of no value in restraining the indulgence of the flesh.
B051C003V001	51	3	1	If you have been raised with Christ, seek those things which are above, where Christ sits on the right hand of God.
B051C003V002	51	3	2	Set your affection on things above, not on things on the earth.
B051C003V003	51	3	3	For you are dead, and your life is hidden with Christ in God.
B051C003V004	51	3	4	When Christ, who is our life, shall appear, then you shall also appear with him in glory.
B051C003V005	51	3	5	Therefore, put to death what is earthly in you: sexual immorality, impurity, lust, evil desire, and covetousness, which is idolatry.
B051C003V006	51	3	6	For because of these things the wrath of God is coming:
B051C003V007	51	3	7	And in them you also walked at one time, when you lived in them.
B051C003V008	51	3	8	But now put off all these: anger, wrath, malice, slander, and filthy speech from your mouth.
B051C003V009	51	3	9	Do not lie to one another, seeing that you have put off the old man with his deeds;
B051C003V010	51	3	10	And have put on the new man, who is being renewed in knowledge after the image of the one who created him.
B051C003V011	51	3	11	Here there is neither Greek or Jew, circumcised or uncircumcised, barbarian or Scythian, slave or free: but Christ is all, and in all.
B051C003V012	51	3	12	Therefore, as the chosen of God, holy and beloved, put on hearts of mercy, kindness, humility, gentleness, and patience;
B051C003V013	51	3	13	Bearing with one another, and forgiving one another. If any man has a complaint against another; just as Christ forgave you, so you do the same.
B051C003V014	51	3	14	And above all these things put on love, which is the perfect bond of unity.
B051C003V015	51	3	15	And let the peace of God rule in your hearts, since as members of one body you were called to this; and be thankful.
B051C003V016	51	3	16	Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly; with all wisdom teaching and admonishing one another with psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing with thankfulness in your hearts to God.
B051C003V017	51	3	17	And whatever you do in word or deed, do all in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father through him.
B051C003V018	51	3	18	Wives, submit to your own husbands, as is fitting in the Lord.
B051C003V019	51	3	19	Husbands, love your wives, and do not be harsh toward them.
B051C003V020	51	3	20	Children, obey your parents in all things: for this is well pleasing to the Lord.
B051C003V021	51	3	21	Fathers, provoke not your children, lest they be discouraged.
B051C003V022	51	3	22	Slaves, obey your earthly masters in all things; not as an outward show, as pleasers of men; but with singleness of heart, fearing the Lord:
B051C003V023	51	3	23	And whatever you do, do it heartily, as for the Lord, and not for men;
B051C003V024	51	3	24	Knowing that from the Lord you shall receive your reward, the inheritance: for you serve the Lord Christ.
B051C003V025	51	3	25	But he who does wrong shall be repaid for the wrong which he has done: and there is no partiality.
B051C004V001	51	4	1	Masters, give to your slaves that which is just and fair; knowing that you also have a Master in heaven.
B051C004V002	51	4	2	Continue in prayer, and be watchful in it with thanksgiving;
B051C004V003	51	4	3	And pray also for us, that God would open for us a door for the word, that we may speak the mystery of Christ, for which I am in prison:
B051C004V004	51	4	4	That I may make it clear, as I should.
B051C004V005	51	4	5	Walk in wisdom toward those who are outside, making the most of the time.
B051C004V006	51	4	6	Let your speech be always with grace, seasoned with salt, that you may know how you ought to answer every man.
B051C004V007	51	4	7	All my affairs Tychicus shall declare to you; he is a beloved brother, and a faithful minister and fellow servant in the Lord.
B051C004V008	51	4	8	I have sent him to you for that very purpose, that you might know of our circumstances, and that he might encourage your hearts.
B051C004V009	51	4	9	With him is Onesimus, a faithful and beloved brother, who is one of you. They shall make known to you all things which have taken place here.
B051C004V010	51	4	10	Aristarchus, my fellow prisoner, greets you, as does Mark, the cousin of Barnabas, (regarding him you received instructions: that if he comes to you, welcome him;)
B051C004V011	51	4	11	And Jesus, who is called Justus. These are my only fellow workers for the kingdom of God who are of the circumcision, and they have been a comfort to me.
B051C004V012	51	4	12	Epaphras, who is one of you, a servant of Christ, greets you, always labouring fervently for you in prayer, that you may stand firm and fully assured in all the will of God.
B051C004V013	51	4	13	For I bear him witness, that he has a great zeal for you, and for those in Laodicea and Hierapolis.
B051C004V014	51	4	14	Luke, the beloved physician, and Demas, greet you.
B051C004V015	51	4	15	Greet the brethren who are in Laodicea, and Nympha, and the church which is in her house.
B051C004V016	51	4	16	And when this letter is read among you, have it also read to the church of the Laodiceans; and you, likewise, read the letter from Laodicea.
B051C004V017	51	4	17	And say to Archippus, Take heed that you fulfill the ministry which you have received in the Lord.
B051C004V018	51	4	18	I, Paul, write this greeting in my own hand. Remember my chains. Grace be with you.
B052C001V001	52	1	1	Paul, and Silvanus, and Timothy, to the church of the Thessalonians which is in God the Father and in the Lord Jesus Christ: Grace to you, and peace.
B052C001V002	52	1	2	We give thanks to God always for you all, making mention of you in our prayers;
B052C001V003	52	1	3	Always remembering your work of faith, and labour of love, and endurance of hope in our Lord Jesus Christ, in the sight of our God and Father;
B052C001V004	52	1	4	Knowing, brethren loved by God, that he has chosen you.
B052C001V005	52	1	5	For our gospel came to you not in word only, but also in power, and in the Holy Spirit, and with full conviction. You know what manner of men we were among you for your sake.
B052C001V006	52	1	6	And you became followers of us, and of the Lord, having received the word despite much affliction, with joy from the Holy Spirit:
B052C001V007	52	1	7	So that you became an example to all who believe in Macedonia and Achaia.
B052C001V008	52	1	8	For from you the word of the Lord sounded out not only in Macedonia and Achaia, but your faith in God has spread abroad; so that we need not speak anything.
B052C001V009	52	1	9	For they themselves testify about what manner of reception we had from you, and how you turned to God from idols to serve a living and true God;
B052C001V010	52	1	10	And to wait for his Son from heaven, whom he raised from the dead, that is, Jesus, who delivers us from the wrath to come.
B052C002V001	52	2	1	For you yourselves know, brethren, that our visit to you was not in vain:
B052C002V002	52	2	2	But even after we had already suffered, and were shamefully treated, as you know, in Philippi, we were bold in our God to speak to you the gospel of God despite much opposition.
B052C002V003	52	2	3	For our exhortation does not spring from error, or impurity, or guile:
B052C002V004	52	2	4	But just as we were approved by God to be entrusted with the gospel, even so we speak; not as pleasing men, but God, who tests our hearts.
B052C002V005	52	2	5	For at no time did we use either flattering words, as you know, or a cloak for greed; as God is witness:
B052C002V006	52	2	6	Nor did we seek glory from men, either from you or from others, when we might have asserted our authority, as the apostles of Christ.
B052C002V007	52	2	7	But we were gentle among you, as a nursing mother cherishes her children:
B052C002V008	52	2	8	So having a yearning affection for you, we were willing to impart to you, not only the gospel of God, but also our own selves, because you had become very dear to us.
B052C002V009	52	2	9	For you remember, brethren, our toil and hardship: we laboured night and day, because we did not want to burden any of you as we preached to you the gospel of God.
B052C002V010	52	2	10	You are witnesses, and so is God, how holy and just and blameless was our behaviour toward you who believe:
B052C002V011	52	2	11	Just as you know how we exhorted and comforted and implored every one of you, as a father does his children,
B052C002V012	52	2	12	That you would walk in a manner worthy of God, who has called you into his kingdom and glory.
B052C002V013	52	2	13	For this reason we also thank God without ceasing, because, when you received the word of God which you heard from us, you received it not as the word of men, but as it is in truth, the word of God, which performs its work in you who believe.
B052C002V014	52	2	14	For you, brethren, became followers of the churches of God in Christ Jesus which are in Judaea: for you also have suffered the same things from your own countrymen, even as they have from the Jews:
B052C002V015	52	2	15	Who both killed the Lord Jesus, and their own prophets, and have persecuted us. They do not please God, and oppose all men,
B052C002V016	52	2	16	By hindering us from speaking to the Gentiles that they might be saved, thus always filling up their sins to the limit: but wrath has come upon them at last.
B052C002V017	52	2	17	But we, brethren, having been torn from you for a short time, in person, not in heart, endeavoured all the more eagerly and with great desire to see you face to face.
B052C002V018	52	2	18	Therefore, we wanted to come to you, and I, Paul, more than once; but Satan hindered us.
B052C002V019	52	2	19	For what is our hope, our joy, our crown of rejoicing in the presence of our Lord Jesus Christ at his coming? Is it not even you?
B052C002V020	52	2	20	For you are our glory and joy.
B052C003V001	52	3	1	Therefore, when we could no longer endure it, we thought it good to be left at Athens alone;
B052C003V002	52	3	2	And sent Timothy, our brother, and fellow-worker for God in the gospel of Christ, to establish you, and to comfort you in your faith:
B052C003V003	52	3	3	That no man should be disturbed by these afflictions: for you yourselves know that we are destined for this.
B052C003V004	52	3	4	For truly, when we were with you, we told you beforehand that we should suffer tribulation; just as it came to pass, as you know.
B052C003V005	52	3	5	For this reason, when I could no longer endure it, I sent to learn of your faith, lest by some means the tempter had tempted you, and our labour might have been in vain.
B052C003V006	52	3	6	But now that Timothy has come from you to us, and brought us good tidings of your faith and love, and reported that you always remember us kindly, greatly desiring to see us, as we also desire to see you:
B052C003V007	52	3	7	Therefore, brethren, in the midst of our affliction and distress, we were comforted about you because of your faith:
B052C003V008	52	3	8	For now we live, if you stand fast in the Lord.
B052C003V009	52	3	9	For what thanks can we render to God for you, for all the joy which we have before our God because of you;
B052C003V010	52	3	10	Night and day praying earnestly that we might see your face, and might supply that which is lacking in your faith?
B052C003V011	52	3	11	Now may our God and Father himself, and our Lord Jesus, direct our way to you.
B052C003V012	52	3	12	And may the Lord make you to increase and abound in love toward one another, and toward all men, even as we do toward you:
B052C003V013	52	3	13	So that he may establish your hearts blameless in holiness before God our Father, at the coming of our Lord Jesus with all his saints.
B052C004V001	52	4	1	Furthermore, we urge you, brethren, and exhort you in the Lord Jesus, that as you have learned from us how you ought to walk and to please God, as indeed you are doing, so you would do more and more.
B052C004V002	52	4	2	For you know what commandments we gave you by the authority of the Lord Jesus.
B052C004V003	52	4	3	For this is the will of God: your sanctification, that you should abstain from sexual immorality,
B052C004V004	52	4	4	That every one of you should know how to possess his own vessel in holiness and honour;
B052C004V005	52	4	5	Not in the lust of passion, as the Gentiles who do not know God:
B052C004V006	52	4	6	That no man might transgress and defraud his brother in any matter: because the Lord is the avenger in all these things, as we also have told you and warned you.
B052C004V007	52	4	7	For God has not called us to impurity, but to holiness.
B052C004V008	52	4	8	Therefore, he who rejects this, does not reject man, but God, who has also given you his Holy Spirit.
B052C004V009	52	4	9	But regarding brotherly love you do not need any one to write to you: for you yourselves have been taught by God to love one another.
B052C004V010	52	4	10	And indeed you do love all the brethren who are in all Macedonia: but we urge you, brethren, that you do so more and more;
B052C004V011	52	4	11	And that you aspire to live quietly, and to mind your own business, and to work with your own hands, as we commanded you;
B052C004V012	52	4	12	That you may behave properly toward those who are outside, and that you may lack nothing.
B052C004V013	52	4	13	Now I would not have you to be ignorant, brethren, concerning those who are asleep, that you may not sorrow, as others who have no hope.
B052C004V014	52	4	14	For if we believe that Jesus died and rose again, even so God will bring with him those who sleep in Jesus.
B052C004V015	52	4	15	For this we say to you by the word of the Lord, that we who are alive and remain until the coming of the Lord shall not precede those who are asleep.
B052C004V016	52	4	16	For the Lord himself shall descend from heaven with a shout, with the voice of the archangel, and with the trumpet of God: and the dead in Christ shall rise first:
B052C004V017	52	4	17	Then we who are alive and remain shall be caught up together with them in the clouds, to meet the Lord in the air: and so shall we ever be with the Lord.
B052C004V018	52	4	18	Therefore comfort one another with these words.
B052C005V001	52	5	1	But of the times and the seasons, brethren, you have no need that I write to you.
B052C005V002	52	5	2	For you yourselves know full well that the day of the Lord shall come as a thief in the night.
B052C005V003	52	5	3	For when they shall say, Peace and safety; then sudden destruction shall come upon them, as birth pangs upon a woman with child; and they shall not escape.
B052C005V004	52	5	4	But you, brethren, are not in darkness, that this day should overtake you as a thief.
B052C005V005	52	5	5	You are all sons of light, and sons of the day: we are not of the night, nor of darkness.
B052C005V006	52	5	6	Therefore let us not sleep, as others do; but let us watch and be sober.
B052C005V007	52	5	7	For those who sleep, sleep in the night; and those who get drunk, get drunk in the night.
B052C005V008	52	5	8	But let us, who are of the day, be sober, putting on the breastplate of faith and love; and for a helmet, the hope of salvation.
B052C005V009	52	5	9	For God has not appointed us to suffer wrath, but to obtain salvation through our Lord Jesus Christ,
B052C005V010	52	5	10	Who died for us, that, whether we wake or sleep, we should live together with him.
B052C005V011	52	5	11	Therefore, comfort one another, and build one another up, just as you are doing.
B052C005V012	52	5	12	And we urge you, brethren, to respect those who labour among you, and are over you in the Lord, and admonish you;
B052C005V013	52	5	13	And esteem them very highly in love for their work's sake. And be at peace among yourselves.
B052C005V014	52	5	14	Now we exhort you, brethren, warn those who are idle or unruly, encourage the timid, support the weak, be patient toward all.
B052C005V015	52	5	15	See that no one repays another with evil for evil; but always seek that which is good, both for yourselves, and for all men.
B052C005V016	52	5	16	Rejoice always.
B052C005V017	52	5	17	Pray without ceasing.
B052C005V018	52	5	18	In everything give thanks: for this is the will of God for you in Christ Jesus.
B052C005V019	52	5	19	Do not quench the Spirit.
B052C005V020	52	5	20	Do not despise prophesying.
B052C005V021	52	5	21	Test all things; hold fast that which is good.
B052C005V022	52	5	22	Abstain from all forms of evil.
B052C005V023	52	5	23	Now may the God of peace himself sanctify you wholly; and may your whole spirit and soul and body be preserved blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B052C005V024	52	5	24	Faithful is he who calls you, who also will do it.
B052C005V025	52	5	25	Brethren, pray for us.
B052C005V026	52	5	26	Greet all the brethren with a holy kiss.
B052C005V027	52	5	27	I charge you by the Lord that this letter be read to all the brethren.
B052C005V028	52	5	28	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
B053C001V001	53	1	1	Paul, and Silvanus, and Timothy, to the church of the Thessalonians in God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ:
B053C001V002	53	1	2	Grace to you, and peace, from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C001V003	53	1	3	We ought always to thank God for you, brethren, as is fitting, because your faith grows abundantly, and the love of every one of you for each other grows greater;
B053C001V004	53	1	4	So that we ourselves boast of you in the churches of God for your steadfastness and faith in all the persecutions and tribulations which you endure:
B053C001V005	53	1	5	Which is evidence of the righteous judgment of God, that you may be counted worthy of the kingdom of God, for which you suffer.
B053C001V006	53	1	6	It is a righteous thing for God to repay with affliction those who afflict you;
B053C001V007	53	1	7	And to give rest to you who are afflicted, along with us, when the Lord Jesus shall be revealed from heaven with his mighty angels in flaming fire,
B053C001V008	53	1	8	Taking vengeance on those who do not know God, and who do not obey the gospel of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C001V009	53	1	9	They shall be punished with eternal ruin and exclusion from the presence of the Lord, and from the glory of his power;
B053C001V010	53	1	10	When he shall come to be glorified in his saints on that day, and to be marveled at among all those who believe, including you, because our testimony among you was believed.
B053C001V011	53	1	11	With this in mind we pray always for you, that our God may count you worthy of his calling, and would with power fulfill every good purpose and work of faith:
B053C001V012	53	1	12	That the name of our Lord Jesus Christ may be glorified in you, and you in him, according to the grace of our God and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C002V001	53	2	1	Now, regarding the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, and our being gathered to him, we ask you, brethren,
B053C002V002	53	2	2	That you not be quickly shaken in mind, or alarmed, either by spirit, or by word, or by letter purporting to be from us, saying that the day of Christ is at hand.
B053C002V003	53	2	3	Let no man deceive you in any way: for that day shall not come, until there is first a falling away, and the man of lawlessness is revealed, the son of perdition;
B053C002V004	53	2	4	Who opposes and exalts himself above all that is called God, or that is worshipped; so that he sits as God in the temple of God, proclaiming himself to be God.
B053C002V005	53	2	5	Do you not remember, that when I was yet with you, I told you these things?
B053C002V006	53	2	6	And you know what restrains him now, that he might be revealed in his time.
B053C002V007	53	2	7	For the mystery of lawlessness is already at work: only he who now restrains it will do so, until he is taken out of the way.
B053C002V008	53	2	8	And then shall the lawless one be revealed, whom the Lord shall slay with the breath of his mouth, and shall destroy by the brightness of his coming.
B053C002V009	53	2	9	The coming of the lawless one is through the working of Satan, with all power and signs and lying wonders,
B053C002V010	53	2	10	And with all wicked deception for those who perish; because they did not receive the love of the truth, that they might be saved.
B053C002V011	53	2	11	And for this reason God shall send them a strong delusion, that they should believe a lie:
B053C002V012	53	2	12	That all those might be condemned who did not believe the truth, but took pleasure in unrighteousness.
B053C002V013	53	2	13	But we ought always to give thanks to God for you, brethren beloved of the Lord, because God has from the beginning chosen you for salvation through sanctification by the Spirit and belief in the truth:
B053C002V014	53	2	14	To this he called you through our gospel, to obtain the glory of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B053C002V015	53	2	15	Therefore, brethren, stand fast, and hold to the traditions which you have been taught by us, whether by word, or by letter.
B053C002V016	53	2	16	Now may our Lord Jesus Christ himself, and God our Father, who has loved us, and has given us eternal comfort and good hope through grace,
B053C002V017	53	2	17	Comfort your hearts, and establish you in every good work and word.
B053C003V001	53	3	1	Finally, brethren, pray for us, that the word of the Lord may spread rapidly, and be glorified, even as it did with you:
B053C003V002	53	3	2	And that we may be delivered from wicked and evil men: for not all have faith.
B053C003V003	53	3	3	But the Lord is faithful, who shall establish you, and keep you from evil.
B053C003V004	53	3	4	And we have confidence in the Lord regarding you, that you are doing and will continue to do the things which we command.
B053C003V005	53	3	5	May the Lord direct your hearts into the love of God, and into the steadfastness of Christ.
B053C003V006	53	3	6	Now we command you, brethren, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that you keep away from every brother who is idle and does not walk according to the tradition which you received from us.
B053C003V007	53	3	7	For you yourselves know how you ought to imitate us: for we were not idle among you;
B053C003V008	53	3	8	Nor did we eat any man's bread without paying; but with labour and toil we worked night and day, that we might not be a burden to any of you:
B053C003V009	53	3	9	Not because we do not have the right, but to make ourselves an example for you to follow.
B053C003V010	53	3	10	For even when we were with you, we gave you this command: if any will not work, neither shall he eat.
B053C003V011	53	3	11	For we hear that there are some among you who walk in idleness, not working at all, mere busybodies.
B053C003V012	53	3	12	Now those who are such we command and exhort by our Lord Jesus Christ, that they work quietly, and eat their own bread.
B053C003V013	53	3	13	But you, brethren, do not be weary in doing good.
B053C003V014	53	3	14	And if any man will not obey our instruction in this letter, note that man, and do not associate with him, that he may be ashamed.
B053C003V015	53	3	15	Yet do not count him as an enemy, but warn him as a brother.
B053C003V016	53	3	16	Now may the Lord of peace himself give you peace always in all ways. The Lord be with you all.
B053C003V017	53	3	17	I, Paul, write this greeting with my own hand, which is the mark of all my letters: this is the way I write.
B053C003V018	53	3	18	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all.
B054C001V001	54	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the commandment of God our Saviour, and of Jesus Christ, our hope;
B054C001V002	54	1	2	To Timothy, my true son in the faith: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God our Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
B054C001V003	54	1	3	As I urged you when I went to Macedonia, remain at Ephesus, that you might warn certain men not to teach any other doctrine,
B054C001V004	54	1	4	Nor to give heed to myths and endless genealogies, which promote useless speculation, rather than godly training, which is by faith.
B054C001V005	54	1	5	Now the aim of this commandment is love from a pure heart, and a good conscience, and a sincere faith:
B054C001V006	54	1	6	From which some have swerved, turning aside to vain discussion;
B054C001V007	54	1	7	Desiring to be teachers of the law; but understanding neither what they say, nor the matters about which they make such confident assertions.
B054C001V008	54	1	8	But we know that the law is good, if a man uses it lawfully;
B054C001V009	54	1	9	Understanding this, that the law is not made for a righteous man, but for the lawless and disobedient, for the ungodly and for sinners, for unholy and profane, for murderers of fathers and murderers of mothers, for manslayers,
B054C001V010	54	1	10	For adulterers, for those who defile themselves with men, for kidnappers, for liars, for perjurers, and for whatever else is contrary to sound doctrine;
B054C001V011	54	1	11	According to the glorious gospel of the blessed God, which was committed to my trust.
B054C001V012	54	1	12	And I thank Christ Jesus our Lord, who has strengthened me, for he counted me faithful, putting me into the ministry;
B054C001V013	54	1	13	Though I was formerly a blasphemer, and a persecutor, and a violent man: but I obtained mercy, because I did it ignorantly in unbelief.
B054C001V014	54	1	14	And the grace of our Lord overflowed for me, along with the faith and love which are in Christ Jesus.
B054C001V015	54	1	15	This is a trustworthy saying, and worthy of full acceptance, that Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners; of whom I am the foremost.
B054C001V016	54	1	16	Yet for this reason I obtained mercy, that in me as the foremost, Jesus Christ might show forth his unlimited patience, as a pattern for those who would believe in him for eternal life.
B054C001V017	54	1	17	Now to the King eternal, immortal, invisible, the only God, be honour and glory for ever and ever. Amen.
B054C001V018	54	1	18	This charge I commit to you, son Timothy, according to the prophecies once made about you, that by them you might fight the good fight;
B054C001V019	54	1	19	Holding on to faith and a good conscience; which some have rejected and so shipwrecked their faith:
B054C001V020	54	1	20	Among whom are Hymenaeus and Alexander; whom I have delivered to Satan, that they may learn not to blaspheme.
B054C002V001	54	2	1	Therefore I urge, first of all, that requests, prayers, intercessions, and giving of thanks, be made for all men;
B054C002V002	54	2	2	For kings, and for all who are in authority; that we may lead quiet and peaceable lives in all godliness and reverence.
B054C002V003	54	2	3	For this is good and acceptable in the sight of God our Saviour;
B054C002V004	54	2	4	Who desires all men to be saved, and to come to the knowledge of the truth.
B054C002V005	54	2	5	For there is one God, and one mediator between God and men, the man Christ Jesus;
B054C002V006	54	2	6	Who gave himself as a ransom for all, the testimony at the proper time.
B054C002V007	54	2	7	And for this I have been appointed a preacher, and an apostle, (I speak the truth in Christ and am not lying;) a teacher of the Gentiles in faith and truth.
B054C002V008	54	2	8	Therefore, I want men everywhere to pray, lifting up holy hands, without anger or dissension.
B054C002V009	54	2	9	In like manner also, let women adorn themselves in proper apparel, modestly and soberly; not with braided hair, or gold, or pearls, or costly attire;
B054C002V010	54	2	10	But with good works, as becomes women professing godliness.
B054C002V011	54	2	11	Let a woman learn in quietness and full submission.
B054C002V012	54	2	12	I do not allow a woman to teach, or to have authority over a man; she must keep silent.
B054C002V013	54	2	13	For Adam was first formed, then Eve;
B054C002V014	54	2	14	And Adam was not deceived, but the woman was deceived and became a transgressor.
B054C002V015	54	2	15	Yet women shall be kept safe through childbirth, if they continue in faith and love and holiness with propriety.
B054C003V001	54	3	1	This is a true saying, If a man desires the office of overseer, he desires a noble task.
B054C003V002	54	3	2	An overseer must be blameless, the husband of one wife, temperate, sensible, respectable, given to hospitality, able to teach;
B054C003V003	54	3	3	Not given to wine, not combative, but gentle, not quarrelsome, not a lover of money;
B054C003V004	54	3	4	One who rules his own house well, having his children under control, commanding their respect in all ways;
B054C003V005	54	3	5	(For if a man does not know how to manage his own house, how shall he take care of the church of God?)
B054C003V006	54	3	6	Not a recent convert, lest being lifted up with pride he fall into the condemnation of the devil.
B054C003V007	54	3	7	Moreover, he must have a good reputation among those who are outside; lest he fall into disgrace and the snare of the devil.
B054C003V008	54	3	8	Deacons, likewise, must be serious, not double-tongued, not given to much wine, not greedy for gain;
B054C003V009	54	3	9	Holding the mystery of the faith with a pure conscience.
B054C003V010	54	3	10	Let these be tested first; then, if blameless, let them serve as deacons.
B054C003V011	54	3	11	In the same way, the women must be serious, not malicious gossips, but temperate, faithful in all things.
B054C003V012	54	3	12	A deacon must be the husband of but one wife, ruling his children and his own house well.
B054C003V013	54	3	13	For those who serve well in the office of deacon acquire for themselves a good standing, and great boldness in their faith in Christ Jesus.
B054C003V014	54	3	14	These things I write to you, hoping to come to you shortly:
B054C003V015	54	3	15	But if I tarry long, I write so you will know how you ought to behave in the household of God, which is the church of the living God, the pillar and bulwark of the truth.
B054C003V016	54	3	16	And beyond question, great is the mystery of godliness: He was revealed in the flesh, vindicated in the Spirit, seen by angels, preached among the nations, believed on in the world, taken up in glory.
B054C004V001	54	4	1	Now the Spirit expressly says that in the latter times some shall depart from the faith, giving heed to seducing spirits, and doctrines of devils;
B054C004V002	54	4	2	Taught by hypocritical liars; who have their consciences seared as with a hot iron;
B054C004V003	54	4	3	Forbidding marriage, and commanding abstinence from foods which God has created to be received with thanksgiving by those who believe and know the truth.
B054C004V004	54	4	4	For everything created by God is good, and nothing is to be refused, if it is received with thanksgiving:
B054C004V005	54	4	5	For it is consecrated by the word of God and prayer.
B054C004V006	54	4	6	If you point out all these things to the brethren, you shall be a good minister of Jesus Christ, nourished by the words of faith and of good doctrine, which you have been following.
B054C004V007	54	4	7	But have nothing to do with godless myths and old wives' tales, but rather train yourself in godliness;
B054C004V008	54	4	8	For bodily exercise is of some value: but godliness is of value in all things, having promise in this life, and in that which is to come.
B054C004V009	54	4	9	This is a faithful saying and worthy of full acceptance.
B054C004V010	54	4	10	For this reason we both labour and strive, because we trust in the living God, who is the Saviour of all men, especially of those who believe.
B054C004V011	54	4	11	Command and teach these things.
B054C004V012	54	4	12	Let no man despise your youth; but be an example to the believers, in word, in conduct, in love, in faith, in purity.
B054C004V013	54	4	13	Until I come, give attention to the public reading of scripture, to exhortation, to doctrine.
B054C004V014	54	4	14	Do not neglect the gift that is in you, which was given to you by prophetic message when the body of elders laid hands upon you.
B054C004V015	54	4	15	Diligently practice these things; give yourself wholly to them; so your progress may appear to all.
B054C004V016	54	4	16	Take heed to yourself, and to your teaching; continue in them: for in doing this you shall save both yourself, and those who hear you.
B054C005V001	54	5	1	Do not rebuke an older man, but entreat him as a father; and the younger men as brothers;
B054C005V002	54	5	2	The elder women as mothers; the younger as sisters, in all purity.
B054C005V003	54	5	3	Honour widows who are widows indeed.
B054C005V004	54	5	4	But if any widow has children or grandchildren, let them first learn to show piety at home, and to repay their parents: for that is good and acceptable before God.
B054C005V005	54	5	5	Now she who is a widow indeed, and left all alone, trusts in God, and continues in supplications and prayers night and day.
B054C005V006	54	5	6	But she who lives in self-indulgence is dead while she lives.
B054C005V007	54	5	7	And these things give as commands, that they may be blameless.
B054C005V008	54	5	8	But if anyone does not provide for his own, and especially for those of his own household, he has denied the faith, and is worse than an unbeliever.
B054C005V009	54	5	9	Let a widow be placed on the roll only if she is at least sixty years old, having been the wife of one man,
B054C005V010	54	5	10	Having a reputation for good works; if she has brought up her children, if she has shown hospitality to strangers, if she has washed the saints' feet, if she has relieved the afflicted, if she has devoted herself to every good work.
B054C005V011	54	5	11	But refuse to enroll the younger widows: for when their sensual desires cause them to disregard their dedication to Christ, they will marry;
B054C005V012	54	5	12	Thus incurring condemnation, because they have cast aside their first pledge.
B054C005V013	54	5	13	Besides, they learn to be idle, wandering about from house to house; and not only idle, but also gossips and busybodies, speaking things which they ought not.
B054C005V014	54	5	14	Therefore, I want the younger women to marry, bear children, guide the house, and give the adversary no occasion to speak reproachfully.
B054C005V015	54	5	15	For some have already turned aside to follow Satan.
B054C005V016	54	5	16	If any woman who believes has dependent widows, let her assist them, and let the church not be burdened; that it may relieve those who are widows indeed.
B054C005V017	54	5	17	Let the elders who rule well be counted worthy of double honour, especially those who labour in preaching and teaching.
B054C005V018	54	5	18	For the scripture says, You shall not muzzle the ox that treads out the grain. And, The labourer is worthy of his wages.
B054C005V019	54	5	19	Do not receive an accusation against an elder, except on the evidence of two or three witnesses.
B054C005V020	54	5	20	Those who continue to sin, rebuke before all, that the others may fear.
B054C005V021	54	5	21	I solemnly charge you before God, and the Lord Jesus Christ, and the chosen angels, that you observe these things without favouring one over another, doing nothing with partiality.
B054C005V022	54	5	22	Do not be hasty in the laying on of hands, nor share in other men's sins: keep yourself pure.
B054C005V023	54	5	23	No longer drink water only, but use a little wine for your stomach's sake and for your frequent ailments.
B054C005V024	54	5	24	Some men's sins are evident, going before them to judgment; and for some men they appear later.
B054C005V025	54	5	25	So also, good works are evident; and even those that are otherwise cannot be hidden.
B054C006V001	54	6	1	Let as many as are under the yoke of slavery count their masters as worthy of all honour, that the name of God and our teaching may be not defamed.
B054C006V002	54	6	2	And those who have believing masters must not despise them because they are brethren; but rather service them all the more, because those who partake of their services are believers and beloved. Teach and exhort these things.
B054C006V003	54	6	3	If any man teaches otherwise, and does not consent to sound words, the words of our Lord Jesus Christ, and to the teaching which accords with godliness;
B054C006V004	54	6	4	He is proud, knowing nothing, but has an unhealthy craving for controversy and disputes about words, from which come envy, strife, malicious talk, evil suspicions,
B054C006V005	54	6	5	And wrangling among men of corrupt minds, who are destitute of the truth, and suppose that godliness is a means to gain.
B054C006V006	54	6	6	But godliness with contentment is great gain.
B054C006V007	54	6	7	For we brought nothing into this world, and we can carry nothing out.
B054C006V008	54	6	8	But if we have food and clothing, we will be content with these.
B054C006V009	54	6	9	But those who want to be rich fall into temptation and a snare, and into many foolish and harmful desires, which plunge men into ruin and destruction.
B054C006V010	54	6	10	For the love of money is the root of all sorts of evil: and some, by craving it, have wandered from the faith, and pierced themselves through with many sorrows.
B054C006V011	54	6	11	But you, O man of God, flee these things; and follow righteousness, godliness, faith, love, steadfastness, and gentleness.
B054C006V012	54	6	12	Fight the good fight of faith; lay hold on eternal life, to which you are called, to which you made the good confession before many witnesses.
B054C006V013	54	6	13	I charge you in the sight of God, who gives life to all things, and of Christ Jesus, who in his testimony before Pontius Pilate made the good confession;
B054C006V014	54	6	14	That you keep the commandment without spot, free of reproach, until the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ:
B054C006V015	54	6	15	Which he will bring about in his own time, he who is the blessed and only Sovereign, the King of kings, and Lord of lords;
B054C006V016	54	6	16	Who alone has immortality, dwelling in light which no man can approach; whom no man has seen, nor can see. To him be honour and power and dominion forever. Amen.
B054C006V017	54	6	17	Command those who are rich in this world not to be arrogant, nor to trust in uncertain riches, but in the living God, who richly gives us all things to enjoy.
B054C006V018	54	6	18	They are to do good, that they may be rich in good works, generous and willing to share;
B054C006V019	54	6	19	Laying up for themselves a good foundation against the time to come, that they may take hold of that which is life indeed.
B054C006V020	54	6	20	O Timothy, guard that which has been entrusted to you. Avoid godless chatter and the contradictions of what is falsely called knowledge:
B054C006V021	54	6	21	Which some have professed and thus erred concerning the faith. Grace be with you.
B055C001V001	55	1	1	Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, according to the promise of life which is in Christ Jesus,
B055C001V002	55	1	2	To Timothy, my dearly beloved son: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
B055C001V003	55	1	3	I thank God, whom I serve as my forefathers did, with a pure conscience, as without ceasing I remember you night and day in my prayers.
B055C001V004	55	1	4	Remembering your tears, I greatly desire to see you, that I may be filled with joy;
B055C001V005	55	1	5	I am reminded of the sincere faith that is in you, which lived first in your grandmother Lois, and your mother Eunice; and I am persuaded is in you also.
B055C001V006	55	1	6	Therefore, I would remind you to stir into flame the gift of God, which is in you by the laying on of my hands.
B055C001V007	55	1	7	For God has not given us the spirit of fear; but of power, and of love, and of self-discipline.
B055C001V008	55	1	8	Therefore, do not be ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, nor of me his prisoner: but share in the afflictions of the gospel, by the power of God;
B055C001V009	55	1	9	Who has saved us, and called us with a holy calling, not by virtue of our works, but because of his own purpose and grace, which was given us in Christ Jesus from all eternity,
B055C001V010	55	1	10	But has now been made manifest by the appearing of our Saviour Jesus Christ, who has abolished death, and has brought life and immortality to light through the gospel.
B055C001V011	55	1	11	Of this gospel I was appointed a preacher, and an apostle, and a teacher,
B055C001V012	55	1	12	And for this reason I also suffer these things: nevertheless, I am not ashamed: for I know whom I have believed, and am persuaded that he is able to keep that which I have committed to him until that day.
B055C001V013	55	1	13	Hold fast the pattern of sound words which you have heard from me, in the faith and love which are in Christ Jesus.
B055C001V014	55	1	14	That good thing which was committed to you, guard by the Holy Spirit, who dwells within us.
B055C001V015	55	1	15	This you know, that all those who are in Asia have turned away from me; among whom are Phygelus and Hermogenes.
B055C001V016	55	1	16	May the Lord give mercy to the house of Onesiphorus; for he often refreshed me, and was not ashamed of my chains:
B055C001V017	55	1	17	But when he was in Rome, he sought me out very diligently, and found me.
B055C001V018	55	1	18	May the Lord grant that he will find mercy from the Lord on that day. You know very well in how many ways he ministered to me at Ephesus.
B055C002V001	55	2	1	Therefore, my son, be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus.
B055C002V002	55	2	2	And the things that you have heard from me among many witnesses, entrust these to faithful men, who shall be able to teach others also.
B055C002V003	55	2	3	Therefore endure hardship, as a good soldier of Christ Jesus.
B055C002V004	55	2	4	No soldier on active service entangles himself with the affairs of civilian life; that he may please him who has chosen him to be a soldier.
B055C002V005	55	2	5	And if anyone competes as an athlete, he is not crowned unless he competes according to the rules.
B055C002V006	55	2	6	The farmer who labours must be first to partake of the fruits.
B055C002V007	55	2	7	Consider what I say; and the Lord will give you understanding in all things.
B055C002V008	55	2	8	Remember Jesus Christ, raised from the dead, descended from David, according to my gospel,
B055C002V009	55	2	9	For which I suffer hardship, even wearing chains like a criminal; but the word of God is not in chains.
B055C002V010	55	2	10	Therefore, I endure all things for the sake of the chosen, that they may also obtain the salvation which is in Christ Jesus, with its eternal glory.
B055C002V011	55	2	11	This is a faithful saying: If we died with him, we shall also live with him:
B055C002V012	55	2	12	If we endure, we shall also reign with him: if we deny him, he will deny us:
B055C002V013	55	2	13	If we are faithless, yet he remains faithful: for he cannot deny himself.
B055C002V014	55	2	14	Remind them of these things, solemnly charging them before the Lord not to dispute about words, which is of no profit, but ruins the hearers.
B055C002V015	55	2	15	Be diligent to present yourself approved to God, a workman who does not need to be ashamed, rightly handling the word of truth.
B055C002V016	55	2	16	But avoid godless and empty chatter: for it will lead people to more ungodliness,
B055C002V017	55	2	17	And their word will spread like gangrene. Among these are Hymenaeus and Philetus;
B055C002V018	55	2	18	Who have strayed from the truth, saying that the resurrection is already past; and thus upset the faith of some.
B055C002V019	55	2	19	Nevertheless, the foundation of God stands firm, having this seal, The Lord knows those who are his. And, Let every one who names the name of the Lord depart from iniquity.
B055C002V020	55	2	20	In a great house there are not only vessels of gold and of silver, but also of wood and of clay; some for noble purposes, and some for ignoble.
B055C002V021	55	2	21	Therefore, if a man purifies himself from the ignoble, he shall be a vessel for noble purposes, consecrated and useful to the master, prepared for every good work.
B055C002V022	55	2	22	Flee youthful lusts: and follow righteousness, faith, love, and peace, with those who call on the Lord from a pure heart.
B055C002V023	55	2	23	Have nothing to do with foolish and ignorant controversies, knowing that they breed strife.
B055C002V024	55	2	24	And the servant of the Lord must not be quarrelsome; but kind to all, able to teach, forbearing,
B055C002V025	55	2	25	In gentleness correcting those who oppose him; that God might grant them repentance leading to the knowledge of the truth;
B055C002V026	55	2	26	And that they may come to their senses and escape the snare of the devil, who has taken them captive to do his will.
B055C003V001	55	3	1	But know this also, that in the last days perilous times shall come.
B055C003V002	55	3	2	For men shall be lovers of their own selves, lovers of money, boastful, arrogant, abusive, disobedient to parents, ungrateful, unholy,
B055C003V003	55	3	3	Without natural affection, implacable, false accusers, intemperate, fierce, despisers of good,
B055C003V004	55	3	4	Treacherous, rash, conceited, lovers of pleasures rather than lovers of God;
B055C003V005	55	3	5	Holding to a form of godliness, but denying its power. From such men turn away.
B055C003V006	55	3	6	For among them are those who creep into houses, and lead captive weak-willed women laden with sins, led away by various desires,
B055C003V007	55	3	7	Ever learning, but never able to acknowledge the truth.
B055C003V008	55	3	8	Now as Jannes and Jambres defied Moses, so these men also resist the truth: men of corrupt minds, rejected as concerns the faith.
B055C003V009	55	3	9	But they shall proceed no further: for their folly shall be made clear to all, as was that of those two.
B055C003V010	55	3	10	But you have fully known my teaching, manner of life, purpose, faith, patience, love, steadfastness,
B055C003V011	55	3	11	Persecutions, afflictions, such as befell me at Antioch, at Iconium, at Lystra; the persecutions I endured: but out of them all the Lord delivered me.
B055C003V012	55	3	12	Yes, and all who will live godly lives in Christ Jesus shall suffer persecution.
B055C003V013	55	3	13	But evil men and impostors shall grow worse and worse, deceiving, and being deceived.
B055C003V014	55	3	14	But you, continue to hold the things which you have learned and have been convinced of, knowing from whom you have learned them;
B055C003V015	55	3	15	And how from childhood you have known the holy scriptures, which are able to make you wise for salvation through faith which is in Christ Jesus.
B055C003V016	55	3	16	All scripture is given by inspiration of God, and is profitable for teaching, for reproof, for correction, for instruction in righteousness:
B055C003V017	55	3	17	That the man of God may be complete, thoroughly equipped for all good works.
B055C004V001	55	4	1	I solemnly charge you before God, and the Lord Jesus Christ, who shall judge the living and the dead, and by his appearing and his kingdom;
B055C004V002	55	4	2	Preach the word; be urgent in season and out of season; reprove, rebuke, exhort with all patience and instruction.
B055C004V003	55	4	3	For the time will come when they will not endure sound doctrine; but having itching ears, they shall gather up teachers for themselves to suit their own desires;
B055C004V004	55	4	4	And they shall turn their ears away from the truth, and shall turn aside to myths.
B055C004V005	55	4	5	But you, be steady in all things; endure afflictions, do the work of an evangelist, fulfill your ministry.
B055C004V006	55	4	6	For I am already being poured out as a drink offering, and the time of my departure is at hand.
B055C004V007	55	4	7	I have fought a good fight, I have finished my course, I have kept the faith:
B055C004V008	55	4	8	Henceforth, there is laid up for me a crown of righteousness, which the Lord, the righteous judge, shall give me on that day: and not only to me, but also to all those who have longed for his appearing.
B055C004V009	55	4	9	Make every effort to come to me shortly:
B055C004V010	55	4	10	For Demas, having loved this present world, has forsaken me and has departed to Thessalonica; Crescens has gone to Galatia, and Titus to Dalmatia.
B055C004V011	55	4	11	Only Luke is with me. Get Mark, and bring him with you: for he is useful to me for the ministry.
B055C004V012	55	4	12	Tychicus I have sent to Ephesus.
B055C004V013	55	4	13	When you come, bring with you the cloak that I left at Troas with Carpus, and the books, and especially the parchments.
B055C004V014	55	4	14	Alexander the coppersmith did me much harm: the Lord will repay him according to his deeds.
B055C004V015	55	4	15	You also beware of him; for he has greatly opposed our message.
B055C004V016	55	4	16	At my first defence no man stood with me, but all forsook me. May it not be counted against them.
B055C004V017	55	4	17	But the Lord stood with me, and strengthened me, that through me the message might be fully proclaimed, and that all the Gentiles might hear. And I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion.
B055C004V018	55	4	18	And the Lord shall deliver me from every evil work, and will bring me safely to his heavenly kingdom: to him be glory for ever and ever. Amen.
B055C004V019	55	4	19	Greet Prisca and Aquila, and the household of Onesiphorus.
B055C004V020	55	4	20	Erastus remained at Corinth: but Trophimus I left sick at Miletus.
B055C004V021	55	4	21	Do your best to come before winter. Eubulus greets you, as do Pudens, and Linus, and Claudia, and all the brethren.
B055C004V022	55	4	22	The Lord be with your spirit. Grace be with you.
B056C001V001	56	1	1	Paul, a servant of God, and an apostle of Jesus Christ, to further the faith of God's chosen and the knowledge of the truth which is according to godliness,
B056C001V002	56	1	2	Which rests in the hope of eternal life, which God, who cannot lie, promised before the beginning of time;
B056C001V003	56	1	3	And at the proper time he revealed his word through the preaching which was entrusted to me according to the commandment of God our Saviour;
B056C001V004	56	1	4	To Titus, my own child in our common faith: Grace and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Saviour.
B056C001V005	56	1	5	For this reason I left you in Crete, that you should set in order the things that remained, and appoint elders in every city, as I directed you.
B056C001V006	56	1	6	Elders must be blameless, the husband of one wife, whose children believe and are not accused of being profligate or unruly.
B056C001V007	56	1	7	For an overseer must be blameless, as the steward of God; not self-willed, not easily angered, not given to wine, not violent, not greedy for gain;
B056C001V008	56	1	8	But a lover of hospitality, a lover of good, sensible, just, holy, self-controlled;
B056C001V009	56	1	9	Holding fast the faithful word as he has been taught, that he may be able by sound doctrine both to exhort and to refute those who oppose it.
B056C001V010	56	1	10	For there are many unruly and empty talkers and deceivers, especially those of the circumcision:
B056C001V011	56	1	11	Whose mouths must be stopped, for they are subverting whole households, teaching things which they ought not, for sordid gain.
B056C001V012	56	1	12	One of themselves, a prophet of their own, said, Cretans are always liars, evil beasts, lazy gluttons.
B056C001V013	56	1	13	This testimony is true. Therefore rebuke them sharply, that they may be sound in the faith;
B056C001V014	56	1	14	Not giving heed to Jewish myths, and commandments of men who turn from the truth.
B056C001V015	56	1	15	To the pure all things are pure: but to those who are defiled and unbelieving, nothing is pure; but both their minds and consciences are defiled.
B056C001V016	56	1	16	They profess that they know God; but by their works they deny him; being detestable, and disobedient, and unfit for any good work.
B056C002V001	56	2	1	But as for you, speak the things which befit sound doctrine.
B056C002V002	56	2	2	Urge the older men to be temperate, dignified, sensible, sound in faith, in love, in steadfastness.
B056C002V003	56	2	3	Urge the older women likewise, to be reverent in behaviour, not malicious gossips, not slaves to much wine, but teaching good things;
B056C002V004	56	2	4	That they may train the young women to love their husbands, to love their children,
B056C002V005	56	2	5	To be sensible, chaste, workers at home, kind, obedient to their own husbands, that the word of God may not be maligned.
B056C002V006	56	2	6	Likewise, urge the young men to be self-controlled.
B056C002V007	56	2	7	In all things show yourself to be an example of good works, and in your teaching show purity, dignity,
B056C002V008	56	2	8	And sound speech, which cannot be condemned; so that he who is opposed may be ashamed, having no evil thing to say of us.
B056C002V009	56	2	9	Urge servants to be obedient to their own masters, and to please them well in all things; not to talk back,
B056C002V010	56	2	10	Not to pilfer, but showing entire and true fidelity; that they may adorn the doctrine of God our Saviour in all things.
B056C002V011	56	2	11	For the grace of God that brings salvation has appeared to all men,
B056C002V012	56	2	12	Teaching us to deny ungodliness and worldly desires, and live sensibly, righteously, and godly, in this present world;
B056C002V013	56	2	13	Looking for the blessed hope, the glorious appearing of our great God and Saviour Jesus Christ;
B056C002V014	56	2	14	Who gave himself up for us, that he might redeem us from all iniquity, and purify for himself a people of his own, zealous for good works.
B056C002V015	56	2	15	Speak these things, and exhort, and rebuke with all authority. Let no man disregard you.
B056C003V001	56	3	1	Remind them to be subject to rulers and authorities, to be obedient, to be ready to do every good work,
B056C003V002	56	3	2	To speak evil of no man, to be peaceable, gentle, showing all courtesy to all men.
B056C003V003	56	3	3	For we ourselves were once foolish, disobedient, deceived, slaves to various lusts and pleasures, living in malice and envy; hated, and hating one another.
B056C003V004	56	3	4	But when the kindness and love of God our Saviour appeared,
B056C003V005	56	3	5	He saved us, not because of works of righteousness which we have done, but according to his mercy, by the washing of regeneration, and renewing by the Holy Spirit;
B056C003V006	56	3	6	Whom he poured out upon us abundantly through Jesus Christ our Saviour;
B056C003V007	56	3	7	That being justified by his grace, we should be made heirs, having the hope of eternal life.
B056C003V008	56	3	8	This is a faithful saying; and I want you to affirm these things constantly, that those who have believed in God might be careful to engage in good works. These things are good and profitable for men.
B056C003V009	56	3	9	But avoid foolish controversies, and genealogies, and dissensions, and wrangling about the law; for they are unprofitable and futile.
B056C003V010	56	3	10	Reject a man who is divisive after a first and second warning;
B056C003V011	56	3	11	Knowing that such a man is perverted and sinful; condemned by himself.
B056C003V012	56	3	12	When I send Artemas or Tychicus to you, be diligent to come to me at Nicopolis: for I have determined to winter there.
B056C003V013	56	3	13	Be diligent to send Zenas the lawyer and Apollos on their way; see that they lack nothing.
B056C003V014	56	3	14	And let our people learn to engage in honest employment, so they may meet urgent needs, and that they may not be unfruitful.
B056C003V015	56	3	15	All who are with me greet you. Greet those who love us in the faith. Grace be with you all.
B057C001V001	57	1	1	Paul, a prisoner of Jesus Christ, and Timothy our brother, to Philemon our beloved fellow labourer,
B057C001V002	57	1	2	And to our sister Apphia, and Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the church in your house:
B057C001V003	57	1	3	Grace to you, and peace, from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
B057C001V004	57	1	4	I thank my God always, making mention of you in my prayers,
B057C001V005	57	1	5	Because I hear of your love and faith, which you have toward the Lord Jesus, and toward all the saints;
B057C001V006	57	1	6	And I pray that the sharing of your faith may promote the knowledge of every good thing which is ours in Christ Jesus.
B057C001V007	57	1	7	For we have great joy and comfort in your love, because the hearts of the saints have been refreshed by you, brother.
B057C001V008	57	1	8	Therefore, though I could be bold in Christ and order you that which is proper,
B057C001V009	57	1	9	Yet for love's sake I prefer to appeal to you, I, Paul, the aged, and now also a prisoner of Jesus Christ.
B057C001V010	57	1	10	I appeal to you for my son Onesimus, whom I have begotten while in these bonds:
B057C001V011	57	1	11	Who in times past was useless to you, but now is useful both to you and to me.
B057C001V012	57	1	12	I am sending him back to you, sending my very heart,
B057C001V013	57	1	13	Whom I would have kept with me, that in your place he might have ministered to me while I am in these bonds for the gospel:
B057C001V014	57	1	14	But without your consent I did not want to do anything; that your benevolence should not be, as it were, of necessity, but willingly.
B057C001V015	57	1	15	For perhaps he was parted from you for a while for this reason, that you should have him back forever;
B057C001V016	57	1	16	No longer as a slave, but more than a slave, as a beloved brother, especially to me, but how much more to you, both in the flesh, and in the Lord?
B057C001V017	57	1	17	Therefore, if you count me as a partner, receive him as you would me.
B057C001V018	57	1	18	If he has wronged you, or owes you anything, charge that to my account;
B057C001V019	57	1	19	I, Paul, am writing this with my own hand, I will repay it: to say nothing of how you owe to me even your own self as well.
B057C001V020	57	1	20	Yes, brother, let me have some benefit from you in the Lord: refresh my heart in Christ.
B057C001V021	57	1	21	Having confidence in your obedience, I write to you, knowing that you will do even more than I say.
B057C001V022	57	1	22	At the same time prepare me a guest room: for I hope that through your prayers I shall be given to you.
B057C001V023	57	1	23	Greetings to you from Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus;
B057C001V024	57	1	24	And from Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, and Luke, my fellow labourers.
B057C001V025	57	1	25	The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.
B058C001V001	58	1	1	God, who spoke in times past to our fathers by the prophets at many times and in various ways,
B058C001V002	58	1	2	Has in these last days spoken to us by his Son, whom he has appointed heir of all things, by whom also he made the worlds.
B058C001V003	58	1	3	He is the brightness of his glory, and the exact representation of his nature, upholding all things by the word of his power. When he had purged our sins, he sat down at the right hand of the Majesty on high;
B058C001V004	58	1	4	Having become as much superior to the angels as the name he has inherited is superior to theirs.
B058C001V005	58	1	5	For to which of the angels has he at any time said, You are my Son, this day I have begotten you? And again, I will be to him a Father, and he shall be to me a Son?
B058C001V006	58	1	6	And again, when he brings the firstborn into the world, he says, Let all the angels of God worship him.
B058C001V007	58	1	7	And of the angels he says, Who makes his angels winds, and his ministers flames of fire.
B058C001V008	58	1	8	But of the Son he says, Your throne, O God, is for ever and ever: a sceptre of righteousness is the sceptre of your kingdom.
B058C001V009	58	1	9	You have loved righteousness, and hated iniquity; therefore God, even your God, has anointed you with the oil of gladness above your fellows.
B058C001V010	58	1	10	And, You, Lord, did lay the foundation of the earth in the beginning; and the heavens are the works of your hands:
B058C001V011	58	1	11	They shall perish; but you remain; and they shall all grow old as does a garment;
B058C001V012	58	1	12	And as a mantle you shall fold them up, and they shall be changed: but you are the same, and your years shall never end.
B058C001V013	58	1	13	But to which of the angels did he at any time say, Sit on my right hand, until I make your enemies a footstool for your feet?
B058C001V014	58	1	14	Are they not all ministering spirits, sent forth to serve those who shall be heirs of salvation?
B058C002V001	58	2	1	Therefore, we ought to give the more earnest heed to the things which we have heard, lest at any time we should slip away.
B058C002V002	58	2	2	For if the word spoken by angels was binding, and every transgression and disobedience received a just recompence;
B058C002V003	58	2	3	How shall we escape, if we neglect so great a salvation? It was at first announced by the Lord, and was confirmed to us by those who heard him;
B058C002V004	58	2	4	God also bearing witness, both with signs and wonders, and with various miracles, and gifts of the Holy Spirit, according to his own will.
B058C002V005	58	2	5	For he did not put in subjection to the angels the world to come, of which we speak.
B058C002V006	58	2	6	But in a certain place someone testified, saying, What is man, that you are mindful of him? or the son of man, that you care for him?
B058C002V007	58	2	7	You made him a little lower than the angels; you crowned him with glory and honour, and did set him over the works of your hands:
B058C002V008	58	2	8	You have put all things in subjection under his feet. For in putting all in subjection under him, he left nothing that is not under him. But now we do not yet see all things put under him.
B058C002V009	58	2	9	But we see Jesus, who was made for a little while lower than the angels, crowned with glory and honour because he suffered death; that he, by the grace of God, should taste death for every man.
B058C002V010	58	2	10	For it was fitting that he, for whom are all things, and by whom are all things, in bringing many sons to glory, should make the author of their salvation perfect through suffering.
B058C002V011	58	2	11	For both he who sanctifies and those who are sanctified are all of one family: for which reason he is not ashamed to call them brethren,
B058C002V012	58	2	12	Saying, I will declare your name to my brethren, in the midst of the congregation I will sing praises to you.
B058C002V013	58	2	13	And again, I will put my trust in him. And again, Behold, here am I, and the children whom God has given me.
B058C002V014	58	2	14	Since then, as the children are partakers of flesh and blood, he himself also partook of the same; that through death he might destroy him who had the power of death, that is, the devil;
B058C002V015	58	2	15	And deliver those who through fear of death were all their lives subject to bondage.
B058C002V016	58	2	16	For truly he does not help angels; but he helps the descendants of Abraham.
B058C002V017	58	2	17	Therefore, in all things he had to be made like his brethren, that he might be a merciful and faithful high priest in things pertaining to God, to make atonement for the sins of the people.
B058C002V018	58	2	18	For since he himself has suffered in being tempted, he is able to help those who are tempted.
B058C003V001	58	3	1	Therefore, holy brethren, partakers of the heavenly calling, consider Jesus, the Apostle and High Priest of our profession;
B058C003V002	58	3	2	Who was faithful to him who appointed him, as also Moses was faithful in all his house.
B058C003V003	58	3	3	For this man was counted worthy of more glory than Moses, just as he who has built the house has more honour than the house.
B058C003V004	58	3	4	For every house has been built by someone; but he who is the builder of all things is God.
B058C003V005	58	3	5	And Moses was faithful in all his house, as a servant, as a testimony of those things which were to be spoken later;
B058C003V006	58	3	6	But Christ was faithful as a son over his own house, whose house we are, if we hold fast our confidence and our joyful hope.
B058C003V007	58	3	7	Therefore, as the Holy Spirit says, Today if you hear his voice,
B058C003V008	58	3	8	Do not harden your hearts, as in the rebellion, on the day of testing in the wilderness:
B058C003V009	58	3	9	When your fathers tested me, tried me, and saw my works for forty years.
B058C003V010	58	3	10	Therefore I was angry with that generation, and said, They always go astray in their hearts; and they have not known my ways.
B058C003V011	58	3	11	So I swore in my wrath, They shall not enter my rest.
B058C003V012	58	3	12	Take heed, brethren, lest there be in any of you an evil heart of unbelief, leading you to turn away from the living God.
B058C003V013	58	3	13	But encourage one another daily, while it is called Today; lest any of you be hardened by the deceitfulness of sin.
B058C003V014	58	3	14	For we have become partakers of Christ, if we hold our first confidence steadfast to the end;
B058C003V015	58	3	15	While it is said, Today if you will hear his voice, do not harden your hearts, as in the rebellion.
B058C003V016	58	3	16	For who were those who rebelled when they had heard? was it not all those who came out of Egypt led by Moses?
B058C003V017	58	3	17	And with whom was he angry for forty years? was it not with those who had sinned, whose bodies fell in the wilderness?
B058C003V018	58	3	18	And to whom did he swear that they should not enter his rest, but to those who disobeyed?
B058C003V019	58	3	19	So we see that they could not enter in because of unbelief.
B058C004V001	58	4	1	Therefore, let us fear, lest while a promise of entering into his rest remains, any of you should seem to fall short of it.
B058C004V002	58	4	2	For the gospel was preached to us, as well as to them: but the word preached did not benefit them, because it was not combined with faith in those who heard it.
B058C004V003	58	4	3	For we who have believed enter into that rest, as he said, As I have sworn in my wrath, they shall never enter my rest: although his works were finished from the foundation of the world.
B058C004V004	58	4	4	For he spoke in a certain place of the seventh day in this manner, And God rested on the seventh day from all his works.
B058C004V005	58	4	5	And again in this passage, They shall never enter my rest.
B058C004V006	58	4	6	Therefore, since it remains that some must enter in, and those to whom it was first preached did not enter in because of unbelief:
B058C004V007	58	4	7	He again fixes a certain day, calling it Today, saying through David after so long a time, as was said before, Today if you hear his voice, do not harden your hearts.
B058C004V008	58	4	8	For if Joshua had given them rest, then he would not afterward have spoken of another day.
B058C004V009	58	4	9	Therefore, there remains a sabbath rest for the people of God.
B058C004V010	58	4	10	For he who has entered his rest, has also has ceased from his own works, as God did from his.
B058C004V011	58	4	11	Therefore, let us labour to enter that rest, lest any man fall by following their example of disobedience.
B058C004V012	58	4	12	For the word of God is alive, and active, and sharper than any two-edged sword, piercing even to the division of soul and spirit, and of the joints and marrow, and discerning the thoughts and intents of the heart.
B058C004V013	58	4	13	Nor is there any creature concealed from his sight: but all are naked and exposed to the eyes of him to whom we must give account.
B058C004V014	58	4	14	Seeing then that we have a great high priest, who has passed through the heavens, Jesus the Son of God, let us hold fast our confession.
B058C004V015	58	4	15	For we do not have a high priest who cannot sympathize with our infirmities; but one who in every respect was tempted as we are, yet without sin.
B058C004V016	58	4	16	Therefore, let us boldly approach the throne of grace, that we may obtain mercy, and find grace to help in time of need.
B058C005V001	58	5	1	For every high priest chosen from among men is ordained to represent men in things pertaining to God, to offer both gifts and sacrifices for sins.
B058C005V002	58	5	2	He can have compassion on the ignorant, and on those who are going astray; for he also is subject to weakness.
B058C005V003	58	5	3	And for this reason he must offer sacrifices for sins, both for the people, and for himself.
B058C005V004	58	5	4	And no man takes this honour upon himself, but he is called by God, as was Aaron.
B058C005V005	58	5	5	So also Christ did not exalt himself to be made a high priest; but was appointed by him who said to him, You are my Son, today I have begotten you.
B058C005V006	58	5	6	As he also says in another place, You are a priest forever in the order of Melchizedek.
B058C005V007	58	5	7	In the days of his flesh, he offered up prayers and supplications with strong crying and tears to him who was able to save him from death, and he was heard because of his piety.
B058C005V008	58	5	8	Though he was a Son, yet he learned obedience through the things which he suffered;
B058C005V009	58	5	9	And being made perfect, he became the author of eternal salvation for all those who obey him;
B058C005V010	58	5	10	Being named by God as a high priest in the order of Melchizedek.
B058C005V011	58	5	11	Of him we have many things to say which are hard to explain, since you have become dull of hearing.
B058C005V012	58	5	12	For though by this time you ought to be teachers, you have need for someone to teach you again the first principles of the oracles of God. You have come to need milk, and not solid food.
B058C005V013	58	5	13	For everyone who lives on milk is unskilled in the word of righteousness: for he is a babe.
B058C005V014	58	5	14	But solid food belongs to those who are of full age, those who by practice have their senses trained to discern both good and evil.
B058C006V001	58	6	1	Therefore, leaving the elementary principles of the doctrine of Christ, let us go on to perfection; not laying again the foundation of repentance from dead works, and of faith toward God,
B058C006V002	58	6	2	Of instructions about baptisms, and of the laying on of hands, and of the resurrection of the dead, and of eternal judgment.
B058C006V003	58	6	3	And this we will do, if God permits.
B058C006V004	58	6	4	For it is impossible for those who were once enlightened, and have tasted of the heavenly gift, and have been made partakers of the Holy Spirit,
B058C006V005	58	6	5	And have tasted the good word of God, and the powers of the world to come,
B058C006V006	58	6	6	If they shall fall away, to be brought back again to repentance; for they crucify to themselves the Son of God afresh, and hold him up to public disgrace.
B058C006V007	58	6	7	For the earth which drinks in the rain that comes often upon it, and brings forth vegetation useful for those by whom it is farmed, receives a blessing from God:
B058C006V008	58	6	8	But that which bears thorns and thistles is worthless, and is near to being cursed; its end is to be burned.
B058C006V009	58	6	9	But, beloved, though we speak thus, we are persuaded of better things concerning you, things that accompany salvation.
B058C006V010	58	6	10	For God is not unrighteous, so as to forget the work and love which you have shown for his name's sake in having ministered to the saints, as you continue to do.
B058C006V011	58	6	11	And we desire that every one of you show the same diligence in realizing the full assurance of hope until the end:
B058C006V012	58	6	12	That you may not grow slothful, but be followers of those who through faith and patience inherit the promises.
B058C006V013	58	6	13	For when God made a promise to Abraham, because he could swear by no one greater, he swore by himself,
B058C006V014	58	6	14	Saying, Surely I will bless you and I will multiply you.
B058C006V015	58	6	15	And so, after he had patiently endured, he obtained the promise.
B058C006V016	58	6	16	For truly, men swear by one who is greater than themselves: and an oath given for confirmation puts an end to all disputes.
B058C006V017	58	6	17	Therefore God, wanting to show more clearly to the heirs of the promise the immutable nature of his purpose, confirmed it by an oath:
B058C006V018	58	6	18	That by two immutable things, in which it is impossible for God to lie, we who have fled for refuge to lay hold upon the hope set before us might have a strong encouragement.
B058C006V019	58	6	19	This hope we have as an anchor of the soul, both sure and steadfast, which enters within the veil;
B058C006V020	58	6	20	Where Jesus, the forerunner, has entered for us, having become a high priest forever in the order of Melchizedek.
B058C007V001	58	7	1	For this Melchizedek, king of Salem, priest of the most high God, met Abraham returning from the slaughter of the kings, and blessed him;
B058C007V002	58	7	2	And to him Abraham gave a tenth part of everything. He is first, by interpretation of his name, King of righteousness, and after that is also King of Salem, which is, King of peace.
B058C007V003	58	7	3	He is without father, without mother, without genealogy, having neither beginning of days, nor end of life; but like the Son of God, he remains a priest continually.
B058C007V004	58	7	4	Now consider how great this man was: to him even the patriarch Abraham gave a tenth of the spoils.
B058C007V005	58	7	5	And truly, those who are of the sons of Levi, who receive the office of the priesthood, have a commandment in the law to take tithes from the people, that is, from their brethren, though these also come out of the loins of Abraham:
B058C007V006	58	7	6	But he whose descent is not traced from them received a tithe from Abraham, and blessed him who had the promises.
B058C007V007	58	7	7	And without any dispute, the lesser is blessed by the greater.
B058C007V008	58	7	8	And here, men who die receive tithes; but there, they are received by him of whom it is witnessed that he lives.
B058C007V009	58	7	9	And, one might even say, Levi, who receives tithes, payed tithes through Abraham.
B058C007V010	58	7	10	For he was yet in the loins of his father, when Melchizedek met him.
B058C007V011	58	7	11	Therefore, if perfection was from the Levitical priesthood, (for under it the people received the law,) what further need was there for another priest to arise, in the order of Melchizedek, and not in the order of Aaron?
B058C007V012	58	7	12	For when the priesthood is changed, there is, of necessity, also a change in the law.
B058C007V013	58	7	13	For he of whom these things are spoken is from another tribe, from which no man ever served at the altar.
B058C007V014	58	7	14	For it is evident that our Lord sprang out of Judah; and of this tribe Moses spoke nothing concerning priests.
B058C007V015	58	7	15	And this becomes far more evident when, in the likeness of Melchizedek, another priest arises,
B058C007V016	58	7	16	Who is made such, not by a law concerning a physical requirement, but by the power of an endless life.
B058C007V017	58	7	17	For it is testified of him, You are a priest forever in the order of Melchizedek.
B058C007V018	58	7	18	So, there is a setting aside of the former commandment because of its weakness and uselessness,
B058C007V019	58	7	19	(For the law made nothing perfect;) but there is the bringing in of a better hope; by which we draw near to God.
B058C007V020	58	7	20	And it was not without an oath.
B058C007V021	58	7	21	For others were indeed made priests without an oath; but he with an oath from the one who said to him, The Lord has sworn and will not change his mind, You are a priest forever.
B058C007V022	58	7	22	By this has Jesus become the guarantee of a better covenant.
B058C007V023	58	7	23	And there were many priests, because they were prevented by death from continuing:
B058C007V024	58	7	24	But he, because he continues forever, has a perpetual priesthood.
B058C007V025	58	7	25	Therefore, he is also able to completely save those who come to God through him, for he ever lives to make intercession for them.
B058C007V026	58	7	26	For it was fitting for us to have such a high priest, holy, blameless, undefiled, separate from sinners, and exalted above the heavens;
B058C007V027	58	7	27	Who has no need, as do those high priests, to offer up daily sacrifices, first for his own sins, and then for those of the people: for this he did once for all, when he offered up himself.
B058C007V028	58	7	28	For the law appoints men, who are frail, to be high priests; but the word of the oath, which came after the law, appoints the Son, who has been made perfect forever.
B058C008V001	58	8	1	Now of that which we have spoken, this is the sum: We have such a high priest, who is seated on the right hand of the throne of the Majesty in heaven;
B058C008V002	58	8	2	A minister in the sanctuary, in the true tabernacle, which the Lord pitched, not man.
B058C008V003	58	8	3	For every high priest is appointed to offer gifts and sacrifices: therefore it is necessary that this one also have something to offer.
B058C008V004	58	8	4	Now if he were on earth, he would not be a priest, for there are priests who offer gifts according to the law.
B058C008V005	58	8	5	They serve at a copy and shadow of the heavenly sanctuary. This is why, when Moses was about to make the tabernacle, he was warned by God, saying, See that you make all things according to the pattern shown to you on the mountain.
B058C008V006	58	8	6	But now he has obtained a ministry that is as much superior to the old as the covenant of which he is the mediator is superior, for it was established upon better promises.
B058C008V007	58	8	7	For if the first covenant had been faultless, then there would have been no occasion sought for a second.
B058C008V008	58	8	8	For he finds fault with them, saying, Behold, the days will come, says the Lord, when I will make a new covenant with the house of Israel and with the house of Judah:
B058C008V009	58	8	9	Not like the covenant that I made with their fathers in the day when I took them by the hand to lead them out of the land of Egypt; for they did not continue in my covenant, and I turned away from them, says the Lord.
B058C008V010	58	8	10	For this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel after those days, says the Lord; I will put my laws into their minds, and write them on their hearts: and I will be their God, and they shall be my people:
B058C008V011	58	8	11	And no longer shall every man teach his neighbour, and every man his brother, saying, Know the Lord: for all shall know me, from the least to the greatest.
B058C008V012	58	8	12	For I will be merciful to their unrighteousness, and their sins I will remember no more.
B058C008V013	58	8	13	When he says, A new covenant, he has made the first one obsolete. Now that which is obsolete and grows old is ready to vanish away.
B058C009V001	58	9	1	Now truly, the first covenant had ordinances of divine service, and an earthly sanctuary.
B058C009V002	58	9	2	For there was a tabernacle prepared, in the first room of which was the lampstand, and the table, and the bread of the presence; this is called the sanctuary.
B058C009V003	58	9	3	And behind the second veil stood the room of the tabernacle which is called the Holiest of all;
B058C009V004	58	9	4	Which had the golden altar of incense, and the ark of the covenant overlaid round about with gold, in which was the golden jar that had manna, and Aaron's rod that budded, and the tables of the covenant;
B058C009V005	58	9	5	And over it were the cherubim of glory overshadowing the mercy seat; of which we cannot now speak in detail.
B058C009V006	58	9	6	Now when these preparations had been made, the priests went regularly into the first room of the tabernacle, performing their ministry.
B058C009V007	58	9	7	But into the second the high priest went alone, once every year, and not without blood, which he offered for himself, and for the sins the people committed in ignorance.
B058C009V008	58	9	8	By this the Holy Spirit signifies that the way into the holiest of all has not yet been disclosed, while the first room of the tabernacle remains standing,
B058C009V009	58	9	9	Which is a symbol for the present age, in which both gifts and sacrifices are offered which cannot make the worshipper perfect in conscience;
B058C009V010	58	9	10	For they are only a matter of food and drink, and various washings, and regulations for the body, imposed until the time of reformation.
B058C009V011	58	9	11	But when Christ appeared as a high priest of the good things to come, then, through a greater and more perfect tabernacle, not made with hands, that is to say, not of this creation;
B058C009V012	58	9	12	Nor by the blood of goats and calves, but by his own blood, he entered once for all into the holy place, having obtained eternal redemption.
B058C009V013	58	9	13	For if the blood of bulls and of goats, and the ashes of a heifer sprinkling those who are unclean, sanctifies them so their flesh is clean:
B058C009V014	58	9	14	How much more shall the blood of Christ, who through the eternal Spirit offered himself without spot to God, cleanse your consciences from dead works to serve the living God?
B058C009V015	58	9	15	And for this reason he is the mediator of a new covenant, since a death has taken place for the redemption of the transgressions committed under the first covenant, those who are called may receive the promised eternal inheritance.
B058C009V016	58	9	16	For where there is a will, the death of the testator must be established.
B058C009V017	58	9	17	For a will is in force only upon death: it has no strength at all while the testator lives.
B058C009V018	58	9	18	Therefore, even the first covenant was not inaugurated without blood.
B058C009V019	58	9	19	For when Moses had spoken every commandment to all the people according to the law, he took the blood of calves and of goats, with water, and scarlet wool, and hyssop, and sprinkled both the book, and all the people,
B058C009V020	58	9	20	Saying, This is the blood of the covenant which God has commanded you to keep.
B058C009V021	58	9	21	In the same way, he sprinkled with blood both the tabernacle, and all the vessels used in the ministry.
B058C009V022	58	9	22	Indeed, under the law almost all things are cleansed with blood; and without the shedding of blood there is no forgiveness.
B058C009V023	58	9	23	It was, therefore, necessary that the copies of the heavenly things should be purified with these sacrifices; but the heavenly things themselves with better sacrifices than these.
B058C009V024	58	9	24	For Christ has not entered a holy place made with hands, a copy of the true one; but into heaven itself, now to appear in the presence of God for us.
B058C009V025	58	9	25	Nor does he need to offer himself often, as the high priest enters into the holy place every year with blood not his own;
B058C009V026	58	9	26	For then he would have needed to suffer often since the foundation of the world: but now he has appeared once at the end of the ages to put away sin by the sacrifice of himself.
B058C009V027	58	9	27	And as it is appointed for men once to die, and after this comes judgment:
B058C009V028	58	9	28	So Christ, having been offered once to bear the sins of many; shall appear a second time, not to bear sin, but to bring full salvation to those who eagerly await him.
B058C010V001	58	10	1	For the law, being only a shadow of the good things to come, and not the very image of the things, can never by those sacrifices, which are offered year by year, continually, make perfect those who draw near.
B058C010V002	58	10	2	Otherwise, would they not have ceased being offered? because the worshippers, once cleansed, would no longer have had a consciousness of sins.
B058C010V003	58	10	3	But those sacrifices are a reminder of sins every year.
B058C010V004	58	10	4	For it is not possible that the blood of bulls and of goats should take away sins.
B058C010V005	58	10	5	Therefore, when he came into the world, he said, Sacrifice and offering you did not desire, but a body you have prepared for me;
B058C010V006	58	10	6	In burnt offerings and sacrifices for sin you have had no pleasure.
B058C010V007	58	10	7	Then I said, Lo, I come (in the scroll of the book it is written of me,) to do your will, O God.
B058C010V008	58	10	8	After he said above, Sacrifices and offerings and burnt offerings and offerings for sin you did not desire, neither did you have pleasure in them, which are offered according to the law;
B058C010V009	58	10	9	Then said he, Lo, I come to do your will, O God. He takes away the first, that he may establish the second.
B058C010V010	58	10	10	And by that will we have been sanctified through the offering of the body of Jesus Christ once for all.
B058C010V011	58	10	11	Every priest stands daily ministering and offering, time and again, the same sacrifices, which can never take away sins.
B058C010V012	58	10	12	But this man, after he had offered one sacrifice for sins forever, sat down on the right hand of God;
B058C010V013	58	10	13	From that time on waiting until his enemies are made his footstool.
B058C010V014	58	10	14	For by one offering he has perfected forever those who are sanctified.
B058C010V015	58	10	15	And the Holy Spirit also is a witness to us: for after he said,
B058C010V016	58	10	16	This is the covenant that I will make with them after those days, says the Lord, I will put my laws into their hearts, and in their minds I will write them;
B058C010V017	58	10	17	Then he adds, Their sins and iniquities I will remember no more.
B058C010V018	58	10	18	Now where there is forgiveness of these, there is no longer an offering for sin.
B058C010V019	58	10	19	Therefore, brethren, having boldness to enter the most holy place by the blood of Jesus,
B058C010V020	58	10	20	By a new and living way which he has opened for us through the veil, that is to say, his flesh;
B058C010V021	58	10	21	And since we have a high priest over the house of God,
B058C010V022	58	10	22	Let us draw near with a true heart in full assurance of faith, having our hearts sprinkled clean from an evil conscience, and our bodies washed with pure water.
B058C010V023	58	10	23	Let us hold fast the profession of our hope, without wavering; (for he who promised is faithful;)
B058C010V024	58	10	24	And let us consider how to arouse one another to love and to good works:
B058C010V025	58	10	25	Not forsaking the assembling of ourselves together, as is the manner of some; but exhorting one another: and so much the more, as you see the day approaching.
B058C010V026	58	10	26	For if we sin wilfully after we have received the knowledge of the truth, there remains no more sacrifice for sins,
B058C010V027	58	10	27	But a certain fearful expectation of judgment and fiery indignation, which shall devour the adversaries.
B058C010V028	58	10	28	He who despised Moses' law died without mercy on the testimony of two or three witnesses:
B058C010V029	58	10	29	How much more severe punishment do you suppose he shall deserve, who has trodden under foot the Son of God, and has counted the blood of the covenant, with which he was sanctified, an unholy thing, and has affronted the Spirit of grace?
B058C010V030	58	10	30	For we know him who has said, Vengeance belongs to me, I will repay. And again, The Lord shall judge his people.
B058C010V031	58	10	31	It is a fearful thing to fall into the hands of the living God.
B058C010V032	58	10	32	But call to remembrance the former days, in which, after you were illuminated, you endured a great struggle in the face of afflictions;
B058C010V033	58	10	33	Sometimes you were made a public spectacle by insults and afflictions; and sometimes, because you became companions to those who were so treated.
B058C010V034	58	10	34	For you had compassion on the prisoners, and joyfully accepted the confiscation of your goods, knowing that you have a better possession, and an enduring one.
B058C010V035	58	10	35	Therefore, do not cast away your confidence, which has a great reward.
B058C010V036	58	10	36	For you have need of endurance, that, after you have done the will of God, you might receive the promise.
B058C010V037	58	10	37	For yet a little while longer, and he who shall come will come, and will not tarry.
B058C010V038	58	10	38	But my righteous one shall live by faith: but if any man draws back, my soul shall have no pleasure in him.
B058C010V039	58	10	39	But we are not of those who draw back to destruction; but of those who have faith and preserve their souls.
B058C011V001	58	11	1	Now faith is the assurance of things hoped for, the conviction of things not seen.
B058C011V002	58	11	2	For by it the men of old obtained approval.
B058C011V003	58	11	3	Through faith we understand that the worlds were framed by the word of God, so that things which are seen were made of things which do not appear.
B058C011V004	58	11	4	By faith Abel offered to God a more excellent sacrifice than Cain, and by it he obtained the testimony that he was righteous, God testifying of his gifts: and by faith, though he is dead, yet he speaks.
B058C011V005	58	11	5	By faith Enoch was caught up so that he should not see death; and he was not found, because God had taken him: now before he was taken he received this testimony, that he pleased God.
B058C011V006	58	11	6	But without faith it is impossible to please him: for he who comes to God must believe that he is, and that he is a rewarder of those who diligently seek him.
B058C011V007	58	11	7	By faith Noah, being warned by God of things not yet seen, reverently prepared an ark for the saving of his household; by which he condemned the world, and became heir of the righteousness which is by faith.
B058C011V008	58	11	8	By faith Abraham, when he was called to go out to a place which he should later receive as an inheritance, obeyed; and he went out, not knowing where he was to go.
B058C011V009	58	11	9	By faith he sojourned in the land of promise, as in a foreign country, dwelling in tents with Isaac and Jacob, heirs with him of the same promise:
B058C011V010	58	11	10	For he looked for a city which has foundations, whose architect and builder is God.
B058C011V011	58	11	11	Through faith Sarah herself received the ability to conceive, and delivered a child when she was past age, because she judged him faithful who had promised.
B058C011V012	58	11	12	Therefore there was born from one man, and him as good as dead, a multitude as great as the stars of the sky, and as innumerable as the sand which is on the sea shore.
B058C011V013	58	11	13	These all died in faith, not having received the promises, but having seen them afar off; and they were persuaded of them, and embraced them, and confessed that they were strangers and exiles on the earth.
B058C011V014	58	11	14	For those who say such things declare plainly that they seek a country of their own.
B058C011V015	58	11	15	And truly, if they had been thinking of that country from which they came out, they would have had opportunity to return.
B058C011V016	58	11	16	Instead, they desire a better country, that is, a heavenly one. Therefore God is not ashamed to be called their God: for he has prepared for them a city.
B058C011V017	58	11	17	By faith Abraham, when he was tested, offered up Isaac: he who had received the promises was ready to offer up his only begotten son,
B058C011V018	58	11	18	Of whom it was said, In Isaac shall your descendants be named:
B058C011V019	58	11	19	For he reasoned that God was able to raise him up, even from the dead; from which, figuratively, he did receive him back.
B058C011V020	58	11	20	By faith Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau concerning things to come.
B058C011V021	58	11	21	By faith Jacob, when he was dying, blessed each of the sons of Joseph; and worshipped, leaning upon the top of his staff.
B058C011V022	58	11	22	By faith Joseph, at the end of his life, made mention of the exodus of the children of Israel; and gave orders concerning his bones.
B058C011V023	58	11	23	By faith Moses, when he was born, was hidden for three months by his parents, because they saw he was a beautiful child; and they were not afraid of the king's decree.
B058C011V024	58	11	24	By faith Moses, when he was grown, refused to be called the son of Pharaoh's daughter;
B058C011V025	58	11	25	Choosing rather to suffer affliction with the people of God, than to enjoy the fleeting pleasures of sin;
B058C011V026	58	11	26	Considering abuse for the sake of Christ greater riches than the treasures of Egypt: for he looked ahead to the reward.
B058C011V027	58	11	27	By faith he left Egypt, not fearing the wrath of the king: for he endured, as seeing him who is invisible.
B058C011V028	58	11	28	By faith he kept the passover, and the sprinkling of blood, lest he who destroyed the firstborn should touch them.
B058C011V029	58	11	29	By faith they passed through the Red sea as on dry land: but when the Egyptians attempted to do so, they were drowned.
B058C011V030	58	11	30	By faith the walls of Jericho fell down, after they were encircled for seven days.
B058C011V031	58	11	31	By faith the prostitute Rahab did not perish with those who were disobedient, because she had received the spies in peace.
B058C011V032	58	11	32	And what more shall I say? for time would fail me if I told of Gideon, and of Barak, and of Samson, and of Jephthah; of David, and Samuel, and of the prophets:
B058C011V033	58	11	33	Who through faith subdued kingdoms, established justice, obtained promises, closed the mouths of lions,
B058C011V034	58	11	34	Quenched the power of the raging fire, escaped the edge of the sword, out of weakness were made strong, grew mighty in battle, turned foreign armies to flight.
B058C011V035	58	11	35	Women received their dead, raised to life again: and others were tortured, not accepting deliverance; that they might obtain a better resurrection:
B058C011V036	58	11	36	And others suffered mockings and scourgings, yea, even chains and imprisonment:
B058C011V037	58	11	37	They were stoned, they were sawn apart, they were tempted, they were slain with the sword: they wandered about in sheepskins and goatskins; being destitute, afflicted, tormented;
B058C011V038	58	11	38	(Men of whom the world was not worthy:) they wandered in deserts, and in mountains, and in dens and caves of the earth.
B058C011V039	58	11	39	And all these, having obtained approval through their faith, did not receive the promise,
B058C011V040	58	11	40	Because God had provided something better for us, that without us they should not be made perfect.
B058C012V001	58	12	1	Therefore, seeing we are surrounded by so great a cloud of witnesses, let us lay aside every weight, and the sin which does so easily entangle us, and let us run with endurance the race that is set before us,
B058C012V002	58	12	2	Looking to Jesus the author and finisher of our faith; who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, despising the shame, and sat down at the right hand of the throne of God.
B058C012V003	58	12	3	For consider him who endured such hostility from sinners against himself, lest you grow weary and fainthearted.
B058C012V004	58	12	4	You have not yet resisted to the point of shedding your blood in your striving against sin.
B058C012V005	58	12	5	And you have forgotten the exhortation which speaks to you as sons, My son, do not think lightly of the discipline of the Lord, nor faint when you are rebuked by him:
B058C012V006	58	12	6	For whom the Lord loves, he disciplines, and scourges every son whom he receives.
B058C012V007	58	12	7	You must endure for discipline. God deals with you as with sons; for what son is there whom his father does not discipline?
B058C012V008	58	12	8	But if you are left without discipline, of which all are partakers, then are you are illegitimate children, and not sons.
B058C012V009	58	12	9	Furthermore, we have had earthly fathers who corrected us, and we gave them respect: shall we not much more be in subjection to the Father of spirits, and live?
B058C012V010	58	12	10	For they disciplined us for a short time as seemed best to them; but he disciplines us for our good, that we might be partakers of his holiness.
B058C012V011	58	12	11	At the time, no discipline seems to be joyful, but painful: nevertheless, afterward it yields the peaceable fruit of righteousness for those who have been trained by it.
B058C012V012	58	12	12	Therefore, strengthen the hands which hang down, and the feeble knees;
B058C012V013	58	12	13	And make straight paths for your feet, so that which is lame may not be put out of joint; but rather be healed.
B058C012V014	58	12	14	Follow peace with all men, and holiness, without which no man shall see the Lord.
B058C012V015	58	12	15	See to it that no man fails to obtain the grace of God; lest any root of bitterness springing up should trouble you, and thereby defile many;
B058C012V016	58	12	16	That there be no sexually immoral, or godless person, like Esau, who for one meal sold his birthright.
B058C012V017	58	12	17	For you know that afterward, when he wanted to inherit the blessing, he was rejected: for he found no place for repentance, though he sought it with tears.
B058C012V018	58	12	18	For you have not come to a mountain that may be touched, that burns with fire, and to darkness, and gloom, and tempest,
B058C012V019	58	12	19	And the sound of a trumpet, and the voice whose words made those who heard beg that no further word should be spoken to them.
B058C012V020	58	12	20	For they could not endure that which was commanded: If so much as a beast touches the mountain, it must be stoned.
B058C012V021	58	12	21	And so terrible was the sight, that Moses said, I am exceedingly afraid and tremble.
B058C012V022	58	12	22	But you have come to mount Zion, and to the city of the living God, the heavenly Jerusalem, and to an innumerable company of angels,
B058C012V023	58	12	23	To the general assembly and church of the first-born, whose names are written in heaven, and to God the Judge of all, and to the spirits of righteous men made perfect,
B058C012V024	58	12	24	And to Jesus, the mediator of the new covenant, and to the sprinkled blood, that speaks better things than that of Abel.
B058C012V025	58	12	25	See that you do not refuse him who speaks. For if they did not escape who refused him who warned them on earth, much less shall we escape, if we turn away from him who warns us from heaven.
B058C012V026	58	12	26	And his voice shook the earth then: but now he has promised, saying, Yet once more I will shake not only the earth, but also heaven.
B058C012V027	58	12	27	And the words, Yet once more, signify the removal of those things which can be shaken, of created things, that those things which cannot be shaken may remain.
B058C012V028	58	12	28	Therefore, since we receive a kingdom which cannot be shaken, let us be grateful, and worship God acceptably, with reverence and awe:
B058C012V029	58	12	29	For our God is a consuming fire.
B058C013V001	58	13	1	Let brotherly love continue.
B058C013V002	58	13	2	Do not forget to show hospitality to strangers: for by so doing some have entertained angels without knowing it.
B058C013V003	58	13	3	Remember those who are in prison, as if in prison with them; and those who suffer adversity, since you yourselves are also in the body.
B058C013V004	58	13	4	Marriage is to be held in honour by all, and the marriage bed is to be undefiled: for the sexually immoral and adulterers God will judge.
B058C013V005	58	13	5	Let your lives be free from the love of money; and be content with such things as you have: for he has said, I will never leave you, nor forsake you.
B058C013V006	58	13	6	So we may boldly say, The Lord is my helper, and I will not fear what man can do to me.
B058C013V007	58	13	7	Remember those who lead you, who have spoken to you the word of God: consider the outcome of their way of life, and imitate their faith.
B058C013V008	58	13	8	Jesus Christ is the same yesterday, and today, and forever.
B058C013V009	58	13	9	Do not be carried away by varied and strange doctrines. For it is a good thing for the heart to be established by grace, not by foods, which have not benefitted those who have been occupied with them.
B058C013V010	58	13	10	We have an altar, from which those who serve at the tabernacle have no right to eat.
B058C013V011	58	13	11	For the bodies of those animals, whose blood is brought into the sanctuary by the high priest as an offering for sin, are burned outside the camp.
B058C013V012	58	13	12	Therefore Jesus also, that he might sanctify the people by his own blood, suffered outside the gate.
B058C013V013	58	13	13	Therefore, let us go forth to him outside the camp, bearing his reproach.
B058C013V014	58	13	14	For here we do not have an enduring city, but we seek the one which is to come.
B058C013V015	58	13	15	Therefore, through him let us continually offer a sacrifice of praise to God, that is, the fruit of lips that confess his name.
B058C013V016	58	13	16	Do not forget to do good and to share: for with such sacrifices God is well pleased.
B058C013V017	58	13	17	Obey those who lead you, and submit to them: for they watch over your souls as those who must give account. Let it be a joyful task for them, not a sad one: for that would be unprofitable for you.
B058C013V018	58	13	18	Pray for us: for we are sure we have a good conscience, in all things desiring to live honestly.
B058C013V019	58	13	19	I urge you more earnestly to do this, that I may be restored to you the sooner.
B058C013V020	58	13	20	Now may the God of peace, who brought back from the dead our Lord Jesus, the great shepherd of the sheep, through the blood of the eternal covenant,
B058C013V021	58	13	21	Equip you with every good thing to do his will, working in you that which is well-pleasing in his sight, through Jesus Christ; to whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.
B058C013V022	58	13	22	And I urge you, brethren, bear with this word of exhortation: for I have written to you a letter of few words.
B058C013V023	58	13	23	I want you to know that our brother Timothy has been set at liberty; with whom, if he arrives shortly, I will come to see you.
B058C013V024	58	13	24	Greet all those who lead you, and all the saints. Those in Italy greet you.
B058C013V025	58	13	25	Grace be with you all. Amen.
B059C001V001	59	1	1	James, a servant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, to the twelve tribes which are scattered abroad, greetings.
B059C001V002	59	1	2	My brethren, count it all joy when you encounter various trials;
B059C001V003	59	1	3	Knowing that the trying of your faith produces endurance.
B059C001V004	59	1	4	And let endurance have its full effect, that you may be perfect and complete, lacking nothing.
B059C001V005	59	1	5	If any of you lack wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives to all men liberally, and without reproach; and it shall be given him.
B059C001V006	59	1	6	But let him ask in faith, without wavering. For he who wavers is like a wave of the sea driven by the wind and tossed.
B059C001V007	59	1	7	Let not that man think that he shall receive anything from the Lord,
B059C001V008	59	1	8	For a double-minded man is unstable in all his ways.
B059C001V009	59	1	9	Let the brother of humble circumstances rejoice that he is exalted:
B059C001V010	59	1	10	And the rich, that he is made humble: because like the flower of the grass he shall pass away.
B059C001V011	59	1	11	For the sun has no sooner risen with a burning heat, but it withers the grass, and its flower falls, and its beauty perishes. In the same way shall the rich man fade away in the midst of his pursuits.
B059C001V012	59	1	12	Blessed is the man who endures trial: for when he has stood the test, he shall receive the crown of life, which the Lord has promised to those who love him.
B059C001V013	59	1	13	Let no man say when he is tempted, I am tempted by God: for God cannot be tempted with evil, nor does he tempt any man:
B059C001V014	59	1	14	But every man is tempted, when he is drawn away and enticed by his own lust.
B059C001V015	59	1	15	Then when lust has conceived, it brings forth sin: and sin, when it is fully-grown, brings forth death.
B059C001V016	59	1	16	Do not be deceived, my beloved brethren.
B059C001V017	59	1	17	Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and comes down from the Father of lights, with whom there is no variation or shifting shadow.
B059C001V018	59	1	18	By his own will he brought us forth with the word of truth, that we should be a kind of first-fruits of his creatures.
B059C001V019	59	1	19	Therefore, my beloved brethren, let every man be swift to hear, slow to speak, and slow to anger:
B059C001V020	59	1	20	For the anger of man does not promote the righteousness of God.
B059C001V021	59	1	21	Therefore, lay aside all filthiness and the wickedness that is so abundant, and receive with humility the implanted word, which is able to save your souls.
B059C001V022	59	1	22	But be doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving yourselves.
B059C001V023	59	1	23	For if anyone is a hearer of the word, and not a doer, he is like a man beholding his natural face in a mirror:
B059C001V024	59	1	24	For he beholds himself, and goes his way, and immediately forgets what manner of man he was.
B059C001V025	59	1	25	But whoever looks into the perfect law of liberty, and perseveres in it, not being a forgetful hearer, but an active doer, this man shall be blessed in what he does.
B059C001V026	59	1	26	If any man among you thinks he is religious, but does not bridle his tongue, he deceives his own heart and his religion is in vain.
B059C001V027	59	1	27	This is pure and undefiled religion before God the Father: To visit the fatherless and widows in their affliction, and to keep oneself unspotted by the world.
B059C002V001	59	2	1	My brethren, do not hold your faith in our Lord Jesus Christ, the Lord of glory, with partiality.
B059C002V002	59	2	2	For if there comes into your assembly a man with a gold ring, in fine apparel, and there also comes in a poor man in shabby clothing,
B059C002V003	59	2	3	And you pay special attention to him who wears the fine clothing, and say to him, Sit here in a good place; and say to the poor man, Stand there, or sit here beside my footstool:
B059C002V004	59	2	4	Have you not then discriminated among yourselves, and become judges with evil thoughts?
B059C002V005	59	2	5	Listen, my beloved brethren, Has not God chosen the poor of this world to be rich in faith, and heirs of the kingdom which he has promised to those who love him?
B059C002V006	59	2	6	But you have despised the poor. Is it not the rich who oppress you, and drag you into court?
B059C002V007	59	2	7	Is it not they who blaspheme the noble name by which you have been called?
B059C002V008	59	2	8	If you fulfill the royal law, according to the scripture, You shall love your neighbour as yourself, you do well,
B059C002V009	59	2	9	But if you show partiality, you commit sin, and are convicted by the law as transgressors.
B059C002V010	59	2	10	For whoever shall keep the whole law, and yet stumble at one point, is guilty of breaking it all.
B059C002V011	59	2	11	For he who said, Do not commit adultery, also said, Do not kill. Now if you do not commit adultery, but you do kill, you have become a transgressor of the law.
B059C002V012	59	2	12	So speak, and so act, as those who shall be judged by the law of liberty.
B059C002V013	59	2	13	For he shall receive judgment without mercy, who has shown no mercy; mercy triumphs over judgment.
B059C002V014	59	2	14	What does it profit, my brethren, if a man say he has faith, but has not works? can that faith save him?
B059C002V015	59	2	15	If a brother or sister is without clothing, and destitute of daily food,
B059C002V016	59	2	16	And one of you says to him, Depart in peace, be warmed and filled; yet you do not give him the things which are necessary for the body; of what benefit is that?
B059C002V017	59	2	17	Even so faith, if it does not have works, is dead, being alone.
B059C002V018	59	2	18	But a man may say, You have faith, and I have works: show me your faith without your works, and I will show you my faith by my works.
B059C002V019	59	2	19	You believe that there is one God; you do well: the devils believe also, and tremble.
B059C002V020	59	2	20	Do you want to be shown, O foolish man, that faith without works is dead?
B059C002V021	59	2	21	Was not Abraham our father justified by works, when he offered Isaac his son upon the altar?
B059C002V022	59	2	22	You see that faith was active with his works, and by works was faith made perfect;
B059C002V023	59	2	23	And the scripture was fulfilled which says, Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness: and he was called the Friend of God.
B059C002V024	59	2	24	You see then that a man is justified by works, and not by faith only.
B059C002V025	59	2	25	And in the same way was not Rahab the prostitute justified by works, when she received the messengers, and had sent them out another way?
B059C002V026	59	2	26	For as the body without the spirit is dead, so faith without works is dead.
B059C003V001	59	3	1	My brethren, let not many of you be teachers, knowing that as such we shall be judged more strictly.
B059C003V002	59	3	2	For we all stumble in many ways. If any man does not stumble in his words, he is a perfect man, and able also to bridle his whole body.
B059C003V003	59	3	3	If we put bits in the mouths of horses, that they may obey us; we guide their whole bodies.
B059C003V004	59	3	4	Behold also the ships, which, though they are so great and are driven by such fierce winds, yet they are guided by a very small rudder, wherever the pilot directs.
B059C003V005	59	3	5	Even so, the tongue is a small part of the body, and it boasts of great things. Behold how great a forest is kindled by a little fire!
B059C003V006	59	3	6	And the tongue is a fire, a world of iniquity among our members. It defiles the whole body, and sets on fire the whole course of life; and is itself set on fire by hell.
B059C003V007	59	3	7	For all kinds of beasts, and birds, and serpents, and creatures of the sea, are tamed, and have been tamed, by mankind:
B059C003V008	59	3	8	But the tongue no man can tame; it is an unruly evil, full of deadly poison.
B059C003V009	59	3	9	With it we bless our Lord and Father; and with it we curse men, who are made in the likeness of God.
B059C003V010	59	3	10	Out of the same mouth proceeds blessing and cursing. My brethren, these things ought not to be so.
B059C003V011	59	3	11	Does a fountain send forth from the same opening fresh and bitter water?
B059C003V012	59	3	12	Can the fig tree, my brethren, bear olives? or a vine bear figs? Neither can a salt spring yield fresh water.
B059C003V013	59	3	13	Who is wise and understanding among you? by his good life let him show forth works done with the humility of wisdom.
B059C003V014	59	3	14	But if you have bitter envy and selfish ambition in your hearts, do not boast and lie against the truth.
B059C003V015	59	3	15	This wisdom does not descend from above, but is earthly, unspiritual, devilish.
B059C003V016	59	3	16	For where there is envy and selfish ambition, there is confusion and every evil work.
B059C003V017	59	3	17	But the wisdom that is from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle, and open to reason, full of mercy and good fruits, without partiality, and without hypocrisy.
B059C003V018	59	3	18	And the harvest of righteousness is sown in peace by those who make peace.
B059C004V001	59	4	1	What causes strife and quarrels among you? do they not come from your passions, which are at war in your members?
B059C004V002	59	4	2	You covet, and do not have, so you kill; and envy, and cannot obtain, so you fight and quarrel. You do not have because you do not ask.
B059C004V003	59	4	3	You ask, and do not receive, because you ask amiss, that you may spend it upon your pleasures.
B059C004V004	59	4	4	You adulteresses, do you not know that friendship with the world is enmity with God? whoever therefore will be a friend of the world is the enemy of God.
B059C004V005	59	4	5	Do you think that the scripture speaks in vain when it says, The spirit he made to dwell in us tends toward envious desires?
B059C004V006	59	4	6	But he gives more grace. Therefore it says, God resists the proud, but gives grace to the humble.
B059C004V007	59	4	7	Therefore, submit yourselves to God. Resist the devil, and he will flee from you.
B059C004V008	59	4	8	Draw near to God, and he will draw near to you. Cleanse your hands, you sinners; and purify your hearts, you double-minded.
B059C004V009	59	4	9	Be miserable, and mourn, and weep: let your laughter be turned to mourning, and your joy to gloom.
B059C004V010	59	4	10	Humble yourselves in the sight of the Lord, and he shall lift you up.
B059C004V011	59	4	11	Do not speak evil of one another, brethren. He who speaks evil of his brother, and judges his brother, speaks evil of the law, and judges the law: but if you judge the law, you are not a doer of the law, but a judge of it.
B059C004V012	59	4	12	There is one lawgiver, who is able to save and to destroy: but who are you to judge your neighbour?
B059C004V013	59	4	13	Come now, you who say, Today or tomorrow we will go to this or that city, and remain there a year, and buy and sell, and make a profit.
B059C004V014	59	4	14	Yet you do not even know what shall happen tomorrow. For what is your life? It is just a vapour, that appears for a little time, and then vanishes away.
B059C004V015	59	4	15	Instead you ought to say, If the Lord wills, we shall live, and do this, or that.
B059C004V016	59	4	16	But now you boast in your presumption: all such boasting is evil.
B059C004V017	59	4	17	Therefore, for him who knows the good he ought to do, and does not do it, for him it is sin.
B059C005V001	59	5	1	Come now, you rich men, weep and howl for the miseries that shall come upon you.
B059C005V002	59	5	2	Your riches have rotted, and your garments are moth-eaten.
B059C005V003	59	5	3	Your gold and silver is corroded; and their rust shall be a witness against you, and shall eat your flesh as if it were fire. You have heaped treasure together in the last days.
B059C005V004	59	5	4	Behold, the wages of the labourers who have reaped your fields, which you withheld, cry out against you: and the cries of those who reaped have been heard by the ears of the Lord of hosts.
B059C005V005	59	5	5	You have lived in luxury on the earth, and in self-indulgence; you have fattened your hearts, as in a day of slaughter.
B059C005V006	59	5	6	You have condemned and killed the just man; and he does not resist you.
B059C005V007	59	5	7	Therefore be patient, brethren, until the coming of the Lord. Behold, the farmer waits for the precious fruit of the earth, and is patient for it, until it receives the early and the late rains.
B059C005V008	59	5	8	You also be patient; establish your hearts: for the coming of the Lord draws near.
B059C005V009	59	5	9	Do not grumble against one another, brethren, lest you be condemned: behold, the judge stands before the door.
B059C005V010	59	5	10	My brethren, take the prophets, who have spoken in the name of the Lord, as an example of suffering, and of patience.
B059C005V011	59	5	11	Behold, we count as happy those who endured. You have heard of the patience of Job, and have seen the outcome the Lord brought about; that the Lord is full of compassion, and of tender mercy.
B059C005V012	59	5	12	But above all things, my brethren, do not swear, either by heaven, or by the earth, or with any other oath: but let your yes be yes; and your no, no; lest you fall into condemnation.
B059C005V013	59	5	13	Is anyone among you afflicted? let him pray. Is anyone merry? let him sing praises.
B059C005V014	59	5	14	Is anyone among you sick? let him call for the elders of the church; and let them pray over him, anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord:
B059C005V015	59	5	15	And the prayer of faith shall save the sick, and the Lord shall raise him up; and if he has committed sins, they shall be forgiven him.
B059C005V016	59	5	16	Confess your sins to one another, and pray for one another, that you may be healed. The fervent prayer of a righteous man is powerful and effective.
B059C005V017	59	5	17	Elijah was a man with a nature such as we have, and he prayed earnestly that it might not rain: and it did not rain on the earth for three years and six months.
B059C005V018	59	5	18	And he prayed again, and the heavens gave rain, and the earth brought forth its fruit.
B059C005V019	59	5	19	Brethren, if any of you strays from the truth, and someone brings him back;
B059C005V020	59	5	20	Let him know, that he who turns a sinner from the error of his ways shall save a soul from death, and shall cover a multitude of sins.
B060C001V001	60	1	1	Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the exiles scattered throughout Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia,
B060C001V002	60	1	2	Chosen according to the foreknowledge of God the Father, and sanctified by the Spirit for obedience to Jesus Christ and sprinkling by his blood: Grace and peace be multiplied to you.
B060C001V003	60	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who by his abundant mercy has given us new birth into a living hope through the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead,
B060C001V004	60	1	4	To an imperishable and undefiled inheritance, that does not fade away, reserved in heaven for you,
B060C001V005	60	1	5	Who are guarded by the power of God through faith for a salvation ready to be revealed in the last time.
B060C001V006	60	1	6	In this you greatly rejoice, though now for a time you may have to suffer various trials:
B060C001V007	60	1	7	That the genuineness of your faith, being much more precious than gold, which perishes, though it is tested by fire, might be found to result in praise and honour and glory at the appearing of Jesus Christ.
B060C001V008	60	1	8	Though you have not seen him, you love him; and though you do not see him now, yet you believe in him and rejoice with inexpressible and glorious joy:
B060C001V009	60	1	9	Receiving the outcome of your faith, the salvation of your souls.
B060C001V010	60	1	10	Of this salvation, the prophets who prophesied of the grace that should come to you enquired and searched diligently:
B060C001V011	60	1	11	Seeking to find to whom and when the Spirit of Christ within them was pointing, when he testified beforehand of the sufferings of Christ, and the glories that should follow.
B060C001V012	60	1	12	It was revealed to them that they did not serve themselves, but you, in the things which have now been made known to you by those who preached the gospel to you through the Holy Spirit sent down from heaven; things into which angels desire to look.
B060C001V013	60	1	13	Therefore gird up your minds, be sober, and fix your hope fully on the grace that is to be brought to you at the revelation of Jesus Christ.
B060C001V014	60	1	14	Live as obedient children, not conforming yourselves to the lusts of your former ignorance:
B060C001V015	60	1	15	But as he who has called you is holy, so be holy in all your conduct;
B060C001V016	60	1	16	Because it is written, Be holy; for I am holy.
B060C001V017	60	1	17	And if you address as Father the one who without partiality judges according to every man's work, then pass the time of your stay on earth in reverent fear:
B060C001V018	60	1	18	For you know that you were not redeemed with perishable things, such as silver and gold, from the vain way of life you inherited from your fathers;
B060C001V019	60	1	19	But with the precious blood of Christ, like that of a lamb without blemish and without spot:
B060C001V020	60	1	20	Who was chosen before the foundation of the world, but was revealed in these last times for you,
B060C001V021	60	1	21	Who through him believe in God, who raised him up from the dead, and gave him glory; that your faith and hope might be in God.
B060C001V022	60	1	22	Since you have purified your souls by obeying the truth, so you have a sincere love of the brethren; love one another fervently from the heart.
B060C001V023	60	1	23	You have been born again, not of perishable seed, but of imperishable, by the word of God, which lives and abides forever.
B060C001V024	60	1	24	For, All flesh is like grass, and all its glory is like the flower of grass. The grass withers, and the flower falls away,
B060C001V025	60	1	25	But the word of the Lord endures forever. And this is the word that was preached to you.
B060C002V001	60	2	1	Therefore, laying aside all malice, and all guile, and hypocrisy, and envy, and all kinds of slander,
B060C002V002	60	2	2	As newborn babes, desire the pure milk of the word, that you may grow by it in your salvation:
B060C002V003	60	2	3	Since you have tasted the kindness of the Lord.
B060C002V004	60	2	4	Coming to him as to a living stone, rejected by men, but chosen by God, and precious,
B060C002V005	60	2	5	You also, as living stones, are being built up into a spiritual house, a holy priesthood, to offer up spiritual sacrifices, acceptable to God through Jesus Christ.
B060C002V006	60	2	6	For this is contained in the scripture, Behold, I lay in Zion a cornerstone, chosen and precious: and he who believes in him shall not be put to shame.
B060C002V007	60	2	7	Therefore, to you who believe, he is precious: but to those who disbelieve, the stone which the builders rejected has become the very cornerstone,
B060C002V008	60	2	8	And a stone of stumbling, and a rock of offence; they stumble at the word, being disobedient: as they were appointed to do.
B060C002V009	60	2	9	But you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people belonging to God; that you should declare the praises of him who has called you out of darkness into his marvellous light.
B060C002V010	60	2	10	In times past you were not a people, but now you are the people of God: once you had not obtained mercy, but now you have obtained mercy.
B060C002V011	60	2	11	Dearly beloved, I urge you as aliens and strangers, abstain from fleshly lusts, which wage war against the soul.
B060C002V012	60	2	12	Conduct yourselves righteously among the Gentiles: that, though they speak against you as evildoers, they may behold your good works and glorify God on the day of visitation.
B060C002V013	60	2	13	Submit yourselves to every ordinance of man for the Lord's sake: whether it be to the king, as supreme authority;
B060C002V014	60	2	14	Or to governors, as to those who are sent by him to punish evildoers, and to praise those who do well.
B060C002V015	60	2	15	For this is the will of God, that by doing right you may silence the ignorance of foolish men:
B060C002V016	60	2	16	Live as free men, not using your liberty as a cloak for evil, but live as the servants of God.
B060C002V017	60	2	17	Honour all men. Love the brotherhood. Fear God. Honour the king.
B060C002V018	60	2	18	Servants, be subject to your masters with all respect; not only to the good and gentle, but also to the perverse.
B060C002V019	60	2	19	For this is commendable, if for the sake of conscience toward God, a man endures sorrow while suffering wrongfully.
B060C002V020	60	2	20	For what credit is there, if, when you are beaten for your wrongs, you endure it patiently? but if, when you do well, and suffer for it, you endure it patiently, this is commendable before God.
B060C002V021	60	2	21	For to this you were called: because Christ also suffered for you, leaving you an example, that you should follow his steps.
B060C002V022	60	2	22	He committed no sin, nor was any deceit found in his mouth;
B060C002V023	60	2	23	And when he was reviled, he did not revile in return; and when he suffered, he did not threaten; but committed himself to him who judges righteously.
B060C002V024	60	2	24	He himself bore our sins in his own body on the tree, that we might die to sins and live to righteousness; by his wounds you have been healed.
B060C002V025	60	2	25	For you were like sheep going astray; but you have now returned to the Shepherd and Guardian of your souls.
B060C003V001	60	3	1	Likewise, you wives, be in subjection to your husbands; so that, if any do not obey the word, they may be won without a word by the behaviour of the wives;
B060C003V002	60	3	2	When they behold your chaste and reverent behaviour.
B060C003V003	60	3	3	Let your beauty not be in outward adornment; the plaiting of hair, the wearing of gold, or the putting on of apparel;
B060C003V004	60	3	4	But let it be of the inner person of your heart, the unfading beauty of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is precious in the sight of God.
B060C003V005	60	3	5	For in this manner the holy women in days of old, who trusted in God, adorned themselves, and were submissive to their husbands.
B060C003V006	60	3	6	Thus Sarah obeyed Abraham, calling him lord: and you are her daughters, if you do right, and do not give way to fear.
B060C003V007	60	3	7	Likewise, you husbands, live with your wives considerately, giving honour to the woman as the weaker vessel, since you are heirs together of the grace of life. Do this that your prayers may not be hindered.
B060C003V008	60	3	8	Finally, be of one mind, have sympathy for one another, love as brethren, be compassionate, be humble.
B060C003V009	60	3	9	Do not return evil for evil, or insult for insult: but instead with blessing; knowing that you were called to this, that you should inherit a blessing.
B060C003V010	60	3	10	For, He who would love life, and see good days, let him restrain his tongue from evil, and his lips from speaking guile:
B060C003V011	60	3	11	Let him turn from evil, and do good; let him seek peace, and pursue it.
B060C003V012	60	3	12	For the eyes of the Lord are upon the righteous, and his ears are open to their prayers: but the face of the Lord is against those who do evil.
B060C003V013	60	3	13	And who will harm you if you are zealous followers of that which is good?
B060C003V014	60	3	14	But even if you do suffer for righteousness' sake, you are blessed. And do not be afraid of their threats, nor be troubled;
B060C003V015	60	3	15	But set apart Christ as Lord in your hearts: and always be ready to give an answer to every man who asks you the reason for the hope that is in you; but do it with gentleness and respect,
B060C003V016	60	3	16	Keeping a good conscience, so that when you are falsely accused, those who revile your good behaviour in Christ may be ashamed.
B060C003V017	60	3	17	For it is better, if it is the will of God, that you suffer for doing right, than for doing evil.
B060C003V018	60	3	18	For Christ died for sins once for all, the just for the unjust, that he might bring us to God, being put to death in the flesh, but made alive in the spirit,
B060C003V019	60	3	19	In which he went and preached to the spirits in prison,
B060C003V020	60	3	20	Who long ago were disobedient, when God patiently waited in the days of Noah, while the ark was prepared, in which a few, that is, eight people, were saved through water.
B060C003V021	60	3	21	This water symbolizes baptism, which now saves us (not by the removal of dirt from the body, but by an appeal of a good conscience to God,) through the resurrection of Jesus Christ,
B060C003V022	60	3	22	Who has gone into heaven, and is on the right hand of God; with angels and authorities and powers made subject to him.
B060C004V001	60	4	1	Therefore, since Christ has suffered in the flesh, arm yourselves with the same mind: for he who has suffered in the flesh has ceased from sin;
B060C004V002	60	4	2	That he may live the rest of his time in the flesh no longer for the lusts of men, but for the will of God.
B060C004V003	60	4	3	For the time past was sufficient for doing the things the Gentiles desire to do: living in debauchery, lust, drunkenness, revelling, carousing, and abominable idolatries.
B060C004V004	60	4	4	They think it strange that you do not run with them into the same excess of dissipation, and they speak evil of you:
B060C004V005	60	4	5	But they shall give an account to him who is ready to judge the living and the dead.
B060C004V006	60	4	6	For this reason the gospel was also preached to those who are dead, that though judged in the flesh as men, they might live according to God in the spirit.
B060C004V007	60	4	7	But the end of all things is at hand: therefore be of sound mind and sober judgement for prayer.
B060C004V008	60	4	8	Above all things have fervent love for one another: for love covers a multitude of sins.
B060C004V009	60	4	9	Be hospitable to one another without grumbling.
B060C004V010	60	4	10	As every man has received a gift, so he should use it to serve one another, as befits good stewards of the manifold grace of God.
B060C004V011	60	4	11	If any man speak, let it be as one who speaks the oracles of God; if any man serves, let him do it as by the strength which God supplies: that in all things God may be glorified through Jesus Christ, to whom belong praise and dominion for ever and ever. Amen.
B060C004V012	60	4	12	Beloved, do not be surprised at the fiery trial which comes upon you to test you, as though some strange thing was happened to you:
B060C004V013	60	4	13	But rejoice, insofar as you are partakers of Christ's sufferings; that, when his glory shall be revealed, you may be triumphantly joyful.
B060C004V014	60	4	14	Blessed are you if you are insulted for the name of Christ; for the spirit of glory and of God rests upon you.
B060C004V015	60	4	15	But let none of you suffer as a murderer, or as a thief, or as an evildoer, or as a meddler in other men's affairs.
B060C004V016	60	4	16	Yet if any man suffers as a Christian, let him not be ashamed; but let him glorify God that he bears that name.
B060C004V017	60	4	17	For the time has come for judgment, which must begin with the household of God: and if it begins with us, what shall the end be for those who do not obey the gospel of God?
B060C004V018	60	4	18	And if it is with difficulty that the righteous are saved, what shall become of the ungodly and the sinner?
B060C004V019	60	4	19	Therefore, let those who suffer according to the will of God commit the keeping of their souls to a faithful Creator by doing right.
B060C005V001	60	5	1	I exhort the elders who are among you, as a fellow elder, and as a witness of the sufferings of Christ and as a partaker of the glory that shall be revealed:
B060C005V002	60	5	2	Tend the flock of God which is in your charge, not by compulsion, but willingly; not for sordid gain, but eagerly;
B060C005V003	60	5	3	Not being lords over those in your charge, but being examples to the flock.
B060C005V004	60	5	4	And when the chief Shepherd shall appear, you shall receive a crown of glory that does not fade away.
B060C005V005	60	5	5	Likewise, you who are younger, submit yourselves to the elders. And all of you, clothe yourselves with humility toward one another: for God opposes the proud, but gives grace to the humble.
B060C005V006	60	5	6	Therefore, humble yourselves under the mighty hand of God, that he may exalt you in due time:
B060C005V007	60	5	7	Casting all your anxiety upon him; for he cares for you.
B060C005V008	60	5	8	Be sober, be vigilant; because your adversary the devil, like a roaring lion, walks about, seeking someone he may devour.
B060C005V009	60	5	9	Resist him, steadfast in faith, knowing that the same experiences of suffering are required of your brethren who are throughout the world.
B060C005V010	60	5	10	But the God of all grace, who has called you to his eternal glory in Christ, after you have suffered a little while, will himself perfect, establish, strengthen, and settle you.
B060C005V011	60	5	11	To him be dominion for ever and ever. Amen.
B060C005V012	60	5	12	Through Silvanus, a faithful brother, as I regard him, I have written briefly to you, exhorting, and testifying that this is the true grace of God; stand fast in it.
B060C005V013	60	5	13	She who is in Babylon, chosen together with you, greets you; and so does Mark, my son.
B060C005V014	60	5	14	Greet one another with a kiss of love. Peace be with all of you who are in Christ Jesus.
B061C001V001	61	1	1	Simon Peter, a servant and an apostle of Jesus Christ, to those who, through the righteousness of our God and Saviour Jesus Christ, have obtained the same precious faith as ours:
B061C001V002	61	1	2	Grace and peace be multiplied to you through the knowledge of God and of Jesus our Lord,
B061C001V003	61	1	3	Whose divine power has given to us all things that pertain to life and godliness, through the knowledge of him who has called us by his own glory and virtue:
B061C001V004	61	1	4	By which he has given to us exceedingly great and precious promises: that by these you might be partakers of the divine nature, having escaped the corruption that is in the world through lust.
B061C001V005	61	1	5	For this very reason, give all diligence to add to your faith virtue; and to virtue knowledge;
B061C001V006	61	1	6	And to knowledge self-control; and to self-control perseverance; and to perseverance godliness;
B061C001V007	61	1	7	And to godliness brotherly kindness; and to brotherly kindness love.
B061C001V008	61	1	8	For if these things are in you, and are increasing, they keep you from being either ineffective or unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B061C001V009	61	1	9	But he who lacks these things is blind, and cannot see afar off, and has forgotten that he was purged from his old sins.
B061C001V010	61	1	10	Therefore, brethren, be all the more diligent to make your calling and election sure: for if you do these things, you shall never fall:
B061C001V011	61	1	11	For in this way an entrance shall be abundantly provided for you into the eternal kingdom of our Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ.
B061C001V012	61	1	12	Therefore, I will always remind you of these things, though you know them, and are established in the truth you now have.
B061C001V013	61	1	13	Yea, I think it right, as long as I am in this tent of my body, to stir you up way of reminder;
B061C001V014	61	1	14	Knowing that shortly I must put off this tent, just as our Lord Jesus Christ has shown me.
B061C001V015	61	1	15	Moreover, I will endeavour to see to it that after my departure you may be able at any time to recall these things.
B061C001V016	61	1	16	For we did not follow cunningly devised fables, when we made known to you the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, but we were eyewitnesses of his majesty.
B061C001V017	61	1	17	For he received from God the Father honour and glory, when there came a voice to him from the Majestic Glory, saying, This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.
B061C001V018	61	1	18	And this voice which came from heaven we heard, when we were with him on the holy mountain.
B061C001V019	61	1	19	And so we have the word of prophecy made more certain; to which you would do well to take heed, as to a light that shines in a dark place, until the day dawns, and the morning star arises in your hearts:
B061C001V020	61	1	20	Knowing this first, that no prophecy of the scripture is a matter of one's private interpretation.
B061C001V021	61	1	21	For prophecy did not come in times of old by the will of man: but holy men spoke from God as they were moved by the Holy Spirit.
B061C002V001	61	2	1	But there were also false prophets among the people, even as there shall be false teachers among you, who secretly shall bring in destructive heresies, even denying the Lord who bought them, and bring upon themselves swift destruction.
B061C002V002	61	2	2	And many shall follow their licentious ways; and because of them the way of truth shall be maligned.
B061C002V003	61	2	3	And in greed they shall exploit you with false words: the judgment against them from of old does not linger, and their condemnation does not slumber.
B061C002V004	61	2	4	For if God did not spare the angels who sinned, but cast them down to hell, and delivered them into pits of gloom, to be reserved for judgment;
B061C002V005	61	2	5	And did not spare the old world, but saved Noah, a preacher of righteousness, with seven others, when he brought a flood upon the world of the ungodly;
B061C002V006	61	2	6	If he condemned the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah, overthrowing them and turning them into ashes, and made them an example to those who would be ungodly;
B061C002V007	61	2	7	And delivered righteous Lot, who was vexed by the licentious lives of the wicked:
B061C002V008	61	2	8	(For that righteous man dwelt among them, seeing and hearing, and his righteous soul was vexed from day to day by their unlawful deeds;)
B061C002V009	61	2	9	Then the Lord knows how to deliver the godly out of temptations, and to reserve the unjust under punishment until the day of judgment:
B061C002V010	61	2	10	And particularly those who walk after the flesh in its unclean lusts, and despise authority. They are presumptuous, self-willed, they are not afraid to speak evil of the glorious ones.
B061C002V011	61	2	11	Whereas angels, which are greater in power and might, do not bring slanderous accusation against them before the Lord.
B061C002V012	61	2	12	But these, like brute beasts, creatures of instinct, made to be taken and destroyed, speak evil of things they do not understand; and shall utterly perish with them in the same destruction;
B061C002V013	61	2	13	And shall receive the reward of unrighteousness. They count it pleasure to carouse in the daytime. They are spots and blemishes, revelling in their own deceptions while they feast with you;
B061C002V014	61	2	14	Having eyes full of adultery, who cannot cease from sin; enticing unstable souls: they have a heart trained in greed; cursed children:
B061C002V015	61	2	15	Who have forsaken the right way, and have gone astray, following the way of Balaam the son of Beor, who loved the wages of unrighteousness;
B061C002V016	61	2	16	But was rebuked for his iniquity: a dumb donkey speaking with a man's voice restrained the madness of the prophet.
B061C002V017	61	2	17	These are wells without water, mists driven before a tempest; for whom the blackest darkness is reserved.
B061C002V018	61	2	18	For they speak great swelling words of vanity, and allure through the lusts of the flesh, through sensuality, those who are just escaping from the ones who live in error.
B061C002V019	61	2	19	While they promise them liberty, they themselves are the slaves of depravity: for by that which a man is overcome, to that he is enslaved.
B061C002V020	61	2	20	For if, after they have escaped the defilements of the world through the knowledge of the Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ, they are again entangled by them, and overcome, they are worse off in the end than at the beginning.
B061C002V021	61	2	21	For it would have been better for them not to have known the way of righteousness, than, having known it, to turn from the holy commandment delivered to them.
B061C002V022	61	2	22	But it has happened to them according to the true proverb, The dog returns to its own vomit; and the sow that is washed returns to wallowing in the mire.
B061C003V001	61	3	1	This is now the second letter, beloved, that I have written to you, in which I stir up your sincere minds by way of remembrance:
B061C003V002	61	3	2	That you may recall the words which were spoken before by the holy prophets, and the commandment of the Lord and Saviour given through your apostles:
B061C003V003	61	3	3	Knowing this first, that in the last days scoffers shall come, scoffing and walking after their own lusts,
B061C003V004	61	3	4	And saying, Where is the promise of his coming? for ever since the fathers fell asleep, all things continue as they were from the beginning of the creation.
B061C003V005	61	3	5	For they willingly ignore this, that by the word of God the heavens existed long ago, and the earth was formed out of water and by water.
B061C003V006	61	3	6	And by water the world that then was, being deluged, perished:
B061C003V007	61	3	7	But by the same word, the heavens and the earth which are now, are reserved for fire on the day of judgment and destruction of ungodly men.
B061C003V008	61	3	8	But, beloved, do not be ignorant of this one thing, that with the Lord one day is like a thousand years, and a thousand years like one day.
B061C003V009	61	3	9	The Lord is not slow concerning his promise, as some men count slowness; but is patient toward you, not wanting that any should perish, but that all should come to repentance.
B061C003V010	61	3	10	But the day of the Lord will come as a thief; in which the heavens shall pass away with a roar, and the elements shall be destroyed with fervent heat, the earth and the works that are upon it shall be burned up.
B061C003V011	61	3	11	Seeing then that all these things shall be destroyed, what kind of people ought you to be? You should live holy and godly lives,
B061C003V012	61	3	12	Looking for and hastening the coming of the day of God, in which the heavens shall be dissolved in fire, and the elements shall melt with fervent heat.
B061C003V013	61	3	13	But we, according to his promise, look for new heavens and a new earth, in which righteousness dwells.
B061C003V014	61	3	14	Therefore, beloved, seeing that you look for these things, be diligent that you may be found at peace with him, without spot, and blameless.
B061C003V015	61	3	15	And consider the patience of our Lord to be salvation; just as our beloved brother Paul has written to you, according to the wisdom given to him,
B061C003V016	61	3	16	Speaking of these things, as he does in all his letters. In them are some things that are hard to understand, which those who are unlearned and unstable distort, as they do the other scriptures, to their own destruction.
B061C003V017	61	3	17	But you, beloved, seeing that you know these things beforehand, beware lest you also, being led away by the error of the wicked, fall from your own steadfastness.
B061C003V018	61	3	18	But grow in grace, and in the knowledge of our Lord and Saviour Jesus Christ. To him be glory both now and forever. Amen.
B062C001V001	62	1	1	That which was from the beginning, which we have heard, which we have seen with our eyes, which we have looked upon, and our hands have handled, concerning the Word of life;
B062C001V002	62	1	2	(For the life was revealed, and we have seen it, and bear witness, and proclaim to you the eternal life, which was with the Father, and was revealed to us;)
B062C001V003	62	1	3	That which we have seen and heard we declare to you, that you also may have fellowship with us: and our fellowship is with the Father, and with his Son Jesus Christ.
B062C001V004	62	1	4	And these things we write to you, that our joy may be complete.
B062C001V005	62	1	5	This then is the message which we have heard from him, and declare to you, that God is light, and in him is no darkness at all.
B062C001V006	62	1	6	If we say that we have fellowship with him, yet walk in darkness, we lie, and do not practice the truth:
B062C001V007	62	1	7	But if we walk in the light, as he is in the light, we have fellowship with one another, and the blood of Jesus his Son cleanses us from all sin.
B062C001V008	62	1	8	If we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and the truth is not in us.
B062C001V009	62	1	9	If we confess our sins, he is faithful and just to forgive us our sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.
B062C001V010	62	1	10	If we say that we have not sinned, we make him a liar, and his word is not in us.
B062C002V001	62	2	1	My little children, these things I write to you, that you may not sin. And if any man does sin, we have an advocate with the Father, Jesus Christ the righteous:
B062C002V002	62	2	2	And he is the atoning sacrifice for our sins: and not for ours only, but also for the sins of the whole world.
B062C002V003	62	2	3	And by this we may be sure that we know him, if we keep his commandments.
B062C002V004	62	2	4	He who says, I know him, and does not keep his commandments, is a liar, and the truth is not in him.
B062C002V005	62	2	5	But whoever keeps his word, in him is the love of God truly perfected. By this we know that we are in him:
B062C002V006	62	2	6	He who says he abides in him ought also to walk as he walked.
B062C002V007	62	2	7	Brethren, I am not writing a new commandment to you, but an old commandment which you had from the beginning. The old commandment is the word which you have heard.
B062C002V008	62	2	8	Yet, I am writing a new commandment to you, which is true in him and in you: because the darkness is passing away, and the true light now shines.
B062C002V009	62	2	9	He who says he is in the light, yet hates his brother, is in darkness even until now.
B062C002V010	62	2	10	He who loves his brother abides in the light, and there is no cause for stumbling in him.
B062C002V011	62	2	11	But he who hates his brother is in darkness, and walks in darkness, and does not know where he goes, because the darkness has blinded his eyes.
B062C002V012	62	2	12	I write to you, little children, because your sins are forgiven for his name's sake.
B062C002V013	62	2	13	I write to you, fathers, because you have known him who is from the beginning. I write to you, young men, because you have overcome the wicked one. I write to you, little children, because you have known the Father.
B062C002V014	62	2	14	I have written to you, fathers, because you have known him who is from the beginning. I have written to you, young men, because you are strong, and the word of God abides in you, and you have overcome the wicked one.
B062C002V015	62	2	15	Do not love the world, nor the things in the world. If any man loves the world, the love of the Father is not in him.
B062C002V016	62	2	16	For all that is in the world, the lust of the flesh, and the lust of the eyes, and the pride of life, is not of the Father, but is of the world.
B062C002V017	62	2	17	And the world passes away, along with its lusts: but he who does the will of God abides forever.
B062C002V018	62	2	18	Little children, it is the last hour: and as you have heard that the antichrist shall come, even now there are many antichrists; by this we know that it is the last hour.
B062C002V019	62	2	19	They went out from us, but they were not of us; for if they had been of us, they would have remained with us: but they went out, that it might be made clear that none of them were of us.
B062C002V020	62	2	20	But you have an anointing from the Holy One, and you all know the truth.
B062C002V021	62	2	21	I have not written to you because you do not know the truth, but because you do know it, and because no lie is of the truth.
B062C002V022	62	2	22	Who is the liar but he who denies that Jesus is the Christ? He is the antichrist, who denies the Father and the Son.
B062C002V023	62	2	23	Whoever denies the Son, does not have the Father: he who acknowledges the Son has the Father also.
B062C002V024	62	2	24	As for you, let that abide in you which you have heard from the beginning. If that which you have heard from the beginning shall abide in you, you shall also abide in the Son, and in the Father.
B062C002V025	62	2	25	And this is the promise which he himself has given us: eternal life.
B062C002V026	62	2	26	These things I have written to you concerning those who would deceive you.
B062C002V027	62	2	27	But the anointing which you have received from him abides in you, and you do not need any man to teach you: but his anointing teaches you all things, and is true, and is no lie, and just as it has taught you, abide in him.
B062C002V028	62	2	28	And now, little children, abide in him; that, when he shall appear, we may have confidence, and not be ashamed before him at his coming.
B062C002V029	62	2	29	If you know that he is righteous, you know that every one who does right has been born of him.
B062C003V001	62	3	1	Behold, how great is the love the Father has bestowed upon us, that we should be called the sons of God; and so we are. The world does not know us, because it did not know him.
B062C003V002	62	3	2	Beloved, now we are the sons of God; and what we shall be has not yet been disclosed: but we know that when he shall appear, we shall be like him, for we shall see him as he is.
B062C003V003	62	3	3	And every man who has this hope in him purifies himself, just as he is pure.
B062C003V004	62	3	4	Whoever commits sin practices lawlessness: for sin is lawlessness.
B062C003V005	62	3	5	And you know that he was revealed to take away our sins; and in him is no sin.
B062C003V006	62	3	6	Whoever abides in him does not sin: no one who sins has either seen him or known him.
B062C003V007	62	3	7	Little children, let no man deceive you: he who does right is righteous, just as he is righteous.
B062C003V008	62	3	8	He who commits sin is of the devil; for the devil has sinned from the beginning. For this reason the Son of God was revealed, that he might destroy the works of the devil.
B062C003V009	62	3	9	No one who is born of God practices sin; for his seed remains in him: and he cannot sin, because he is born of God.
B062C003V010	62	3	10	By this the children of God and the children of the devil are revealed: whoever does not practice righteousness is not of God, nor is he who does not love his brother.
B062C003V011	62	3	11	For this is the message that you heard from the beginning, that we should love one another.
B062C003V012	62	3	12	Do not be like Cain, who was of the wicked one, and killed his brother. And why did he kill him? Because his own works were evil, and his brother's were righteous.
B062C003V013	62	3	13	Do not marvel, my brethren, if the world hates you.
B062C003V014	62	3	14	We know that we have passed from death to life, because we love the brethren. He who does not love abides in death.
B062C003V015	62	3	15	Whoever hates his brother is a murderer: and you know that no murderer has eternal life abiding in him.
B062C003V016	62	3	16	By this we know love, because he laid down his life for us: and we ought to lay down our lives for the brethren.
B062C003V017	62	3	17	But whoever has this world's goods, and sees his brother in need, and shuts his heart against him, how does the love of God abide in him?
B062C003V018	62	3	18	My little children, let us not love in word or in speech; but in deed and in truth.
B062C003V019	62	3	19	And by this we know that we are of the truth, and shall assure our hearts before him,
B062C003V020	62	3	20	Whenever our heart condemns us; for God is greater than our heart, and knows all things.
B062C003V021	62	3	21	Beloved, if our heart does not condemn us, then we have confidence toward God;
B062C003V022	62	3	22	And whatever we ask, we receive from him, because we keep his commandments, and do those things that are pleasing in his sight.
B062C003V023	62	3	23	And this is his commandment, That we should believe in the name of his Son Jesus Christ, and love one another, as he commanded us.
B062C003V024	62	3	24	And he who keeps his commandments abides in him, and he in him. And by this we know that he abides in us, by the Spirit which he has given us.
B062C004V001	62	4	1	Beloved, do not believe every spirit, but test the spirits to see whether they are from God: because many false prophets have gone out into the world.
B062C004V002	62	4	2	By this you know the Spirit of God: Every spirit that confesses that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh is of God:
B062C004V003	62	4	3	And every spirit that does not confess Jesus, is not of God: this is the spirit of antichrist, of which you have heard that it was coming; and now is already in the world.
B062C004V004	62	4	4	You are of God, little children, and have overcome them: because greater is he who is in you, than he who is in the world.
B062C004V005	62	4	5	They are of the world: therefore what they speak is of the world, and the world hears them.
B062C004V006	62	4	6	We are of God: he who knows God hears us; he who is not of God does not hear us. By this we know the spirit of truth, and the spirit of error.
B062C004V007	62	4	7	Beloved, let us love one another: for love is of God, and every one who loves is born of God, and knows God.
B062C004V008	62	4	8	He who does not love does not know God; for God is love.
B062C004V009	62	4	9	In this was the love of God revealed among us, that God sent his only begotten Son into the world, that we might live through him.
B062C004V010	62	4	10	In this is love, not that we loved God, but that he loved us, and sent his Son to be the atoning sacrifice for our sins.
B062C004V011	62	4	11	Beloved, if God so loved us, we also ought to love one another.
B062C004V012	62	4	12	No man has seen God at any time, but if we love one another, God abides in us, and his love is perfected in us.
B062C004V013	62	4	13	By this we know that we abide in him, and he in us, because he has given us of his Spirit.
B062C004V014	62	4	14	And we have seen and testify that the Father sent the Son to be the Saviour of the world.
B062C004V015	62	4	15	Whoever shall confess that Jesus is the Son of God, God abides in him, and he in God.
B062C004V016	62	4	16	And we have known and believed the love that God has for us. God is love; and he who abides in love abides in God, and God in him.
B062C004V017	62	4	17	In this is our love made perfect, that we may have boldness in the day of judgment: because as he is, so we are in this world.
B062C004V018	62	4	18	There is no fear in love; but perfect love casts out fear: because fear has to do with punishment. He who fears is not made perfect in love.
B062C004V019	62	4	19	We love, because he first loved us.
B062C004V020	62	4	20	If a man says, I love God, and hates his brother, he is a liar: for he who does not love his brother whom he has seen cannot love God whom he has not seen.
B062C004V021	62	4	21	And this commandment we have from him, That he who loves God must also love his brother.
B062C005V001	62	5	1	Whoever believes that Jesus is the Christ is born of God: and every one who loves the parent also loves the child.
B062C005V002	62	5	2	By this we know that we love the children of God, when we love God, and keep his commandments.
B062C005V003	62	5	3	For this is the love of God, that we keep his commandments: and his commandments are not burdensome.
B062C005V004	62	5	4	For everyone who is born of God overcomes the world: and this is the victory that overcomes the world, our faith.
B062C005V005	62	5	5	Who is the one who overcomes the world, but he who believes that Jesus is the Son of God?
B062C005V006	62	5	6	This is he who came by water and blood, Jesus Christ; not by water only, but by water and blood.
B062C005V007	62	5	7	And it is the Spirit who bears witness, because the Spirit is truth.
B062C005V008	62	5	8	For there are three who bear witness, the Spirit, and the water, and the blood: and these three agree.
B062C005V009	62	5	9	If we receive the testimony of men, the testimony of God is greater, for it is the testimony of God, which he has given regarding his Son.
B062C005V010	62	5	10	He who believes in the Son of God has the testimony in himself: he who does not believe God has made him a liar; because he does not believe the testimony that God has given regarding his Son.
B062C005V011	62	5	11	And this is the testimony, that God has given to us eternal life, and this life is in his Son.
B062C005V012	62	5	12	He who has the Son has life; he who does not have the Son of God does not have life.
B062C005V013	62	5	13	These things I have written to you who believe in the name of the Son of God; that you may know that you have eternal life.
B062C005V014	62	5	14	And this is the confidence that we have in him, that if we ask anything according to his will, he hears us.
B062C005V015	62	5	15	And if we know that he hears us in whatever we ask, we know that we have that which we have requested of him.
B062C005V016	62	5	16	If any man sees his brother commit a sin which does not lead to death, he shall ask, and God shall grant him life, for those whose sin is not to death. There is a sin to death: I do not say that he should pray for that.
B062C005V017	62	5	17	All unrighteousness is sin, and there is a sin that does not lead to death.
B062C005V018	62	5	18	We know that whoever is born of God does not sin; but he who was begotten of God keeps him, and the wicked one does not touch him.
B062C005V019	62	5	19	We know that we are of God, and that the whole world lies under the power of the wicked one.
B062C005V020	62	5	20	And we know that the Son of God has come, and has given us understanding, that we may know him who is true; and we are in him who is true, in his Son Jesus Christ. This is the true God, and eternal life.
B062C005V021	62	5	21	Little children, keep yourselves from idols.
B063C001V001	63	1	1	The elder to the chosen lady and her children, whom I love in the truth; and not only I, but also all those who know the truth,
B063C001V002	63	1	2	For the sake of the truth, which dwells in us, and shall be with us forever:
B063C001V003	63	1	3	Grace, mercy, and peace, shall be with us, from God the Father, and from Jesus Christ, the Son of the Father, in truth and love.
B063C001V004	63	1	4	I rejoiced greatly to find some of your children walking in truth, just as we have been commanded by the Father.
B063C001V005	63	1	5	And now I urge you, lady, not as though I were writing a new commandment to you, but the one which we have had from the beginning, that we love one another.
B063C001V006	63	1	6	And this is love, that we walk in obedience to his commandments. This is the commandment you have heard from the beginning, that you should walk in love.
B063C001V007	63	1	7	For many deceivers have gone out into the world, who do not confess that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh. Such a one is a deceiver and an antichrist.
B063C001V008	63	1	8	Look to yourselves, that you do not lose those things which we have worked for, but that you may receive a full reward.
B063C001V009	63	1	9	Whoever runs too far ahead, and does not abide in the teaching of Christ, does not have God. He who abides in the teaching of Christ has both the Father and the Son.
B063C001V010	63	1	10	If anyone comes to you, and does not bring this teaching, do not receive him into your house, or give him any encouragement:
B063C001V011	63	1	11	For he who encourages him is a partaker in his evil deeds.
B063C001V012	63	1	12	Though I have many things to write to you, I do not want to do so with paper and ink: but I hope to come to you, and speak face to face, that our joy may be full.
B063C001V013	63	1	13	The children of your chosen sister greet you.
B064C001V001	64	1	1	The elder to the beloved Gaius, whom I love in the truth.
B064C001V002	64	1	2	Beloved, I pray that in all things you may prosper and be in good health, just as your soul prospers.
B064C001V003	64	1	3	For I rejoiced greatly, when some brethren came and testified of the truth that is in you, how you walk in the truth.
B064C001V004	64	1	4	I have no greater joy than to hear that my children walk in truth.
B064C001V005	64	1	5	Beloved, you act faithfully whenever you perform any service for the brethren, especially when they are strangers.
B064C001V006	64	1	6	For they have borne witness of your love before the church. If you send them on their journey in a manner worthy of God, you shall do well:
B064C001V007	64	1	7	Because for his name's sake they went forth, accepting nothing from the Gentiles.
B064C001V008	64	1	8	Therefore we ought to support such men, that we might be fellow workers in the truth.
B064C001V009	64	1	9	I wrote to the church: but Diotrephes, who loves to be first among them, does not accept us.
B064C001V010	64	1	10	Therefore, if I come, I will call attention to his deeds, prating against us with malicious words: and not content with that, he refuses to welcome the brethren, and forbids those who would, and casts them out of the church.
B064C001V011	64	1	11	Beloved, do not follow that which is evil, but that which is good. He who does good is of God: but he who does evil has not seen God.
B064C001V012	64	1	12	Demetrius is well spoken of by everyone, and by the truth itself: and we also bear witness; and you know that our testimony is true.
B064C001V013	64	1	13	I had many things to write, but I prefer not to write with pen and ink:
B064C001V014	64	1	14	But I hope I shall see you shortly, and we shall speak face to face. Peace be to you. The friends greet you. Greet the friends by name.
B065C001V001	65	1	1	Jude, the servant of Jesus Christ, and brother of James, to those who are called by God the Father, and kept for Jesus Christ:
B065C001V002	65	1	2	May mercy, and peace, and love, be yours in abundance.
B065C001V003	65	1	3	Beloved, while my whole concern was to write to you about our common salvation, I found it necessary to write and exhort you to earnestly contend for the faith which was once for all delivered to the saints.
B065C001V004	65	1	4	For certain men have crept in secretly, who were long ago ordained for this condemnation; ungodly men, turning the grace of our God into licentiousness, and denying our only Master and Lord, Jesus Christ.
B065C001V005	65	1	5	Now I wish to remind you, though you already know all this, that the Lord, having saved the people out of the land of Egypt, afterward destroyed those who did not believe.
B065C001V006	65	1	6	And the angels which did not keep their own domain, but left their proper abode, he has kept in eternal chains under darkness for the great day of judgment.
B065C001V007	65	1	7	Just as Sodom and Gomorrah, and the cities about them, which gave themselves over in a similar manner to sexual immorality, and to going after strange flesh, are set forth as an example of suffering the vengeance of eternal fire.
B065C001V008	65	1	8	Likewise, these dreamers defile the flesh, despise authority, and speak evil of the glorious ones.
B065C001V009	65	1	9	Yet Michael the archangel, when he contended with the devil and argued over the body of Moses, did not dare to bring against him a railing accusation, but said, The Lord rebuke you.
B065C001V010	65	1	10	But these men speak evil of things which they do not understand: but what they know by instinct, like brute beasts, by these things they corrupt themselves.
B065C001V011	65	1	11	Woe to them! for they have gone the way of Cain, and for profit have plunged into the error of Balaam, and have perished in the rebellion of Korah.
B065C001V012	65	1	12	These men are blemishes at your feasts of love, when they eat with you without fear: clouds without water, carried about by the winds; autumn trees without fruit, twice dead, plucked up by the roots;
B065C001V013	65	1	13	Raging waves of the sea, flinging up the foam of their own shame; wandering stars, for whom the blackest darkness is reserved forever.
B065C001V014	65	1	14	And Enoch, the seventh from Adam, prophesied of these, saying, Behold, the Lord comes with myriads of his holy ones,
B065C001V015	65	1	15	To execute judgment upon all, and to convict all who are ungodly of all their ungodly deeds which they have committed in an ungodly way, and of all the harsh words which ungodly sinners have spoken against him.
B065C001V016	65	1	16	These are grumblers, complainers, following after their own lusts; and their mouths speak great swelling words, flattering people to gain an advantage.
B065C001V017	65	1	17	But, beloved, remember the words which were spoken before by the apostles of our Lord Jesus Christ;
B065C001V018	65	1	18	They told you there would be mockers in the last time, who would walk after their own ungodly lusts.
B065C001V019	65	1	19	These are the ones who cause division, worldly men who do not have the Spirit.
B065C001V020	65	1	20	But you, beloved, build yourselves up on your most holy faith, praying in the Holy Spirit,
B065C001V021	65	1	21	Keep yourselves in the love of God, waiting for the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ to bring you to eternal life.
B065C001V022	65	1	22	And have compassion on some, who are doubting:
B065C001V023	65	1	23	Save others, pulling them out of the fire; and on some have mercy with fear, hating even the garment stained by the flesh.
B065C001V024	65	1	24	Now to him who is able to keep you from falling, and to present you faultless in the presence of his glory with exceedingly great joy,
B065C001V025	65	1	25	To the only God our Saviour, through Jesus Christ our Lord, be glory and majesty, dominion and authority, before all time, and now, and forevermore. Amen.
B066C001V001	66	1	1	The Revelation of Jesus Christ, which God gave to him, to show to his servants the things which must shortly come to pass; and he sent his angel to make it known to his servant John:
B066C001V002	66	1	2	Who bore witness to the word of God, and to the testimony of Jesus Christ, to all things that he saw.
B066C001V003	66	1	3	Blessed is he who reads, and those who hear the words of this prophecy, and heed those things which are written in it: for the time is at hand.
B066C001V004	66	1	4	John to the seven churches which are in Asia: Grace be to you, and peace, from him who is, and who was, and who is to come; and from the seven Spirits who are before his throne;
B066C001V005	66	1	5	And from Jesus Christ, the faithful witness, and the firstborn of the dead, and the ruler of the kings of the earth. To him who loves us, and freed us from our sins by his own blood,
B066C001V006	66	1	6	And has made us a kingdom, and priests to his God and Father; to him be glory and dominion for ever and ever. Amen.
B066C001V007	66	1	7	Behold, he comes with the clouds; and every eye shall see him, even those who pierced him: and all families of the earth shall mourn because of him. Even so, Amen.
B066C001V008	66	1	8	I am Alpha and Omega, says the Lord, who is, and who was, and who is to come, the Almighty.
B066C001V009	66	1	9	I, John, your brother and companion in the tribulation, and kingdom, and endurance which are ours in Jesus, was on the island that is called Patmos, because of the word of God and the testimony of Jesus.
B066C001V010	66	1	10	I was in the Spirit on the Lord's day, and heard behind me a great voice, as of a trumpet,
B066C001V011	66	1	11	Saying, What you see, write in a book, and send it to the seven churches: to Ephesus, and to Smyrna, and to Pergamum, and to Thyatira, and to Sardis, and to Philadelphia, and to Laodicea.
B066C001V012	66	1	12	And I turned to see the voice that was speaking to me. And having turned, I saw seven golden lampstands;
B066C001V013	66	1	13	And in the midst of the seven lampstands, one like a Son of man, clothed with a garment down to his feet, and around his breast a golden girdle.
B066C001V014	66	1	14	His head and his hair were white like wool, as white as snow; and his eyes were like a flame of fire;
B066C001V015	66	1	15	And his feet like burnished bronze, as if they glowed in a furnace; and his voice like the sound of many waters.
B066C001V016	66	1	16	And he had in his right hand seven stars: and out of his mouth came a sharp two-edged sword: and his face was like the sun shining at full strength.
B066C001V017	66	1	17	And when I saw him, I fell at his feet as if dead. And he laid his right hand upon me, saying to me, Do not fear; I am the first and the last,
B066C001V018	66	1	18	The one who lives; I was dead, and, behold, I am alive forevermore, and possess the keys of death and of Hades.
B066C001V019	66	1	19	Write the things which you have seen, and the things which are, and the things which shall be hereafter;
B066C001V020	66	1	20	The mystery of the seven stars which you saw in my right hand, and the seven golden lampstands, is this: The seven stars are the angels of the seven churches, and the seven lampstands are the seven churches.
B066C002V001	66	2	1	To the angel of the church of Ephesus write; These are the words of him who holds the seven stars in his right hand, who walks in the midst of the seven golden lampstands;
B066C002V002	66	2	2	I know your works, and your labour, and your patience, and how you cannot bear those who are evil, and how you have tested those who say they are apostles, and are not, and have found them to be liars;
B066C002V003	66	2	3	And how you have persevered, and have endured for my name's sake, and have not grown weary.
B066C002V004	66	2	4	Yet I have this against you, that you have left your first love.
B066C002V005	66	2	5	Remember the height from which you have fallen, and repent, and do the works you did at first; or else I will come to you, and will remove your lampstand from its place, unless you repent.
B066C002V006	66	2	6	But this you have in your favour, that you hate the deeds of the Nicolaitans, which I also hate.
B066C002V007	66	2	7	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches; To him who overcomes I will give the right to eat of the tree of life, which is in the paradise of God.
B066C002V008	66	2	8	And to the angel of the church in Smyrna write; These are the words of him who is the first and the last, who was dead, and came to life;
B066C002V009	66	2	9	I know your tribulation and your poverty, (but you are rich) and the slander of those who say they are Jews, and are not, but are a synagogue of Satan.
B066C002V010	66	2	10	Do not fear any of those things which you shall suffer: behold, the devil shall cast some of you into prison, that you may be tested; and you shall have tribulation ten days: be faithful to death, and I will give you the crown of life.
B066C002V011	66	2	11	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches; He who overcomes shall not be hurt by the second death.
B066C002V012	66	2	12	And to the angel of the church in Pergamum write; These are the words of him who has the sharp sword with two edges;
B066C002V013	66	2	13	I know where you dwell, where Satan's throne is: and that you hold fast to my name, and have not denied my faith, even in the days of Antipas, my faithful witness, who was slain among you, where Satan dwells.
B066C002V014	66	2	14	But I have a few things against you, because you have there those who hold to the teaching of Balaam, who taught Balak to cast a stumbling block before the sons of Israel, that they might eat things sacrificed to idols, and commit sexual immorality.
B066C002V015	66	2	15	In the same way you also have those who hold to the teachings of the Nicolaitans.
B066C002V016	66	2	16	Therefore repent; or else I will come to you quickly, and will fight against them with the sword of my mouth.
B066C002V017	66	2	17	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches; To him who overcomes I will give some of the hidden manna, and will give him a white stone, and on the stone a new name written, which no man knows except him who receives it.
B066C002V018	66	2	18	And to the angel of the church in Thyatira write; These are the words of the Son of God, who has eyes like a flame of fire, and whose feet are like burnished bonze;
B066C002V019	66	2	19	I know your works, and your love, and faith, and service, and perseverance, and that your recent works are greater than those you did at first.
B066C002V020	66	2	20	Nevertheless, I have this against you, that you tolerate that woman Jezebel, who calls herself a prophetess, and teaches and beguiles my servants to commit sexual immorality, and to eat things sacrificed to idols.
B066C002V021	66	2	21	And I gave her time to repent; but she refuses to repent of her immorality.
B066C002V022	66	2	22	Behold, I will cast her upon a bed of anguish, and those who commit adultery with her into great tribulation, unless they repent of their deeds.
B066C002V023	66	2	23	And I will strike her children with death; and all the churches shall know that I am he who searches minds and hearts: and I will give to every one of you as your deeds deserve.
B066C002V024	66	2	24	But I say to you, and to the rest in Thyatira, as many as do not hold to this teaching, and who have not known the depths of Satan, as they call them; I will put upon you no other burden;
B066C002V025	66	2	25	Only that you hold fast to what you have, until I come.
B066C002V026	66	2	26	And he who overcomes, and does my will to the end, to him I will give authority over the nations;
B066C002V027	66	2	27	And he shall rule them with a rod of iron, as when the vessels of a potter are broken to pieces: just as I received authority from my Father.
B066C002V028	66	2	28	And I will give him the morning star.
B066C002V029	66	2	29	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.
B066C003V001	66	3	1	And to the angel of the church in Sardis write; These are the words of him who has the seven Spirits of God, and the seven stars; I know your works, that you have a reputation of being alive, but you are dead.
B066C003V002	66	3	2	Awake, and strengthen those things which remain, that are ready to die: for I have not found your works perfect in the sight of God.
B066C003V003	66	3	3	Therefore, remember what you have received and heard, and hold fast, and repent. If you will not awaken, I will come like a thief, and you shall not know at what hour I will come upon you.
B066C003V004	66	3	4	Yet you have a few people in Sardis who have not defiled their garments; and they shall walk with me in white: for they are worthy.
B066C003V005	66	3	5	He who overcomes, the same shall be clothed in white garments; and I will not blot his name out of the book of life, but I will confess his name before my Father, and before his angels.
B066C003V006	66	3	6	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.
B066C003V007	66	3	7	And to the angel of the church in Philadelphia write; These are the words of he who is holy, he who is true, he who has the key of David, he who opens, and no man shuts; and shuts, and no man opens;
B066C003V008	66	3	8	I know your works: behold, I have set before you an open door, and no man can shut it: I know you have but little strength, yet you have kept my word, and have not denied my name.
B066C003V009	66	3	9	Behold, I will make those of the synagogue of Satan, who say they are Jews, and are not, but lie; behold, I will make them to come and bow down before your feet, and to know that I have loved you.
B066C003V010	66	3	10	Because you have kept my word to patiently endure, I will keep you from the hour of trial, which shall come upon all the world, to test those who live upon the earth.
B066C003V011	66	3	11	Behold, I come quickly: hold fast to that which you have, that no man may take your crown.
B066C003V012	66	3	12	He who overcomes I will make a pillar in the temple of my God, and he shall never go out of it: and I will write upon him the name of my God, and the name of the city of my God, which is the new Jerusalem, which comes down out of heaven from my God: and I will also write upon him my new name.
B066C003V013	66	3	13	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.
B066C003V014	66	3	14	And to the angel of the church of the Laodiceans write; These are the words of the Amen, the faithful and true witness, the beginning of the creation of God;
B066C003V015	66	3	15	I know your works, that you are neither cold nor hot: I wish that you were either cold or hot.
B066C003V016	66	3	16	So then, because you are lukewarm, and neither cold nor hot, I will spew you out of my mouth.
B066C003V017	66	3	17	For you say, I am rich, and have grown wealthy, and have need of nothing; but you do not know that you are wretched, and miserable, and poor, and blind, and naked.
B066C003V018	66	3	18	I counsel you to buy from me gold refined in the fire, that you may be rich; and white clothing, that you may be clothed, and that the shame of your nakedness may not appear; and salve to anoint your eyes, that you may see.
B066C003V019	66	3	19	As many as I love, I rebuke and chasten: therefore be zealous, and repent.
B066C003V020	66	3	20	Behold, I stand at the door, and knock: if any man hears my voice, and opens the door, I will come in to him, and will eat with him, and he with me.
B066C003V021	66	3	21	To him who overcomes I will grant the right to sit with me on my throne, just as I overcame, and sat down with my Father on his throne.
B066C003V022	66	3	22	He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the churches.
B066C004V001	66	4	1	After this I looked, and, behold, a door was opened in heaven: and the first voice, which I had heard speaking to me like a trumpet, said, Come up here, and I will show you things which must take place after this.
B066C004V002	66	4	2	And immediately I was in the spirit: and, behold, a throne was standing in heaven, and one sat on the throne.
B066C004V003	66	4	3	And he who sat there appeared like jasper and carnelian: and there was a rainbow around the throne, like an emerald in appearance.
B066C004V004	66	4	4	And surrounding the throne were twenty-four thrones: and upon the thrones I saw twenty-four elders sitting, clothed in white garments; and upon their heads they had crowns of gold.
B066C004V005	66	4	5	And out of the throne came flashes of lightning and peals of thunder: and there were seven lamps of fire burning before the throne, which are the seven Spirits of God.
B066C004V006	66	4	6	And before the throne there was a sea of glass, like crystal: and in the center, around the throne, were four living creatures full of eyes in front and behind.
B066C004V007	66	4	7	And the first creature was like a lion, and the second creature like a calf, and the third creature had a face like that of a man, and the fourth creature was like a flying eagle.
B066C004V008	66	4	8	And the four living creatures each had six wings, covered with eyes around and within: and day and night they never stop saying, Holy, holy, holy, is the Lord God Almighty, who was, and is, and is to come.
B066C004V009	66	4	9	And when those living creatures give glory and honour and thanks to him who sits on the throne, who lives forever and ever,
B066C004V010	66	4	10	The twenty-four elders fall down before him who sits on the throne, and worship him who lives forever and ever, and cast their crowns before the throne, saying,
B066C004V011	66	4	11	You are worthy, O Lord, to receive glory and honour and power: for you have created all things, and by your will they were created and have their being.
B066C005V001	66	5	1	And I saw in the right hand of him who sat on the throne a scroll, with writing inside and on the back, sealed with seven seals.
B066C005V002	66	5	2	And I saw a strong angel proclaiming with a loud voice, Who is worthy to open the scroll, and to break its seals?
B066C005V003	66	5	3	And no man in heaven, or on earth, or under the earth, was able to open the scroll, or to look into it.
B066C005V004	66	5	4	And I wept much, because no man was found worthy to open and to read the scroll, or to look into it.
B066C005V005	66	5	5	Then one of the elders said to me, Do not weep: behold, the Lion of the tribe of Judah, the Root of David, has conquered, so he can open the scroll and its seven seals.
B066C005V006	66	5	6	And then I beheld between the throne and the four living creatures, and in the midst of the elders, a Lamb standing as if it had been slain, having seven horns and seven eyes, which are the seven Spirits of God sent forth into all the earth.
B066C005V007	66	5	7	And he came and took the scroll out of the right hand of him who sat upon the throne.
B066C005V008	66	5	8	And when he had taken the scroll, the four living creatures and the twenty-four elders fell down before the Lamb; each one had a harp, and they had golden bowls full of incense, which are the prayers of the saints.
B066C005V009	66	5	9	And they sang a new song, saying, You are worthy to take the scroll, and to break its seals: for you were slain, and by your blood have purchased men for God out of every tribe, and tongue, and people, and nation;
B066C005V010	66	5	10	And have made them to be a kingdom and priests to serve our God: and they shall reign upon the earth.
B066C005V011	66	5	11	And I beheld, and I heard the voice of many angels around the throne and the living creatures and the elders: and the number of them was ten thousand times ten thousand, and thousands upon thousands;
B066C005V012	66	5	12	Saying with a loud voice, Worthy is the Lamb who was slain to receive power, and riches, and wisdom, and strength, and honour, and glory, and blessing.
B066C005V013	66	5	13	And I heard every creature which is in heaven, and on the earth, and under the earth, and on the sea, and all that is in them, saying, Blessing, and honour, and glory, and power, be to him who sits upon the throne, and to the Lamb forever and ever.
B066C005V014	66	5	14	And the four living creatures said, Amen. And the elders fell down and worshipped.
B066C006V001	66	6	1	Then I saw when the Lamb opened one of the seals, and I heard one of the four living creatures saying, as with a voice of thunder, Come.
B066C006V002	66	6	2	And I saw, and behold, a white horse: and he who sat upon it had a bow; and a crown was given to him: and he went forth conquering, and to conquer.
B066C006V003	66	6	3	And when he had opened the second seal, I heard the second living creature say, Come.
B066C006V004	66	6	4	And there went out another horse that was red: and power was given to him who sat upon it to take peace from the earth, that men should slay one another: and there was given to him a great sword.
B066C006V005	66	6	5	And when he had opened the third seal, I heard the third living creature say, Come. And I beheld, and lo, a black horse; and he who sat upon it had a pair of scales in his hand.
B066C006V006	66	6	6	And I heard a voice in the midst of the four living creatures saying, A quart of wheat for a denarius, and three quarts of barley for a denarius; and do not hurt the oil and the wine.
B066C006V007	66	6	7	And when he had opened the fourth seal, I heard the voice of the fourth living creature say, Come.
B066C006V008	66	6	8	And I looked, and behold, a pale horse: and the name of him who sat upon it was Death, and Hades followed with him. And power was given to them over the fourth part of the earth, to kill with sword, and with hunger, and with plague, and with the wild beasts of the earth.
B066C006V009	66	6	9	And when he had opened the fifth seal, I saw under the altar the souls of those who were slain for the word of God, and for the testimony which they maintained:
B066C006V010	66	6	10	And they cried with a loud voice, saying, How long, O Lord, holy and true, must it be before you judge those who live on the earth, and avenge our blood?
B066C006V011	66	6	11	And white robes were given to every one of them; and it was said to them, that they should rest yet for a little longer, until the number of their fellow servants and their brethren, who would be killed as they were, should be completed.
B066C006V012	66	6	12	And I beheld, and, lo, when he had opened the sixth seal, there was a great earthquake; and the sun became black as sackcloth of hair, and the moon became as blood;
B066C006V013	66	6	13	And the stars of the sky fell to the earth, as a fig tree casts down its unripe figs, when it is shaken by a mighty wind.
B066C006V014	66	6	14	And the sky vanished, as a scroll when it is rolled together; and every mountain and island was moved out of its place.
B066C006V015	66	6	15	And the kings of the earth, and the great men, and the rich men, and the chief captains, and the mighty men, and every slave, and every free man, hid in the caves and among the rocks of the mountains;
B066C006V016	66	6	16	And they called to the mountains and rocks, Fall on us, and hide us from the face of him who sits on the throne, and from the wrath of the Lamb:
B066C006V017	66	6	17	For the great day of his wrath has come; and who shall be able to stand?
B066C007V001	66	7	1	And after these things I saw four angels standing at the four corners of the earth, holding back the four winds of the earth, that the wind should not blow on the earth, nor on the sea, nor on any tree.
B066C007V002	66	7	2	And I saw another angel ascending from the east, having the seal of the living God: and he cried with a loud voice to the four angels, to whom had been given power to hurt the earth and the sea,
B066C007V003	66	7	3	Saying, Do not hurt the earth, or the sea, or the trees, until we have sealed the servants of our God on their foreheads.
B066C007V004	66	7	4	And I heard the number of those who were sealed: and there were sealed a hundred and forty-four thousand from all the tribes of the sons of Israel.
B066C007V005	66	7	5	From the tribe of Judah were sealed twelve thousand. From the tribe of Reuben were sealed twelve thousand. From the tribe of Gad were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V006	66	7	6	From the tribe of Asher were sealed twelve thousand. From the tribe of Naphtali were sealed twelve thousand. From the tribe of Manasseh were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V007	66	7	7	From the tribe of Simeon were sealed twelve thousand. From the tribe of Levi were sealed twelve thousand. From the tribe of Issachar were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V008	66	7	8	From the tribe of Zebulun were sealed twelve thousand. From the tribe of Joseph were sealed twelve thousand. From the tribe of Benjamin were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V009	66	7	9	After this I beheld, and, lo, a great multitude, which no man could number, from all nations, and tribes, and peoples, and tongues, stood before the throne, and before the Lamb, clothed with white robes, with palm branches in their hands;
B066C007V010	66	7	10	And cried out with a loud voice, saying, Salvation belongs to our God who sits upon the throne, and to the Lamb.
B066C007V011	66	7	11	And all the angels stood around the throne and around the elders and the four living creatures, and they fell before the throne on their faces, and worshipped God,
B066C007V012	66	7	12	Saying, Amen: Blessing, and glory, and wisdom, and thanksgiving, and honour, and power, and might, be to our God forever and ever. Amen.
B066C007V013	66	7	13	And one of the elders addressed me, saying, Who are these who are arrayed in white robes? and from where did they come?
B066C007V014	66	7	14	And I said to him, Sir, you know. And he said to me, These are the ones who have come out of the great tribulation, and have washed their robes, and made them white in the blood of the Lamb.
B066C007V015	66	7	15	Therefore, they are before the throne of God, and serve him day and night in his temple: and he who sits on the throne shall spread his tabernacle over them.
B066C007V016	66	7	16	They shall hunger no more, nor shall they thirst any more; nor shall the sun beat upon them, nor shall any scorching heat.
B066C007V017	66	7	17	For the Lamb who is at the center of the throne shall be their shepherd, and shall lead them to the springs of the waters of life: and God shall wipe away all tears from their eyes.
B066C008V001	66	8	1	And when he had opened the seventh seal, there was silence in heaven for about half an hour.
B066C008V002	66	8	2	And I saw the seven angels who stand before God; and to them were given seven trumpets.
B066C008V003	66	8	3	And another angel came and stood at the altar, having a golden censer; and there was given to him much incense, that he should offer it with the prayers of all the saints upon the golden altar which was before the throne.
B066C008V004	66	8	4	And the smoke of the incense, with the prayers of the saints, ascended before God out of the angel's hand.
B066C008V005	66	8	5	And the angel took the censer, and filled it with fire from the altar, and cast it upon the earth: and there were rumblings, and peals of thunder, and flashes of lightning, and an earthquake.
B066C008V006	66	8	6	And the seven angels who had the seven trumpets prepared to sound them.
B066C008V007	66	8	7	The first angel sounded, and there followed hail and fire mingled with blood, and they were cast upon the earth: and a third of the earth was burned up, and a third of the trees were burned up, and all the green grass was burned up.
B066C008V008	66	8	8	And the second angel sounded, and something like a great mountain burning with fire was cast into the sea: and a third of the sea became blood;
B066C008V009	66	8	9	And a third of the creatures which were in the sea, and had life, died; and a third of the ships were destroyed.
B066C008V010	66	8	10	And the third angel sounded, and a great star fell from heaven, burning as if it were a torch, and it fell upon a third of the rivers, and upon the springs of waters;
B066C008V011	66	8	11	And the name of the star is Wormwood: and a third of the waters became wormwood; and many men died from the waters, because they were made bitter.
B066C008V012	66	8	12	And the fourth angel sounded, and a third of the sun was smitten, and a third of the moon, and a third of the stars; so that a third of them was darkened, and a third of the day the light did not shine, and likewise a third of the night.
B066C008V013	66	8	13	And I beheld, and heard an eagle flying through mid-heaven, saying with a loud voice, Woe, woe, woe, to the inhabitants of the earth, because of the blasts of the trumpets by the other three angels, which are about to sound!
B066C009V001	66	9	1	And the fifth angel sounded, and I saw a star fall from heaven to the earth: and to him was given the key to the bottomless pit.
B066C009V002	66	9	2	And he opened the bottomless pit; and there arose smoke out of the pit, like the smoke of a great furnace; and the sun and the air were darkened by the smoke from the pit.
B066C009V003	66	9	3	And there came out of the smoke locusts upon the earth: and to them was given power, as the scorpions of the earth have power.
B066C009V004	66	9	4	And they were told not to harm the grass of the earth, nor any green thing, nor any tree; but only those men who do not have the seal of God on their foreheads.
B066C009V005	66	9	5	And they were not permitted to kill them, but only to torment them for five months: and their torment was like the torment of a scorpion, when he stings a man.
B066C009V006	66	9	6	And in those days shall men seek death, and shall not find it; and shall desire to die, and death shall flee from them.
B066C009V007	66	9	7	And the appearance of the locusts was like horses prepared for battle; and on their heads were what looked like crowns of gold, and their faces were like the faces of men.
B066C009V008	66	9	8	And they had hair like the hair of women, and their teeth were like the teeth of lions.
B066C009V009	66	9	9	And they had breastplates, like breastplates of iron; and the sound of their wings was like the sound of chariots and horses rushing to battle.
B066C009V010	66	9	10	And they had tails like scorpions, and stings; and in their tails they had the power to hurt men for five months.
B066C009V011	66	9	11	And they had a king over them, the angel of the bottomless pit, whose name in the Hebrew tongue is Abaddon, but in the Greek tongue, Apollyon.
B066C009V012	66	9	12	One woe is past; behold, there are two more woes yet to come.
B066C009V013	66	9	13	And the sixth angel sounded, and I heard a voice from the four horns of the golden altar which is before God,
B066C009V014	66	9	14	Saying to the sixth angel who had the trumpet, Release the four angels who are bound at the great river Euphrates.
B066C009V015	66	9	15	And the four angels were released, who had been prepared for this hour, and day, and month, and year, to kill a third of mankind.
B066C009V016	66	9	16	And the number of the armies of the horsemen were two hundred million: I heard the number of them.
B066C009V017	66	9	17	And in the vision, this was how I saw the horses and those who sat upon them: they wore breastplates of fiery red, sapphire blue, and sulphur yellow: and the heads of the horses were like the heads of lions; and out of their mouths came fire and smoke and sulphur.
B066C009V018	66	9	18	By these three was a third of mankind killed, by the fire, and by the smoke, and by the sulphur, which came out of their mouths.
B066C009V019	66	9	19	For the power of the horses is in their mouths, and in their tails: for their tails were like serpents, and had heads, and with them they do harm.
B066C009V020	66	9	20	And the rest of mankind, who were not killed by these plagues, still did not repent of the works of their hands; they did not stop worshipping devils, and idols of gold, and silver, and bronze, and stone, and wood: which can neither see, nor hear, nor walk:
B066C009V021	66	9	21	Nor did they repent of their murders, or of their sorceries, or of their sexual immorality, or of their thefts.
B066C010V001	66	10	1	And I saw another mighty angel come down from heaven, clothed with a cloud: and a rainbow was upon his head, and his face was like the sun, and his feet like pillars of fire.
B066C010V002	66	10	2	And he had open in his hand a little scroll: and he set his right foot upon the sea, and his left foot upon the earth,
B066C010V003	66	10	3	And he cried out with a loud voice, as when a lion roars: and when he had cried out, the voices of seven thunders spoke.
B066C010V004	66	10	4	And when the seven thunders had spoken, I was about to write: and I heard a voice from heaven saying to me, Seal up those things which the seven thunders spoke, and do not write them.
B066C010V005	66	10	5	And the angel, whom I saw standing upon the sea and upon the earth, lifted up his hand to heaven,
B066C010V006	66	10	6	And swore by him who lives forever and ever, who created heaven, and the things that are in it, and the earth, and the things that are in it, and the sea, and the things that are in it, that there should be no more delay:
B066C010V007	66	10	7	But in the days of the voice of the seventh angel, when he is about to sound, the mystery of God will be fulfilled, as he has declared to his servants the prophets.
B066C010V008	66	10	8	And the voice which I heard from heaven spoke to me again, and said, Go and take the little scroll which is open in the hand of the angel who stands upon the sea and upon the earth.
B066C010V009	66	10	9	And I went to the angel, and said to him, Give me the little scroll. And he said to me, Take, and eat it; it shall make your stomach bitter, but in your mouth it shall be sweet as honey.
B066C010V010	66	10	10	And I took the little scroll out of the angel's hand, and ate it; and in my mouth it was sweet as honey: but as soon as I had eaten it, my stomach was made bitter.
B066C010V011	66	10	11	And he said to me, You must prophesy again about many peoples, and nations, and tongues, and kings.
B066C011V001	66	11	1	And there was given to me a reed like a measuring rod: and I was told, Rise, and measure the temple of God, and the altar, and those who worship there.
B066C011V002	66	11	2	But the court which is outside the temple leave out, and do not measure it; for it is given to the Gentiles: and they shall tread the holy city under foot for forty-two months.
B066C011V003	66	11	3	And I will give power to my two witnesses, and they shall prophesy for a thousand two hundred and sixty days, clothed in sackcloth.
B066C011V004	66	11	4	These are the two olive trees, and the two lampstands standing before the Lord of the earth.
B066C011V005	66	11	5	And if any man wants to harm them, fire proceeds out of their mouths, and devours their enemies: and if any man wants to harm them, he must in this manner be killed.
B066C011V006	66	11	6	These two have power to shut up the sky, so that it does not rain during the days of their prophesying: and have power over the waters, to turn them to blood, and to strike the earth with all manner of plagues, as often as they desire.
B066C011V007	66	11	7	And when they shall have finished their testimony, the beast that ascends out of the bottomless pit shall make war against them, and shall overcome them, and kill them.
B066C011V008	66	11	8	And their dead bodies shall lie in the street of the great city, which figuratively is called Sodom and Egypt, where also their Lord was crucified.
B066C011V009	66	11	9	For three days and a half, men from the peoples and tribes and tongues and nations shall see their dead bodies, and shall not allow their dead bodies to be put in a tomb.
B066C011V010	66	11	10	And those who live upon the earth shall rejoice over them, and make merry, and shall send gifts to one another; because these two prophets tormented those who dwell upon the earth.
B066C011V011	66	11	11	And after three days and a half the breath of life from God entered them, and they stood upon their feet; and great fear fell upon those who saw them.
B066C011V012	66	11	12	And they heard a great voice from heaven saying to them, Come up here. And they ascended to heaven in a cloud; and their enemies beheld them.
B066C011V013	66	11	13	And that hour there was a great earthquake, and a tenth of the city fell, and in the earthquake were slain seven thousand men: and the remnant were terrified, and gave glory to the God of heaven.
B066C011V014	66	11	14	The second woe is past; behold, the third woe comes quickly.
B066C011V015	66	11	15	And the seventh angel sounded; and there were great voices in heaven, saying, The kingdom of the world has become the kingdom of our Lord, and of his Christ; and he shall reign forever and ever.
B066C011V016	66	11	16	And the twenty-four elders, who sit before God on their thrones, fell upon their faces, and worshipped God,
B066C011V017	66	11	17	Saying, We give you thanks, O Lord God Almighty, who are, and were; because you have taken your great power, and have begun to reign.
B066C011V018	66	11	18	The nations raged, and your wrath came; and the time came for the dead to be judged, and to reward your servants the prophets, and the saints, and those who fear your name, both small and great; and to destroy those who destroy the earth.
B066C011V019	66	11	19	Then the temple of God in heaven was opened, and there was seen in his temple the ark of his covenant: and there were flashes of lightning, and rumblings, and peals of thunder, and an earthquake, and a great hailstorm.
B066C012V001	66	12	1	And there appeared a great sign in heaven; a woman clothed with the sun, and the moon under her feet, and upon her head a crown of twelve stars:
B066C012V002	66	12	2	And she was with child, and in the pains of birth cried out to be delivered.
B066C012V003	66	12	3	And there appeared another sign in heaven; behold, a great red dragon, having seven heads and ten horns, and seven crowns upon his heads.
B066C012V004	66	12	4	And his tail swept away a third of the stars of heaven, and cast them to the earth: and the dragon stood before the woman who was about to give birth, to devour her child as soon as it was born.
B066C012V005	66	12	5	And she brought forth a male child, who is to rule all nations with a rod of iron: and her child was caught up to God, and to his throne.
B066C012V006	66	12	6	And the woman fled into the wilderness, where she has a place prepared by God, in which she might be sustained for one thousand two hundred and sixty days.
B066C012V007	66	12	7	And there was war in heaven: Michael and his angels fought against the dragon; and the dragon and his angels fought,
B066C012V008	66	12	8	But were not strong enough; and there was no longer any place for them in heaven.
B066C012V009	66	12	9	And the great dragon was cast down, that old serpent, called the Devil, and Satan, who deceives the whole world: he was cast down to the earth, and his angels were cast down with him.
B066C012V010	66	12	10	And I heard a loud voice in heaven saying, Now salvation, and strength, and the kingdom of our God, and the authority of his Christ have come: for the accuser of our brethren has been cast down, who accuses them before our God day and night.
B066C012V011	66	12	11	And they overcame him by the blood of the Lamb, and by the word of their testimony; and they did not love their lives to death.
B066C012V012	66	12	12	Therefore rejoice, you heavens, and you who live in them. Woe to the inhabitants of the earth and of the sea! for the devil has come down to you, having great wrath, because he knows that he has but a short time.
