B066C012V014	66	12	14	And to the woman was given the two wings of a great eagle, that she might fly into the wilderness, to her place, where she would be sustained for a time, and times, and half a time, away from the face of the serpent.
B066C012V015	66	12	15	And the serpent spewed out of his mouth water like a river after the woman, that he might cause her to be carried away by the flood.
B066C012V016	66	12	16	And the earth helped the woman, and the ground opened its mouth, and swallowed up the flood which the dragon spewed out of his mouth.
B066C012V017	66	12	17	And the dragon was furious with the woman, and went to make war against the rest of her descendants, those who keep the commandments of God, and hold to the testimony of Jesus.
B066C013V001	66	13	1	And I saw a beast rise up out of the sea, having seven heads and ten horns, and upon his horns ten crowns, and upon each head a name of blasphemy.
B066C013V002	66	13	2	And the beast which I saw was like a leopard, and his feet were like the feet of a bear, and his mouth like the mouth of a lion: and the dragon gave him his power, and his throne, and great authority.
B066C013V003	66	13	3	And one of his heads seemed to have had a death-blow; but his deadly wound was healed: and all the world was astonished and followed after the beast.
B066C013V004	66	13	4	And they worshipped the dragon, because he gave authority to the beast: and they worshipped the beast, saying, Who is like the beast? who is able to make war against him?
B066C013V005	66	13	5	And there was given to him a mouth speaking proud words and blasphemies; and authority was given to him to act for forty-two months.
B066C013V006	66	13	6	And he opened his mouth in blasphemy against God, to blaspheme his name, and his dwelling, and those who live in heaven.
B066C013V007	66	13	7	And it was given to him to make war on the saints, and to overcome them: and authority was given to him over every tribe, and people, and tongue, and nation.
B066C013V008	66	13	8	And all who live upon the earth shall worship him, every one whose name is not written in the book of life of the Lamb that was slain from the foundation of the world.
B066C013V009	66	13	9	If any man has an ear, let him hear.
B066C013V010	66	13	10	He who is to go into captivity shall go into captivity: he who kills with the sword must be killed with the sword. Here is the endurance and the faith of the saints.
B066C013V011	66	13	11	And I beheld another beast coming up out of the earth; and he had two horns like a lamb, and he spoke like a dragon.
B066C013V012	66	13	12	And he exercises all the power of the first beast in his presence, and causes the earth and those who live in it to worship the first beast, whose deadly wound was healed.
B066C013V013	66	13	13	And he performs great wonders, so that he even makes fire come down from heaven to the earth in the sight of men,
B066C013V014	66	13	14	And deceives those who live on the earth by the miracles which he had the power to do in the sight of the beast; bidding those who live on the earth to make an image in honour of the beast, who was wounded by the sword, and yet lived.
B066C013V015	66	13	15	And he had power to give breath to the image of the beast, that the image of the beast should both speak, and cause as many as would not worship the image of the beast to be killed.
B066C013V016	66	13	16	And he causes everyone, both small and great, rich and poor, free and slave, to receive a mark on his right hand, or on his forehead:
B066C013V017	66	13	17	And no man might buy or sell, unless he had the mark, or the name of the beast, or the number of his name.
B066C013V018	66	13	18	This calls for wisdom. Let him who has understanding calculate the number of the beast, for it is the number of a man; and his number is six hundred and sixty-six.
B066C014V001	66	14	1	And I looked, and, lo, a Lamb stood on mount Zion, and with him a hundred and forty-four thousand, who had his name and his Father's name written on their foreheads.
B066C014V002	66	14	2	And I heard a voice from heaven, like the sound of many waters, and like the roar of great thunder: the voice I heard was like the sound of harpists playing upon their harps:
B066C014V003	66	14	3	And they sang a new song before the throne, and before the four living creatures, and the elders: and no man could learn that song but the hundred and forty-four thousand, who had been redeemed from the earth.
B066C014V004	66	14	4	These are the ones who have not defiled themselves with women; for they are chaste. These are those who follow the Lamb wherever he goes. They were redeemed from among men, as first-fruits to God and to the Lamb.
B066C014V005	66	14	5	And no lie was found in their mouths: for they are without fault.
B066C014V006	66	14	6	And I saw another angel flying in mid-heaven, having an eternal gospel to preach to those who live on the earth, to every nation, and tribe, and tongue, and people,
B066C014V007	66	14	7	Saying with a loud voice, Fear God, and give glory to him; for the hour of his judgment has come: and worship him who made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and the springs of water.
B066C014V008	66	14	8	And there followed another angel, saying, Fallen, fallen, is Babylon the great, she who made all the nations drink of the maddening wine of her adulteries.
B066C014V009	66	14	9	And the third angel followed them, saying with a loud voice, If any man worships the beast and his image, and receives his mark on his forehead, or on his hand,
B066C014V010	66	14	10	He shall also drink of the wine of the wrath of God, which is poured out at full strength into the cup of his anger; and he shall be tormented with fire and sulphur in the presence of the holy angels, and in the presence of the Lamb:
B066C014V011	66	14	11	And the smoke of their torment ascends forever and ever: and they have no rest day or night, who worship the beast and his image, or who receive the mark of his name.
B066C014V012	66	14	12	Here is the endurance of the saints, who keep the commandments of God and their faith in Jesus.
B066C014V013	66	14	13	And I heard a voice from heaven saying to me, Write, Blessed are the dead who die in the Lord henceforth: Yes, says the Spirit, that they may rest from their labours; for their works follow them.
B066C014V014	66	14	14	And I looked, and behold, a white cloud, and upon the cloud sat one like a son of man, having on his head a golden crown, and in his hand a sharp sickle.
B066C014V015	66	14	15	And another angel came out of the temple, crying out with a loud voice to him who sat on the cloud, Thrust in your sickle, and reap: for the time has come to reap; for the harvest of the earth is ripe.
B066C014V016	66	14	16	And he who sat upon the cloud swung his sickle on the earth; and the earth was reaped.
B066C014V017	66	14	17	And another angel came out of the temple which is in heaven, and he also had a sharp sickle.
B066C014V018	66	14	18	And another angel came out from the altar, the angel who has power over fire; and cried out with a loud cry to him who had the sharp sickle, saying, Thrust in your sharp sickle, and gather the clusters from the vine of the earth; for her grapes are fully ripe.
B066C014V019	66	14	19	And the angel swung his sickle upon the earth, and gathered the grapes from the vine of the earth, and cast them into the great winepress of the wrath of God.
B066C014V020	66	14	20	And the winepress was trodden outside the city, and blood came out of the winepress, as high as the horses' bridles, for a distance of a thousand and six hundred stadia.
B066C015V001	66	15	1	And I saw another sign in heaven, great and marvellous, seven angels having the seven last plagues; for with them the wrath of God is completed.
B066C015V002	66	15	2	And I saw, as it were, a sea of glass mingled with fire: and those who had won the victory over the beast, and over his image, and over his mark, and over the number of his name, standing on the sea of glass, holding the harps of God.
B066C015V003	66	15	3	And they sang the song of Moses, the servant of God, and the song of the Lamb, saying, Great and marvellous are your works, Lord God Almighty; just and true are your ways, O King of the ages.
B066C015V004	66	15	4	Who shall not fear you, O Lord, and glorify your name? for you alone are holy: all nations shall come and worship before you; for your righteous acts have been revealed.
B066C015V005	66	15	5	And after that I looked, and the temple of the tabernacle of testimony in heaven was opened:
B066C015V006	66	15	6	And the seven angels came out of the temple, having the seven plagues, clothed in pure and white linen, and having their breasts girded with golden girdles.
B066C015V007	66	15	7	And one of the four living creatures gave to the seven angels seven golden bowls full of the wrath of God, who lives forever and ever.
B066C015V008	66	15	8	And the temple was filled with smoke from the glory of God, and from his power; and no man was able to enter the temple, until the seven plagues of the seven angels were ended.
B066C016V001	66	16	1	And I heard a great voice out of the temple saying to the seven angels, Go and pour out the bowls of the wrath of God upon the earth.
B066C016V002	66	16	2	And the first went, and poured out his bowl upon the earth; and foul and malignant sores fell upon the men who had the mark of the beast, and upon those who worshipped his image.
B066C016V003	66	16	3	And the second angel poured out his bowl upon the sea; and it became like the blood of a dead man: and every living thing in the sea died.
B066C016V004	66	16	4	And the third angel poured out his bowl upon the rivers and springs of water; and they became blood.
B066C016V005	66	16	5	And I heard the angel of the waters say, You are righteous, you who are, and were, O Holy One, because you have judged thus.
B066C016V006	66	16	6	For they have shed the blood of saints and prophets, and you have given them blood to drink; for such is their due.
B066C016V007	66	16	7	And I heard the altar say, Yes, Lord God Almighty, true and righteous are your judgments.
B066C016V008	66	16	8	And the fourth angel poured out his bowl upon the sun; and it was given power to scorch men with fire.
B066C016V009	66	16	9	And men were scorched with great heat, and blasphemed the name of God, who has power over these plagues: and they did not repent and give him glory.
B066C016V010	66	16	10	And the fifth angel poured out his bowl upon the throne of the beast; and his kingdom was filled with darkness; and they gnawed their tongues in pain,
B066C016V011	66	16	11	And blasphemed the God of heaven because of their pains and their sores, and did not repent of their deeds.
B066C016V012	66	16	12	And the sixth angel poured out his bowl upon the great river Euphrates; and its water was dried up, that the way for the kings of the east might be prepared.
B066C016V013	66	16	13	And I saw three unclean spirits like frogs come out of the mouth of the dragon, and out of the mouth of the beast, and out of the mouth of the false prophet.
B066C016V014	66	16	14	For they are the spirits of devils, working miraculous signs, who go forth to the kings of the whole world, to gather them for battle on the great day of God Almighty.
B066C016V015	66	16	15	Behold, I come like a thief. Blessed is he who stays awake, and keeps his garments with him, lest he walk naked and ashamed for all to see.
B066C016V016	66	16	16	And they gathered them together at the place which in Hebrew is called Armageddon.
B066C016V017	66	16	17	And the seventh angel poured out his bowl into the air; and there came a great voice out of the temple, from the throne, saying, It is done.
B066C016V018	66	16	18	And there were flashes of lightning, and rumblings, and peals of thunder; and there was a great earthquake, such as had never been since men were upon the earth, so mighty an earthquake it was, and so great.
B066C016V019	66	16	19	And the great city was broken into three parts, and the cities of the nations fell: and God remembered Babylon the great, to give her the cup of the wine of the fury of his wrath.
B066C016V020	66	16	20	And every island fled away, and the mountains were not found.
B066C016V021	66	16	21	And there fell upon men a great hail out of heaven, every stone about the weight of a talent: and men blasphemed God because of the plague of hail; for the plague was exceedingly great.
B066C017V001	66	17	1	Then one of the seven angels who had the seven bowls, came and spoke to me, saying, Come here; I will show you the judgment of the great harlot who sits upon many waters.
B066C017V002	66	17	2	With her the kings of the earth have committed acts of adultery, and the inhabitants of the earth have been made drunk with the wine of her adulteries.
B066C017V003	66	17	3	So he carried me away in the spirit into the wilderness: and I saw a woman sitting upon a scarlet coloured beast, which was full of names of blasphemy, and had seven heads and ten horns.
B066C017V004	66	17	4	And the woman was arrayed in purple and scarlet, and decked with gold and precious stones and pearls, having a golden cup in her hand full of abominations and of the filthiness of her adulteries:
B066C017V005	66	17	5	And upon her forehead was a name written, MYSTERY, BABYLON THE GREAT, THE MOTHER OF HARLOTS AND OF THE ABOMINATIONS OF THE EARTH.
B066C017V006	66	17	6	And I saw the woman drunk with the blood of the saints, and with the blood of the martyrs of Jesus: and when I saw her, I wondered greatly.
B066C017V007	66	17	7	And the angel said to me, Why do you wonder? I will tell you the mystery of the woman, and of the beast that carries her, which has the seven heads and ten horns.
B066C017V008	66	17	8	The beast that you saw was, and is not; and shall ascend out of the bottomless pit, and go to perdition: and those who live on the earth whose names have not been written in the book of life from the foundation of the world, shall marvel when they behold the beast, because he was, and is not, and is to come.
B066C017V009	66	17	9	This calls for a mind with wisdom. The seven heads are seven mountains, on which the woman sits.
B066C017V010	66	17	10	And there are seven kings: five have fallen, and one is, and the other has not yet come; and when he comes, he must remain for a short time.
B066C017V011	66	17	11	And the beast that was, and is not, is the eighth; and yet is one of the seven, and he goes to perdition.
B066C017V012	66	17	12	And the ten horns which you saw are ten kings, who have received no kingdom as yet; but receive authority as kings for one hour, along with the beast.
B066C017V013	66	17	13	These are of one mind, and shall give their power and authority to the beast.
B066C017V014	66	17	14	They shall make war against the Lamb, and the Lamb shall overcome them: for he is Lord of lords, and King of kings: and those who are with him are called, and chosen, and faithful.
B066C017V015	66	17	15	And he said to me, The waters which you saw, where the harlot sits, are peoples, and multitudes, and nations, and tongues.
B066C017V016	66	17	16	And the ten horns which you saw, and the beast, they shall hate the harlot, and shall make her desolate and naked, and shall eat her flesh, and burn her with fire.
B066C017V017	66	17	17	For God has put in their hearts to accomplish his purpose, by agreeing to give their sovereignty to the beast, until the words of God shall be fulfilled.
B066C017V018	66	17	18	And the woman you saw is the great city, which reigns over the kings of the earth.
B066C018V001	66	18	1	And after these things I saw another angel come down from heaven, having great power; and the earth was illuminated by his glory.
B066C018V002	66	18	2	And he cried out with a mighty voice, saying, Fallen, fallen is Babylon the great. It has become the dwelling place of devils, and the haunt of every foul spirit, and a haunt of every unclean and loathsome bird.
B066C018V003	66	18	3	For all nations have drunk of the wine of the wrath of her adulteries, and the kings of the earth have committed adultery with her, and the merchants of the earth have grown rich with her excessive luxuries.
B066C018V004	66	18	4	And I heard another voice from heaven, saying, Come out of her, my people, that you may not be partakers of her sins, and that you may not receive her plagues.
B066C018V005	66	18	5	For her sins have piled up to heaven, and God has remembered her iniquities.
B066C018V006	66	18	6	Repay her as she has paid, and double, according to her works: in the cup which she has mixed for others, mix for her a double portion.
B066C018V007	66	18	7	As she glorified herself and lived in luxury, give to her that measure of torment and grief: for she says in her heart, I sit as a queen, and am no widow, and shall never see sorrow.
B066C018V008	66	18	8	Therefore her plagues shall come in one day, pestilence, and mourning, and famine; and she shall be utterly burned with fire: for mighty is the Lord God who judges her.
B066C018V009	66	18	9	And the kings of the earth, who have committed adultery and lived luxuriously with her, shall bewail her, and lament for her, when they shall see the smoke of her burning;
B066C018V010	66	18	10	They shall stand far off in fear of her torment, saying, Alas, alas, the great city Babylon, that mighty city! for in one hour your judgment has come.
B066C018V011	66	18	11	And the merchants of the earth shall weep and mourn over her; for no man buys their cargoes any more:
B066C018V012	66	18	12	Cargoes of gold, and silver, and precious stones, and of pearls, and fine linen, and purple, and silk, and scarlet, and all citron wood, and all articles of ivory, and all articles of precious wood, and of bronze, and iron, and marble,
B066C018V013	66	18	13	And cinnamon, and spice, and incense, and myrrh, and frankincense, and wine, and oil, and fine flour, and wheat, and cattle, and sheep, and horses, and chariots, and slaves, and the souls of men.
B066C018V014	66	18	14	And the fruits that your soul longed for have departed from you, and all the luxuries and splendour have vanished, never to be found again.
B066C018V015	66	18	15	The merchants of these things, who were made rich by her, shall stand far off in fear of her torment, weeping and mourning,
B066C018V016	66	18	16	And saying, Alas, alas, the great city, that was clothed in fine linen, and purple, and scarlet, and decked with gold, and precious stones, and pearls!
B066C018V017	66	18	17	For in one hour such great wealth has come to ruin. And every shipmaster, and all voyagers in ships, and sailors, and as many as make their living by the sea, stood far off,
B066C018V018	66	18	18	And cried out when they saw the smoke of her burning, saying, What city was ever like this great city!
B066C018V019	66	18	19	And they cast dust upon their heads, and cried, weeping and mourning, saying, Alas, alas, the great city, by which all who had ships on the sea were made rich by her wealth! for in one hour she has been laid waste.
B066C018V020	66	18	20	Rejoice over her, O heaven, and you saints and apostles and prophets; for God has judged her for what she did to you.
B066C018V021	66	18	21	And a mighty angel took up a stone like a great millstone, and cast it into the sea, saying, With such violence shall the great city Babylon be thrown down, and shall never be found again.
B066C018V022	66	18	22	And the sound of harpists, and musicians, and of flute players, and trumpeters, shall never be heard in you again; and no craftsman, of whatever craft, shall be found in you any more; and the sound of a millstone shall never be heard in you again;
B066C018V023	66	18	23	And the light of a lamp shall never shine in you again; and the voice of the bridegroom and of the bride shall never be heard in you again: your merchants were the great men of the earth; and by your sorceries all nations were deceived.
B066C018V024	66	18	24	And in her was found the blood of prophets, and of saints, and of all who have been slain upon the earth.
B066C019V001	66	19	1	And after these things I heard the roar of a great multitude in heaven, saying, Alleluia; Salvation, and glory, and power belong to our God:
B066C019V002	66	19	2	For true and righteous are his judgments: for he has judged the great harlot, who corrupted the earth with her adulteries, and has avenged on her the blood of his servants.
B066C019V003	66	19	3	And again they said, Alleluia. Her smoke rises up forever and ever.
B066C019V004	66	19	4	And the twenty-four elders and the four living creatures fell down and worshipped God who sits on the throne, saying, Amen; Alleluia.
B066C019V005	66	19	5	And a voice came from the throne, saying, Praise our God, all you his servants, you who fear him, both small and great.
B066C019V006	66	19	6	And I heard, as it were, the voice of a great multitude, like the sound of many waters, like the sound of mighty peals of thunder, saying, Alleluia: for the Lord our God omnipotent reigns.
B066C019V007	66	19	7	Let us be glad and rejoice, and give glory to him: for the marriage of the Lamb has come, and his bride has made herself ready.
B066C019V008	66	19	8	And it was granted to her to be clothed in fine linen, clean and white: for the fine linen is the righteous deeds of the saints.
B066C019V009	66	19	9	And he said to me, Write, Blessed are those who are invited to the marriage supper of the Lamb. And he said to me, These are the true words of God.
B066C019V010	66	19	10	And I fell at his feet to worship him. And he said to me, Do not do that: I am a fellow servant with you and your brethren, who hold to the testimony of Jesus: worship God: for the testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy.
B066C019V011	66	19	11	And I saw heaven opened, and behold, a white horse; and he who sat upon it was called Faithful and True, and in righteousness he judges and makes war.
B066C019V012	66	19	12	His eyes were like a flame of fire, and on his head were many crowns; and he had a name written upon him, that no man knew, but he himself.
B066C019V013	66	19	13	And he was clothed with a robe dipped in blood: and his name is called The Word of God.
B066C019V014	66	19	14	And the armies of heaven followed him upon white horses, clothed in fine linen, white and clean.
B066C019V015	66	19	15	And out of his mouth comes a sharp sword, with which he may strike the nations: and he shall rule them with a rod of iron: and he treads the winepress of the fury of the wrath of Almighty God.
B066C019V016	66	19	16	And he has on his robe and on his thigh a name written, KING OF KINGS, AND LORD OF LORDS.
B066C019V017	66	19	17	And I saw an angel standing in the sun; and he cried out with a loud voice, saying to all the birds that fly in mid-heaven, Come and gather yourselves together for the great supper of God;
B066C019V018	66	19	18	That you may eat the flesh of kings, and the flesh of captains, and the flesh of mighty men, and the flesh of horses, and of those who sit upon them, and the flesh of all men, both free and slave, both small and great.
B066C019V019	66	19	19	And I saw the beast, and the kings of the earth, and their armies, gathered together to make war against him who sat upon the horse, and against his army.
B066C019V020	66	19	20	And the beast was seized, and with him the false prophet who performed miraculous signs in his presence, with which he deceived those who had received the mark of the beast, and those who worshipped his image. They were both cast alive into the lake of fire that burns with sulphur.
B066C019V021	66	19	21	And the rest were slain with the sword that came out of the mouth of him who sat upon the horse: and all the birds were filled with their flesh.
B066C020V001	66	20	1	And I saw an angel come down from heaven, having the key of the bottomless pit and a great chain in his hand.
B066C020V002	66	20	2	And he laid hold of the dragon, that old serpent, who is the Devil, and Satan, and bound him for a thousand years,
B066C020V003	66	20	3	And cast him into the bottomless pit, and shut him up, and sealed it over him, that he should no longer deceive the nations, until the thousand years should be ended: and after that he must be released for a short time.
B066C020V004	66	20	4	And I saw thrones, on which were seated those to whom judgment had been given: and I saw the souls of those who had been beheaded for their witness for Jesus, and for the word of God, and who had not worshipped the beast, nor his image, nor had they received his mark upon their foreheads, or on their hands; and they lived again and reigned with Christ for a thousand years.
B066C020V005	66	20	5	But the rest of the dead did not come to life again until the thousand years were ended. This is the first resurrection.
B066C020V006	66	20	6	Blessed and holy is he who takes part in the first resurrection: over these the second death has no power, but they shall be priests of God and of Christ, and shall reign with him for a thousand years.
B066C020V007	66	20	7	And when the thousand years have expired, Satan shall be released from his prison,
B066C020V008	66	20	8	And shall go out to deceive the nations which are in the four quarters of the earth, Gog and Magog, to gather them together for battle: the number of them is like the sand of the sea.
B066C020V009	66	20	9	And they marched across the breadth of the earth, and surrounded the camp of the saints, and the beloved city: and fire came down from God out of heaven, and devoured them.
B066C020V010	66	20	10	And the devil, who deceived them, was cast into the lake of fire and sulphur, where the beast and the false prophet were, and they shall be tormented day and night forever and ever.
B066C020V011	66	20	11	And I saw a great white throne, and him who sat upon it, from whose face earth and heaven fled away; and there was found no place for them.
B066C020V012	66	20	12	And I saw the dead, great and small, standing before the throne; and the books were opened: and another book was opened, which is the book of life: and the dead were judged by those things which were written in the books, according to their deeds.
B066C020V013	66	20	13	And the sea gave up the dead who were in it; and death and Hades delivered up the dead who were in them: and they were judged, every man according to his deeds.
B066C020V014	66	20	14	And death and Hades were cast into the lake of fire. This is the second death, the lake of fire.
B066C020V015	66	20	15	And whoever was not found written in the book of life was cast into the lake of fire.
B066C021V001	66	21	1	And I saw a new heaven and a new earth: for the first heaven and the first earth had passed away; and there was no more sea.
B066C021V002	66	21	2	And I saw the holy city, new Jerusalem, coming down from God out of heaven, prepared as a bride adorned for her husband.
B066C021V003	66	21	3	And I heard a great voice from the throne saying, Behold, the tabernacle of God is with men, and he shall live among them, and they shall be his people, and God himself shall be with them, and be their God.
B066C021V004	66	21	4	And he shall wipe away every tear from their eyes; and there shall be no more death, or sorrow, or crying, or pain: for the former things have passed away.
B066C021V005	66	21	5	And he who sits upon the throne said, Behold, I make all things new. And he said to me, Write: for these words are faithful and true.
B066C021V006	66	21	6	And he said to me, It is done. I am the Alpha and the Omega, the beginning and the end. I will give to him who is thirsty, without cost, from the spring of the water of life.
B066C021V007	66	21	7	He who overcomes shall inherit all these things; and I will be his God, and he shall be my son.
B066C021V008	66	21	8	But the cowardly, and unbelieving, and the vile, and murderers, and the sexually immoral, and sorcerers, and idolaters, and all liars, shall have their part in the lake which burns with fire and sulphur: which is the second death.
B066C021V009	66	21	9	And there came to me one of the seven angels who had the seven bowls full of the seven last plagues, and spoke to me, saying, Come here, I will show you the bride, the wife of the Lamb.
B066C021V010	66	21	10	And he carried me away in the spirit to a great and high mountain, and showed me the holy city, Jerusalem, descending out of heaven from God,
B066C021V011	66	21	11	Having the glory of God: and her radiance was like a stone most precious, like a jasper, clear as crystal.
B066C021V012	66	21	12	It had a great and high wall, and twelve gates, and at the gates twelve angels, and on the gates were written the names of the twelve tribes of the sons of Israel.
B066C021V013	66	21	13	On the east were three gates; on the north three gates; on the south three gates; and on the west three gates.
B066C021V014	66	21	14	And the wall of the city had twelve foundations, and on them the names of the twelve apostles of the Lamb.
B066C021V015	66	21	15	And he who spoke to me had a measuring rod of gold to measure the city, and its gates, and its wall.
B066C021V016	66	21	16	And the city was laid out in a square, its length equal to its breadth: and he measured the city with the rod, twelve thousand stadia. The length and the breadth and the height of it are equal.
B066C021V017	66	21	17	And he measured its wall, a hundred and forty-four cubits, according to man's measurement, which the angel was using.
B066C021V018	66	21	18	And the wall was made of jasper: and the city of pure gold, like clear glass.
B066C021V019	66	21	19	And the foundations of the wall of the city were adorned with all kinds of precious stones. The first foundation was jasper; the second, sapphire; the third, chalcedony; the fourth, emerald;
B066C021V020	66	21	20	The fifth, sardonyx; the sixth, sardius; the seventh, chrysolite; the eighth, beryl; the ninth, topaz; the tenth, chrysoprase; the eleventh, jacinth; the twelfth, amethyst.
B066C021V021	66	21	21	And the twelve gates were twelve pearls; each gate made of a single pearl: and the street of the city was pure gold, like transparent glass.
B066C021V022	66	21	22	And I saw no temple in it: for the Lord God Almighty and the Lamb are its temple.
B066C021V023	66	21	23	And the city had no need of the sun, or the moon, to shine upon it: for the glory of God is its light, and the Lamb its lamp.
B066C021V024	66	21	24	And the nations shall walk by its light: and the kings of the earth shall bring their glory into it.
B066C021V025	66	21	25	And its gates shall never be shut by day: and there shall be no night there.
B066C021V026	66	21	26	And they shall bring the glory and honour of the nations into it.
B066C021V027	66	21	27	But nothing impure shall enter into it, nor shall any man who commits shameful acts, or who lies: but only those whose names are written in the Lamb's book of life.
B066C022V001	66	22	1	And he showed me the river of the water of life, clear as crystal, flowing from the throne of God and of the Lamb,
B066C022V002	66	22	2	Down the middle of the street of the city. And on either side of the river was the tree of life, which bore twelve kinds of fruits, and yielded its fruit every month: and the leaves of the tree were for the healing of the nations.
B066C022V003	66	22	3	And there shall no longer be any curse: but the throne of God and of the Lamb shall be in it; and his servants shall serve him:
B066C022V004	66	22	4	And they shall see his face; and his name shall be upon their foreheads.
B066C022V005	66	22	5	And there shall be no night there; and they shall need no lamp, nor light from the sun; for the Lord God shall give them light: and they shall reign for ever and ever.
B066C022V006	66	22	6	And he said to me, These words are faithful and true: and the Lord, the God of the spirits of the prophets, has sent his angel to show to his servants the things which must shortly come to pass.
B066C022V007	66	22	7	Behold, I come quickly: blessed is he who keeps the words of the prophecy of this book.
B066C022V008	66	22	8	I, John, heard and saw these things. And when I had heard and seen, I fell down to worship at the feet of the angel who showed me these things.
B066C022V009	66	22	9	Then he said to me, Do not do that: I am a fellow servant with you and your brethren the prophets, and with those who keep the words of this book: worship God.
B066C022V010	66	22	10	And he said to me, Do not seal up the words of the prophecy of this book: for the time is at hand.
B066C022V011	66	22	11	He who is unjust, let him be unjust still: and he who is filthy, let him be filthy still: and he who is righteous, let him be righteous still: and he who is holy, let him be holy still.
B066C022V012	66	22	12	Behold, I am coming quickly; and my reward is with me, to give to every man according to what he has done.
B066C022V013	66	22	13	I am the Alpha and the Omega, the first and the last, the beginning and the end.
B066C022V014	66	22	14	Blessed are those who wash their robes, that they may have the right to the tree of life, and may enter through the gates into the city.
B066C022V015	66	22	15	Outside are dogs, and sorcerers, and the sexually immoral, and murderers, and idolaters, and everyone who loves and practices falsehood.
B066C022V016	66	22	16	I, Jesus, have sent my angel to you to testify of these things for the churches. I am the root and the offspring of David, the bright morning star.
B066C022V017	66	22	17	And the Spirit and the bride say, Come. And let him who hears say, Come. And let him who is thirsty come. And whoever will, let him take the water of life without cost.
B066C022V018	66	22	18	For I testify to every man who hears the words of the prophecy of this book, If any man shall add to these things, God shall add to him the plagues that are written in this book:
B066C022V019	66	22	19	And if any man shall take away from the words of the book of this prophecy, God shall take away his part in the tree of life, and in the holy city, which are described in this book.
B066C022V020	66	22	20	He who testifies to these things says, Surely I am coming quickly. Amen. Come, Lord Jesus.
B066C022V021	66	22	21	The grace of the Lord Jesus be with you all. Amen.
